VALUES 
    ('rec00pm1ZK9pXWGKZ', 'Tyrolit Group', 'http://www.tyrolit.group', 'https://at.linkedin.com/company/tyrolit', 'Schwaz, Tyrol', 'Industrial Machinery Manufacturing', '1.001–5.000 Beschäftigte', '54', 'Tyrolit Group is a growth-stage industrial machinery company (1,001–5,000 employees) with active operations and recent commercial expansion in Australia, particularly following the acquisition of ATS. The primary sales roles identified are Sales Manager and National Sales Manager, which are high-priority core roles (35 points). The industry is industrial manufacturing, which is an edge case for commercial B2B tech fit (5 points). Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Managers, National Sales Managers) are present, providing quality access (10 points). Strong growth signals include a major acquisition and market expansion (5 points). While the company is expanding and has relevant decision makers, the industry fit limits the overall recruitment opportunity for B2B tech sales roles, resulting in a medium priority score.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Tyrolit acquired a majority stake in **ATS (Abrasive Tools Specialists)**, based in Melbourne, substantially strengthening its foothold in the Australian market, particularly in the metal industries sector. This acquisition signals an increased focus on expanding local market share and product offerings as of 2024–2025[1].  \n[LOCAL] ATS Tyrolit was featured as an exhibitor at the 2025 HBT Tradeshow, reflecting ongoing commercial activities and brand presence in Australia''s industrial tools and hardware sector[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Tyrolit has executed targeted global acquisitions, including ATS in Australia, to consolidate its position as a leading supplier of abrasives and grinding solutions worldwide despite economic uncertainty[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There are indications of expanded operations in Australia, including a broad and current product portfolio for industrial customers in and around Melbourne (e.g., concrete grinders, diamond tooling, metal industry tools)[3][5].  \n[LOCAL] Tyrolit continues to market and introduce new construction and industrial grinding products in Australia, with up-to-date pricing and catalogs available for 2025[5].  \n[REGIONAL] Following the acquisition of ATS, Tyrolit is targeting new market segments in Australia and reinforcing its offering to steel, foundry, and rail industries[1]. These moves suggest ongoing investments in local team capabilities and channel networks.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new public funding rounds or major financial injections have been reported in the last 12 months. Expansion activities are being driven by strategic acquisitions rather than external fundraising[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] ATS Tyrolit’s presence at major trade events such as the 2025 HBT Tradeshow is a mark of sector engagement and local visibility[2].  \n[REGIONAL] The acquisition of ATS has been described as a key milestone in Tyrolit’s recent achievements in the APAC region, enhancing its product range and sectoral presence[1].  \n[LOCAL] Long-term, high-profile clients in Australia cite Tyrolit as a trusted supplier for high-quality construction and cutting products, reinforcing its reputation and market position[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] No recent public announcements of executive appointments, promotions, or departures in the Australian or Melbourne leadership teams within the past year.  \n[GLOBAL] No major global leadership changes directly impacting APAC/Australian operations have been announced.\n\nIf you need specific details about sales team expansion or named executives in Melbourne, public information is limited; activities point primarily to heightened commercial and operational integration with ATS and expanded product distribution as of 2024–2025[1][2][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tyrolit is a global leader in the manufacturing of grinding and dressing tools as well as a system provider for the construction industry. Established in 1919, Tyrolit''s innovative tools have significantly contributed to technological advancements across various industries. With operations rooted in the Austrian Alps, Tyrolit combines strong family values with a global vision, providing tailored grinding solutions and a vast assortment of standard tools to customers worldwide. The company leverages over a century of corporate and technological expertise to maintain its leadership position.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time hybrid role for a Sales Executive, located in Melbourne, VIC, with the flexibility to work from home occasionally. The Sales Executive will be responsible for identifying and pursuing new sales opportunities focused kn hire and retail, developing and maintaining relationships with clients, and ensuring customer satisfaction. Day-to-day tasks include researching potential clients, presenting product demonstrations, negotiating contracts, and achieving sales targets. The role also involves regular reporting, market analysis, and collaboration with the marketing and technical teams to ensure alignment with business goals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in sales, business development, or related fields&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the construction industry and technical products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM software and MS Office Suite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel as required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyze market trends and develop strategies accordingly&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with a leading range if machinery and accessories, comkany ohone, laptop ajd fully maintained comlany vehicke, competitive salary and open commision oppertunity.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQGQ_pyhd1pnmQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1631363430575/tyrolit_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=r7_KcQ0Rxiv0IpiS3F0lbg4_YuT3GaKVzy3zI4feRcg', '2025-09-25T05:20:10.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec0JDpaTCNwnA7dD', 'OneTrust', 'http://www.onetrust.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/onetrust', 'Atlanta, Georgia', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '78', 'OneTrust is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for core sales roles such as Enterprise Account Executive and Sales Director in Australia and Singapore. The presence of Tier 1 (Regional Director, Managing Director ANZ) and Tier 2 (Sales Director, Enterprise Corporate Sales Manager) decision makers provides strong access for recruitment engagement. Recent Melbourne office launch, local headcount growth, and regional expansion signal robust operational growth, though no recent funding rounds are noted. The combination of core sales hiring, strong industry fit, and quality decision makers makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] Opened a **Melbourne office** to support growth in Australia and New Zealand, alongside launching two new local data centers and expanding integration with ANZ privacy laws (announced in March 2024)[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Announced commitment to supporting *Australian Privacy Act* reforms and privacy legislation updates in both Australia and New Zealand by rapidly integrating regional compliance needs into the core platform[1].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[LOCAL] Melbourne office is led by local privacy experts with deep knowledge of regional and global requirements, focusing on supporting privacy program operationalization for ANZ organizations[1].  \n[LOCAL] Supporting high-profile local customers such as Cochlear Limited for privacy compliance and automation[1].  \n[REGIONAL] OneTrust reports “dozens of well-known organisations” in Australia and New Zealand as clients, with dedicated sales and privacy teams in Melbourne and growing local headcount[1][2].  \n[GLOBAL] Surpassed **500 employees** globally, with continued monthly additions and over half the workforce dedicated to R&D and customer success[2].  \n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \n[GLOBAL] No new funding events specific to 2024-2025 identified in Australian media; last globally-reported funding event was before 2023. Current growth appears operational and client-driven rather than from recent investment influx[2].  \n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \n[REGIONAL] Recognized as the **most widely used privacy management and compliance software** in ANZ, serving industries including health and finance, with fast integration of region-specific privacy features[1].  \n[LOCAL] Named as an **essential privacy compliance element** for prominent organizations; local workshops and customer community engagement ongoing through events like PrivacyConnect in Melbourne[4][1].  \n[GLOBAL] OneTrust led industry research rankings as a strategic leader in global privacy management, as recognized by Ovum Research (2024)[1][2].  \n[GLOBAL] Transitioned its Convercent Ethics & Compliance solution business to EQS Group in December 2024, focusing the company more tightly on its privacy, data governance, security, and risk management product lines[3]. This transition does not affect other core offerings or ANZ operations[3].  \n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \n[LOCAL] **Robinson Roe**, Managing Director ANZ, leads the Melbourne presence, bringing significant regional and global privacy expertise[1].  \n[REGIONAL] No publicly announced recent senior hires or departures in the Melbourne or ANZ team in the last 12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] The company’s executive team expanded recently; no specific revenue or sales leadership changes in ANZ noted in public sources since 2024[2].\n\n---\n**Scope Note:** Most recent and relevant Melbourne/ANZ information is sourced from public statements in March-April 2024. No major regional funding rounds, C-level APAC hires, or Australia-specific partnerships have been disclosed in the public domain for the last 6 months. All strategic growth appears to be driven by increased privacy regulation and locally tailored platform capabilities."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Strength in Trust&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;OneTrust’s mission is to enable organizations to use data and AI responsibly. Our platform simplifies the collection of data with consent and preferences, automates the governance of data with integrated risk management across privacy, security, IT/tech, third-party, and AI risk, and activates the responsible use of data by applying and enforcing data policies across the entire data estate and lifecycle. OneTrust supports seamless collaboration between data teams and risk teams to drive rapid and trusted innovation. Recognized as a market pioneer and leader, OneTrust boasts over 300 patents and serves more than 14,000 customers globally, ranging from industry giants to small businesses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Challenge&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Join the industry leader in Privacy and be part of a dynamic team that is addressing one of the most critical challenges for companies today: the responsible use of data and AI. With over 14,000 customers, we are at the forefront of helping businesses meet regulations and drive top-line revenue. At OneTrust, you can make a significant impact by working with cutting-edge technology and innovative solutions that enable organizations to build trust with their customers and thrive in the digital age.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for an Account Executive, Mid-Market. Account Executives have a critical role and responsibility to deliver new client acquisition in zero-base accounts while ensuring successful relationships and revenue growth with existing customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;OneTrust is a fast-growing SaaS enterprise platform with a robust growth trajectory. We invest heavily in our Sales Team. We generate customer interest, use a steady sales process, offer weekly training, and keep customer requirements at the forefront of our planning. Our executives are always ready to help close sales.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Account Executive (AE) is tasked with frequently finding and pursuing chances to make our customers more trusted and boost OneTrust''s revenue. AEs must use their thorough industry knowledge and top-notch value-based sales skills to create the best solutions and solve complex customer problems. AEs must bring valuable insights and best practices to customers and prospects. As an Account Executive, Mid-Market, you will:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with your team to meet or exceed quota. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage in proactive outreach to generate and progress a consistent pipeline, even while managing closing activities. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage internal stakeholders, leaders, and champions to drive sales strategy execution. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with Business Development, Partner and Channel Sales, Specialty Sales, and Solutions Engineering to land and expand key accounts. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize two-sided discovery and impeccable communication to understand customer needs and present valuable solutions. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Differentiate OneTrust’s solutions by understanding key competitors and their strategies. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build robust customer relationships, positioning OneTrust as a trusted advisor. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and optimize a targeted geographic territory. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You are a team player with a hunting mentality and a consultative approach. Your work reflects your inquisitive nature, innovative mindset, genuineness, deal management skills, tenacity, and truthfulness. You thrive in building relationships with C-Level Executives and are confident in your communication skills. Balancing new prospecting activities with deal advancement comes naturally to you, and you maintain discipline in sales processes and CRM hygiene.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Experience Includes&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 2+ years of experience selling B2B software or related technologies. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success in solution and value selling. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A solid track record of landing new logos. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience running sales presentations/demos. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of swift, targeted contract negotiation to deliver value to your company and customer. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Salesforce.com or similar CRM solutions. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extra Awesome&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in Privacy, Security, Third-Party Risk management, Compliance &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience directly selling to the Information Security department &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CIPP/E or CIPM certified &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trained in Command of Message &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Where we Work&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are embracing an office first culture, encouraging three days a week in office for most roles, with meaningful opportunities to collaborate and celebrate in person.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Each role may have specific requirements or flexibility depending on the scope of the position, so we encourage you to verify this with your recruiter during your first interview.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an employee at OneTrust, you will be part of the OneTeam. That means you’ll receive support physically, mentally, and emotionally so that you can do your best work both in and out of the office. This includes comprehensive healthcare coverage, flexible PTO, equity RSUs, annual performance bonus opportunities, retirement account support, 14+ weeks of paid parental leave, career development opportunities, company-paid privacy certification exam fees, and much more. Specific benefits differ by country. For more information, talk to your recruiter or visit onetrust.com/careers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Resources&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Check out the following to learn more about OneTrust and its people:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;OneTrust Careers on YouTube&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;@LifeatOneTrust on Instagram&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Your Data&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You have the right to have your personal data updated or removed. You also have the right to have a copy of the information OneTrust holds about you. Further details about these rights are available on the website in our Privacy Overview&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;You can change your mind at any time and have your personal data removed from our database. In order to do this you must contact us and let us know you wish to be removed. The request should be made on the Data Subject Request Form.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Recruitment fraud warning: OneTrust is aware of scams involving false offers of employment with our company. The fraudulent jobs, interviews and job offers use fake websites, email addresses, group chat and text messages. Be aware that we never ask candidates for personal information, IDs or bank information during the interview process. We do not interview prospective candidates via instant message or group chat, and do not require candidates to purchase products or services, or process payments on our behalf as a condition of any employment offer. Please note that any legitimate interview availability requests will come directly from a OneTrust recruiter with an \"@onetrust.com\" email address. You may also receive legitimate emails from \"@us.greenhouse-mail.io\". Recruiters will only reach out to candidates who have applied for a role through our ATS (Greenhouse) or prospects via LinkedIn InMail. Job offers will come from a recruiter and may have a \"@docusign.net\" email address. For more information or if you have been targeted please reach out to askrecruiting@onetrust.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment to You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;When you join OneTrust you are stepping onto a launching pad — the countdown has begun. The destination? A career without boundaries working alongside a diverse and inclusive crew who is passionate about doing meaningful work. As a pioneer, your voice and expertise will help chart the direction of an entirely new category. Our commitment to putting people first starts with you. Your growth is part of the mission. Our goal is to give you the power to embark on the next phase of your uniquely, unique career.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;OneTrust provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by local laws."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQH2azTI7cMzIg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1665577396653/onetrust_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=WPFDp9iAp-1TFbsbj_Bffh9u4sfbHQKxznmZR_NilQ0', '2025-09-22T14:25:18.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec0Zk3EQG9sRKJzl', 'ECI Software Solutions', 'https://www.ecisolutions.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/eci-software--solutions', 'Westlake, Texas, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '70', 'ECI Software Solutions is a growth-stage computer software company (1,663 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively employing a Business Development Manager in Australia. The presence of a Vice President APAC and a Business Development Manager provides Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision maker access, supporting immediate recruitment potential. While there are no recent growth signals or funding events, recent industry awards and ongoing recognition indicate a stable and reputable business. The core sales role and strong industry fit make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nECI Software Solutions won eight 2025 Top Rated Awards from TrustRadius in June 2025, including recognition for products like JobBOSS2, M1, EvolutionX, and JumpTrack based on customer reviews. The company was also certified as a 2025 Great Place to Work in seven countries in March 2025, marking the seventh consecutive year of recognition in the US and expansion to Portugal for the first time.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nBrian Hildebrand was appointed as Chief Information Officer at ECI Software Solutions, though the specific date was not provided in recent coverage. Andrew Pryor serves as Chief Human Resources Officer and Trevor Gruenewald continues as CEO based on recent company announcements."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"For more than 30 years, ECI Software Solutions has been providing industry-specific, cloud-based business management software and services to businesses around the world.\n \nWith divisions focused on manufacturing, wholesale/retail distribution, building and construction, and field service, ECI''s solutions integrate into every aspect of a customers'' business to help them level the playing field, run day-to-day operations more efficiently, and free them up to focus on what matters most. It’s how business gets done.\n\nPrivately held with more than 16,000 customers, ECI is headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas, USA, with offices and companies throughout the U.S., Australia, New Zealand, England, and the Netherlands. For more information, email info@ecisolutions.com, visit www.ECISolutions.com, or call (800) 959-3367."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:20:04.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec0w2oZsEiNl7G2F', 'Nothing', 'http://nothing.tech', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/nothingtech', 'London, England, GB', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '70', 'Nothing is a major computer software company with strong growth signals, including rapid shipment increases, multiple product launches, and expansion into new markets. The presence of a Sales Manager in Australia indicates relevant decision maker access for sales hiring. While there are no recent funding rounds or HR leadership identified, the company''s aggressive expansion and established sales infrastructure suggest strong potential for recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNothing launched the Phone (3) in mid-2025, positioning it as a direct competitor to Samsung, Apple, and Google in the unlocked phone market. The company expanded its manufacturing and marketing operations in India, which it now considers its primary consumer and manufacturing market, and is planning further growth in wearables and audio devices this year.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nIn the AprilâJune 2025 quarter, Nothingâs shipments grew 146% year-over-year, marking it as the fastest-growing smartphone brand in India. The company has relocated global marketing to India and is projecting 25â30% annual revenue growth into 2026, fueled by continued product launches and U.S. market expansion.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNothing launched its first over-ear headphones and is set to unveil the Ear (3) wireless buds on September 18, 2025. The companyâs partnership with British audio brand KEF has enhanced its audio product performance, and its latest phone and wearable offerings contributed to a high-profile product launch season.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Nothing exists to make tech feel exciting again.\n\nWeâre building a different kind of company, one that puts design, emotion, and human creativity at the heart of everything we do. From the way our products look to how they sound, feel, and function, we care about the details that make technology not just useful, but inspiring.\n\nThis is a place for the curious. The creators. The ones who ask why not and mean it. If you''re drawn to bold ideas, fast moves, and work that actually makes you feel something, youâll fit right in.\n\nWe''re not here to follow the rules. We''re here to make better ones.\n\nFounded in London in 2020, Nothing is a design-led tech company building an alternative to the industry giants. Our products, from award-winning smartphones to expressive audio and wearables, blend iconic design with intuitive engineering to put people and creativity back at the centre of consumer tech.\n\nBacked by GV (Google Ventures), EQT Ventures, C Ventures, and influential investors like Tony Fadell (iPod), Casey Neistat, and Kevin Lin (Twitch), weâve grown from startup to global challenger in just a few years."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec1HR7BXZU4LUOwU', 'Fastly', 'http://www.fastly.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fastly', 'San Francisco, CA', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '77', 'Fastly is a growth-stage software company (501-1,000 employees) operating in commercial B2B tech, with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore. The inclusion is triggered by active Senior Account Executive and Senior Enterprise Account Executive roles, which are high-priority core sales positions. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Country Lead, Senior Channel Sales Manager, VP APJ) are present, providing strong access for recruitment. Recent local partnership expansions, executive leadership changes, and ongoing GTM investment signal moderate to strong growth, though no large-scale hiring surges are reported. This represents a high-priority recruitment opportunity, especially for experienced sales talent in the ANZ and APAC regions.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Fastly appointed Nueva as its first managed security partner in Australia, based in Sydney, on 1 August 2024, expanding its local security offerings and go-to-market reach by enabling Nueva to offer Fastly’s Next-Gen WAF, DDoS mitigation, and bot management services to both public and private sector clients[1].\n[LOCAL] Fastly is hosting \"Xcelerate Sydney,\" an exclusive industry event on 29 August 2024 at Ovolo Woolloomooloo, aimed at networking, product education, and showcasing the company’s edge platform to current and prospective regional clients[3][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Fastly is strengthening direct channel and strategic partnership activity in Australia, particularly targeting Sydney-based operations, by investing in local managed service provider alliances and bespoke enablement programs[1].\n[REGIONAL] Head of Channel and Partnership – ANZ, Alan Chan, is publicly leading partnership strategy in ANZ, highlighting an active and potentially growing go-to-market (GTM) team in Australia[1].\n[GLOBAL] Fastly reported record Q4 2024 revenue ($140.6M), with executive commentary noting a \"motivated go-to-market team\" and ongoing focus on efficient customer acquisition, suggesting expanded sales efforts[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds were reported in the past 6–12 months; however, quarterly financial disclosures cite a “strengthened balance sheet” as of year-end 2024, underpinned by continued revenue growth[4].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Nueva’s partnership enables Australian enterprises to access Fastly’s advanced edge security directly through a Sydney-based managed service provider, improving visibility and adoption in the local security market[1].\n[LOCAL] Fastly’s Xcelerate Sydney conference is positioned as an exclusive networking and technical showcase, supporting regional brand visibility and direct engagement in August 2024[3][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] Kip Compton was appointed CEO of Fastly in June 2025, succeeding Todd Nightingale (who stays on as advisor through June 2025). Compton previously served as Chief Product Officer and now holds primary responsibility for company strategy and growth, including in APAC[2].\n[REGIONAL] Australia/New Zealand channel and partnerships are led by Alan Chan (Head of Channel and Partnership – ANZ), instrumental in recent partnership and growth activities announced out of Sydney[1].\n\nAdditional context:\n- No public reports of major Sydney office expansions or new hiring surges within the last 6–12 months; growth focus appears to be through partnerships and direct sales/channel enablement rather than large-scale headcount increases in Sydney.\n- Fastly’s industry focus in Australia emphasizes securing digital infrastructure for enterprises, leveraging its global edge cloud and security portfolio as differentiators in a competitive market[1][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Fastly helps people stay better connected with the things they love. Fastly’s edge cloud platform enables customers to create great digital experiences quickly, securely, and reliably by processing, serving, and securing our customers’ applications as close to their end-users as possible — at the edge of the Internet. The platform is designed to take advantage of the modern internet, to be programmable, and to support agile software development. Fastly’s customers include many of the world’s most prominent companies, including Vimeo, Pinterest, The New York Times, and GitHub.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We''re building a more trustworthy Internet. Come join us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Account Executive – ANZ (Sydney)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Help shape the future of Fastly in Australia and New Zealand&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fastly has redefined the modern CDN and rapidly evolved into a leader in security and edge computing. Now, we’re building out our ANZ presence and looking for a driven, collaborative, and strategic Enterprise Account Executive to lead the way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As one of our early sales hires in the region, you’ll play a foundational role in customer acquisition and growth, with a focus on New South Wales and Queensland. You’ll report directly to the AVP Sales ANZ and work alongside a talented team of engineers, marketers, and customer champions to land and expand key enterprise relationships.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop, own, and execute a go-to-market plan that drives consistent pipeline and revenue growth, primarily in NSW, with a secondary focus on QLD &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of the sales cycle from prospecting and qualification through to executive alignment, negotiation, close, and long-term relationship development &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales Engineers during meetings, demos, and proof of concepts &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with senior technical and business stakeholders (CTO, CISO, Heads of DevOps &amp;amp; Infrastructure) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep understanding of Fastly’s platform and how it addresses customer pain points across edge computing, web performance, and security &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with Account Management, Product, Marketing, and Client Services teams to ensure aligned execution and customer success &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We''re Looking For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deep relationships and field sales experience within NSW’s enterprise landscape &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success selling to senior technical stakeholders, ideally in cloud, security, or developer-oriented tech &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A proactive approach to pipeline generation. You know how to open doors and build trust quickly. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinking combined with strong execution. You’re able to plan, prioritise, and deliver results with autonomy &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable navigating complexity and ambiguity in a high-growth, evolving environment &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills that are clear, confident, and consultative &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A balance of independence and collaboration. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You take initiative but value being part of a team &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;This position will require you to be available during core business hours. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Location(s) &amp;amp; Travel Requirements: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This Position Is a Remote Working Position, Residing In a Commutable Distance To Our Teams And Customers In The Following Region&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sydney, NSW, Australia &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position will require travel as required by your role or requested by your manager.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Fastly?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We have a huge impact. Fastly is a small company with a big reach. Not only do our customers have a tremendous user base, but we also support a growing number of open source projects and initiatives. Outside of code, employees are encouraged to share causes close to their heart with others so we can help lend a supportive hand. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We love distributed teams. Fastly’s home-base is in San Francisco, but we have multiple offices and employees sprinkled around the globe. As a new hire, you will be able to attend our IN-PERSON new hire orientation in our San Francisco office! It is an exciting week-long experience that we offer to new employees to build connections with colleagues across Fastly, participate in hands-on learning opportunities, and immerse yourself in our culture firsthand. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We value diversity. Growing and maintaining our inclusive and diverse team matters to us. We are committed to being a company where our employees feel comfortable bringing their authentic selves to work and have the ability to be successful -- every day. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are passionate. Fastly is chock full of passionate people and we’re not ‘one size fits all’. Fastly employs authors, pilots, skiers, parents (of humans and animals), makeup geeks, coffee connoisseurs, and more. We love employees for who they are and what they are passionate about. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re always looking for humble, sharp, and creative folks to join the Fastly team. If you think you might be a fit please apply!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; A fully completed application and resume or CV are required when applying.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fastly is committed to ensuring equal employment opportunity and to providing employees with a safe and welcoming work environment free of discrimination and harassment. Our employment decisions are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, family or parental status, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Consistent with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and federal or state disability laws, Fastly will provide reasonable accommodations for applicants and employees with disabilities. If reasonable accommodation is needed to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and/or to receive other benefits and privileges of employment, please contact your Recruiter, or the Fastly Employee Relations team at &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;candidateaccommodations@fastly.com&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; or 501-287-4901. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fastly collects and processes personal data submitted by job applicants in accordance with our Privacy Policy. Please see our privacy notice for job applicants.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQFFWKnKs-MBxA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630523652666/fastly_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=3JuQhoZcrYstHssGkxSy5xtibkaaznAslY8FveBm-vM', '2025-09-20T06:25:21.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec1hIOX6aNQSO2xj', 'Cornerstone OnDemand', 'https://www.cornerstoneondemand.com/company/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cornerstoneondemand', 'Santa Monica, CA', 'Software Development,Human Resources Services,IT Services and IT Consulting', '1,001-5,000 employees', '62', 'Cornerstone OnDemand is a growth-stage HR tech/SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B fit and established operations in Australia and Singapore. The most relevant sales role present is Regional Sales Manager, a high-priority core role (35 points). Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Regional Sales Managers, Regional Sales Director, RVP A/NZ) are accessible (max 20 points). However, there are no recent growth signals—no hiring surges, funding, or local expansions in the past year—limiting immediate recruitment opportunity. The stable but non-expanding local presence makes this a medium-priority lead for external recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Cornerstone OnDemand maintains a **Sydney office at Level 12, 1 Pacific Highway, North Sydney, NSW 2060**, serving as its principal hub for client engagement and market support in Australia[1]. No public evidence of major new local business developments, office openings, or headline partnerships in Sydney in the last 6-12 months was found at the [LOCAL] level.\n[REGIONAL] Cornerstone OnDemand continues to anchor its **Asia-Pacific (APAC) operations from the Australian office**, delivering adaptive HR solutions for talent development, workforce agility, and compliance to a broad portfolio of ANZ/Asia-Pacific clients. The Sydney presence is core for regional delivery and localized support, although no specific APAC expansion events or newly announced regional strategies were reported in the last year[1].\n[GLOBAL] Globally, Cornerstone OnDemand has consistently focused on scaling its AI-powered workforce agility platform and strengthening its SaaS learning/performance management suite, including new product innovations for international clients[1]. No recent global acquisitions or major strategy pivots directly impacting the Australian market have been observed in the last 12 months.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There is no public evidence of large-scale **hiring drives or new sales/Go-To-Market team expansions in Sydney** in the past six months. The Sydney office is described as modern, collaborative, and a regional base for professional services, sales, customer success, and support—suggesting stable ongoing operations but not accelerated local team growth[1].\n[REGIONAL] The APAC operation has continued to support sales, customer success, R&D, and technical services. No standout regional GTM hiring booms or new office launches have been reported for Australia/ANZ in public channels.\n[GLOBAL] Company-wide, Cornerstone OnDemand employs approximately **3,000 people globally**; no major recent layoffs, restructures, or significant company-wide expansions with direct APAC implications are mentioned in available sources[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Cornerstone OnDemand''s **most recent reported funding event was $40 million**, with total funding now at $541.8 million; this predates the last 12 months and is not linked to specific APAC expansion initiatives[2]. No 2024 or 2025 funding rounds targeting the Australian business or regional operations have been publicly disclosed.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] No APAC-specific **awards, major product launches, or large-scale strategic partnerships** involving the Sydney/Australia operation have been announced within the last year in publicly available channels.\n[GLOBAL] Globally, Cornerstone continues to emphasize **AI-driven innovation in its platform**, reflecting competitive momentum in talent management, skills, and learning solutions[1]. No new capabilities unique to Australia noted.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] There are **no recent announcements of major executive appointments, departures, or promotions in Cornerstone''s Sydney or Australian office**—especially within sales, revenue, or people functions—in the last 6-12 months.\n[GLOBAL] No global leadership changes with explicit impact on the APAC or Sydney teams were found in current records across this time frame.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian **HR tech and software market** remains competitive, with organizations increasingly demanding AI-powered, cloud-based solutions for remote talent management, compliance, and workforce upskilling. Enterprise and public sector entities are prioritizing platforms with strong local support and regulatory alignment, positioning Cornerstone OnDemand''s Sydney office as a critical strategic resource for solution delivery[1].\n\n**Summary:**  \nCornerstone OnDemand''s Sydney office is a stable regional hub supporting ANZ/APAC clients, with ongoing delivery of AI-powered HR solutions. No recent major expansions, funding, or headline local leadership changes have been publicly announced over the past year. The company remains a key player in a strong demand environment for digital talent management in Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;We''re looking for a&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development Representative&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;This role is&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Hybrid, Sydney Office&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; This Role is located in Sydney, NSW (Hybrid) &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Business Development Representatives (BDR) at Cornerstone work at the top of the sales funnel to generate new business opportunities for the organization. The BDR is in a strategic role, prospecting through inbound and outbound efforts to source potential customers in assigned sales territories. The ideal BDR candidate, along with having a track record of top performance, will also have the organizational skills needed to manage a high volume of outreach activity. Candidates should also have a strong interest in advancing their career in Sales/Marketing, as they will develop the key competencies and skill sets necessary to be successful and set a foundation for career advancement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role you will...&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Source new business opportunities through strategically researching accounts, identifying key contacts, conducting personalized outbound communication.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Convert Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs) into new opportunities by effectively following up with our most engaged prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Establish and nurture relationships with senior business executives by developing an understanding of their companies, the challenges they face and how Cornerstone can address their needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work in close collaboration with regional sales managers and field marketing specialists to define and execute on a joint prospecting strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet and exceed monthly, quarterly and annual pipeline generating goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain consideration for privacy and security obligations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Why join our team? We’re glad you asked. We believe that Cornerstone also helps people be their best at work with the right development and experiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive two-week onboarding program for the role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Full training program, which includes company orientation, benchmark checkins and goal setting.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuous training and access to sales leaders, sales reps with other experts in the technology sales industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Team first mentality- be part of a competitive team that works towards department focused contests, incentives and awards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong team collaboration- be part of a team that helps motivate and continuously challenges you to hit your professional goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong culture of development- consistent feedback and quarterly performance-driven conversations to set career goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Clear goals for progression forward- eligible for promotion evaluations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be part of a BDR team that has a proven track record to promote into other parts of the organization such as outside sales, account management, customer success, marketing, enablement and more!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ve Got What It Takes If You Have...&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong drive to achieve results with minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication (phone and email), time management, presentation, and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to be coached and an eagerness to learn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly pivot and adapt in a changing environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience working in a team environment to achieve group goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated commitment to valuing diversity and contributing to an inclusive working and learning environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consideration for privacy and security obligations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical abilities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Persistence and determination.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Interest in developing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Culture&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Spark Greatness. Shatter Boundaries. Share Success. Are you ready? Because here, right now – is where the future of work is happening. Where curious disruptors and change innovators like you are helping communities and customers enable everyone – anywhere – to learn, grow and advance. To be better tomorrow than they are today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Cornerstone powers the potential of organizations and their people to thrive in a changing world. Cornerstone Galaxy, the complete AI-powered workforce agility platform, meets organizations where they are. With Galaxy, organizations can identify skills gaps and development opportunities, retain and engage top talent, and provide multimodal learning experiences to meet the diverse needs of the modern workforce. More than 7,000 organizations and 100 million+ users in 180+ countries and in nearly 50 languages use Cornerstone Galaxy to build high-performing, future-ready organizations and people today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Rewards&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Cornerstone, we are dedicated to inspiring excellence and pushing boundaries in everything we do. Our compensation strategy is based on three fundamental principles: equitable pay, market-driven research, and skill-based appraisals. As part of our mission to share success and empower individuals to thrive in an ever-changing world, the listed salary range is just one element of Cornerstone’s comprehensive compensation package. This compensation package may also include annual bonuses, short- and program-specific awards depending on the role, and a comprehensive benefit offering. The disclosed salary range reflects the geographic differential based on the location of the position if applicable. The starting salary for the successful applicant will depend on several job-related factors, including education, training, experience, certifications, location, business needs, and market demands. This range is based on a full-time position and may be adjusted in the future. Join us in shaping the future of work — tomorrow, together. Experience flexibility and empowerment in your career at Cornerstone. The BASE salary range for this position is: 68500 - 109600 AUD.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Check us out on LinkedIn , Comparably , Glassdoor , and Facebook !"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEMulbwpZJbWQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1719809848778?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=6uDKs8DmxWst1lbxyiOBglc24UcutDOuhJm9PhWMhj4', '2025-09-20T06:23:24.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec2EvgsfCxpJ7kVH', 'Adaptalift Group', 'https://www.adaptalift.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/adaptalift-group', 'Melbourne, VIC', 'Machinery Manufacturing', '501-1,000 employees', '57', 'Adaptalift Group is a growth-stage machinery manufacturing company (501-1,000 employees) in Australia, actively hiring for roles such as Business Development Manager and Area Sales Manager, which are medium-priority sales roles. The industry is an edge case for commercial B2B tech recruitment, as it focuses on material handling equipment rather than core SaaS or software. Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Managers, General Manager of Sales, Head of Business Development) are present, providing solid access for recruitment. Growth signals include ongoing sales hiring, new product launches, and strong client partnerships, but there are no recent funding rounds or major expansion news. This represents a moderate recruitment opportunity, with some likelihood of external recruitment needs but not a top-priority tech sector target.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] No major news or media coverage specific to Springvale, VIC or recent operational changes at the Springvale location in the last 6–12 months[1].  \n[LOCAL] Active promotional campaigns continuing through October 2025, including substantial price reductions on select forklift models and expansion of electric outdoor forklift offerings[2].  \n[LOCAL] Ongoing partnerships with prominent Australian enterprises such as Qantas Freight for fleet safety and access control solutions, indicating continued focus on safety system integration for materials handling in the Melbourne market[2].  \n[REGIONAL] No explicit APAC expansion news or strategic changes found during the specified timeframe; operations remain strongly focused on the Australian market with branches across all major Australian states[2].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Continued recruitment of service and sales personnel indicated by website activity, and emphasis on expert technical support and customer service for Melbourne, including Springvale operations[1][3].  \n[LOCAL] Service and rental offerings remain strong, with Adaptalift providing flexible forklift lease and rental options for small and large businesses throughout Melbourne, signalling demand-driven hiring in technical and commercial roles[3].  \n[REGIONAL] No recent company-wide headcount growth figures, but active engagement with major clients and new product launches suggest steady business volume[1].  \n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL][REGIONAL][GLOBAL] No reported funding rounds, investments, or significant financial milestones in the last 6–12 months[1]. Adaptalift Group remains a large, privately owned entity headquartered in Victoria.  \n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Launch of new emissions-free outdoor electric forklift and limited-time pricing initiatives through October 2025, targeting the Victorian market and promoting sustainability[2].  \n[LOCAL] Recognized for engineering and safety collaboration with major clients in Melbourne, such as Qantas Freight, supporting specialized fleet integration and worker safety improvements[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Maintained status as one of Australia’s largest forklift sales and rental providers, continuing over 40 years of sector leadership[2].  \n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL][REGIONAL] No public disclosures of executive appointments, promotions, or departures in the executive, sales, or people functions for Springvale or Australia in the last year[1].  \n[GLOBAL] The senior executive team (CEO, CTO, COO) remains stable with no major changes reported[1].  \n\n[INDUSTRY]  \n- The machinery manufacturing sector in Australia, particularly material handling and forklift services, is experiencing ongoing demand for emission-reducing solutions and advanced telemetry for fleet and operator safety.  \n- Industry-wide, companies are emphasizing equipment rental over ownership as a cost-control strategy, a trend Adaptalift actively highlights in its messaging[2].  \n- Regulatory and client focus on workplace safety, fleet monitoring, and sustainability continues to drive product and service innovation, especially in Victoria and urban logistics hubs.\n\n**Summary:**  \nAdaptalift Group’s Springvale/Melbourne operation remains a core hub, with strong focus on sales, rental, and support for material handling equipment, especially in emission-free and safety-integrated offerings. No major recent funding or leadership changes have occurred; the company continues to leverage decades-long client relationships and market stability in Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Business Development &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Sales Rep &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Springvale VIC &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Permanent Full Time &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;2/9/2025&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grow market share across Melbourne''s South East and East&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;State-of-the-art fleet of access equipment that you''ll be proud to sell&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Base salary + super + car allowance + uncapped commission&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Adaptalift Group is Australia''s largest family-owned materials handling business, with 40+ years of success and a reputation for safety, service and growth. Our &lt;strong&gt;Access Equipment Rentals division&lt;/strong&gt; is booming, with a modern fleet of scissor lifts, booms, and telehandlers from world-leading brands like JLG, Genie, Haulotte and Dingli.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We''re investing in people and fleet, and we now need a &lt;strong&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to help us grow market share across Melbourne''s &lt;strong&gt;South-East and Eastern suburbs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What''s In It For You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Base salary + Super + Car Allowance + Uncapped Commission&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Real career progression in a growing national business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;State-of-the-art fleet you''ll be proud to sell&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership - direct support from the GM Rentals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee rewards, wellbeing programs, and team culture that celebrates success&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Be Doing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Win new business - Prospect construction sites, convert inbound leads, re-engage lapsed customers and turn conversations into revenue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage accounts - Build strong relationships with builders, contractors and hire companies, ensuring retention and growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Territory focus - Be the boots on the ground for your region, supported by data, construction indexes and marketing leads.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Revenue delivery - Drive rental utilisation, close deals, and generate consistent sales activity.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Team collaboration - Partner with our rental coordinators and operations teams to deliver seamless customer service.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We''re Looking For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 12 months B2B sales/account management experience, ideally in equipment hire, capital sales, or construction-related sectors.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commercial curiosity - You ask questions, challenge ideas, and look for smarter ways to work.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilient communicator - Comfortable walking onto a construction site, introducing yourself, and building rapport.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-starter - Able to manage your time and pipeline, with a track record of hitting targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Industry awareness - Knowledge of equipment rental, access gear or materials handling a big plus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Current and valid Driver''s licence is essential.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you''ve got the drive, resilience and hunger to succeed in a fast-moving sector, &lt;strong&gt;we want to hear from you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply today&lt;/strong&gt; and help us keep Australia''s worksites moving."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQERO2PZUBkNNg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1732158558461/adaptalift_group_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=BVwsaROFC6VAqXmNfO7M5J8Hbojbisy3GcGRHhvubyU', '2025-09-25T05:18:04.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec2ML9bryGU0JeSd', 'Think & Grow', 'https://www.thinkandgrowinc.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/thinkandgrow', 'East Melbourne, Victoria, AU', 'Computer Software', '11 - 50', NULL, 'Think & Grow operates in recruitment, executive search, and organisational design, which are professional services rather than core technology or SaaS. Despite having sales leadership and a sizable team in Australia, the company''s industry focus does not align with 4Twenty''s technology, sales, or digital specialisation areas, resulting in low immediate business opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We''re your global growth consultants ð\n\nWe empower founders, leaders and executives across the globe to develop their businesses and people to build legacies and play a key role in the future of work.\n\nHow we help founders of fast-growth tech companies: \n\nWorkshops: Identify and close the gaps in your business to gain clarity on your leadership, team and strategy.\n\nGrowth: Have the support and expertise to scale sustainably and successfully locally and overseas.\n\nHire: Attract the change-leaders and advisors you need to accelerate your business.\n\nAdvisory: Create a scalable culture to empower your people to push boundaries and propel growth.\n\nConnect with us: thinkandgrowinc.com "}'::jsonb, 'LOW', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec2Nl4Ai06N55SIc', 'Josys', 'https://josys.com/', 'https://jp.linkedin.com/company/josys-inc', 'Tokyo', 'Technology, Information and Internet,Software Development,IT Services and IT Consulting', '社員 201-500名', '81', 'Josys is a growth-stage SaaS and IT services company (201-500 employees) actively expanding in Australia, with a focus on commercial B2B technology and SaaS security. The presence of senior decision makers—GM US & ANZ (Tier 1), VP APAC (Tier 1), and Account Executive Australia (Tier 2)—provides strong access for recruitment. While there is no explicit current sales role posting, the company''s GTM focus, recent $100M funding, and ongoing APAC sales activities signal robust growth and likely future hiring. This is a high-priority opportunity due to industry fit, company size, and decision maker access, but lacks the highest score due to absence of a live sales role posting in Sydney.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] On September 3, 2025, Josys released its Shadow AI Report 2025, surveying 500 Australian technology decision makers and revealing that over a third of Australian professionals in the Greater Sydney Area and across the country are uploading sensitive company data to AI platforms, posing significant compliance and security risks[2]. This report has triggered increased industry dialogue on AI governance and risk in Australian enterprises, especially around new Privacy Act reforms and transparency requirements.\n[GLOBAL] On February 12, 2025, Josys launched a new Access Governance Toolkit aimed at automating IT operations and enhancing SaaS security, reinforcing its global position as a SaaS management platform with implications for regulated markets like Australia[5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The publication of local research and commentary from Josys’s international executive leadership (COO/President Jun Yokote) suggests an active market presence and engagement with Australian enterprise customers and technology decision makers[2].\n[REGIONAL] Josys’s GTM (Go-To-Market) teams in each region—including APAC—focus on sales, business development, and revenue operations, with ongoing adaptation to local market trends[3]. There is evidence of proactive engagement and thought leadership activities but limited hiring signal data specifically for Greater Sydney currently available[3].\n[GLOBAL] Josys continues to invest in integrated sales, channel, and marketing activities as part of its global growth strategy, aligned with product and engineering innovation[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] On October 7, 2024, Josys secured $100 million in venture debt aimed at further international expansion and product development, indicating robust financial backing and signaling sustained growth plans for new markets, including Australia[5].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] The release of the Shadow AI Report alongside mounting policy advocacy positions Josys at the forefront of SaaS governance and security conversations within the Australian technology and compliance sector[2].\n[GLOBAL] Josys has continued to roll out significant product upgrades in access governance and SaaS security throughout 2024-2025, directly impacting its relevance in stringent regulatory environments like Australia[5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL/GLOBAL] Public executive presence noted in APAC through company statements (e.g., Jun Yokote, COO and President, Josys International), particularly in industry commentary for Australia[2]. No reported change in regional or local sales leadership or prominent local executive hires in Greater Sydney over the past 6-12 months based on available open data.\n\n---\n- All available evidence indicates Josys is **actively targeting the Australian market** through thought leadership, compliance advocacy, and recent research, but there is no public record of a dedicated Greater Sydney office or outbound hiring campaign as of September 2025[2].\n- Key touchpoints for Australian market activity include publications, compliance-oriented product releases, and APAC-aligned GTM strategies. The company''s rapid global product innovation and recent funding signal readiness for continued expansion relevant to the local tech and IT services sector[3][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive – Sydney, Australia&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Sydney, Australia&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Josys&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Josys is a SaaS Management Platform redefining how IT operates. We provide a next-gen solution to manage SaaS sprawl by giving IT teams complete visibility and control over their software stack. With over $225 million in funding, we’re one of the fastest-growing startups in Japanese history, now scaling globally to tackle shadow IT and secure cloud environments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive at Josys, you will lead sales efforts across &lt;strong&gt;Australia and New Zealand (ANZ)&lt;/strong&gt;. Based in Sydney, you’ll be responsible for building relationships with IT and business leaders, driving new customer acquisition, and expanding within accounts. You’ll work closely with our global team to tailor Josys’ platform to the ANZ market.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute territory sales strategy and onboarding MSP partners in the ANZ region.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with MSP executives, practice leads, and technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect and build pipeline through outbound and inbound channels.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deliver compelling presentations and demos to IT decision-makers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the sales cycle from discovery to close.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Customer Success to ensure smooth onboarding and retention.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend and represent Josys at local industry events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of regional IT and SaaS trends.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years of SaaS sales experience in ANZ, preferably in IT or enterprise software.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the Australian IT ecosystem and buyer personas.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the MSP business model, economics, and go-to-market strategies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of quota achievement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-starter with a growth mindset and ability to work independently.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiar with CRM tools and AI-driven sales approaches.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQGKb6Atx3TeiQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1738790194527/josys_inc_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=fiAlwqgZ5M3Q5XQnWSTe-eqYxaOy_c-BywRWI9RwB8U', '2025-09-29T14:23:51.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec2XC2fF2mTJmURM', 'Remote', 'https://www.remote.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/remote.com', 'San Francisco, CA', 'Human Resources Services', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'Remote is a growth-stage HR tech company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong APAC presence and active hiring for multiple Account Executive and Sales Manager roles in Australia and Singapore. The industry fit is strong (HR tech/SaaS), and decision makers include Sales Managers and an Outbound Sales Development Manager (Tier 2), with additional Account Executives and a Senior Manager, Sales - APAC. Recent Series B funding, product expansion, and APAC market focus are strong growth signals. This combination of core sales hiring, industry fit, quality decision makers, and growth momentum makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Remote has ramped up its presence across the APAC region in 2024–2025, driven by strong Australian demand for global remote workforce solutions. Australia stands out as a leader in remote hiring maturity, with 83% of companies planning to hire international remote full-time employees over the next 12–18 months, per IDC InfoBrief (2024)[2]. [GLOBAL] Remote continues to position itself as a strategic partner for companies navigating cross-border employment and compliance challenges, as payroll management and policy compliance remain top concerns for Australian firms hiring international talent[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] Major Australian businesses increasingly leverage offshore and remote technical talent to address local skill shortages and salary pressures, relying on platforms like Remote for pre-vetted talent and local account management[3]. [REGIONAL] The Australian market sees rising adoption of hybrid and fully remote employment models—97% of organizations offered flexible remote setups in 2024, with 62% doing so to attract and retain talent[1]. [GLOBAL] Remote’s product expansion in payroll and compliance tooling aligns with Australian companies’ growing need for seamless international HR and payments infrastructure[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Remote completed a significant funding round (Series B, $150M) in June 2024 to fuel international product development and compliance expansion, with Australia cited as a priority market for servicing fast-growing businesses seeking global talent[GLOBAL scope, inferred from industry tracking].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Named a top HR partner platform in Australia for offshore/hybrid technical teams in 2025, according to multiple market reviews and business use cases[3]. [GLOBAL] Remote was recognized as a leader in remote employment compliance and payroll innovation at various SaaS industry events in 2024–2025, further supporting its adoption by APAC organizations[GLOBAL scope, industry recognition].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] No reported executive appointment specific to Australia in the last 6–12 months, though strategic hires are inferred at the APAC regional level to support client growth (inferred, as no specific names found in current data). [GLOBAL] Recent additions to Remote’s executive team—including a new Chief Revenue Officer in Q2 2024—are tasked with accelerating APAC growth and expanding product capabilities for cross-border hiring[GLOBAL scope, industry news].\n\n[INDUSTRY CONTEXT]\nAustralian companies are increasing reliance on platforms like Remote due to:\n- **Remote-first hiring** trending upward, especially for roles in engineering, product, and customer success.\n- **Advances in technology** (5G, AI-powered HR tooling, collaboration platforms) making global team management and onboarding seamless[1][2].\n- **Policy shifts** favoring more flexible remote work, enabling Australian firms to compete for global talent and address local shortages[1][2].\n\nScope notes: Most details above are regional or global due to limited direct company reporting for recent local (San Francisco or Australia-specific) changes. Remote is a leading global HR/payroll platform enabling companies to hire and pay internationally, with robust activity in Australia and the broader APAC region over the past year."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"About RemoteRemote is solving modern organizations’ biggest challenge – navigating global employment compliantly with ease. We make it possible for businesses of all sizes to recruit, pay, and manage international teams. With our core values at heart and future focused work culture, our team works tirelessly on ambitious problems, asynchronously, around the world. You can find Remoters working from 6 different continents (Antarctica left to go!) and all of our positions are fully remote.We encourage every member of the Remote team to bring their talents, experiences and culture to the table to help us build the best-in-class HR platform.If you are energetic, curious, motivated and ambitious, be part of our world. Apply now and define the future of work!What This Job Can Offer YouSales helps our prospective customers and active customers to fully experience our Global HR Platform. Sales is the team responding to incoming queries and helping customers understand how to maximise Remote’s full suite of products to meet their employment needs. To enable them to embody our value of Transparency, we have a fair price guarantee. This is an exciting time to join Remote and make a personal difference in the global employment space as a Outbound Sales Development Representative, joining our Sales team.What You BringProven business development success through effective use of core sales tools (Knowledge of Hubspot, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Chorus is a plus)Experience working as an SDR in a B2B SaaS Tech companyAble to negotiate skillfully, promote/sell ideas persuasivelyExceptional communication skills, both oral and written, coupled with excellent listening skills and a positive and energetic phone presenceAble to think strategically and tactically. Able to maintain a positive attitude in the face of criticism, rejection, or failurePromotes a strong sense of urgency for reaching goals and key deliverables. Self Starter. proactive and brings new ideas to the teamExtremely self-motivated with a diligent work ethicDemonstrated success in the below areas listed in key responsibilitiesWrites and speaks fluent EnglishIt''s not required to have experience working remotely, but considered a plusKey ResponsibilitiesRespond, engage and qualify outbound leads and inquiriesSourcing new sales prospects and reaching out to them to book appointments for Account ExecutivesClearly communicating Remote''s value propositions to prospects and learning about their needs to see if there’s a good fitProviding support to Account Executive team as neededBe responsible for educating and developing prospects leading to hand-off to sales teamsCreate target prospects lists and penetrate key accountsCold call into prospects generated by variety of outside sourcesIdentify key players, researching and obtaining business requirements, and presenting solutions to begin sales cyclePracticalsYou''ll report to: Manager, Outbound Sales DevelopmentTeam: SalesLocation: Australia/ New ZealandStart date: As soon as possibleRemote Compensation PhilosophyRemote''s Total Rewards philosophy is to ensure fair, unbiased compensation and fair equity pay along with competitive benefits in all locations in which we operate. We do not agree to or encourage cheap-labor practices and therefore we ensure to pay above in-location rates. We hope to inspire other companies to support global talent-hiring and bring local wealth to developing countries.At first glance our salary bands seem quite wide - here is some context. At Remote we have international operations and a globally distributed workforce. We use geo ranges to consider geographic pay differentials as part of our global compensation strategy to remain competitive in various markets while we hiring globally.The On-Target Earnings for this position is between $61,000 USD to $71,000 USD. The base salary is 70%. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level and location, and our job titles may span more than one career level. The actual base pay for the successful candidate in this role is dependent upon many factors such as location, transferable or job-related skills, work experience, relevant training, business needs, and market demands. The base salary range may be subject to change.Application processInterview with RecruiterInterview with Manager, Outbound Sales Development Exercise Stage + Mock Call SessionInterview with Senior ManagerBar RaiserPrior employment verification check BenefitsOur full benefits & perks are explained in our handbook at remote.com/r/benefits. As a global company, each country works differently, but some benefits/perks are for all Remoters:work from anywhereflexible paid time offflexible working hours (we are async)16 weeks paid parental leavemental health support servicesstock optionslearning budgethome office budget & IT equipmentbudget for local in-person social events or co-working spacesHow You’ll Plan Your Day (and Life)We work async at Remote which means you can plan your schedule around your life (and not around meetings). Read more at remote.com/async.You will be empowered to take ownership and be proactive. When in doubt you will default to action instead of waiting. Your life-work balance is important and you will be encouraged to put yourself and your family first, and fit work around your needs.If that sounds like something you want, apply now!How To ApplyPlease fill out the form below and upload your CV with a PDF format.We kindly ask you to submit your application and CV in English, as this is the standardised language we use here at Remote.If you don’t have an up to date CV but you are still interested in talking to us, please feel free to add a copy of your LinkedIn profile instead.Not only do we encourage folks from all ethnic groups, genders, sexuality, age, abilities, disability status and any other under-represented group to apply, but we prioritize a sense of belonging. We have 4 ERGs (Women, Disability, Queer, Minorities in Tech) who meet regularly with the People team. During your interviews and beyond, we ask & encourage anybody who needs an accommodation to request one from their recruiter.We will ask you to voluntarily tell us your pronouns at interview stage, and you will have the option to answer our anonymous demographic questionnaire when you apply below. As an equal employment opportunity employer it’s important to us that our workforce reflects people of all backgrounds, identities, and experiences and this data will help us to stay accountable. We thank you for providing this data, if you chose to.At Remote, we embrace AI as a valuable tool while prioritizing human creativity and authenticity. We look forward to meeting candidates who balance innovation with genuine expertise and experience. To learn more about Remote''s AI guidelines check see here.Please note we accept applications on an ongoing basis."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-28T04:09:00.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec36r5MujzVcCBGX', 'RIB Software', 'https://www.rib-software.com/en/home/', 'https://de.linkedin.com/company/rib-software', 'Stuttgart, Baden-Württemberg', 'Software Development', '1.001–5.000 Beschäftigte', '80', 'RIB Software is a growth-stage software company (1,001–5,000 employees) in the core commercial B2B tech sector, actively hiring for sales roles such as Senior Business Development Manager and Enterprise Account Manager. The company operates in Australia with strong local leadership (Sales Directors, Managing Director) providing Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision-maker access. Multiple growth signals are present, including major project wins, team expansion, and new product launches in the Australian market. While there is no recent independent funding, the Schneider Electric acquisition ensures robust backing. The combination of high-priority sales roles, strong industry fit, and clear growth indicators makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] RIB Software has played a pivotal role in a series of signature Sydney and NSW infrastructure projects in the past 12 months, including the completion of the WestConnex M4-M5 Link Tunnels (finished 2023) and ongoing work on Sydney Metro (with a stage completion scheduled for 2024)[2]. Their platform, RIB CX, supported contracts management, quality control, and project documentation in both projects, and is being used on HumeLink, New South Wales’ largest energy infrastructure build[2].\n\n[LOCAL] RIB Software has also supported the Alkimos Seawater Desalination Plant (construction started late 2023) and over 30 confidential defense projects throughout Australia in the past year, handling quality assurance, risk management, and workflow automation[2].\n\n[REGIONAL] The firm’s Pacific Managing Director, Chris Smith, reported in 2024 that RIB Software is now a \"major player in the Australian construction industry\" due to rising demand for digital transformation in building and infrastructure management[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] RIB Software continues to invest in Australian capability, positioning its Sydney operations as a technology hub for major infrastructure clients. The company has expanded consulting and client success teams in NSW to support rising user demand and large project wins[1][2]. Their hiring focus has emphasized roles in construction digitalization, project controls, and client implementation specialists, with indications of continued recruitment throughout 2024[1].\n\n[GLOBAL] Following Schneider Electric’s acquisition, RIB Software benefits from integration into a global ecosystem that is investing in the build phase of construction technology, bringing international best practice and capital to its Sydney and ANZ operations[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There have been no independent RIB Software funding rounds reported in the past year; instead, growth is being fueled by Schneider Electric’s backing as part of its strategic build portfolio post-acquisition in 2021[1]. Expansion resources for Australia come from broader SE digital transformation initiatives.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] RIB Software’s partnership with ACCIONA Geotech was cited as a best-in-class example in 2024, where use of RIB CX enabled digitized governance and contributed to an international quality award for ACCIONA[1].\n\n[LOCAL] The company launched the RIB Carbon Quantifier tool for local clients, providing free embodied carbon measurement for projects in Australia to help reduce emissions and support sustainability reporting in line with government and industry mandates[1].\n\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] RIB CX is central to compliance and timely delivery for large infrastructure clients, with reported outcomes including 25% average cost/overhead reduction and an 80% drop in non-conformances among Sydney-area projects adopting the platform[1][2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Chris Smith continues as Managing Director and Vice President for RIB Software Pacific, based in Australia, providing a stable APAC leadership presence through late 2024[1].\n\n[GLOBAL] No major executive turnover at the global or regional level impacting the Sydney or AU business has been disclosed in the past 12 months[1].\n\n**SCOPE INDICATORS:**  \n- Most insights above are [LOCAL] to Sydney and the broader NSW/AU market, reflecting major project participation and client expansion.  \n- [REGIONAL] details reference Pacific/APAC leadership and expanded consulting teams.  \n- [GLOBAL] context provided for funding, as all major investment activity is now through parent Schneider Electric.  \n- Broader [INDUSTRY] signals point to ongoing growth in digital construction and project controls software adoption across Australia in 2024, with RIB a market leader in infrastructure and public sector builds[1][2][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Driven by transformative digital technologies and trends, we are RIB and we’ve made it our purpose to propel the industry forward and make engineering and construction more efficient and sustainable. Built on deep industry expertise and best practice, and with our people at the heart of everything we do, we deliver the world''s leading end-to-end lifecycle solutions that empower our industry to build better.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With a steadfast commitment to innovation and a keen eye on the future, RIB comprises over 2,500 talented individuals who extend our software’s reach to over 100 countries worldwide. We are experienced experts and professionals from different cultures and backgrounds and we collaborate closely to provide transformative software products, innovative thinking and professional services to our global market. Our strong teams across the globe enable sustainable product investment and enhancements, to keep our clients at the cutting-edge of engineering, infrastructure and construction technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We know our people are our success – join us to be part of a global force that uses innovation to enhance the way the world builds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Find out more at RIB Careers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Sales Director - APAC&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Brisbane, Australia /Sydney, Australia&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; full-time&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The job &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are seeking a strategic, results-driven Sales Director for the APAC territory to lead and grow our territory sales operations. This role is responsible for developing and executing the APAC sales strategy, managing key customer relationships, driving revenue growth, and leading a high-performing sales team across multiple markets. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of the APAC business landscape, a strong track record in B2B sales, and the ability to work cross-functionally to support market expansion and customer success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the APAC territory sales strategy aligned with global business objectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop a sales team to meet and exceed targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify new market opportunities and drive business development across diverse APAC markets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with key customers, partners, and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Forecast regional revenue, monitor performance metrics, and report to senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with marketing, product, and operations teams to support go-to-market initiatives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum 8–10 years’ experience in territory sales leadership, ideally within APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Background in engineering and construction software is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of delivering consistent revenue growth and managing cross-country teams&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of cultural, regulatory, and market dynamics across APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent leadership, negotiation, and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel within the region as required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you''re passionate about driving growth, tackling complex business challenges, and fostering strong customer relationships, you''ll find success and fulfilment in our Commercial team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;RIB may require all successful applicants to undergo and pass a comprehensive background check before they start employment. Background checks will be conducted in accordance with local laws and may, subject to those laws, include proof of educational attainment, employment history verification, proof of work authorization, criminal records, identity verification, credit check. Certain positions dealing with sensitive and/or third party personal data may involve additional background check criteria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;RIB is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are committed to being an exemplary employer with an inclusive culture, developing a workplace environment where all our employees are treated with dignity and respect. We value diversity and the expertise that people from different backgrounds bring to our business.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Come and join RIB to create the transformative technology that enables our customers to build a better world."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQEAcLCsjCUx5w/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1675178824933/rib_software_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=LNk-owfpw6wefY5ek8sdmB5kfSQsFOEaq01tyvUkhD0', '2025-09-28T03:49:56.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec3YHnI4PHSWfAwe', 'Diligent', 'http://www.diligent.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/diligent-board-member-services', 'New York, NY', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '82', 'Diligent is a growth-stage SaaS company (1,001–5,000 employees) in the core commercial B2B tech sector, actively employing a Business Development Representative (BDR) in Sydney. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Regional VP Sales, Regional Sales Directors, Solution Sales Directors) in both Australia and Singapore provides strong access for recruitment engagement. Recent growth signals include major APAC events, ongoing platform innovation, and deepening regional market penetration, although no recent local funding or leadership changes are noted. The BDR role is a primary target, and the company’s scale, industry fit, and regional activity make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Diligent is hosting *Diligent Connections 2025* in Sydney (Darlinghurst) at the Australian Museum, gathering governance, risk, and compliance (GRC) leaders to explore AI-driven advancements and strategies in GRC as of February 2025[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Diligent Connections 2025 is touring key APAC cities (including Sydney, Singapore, Manila), with a focus on how AI and the Diligent One Platform are transforming risk and compliance practices for boards and executives across the region[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The scale of the 2025 Sydney AI & GRC Conference, now in its third year, evidences Diligent’s embedded presence in the NSW GRC community and ongoing investment in local market leadership[1]. Multiple expert speakers from prominent Australian organizations (e.g., Harvey Norman, Healius, Yancoal, Snowy Hydro, QBE) are featured, indicating substantial local client engagement[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Diligent’s regional events and platform demonstrations at APAC locations suggest ongoing efforts to deepen market penetration and customer success in Australia and across the APAC GRC sector[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Diligent reports a user base of *25,000 organizations and 1 million users globally*, unified on the Diligent One Platform, confirming strong global adoption with likely spill-over growth effects in Australia[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There are no new funding rounds or financial milestones specific to Australia or APAC in the last 6–12 months found in current search results. Global development and ongoing investment in AI-powered platform enhancements were highlighted, which would impact all operating regions[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Diligent is showcasing cutting-edge AI features for corporate governance, risk, and entity management at the 2025 Sydney conference, including demos of “AI-powered risk & assurance,” a new “Entities Management interface,” and audit innovations (ACL AI)[1].  \n[REGIONAL] APAC events position Diligent as a regional leader in AI-driven GRC solutions, with immersive panels and interactive demos receiving regional attention[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Launch and active marketing of the “Diligent One Platform”—a unified GRC solution leveraging automation and analytics—represent the company’s flagship innovation globally with cascading benefits for Australian clients[2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] There are no specific reports of Sydney- or APAC-based leadership appointments, departures, or promotions in the last 6–12 months in the results reviewed.  \n[GLOBAL] No major global leadership changes impacting the APAC region are noted in this timeframe.\n\nIf you require more detailed information about hiring activity, partnerships, or individual Sydney office leadership, the company does not appear to have publicized such details in recent months. Diligent’s external-facing activity in Sydney is currently concentrated around high-profile ecosystem building, AI-driven platform launches, and enterprise GRC thought leadership[1][2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Diligent is the AI leader in governance, risk and compliance (GRC) SaaS solutions, helping more than 1 million users and 700,000 board members to clarify risk and elevate governance. The Diligent One Platform gives practitioners, the C-Suite and the board a consolidated view of their entire GRC practice so they can more effectively manage risk, build greater resilience and make better decisions, faster.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Diligent, we''re building the future with people who think boldly and move fast. Whether you''re designing systems that leverage large language models or part of a team reimaging workflows with AI, you''ll help us unlock entirely new ways of working and thinking. Curiosity is in our DNA, we look for individuals willing to ask the big questions and experiment fearlessly - those who embrace change not as a challenge, but as an opportunity. The future belongs to those who keep learning, and we are building it together. At Diligent, you’re not just building the future - you’re an agent of positive change, joining a global community on a mission to make an impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Learn more at diligent.com or follow us on LinkedIn and Facebook&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Diligent Business Development Representative I (BDR I) plays an instrumental role in the direct growth of Diligent by seeking new business opportunities through prospecting and engaging with potential clients. The BDR I is expected to build new outbound pipeline and generate interest as a brand ambassador for the Diligent products. A BDR I should demonstrate conversational excellence and in-depth product knowledge to achieve outbound targets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a market leading and rapidly growing business, highly focused on achieving goals and delivering results. The role offers an excellent basic and competitive commission structure, with high achievers given the opportunity to progress within the business becoming an expert in corporate software sales.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate expertise at using lead generation tools to routinely extract contacts and create accurate and targeted lists of prospects (Cold calling, LinkedIn, Outreach, Sales Force, ZoomInfo, etc). &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct sales development best practices through email, phone, and social activities using the various software tools to connect with new prospects. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize smart, targeted questions to speak knowledgeably to qualify the right decisions makers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skillfully build interest and influence opportunities with new prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate meetings/demonstrations on account executive’s calendar and log activities in CRM.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet or exceed targets &amp;amp; key performance indicators (KPIs) as determined by the business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to assist others with viable techniques to drive overall team performance.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Other duties may be requested in accordance with business need.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience/Skills&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong passion for working in a sales-focused, target-driven environment. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of the sales process, including marketing, prospecting, cold calling, and managing the sales cycle. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to effectively communicate the product’s unique value proposition and quickly gain in-depth product knowledge. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills, with a track record of engaging and influencing senior-level executives. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written presentation skills, with the ability to deliver clear and persuasive messages. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High energy, with a positive and can-do attitude that drives success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in SaaS sales Experience building strong stakeholder relationships at c-suite level.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Diligent Offers You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Creativity is ingrained in our culture. We are innovative collaborators by nature. We thrive in exploring how things can be differently both in our internal processes and to help our clients&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We care about our people. Diligent offers a flexible work environment, global days of service, comprehensive health benefits, meeting free days, generous time off policy and wellness programs to name a few&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We have teams all over the world. We may be headquartered in New York City, but we have office hubs in Washington D.C., Vancouver, London, Galway, Budapest, Munich, Bengaluru, Singapore, and Sydney.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Diversity is important to us. Growing, maintaining and promoting a diverse team is a top priority for us. We foster and encourage diversity through our Employee Resource Groups and provide access to resources and education to support the education of our team, facilitate dialogue, and foster understanding.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Diligent created the modern governance movement. Our world-changing idea is to empower leaders with the technology, insights and connections they need to drive greater impact and accountability – to lead with purpose. Our employees are passionate, smart, and creative people who not only want to help build the software company of the future, but who want to make the world a more sustainable, equitable and better place.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Headquartered in New York, Diligent has offices in Washington D.C., London, Galway, Budapest, Vancouver, Bengaluru, Munich, Singapore and Sydney.  To foster strong collaboration and connection, this role will follow a hybrid work model. If you are within a commuting distance to one of our Diligent office locations, you will be expected to &lt;strong&gt;work onsite at least 50% of the time.&lt;/strong&gt; We believe that in-person engagement helps drive innovation, teamwork, and a strong sense of community.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are a drug free workplace. Diligent is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religious creed, sex, national origin, ancestry, citizenship status, pregnancy, childbirth, physical disability, mental disability, age, military status, protected veteran status, marital status, registered domestic partner or civil union status, gender (including sex stereotyping and gender identity or expression), medical condition (including, but not limited to, cancer related or HIV/AIDS related), genetic information, or sexual orientation in accordance with applicable federal, state and local laws. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Diligent''s EEO Policy and Know Your Rights. We are committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at recruitment@diligent.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To all recruitment agencies:&lt;/strong&gt; Diligent does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Diligent employees or any other organization location. Diligent is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGoBATEkMWfSA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1700083885027/diligent_board_member_services_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=ui7yNiTe9g6DuqH2wwuMlWZs37LTAGZJZodlk-xvzGY', '2025-09-20T06:35:15.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec3ahYk1hpyxi31g', 'Meltwater', 'http://meltwater.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/meltwater', 'San Francisco, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '65', 'Meltwater is a growth-stage computer software (SaaS) company with 2,563 employees, fitting the ideal client profile for commercial B2B tech recruitment. While the specific sales role trigger is not provided, the company operates in a core industry and has recently launched major AI-driven products and expanded partnerships, indicating strong growth signals. Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Directors, Regional Managers) are present, supporting viable recruitment engagement. However, the absence of explicit sales hiring activity or recent funding limits the score to high rather than very high.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOn May 6, 2025, Meltwater officially launched Mira AI, a comprehensive intelligence engine to accelerate PR and marketing insights, at their annual Meltwater Summit in New York. The company also expanded its AI partnership with Microsoft, rolling out Meltwater Copilot for Microsoft Teams during its 2025 Mid-Year Product Release.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nMeltwater has introduced new enterprise products such as Explore+ for large-scale social and media intelligence, suggesting a focus on expanding sales to global enterprise customers. There is no recent public data on specific hiring or headcount growth within sales or GTM functions.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn July 2025, Meltwater released major product enhancements including GenAI Lens for brand monitoring in generative AI, and new TikTok analytics. The company also launched Explore+ in July 2025 for advanced enterprise media intelligence and rolled out significant upgrades to influencer and campaign reporting features.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Meltwater empowers companies with a suite of solutions that spans media, social, consumer, and sales intelligence. By analyzing ~1 billion pieces of content each day and transforming them into vital insights, Meltwater unlocks the competitive edge to drive results. With 27,000 global customers, 50 offices across six continents, and 2,300 employees, Meltwater is the industry partner of choice for global brands making an impact."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec4AJdmaA6pXH3xC', 'Saviynt', 'http://www.saviynt.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/saviynt', 'El Segundo, California', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '80', 'Saviynt is a growth-stage software company (1,001-5,000 employees) in the core B2B tech sector, actively expanding its APAC presence with a focus on sales and technical enablement in Australia and Singapore. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Regional VP, SVP APJ, Sales Directors) provides strong access for recruitment engagement. While no specific active sales role is listed, recent regional sales leadership appointments, office openings, and ongoing partner enablement initiatives indicate sustained hiring and growth momentum. These factors make Saviynt a high-priority recruitment opportunity for commercial sales roles in APAC.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] In May 2025, Saviynt hosted partner bootcamps in Sydney and Melbourne as part of its Saviynt University initiative, training over 40 individuals from 19 organizations in two days to address Australia’s acute cybersecurity skills gap[1].  \n[LOCAL] Saviynt held local events in Sydney, including its UNLOCK 2025 global identity security tour, highlighting its focus on AI-driven identity platforms for the enterprise market[4].  \n[REGIONAL] Saviynt is deepening its APAC presence, naming new regional offices and investments as part of a wider global expansion effort announced in July 2025, with Sydney serving as a base for ANZ growth and partner development[2][3].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Sydney office located at Level 24, Three International Towers, 300 Barangaroo Avenue, serves as a market entry and customer engagement hub for Australia and New Zealand[3].  \n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] Senior leadership has prioritized technical enablement, sales, and local partnership growth in Sydney and Melbourne since early 2025[1][3].  \n[GLOBAL] Over the past 12 months, Saviynt strategically consolidated and strengthened its executive and regional sales leadership, but no major C-level departures were reported[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new public funding rounds announced in the last 6–12 months. Saviynt remains well-capitalized, having previously raised significant investment, including growth rounds focused on international expansion[3].  \n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Rapid upskilling of local partners in Sydney, with Saviynt University sessions praised for improving solution implementation and technical confidence in Australia’s identity security ecosystem[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Australian partners cited as market leaders in deploying “faster go-lives and smarter solutions that scale,” aided by Saviynt’s cloud-native platform and AI-driven identity intelligence[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Dan Mountstephen (SVP, Asia Pacific & Japan) and Suraj Krishnaiah (VP, Enablement and Solutions) are named as driving local and regional growth, overseeing technical and partner investments across ANZ[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Company-wide, there have been new appointments in revenue, global channels, and regional sales roles over the last 12 months to support growth; no significant APAC-specific departures or country head appointments for Australia were publicly disclosed[3].\n\n---\nSaviynt demonstrates sustained investment and partnership enablement in Sydney and broader Australia, focusing on upskilling, local technical ecosystem growth, and regional expansion—consistent with trends in the rapidly evolving identity security software market."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Saviynt is an identity authority platform built to power and protect the world at work. In a world of digital transformation, where organizations are faced with increasing cyber risk but cannot afford defensive measures to slow down progress, Saviynt’s Enterprise Identity Cloud gives customers unparalleled visibility, control and intelligence to better defend against threats while empowering users with right-time, right-level access to the digital technologies and tools they need to do their best work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Saviynt is looking for a professional, highly motivated and energetic Account Executive to drive regional enterprise sales for our disruptive IaaS Cloud Security, Access Governance &amp;amp; Privileged Access Management solutions in the greater Melbourne Area.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The AE will combine good working knowledge of (IaaS &amp;amp; SaaS) Identity, Cloud Security or&amp;nbsp;PAM technology with prospecting and sales skills.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This person is ultimately responsible for the entire enterprise sales cycle within their territory and meeting or exceeding territory quota.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Account Executives are the primary interface to both Prospects and Customers and responsible for actively driving and managing day-to-day prospecting &amp;amp; selling activity in the region.&amp;nbsp; This activity includes opportunity Discovery, Demo, RFP/RFI, Evaluation &amp;amp; POC stages of the sales process, working in conjunction with SE &amp;amp; Product Management Teams to identify &amp;amp; close new deals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively interact with Field Sales, Cloud Team, and Line of Business decision-makers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learn and maintain knowledge of Saviynt’s solutions, focused on Cloud&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Security, Cloud Access Governance &amp;amp; PAM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Aggressively identify qualified sales opportunities across all assigned accounts/ territory&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and leverage all lead sources (personal and partner contacts, inbound leads, events, and outbound prospecting) to generate meaningful pipeline&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain disciplined, detailed, and up-to-date records on Lead &amp;amp; Opportunity activity in SFDC to ensure effective lead development, proper team communication, and executive visibility&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be diligent in timely follow-up and provide quality work products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend and assist with corporate and field sales &amp;amp; marketing events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve monthly and quarterly revenue objectives&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU BRING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be located in Melbourne&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;7+ years experience in enterprise Identity, Cloud Security, or PAM Sales preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Possess a knowledge base of Cloud Identity Management, Cloud Privileged&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access Management and/or Cloud Security Governance technology&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Solid cybersecurity territory contacts at VP, SVP, CxO levels&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Successful history of working with Resellers, SI’s, and Advisories&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong Customer Service orientation, persistence, and ability to follow through&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability and skill to navigate through all levels of an enterprise organization to drive sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Professional, ambitious, determined, and results-oriented mindset&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Positive attitude, team-oriented, self-starter who can work alone and in a collaborative manner to achieve regional goals&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Saviynt is an amazing place to work. We are a high-growth, Platform as a Service company focused on Identity Authority to power and protect the world at work. You will experience tremendous growth and learning opportunities through challenging yet rewarding work that directly impacts our customers, all within a welcoming and positive work environment. If you''re resilient and enjoy working in a dynamic environment you belong with us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Saviynt is an equal opportunity employer and we welcome everyone to our team.&amp;nbsp; All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or veteran status.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQE_dyiI2DinaQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1720471093310/saviynt_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=pgp9bKZmgCOBsx5tfMlK2P305Q3J3FalwNL2XhKff-M', '2025-09-23T14:14:26.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec4dnkPynpjBd3CX', 'Syniti', 'http://www.syniti.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/synitidata', 'Needham, Massachusetts', 'Software Development,IT Services and IT Consulting,IT System Data Services', '1,001-5,000 employees', '75', 'Syniti is a growth-stage IT services and software company (1,001-5,000 employees) with active ANZ operations and a clear regional expansion strategy. The presence of a Head of Sales ANZ and Country Sales Manager (Tier 2 decision makers) provides strong access for recruitment discussions. While the specific sales role triggering inclusion is not listed, the company''s commercial B2B tech focus and recent growth signals (regional expansion, leadership appointments, major client wins) indicate a high likelihood of external recruitment needs for sales roles. No recent funding but significant mergers and APAC investment reinforce opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Syniti operates locally as \"BackOffice Associates Australia Pty Ltd\" with a Sydney office at Level 5, 309 George Street, supporting enterprise data transformation through software and services, including data migration and master data management[1][3].\n[REGIONAL] Syniti has identified the ANZ region, including Sydney, as a priority market within its broader Asia Pacific expansion strategy, focusing on increased investment and on-the-ground presence in recent quarters[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] Syniti has expressed a clear goal to expand further into the ANZ region, citing ANZ as one of the largest Asia Pacific markets and emphasizing \"exciting\" growth plans[2]. Their consultants deliver both technical and business-oriented data services, with recent projects in natural resources and food & beverage sectors, signaling continued engagement with key industries in Australia[2].\n[GLOBAL] As of their most recent official update, Syniti reported over 1,300 global employees, suggesting strong headcount and delivery capacity that also benefits regional clients[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] While no new funding specific to Australia or APAC in the past 6-12 months was found, Syniti completed notable strategic mergers globally (including DMR and 360Science) and expanded its product capabilities, which are being leveraged in APAC[4].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Syniti has achieved significant outcomes for APAC clients, notably saving an Australian natural resources company $10 million annually by eliminating duplicate equipment records, and delivering cash flow improvements in the food & beverage sector by fixing vendor payment misalignment[2].\n[GLOBAL] Expanded global delivery centers (e.g., in Walldorf, Germany, Latin America, and Eastern Europe) and developed stronger SAP partnerships and alliances that extend to ANZ delivery[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Gaj Pasuathy was named Senior Vice President of Delivery in 2022, overseeing Syniti’s global and APAC consulting operations, impacting delivery leadership for regional clients[2].\n[GLOBAL] Recent appointments at the VP/SVP level globally (including go-to-market and SAP alliance leads) indicate investment in executive talent supporting APAC growth, although no local Australian leadership changes have been reported in the last 6-12 months[4].\n\nScope notes: Most information specific to Syniti’s Australia/Sydney operations is limited; regional sources confirm active expansion and delivery for local enterprise customers. Global updates provide context around investment, mergers, product strategy, and executive activity that have a direct impact on APAC operations."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT US&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Syniti&lt;/strong&gt;, part of Capgemini, tackles the hardest work in data for the world’s largest organizations. We combine intelligent software with deep data expertise to help the Fortune2000 tackle complex data challenges and drive measurable business outcomes with business-ready data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Syniti’s Data First strategy transforms data from an afterthought into a strategic asset—unlocking insights, reducing risk, and fueling growth. With over 5,000 successful projects, we support the full data lifecycle through a unified platform for migration, quality, replication, matching, master data management, analytics, governance, and strategy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Operating globally across industries, Syniti’s award-winning software, expert consultants give enterprises a unique edge in managing and maximizing their data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Client Account Executive is responsible for overseeing a portfolio of assigned customers, at the same time developing a network of customers and partners for new business and driving revenue in all lines of business that include software sales, consulting, training and maintenance. In this role, you will liaise with cross-functional internal teams to improve the entire customer experience and provides overall management support for all assigned accounts across various industries in Australia and New Zealand.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Establish and maintain business relationships with existing and future clients.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Source &amp;amp; nurture new clients and sales strategies and manage the full sales cycle of new potential clients (in collaboration with the marketing team) until deals are finalized.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Prospect the market of SAP and non-SAP partners and customer in search of sales opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Understand strategies, business objectives and client needs in order to propose services in line with these strategies, objectives and needs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Build commercial offers and respond to RFPs while working in collaboration with the presales team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Organize discovery sessions and demonstrations with the pre-sales team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Negotiate and conclude sales.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Write and finalize contracts with the support of the management team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Support the delivery of sold services and monitor client satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Participate in steering committees during the implementation of SAP solutions, as needed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Maintain relationships with our strategic Alliances to drive existing opportunities and in search of new sales opportunities&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Maintain relationships with the Syniti Sales Team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT IT TAKES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Minimum of 5 years of experience in sales of professional services, projects and ERP solutions (&lt;strong&gt;SAP experience&lt;/strong&gt; considered a very strong asset).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Proven sales history of meeting objectives and targets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Ability to capitalize on existing relationships and knowledge in order to increase sales.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Strong understanding of &lt;strong&gt;Data Management&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Data Governance&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Data Transformation&lt;/strong&gt; is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Excellent communication skills in English (spoken and written)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Ability to multitask and prioritize.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Ability to work in a team environment, effectively interacting with others&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Must be results-oriented, and demonstrate a “Can-do” attitude – adaptability, flexibility and resourcefulness&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;· Be fully aligned to the &lt;strong&gt;core values&lt;/strong&gt; of our organization which are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;o &lt;strong&gt;Think Big&lt;/strong&gt; - Be courageous and bold. Aspire to greatness. Relentlessly pursue market innovation. Set the standard by which others follow. Create solutions that have a meaningful impact. Solve the challenges our customers don’t know they have.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;o &lt;strong&gt;Be Curious&lt;/strong&gt; - Be a lifelong learner. Seek out new ideas to serve customers. Understand our competition and the world. Be permanently dissatisfied with the status quo. Challenge preconceptions. Focus on the future rather than yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;o &lt;strong&gt;Take Action&lt;/strong&gt; - Be the first. Don’t wait. Take accountability. Inspire others by doing. Fail fast and learn from mistakes. Make a difference every day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;o &lt;strong&gt;Stronger Together&lt;/strong&gt; - Respect, trust and look out for each other. Celebrate diverse perspectives. Listen. Build connections and belonging. Act with integrity. Give back. One Syniti family.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE OFFER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust&lt;/strong&gt; in your talent. At Syniti you will find a supportive environment and access to learning tools, but micromanagement is not our style.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth&lt;/strong&gt;. We are growing rapidly and steadily solving the biggest challenges enterprise companies are faced with today. There was never a better time to join and grow with us. Most importantly you will have the chance to shape our journey and share in our success story.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support&lt;/strong&gt;. We all rely on each other and enable each other to be successful. You won’t stand alone.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curiosity and genuine interest in you&lt;/strong&gt;. We all have our different stories, all equally fascinating with each depicting a different journey and we want to hear them all.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recognition&lt;/strong&gt;. We are the sum of individual achievements, and we always take the time to celebrate them.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An open organisation&lt;/strong&gt;. Titles don’t define access at Syniti. We stay humble regardless of where we sit in the organisation. We want to hear every voice, listen to all the ideas and make sure everyone’s work is seen and valued.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR COMMITMENT TO INCLUSION &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Syniti, we’re committed to creating a respectful, inclusive, and fair workplace where everyone belongs and thrives. We believe that diverse perspectives make us stronger — and we value the unique backgrounds, experiences, and voices each person brings to our team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We welcome applicants based on their skills and potential, and we’re dedicated to ensuring equal opportunities for all, regardless of personal background. If you need accommodations during the hiring process, please let us know — we’re here to support you.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQHgi701vN-3KQ/company-logo_200_200/B4EZXYBN0SHUAI-/0/1743085952596/synitidata_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=slPzlmvm5VORnK7PeeHYxNs-ej9q0ZvaU5wyjiuzXjQ', '2025-09-22T14:17:48.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec4xPUTqQBcP7UDj', 'Securiti', 'https://securiti.ai', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/securitiai', 'San Jose, California, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '501 - 1000', '66', 'Securiti is a growth-stage computer & network security company (1,133 employees) with operations in Australia and Singapore, actively hiring for regional sales leadership and management roles (Regional Sales Director, Regional Sales Manager). The industry fit is strong (core B2B tech), and decision maker access is excellent with multiple Tier 1 (VP International Sales, Regional Sales Directors) and Tier 2 (Regional Sales Manager) contacts. However, there are no recent growth or hiring signals, funding, or expansion activity reported, which slightly tempers the immediate recruitment opportunity. The combination of strong role priority, industry fit, and decision maker access makes this a HIGH priority lead.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSecuriti was named one of the \"20 Coolest Network Security Companies of 2025\" by CRN in January 2025, indicating rising industry recognition and market demand for its offerings. No major strategic changes or M&A activity reported in the last six months[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent hiring or headcount expansion publicly reported in the last 6-12 months. No significant evidence of market expansion or increased sales/GTM recruitment identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding announcements or financial milestones have been reported for Securiti in the last 6-12 months. No new investment rounds identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nRecognition as a top network security company on CRNâs Security 100 list in January 2025 is a notable achievement. No additional product launches, awards, or major milestones have been reported recently[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes, executive hires, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles have been publicly disclosed in the past 6-12 months. No recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Securiti is the pioneer of the DataAI Command Center, a centralized platform that enables the safe use of data and GenAI. It provides unified data intelligence, controls and orchestration across hybrid multicloud environments. Large global enterprises rely on Securiti''s Data Command Center for data security, privacy, governance, and compliance. \n\nSecuriti has been recognized with numerous industry and analyst awards, including \"Most Innovative Startup\" by RSA, \"Top 25 Machine Learning Startups\" by Forbes, \"Most Innovative AI Companies'''' by CB Insights, \"Cool Vendor in Data Security\" by Gartner, and \"Privacy Management Wave Leader'''' by Forrester.\n\nFor more information, please follow us on LinkedIn and visit Securiti.ai."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec5Ay4AuRtTcYbVw', 'Celigo', 'http://www.celigo.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/celigo-inc', 'Redwood City, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '65', 'Celigo is a growth-stage computer software company (720 employees) specializing in commercial B2B SaaS and integration solutions, which is a strong industry fit. The presence of an Account Executive APAC and Channel Sales Director in Australia provides Tier 2 decision maker access for sales recruitment. While there are no recent funding rounds or major headcount growth signals, ongoing product enhancements and regional sales leadership indicate sustained investment and market activity. The current sales role context (Account Executive) is high-priority, making this a high-probability recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCeligo participated as a sponsor at Manifest 2025 in February, showcasing its intelligent automation platform for supply chain integration and unveiling innovations in B2B EDI management and AI-driven automation. The company emphasized end-to-end supply chain visibility and streamlined onboarding during the event[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nCeligo has announced platform enhancements and new features through its August 2025 release, indicating ongoing product investment and development. No specific headcount growth or Australia-focused hiring in sales or GTM roles identified in recent sources[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or financial milestones identified in the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCeligo launched significant platform updates in August 2025, including improvements to Flow Builder, API Builder, and B2B Manager, as well as a migration to a new Builder UI for all accounts. The company received recognition for its B2B Manager for EDI as a scalable solution for modern supply chain operations at Manifest 2025[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, departures, or leadership changes identified in the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"The Celigo platform is a world-class integration platform as a service (iPaaS) that allows IT and line of business teams alike to automate both common and custom business processes, enabling the entire organization to be more agile and innovate faster than ever before."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFiJ7FyRjn4bg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1706025797969/celigo_inc_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=8CiYMHkC3VRwSbHgth4mIZF2VhvpHWu8F-F9qR0gCpc', '2025-09-18T20:53:10.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec5Nb3UbaFt2Qoif', 'Nearmap', 'https://www.nearmap.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/nearmap-com', 'Barangaroo, NSW, AU', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '75', 'Nearmap is a growth-stage computer software company (498 employees) actively expanding its insurance-focused product suite, indicating strong commercial B2B tech fit. While the specific sales role is not listed, the company has a history of strategic acquisitions and product launches, signaling ongoing growth. The filtered employee list does not show clear Tier 1 or Tier 2 sales decision makers, but the company size and industry fit make it a strong recruitment opportunity. Recent acquisitions and product launches are strong growth signals, supporting a high priority for external recruitment needs.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNearmap announced the acquisition of ITEL Laboratories from GTCR on May 20, 2025, aiming to integrate ITEL''s insurance technology solutions and expand Nearmap''s property and casualty insurance offerings. Earlier, on October 14, 2024, Nearmap acquired assets from Tensorflight, an AI platform for risk prediction in insurance.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNearmap has expanded its insurance-focused product suite and client base, now serving approximately 250 insurance carrier customers including seven of the top ten U.S. insurers. Recent acquisitions of Betterview and Tensorflight indicate strategic growth in both data capabilities and industry reach.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or new investment announcements identified in the past 6-12 months. Thoma Bravo continues as the lead strategic investor following prior acquisitions and remains involved during the ITEL deal.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nLaunched the Generation 6 (Gen 6) AI system in October 2024, offering over 130 AI-derived detections and scores for deeper location intelligence. Released Portfolio Intelligence, an AI-powered product on the Betterview platform, enabling advanced risk analysis for insurance carriers in March 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nAndy Watt continues as CEO of Nearmap, and ITEL CEO Brian Matthews will join the Nearmap Board of Directors following the acquisition. No other major leadership changes or new appointments in sales/revenue roles identified recently."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Nearmap is the location intelligence provider that our customers rely on for consistent, reliable, high-resolution imagery, insights, and answers to create meaningful change in our world and propel industries forward. \n\nHarnessing the power of state-of-the-art camera systems, aerial imagery, artificial intelligence (AI) and advanced SaaS platforms, our customers receive tailored solutions for complex challengesâempowering them to make an impact on peopleâs lives, build the resilient infrastructure of tomorrow, and protect homes, businesses, and communities. Nearmap stands as the definitive source of truth that shapes our liveable world. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec5QLrrwSGGrlLV2', 'ShiftCare', 'https://shiftcare.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/shiftcare', 'Macquarie Park, New South Wales, AU', 'Computer Software', '51 - 200', '73', 'ShiftCare is a growth-stage SaaS company (110 employees) in commercial B2B tech, actively employing a Sales Development Representative (SDR)—a primary target role. The presence of two Sales Directors and a Sales Operations Manager provides Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision maker access, supporting strong recruitment engagement. Recent product releases and onboarding enhancements signal ongoing growth and hiring readiness, though no recent funding or leadership changes are noted. This combination of role, industry fit, company size, and decision maker access makes ShiftCare a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nShiftCare has been actively advising providers on the operational impact and necessary system changes driven by Australia’s Aged Care Bill 2024, which introduces significant reforms effective 1 July 2025. The company also updated its platform to support compliance and operational adjustments for NDIS pricing changes in 2025.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nShiftCare has introduced features to streamline onboarding, allowing faster addition of new staff members and making roster building more efficient, which could indicate investment in supporting headcount growth and improved hiring workflows. There is an emphasis on technology that facilitates recruitment and team expansion, although specific hiring volume is not publicly detailed.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nRecent product releases include enhancements for pay rate management, streamlined onboarding, expanded integration capabilities (notably with QBO Australia and Xero), and a new messaging feature for care teams released within the last 6-12 months. The Family Portal and Medicaid-compliant EVV integration for US providers were also announced, showing product innovation through 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"ShiftCare software makes home care more efficient. From shared client profiles and team organisation, to simplified billing, we enable service providers to deliver higher standards of care, and grow their business.\n\nhttps://linktr.ee/shiftcare\n\nShiftCare has several advantages that make it highly suitable for Australian and North American service providers:\n\n1. Less time to manage schedules, staff and clients\n\n2. Taking the complexity out of managing many patients with different care requirements and billing rates\n\n3. Integration with National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS) means less time to submit claims and faster payments\n\n4. Connecting data between patients, shifts, time sheets and billing, eliminating duplication, errors and revenue leakage\n\n5. Automated notifications (SMS or email) to staff when a shift is confirmed, changed or cancelled, improving the communication between staff and management\n\n>>> \n\nIf you need to change the way you manage staff and bill your clients, please get in touch to arrange a free trial of ShiftCare. \n\n>>>\n\nShiftCare\nRoster staff. Manage clients. Fetch payments.\nhttps://shiftcare.com"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFWVG7zpokbzA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1693458448714/shiftcare_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=8vlknQFqKrLwcVyYwaqbrUUTDQsSmMZk_LRiltXmzmQ', '2025-09-18T20:56:33.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec5iNAjE4VrDRiFO', 'Ideagen', 'http://www.ideagen.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ideagen', 'Ruddington, Nottingham, GB', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '77', 'Ideagen is a growth-stage computer software company (1,284 employees) with a strong commercial B2B SaaS focus, actively hiring for core sales roles such as Enterprise Account Executive and Account Manager in Australia. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (VP Revenue APAC, Head of Sales, Country Manager, Sales Managers) provides direct access for recruitment engagement. While there are no recent funding rounds or direct headcount growth data, multiple acquisitions and new product launches in 2025 signal ongoing expansion and market activity. This combination of core role hiring, strong industry fit, quality decision makers, and acquisition-driven growth makes Ideagen a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIdeagen acquired WorkSafe Guardian on August 11, 2025, to expand its environmental, health, and safety (EHS) solutions and strengthen its presence in the Asia-Pacific region. On August 17, 2025, Ideagen also acquired Reactec, a provider of wearable safety technology, further enhancing its portfolio for high-risk industries and demonstrating continued acquisition-driven growth.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo direct hiring or headcount growth data identified in the last 6-12 months, but the pattern of rapid acquisitionsâincluding multiple companies in 2025âsuggests continued market and portfolio expansion.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, new investment announcements, or financial milestones identified in the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIdeagen achieved record-breaking results in the Summer 2025 G2 Reports, securing 84 badges and 34 number one rankings, including 46 consecutive âLeaderâ badges across categories like Quality Management and Regulatory Change Management (June 25, 2025). The company also launched a new Food & Beverage Solutions division in July 2025 to deliver end-to-end supply chain compliance for global brands.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo new executive appointments, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles identified within the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Ideagen brings clarity and confidence to the safe hands and trusted voices protecting our world.\n\nBy unifying deep regulatory expertise and innovation with affordable, best-in-class software we provide trusted, meaningful intelligence to regulated and high-compliance industries such as life sciences, healthcare, banking and finance, aviation, defense, manufacturing and construction.\n\nFrom the shop floor to the flight deck, from the front line to the boardroom, our 11,400 customers include more than 250 global aviation organizations, nine of the top ten accounting firms, nine of the top ten global aerospace and defense corporations, 15 of the top 20 global pharmaceutical companies and 65% of the top 20 global food & beverage companies and includes blue chip brands such as Heineken, British Airways, BAE, Aggreko, US Navy, Bank of New York and Johnson Matthey.â¯\n\nHeadquartered in Nottingham UK, with offices across the US, Australia, India, Malaysia and UAE, our 1400+ colleagues are dedicated to supporting industries to turn risk into resilience. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec6RZ65eUgEpENWC', 'Micromine', 'https://www.micromine.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/micromine', 'Perth, Western Australia', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '81', 'Micromine is a growth-stage software development company (201-500 employees) in commercial B2B tech, recently acquired by Weir, with strong SaaS revenue growth and major product launches. The presence of Tier 1 (General Manager) and Tier 2 (Sales Director, Enterprise Sales Manager, Business Development Manager) decision makers provides direct access to hiring authorities. The most relevant sales role is Business Development Manager, a medium-priority role. Multiple strong growth signals are present, including acquisition, leadership changes, product launches, and market expansion. This represents a high-priority recruitment opportunity, though not the highest due to the absence of primary target SDR/BDR roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] On 28 February 2025, Weir announced a binding agreement to acquire Micromine, a Perth-based mining software leader, for A$1.31 billion, subject to regulatory approval, with the transaction expected to complete by June 2025[1][2]. \n[LOCAL] Micromine hosted the APAC User Conference in Perth on 5 February 2025, featuring presentations from major mining clients such as Rio Tinto, Fortescue Metals Group, and Northern Star Resources, and showcased advancements in AI and the software development roadmap for 2025[3][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The company is maintaining a strong community presence in Perth, evidenced by major events like the APAC User Conference which drew 300 users from over 130 companies, reflecting active client engagement and a growing user base[5]. \n[GLOBAL] Micromine has demonstrated revenue growth of around 25% CAGR, with recurring SaaS income making up 90% of revenue, and sector-leading margins and cash generation—indicating continued business scaling and investment in digital mining technology[1]. \n[GLOBAL] Weir intends to leverage its global distribution network with Micromine’s offerings post-acquisition, signaling anticipated international market penetration from the Perth base[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] The acquisition by Weir constitutes a major financial milestone, valuing Micromine at A$1.31 billion ($814 million), and marks the largest investment event involving the company in the last year[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Showcased new AI-driven features and announced the launch of Micromine Advance for underground mine scheduling during the February 2025 Perth user conference[3]. \n[LOCAL] Continued collaboration and product demonstrations with major clients such as Rio Tinto, Fortescue, and Northern Star Resources reinforce Micromine’s leading industry position within Western Australia[3][5].\n[GLOBAL] Integration with Weir’s digital mining portfolio (including MOTION METRICS™ and NEXT) is expected post-acquisition—intended to create a platform for end-to-end process optimisation in mining globally, with implications for local technology leadership[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL/LOCAL] Kristen Walsh, currently Managing Director of Weir’s Minerals Division (APAC), will oversee the integrated digital business—including Micromine—after completion of the acquisition; Andrew Birch (current CEO, Micromine) will remain for up to 12 months in an advisory capacity for transition purposes[1].\n\n---\nSCOPE INDICATORS SUMMARY:\n- [LOCAL]: Major acquisition announcement in Perth; user conference; ongoing client engagement and technology showcase in WA.\n- [GLOBAL]: Acquisition details, growth indicators, leadership transition, strategic alignment with Weir’s global operations.\n- No significant [REGIONAL] or [INDUSTRY] context required, as substantial local and global company-specific data available.\n\nKey personnel or event names and dates are current through February 2025; primary sources are trade, company, and business news outlets."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;With over 39 years of innovation, Micromine is a global leader in mining software solutions. Our products are trusted by the world’s leading Mining Companies across more than 90 countries, empowering mining operations with real-time data, enhanced safety, and operational efficiency.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;An established multinational business, growing fast, with great benefits:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;High growth company providing growth opportunities for our people&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work from home (WFH) and flexibility options to balance work and home life&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;12 weeks paid parental leave – primary and secondary careers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Free gym membership&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Program for you and your family&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Social Connection and Responsibility Program&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discounted private health insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Novated leasing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work across both the Mining and Technology sectors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An engaging team culture and a modern office within Perth&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Opportunity&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re on the hunt for an Enterprise Sales Manager to join our APAC Sales team in Perth. This is a senior role with real impact, you’ll be at the forefront of expanding Micromine Beyond into the world’s largest mining companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Working closely with our Technical Presales and Operations teams, you’ll be the driving force behind identifying new opportunities, building executive-level relationships, and closing complex enterprise deals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities Include&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Presenting and selling Micromine’s enterprise solutions to major mining prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developing account strategies to identify, qualify, and close new business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Building long-term relationships with new and existing clients, including annual renewals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with presales, marketing, product, and services teams to deliver proposals and ensure successful outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Representing Micromine at industry events, seminars, and trade shows.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You will have a proven background in enterprise software sales, with a strong ability to influence senior stakeholders and deliver results in complex environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Skills, Experience, And Qualifications Include&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Significant experience in business development, client consultation, or enterprise software sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mining industry exposure and an understanding of mine planning and production team needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A stable track record of achieving above-budget sales performance, with revenue primarily from new customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, networking, and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience applying sales methodologies to enterprise-scale opportunities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;If you are looking to shape the future direction of technology in the mining industry, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To learn more or apply, visit our website at &lt;strong&gt;www.micromine.com&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Micromine is dedicated to fostering a diverse and inclusive work environment, and we welcome applicants from a variety of backgrounds to apply.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQG5gWmgoRwyFg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1720064584389/micromine_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=1UeCxy6ujrPwoIV3V-K4JHdW23D1jh89T4pcLxXdLgc', '2025-09-28T04:03:58.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec6VWzlHKkxP4NbM', 'menumiz™ (AU)', 'http://www.menumiz.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/universal-apps-menumiz', 'Adelaide, South Australia, AU', 'Computer Software', '11 - 50', '56', 'menumiz™ (AU) is a small growth-stage computer software company (18 employees) currently hiring for a Business Development Executive, a medium-priority sales role for 4Twenty. The company fits the core commercial B2B tech profile and has a Tier 2 decision maker (Sales Manager) available for recruitment engagement. However, there are no recent growth signals, funding, or hiring surges, which limits the immediate recruitment opportunity. This is a moderate opportunity due to company size and role fit, but lack of growth activity tempers the overall priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent hiring or team expansion activity detected. Headcount indicators from available sources remain unchanged in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNo recent awards, product launches, or specific milestone announcements found within the last 6-12 months.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures identified in available sources."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"menumiz™ is a comprehensive cafe & restaurant management and POS system designed for the modern dining experience, streamlining operations with digital menus, self-service ordering, direct kitchen communication, and seamless payment processing. By harnessing mobile technology, menumiz™ enhances service speed, improves quality, and simplifies payments, allowing restaurants to operate at peak efficiency, delight diners, and boost profitability effortlessly."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:35:57.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec6dKDlG74PvnckD', 'Huntress', 'https://huntress.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/huntress-labs', 'Columbia, Maryland, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '501 - 1000', '80', 'Huntress is a growth-stage cybersecurity SaaS company (747 employees) with active hiring for Account Executive and Sales Manager roles in Australia, both high-priority core sales positions. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech and has strong Tier 1 (Regional Director APAC) and Tier 2 (Sales Manager, Account Executive) decision makers present. Multiple strong growth signals are evident: recent $150M Series D funding, rapid headcount expansion, major product launches, and industry awards. While there is an internal recruiter, the scale and pace of growth suggest a high likelihood of external recruitment needs for sales talent.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nHuntress celebrated its 10th anniversary in August 2025, emphasizing a renewed mission focus and expansion of AI-assisted security operations[1]. In April 2025, the company launched a managed SIEM solution targeting smaller businesses and announced major enhancements for Microsoft security products integration[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHuntress now employs 600 staff, up significantly over the last year as indicated by its CEO during the anniversary announcement in August 2025[1]. The company continues to add new products and features to its platform and has ranked No. 773 on the 2025 Inc. 5000 list, demonstrating strong growth and operational scale[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nHuntress has raised a total of $300 million to date, including a $150 million Series D round in 2024 that valued the company at $1.5 billion[1][3][4]. Key investors include Forgepoint Capital, JMI Equity, Kleiner Perkins, Meritech Capital, and Sapphire Ventures[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nHuntress Managed EDR ranked #1 across 25 customer review reports in 2025, and the company was named to the Inc. Best Workplaces list and recognized by G2 as one of the worldâs best software companies[2]. Huntress became the first vendor to offer proactive protection against OAuth application threats in Microsoft 365 environments and launched new educational SAT features in early 2025[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nJen Easterly, former CISA director, joined the Huntress advisory board in August 2025 to help drive innovation and partnerships, with a particular focus on AI and strategic cybersecurity initiatives[3][4]. No other recent executive-level changes in sales or people roles have been identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Protect Your Endpoints, Identities, Logs, and Employees.\n\nThe fully managed security platform that combines endpoint detection and response, Microsoft 365 identity protection, a predictably affordable SIEM and science-based security awareness training. Powered by custom-built enterprise technology for mid-market enterprises, small businesses, and the MSPs that support them and delivered by unrivaled industry analysts in our 24/7 Security Operations Center. \n\nBy delivering a suite of purpose-built solutions that meet budget, security, and peace-of-mind requirements, Huntress is how the globeâs most underresourced businesses defend against todayâs cyberthreats. \n\nAs long as hackers keep hacking, we keep hunting."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
