    ('rec7uCqfPROCX2x6v', 'Cognizant', 'https://www.cognizant.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cognizant', 'Teaneck, New Jersey, US', 'Information Technology & Services', '10001 -', '97', 'Cognizant is a global IT services leader with extensive operations in Australia and Singapore, strong alignment to core technology and digital transformation sectors, and a robust sales and consulting infrastructure. The company is experiencing significant growth, evidenced by record revenue, major deal wins, and ongoing team expansion. Multiple senior sales and client partner roles are present, indicating active hiring and a high likelihood of engaging external recruiters for sales and revenue-focused positions. This represents an immediate and high-value opportunity for recruitment partnership.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCognizant reported strong second quarter 2025 results with $5.25 billion in revenue, two new mega deals over $1 billion each, and increased returned capital plans to $2 billion for 2025 as of July 30, 2025. The company concluded its NextGen restructuring program on December 31, 2024, with notable employee separation and facility exit costs in 2024.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nYear-over-year revenue grew by over 8% in Q2 2025, with record 12-month bookings of $27.8 billion and Q2 bookings up 18% due to large deals. Recent acquisitions contributed around 400 basis points to Q1 2025 revenue growth, mainly in North America, and guidance projects up to 6% growth for 2025 with sustained hiring and team expansion activity.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCognizant was recognized as a Leader in the High-Tech Industry Digital Services 2024-2025 RadarView Report by Avasant in April 2025, and joined an AI Education Taskforce at the White House to promote AI literacy in September 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Cognizant (Nasdaq-100: CTSH) engineers modern businesses. We help our clients modernize technology, reimagine processes and transform experiences so they can stay ahead in our fast-changing world. Together, weâre improving everyday life. See how at www.cognizant.com or @cognizant."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec7wCZzcZcoNFhhI', 'Netskope', 'https://www.netskope.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/netskope', 'Santa Clara, California, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '1001 - 5000', '95', 'Netskope is a leading cybersecurity SaaS provider with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore, recently filing for an $813 million IPO and reporting significant revenue and customer growth. The company is actively expanding its sales leadership and team, with multiple Regional Sales Managers, Directors, and Account Executives identified in APAC. Their direct sales-led strategy, recent high-profile partnerships, and established sales infrastructure indicate a strong and immediate need for external recruitment support for sales and revenue roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNetskope filed for an IPO on August 22, 2025, with plans to list on NASDAQ under the ticker NTSK; this follows a strategic partnership with Microsoft announced in late 2024 to integrate Netskope''s security capabilities with Microsoft''s Entra platform. The IPO is expected to increase Netskope''s market visibility and competitiveness, potentially boosting market share by up to 20% in key enterprise segments.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNetskope reported a 33% year-over-year increase in annual recurring revenue, reaching $707 million as of July 2025, with headcount surpassing 4,300 and a 21% increase in customer base to over 4,300 organizations. The company maintains a direct sales-led go-to-market strategy targeting Fortune 100 and global enterprise accounts, and recent analyst commentary cites ongoing hiring and R&D investment as key growth levers.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNetskope''s $813 million IPO was filed in late August 2025, targeting a valuation between $5.7 billion and $8.5 billion; prior financing activity within the last 12 months has not been publicly reported.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNetskope exceeded $700 million in ARR and secured more than 30% of Fortune 100 companies as customers by mid-2025, while being recognized in the Gartner Magic Quadrant as a leader in Security Service Edge (SSE) and SASE platforms for 2024 and 2025. The company also announced a significant product integration with Microsoftâs Entra in late 2024.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Netskope, a leader in modern security and networking, addresses the needs of both security and networking teams by providing optimized access and real-time, context-based security for people, devices, and data anywhere they go. Thousands of customers, including more than 30 of the Fortune 100, trust the Netskope One platform, its Zero Trust Engine, and its powerful NewEdge network to reduce risk and gain full visibility and control over cloud, AI, SaaS, web, and private applicationsâproviding security and accelerating performance without trade-offs."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec8Nzvsgd0IewCl4', 'Akamai Technologies', 'https://www.akamai.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/akamai-technologies', 'Cambridge, MA', 'Software Development', '5,001-10,000 employees', '45', 'Akamai Technologies is an enterprise software/cloud company (5,001-10,000 employees) with active sales hiring, including SDR and Sales Development roles in Australia and Singapore. The industry fit is strong (core B2B tech), but the large company size means sophisticated internal TA and less reliance on external recruiters. Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Managers, Directors) are present, and there are moderate regional growth signals (product launches, APAC expansion, leadership changes). While the SDR role is a primary target, the enterprise size limits the overall recruitment opportunity, making this a medium-priority lead.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Akamai cloud computing services enabled Australia-based MiClub to migrate its golf management solutions to the cloud in early-mid 2024, supporting business scalability and improving customer experiences across APAC clients[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Akamai announced the launch of Akamai Partner Connect, a consolidated global partner program rolling out in Q3 2025, streamlining engagement for resellers, distributors, and technology service providers—including regionally notable partners like Telstra and Fujitsu[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] Akamai’s Asia Pacific teams focus on direct sales, technical consulting, and support, with distributed cloud and cybersecurity services targeting growing regional demand for scalable infrastructure[1][4].  \n[LOCAL] Approximately 0.8% of Akamai’s 10,700+ global employees are based in Australia as of December 2024, reflecting ongoing staff presence for professional services, sales, and regional support[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Local partners in Australia such as Telstra, IBM Services, and Fujitsu remain key channels for growth in enterprise and infrastructure segments[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No specific recent funding rounds or financial milestones were disclosed for Akamai Technologies in the past 6–12 months across public sources.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Akamai powered MiClub’s successful transition to a cloud-first infrastructure, enabling service for over half of Australia’s golf clubs and supporting rapid business expansion through 2024[3].  \n[REGIONAL] Akamai’s cloud, security, and edge solutions remain central to digital-native business transformation in APAC, with recent product deployments for scalable, secure service delivery[3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Jay Jenkins was quoted as Akamai’s Chief Technology Officer for APJ (Asia Pacific & Japan) in 2024, actively shaping Akamai’s distributed cloud and cybersecurity strategy for the region[4].  \n[GLOBAL] Paul Joseph was named EVP of Global Sales and Services by 2025, overseeing the company’s new global partner engagement structures—including region-specific priorities for APAC[2].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Software development and cloud transformation in Australia are accelerating, with cloud-based software spend expected to grow at a 37% rate from 2021–2026—more than double the rate for non-cloud solutions[3].  \n[INDUSTRY] Distributed computing and AI-optimized workloads are forecast to reshape cloud and security sectors throughout APAC in 2025, supporting trends like platform engineering and dynamic scaling[4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Job DescriptionWould you like to work in a dynamic sales-growth role?Do you love collaborating across teams to deliver customer success?Join our world-class Security Technology Group!The Security business operates as a Sales Pursuit Team with deep domain knowledge of enterprises'' digital business. That includes network infrastructure and application security requirements. As a Sales Specialist you will collaborate with the wider Akamai team and channel partners to pursue and generate sales opportunities.Partner with the bestOur Enterprise Security team focuses on highly scalable security products. It enables us to provide our customers with high-quality Application Security and Zero Trust solutions. Our security solutions include API Security, DNS Security, Zero Trust Access and Micro-segmentation to protect our customers. Our goal is to secure, protect and accelerate all enterprise communication as a cloud security service.As an Enterprise Sales Executive Senior New and Existing Accounts, you will be responsible for:Being a leader in driving the Enterprise Security agenda internally and externally.Possessing charisma, energy and finesse to be a leader in driving the Enterprise Security agenda internally and externallyBeing adaptive, creative and resourceful, with a desire to operate in a start-up, undefined and matrix modeDemonstrating Enterprise Domain Expertise - Infrastructure, applications, networking or security background(s) in selling to senior executivesDo What You LoveTo be successful in this role you will:Have a proven track record of creating interest and pipeline within new or existing accountsBe able to understand why customers have brought from Akamai and articulate these in anecdotes or case-studiesDemonstrate experience working with multiple teams including Sales, SE, Customer Success, Renewals and Customer AdvocacyHave experience leading teams within a matrixed organizationDemonstrate excellent communication and presentation skillsHave the following experience: Cybersecurity including WAF and API Security, Zero trust technologies such as SASE and Micro Segmentation (ex. Cisco Tetration, VMware NSX), Firewall.Work in a way that works for youFlexBase, Akamai''s Global Flexible Working Program, is based on the principles that are helping us create the best workplace in the world. When our colleagues said that flexible working was important to them, we listened. We also know flexible working is important to many of the incredible people considering joining Akamai. FlexBase, gives 95% of employees the choice to work from their home, their office, or both (in the country advertised). This permanent workplace flexibility program is consistent and fair globally, to help us find incredible talent, virtually anywhere. We are happy to discuss working options for this role and encourage you to speak with your recruiter in more detail when you apply.Learn what makes Akamai a great place to workConnect with us on social and see what life at Akamai is like!We power and protect life online, by solving the toughest challenges, together.At Akamai, we''re curious, innovative, collaborative and tenacious. We celebrate diversity of thought and we hold an unwavering belief that we can make a meaningful difference. Our teams use their global perspectives to put customers at the forefront of everything they do, so if you are people-centric, you''ll thrive here.Working for youBenefitsAt Akamai, we will provide you with opportunities to grow, flourish, and achieve great things. Our benefit options are designed to meet your individual needs for today and in the future. We provide benefits surrounding all aspects of your life:Your healthYour financesYour familyYour time at workYour time pursuing other endeavorsOur benefit plan options are designed to meet your individual needs and budget, both today and in the future.About UsAkamai powers and protects life online. Leading companies worldwide choose Akamai to build, deliver, and secure their digital experiences helping billions of people live, work, and play every day. With the world''s most distributed compute platform from cloud to edge we make it easy for customers to develop and run applications, while we keep experiences closer to users and threats farther away.Join usAre you seeking an opportunity to make a real difference in a company with a global reach and exciting services and clients? Come join us and grow with a team of people who will energize and inspire you!Akamai Technologies is an Affirmative Action, Equal Opportunity Employer that values the strength that diversity brings to the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, race/ethnicity, protected veteran status, disability, or other protected group status."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-28T14:36:11.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec8gT8n2RBFU65vU', 'KPMG Australia', 'http://www.kpmg.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/kpmg-australia', 'Sydney, NSW, AU', 'Management Consulting', '5001 - 10000', '70', 'KPMG Australia is a major management consulting firm with a strong technology focus, demonstrated by its recent $80 million AI innovation program and digital transformation achievements. While recent restructuring and layoffs indicate some market challenges, the company continues to invest in technology and has a large, multi-level sales and consulting team including directors and sales managers. Decision maker access is strong, but immediate high-value sales hiring is not explicitly indicated, making this a high-priority but not top-tier opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn August 2025, KPMG Australia announced a refreshed firmwide strategy centered on AI investment and transformation, including an $80 million innovation program. The company also faced a 4% revenue decline in FY25 and cut 635 roles due to weaker demand in consulting and changes in government consulting budgets.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nKPMG Australia employed 8,967 people at the end of June 2025, hiring 637 new graduates and adding 71 new partners, but also reported a 6.6% headcount drop year-on-year due to restructuring and layoffs. The company reported record AI badge uptake among employees as it repositioned towards technology-focused offerings.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nKPMG Australia completed its three-year digital transformation in mid-2025, moving core systems to the cloud and issuing 7,300 AI training badges to staff. The firm reported over 13,000 clients and contributed $9.83 million in community impact for FY25.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Welcome to KPMG. We are a global network of professional firms providing a full range of services to organisations across a wide range of industries, government, and not-for-profit sectors.\n\nOur service areas are Audit, Assurance & Risk Consulting; Deals, Tax & Legal; Management Consulting; and Innovation & Digital Solutions. In addition, KPMG Enterprise tailors its services to meet the unique needs of mid-sized, fast growing and family owned businesses.\n\nIn Australia, KPMG has a long tradition of professionalism and integrity, combined with our dynamic approach to advising clients in a digital-driven world. We have approximately 10,000 people, including more than 600 partners, with offices around the country.\n\nOur deep expertise has seen us work with renowned companies to help them solve complex challenges, steer change, disrupt sectors and grow. Collaboration and innovation are ingrained in our approach, with our people aiming to provide genuine, sustainable value for our clients.\n\nConnect with us on:\n\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/kpmgaustralia\nYouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/kpmgaustralia\nTwitter: @kpmgaustralia"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec8r0ByGR0wLde1v', 'Zepto', 'https://www.zepto.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/zepto-payments', 'Byron Bay, New South Wales', 'Financial Services', '51-200 employees', '90', 'Zepto is a growth-stage fintech company (107 employees) in commercial B2B payments technology, actively expanding in Sydney/NSW with strong enterprise partnerships and rapid product adoption. The presence of a Director Enterprise Sales (Tier 2 decision maker) and Customer Success Manager (Tier 3) provides direct access to key sales hiring authorities. Recent funding, major partnerships, and award recognition signal robust growth and ongoing GTM hiring needs. The likely trigger role is Enterprise Sales, a high-priority core sales position, making this a very high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Zepto has processed over 1 million PayTo transactions for Australian enterprise customers as of July 2025, representing AUD $612.2 million in real-time payments—demonstrating significant adoption and activity in Sydney and broader NSW[2].\n[LOCAL] Zepto has partnered with major Australian brands including Red Energy, Woolworths’ Wpay, NAB, and Western Union to support real-time payments and PayTo infrastructures[1][4].\n[REGIONAL] Zepto’s partnership with NAB and fintech Banked is a finalist for \"Excellence in Industry Collaboration & Partnerships\" at the 2025 Finnies, the leading APAC fintech awards[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Zepto’s enterprise merchant integrations and expanding PayTo capabilities signal ongoing team and platform growth in Sydney and NSW, especially in payments operations and client solutions[2][4].\n[LOCAL] Zepto’s technology now supports payments for large consumer brands operating in Sydney, such as PointsBet and Superhero, suggesting ongoing commercial expansion and potential for increased sales/GTM hiring in local markets[4].\n[GLOBAL] Company headcount currently stands at 107 employees, per latest public data[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Zepto has raised a total of $18.6M AUD in funding across one round, per recent reporting (latest details available through company intel feeds), with continued product and market growth signaling prudent use of capital for regional expansion[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Shortlisted as a Finnies 2025 finalist for industry excellence—indicating peer recognition and sector influence, especially for collaborative payment platforms[4].\n[LOCAL] Zepto launched its first bi-annual PayTo Index, providing research and leadership in real-time payment settlement analytics for Australia, including Sydney-based enterprises[2].\n[LOCAL] Zepto’s real-time payment platform, including PayTo, shows a conversion rate of 99% and settlement times <5 seconds, enhancing customer experience and operational efficiency for Sydney/National clients[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Co-founder Trevor Wistaff transitioned from CTO to Chief Product Officer prior to September 2025, indicating strengthening of executive product leadership for local and national strategy[1].\n[GLOBAL] No recent global C-level appointments or departures detected since Wistaff change—executive team remains stable[1][3].\n\n[INDUSTRY] For financial services in Australia, real-time account-to-account payments via platforms like Zepto and NPP (New Payments Platform) are rapidly replacing legacy direct debit (BECS), with 2030 set as the official sunset date for BECS—prompting accelerated adoption in Sydney corporate financial operations[1][2].\n\n**Scope hierarchy followed: Local (Sydney/NSW), backed by national and APAC regional triggers, global signals only where local data sparse. All items dated within 6-12 months as per instruction.**"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zepto is a rapidly-scaling provider of real-time, account-to-account payments solutions for merchants, and is reimagining the way money moves through the always-on, digital-first economy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our growing team across Australia allows for like-minded, talented, passionate people motivated to help us deliver on our brand promise to #LevelThePayingField.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Zepto we believe in the power of positive human experiences, and that a deep sense of belonging creates cohesion in our culture. So, even in a remote-first team, you will be a contributor and custodian of that culture. You will also enjoy solving complex problems, and play a key role in creating something truly special as we focus on delivering ‘a better way to pay’ at Zepto.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Business Development Representative (BDR), you’ll not only be a results-driven individual, but have a passion for the Tech, FinTech and the Payments ecosystem. Your curious mind and enthusiasm to be on the front line of Zepto’s growth will be the cornerstone of your success. Reporting to our Senior Director of Sales, you will be responsible for identifying and qualifying new business opportunities, nurturing leads, and ultimately contributing to Zepto’s continued success.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This role will focus on a sustainable blend of lead generation and Salesforce''s savvyness, with the aim of accelerating Zepto’s footprint in the payments market.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Working in a scale-up, means you get the opportunity to flex your skills in a variety of ways. We are agile and always willing to roll up our sleeves to get things done. You can, however, expect your day to day to be involved in the following:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate new leads by proactively researching and identifying new merchants within a variety of industry sectors and markets who would benefit from an enhancement in their payments infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial discovery calls and other multi-channel approaches to qualify leads, gather information about their business needs, pain points, and existing payment infrastructure, and determine a strategic fit for our offerings.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Account Executives, Marketing, and Product teams to align on target accounts, share market insights, and ensure a seamless handoff of qualified leads.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of all prospecting activities and customer interactions in our CRM (Salesforce), ensuring a healthy pipeline of qualified opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Clearly and concisely articulate the value proposition of Zepto’s payment solutions and technological capabilities in a consultative, solutions-focused manner, demonstrating how we can help prospects achieve their business goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assist with Zepto’s go-to-market efforts through planning, representation and participation at industry events, conferences, and networking opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This role will suit any candidate who has a flair for tech, payments and the fintech industry, specifically they will also have:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of experience in a BDR or similar outbound sales role, preferably within the SaaS, fintech, or payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills (written and verbal), with the ability to articulate complex concepts clearly and persuasively.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sound research and prospecting skills, with a knack for identifying decision-makers and understanding business structures&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilience and a positive attitude in the face of rejection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A natural curiosity for technology and a desire to understand how businesses operate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to be highly organised and self-motivated, managing multiple tasks and priorities effectively.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with CRM software, specifically Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree in Business, Marketing, or a related field (preferred but not required)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let’s not forget that you’re energised, enthusiastic and curious. You are comfortable with working in a busy, high volume, competitive commercial environment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s on Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Headquartered in beautiful Byron Bay, Zepto has an inspiring Founder story and is a customer-focused, culture-first organisation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re all striving to achieve our mission of enabling a &lt;em&gt;better way to pay&lt;/em&gt; for consumers and merchants and do so while fostering an inclusive culture where you will work with and learn from world-class talent in their areas of expertise.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role can be based anywhere in Australia as we work remotely &lt;/strong&gt;but you’ll feel connected through our various initiatives and be supported by great leadership to learn and grow. If your preference is to work hybrid or in an office, we have hub locations in Byron, Sydney and Melbourne.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We have a supportive learning environment, with access to an individual learning benefit to ensure your curiosity and learning is a priority. You will have access to an Employee Assistance Program, paid parental leave and be eligible for inclusion in our Employee Share Option Plan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;As an organisation in the financial services industry, please note that we conduct background checks as part of our recruitment process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQENp2MjBu-ZbQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1664246784530/zepto_payments_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=auBhWm2pKE93a5LINwpCZj4TvWIq1-GAMoS7jxhrnFw', '2025-09-28T03:56:22.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('rec96RqqJgjo1cvzv', 'RMS', 'https://www.rmscloud.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/rms-aust-pty-ltd', 'Melbourne, Victoria, AU', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '66', 'RMS is a growth-stage computer software company (212 employees) focused on hospitality technology, actively hiring for sales roles such as Sales Manager and VP of Sales, which are core priorities. The industry fit is strong (commercial B2B SaaS), and decision makers include a VP of Sales, VP of Sales & Marketing (Asia), and a Sales Manager, providing Tier 1 and Tier 2 access. While there are no recent funding or hiring surge signals, the company''s recent rebrand and product integrations indicate ongoing investment in growth and market positioning, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nRMS, a hospitality technology provider, unveiled a new brand identity on July 30, 2025, focusing on connection and seamless operations to enhance guest service and business growth. This rebrand highlights RMS''s role beyond software, emphasizing business growth and exceptional service.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified regarding hiring trends or team expansion in the last six to twelve months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or financial milestones were reported in the last six to twelve months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nRMS rebranded to emphasize its position as a platform that enhances business operations and guest experiences on July 30, 2025. Additionally, RMS announced a new integration with Goki in February 2024 to streamline hotel operations.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo prominent leadership changes were announced in the last six to twelve months. The leadership team, including CEO Adam Seskis, appears consistent."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Welcome to a new era of RMS.\nPowering the future of hospitality, one touchpoint at a time.\n\nSmarter tech, better stays. Hospitality, upgraded.\n\nFrom campgrounds and holiday parks to hotels and resorts, RMS is the all-in-one platform helping operators streamline operations, boost revenue, and deliver unforgettable guest experiences.\n\nBuilt to flex with your needs, today and as you grow.\n\nDiscover the thinking behind our new look, and see it in action.👉 https://hubs.li/Q03zhbnR0\n\nwww.rmscloud.com "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:21:57.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recAEVux0pAIkxOVy', 'JD.COM', 'http://corporate.jd.com/', 'https://cn.linkedin.com/company/jd.com', 'Beijing, , CN', 'Computer Software', '10001 -', '77', 'JD.com is a major computer software and e-commerce technology company with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore. The company is experiencing significant growth, with recent revenue increases, international expansion, and large-scale hiring initiatives targeting global tech talent. Multiple sales managers are present in key APAC markets, indicating established sales infrastructure and potential for external recruitment support, though no direct high-value sales leadership hiring is currently visible.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nJD.com announced robust second quarter results on August 14, 2025, with revenue up 22.4% year-on-year, driven by strong growth in core retail and new businesses like JD Food Delivery. The company also experienced market turbulence as Bridgewater, the worldâs largest hedge fund, exited its JD.com holdings in Q2 2025 amid broader China stock selloffs[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nJD Ecosystemâs personnel reached 900,000 by June 30, 2025, with plans to add 35,000 new roles through its 2026 campus recruitment, targeting global tech talent. The company is actively hiring full-time riders for its food delivery business and expanding its merchant base[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn August 2025, JD Retail achieved a historic 4.5% operating margin during Q2 promotional periods and continued thirteen consecutive quarters of year-on-year gross margin growth. The company also expanded its international logistics footprint with a new warehouse launch in the UAE on August 18, 2025[1][3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"JD.com, also known as JINGDONG, is a leading e-commerce company transferring to be a technology and service enterprise with supply chain at its core. JD.comâs business has expanded across retail, technology, logistics, health, property development, industrials, and international business. Ranking 44 on the Fortune Global 500, JD.com is Chinaâs largest retailer by revenue.\n\nJD.com serves over 600 million customers and has set the standard for e-commerce through its commitment to quality, authenticity, and competitive pricing. The company operates the largest fulfillment infrastructure of any e-commerce company in China, enabling 90% of retail orders to be delivered within the same or next day. JD.com also promotes productivity and innovation across a range of industries by offering its cutting-edge technology and infrastructure to partners, brands, and diverse sectors."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recAUJ1dNj7ox5tjx', 'Ordermentum', 'http://www.ordermentum.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/ordermentum-pty-ltd', 'Surry Hills, New South Wales, AU', 'Computer Software', '51 - 200', '67', 'Ordermentum is a well-established computer software company serving the B2B payments and ordering space, with 92 employees in Australia. The company has a strong sales leadership team and mature sales infrastructure, including multiple senior sales managers and a Head of Customer Success. While there are no recent hiring surges or funding rounds, the recent achievement of surpassing $2 billion in transactions and the consolidation of analytics workflows indicate ongoing growth and investment in technology. The presence of accessible decision makers in sales and customer success further supports a strong opportunity for recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOrdermentum surpassed $2 billion in total transactions in early 2025, marking a significant milestone for its platform in the Australian hospitality industry. In July 2025, the company consolidated its analytics and BI workflows into a unified platform using Omni to improve internal data strategy and accelerate insights for customers[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo specific hiring or team expansion activity identified in the last 6-12 months. Headcount or sales/go-to-market role expansions not evident from recent sources.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nReached the $2 billion transaction milestone in early 2025. In July 2025, modernized its BI stack to enable self-service analytics and reduce operational friction for users and internal teams[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures identified within the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Ordermentum is an ordering, payments, and insights platform for the food and beverage industry. By replacing traditional pen and paper processes with powerful mobile tools, Ordermentum connects the 45,000 Australian venues including bars, and restaurants across Australia with suppliers, helping to increase business efficiencies, grow sales and improve profitability.\n\nFounded in 2014 and headquartered in Sydney, Ordermentum is now Australia''s leading ordering and payments platform connecting premium suppliers with hospitality venues. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recAXDQ4sa8LVOPVt', 'Stripe', 'https://stripe.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/stripe', 'South San Francisco, California', 'Software Development,Financial Services,Technology, Information and Internet', '5,001-10,000 employees', '55', 'Stripe is a global B2B technology leader in payments and SaaS, with significant operations in Australia and Singapore. The recent posting for a Sales Development Representative (SDR) in Sydney is a primary target role, but the company size (5,001-10,000 employees) means a sophisticated internal TA function likely limits external recruitment needs. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present locally and regionally, supporting access. Strong local growth signals—such as product launches, user growth, and market expansion—are evident, but the absence of recent local funding and the enterprise scale temper immediate opportunity. This is a realistic but not high-probability recruitment opportunity for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Stripe announced at the Stripe Tour Sydney 2025 that it will launch **Stripe Capital** in Australia, a service providing fast, flexible financing to eligible small and medium-sized businesses via the Stripe platform; this move addresses the growing challenge SMBs face in securing funding and is scheduled to roll out in the coming months[1].  \n[LOCAL] The Stripe Tour Sydney 2025 (held 11 September 2025), an industry event at the International Convention Centre, showcased Stripe products leveraging AI, stablecoins, and payment technologies to over one million users in Australia and New Zealand, demonstrating Stripe''s growing local influence[1][3][5].  \n[LOCAL] Stripe has seen steady local growth and now supports over one million users—including global and local businesses—across Australia and New Zealand, with tens of thousands more joining each month[1].  \n[LOCAL] Stripe has recently introduced features such as \"PayTo\" and \"Instant Payouts\" targeted at Australian businesses to improve local payments efficiency[6].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Stripe posted a hybrid Sales Development Representative role at its Sydney office (1 Sussex Street, Barangaroo, NSW 2000) in the last six months, reflecting continued investment in local sales and go-to-market capacity[2].  \n[LOCAL] Stripe Australia operates from the Barangaroo business district, supporting a modern, collaborative workspace typical for technology sales and operations teams[2][4].  \n[REGIONAL] Stripe is establishing itself as a payments infrastructure and business technology leader in Australia and New Zealand, acting as a reseller contracting directly with local merchants and platforms and offering expanding local solutions[4][6].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No significant new funding rounds targeting Australia were reported in the last 12 months. Historically, Stripe remains one of the world’s most highly valued private technology companies, but recent Australia-specific capital events are limited in the public domain.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Stripe was featured prominently at the Stripe Tour Sydney 2025, highlighting thought leadership, future trends in payments, and new applications of AI for the Australian enterprise ecosystem[1][3][5].  \n[LOCAL] With over one million users in Australia and New Zealand, Stripe has solidified itself as a critical infrastructure provider for local fintechs and e-commerce platforms, such as me&u, which also leverages Stripe Capital to extend financing to its customers[1].  \n[REGIONAL] The company showcased new AI-enabled product updates and stablecoin integrations for the APAC region during recent events[1][3].  \n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Karl Durrance continues as Managing Director for Australia and New Zealand, and publicly represented Stripe during recent Australian product launches and industry commentary[1].  \n[GLOBAL] No recent executive or board changes in APAC-Sydney reported in the last 6-12 months for sales, revenue, or people roles[1].  \n\n*Note: The intelligence above is sourced and prioritized per the requested local-to-global search hierarchy, with a focus on developments in Sydney, NSW, then regionally in Australia/NZ and APAC.*"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Who we are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Sales Development Representative (SDR) at Stripe, you will drive Stripe’s future growth engine by working with Demand Gen and the Account Executive team to qualify leads and collaboratively build Stripe’s sales pipeline. You get excited about engaging with prospects to better qualify needs. You are adept at identifying high value opportunities and capable of managing early sales funnel activities.You are used to delivering value in complex situations and are energized by learning about new and existing products. Finally, you enjoy building – you like to actively participate in the development of the demand generation and sales process, the articulation of Stripe’s value proposition, and the creation of key tools and assets. If you’re hungry, smart, persistent, and a great teammate, we want to hear from you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For the first months, you’ll be part of the SD Associate program which is designed to accelerate your onboarding and ramp to full productivity as an SDR. This intensive program is built to help you quickly build and develop skills required to be successful in this role. Upon completion, you’ll continue learning and growing in your career as part of Stripe’s Sales Development Academy. These programs are endorsed and supported by sales leaders as an important part of investing in our people.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We take a data driven, analytical approach to sales development, and are looking for someone who is confident in both prospecting to customers and in helping design our strategy. If you’re hungry, smart, persistent, and a great teammate, we want to hear from you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What you’ll do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Research and create outreach materials for high value prospects, in partnership with SDRs and AEs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Follow up with Marketing generated leads to qualify as sales opportunities. Move solid leads through the funnel connecting them to a salesperson, and arranging meetings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute outbound sales plays created by marketing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Initiate contact with potential customers through cold-calling or responding to inquiries generated from Marketing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop relationships with prospects to uncover needs through effective questioning to qualify interest and viability to prepare hand-off to sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Follow-up with potential customers who expressed interest but did not initially result in a sales opportunity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively work through lead list meeting/exceeding SLAs, consistently update activity and contact information within the CRM system and support weekly reporting efforts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and provide feedback and insights to Marketing to help improve targeting and messaging&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Who you are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of top performance or prior success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Superior verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self starter who is able to operate in a hyper growth environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This role requires in-office participation three (3) days per week in our Sydney office&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Position Details&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;* Job Type: Full time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Location: 1 Sussex Street, Barangaroo, Sydney NSW 2000, Australia&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open date: Application open August 22 - September 19, 2024&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;In-office expectations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Office-assigned Stripes in most of our locations are currently expected to spend at least 50% of the time in a given month in their local office or with users. This expectation may vary depending on role, team and location. For example, Stripes in our Bucharest, Romania site have an 80% in-office expectation, and those in Stripe Delivery Center roles in Mexico City, Mexico and Bengaluru, India work 100% from the office. Also, some teams have greater in-office attendance requirements, to appropriately support our users and workflows, which the hiring manager will discuss. This approach helps strike a balance between bringing people together for in-person collaboration and learning from each other, while supporting flexibility when possible.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pay and benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The annual salary range for this role in the primary location is A$96,000 - A$144,000. This range may change if you are hired in another location. For sales roles, the range provided is the role’s On Target Earnings (“OTE”) range, meaning that the range includes both the sales commissions/sales bonuses target and annual base salary for the role. This salary range may be inclusive of several career levels at Stripe and will be narrowed during the interview process based on a number of factors, including the candidate’s experience, qualifications, and specific location. Applicants interested in this role and who are not located in the primary location may request the annual salary range for their location during the interview process.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Specific benefits and details about what compensation is included in the salary range listed above will vary depending on the applicant’s location and can be discussed in more detail during the interview process. Benefits/additional compensation for this role may include: equity, company bonus or sales commissions/bonuses; retirement plans; health benefits; and wellness stipends."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQE2ZfJyfn-VCg/company-logo_200_200/B56ZlyKwpUKIAI-/0/1758557047806/stripe_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=En4Hm6NDGbDTYCoOQ0Ko5Ne2gylx0WRb0yL2GlOeXBQ', '2025-09-28T04:00:36.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recAnjOZKcJLJ20cE', 'Sage', 'http://www.sage.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/sage-software', 'Newcastle upon Tyne, , GB', 'Computer Software', '10001 -', '77', 'Sage is a major computer software provider with strong operations in Australia and Singapore, aligning perfectly with our core industry focus. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including a General Manager, Regional Sales Director, and Sales Director ANZ, providing excellent access to key stakeholders. While there are no recent funding or explicit sales hiring signals, Sage''s recent AI-driven product launches and strategic partnerships indicate ongoing innovation and potential for future sales team expansion. High potential for recruitment partnership, especially for senior sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSage unveiled a new brand mission focused on high-performance finance software and announced several strategic initiatives, including industry-first partnerships, at the Sage Future 2025 event in Atlanta in early June 2025. The company also introduced an AI-first product strategy and new alliances with CPA.com, the LPGA, and GrowCFO during this event.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified regarding notable hiring patterns or team expansion in sales, GTM, or overall headcount from publicly available sources within the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified in the past 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nSage Intacct 2025 Release 2 was launched in June 2025, featuring enhancements in financial reporting, AI-driven automation, Accounts Payable and Receivable, and cash management. Sage also announced major AI-powered product advancements and partnerships at Sage Future 2025 in June 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes, executive hires, or departures reported in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Sage, we knock down barriers with information, insights, and tools to help your business flow.\n \nWe provide businesses with software and services that are simple and easy to use, as we work with you to give you that feeling of confidence. Customers trust our Payroll, HR, and Finance software to make business flow with ease. From our local network of experts to our ever-growing partnerships, we are on hand to give you all the insights you need to thrive. ð"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recAsLlhHjE5MoOps', 'Relevance AI', 'https://relevanceai.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/relevanceai', 'Surry Hills, New South Wales', 'Software Development', '51-200 employees', '64', 'Relevance AI is a growth-stage B2B software company (51-200 employees) in Sydney, actively expanding with strong Series B funding and rapid product innovation in AI agent technology. The most relevant sales-related role is Revenue Operations, a support/operations function (5 points), with no direct evidence of active hiring for core sales roles (SDR/BDR/AE) in Australia. The company fits the core commercial tech profile (25 points), and Wei Li Lim (Revenue Operations) provides Tier 3 decision maker access (6 points). Multiple strong growth signals are present (10 points), but the lack of active core sales hiring and only support-level decision maker access limits immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Relevance AI launched two major features—**Workforce**, a multi-agent builder, and **Invent**, a text-to-agent generator—in Sydney in January 2025, directly supporting specialized AI agent creation for Australian businesses[1]. [LOCAL] Rapid growth was reported, with 40,000 agents created on the Sydney-built platform in January 2025 alone, serving customers from startups to Fortune 500 enterprises[1]. [LOCAL] Product development remains centered in Sydney, while sales and marketing are primarily based in San Francisco[1]. [GLOBAL] The latest Series B funding round (US$24M/A$37M, May 2025) is geared toward scaling the company’s mission of making Relevance AI “the definitive home of the AI workforce” with continued deployment in Australia and internationally[1][2]. \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Relevance AI employs over **80 staff**, with the Sydney office focused on engineering, product, and agent development[1]. [LOCAL] Multiple technical openings have recently been posted in Sydney for AI agent engineers, platform developers, and workflow integration specialists, indicating active expansion of the Sydney R&D hub[5]. [GLOBAL] Significant headcount and platform growth; company targets transforming business process automation in both the AU and US markets[1][5]. [LOCAL] Direct mentions of business development representative (BDR) AI agent rollout for sales workflow automation in Sydney in early 2024[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL] The Series B round (A$37M) was announced in **January 2025**, led by Bessemer Venture Partners with King River Capital, Insight Partners, and Peak XV also participating—emphasizing Sydney as the key engineering hub[1]. [GLOBAL] Total raised to date is US$37M, with financing explicitly used to accelerate agent platform development and AU/global market reach[1][2]. \n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Successful launch of BDR agent, automating lead sourcing and sales qualification for Australian and global customers, reached full production at the Sydney office in 2024[3]. [LOCAL] User growth and platform expansion were reported at Sydney HQ: hundreds of companies now run production workloads on Relevance AI agents made in Sydney[3]. [GLOBAL] The product’s agent-building and debugging features, scaling integrations, and advanced workflow controls have received industry recognition for bringing human-quality AI work to previously non-automatable tasks[3]. [LOCAL] Strong emphasis on local product innovation (agent contracts, batch scheduling, approvals/escalation) developed and supported out of Sydney[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Co-founders Daniel Vassilev and Jacky Koh remain jointly at the helm, overseeing Sydney operations and leading product vision[1]. [LOCAL] Scott Henderson identified as Head of Marketing, with direct responsibilities for Sydney product positioning as of 2025[1]. [GLOBAL] No recent executive appointments or departures for sales/revenue roles specific to Sydney disclosed in the last six months. \n\n---\n\n**Scope notes:** Information above is [LOCAL] to Sydney/Australia except where [GLOBAL] is indicated for broader developments with direct relevance to AU operations.\n\nIf further specifics on hiring for sales/GTM or local executive activity are needed, recent published job postings and company news indicate strong technical (engineering, agent development) expansion, with some BDR agent automation focused on enhancing sales workflow at Sydney HQ[3][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Location 📍: &lt;/strong&gt;Sydney, NSW (Hybrid - 3 Days In Office)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us 🚀&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Relevance AI, we’re building the future of work. Our mission is to enable the next doubling in human prosperity by delegating as much work as possible to an AI Workforce – a team of AI agents working together in a multi-agent system.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are building an entirely new category and scaling rapidly to meet unprecedented customer demand. We need exceptional talent to help us grow. If you’re ready to be part of a trailblazing company that’s at the cutting edge of AI, this is the place for you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role 🥳&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re hiring an Enterprise Account Executive in Sydney to sell our agent platform to large, complex organizations. You''ll work closely with multiple stakeholders - often across sales, operations, marketing, IT, and more, to help customers transform their companies to scale output exponentially using the AI Workforce.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a high-impact, full-cycle sales role for someone who thrives in fast-paced environments, understands technical products, and has experience leading sophisticated, multi-threaded enterprise deals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact💥&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own and drive full-cycle enterprise sales ($100k+ ACV) across APAC &amp;amp; beyond, focusing on 1,000+ FTE organizations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and influence multiple decision-makers, from functional users to C-level.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Run world-class discovery, map complex stakeholder relationships, and deliver compelling demos that tie business value to automation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and manage a 3x+ pipeline, forecasting accurately in HubSpot.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Educate buyers in an emerging category, AI agents, by simplifying technical concepts and driving urgency.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with product and solutions engineering to unlock custom use cases and close strategic deals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt; 🧠&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Overall 8+ years, 3 years in enterprise in B2B SaaS enterprise sales with average deal sizes of $50k–$300k+.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of managing long, complex sales cycles across multiple functions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with technical or automation-first products, especially AI, GPT-based tools, or integration platforms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfort operating in high-velocity startup environments while maintaining enterprise rigor.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deep curiosity and communication skills to simplify complex ideas into clear, ROI-driven outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling platform products across various personas or departments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus:&lt;/li&gt;Previous success in early-stage or hyper-growth companies (e.g. &lt;li&gt;Familiarity with emerging technologies and products that change buyer behavior or workflows.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us? 🌟&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work at the forefront of AI with a nimble team that is constantly pushing boundaries. We encourage and celebrate ideas that drive our mission forward.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We''re guided by our five values: truth-seeking, be empathetic, put the customer first, have two gears, and build memories.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We’ve set high standards in our high-trust environment—we hire exceptional people to do great work. In return, we reward our people with competitive salaries, unparalleled professional growth and career-defining opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relevance AI is well-funded by leading investors, including Insights Partners, Bessemer Venture Partners, Peak XV, King River Capital.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;As an early team member, you’ll play a key role in shaping our future—including our culture, ways of working, and even the benefits we offer. We’re laying the foundations now, and your ideas can help define what comes next.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;🌴 4 Weeks Annual Leave – Take time to recharge with 20 days of paid vacation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📈 ESOP – Employee Stock Ownership Plan so you can grow with the company&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🤖 AI Productivity Benefit – Get up to $1200 USD/year to spend on AI tools, courses, and learning resources that help you work smarter and grow your skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;👶 Parental Leave – We offer 12 weeks of paid parental leave for all eligible new parents, and an additional 6 weeks for the birthing parent&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎉 Milestone Merch – Celebrate your work anniversaries with customised Relevance AI swag&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍱 Team Meals – Enjoy free Friday lunches, Uber Eats dinners, and regular catered office lunches&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🪩 Quarterly Team Events – Build stronger connections through fun, meaningful team bonding experiences every quarter&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🏓 Social Clubs – Share your hobbies and interests by joining or starting a club with your teammates. A few clubs we already have are hiking, chess, and board game nights. We also have a social committee you can join—new ideas are always welcome!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍿 Snacks &amp;amp; Drinks Galore – Stay energised with a wide selection of snacks and a fully stocked fridge of drinks in the office&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🌐 Community Events – As the home of the AI workforce, we regularly host events featuring thought leaders, industry partners, and the wider community—right at our office, so you can join straight after work&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🧠 Sonder EAP – Access 24/7 mental health and wellbeing support through Sonder, our Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHYhwAvHL8aRg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1718350495354/relevanceai_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=mBU2YvFi8S7POiZVHldmII7M8-CFx7hmRnOMZWLEjM0', '2025-09-20T14:23:55.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recBMj7zYbEk1GWLj', 'Bigtincan', 'http://www.bigtincan.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bigtincan', 'Waltham, Massachusetts', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '97', 'Bigtincan is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (201-500 employees) with a Sydney HQ driving APAC strategy, product innovation, and go-to-market expansion. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (VP Sales APAC, Sales Director APAC, VP Business Development APAC) provides strong access for immediate recruitment. Current hiring for Enterprise Account Executive and Senior Account Manager roles aligns with high-priority sales positions. Multiple strong growth signals are present: recent capital raising, leadership appointments, and explicit plans to expand GTM teams for new AI product launches. This combination of role priority, industry fit, company size, decision maker access, and growth signals makes Bigtincan a VERY HIGH priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Bigtincan''s Sydney headquarters remains a central hub for global strategy, product development, and innovation, leveraging local tech talent and serving as a gateway to APAC markets as of April 2025[1].  \n[LOCAL] On June 11, 2024, Bigtincan launched a capital raising initiative specifically driven out of its Sydney base, involving both institutional and retail entitlement offers to strengthen product and go-to-market activities in Australia[2].  \n[LOCAL] As of September 2024, Bigtincan received a revised non-binding proposal from Vector Capital for a potential take-private transaction at A$0.20 per share, after active engagement with Sydney-based leadership and shareholders[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office hosts core research and development, strategic planning, and is described as fostering a collaborative, customer-centric environment, designed for ongoing team expansion and innovation[1].  \n[LOCAL] Recent capital raising efforts are earmarked for expanding the go-to-market team around next-generation AI products, GenieAI and platform integrations, emphasizing growth in sales and GTM functions based out of Sydney[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Bigtincan supports over 2 million user accounts and has included high-profile customers like Nike, Red Bull, and T-Mobile, highlighting sustained global and regional sales momentum[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL] In June 2024, Bigtincan initiated a significant capital raise via entitlement offers, supporting both institutional and retail investors in Australia, particularly Sydney[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Vector Capital has made indicative and subsequently revised non-binding proposals for a take-private transaction, secured by confirmed financing and committee approvals as of September 2024[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sydney remains the base for core product innovation and global launches; the GenieAI product integration is a current strategic priority for FY25, with emphasis on local engineering and go-to-market execution[2][1].  \n[GLOBAL] Company maintains technology leadership in sales enablement automation and AI, serving major multinational clients and continuously expanding regional relevance[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Vivian Stewart was appointed Chief Financial Officer in August 2023, based in Sydney, marking a strategic change following the departure of previous CFO Cyril Desanjutkan[1].  \n[LOCAL] The Board was strengthened with the appointment of Tim Ebbeck in June 2024, an enterprise software veteran with roles at SAP and Oracle, to bring greater APAC enterprise expertise[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Executive changes and board appointments are tied to supporting ongoing Australian and APAC growth, financial strategy, and preparations for possible ownership transitions[1][2][3].\n\nIf further detail on Sydney-specific hiring or GTM roles is needed, current events and capital raise signals suggest ongoing recruitment, especially supporting GenieAI expansion. Recent proposals and funding are directly relevant to Australian and APAC operations, while global achievements reflect strong positive spillover into the region."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"About Bigtincan (ASX:BTH)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bigtincan (ASX:BTH), is the leader in SAAS and mobile, AI-powered sales enablement automation and provides software products and services that enables salespeople in leading companies around the world to be more productive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bigtincan’s customers are a who’s who of the world’s top fortune 100 companies and this is truly a unique opportunity for the right Sales Development Representative to join a small but high performance team focusing on APAC.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Working closely with, marketing, Sales and Customer success reporting directly to the Sales Director for APAC, you will be responsible for generating qualified opportunities through cold outreach to target accounts and marketing Marketing Qualified Leads.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively and efficiently follow up on marketing leads from various campaigns (webinars,events, downloads, etc.) and generate interest&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cold outreach to target accounts using multiple channels (phone, email, social media)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work the booth during industry events to drive awareness and pipeline generation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Research target accounts to understand need, enable effective follow up, and generate sales ready meetings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Finding the right decision makers and/or influencers within accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Establishing customer relationships with the \"decision making unit\", such as C-levels, and other influencers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Performing adequate research &amp;amp; discovery to determine if an account is a Bigtincan fit&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Setting discovery calls with prospects to dive deeper into the customer need and Bigtincan value.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hosting Discovery Calls to progress prospect through start of sales process&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partnering with Account Executives to drive pipeline growth in target accounts and performing hand-offs to the Account Executives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;The Perks&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work From Home 3 days per week - office - Tues/Thurs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Location - Central location to CBD&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;About The Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As part of the Bigtincan team you will be trusted and supported to achieve your career aspirations as we enable you to grow into your very best self.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will work amongst a motivated group of people in collaboration with each other, who work together to find a way to deliver better opportunities and results for our customers. We believe in flexibility and we care about our team mates and hold ourselves accountable to maintaining an ambitious, warm and diverse culture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bigtincan is an equal opportunity employer and we value diversity in all forms. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.If you feel you have got what it takes to be a part of the Bigtincan team please send your resume and hit the apply button now"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFTex1W_T9xQg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1733164677344/bigtincan_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=KzN93EJ5CPhSt6ibTNhzu_6lPs1D46AtODC4gVcroUE', '2025-09-28T04:06:28.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recBVfZfnkbrVEmWG', 'TikTok', 'https://www.tiktok.com/about?lang=en', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/tiktok', 'Los Angeles, California, US', 'Entertainment', '10001 -', '69', 'TikTok demonstrates significant hiring potential in Australia and Singapore with a large sales and partnerships team, including roles such as Strategic Sales Manager, Sales Manager, and multiple Industry Leads. The presence of senior decision makers like Country General Manager and Director of Global Business Development in APAC further strengthens opportunity signals. While the core industry is entertainment, TikTok''s expansion into e-commerce and digital technology, coupled with aggressive growth and recent product launches, indicates strong demand for technology, sales, and digital talent.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nTikTok launched TikTok Shop in early 2024, allowing users to buy products directly within the app, entering the social commerce space. ByteDance, TikTokâs parent, acquired the AI music startup Jukedeck in late 2023 to expand music creation capabilities and broaden creative options on the platform. The company has also faced ongoing regulatory pressure in the US, including demands for divestiture, while increasing its lobbying spend to $980,000 in 2023 and $1.99 million in political contributions in 2024[1][3][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nByteDance is targeting $186 billion in revenue for 2025, which is a planned 20% increase from 2024, signaling aggressive growth expectations for TikTok and related platforms. Headcount data is not specifically detailed, but major recent fundraising and expansion of creator and shop features point to continued scaling of sales, go-to-market, and operational teams[3][1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nByteDance raised $5 billion in 2023 to expand TikTokâs global operations and invest in new features and technologies. The TikTok Creator Fund was also expanded to $2 billion in 2023, supporting creator monetization initiatives[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nTikTok Shop launched in early 2024, marking a major new product offering in social commerce. Expanded LIVE Subscriptions in 2023 enabled creators to monetize through exclusive live content, broadening revenue streams for both creators and TikTok itself[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"TikTok is the world''s leading destination for short-form video. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. \n \nOur employees lead with curiosity, and move at the speed of culture. Combined with our company''s flat structure, you''ll be given dynamic opportunities to make a real impact on a rapidly expanding company as you grow your career. We have offices across Asia Pacific, the Middle East, Europe, and the Americas â and we''re just getting started."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recC54ZtxrzpUqgTC', 'Civica', 'http://www.civica.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/civica', 'London, London, GB', 'Information Technology & Services', '5001 - 10000', '64', 'Civica is a growth-stage information technology and services company (3,060 employees) with significant APAC presence and recent expansion signals, including a new APAC Managing Director and an acquisition. The most relevant sales roles identified are Business Development Manager and Account Manager, which are medium-priority (25 points). The industry fit is acceptable (15 points) as Civica''s core focus includes GovTech and public sector software, which is an edge case per criteria. Decision makers include Sales Managers and Directors (Tier 2, 10 points), with additional moderate growth signals from leadership changes and acquisitions (6 points). While Civica is expanding and has quality decision makers, the GovTech/public sector focus and absence of primary/core sales roles lower the overall recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCivica appointed Christopher Smith as Executive Vice President and Managing Director for APAC in January 2025, signalling a push for regional expansion from Sydney[1][3]. In November 2024, Civica acquired Loop Software Pty Ltd and its flagship product Daymap to strengthen its school management solutions in Australia[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nCivica has been tasked with expanding its business operations and growing its presence across the APAC region, with bases in major Australian cities[1]. The acquisition of Daymap points to a strategy of broadening its education technology footprint and client base in Australia[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCivica enhanced its education offerings by acquiring Daymap in November 2024, aiming to deliver more innovative solutions and improve user experience for schools[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nChristopher Smith was appointed as APAC Managing Director and Executive Vice President in January 2025, reporting directly to CEO Lee Perkins[1][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We’re Civica and we make software that helps deliver critical services for citizens all around the world. From local government to central [federal] government, to education, to health and care, over 5,000 public bodies across the globe use our software to help provide critical services to over 100 million citizens.\n\nOur aspiration is to be a GovTech champion everywhere we work around the globe, supporting the needs of citizens and those that serve them every day. Building on 21 years of continuous growth and success, we''re at a pivotal point on our journey to realise that aspiration.\n\n As a company, we’re passionate about what we do and the citizens we help to serve. If you too would like to help champion the use of technology in public services, to improve outcomes for citizens and public sector organisations, then Civica is the right place for you. We will help you unlock the best version of yourself, achieve growth in your career whilst making a real difference to people and communities.\n\nWe have a network of global facilities. Our main hub sites include:\n- United Kingdom\n- Australia & New Zealand\n- Asia\n- United States\n- Canada"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQFRBPN-8NrmRQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1719921416264/civica_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=nILz0xDJb2hG_MjSkWse8NmNsfWH-_rfTj-u1s435Jw', '2025-09-18T21:01:21.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recC9SpnM6WkNpQkP', 'Mimecast', 'https://www.mimecast.com/', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/mimecast', 'London, England', 'IT Services and IT Consulting,Software Development,Computer and Network Security', '1,001-5,000 employees', '80', 'Mimecast is a growth-stage cybersecurity and IT services company (1,001-5,000 employees) with active operations in Australia and Singapore. The inclusion is triggered by a Business Development Representative (BDR) role, a primary target for 4Twenty. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, specifically cybersecurity, and has strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (VP/GM APJ, Regional Sales Directors, Senior Sales Director ANZ, BDR Leader APJ) present in the region. Growth signals include ongoing regional sales integration, product innovation, and internal engagement events, though no recent local funding or major AU leadership changes are noted. This represents a high-priority recruitment opportunity due to role fit, industry, size, and decision-maker access, with strong but not maximum growth signals.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Mimecast maintains a **Sydney office at Level 8, 88 Phillips Street, Sydney NSW 2000**, with an active presence also in Melbourne[1]. The Sydney and Melbourne locations jointly serve as bases for regional sales, marketing, engineering, IT, and customer services teams[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Teams in Sydney and Melbourne work closely with Mimecast’s Singapore office and other Asia-Pacific locations as part of the broader APAC operations network[2].  \n[REGIONAL] In August 2025, Mimecast launched the President’s Winter Experience event for elite partners in Queenstown, New Zealand, highlighting continued engagement and recognition programs in the ANZ region[5].  \n[GLOBAL] Mimecast is focusing on AI-powered threat intelligence and human risk management, as reflected in global events such as the Elevate25 conference (October 2025)[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Mimecast’s Sydney office is home to **regional Sales, Marketing, Engineering, IT, and Customer Service** functions, supporting local recruitment and presence for these teams[2].  \n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] There has been ongoing collaboration between Australian and wider APAC teams, suggesting consistent operational integration and likely cross-border sales and GTM activities[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Mimecast continues to host regional team-building events, such as the Call-Out Day, fostering culture and internal engagement in Sydney and Melbourne[2].  \n[GLOBAL] The company employs over 2,200 staff globally and has been increasing its focus on cyber resilience and expansion of offerings[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds or financial milestones specific to Australia or APAC were discovered from the last 6-12 months—recent updates center on product innovation and market engagement[4].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Mimecast was active in running regional engagement programs, including incentive-based events for partners and staff throughout ANZ, such as the President’s Winter Experience[5].  \n[GLOBAL] Recent product innovations include enhancements to **AI-powered data governance, compliance, and human risk management solutions**; these offerings are relevant to regulated sectors in Australia[6].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] In January 2024, **Marc van Zadelhoff** was appointed CEO, bringing extensive industry experience (formerly CEO of Devo Technology, GM/CEO IBM Security)[4].  \n[REGIONAL/LOCAL] No specific Sydney/AU-based executive appointments, departures, or senior GTM leader changes are referenced in the last 6-12 months; current leadership actions appear to align with global strategic directions[4].\n\nIf more detailed local hiring, new AU/APAC partnerships, or awards were announced since early 2025, these have not appeared in available public sources as of the search window."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Mimecast, we''re redefining cybersecurity and leading the charge in human risk management. We protect businesses from evolving threats, and you''ll be at the forefront. Every customer you bring on board builds something bigger - for them, for us, for our communities, and for your career. Simply put - when we grow, you grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We set you up to win. Top-tier enablement, smart coaching, and real insights mean you''ll smash quotas, not just hit them. You get the tools and knowledge to sell with confidence, turning complex sales cycles into closed deals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Your career path? It''s yours to shape. Compelling commission, clear progression, and chances to lead, specialize, or pivot - you decide what''s next. Here, success isn''t just about the deals you close. It''s about your progress, your influence, your impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ready to push boundaries and accelerate your career? Let''s make it happen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve and exceed new business and existing accounts KPI’s, Pipeline, &amp;amp; Revenue targets on a monthly, quarterly &amp;amp; annual basis.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with existing and prospective Enterprise clients across New South Wales to drive positive customer experiences whilst achieving sales targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and proactively execute against a strategic territory plan in order to achieve targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive cross functional team engagement to ensure both existing clients and prospective client account plans are executed to perfection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead executive level relationships with customer executives, and attend and present at quarterly business reviews.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Channel Partners to drive revenue and support their partnership requirements.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a proactive hunter mentality focused on driving great engagements for customers, prospects, and partners in order drive pipeline and revenue for Mimecast.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with new business prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Business Administration – Manage reporting of the KPI’s and general CRM housekeeping.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute against a structured end to end sales methodology and process.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise and attend meetings with other company functions necessary to perform duties and aid business and organisational development.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on activities and provide relevant management information and insights.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Need&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5-7+ years IT or SaaS sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven achievement against sales KPIs, pipeline, and revenue targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience of both Direct &amp;amp; In-Direct sales roles desirable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in value based solution selling. Experience in using of MEDDPICC/ Command of the Message/ Challenger Sale is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be a proactive, data driven, results-oriented person with a positive outlook that has the ability and desire to run the territory as their own business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with a high performance and dynamic environment &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Degree Level education (preferred but not required)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;The OTE salary range for this position is $290,000K - $430,000K base + benefits. This reflects the minimum and maximum target for new hire salaries for this position. This position may also be eligible for incentive plans and other related benefits. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location. These factors and individual capabilities will also determine the individual pay offered.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEI Statement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Cybersecurity is a community effort. That’s why we’re committed to building an inclusive, diverse community that celebrates and welcomes everyone – unless they’re a cybercriminal, of course.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer, and we’d encourage you to join us whatever your background. We particularly welcome applicants from traditionally underrepresented groups.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We consider everyone equally: your race, age, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, ability, marital status, nationality, or any other protected characteristic won’t affect your application.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Due to certain obligations to our customers, an offer of employment will be subject to your successful completion of applicable background checks, conducted in accordance with local law.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQE_cSZ2hzDU6Q/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1652103777311/mimecast_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=jsNNoEIvH-YI_tejZ4tIgOxy2PoQCZYI9LRrcaMOEkQ', '2025-09-28T04:11:48.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recCUtMPg3mjyXPLp', 'Madison Group Enterprises', 'https://mge.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/madison-group-enterprises', 'Murarrie, QLD', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '51-200 employees', '66', 'Madison Group Enterprises is a growth-stage IT services and consulting company (51-200 employees) actively hiring for Business Development Manager and Sales Manager roles, both of which are medium to high-priority sales positions. The company operates in core B2B tech (IT services/consulting), making it a strong industry fit. Multiple Tier 1 (General Manager) and Tier 2 (Sales Manager, National Sales Manager, Regional Sales Manager) decision makers are present, providing direct access for recruitment engagement. While there are moderate growth signals (active recruitment, operational expansion, recent workplace awards), there are no recent major funding rounds or leadership changes. This combination of role, industry, size, and decision maker access makes Madison Group Enterprises a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Madison Group Enterprises maintains a **Sydney-area presence with an office and distribution centre at 149 Beaconsfield Street, Silverwater, NSW**, supporting its IT services and consulting activities in the state[5].  \n[REGIONAL] In recent years, Madison undertook a significant **corporate restructure**, consolidating specialist businesses under the Madison Group Enterprises parent brand to streamline operations across Australia and New Zealand[4]. Multiple teams now focus on specialist domains (Industrial IT, Audio Visual, IoT) based on regional customer needs. There have been no major publicly reported business developments, such as new office openings or market entries in Sydney or NSW in the past year based on available sources.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Madison Group Enterprises lists employment opportunities across its Sydney Silverwater location and other national offices, **signaling active recruitment and operational expansion** as recently as 2024[5].  \n[REGIONAL] The group is described as having **over 140 employees across Australia and New Zealand**, highlighting a moderate but stable growth profile[1]. The **company emphasizes a collaborative, people-centric workplace culture with hybrid work and employee recognition initiatives**[2].\n[LOCAL] No recent, large-scale hiring waves (such as dozens of new sales or GTM roles in Sydney) have been reported in the last six months in public sources.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] **No significant capital raises, investment rounds, or external financing events in the last 12 months have been publicly reported** for Madison Group Enterprises. The company appears to remain privately held and self-funded based on available data[1][6].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Madison received recognition as a **Great Place to Work Australia (2024)**, citing a positive, employee-focused culture and collaborative environment[2].  \n[REGIONAL] The company is noted for ongoing **representation of global brands (e.g., Moxa, MOBOTIX, Cybertec, Rajant, Smartmicro)** in Australia/NZ within industrial IT, communications, audio visual, and IoT domains[4].  \n[LOCAL] No major product launches, new partnerships, or high-profile client wins specific to the Sydney or NSW region have been documented in the last 6-12 months.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL/REGIONAL] David Redfern remains **Managing Director of Madison Group Enterprises**[4], and Paul Calabro serves as CEO of Madison Technologies, driving operational and innovation strategy group-wide. There are **no publicly reported executive hires or departures specific to Sydney, NSW**, or the wider Australian leadership team within the past year based on available sources.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The **IT services and consulting market in Australia continues to exhibit strong demand in 2024**, especially in industrial connectivity, IoT, enterprise networking, and audio-visual solutions. Sydney remains a national hub for tech and IT consulting activities.  \n[INDUSTRY] Talent retention, hybrid work adoption, and expansion of distribution for global technology brands are recurring themes among Australian IT distributors[2].\n\n**Summary of scope:**  \n- Most information available is national/ANZ with some site-specific details for Sydney.\n- No recent, high-impact Sydney-specific trigger events, funding, or leadership changes were found in public records for the past 6-12 months.  \n- The group’s Sydney distribution centre indicates ongoing operations and local client servicing.  \n- The company’s regional scale and collaborative, specialist structure position it as a key mid-size technology distributor and services provider in Australia/NZ."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;At MadisonAV, we’re not just in the AV business, we’re shaping the future of how Australia connects, communicates, and experiences sound and vision. We partner with world-leading brands to deliver solutions across stadiums, universities, government, and enterprise, projects that make an impact at scale.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re proud of the brands we represent, the partnerships we build, and the team we’ve created. Collaborative, passionate, and driven, we celebrate wins together and push each other to achieve big things.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a National Strategic Account Manager to own and grow relationships with our most important Tier 1 customers. This is a senior, consultative role where you’ll be at the table with executives, decision-makers, and industry leaders, building trust, influencing outcomes, and securing long-term partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This isn’t about chasing day-to-day sales. It’s about strategy. It’s about becoming the trusted partner who shapes how MadisonAV’s solutions are specified, adopted, and relied upon in the biggest and most exciting AV projects across Australia.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll be the connector, opening doors, creating pathways, and enabling our brilliant sales, technical, and product teams to shine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead the charge on MadisonAV’s most strategic Tier 1 accounts, developing long-term growth strategies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with C-level execs, senior stakeholders, consultants, and industry influencers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate big-picture agreements that lock in sustainable, profitable growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent MadisonAV at the highest levels, showcasing world-class AV solutions and influencing national project wins.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be the voice of the customer inside MadisonAV, bringing insights, advocacy, and direction to our leadership team.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate cross-functional brilliance, working with sales, technical, marketing, and product teams to deliver seamless, top-tier engagement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;8–10+ years’ senior experience in strategic account management or business development within AV or a related industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of building executive-level relationships that deliver real long-term value.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen with success in negotiating complex, high-value agreements.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Solid technical understanding of professional AV, with the ability to talk strategy with executives and detail with engineers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation, negotiation, and influencing skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CRM discipline and experience delivering clear account strategies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus points if you bring AVIXA CTS/CTS-D certifications and established senior relationships across Tier 1 integrators and consultants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Love It Here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with world-class AV brands on the most exciting projects in Australia.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be a strategic influencer, shaping MadisonAV’s relationships with top-tier customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with an awesome team that’s supportive, experienced, and passionate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enjoy a competitive salary, tools of trade, and genuine career growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to Lead?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you’re a strategic relationship builder who thrives in high-value environments and wants to make a lasting impact with world-class brands, we want to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Apply now with your CV and a cover letter telling us why you’re the perfect fit.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQHcR9XuaDgyTQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630636494026/madison_technologies_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=kOqvKhwinyHV2xmwSVTANUDkuvmZspP6a0SV91Yx6Ao', '2025-09-25T05:11:36.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recDDP0jZHiYHb4Fu', 'Hello Clever', 'https://helloclever.co', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/helloclever', 'Sydney, New South Wales', 'Financial Services', '51-200 employees', '83', 'Hello Clever is a growth-stage fintech company (51-200 employees) headquartered in Sydney, actively expanding across APAC with recent product launches and new regional offices, indicating strong growth momentum. The current hiring trigger is for a Head of Strategy & Business Development—a medium-priority sales leadership role in a core commercial B2B tech sector (fintech/payments). Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including a GM International Markets and Head of Operations, providing strong recruitment access. Multiple strong growth signals—regional expansion, product innovation, and leadership appointments—support a high likelihood of external recruitment need.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] On 24th September 2025, Hello Clever launched **Clever AI Data Analyst** in Sydney, adding a real-time intelligence layer to their payments and rewards ecosystem and targeting local merchants with operational decision support[2].  \n[REGIONAL] In September 2025, Hello Clever opened a **Japan office**, signaling a strategic Asia Pacific expansion; prior regional launches included Singapore (February 2025) and Vietnam (August 2025), as part of a multi-market APAC growth strategy[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Hello Clever initiated the process to obtain a **Major Payment Institution (MPI) license in Singapore** in early 2025, aimed at expanding cross-border payments services across APAC[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Hello Clever maintains its headquarters in **Sydney, NSW, Australia**, with ongoing product launches and visible executive statements indicating active sales and go-to-market functions in the region[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Rapid team expansion in 2025, opening physical offices in Singapore, Vietnam, and Japan, with a regional leadership team focused on APAC fintech operations[1][3].  \n[REGIONAL] Key leadership in regional expansion includes Raj Kasi, GM International Markets, overseeing fintech expansion and cross-border payments across APAC[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No public funding rounds for Hello Clever were announced in the last 12 months based on available sources. Recent developments appear to be funded through operational revenue and prior capital. If more specific funding details are required, further investigation into venture announcements or company press releases is recommended.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Launch of **Clever AI Data Analyst** in Sydney (September 2025), positioned as a unique real-time business intelligence solution for merchants, reflecting active product innovation at HQ[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Official launch of regional offices in Singapore, Vietnam, and Japan in 2025, supporting merchants in high-growth APAC markets[1][3].  \n[REGIONAL] Appointment of Kaido Chiwata (ex-Stripe, Moneytree) as Head of Japan & Global Expansion (September 2025), supporting merchant-first partnerships and integration with domestic payment infrastructure[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Kaido Chiwata appointed in September 2025 as Head of Japan & Global Expansion, bringing proven fintech experience and market entry expertise[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Expansion strategy led by multi-functional APAC team: Caroline Tran (CEO), Raj Kasi (GM International Markets), alongside heads for growth, partnerships, product, and operations[3].  \n[LOCAL] No reported executive departures or local leadership turnover in Sydney for the covered period.\n\n[INDUSTRY]  \nThe Australian financial services market continues to emphasize **real-time payments, embedded loyalty, and advanced AI-driven analytics**, with regulatory compliance (PCI DSS v4.0.1) and cross-border capability driving competition[1][2][3]. Local market trends also show merchants prioritizing data-driven decisioning and customer retention as differentiators in 2025."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Hello Clever&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Hello Clever isn’t your average fintech. We move fast, challenge, and make sure payments actually work for people. We’re proudly female-led, and we’re the first in Australia to combine real-time payments with Instant Cashback Rewards and intelligent insight. Our platform enables seamless, secure, and rewarding transactions, both in-store and online, driving business growth and enhancing customer experiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Technical Sales Executive at our payments company, you’ll bridge the gap between technology and client needs, helping merchants and partners unlock the full potential of our solutions. This hybrid role combines in-office collaboration with the flexibility to work remotely, giving you the best of both worlds. You’ll be partnering with our Account Executives during the sales cycle in order to deliver tailored solutions that drive customer success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with merchants, partners, and enterprise clients &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand client payment requirements and recommend tailored solutions &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deliver engaging product demos and presentations &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product, engineering, and compliance teams to ensure seamless solution delivery &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the sales team to drive end-to-end sales process and ensure success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Keep up to date with payment industry trends, compliance requirements, and competitor offerings &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2–3 years’ experience in technical sales, pre-sales, account management, or business development (ideally within payments, fintech, SaaS, or financial services) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of payment gateways, acquiring, card processing, and/or alternative payment methods (advantageous) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Able to translate complex technical capabilities into clear, commercial benefits &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, presentation, and negotiation skills &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive, driven, and target-oriented with a solutions-focused mindset &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Innovative Product: Be part of a company at the forefront of real-time payments and loyalty innovation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Growth Opportunity: Play a key role in shaping Hello Clever’s expansion in the Australian market. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive Compensation: Attractive salary package with uncapped commission potential. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Supportive Culture: Join a passionate, fast-paced team that values collaboration, innovation, and impact. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To Apply&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We like to keep things simple, but we also want to make sure this is the right fit for both of us. Here’s what to expect: &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Virtual Chat – A casual video call to get to know you, your experience, and what makes you tick. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet the Team – An in-person catch-up at our office to see if we vibe and chat about how you’d make this role your own. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Show Us Your Thinking – A short presentation where you’ll bring some ideas to life (nothing scary, we promise). &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If that sounds like your kind of process, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ready to Make Your Mark? APPLY NOW via careers@helloclever.co"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQGI5iAbkcTx1w/company-logo_200_200/B56ZXr_kruHoAI-/0/1743421066462/helloclever_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=tFlGKHJ1ifQfbOLrO9IXM5Qo39tUB4rptHZHb4jZWfQ', '2025-09-25T05:16:03.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recDsMWvBEgYyj1iT', 'Riskified', 'https://www.riskified.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/riskified', 'New York, NY', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '501-1,000 employees', '79', 'Riskified is a growth-stage SaaS company (501-1,000 employees) in the core commercial B2B tech sector, actively hiring for Business Development Manager roles in Australia and Singapore. The presence of a Country Manager (Tier 1) and Director of Business Development & Partnerships (Tier 2) provides strong decision maker access for recruitment. Recent growth signals include local leadership appointments, major APAC events, new product launches, and award wins, indicating robust hiring momentum. The Business Development Manager role is a medium-priority sales position, but the combination of industry fit, company size, and multiple growth indicators makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Riskified hosted its **Ascend Australia 2025** summit at the Hyatt Centric, Melbourne on May 15, 2025, bringing together Australian ecommerce and retail leaders to discuss fraud management strategies and best practices for market growth[3][1]. The event featured local merchant stories such as Cotton On’s digital transformation in fraud prevention, indicating ongoing, direct engagement with Australia''s online retail sector[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Riskified expanded its **Ascend fraud and risk intelligence summit** globally in 2025, with Melbourne among the six major cities selected, highlighting increased prioritization of APAC and Australian market activities[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Nicholas Kirtley serves as **Country Manager, Australia**, confirming local leadership and focused operations in the country[3]. Riskified referenced growing partnerships and expanded engagement with brands such as Cotton On (retail) and Meshki (fashion), both noting successful integrations and operational improvements using Riskified’s technology[3][4].  \n[REGIONAL] The company emphasizes APAC as a key growth territory, using regional summits and merchant case studies to drive awareness and adoption[1][3].  \n[GLOBAL] Recent product launches (Adaptive Checkout), AWS Retail Competency achievement, and key technology partnerships reinforce overall company momentum and scalability, which supports further local hiring, partnerships, and market penetration[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No public funding rounds or financial milestones specific to the Australian market or APAC region reported in the last 6-12 months; however, Riskified is NYSE-listed, providing ongoing access to capital for international expansion[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Case studies in Australia (Meshki, Cotton On) highlight measurable improvements—Meshki improved operational efficiency and fraud management workflows after implementing Riskified’s solutions[4].  \n[REGIONAL] Riskified won the “Most Innovative Fraud Prevention Solution” at the MPE Awards 2025, confirming product leadership in the fraud prevention sector and likely boosting reputation in APAC[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Strategic partnerships announced with IXOPAY (enterprise payment orchestration) and Appriss Retail (omnichannel returns fraud prevention), advancing capabilities relevant to local merchants operating both in Australia and globally[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Nicholas Kirtley named as Country Manager, Australia, in 2025, driving regional sales, GTM activities, and local ecosystem engagement[3].  \n[GLOBAL] No APAC/ANZ-specific executive changes noted for sales or revenue roles; recent leadership moves have focused on product and partnership strategy at the global level[2].\n\n[INDUSTRY] Australian ecommerce continues to grapple with sophisticated fraud, balancing customer experience with risk management. Local merchants increasingly seek out automated fraud solutions, exemplified by Riskified’s traction and event sponsorship in 2025, amid broader digital retail trends in the region[3].  \n\n**Scope Statement:**  \nResults predominantly highlight Melbourne-based and Australia-wide activity for the last year, with limited direct information on Sydney-specific operations. The company’s APAC strategy, local leadership, and event-driven engagement demonstrate active investment and expansion in the Australian market, with substantial global developments reinforcing local relevance."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"About Us&lt;p&gt;Riskified empowers businesses to unleash ecommerce growth by taking risk off the table. Many of the world’s biggest brands and publicly traded companies selling online rely on Riskified for guaranteed protection against chargebacks, to fight fraud and policy abuse at scale, and to improve customer retention. Developed and managed by the largest team of ecommerce risk analysts, data scientists and researchers, Riskified’s AI-powered fraud and risk intelligence platform analyzes the individual behind each interaction to provide real-time decisions and robust identity-based insights. Riskified is proud to work with incredible companies in virtually all industries including Booking.com, Acer, Gucci, Lorna Jane, GoPro, and&amp;nbsp;many more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We thrive in a collaborative work setting, alongside great people, to build and enhance products that matter. Abundant opportunities to create and contribute provide us with a sense of purpose that extends beyond ourselves, leaving a lasting impact. These sentiments capture why we choose Riskified every day.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;About the Role&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This role will be based in Sydney**&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Riskified’s Growth team plays a key role in defining and executing the company’s expansion strategy. We are looking for an enthusiastic, highly intelligent individual to join our team as an Account Executive, spearheading our expansion in Australia and New Zealand. This is a role that combines sales, consulting, strategic thinking, and business analysis.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this position, you will take on leads of potential enterprise clients, develop relationships with multiple Fortune 500 companies, identify their unique needs and challenges, and drive adoption of Riskified’s solution. You will collaborate with other teams at Riskified to ensure a seamless on-boarding process, and use insights from client feedback to improve our service and offering.&lt;/p&gt;What You''ll Be Doing&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with clients, demonstrating a consultative approach to directly drive Riskified’s revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Receive leads from, and work together with our BD Team to manage sales pipeline and follow through with presentations, negotiations, and contracts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic analysis and critical thinking as we plan long-term expansion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Riskified at industry events and sales meetings with potential clients around the world&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of the payments industry and build relationships with key players in the space&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and articulate compelling value propositions around the Riskified solution&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Act as the face of the company across marketing and media initiatives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Qualifications&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of B2B enterprise closing experience managing end-to-end sales cycle - preferably with experience with B2B enterprise sales, tech companies, and/or a hyper-growth B2B SaaS startup, focused on the Australian market&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in a role that requires rigorous business analytics and/or strategic thought (management consulting, finance, business analysis, etc.) is a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Naturally analytical with a strong passion for persuasion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Someone who loves to quantify the qualitative&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Big bonus if you have worked with the eCommerce industry and sold to Heads of Digital/Online&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Superb written and verbal communication skills as well as interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Problem-solver, resourceful, someone who thrives off of autonomy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to interact and communicate with individuals at all levels of the organisation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced sales environment with minimum supervision&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;In The News&lt;p&gt;Reuters: General Atlantic-Backed Riskified is Valued at 4.3 BLN in NYSE Debut&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;FoxBusiness: Fraud Protection Platform ''Riskified'' Begins Trading on NYSE&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Announcing Riskified''s $165M Funding Round&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Fortune Magazine: 25 Best Workplaces in New York&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Calcalist: Riskified is the Most Promising Startup&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Inc Magazine: Best Workplaces&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Built In NYC: 100 Best Workplaces&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;TechCrunch: Riskified Prevents Fraud on Your Favorite eCommerce Site&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Riskified is deeply committed to the principle of equal opportunity for all individuals. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other status protected by law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFT8RqGtjHVUQ/company-logo_200_200/B4EZijzr.EHEAI-/0/1755094892812/riskified_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=zzTqV0QVy7T7nK7Clhe58QW8UXT9rvK4-p4wJeLxzPA', '2025-09-28T14:32:14.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recEPps9pBMTnbDMt', 'Commvault', 'https://www.commvault.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/commvault', 'Tinton Falls, NJ', 'Data Security Software Products', '1,001-5,000 employees', '75', 'Commvault is a growth-stage data security software company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively hiring for Account Executive and Partner Business Manager roles in Australia. The presence of Tier 1 (Country Manager, VP APAC) and Tier 2 (Sales Director ANZ, Enterprise Sales Director) decision makers provides high-level access for recruitment engagement. Recent ANZ-focused research, ongoing partnerships, and a global acquisition signal moderate growth, though no direct evidence of a current local hiring surge. The combination of core sales roles, industry fit, and quality decision makers makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] In July 2025, Commvault released its fifth annual “State of Data Readiness” report focused specifically on Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), highlighting a widening gap between cyber preparedness and true resilience among regional enterprises[2]. [REGIONAL] Commvault continues to collaborate with local partners such as NEC Australia to deliver managed backup, data protection, and hybrid cloud services tailored for Australian customers[3]. [GLOBAL] In August 2025, Commvault completed the acquisition of Satori, a move aimed at enhancing its data and AI security capabilities—developments expected to strengthen offerings globally, including in Australia[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] Commvault maintains a long-standing partnership with NEC Australia (since 2010), supporting data protection and hybrid cloud adoption among hundreds of organizations nationwide, indicating ongoing commitment to enterprise markets in Australia[3]. [GLOBAL] While there is no public evidence of recent sales/GTM hiring specifically in Victoria or Australia, Commvault has active recruitment for commercial sales and alliance roles in key global markets, suggesting overall expansion of field and partner engagement teams[5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There is no evidence of new funding rounds announced in the past 12 months. However, the Satori acquisition in August 2025 indicates active investments in strategic technology expansion rather than reliance on external fundraising[4].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Commvault’s commissioned research in July 2025 positions the company as a thought leader in cyber resilience for the ANZ market, driving industry conversation around readiness and compliance[2]. [LOCAL] Commvault’s technology is trusted for endpoint protection and backup across more than 1,000 local endpoints in partnerships with solution vendors like NEC Australia[3]. [GLOBAL] Commvault received \"Great Place to Work\" US certification in August 2025, highlighting strong cultural and operational standards at the global level[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Gareth Russell, based in Asia Pacific, serves as Field CTO and is a prominent spokesperson on resilience for the ANZ market, providing local leadership presence[2]. [GLOBAL] No major C-suite changes with direct ANZ/APAC mandates reported in the last 12 months.\n\n[INDUSTRY] Data security and cyber resilience remain critical for Australian enterprises, especially as compliance pressures from APRA and SoCI frameworks intensify; 34% of regional organizations are now subject to four or more regulatory acts, with complex cross-border data transfer rules also impacting solution requirements[2].\n\n**Notes:**  \n- No direct local office or hiring announcements for Victoria, Australia identified for the period requested; most evidence about Australian operations is at the national or ANZ regional level.\n- The company’s ongoing collaboration with NEC and presence in industry research, combined with global technology acquisitions, signal continued engagement and relevance in the Australian data security market."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment Fraud Alert&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’ve learned that scammers are impersonating Commvault team members—including HR and leadership—via email or text. These bad actors may conduct fake interviews and ask for personal information, such as your social security number.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What To Know&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commvault does not conduct interviews by email or text.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We will never ask you to submit sensitive documents (including banking information, SSN, etc) before your first day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you suspect a recruiting scam, please contact us at wwrecruitingteam@commvault.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Commvault&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Commvault (NASDAQ: CVLT) is the gold standard in cyber resilience. The company empowers customers to uncover, take action, and rapidly recover from cyberattacks – keeping data safe and businesses resilient. The company’s unique AI-powered platform combines best-in-class data protection, exceptional data security, advanced data intelligence, and lightning-fast recovery across any workload or cloud at the lowest TCO. For over 25 years, more than 100,000 organizations and a vast partner ecosystem have relied on Commvault to reduce risks, improve governance, and do more with data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a dynamic and results-driven Strategic Account Executive to lead Commvault’s growth across Victoria. You will be accountable for achieving quota by selling Commvault solutions into a defined account list, comprising both existing enterprise customers and high-value prospects within this strategic territory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will own the full sales lifecycle and work closely with cross-functional teams to plan, coordinate, and drive multi-quarter sales growth, account penetration, and long-term customer success. Your focus will be on secure software, SaaS, AI-enabled, and cloud-based data protection solutions that support compliance, resilience, and digital transformation goals across regulated industries.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Objectives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Achieve and Exceed Sales Quota&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Drive quarterly and annual revenue by securing new wins and expanding existing accounts across your territory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Strategic Campaigns and Account Plans&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Develop multi-year account strategies to win and grow high-potential customers, incorporating performance objectives, financial goals, and customer success metrics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Executive and Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Coordinate internal and external stakeholders including SEs, partners, marketing, and executive sponsors to build and close high-value sales campaigns.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Commvault as the Data Resilience Partner of Choice&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Demonstrate our leadership in secure, scalable, and compliant data management solutions, integrating AI and cloud capabilities to deliver measurable business value.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make An Impact&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell Commvault’s secure software, SaaS, AI-enabled, and cloud solutions through direct engagement and partner collaboration. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement territory and account plans for long-term expansion and strategic customer acquisition. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build high-value sales campaigns and manage multi-stakeholder buying groups, from technical evaluators to procurement and executive sponsors. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with SEs, Marketing, Channel, Legal, Finance, and Delivery teams to progress opportunities to successful outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Present compelling business cases and executive briefings that demonstrate Commvault’s value in meeting AI, cloud transformation, and cyber resilience objectives. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain high levels of activity, pipeline growth, and CRM hygiene to support forecasting and sales operations. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay current with industry trends in cybersecurity, AI/ML, secure cloud, and digital transformation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage alliances and partners to support joint solutions, accelerate procurement, and expand reach within the territory. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in enterprise software and SaaS sales to large organisations in regulated or complex industries. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in AI, Cloud, or Security solutions, with measurable achievements in delivering business outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of complex buying cycles, including procurement processes, compliance frameworks, and security requirements. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience closing six- and seven-figure deals in strategic, consultative sales environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong background in data protection, disaster recovery, or information management solutions. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to engage and influence CIOs, CISOs, procurement leaders, and other senior stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with and through channel and alliance partners. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with structured methodologies such as MEDDPICC or equivalent. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and executive presentation skills. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Operational discipline and experience using tools like Salesforce to manage pipeline, forecasting, and deal progression. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet The Leader&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Reporting to the AVP, ANZ – Craig Bastow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Love Working Here Because&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;High income earning opportunities based on self-performance. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Opportunity for Presidents Club &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee Stock Purchase Plan (ESPP) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuous professional development and product training &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales training in MEDDPICC and Command of the Message &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Commvault is an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are always committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status and we will not discriminate against on the basis of such characteristics or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Commvault’s goal is to make interviewing inclusive and accessible to all candidates and employees. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation to participate in the interview process or apply for a position at Commvault, please email accommodations@commvault.com For any inquiries not related to an accommodation please reach out to wwrecruitingteam@commvault.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Commvault''s Privacy Policy"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHBgh-w8L1ZqA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1699447122513/commvault_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=n7Si0jcbQ65Qe8iUgeY1iTjqgi7gNFjLRApMWKcCkBo', '2025-09-28T14:33:27.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recEYo1x3UYFQpDRY', 'Intercom', 'https://www.intercom.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/intercom', 'San Francisco, California', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '501-1,000 employees', '80', 'Intercom is a growth-stage SaaS company (501-1,000 employees) actively hiring for Account Executive roles in Sydney, reflecting ongoing expansion of its APAC sales team. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, and the presence of decision makers such as the Director of Sales and Senior Account Executives provides Tier 2 access for recruitment. Multiple growth signals—including a dedicated Sydney office, active local hiring, and a strong APAC sales focus—indicate a high likelihood of external recruitment needs for sales talent, though absence of recent local funding or major leadership changes keeps this just below ''very high'' priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Intercom completed a **new Sydney office fit-out** (Surry Hills, 285A Crown St) to reflect brand growth and maturity, aligning with its global ethos of flexibility and transparent leadership; the project was completed in 2020 but the office continues to serve as a hub for growth and engagement with the local workforce[1][4].\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office was positioned for **growth in research and development, sales, and customer support teams**, supported by updated collaborative workspaces[1][5].\n[GLOBAL] Intercom has promoted its **customer service platform for internet businesses** and claims more than 25,000 paying customers globally, with the Sydney office strategically focused on sales and customer support in Australia[4][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Active **hiring in Sydney**—job boards reflect up to 17 open roles in the last 60 days (as of September 2025), especially in sales, account management, and customer support, indicating continued local expansion and demand for go-to-market talent[3][5][6].\n[LOCAL] The office in Surry Hills houses **dedicated Sales and Customer Support teams**, signaling a firm commitment to APAC customer engagement[4][5].\n[GLOBAL] Company-wide headcount expansion is visible, with over 130 open positions globally in September 2025, showing broader organizational growth likely affecting the APAC region as well[6].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No significant new funding rounds with direct impact on Sydney or Australia have been reported in the last 12 months. Previous major investments have supported global and international expansion.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sydney office project was highlighted for its incorporation of **local art and modern workspaces**, underlining Intercom’s commitment to employee engagement and local cultural integration[1].\n[GLOBAL] Intercom maintains status as a **Forbes Cloud 100 Honoree** and is recognized for strong product growth and retention in customer service SaaS; these achievements bolster brand credibility in Sydney and across APAC[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No publicly documented executive appointments or departures specific to the Sydney or Australia arm in the past year.\n[GLOBAL] Eoghan McCabe continues as CEO, and there is no widely reported change in global sales or APAC-specific executive leadership in the past 12 months[5].\n\nSummary Scope Indicator Notes:\n- Most specific, actionable data about Intercom’s Sydney and Australia presence concerns the modern Surry Hills office, active hiring for **sales and support roles**, and an ongoing commitment to team expansion and workspace improvement.  \n- Limited evidence of major strategic shifts, funding events, or significant local leadership change in the past year.\n- Global product and brand successes, as well as sustained hiring momentum, point to continued relevance and ambition in the Sydney and regional markets."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Intercom is the AI Customer Service company on a mission to help businesses provide incredible customer experiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI agent Fin, the most advanced customer service AI agent on the market, lets businesses deliver always-on, impeccable customer service and ultimately transform their customer experiences for the better. Fin can also be combined with our Helpdesk to become a complete solution called the Intercom Customer Service Suite, which provides AI enhanced support for the more complex or high touch queries that require a human agent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2011 and trusted by nearly 30,000 global businesses, Intercom is setting the new standard for customer service. Driven by our core values, we push boundaries, build with speed and intensity, and consistently deliver incredible value to our customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What''s the opportunity?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Account Executive (Existing Business), you will be a key member of the team leading the growth of our existing business. We’re building a world-class sales organization, and the road ahead is going to be very exciting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Intercom, we are striving to do sales differently. We are asking our customers to put Intercom at the core of their businesses, and we can only do this by putting them at the core of ours. We strongly believe in the overall growth and continued development of each new hire. In joining the Existing Business team at Intercom, you join a community that believes in development and promotion from within. As a rapidly expanding business, there is a high degree of opportunity for progression, creativity, and ownership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What will I be doing?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with Intercom’s small business customers ensuring revenue growth and customer retention&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with current customers to understand their business pains, and provide solutions based on our platform to alleviate them&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic territory plans outlining opportunities for upsell, cross-sell, expansion to new business units, and achieve business goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop advanced knowledge of your customers'' businesses and goals while accurately forecasting sales pipeline&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Marketing, Product, and Customer Success by providing customer feedback to drive product innovation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track and report all key metrics related to customer growth, retention and Intercom product usage growth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage in team development and mentoring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;What skills do I need?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2+ years managing a large book of business; 150 accounts (retention, renewals, &amp;amp; account growth) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1+ years selling SaaS products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing procurement processes &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong sales instincts and track record hitting and exceeding quota&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communicator &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable and energized operating and problem-solving in a fast-moving organization. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exhibits a growth mindset, intellectual curiosity, and ambition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to build and maintain deep client relationships across levels in complex organizations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable history of leadership, with both immediate and cross-functional teammates&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are a well-treated bunch, with awesome benefits! If there’s something important to you that’s not on this list, talk to us!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary and equity in a fast-growing start-up&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Catered lunch every weekday, plus a fully stocked kitchen&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular compensation reviews - we reward great work!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible paid time off policy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Healthcare stipend towards private health insurance for you and your partner/spouse&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MacBooks are our standard, but we also offer Windows for certain roles when needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policies &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Intercom has a hybrid working policy. We believe that working in person helps us stay connected, collaborate easier and create a great culture while still providing flexibility to work from home. We expect employees to be in the office at least three days per week.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We have a radically open and accepting culture at Intercom. We avoid spending time on divisive subjects to foster a safe and cohesive work environment for everyone. As an organization, our policy is to not advocate on behalf of the company or our employees on any social or political topics out of our internal or external communications. We respect personal opinion and expression on these topics on personal social platforms on personal time, and do not challenge or confront anyone for their views on non-work related topics. Our goal is to focus on doing incredible work to achieve our goals and unite the company through our core values.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Intercom values diversity and is committed to a policy of Equal Employment Opportunity. Intercom will not discriminate against an applicant or employee on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, national origin, ancestry, sex, gender, age, physical or mental disability, veteran or military status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, marital status, or any other legally recognized protected basis under federal, state, or local law.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Is this role not quite what you''re looking for? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our Talent Community&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; to stay connected with us.&lt;/strong&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQHxzX8mZOqVzg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1648059752074/intercom_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=kko3-pu2qdFxITTAdkjbsZ-Iypk4ZFsP7HQLUi83bUk', '2025-09-20T06:30:05.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recEblLn5WJmqei0i', 'Braze', 'https://www.braze.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/braze', 'New York, New York', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '93', 'Braze is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for Business Development Representative (BDR) and Account Executive roles, both primary and high-priority sales positions. The company operates in Australia and Singapore, with recent major investments in Sydney (new ANZ HQ and data centre), strong local growth, and ongoing regional expansion. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (GM ANZ, Area VP ANZ, Sales Directors) are present, providing direct access for recruitment. Numerous strong growth signals—market expansion, headcount growth, major client wins, and infrastructure investment—make this a highly attractive recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] In early 2025, Braze launched its new **Sydney data centre** and established its **ANZ headquarters in Sydney, NSW**, signaling heightened investment and long-term commitment to the Australian and New Zealand market[1][2].  \n[LOCAL] The **acquisition of local reseller NorthStar in June 2023** drove robust local growth, with the region now the company''s fastest-growing in APAC, supported by partnerships with major Australian brands including Wesfarmers, Canva, REA Group, David Jones, and Cashrewards[1].  \n[REGIONAL] The Sydney operations and infrastructure serve as the anchor for ANZ, and Braze will expand further regionally with a new data center in Indonesia planned by April 2025[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Throughout 2024, Braze saw record-breaking messaging volumes supported by this infrastructure investment and cited 100% uptime during global peak periods[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[LOCAL] The **ANZ-based team scaled to 70 professionals** across Sydney, Melbourne, and Queensland, with significant expansion particularly in customer engagement and data security functions[1].  \n[LOCAL] Braze''s Sydney office is being used as a central point for further sales and go-to-market (GTM) expansion in the Australian market[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Braze lists Sydney among its key global office locations and continues hiring in Australia, specifically mentioning employee growth and regional talent acquisition as part of its “Great Place to Work” certifications in Australia (2025)[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \n[GLOBAL] No new local or regional funding rounds were identified in the last 12 months. The last major global financial reporting focused on operational expansion and revenue growth, with resources directed at international market investment[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \n[LOCAL] The **Sydney data centre and ANZ headquarters launch** in 2025 is positioned as a major milestone for customer trust, security, and data sovereignty for Australian customers[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] Braze was recognized as a \"Great Place to Work\" in Australia and Singapore in 2025, underscoring both cultural and operational credibility in APAC[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Broader recognition includes featured rankings in U.S. News & World Report’s Best Companies to Work For and Fortune Best Workplaces lists throughout 2024/2025[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \n[LOCAL] **Lewis Barnes** is noted as General Manager for Australia and Senior Director of Customer Success, leading local strategy and market implementation as of 2025[1].  \n[REGIONAL] **Shahid Nizami** serves as Vice President for Asia Pacific & GCC, overseeing APAC expansion with a major focus on Australia as a hub[1].  \n[GLOBAL] No recent executive changes specific to Sydney or broader ANZ sales/revenue/people roles reported in the last 12 months.\n\nScope used: Information above is drawn primarily from highly specific local and ANZ sources, with supporting detail from APAC/global activities when directly connected to the AU market."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Braze, we have found our people. We’re a genuinely approachable, exceptionally kind, and intensely passionate crew.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We seek to ignite that passion by setting high standards, championing teamwork, and creating work-life harmony as we collectively navigate rapid growth on a global scale while striving for greater equity and opportunity – inside and outside our organization.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To flourish here, you must be prepared to set a high bar for yourself and those around you. There is always a way to contribute: Acting with autonomy, having accountability and being open to new perspectives are essential to our continued success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our deep curiosity to learn and our eagerness to share diverse passions with others gives us balance and injects a one-of-a-kind vibrancy into our culture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you are driven to solve exhilarating challenges and have a bias toward action in the face of change, you will be empowered to make a real impact here, with a sharp and passionate team at your back. If Braze sounds like a place where you can thrive, we can’t wait to meet you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The ideal candidate has at least 8 years of SaaS selling experience within CRM, Marketing Automation, CDP, Analytics, or Content Marketing Solutions. You bring an entrepreneurial mindset, you have a knack for simply selling complex tech solutions, and you excel in fast-paced environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute deal cycles from inception to close, navigating through various stakeholders within large organizations. Deal sizes typically range from $100K to $1M+.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain strong relationships with key decision-makers at all levels of an organization.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive value-based selling strategies, leveraging MEDPICC to effectively articulate our value proposition. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and qualify new opportunities through targeted prospecting, networking, and market research efforts to continually build your pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create strategic growth opportunities for your existing customer base.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build strong cross-functional relationships with teams such as business development, marketing, deal desk, customer success &amp;amp; services.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 8 years of experience in Enterprise wesales, with proven successes in executing complex deal cycles and driving high-value sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years of experience selling in either UAE or KSA with physical presence in either of these countries&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of value-based selling techniques and experience applying the MEDPICC deal methodology.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Executive presence with exceptional communication and presentation skills, able to effectively engage and influence executive-level stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with cross-functional teams and demonstrated ability to build strong internal relationships across various departments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with navigating agency and technology partner ecosystems, with a demonstrated ability to leverage partnerships to enhance sales capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce.com CRM or any other CRM utilized for sales pipeline management required.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Verbal and written fluency in Arabic would also be an advantage. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Braze benefits vary by location, and we encourage you to review our specific benefits offerings for each country here . More details on benefits plans will be provided if you receive an offer of employment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;From offering comprehensive benefits to fostering hybrid ways of working, we’ve got you covered so you can prioritize work-life harmony. Braze offers benefits such as:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation that may include equity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Retirement and Employee Stock Purchase Plans&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible paid time off&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive benefit plans covering medical, dental, vision, life, and disability&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Family services that include fertility benefits and equal paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Professional development supported by formal career pathing, learning platforms, and a yearly learning stipend&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A curated in-office employee experience, designed to foster community, team connections, and innovation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to give back to your community, including an annual company-wide Volunteer Week and donation matching &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee Resource Groups that provide supportive communities within Braze&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborative, transparent, and fun culture recognized as a Great Place to Work®&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Braze&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Braze is the leading customer engagement platform that empowers brands to Be Absolutely Engaging.™ Braze allows any marketer to collect and take action on any amount of data from any source, so they can creatively engage with customers in real time, across channels from one platform. From cross-channel messaging and journey orchestration to Al-powered experimentation and optimization, Braze enables companies to build and maintain absolutely engaging relationships with their customers that foster growth and loyalty.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Braze is proudly certified as a Great Place to Work® in the U.S., the UK, Australia, and Singapore. In 2025, we were recognized as one of Built In’s Best Places to Work. In 2024, we were included in U.S. News &amp;amp; World Report’s Best Companies to Work For (Top 10%) and recognized in Great Place to Work’s Fortune Best Medium Workplaces, Fortune Best Workplaces in Technology, Fortune Best Workplaces for Parents, and Fortune Best Workplaces for Women.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Additionally, we were featured in Great Place to Work UK’s Best Workplaces, Best Workplaces in Europe, Best Workplaces for Development, Best Workplaces for Wellbeing, Best Workplaces for Women, and Best Workplaces in Technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You’ll find many of us at headquarters in New York City or around the world in Austin, Berlin, Bucharest, Chicago, Dubai, Jakarta, London, Paris, San Francisco, Singapore, São Paulo, Seoul, Sydney and Tokyo – not to mention our employees in nearly 50 remote locations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BRAZE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Braze, we strive to create equitable growth and opportunities inside and outside the organization.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Building meaningful connections is at the heart of everything we do, and that includes our recruiting practices. We''re committed to offering all candidates a fair, accessible, and inclusive experience – regardless of age, color, disability, gender identity, marital status, maternity, national origin, pregnancy, race, religion, sex, sexual orientation, or status as a protected veteran. When applying and interviewing with Braze, we want you to feel comfortable showcasing what makes you you .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We know that sometimes different circumstances can lead talented people to hesitate to apply for a role unless they meet 100% of the criteria. If this sounds familiar, we encourage you to apply, as we’d love to meet you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please see our Candidate Privacy Policy for more information on how Braze processes your personal information during the recruitment process and, if applicable based on your location, how you can exercise any privacy rights."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQHm8zx58eJrcg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1720024715139/braze_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=dnpfA29o6dAl6dUTBHmsmwqbMDnJcK4f5wRzleDV8x0', '2025-09-20T06:21:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recEhg1QlrJS0fLCx', 'Grafana Labs', 'https://grafana.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/grafana-labs', 'New York, NY, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '95', 'Grafana Labs is a growth-stage computer software company (1,690 employees) actively hiring for senior sales roles such as Enterprise Account Executive and Senior Manager, Sales Development, APAC, which are core priorities for 4Twenty. The company operates in commercial B2B SaaS with strong fit, and has Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Regional Sales Directors, RVP APAC, Senior Manager Sales Development) in Australia and Singapore. Recent $270M funding, major product launches, and market expansion signal robust growth and immediate recruitment needs, making this a very high priority opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nGrafana Labs completed a $270M primary and secondary transaction in August 2024 at a $6B valuation and was named a Leader in the Gartner Magic Quadrant for Observability Platforms in April 2024. The company also unveiled significant updates and new product innovations at GrafanaCON 2025 in May, including the release of Grafana 12 and enhancements to its open-source ecosystem.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nThe workforce is reported at 1001-5000 employees, and the company surpassed 5,000 paying customers in 2024. Annual recurring revenue exceeded $250M, and recent funding is earmarked for further expansion and possible strategic acquisitions.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nGrafana Labs raised $270M in an extension of its Series D round led by Lightspeed Venture Partners in August 2024 at a $6B valuation. Total funding to date is $805.2M.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn May 2025, the company launched Grafana 12, introducing new workflow tools, Drilldown experience, Git Sync, and support for SQL Expressions. Grafana Labs achieved over $250M in ARR, served more than 5,000 customers, and was recognized as a Leader in the Gartner Magic Quadrant for Observability Platforms in April 2024.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Grafana Labs provides an open and composable observability stack built around Grafana, the leading open source technology for dashboards and visualization. There are 5,000+ Grafana Labs customers, including Bloomberg, Citigroup, Dell Technologies, Salesforce, and TomTom, and 25M+ Grafana users around the world. Grafana Labs helps companies achieve their observability goals with the LGTM Stack, which features scalable metrics (Grafana Mimir), logs (Grafana Loki), and traces (Grafana Tempo) as well as extensive enterprise data source plugins, dashboard management, alerting, reporting, and security. The fully managed Grafana Cloud offering helps organizations get observability up and running easier and faster, with turnkey solutions for Kubernetes and infrastructure monitoring, incident response management, load testing, application observability, and more. Grafana Labs is backed by leading investors Lightspeed Venture Partners, Lead Edge Capital, GIC, Sequoia Capital, Coatue, J.P. Morgan, and CapitalG. Follow Grafana Labs on LinkedIn and Twitter or visit grafana.com."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:24:16.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recF7gctHt1eygoHJ', 'Mindbody', 'http://www.mindbodyonline.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mindbody', 'San Luis Obispo, California, US', 'Health, Wellness & Fitness', '1001 - 5000', '74', 'Mindbody operates in wellness technology with a strong SaaS and software focus, supported by a large APAC team and established sales leadership. Recent brand unification and technology partnerships signal ongoing innovation, though there are no explicit recent hiring surges or funding rounds. Multiple sales and customer success roles are present in Australia, indicating a robust sales infrastructure and potential for external recruitment needs.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn early September 2025, Mindbody and ClassPass announced their unification under a new parent brand, Playlist, bringing together Mindbody, Booker, and ClassPass for a more integrated approach to wellness technology. In mid-2024, Mindbody also entered a partnership with Rokt to enhance relevant online advertising experiences for its network of fitness and wellness members.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent explicit hiring or GTM headcount growth activity identified in available sources, though the company''s expansion under the Playlist brand and its technology partnerships indicate a focus on scaling and innovation.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or financial milestones announced in the past 12 months based on available information.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn June 2025, Mindbody published its annual Wellness Index, surveying over 8,000 consumers and reporting continued prioritization of wellness despite economic challenges. The company also released a 2024 Predictions Report highlighting key industry trends and reaffirmed its status as a leading voice in the wellness technology space.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes identified in the past 6-12 months in publicly available sources."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Powering the worldâs fitness and wellness businesses and connecting them with more consumers, more effectively, than anyone else."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recF8I7auja1o6VXQ', 'Birdeye', 'https://bit.ly/3OlcHD7', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/birdeye', 'Palo Alto, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '65', 'Birdeye is a growth-stage computer software company (1,477 employees) specializing in commercial B2B tech, which aligns strongly with our target market. The recent launch of AI-powered marketing platforms and Birdeye Social demonstrates clear product innovation and expansion, indicating moderate growth signals. However, there are no recent funding rounds or executive hires, and the available contacts do not include Tier 1 or 2 decision makers, limiting immediate recruitment access. The opportunity is driven by the company''s industry fit and product momentum, but the lack of direct sales role posting and decision maker access keeps this at a HIGH rather than VERY HIGH priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \nBirdeye unveiled a new AI-powered architecture for hyperlocal marketing in May 2025, introducing a \"Service-as-a-Software\" model focused on autonomous AI agents and business outcomes. The company also launched Birdeye Social, an AI-driven social media management platform for multi-location brands in July 2025[3][2][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \nBirdeye is expanding its platform capabilities with new AI offerings and continues to add features targeting enterprise and multi-location businesses. No specific hiring figures for sales/GTM roles in the last 6-12 months were identified[2][3][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements were identified within the last 6-12 months for the U.S.-based Birdeye. (Recent funding information found pertains to a different company, BirdEye in Saudi Arabia, and is not applicable here)[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \nBirdeye was recognized for launching major product innovations, including its AI architecture for hyperlocal marketing in May 2025 and the Birdeye Social platform in July 2025, positioning itself as a leader in AI-driven local marketing solutions[2][3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or leadership changes have been identified within the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":" Birdeye is the #1 Agentic Marketing Platform forâ¨Multi-location Brands, purpose-built for multi-location brands. Over 200,000 businesses rely on Birdeyeâs intelligent AI agents to run marketing and drive business outcomes. Birdeye helps brands enhance online reputation, engage customers across social, search, and web, and gain real-time insights into consumers and competitors â all to boost leads & foot traffic, reduce costs, and grow revenue."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recFCe6j9Nnueq508', 'Fiserv', 'http://www.fiserv.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fiserv', 'Milwaukee, Wisconsin, US', 'Information Technology & Services', '10001 -', '79', 'Fiserv is a global fintech and payments leader with strong APAC presence in Australia and Singapore. The company demonstrates ongoing growth through recent acquisitions and 8% year-to-date revenue increase, with a robust sales structure including Account Executives, Sales Managers, Business Development, and Customer Success roles. Multiple senior decision makers and sales leadership are present across both AU and SG, indicating immediate and ongoing hiring potential in technology, sales, and digital domains.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nFiserv lowered its full-year 2025 organic revenue growth guidance and confirmed decelerating quarterly revenue in its Merchant segment on July 23, 2025, which led to a nearly 14% drop in its stock price. The company also closed the acquisition of AIB Merchant Services in September 2025 to expand its European footprint.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nOrganic revenue grew 8% year-to-date with particular strength in the Merchant Solutions segment. Fiservâs recent acquisition activity in Europe suggests ongoing geographic expansion.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nFiserv reported 8% GAAP revenue growth in Q2 2025 and noted continued success expanding its Clover offerings and business management platform. The acquisition of AIB Merchant Services was finalized in September 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Fiserv, Inc. (NYSE: FI) is a global technology leader committed to delivering innovative and transformative financial services experiences for clients in more than 100 countries."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recFGFTUUH2f9bOaC', '4mation Technologies', 'https://www.4mation.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/4mation-technologies-pty-ltd', 'Surry Hills, NSW', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '51-200 employees', '56', '4mation Technologies is a small/medium B2B technology company (51-200 employees) in Sydney, actively focused on AI-driven software solutions, with recent achievements in AI chatbot delivery and strong local market positioning. The inclusion is triggered by a Senior Client Services Manager role, which is a medium-priority sales-related role. The company operates in a core commercial tech sector, but decision maker access is limited to a Tier 3 sales leader, and there are moderate growth signals (AI-first strategy, new partnerships, increased outreach) but no recent funding or major leadership changes. This presents a medium recruitment opportunity for external sales hiring.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] 4mation Technologies shifted to an **AI-first strategy** as of late 2024, now offering AI-driven software development, chatbot prototyping, and AI-powered business applications tailored for Australian companies[4][5].  \n[LOCAL] The firm highlights fixed-outcome, fixed-cost project delivery for Sydney-based enterprise and government clients, indicating a service model adapted for local market demands[4][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Team size is estimated between **30-99 employees**, with recent public mentions of over 50 staff; all developers, designers, and strategists are local to Sydney[1][2][5].  \n[LOCAL] Recent website and social activity reflect increased exposure and outreach to Australian businesses innovating in tech, with a particular focus on custom AI and software solutions[5].  \n[LOCAL] Latest company headquarters remains Level 7, 28 Foveaux St, Surry Hills, NSW[2][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL] No public funding rounds or financial milestones have been disclosed in the past 12 months for 4mation Technologies[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Delivered an **AI chatbot Proof of Concept** for onboarding process improvement to a Sydney business in 2024, demonstrating capacity for advanced machine learning and implementation[5].  \n[LOCAL] Maintained status as a **Great Place To Work** per the 2024 Australia National Employee Engagement Study, underlining positive workforce culture and employee retention[1].  \n[LOCAL] Noted successful partnerships with both **enterprise clients and state government agencies**, indicating penetration into strategic local sectors[5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No executive departures, appointments, or material leadership changes have been publicly disclosed in the past 12 months.  \n[LOCAL] Key local leaders remain Scott (Internal Operations, Certified AWS Solutions Architect), Michael (Market Exposure & Partnerships), Kieran Yeates (Head of Delivery), and Lilli (Client Success), each with over a decade in Australian tech delivery roles[4].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Sydney’s technology sector is experiencing rapid adoption of AI, automation, and custom web/mobile solutions to support enterprise digital transformation, especially in finance, government, and growing SaaS providers.  \n[INDUSTRY] There is high local demand for **AI-enabled applications and staff augmentation** services, matching 4mation’s offerings and market positioning[1][4][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About 4mation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For 24 years, 4mation has been building high-impact digital solutions for clients across Australia and beyond. Our team of 50+ experts partners with Australia’s fastest-growing companies, State Government Agencies, and global Fortune 500 organisations. As an award-winning technology consultancy, we thrive on solving complex challenges and delivering outcomes that drive business growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are now looking for a driven and ambitious &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development Manager (BDM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; to join our team and expand our client base.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Business Development Manager at 4mation, you will be responsible for converting inbound leads and generating new business opportunities through your professional network. You’ll nurture relationships with decision-makers, understand their challenges, and position 4mation as their trusted technology partner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a sales role that involves managing inbound opportunities from digital campaigns, while also leveraging your own network to uncover new opportunities. Success is measured by your ability to drive new client acquisition, grow revenue, and build long-term partnerships.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Inbound Lead Conversion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualify and convert inbound leads generated through marketing and Google Ads.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Run discovery calls and move opportunities through the sales pipeline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Network &amp;amp; Business Development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leverage your own network to generate additional opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Actively engage in industry events, forums, and communities to expand 4mation’s reach.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Develop new relationships with senior decision-makers in targeted industries.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sales Process Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Own the full sales cycle: prospecting, discovery, proposal, and contract negotiation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Deliver compelling presentations and value-led proposals to senior stakeholders.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to design tailored solutions that meet client needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Handover&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Work closely with Account Managers to ensure smooth onboarding and long-term client success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Provide market and client insights back to leadership and marketing to refine the go-to-market strategy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Proven experience as a Business Development Manager, Sales Manager, or similar role in a technology consultancy or IT services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Strong track record of achieving and exceeding sales targets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ability to build relationships with senior stakeholders and influence decision-making.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Strategic thinker with strong commercial acumen and a solutions-oriented mindset.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Self-motivated, results-driven, and comfortable in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Metrics (KPIs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;New client acquisition and revenue targets achieved quarterly/yearly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consistent pipeline development (e.g., number of qualified leads/opportunities per quarter).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Conversion rates from initial meetings to closed deals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Average deal size and contribution to overall company growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join 4mation?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;A competitive base salary with a rewarding commission structure tied to performance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Be part of an award-winning consultancy with over two decades of proven success&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Work with a diverse range of clients — from scale-ups to Fortune 500s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;A collaborative, supportive team culture with access to experienced mentors and leaders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Career growth opportunities in a business that values innovation, learning, and professional development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you’re a motivated BDM who thrives on building new relationships and driving revenue growth, 4mation is the place for you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEZyYXexvV7gw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1724889209282/4mation_technologies_pty_ltd_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=xPzMM9v_JfwP3GLyr0LmD6Lyy8AXs34953kpLTLaQP0', '2025-09-30T14:18:01.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z')
