    ('recGE3SxquQ3dJaUl', 'Wiise', 'https://wiise.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/wiisesoftware', 'Barangaroo, New South Wales, AU', 'Computer Software', '11 - 50', '54', 'Wiise is a small commercial B2B SaaS company (43 employees) in the computer software sector, fitting the core industry criteria. The inclusion is triggered by the presence of a Business Development Manager, a medium-priority sales role. The company shows moderate growth signals through recent product launches, geographic expansion, and new partnerships, but lacks evidence of recent funding or active sales hiring. Decision maker access includes a Head of Sales and Strategy (Tier 2) and a Chief Customer Officer (Tier 2), supporting recruitment engagement. Overall, this is a medium-priority opportunity due to acceptable role/industry fit, moderate growth, and decision maker access, but limited immediate sales hiring signals.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nWiise announced Endeavour and Thyme Technology as its first two delivery partners in New Zealand in February 2024, following recent entry into the Kiwi market. The company is accelerating product innovation, particularly with AI-powered ERP solutions and is preparing to launch the Warehouse on Time extension for advanced warehouse mobility.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent expansion into New Zealand with partners and acquisition of new customers signals ongoing geographic and customer growth. No substantial evidence of targeted sales or GTM team hiring activity identified in the public domain from the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or financial milestones identified in the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nLaunched major product updates in April 2025 and August 2025, including enhancements to manufacturing workflows, AI Copilot features, and Power BI financial dashboards. Introduced Wiise Academy and finalized key integrations such as Stripe and new warehouse features between October 2024 and August 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people leadership roles identified in the past 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Wiise is all-in-one business management software that helps you streamline your workflows, manage complex operations and make smarter and faster decisions to accelerate your growth. Visit wiise.com to find out more today."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recGLH3p9BtAkyhl3', 'Datadog', 'http://datadoghq.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/datadog', 'New York, NY, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '97', 'Datadog is a global SaaS leader in cloud and AI observability with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore. The company has multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 sales decision makers, including Vice Presidents, Sales Directors, and Managers across APAC. Recent $775M funding, major AI product launches, and international expansion signal robust growth and high likelihood of ongoing sales hiring. This represents an immediate and high-value recruitment opportunity for core sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn September 2025, Datadog shifted its strategy toward AI-driven growth, focusing on geographic expansion into India, Brazil, and the Middle East to meet AI observability demand. Investors expressed concern over slower projected revenue growth for 2025 (18â19%, down from 26% in 2024) as the company recalibrates towards long-term AI market positioning.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nDatadog is actively expanding its presence in new international markets (India, Brazil, Middle East) and is emphasizing retention and upsell, particularly through its AI-native customer base, which grew its contribution to 11% of Q2 2025 revenue (up from 4% in 2024). No specific hiring or headcount growth data identified in the past 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nOn December 9, 2024, Datadog announced a proposed private offering of $775 million of convertible senior notes due 2029, with an option for initial purchasers to buy an additional $116.25 million.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAt DASH 2025, Datadog announced major updates to its platform, including the Bits AI Dev Agent for autonomous code fixes and the Bits AI Security Analyst for automating security investigations. On June 10, 2025, Datadog expanded its LLM observability capabilities for monitoring agentic AI and improving model performance.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Datadog is the essential monitoring platform for cloud applications. We bring together data from servers, containers, databases, and third-party services to make your stack entirely observable. These capabilities help DevOps teams avoid downtime, resolve performance issues, and ensure customers are getting the best user experience.\n\n"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
