    ('recGlnjiLpP9x0uU5', 'Airlock Digital', 'https://www.airlockdigital.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/airlock-digital', 'Adelaide, , AU', 'Computer & Network Security', '51 - 200', '53', 'Airlock Digital operates in the core cybersecurity sector with over 100 employees, aligning well with target industries. The presence of a Head of Customer Success provides Tier 2 decision maker access, but there are no current core sales role postings or explicit hiring signals. Recent product launches and industry recognition indicate moderate growth, making this a potential pipeline opportunity rather than an immediate priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAirlock Digital launched an auto-scale, multi-tenant cloud platform in August 2024, allowing enterprise customers to manage application control across segmented environments more flexibly. The company also showcased its enterprise-class application control solution at Black Hat USA 2025 and RSAC 2025, highlighting advancements and aligning with new cybersecurity trends.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent explicit hiring or headcount growth activity identified. Notable focus remains on expanding presence in key markets, including the US, UK, and Australia, and deepening customer and partner engagement through summits and industry events.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investment announcements, or financial milestones publicly identified for the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAirlock Digital released Version 6.1, its most significant update since founding, in April 2024, introducing a policy change history feature, a revamped user interface, and integration with Microsoft Entra cloud. The company was recognized as a High Performer in G2''s Spring 2024 Reports for Endpoint Management and actively demonstrated innovations at major cybersecurity events like Black Hat 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership additions, executive promotions, or departures identified in the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Airlock Digital is the global leader in application control and allowlisting, trusted by organizations worldwide to protect against ransomware, malware and other cyber threats. Our deny by default solution enables customers to run only the applications and files they trust, with all others blocked from executing. This approach minimizes attack surfaces and helps organizations align their cybersecurity strategies with government frameworks and standards.\n\nServing customers globally, Airlock Digital supports a broad spectrum of industries, including financial services, healthcare, manufacturing and government. We protect legacy systems and the latest versions of the Windows, macOS and Linux operating systems, enabling us to secure modern environments as well as older technologies. Our scalable, simple-to-implement solution forms a key pillar of cybersecurity strategies, delivering robust protection to organizations of all sizes."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recHDosRLFHFVt3wr', 'SafetyCulture', 'http://www.safetyculture.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/safetyculturehq', 'Surry Hills, New South Wales', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '92', 'SafetyCulture is a growth-stage B2B SaaS leader in operational excellence, actively hiring for core sales roles such as Account Executive, Senior Account Executive, and Sales Manager. The company operates in the ideal 501-1,000 employee range, with a strong commercial tech fit and ongoing team expansion in Sydney. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Directors of Sales, Sales Managers, General Manager) are accessible, providing direct recruitment access. Frequent sales hiring, regular product and networking events, and a top employer reputation signal robust organic growth, making this a top-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] SafetyCulture hosted its flagship \"Better by SafetyCulture\" event in Sydney on August 18-19, 2025, bringing together industry experts, customers, and platform engineers to showcase operational excellence solutions and provide integrated improvement training courses[2][3]. [LOCAL] Regular professional networking events and MeetUps are held at the Surry Hills office, contributing to product feedback and knowledge exchange among Sydney’s business and tech community[1]. [REGIONAL] The Asia-Pacific agenda includes recurring online and in-person sessions focused on platform updates and compliance best practice, indicating regional user engagement[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] SafetyCulture’s Sydney HQ employs a large, diverse team in an environment voted Australia’s 3rd Best Place to Work, with ongoing recruitment for product, engineering, and customer-facing roles[1]. Team expansion is also signaled by frequent postings for featured roles in sales and operations across Sydney[1]. [GLOBAL] The company continues to invest in physical office space and employee experience globally, with Sydney cited as a melting pot for internal growth and cross-functional collaborations[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No public information found regarding new funding rounds in the last 12 months specific to Sydney or Australia. Historical data indicates that previous investments have supported technology expansion and regional market penetration; absence of recent directly quoted events suggests a period of organic growth rather than large capital injections in this timeframe.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office was recognized among top Australian employers and continues to enhance culture through events, amenities, and learning opportunities[1]. [LOCAL] Sydney’s annual \"Better by SafetyCulture\" event is a flagship achievement, focusing on technology integration and customer-led workshops[2][3]. [REGIONAL] Asia-Pacific and ANZ users benefit from new platform functionalities and compliance-focused courses, including specialized training such as AED awareness in partnership with public figures (e.g., with Greg Page in April 2025)[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No reported executive appointments, promotions, or departures specific to Sydney or Australia in the past 6-12 months among public sources. Leadership continuity inferred for local operations in this period. [GLOBAL] No company-wide leadership changes impacting APAC found in the last year; regional management remains stable according to publicly available details.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Sydney’s software development sector, especially B2B SaaS and workplace tools, continues seeing strong demand for compliance, safety, and operational excellence platforms. SafetyCulture is considered a market leader for mobile-first solutions supporting EHS, GRC, asset management, and digital process improvement among enterprise clients in Australia and globally[5]. Industry-wide, the trend is toward integrated, AI-enhanced solutions with high scalability for large teams working in regulated industries and distributed locations[5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"SafetyCulture is a global technology company that is helping to transform workplaces around the world. Our mission is to help working teams get better every day and our technology platform and products give front line workers a voice and leaders the visibility to make smart decisions when driving safety, quality and continuous improvement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SafetyCulture is one of the fastest-growing tech companies. Our bold ambition is to reach 100 million users worldwide by 2032. Opportunities to help shape a journey like this do not come around often!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a customer-centric and ambitious Senior Account Executive within our Enterprise team to join APAC Sales at SafetyCulture. Our Senior Account Executives play an instrumental role in developing and managing customer relationships at an Enterprise level through effective business partnership and solving customer problems. Your collaborative, personable and driven approach, coupled with your strategic value-driven thinking, will seal your success in driving growth and product adoption.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Spend Your Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic business plans to drive and deliver commercial business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and implement a strong outbound sales plan for your territory&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain and grow your existing portfolio of customers to deliver long term value&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend roadshows and customer summits, educating prospective customers &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform in-person and online demos, sharing the value of our products to prospective customers, tailored to their needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage the full sales process to close in order to achieve quarterly targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partnering closely with our Customer Success and Business Development teams to ensure customers have a smooth onboarding and supporting the development of long-term, successful customer relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be the voice of the customer to our cross-functional partners, including our world-class product team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain data integrity through Salesforce and report on all sales activities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand market trends and proactively engage with customers in a meaningful way based on the insights captured. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Senior professional B2B enterprise selling experience with a proven track record in managing a sales pipeline and achieving targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative and customer-centric approach with demonstrated ability to build trust, establish rapport and uncover customer pain points&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Motivated to identify new customer opportunities in conjunction with driving expansion opportunities with existing customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in an agile, fast-moving organisation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in managing opportunities with cross-functional teams including customers success and partnerships. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to demonstrate SafetyCulture values (Think Customer, Open Honest Always, Better as a Team, Be Bold Bring Action)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SaaS sales experience highly desirable&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At SafetyCulture, we care about people and growing the team, through:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Equity with high growth potential, and a competitive salary, &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible working arrangements, we encourage you to create the best work blend while working from your home and the local SafetyCulture office;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access to professional and personal training and development opportunities; Hackathons, Workshops, Lunch &amp;amp; Learns; &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We encourage involvement in the community, open source work, attending talks and events, and experimenting with new technologies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Also Receive Other Perks Such As&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;In-house Culinary Crew serving up daily breakfast, lunch and snacks&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing initiatives such as subsidised fitness programs, EAP services and generous parental leave policy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Quarterly celebrations and team events, including the annual Shiplt global offsite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Table tennis, board games, gym sessions, book club, and pet-friendly offices.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We’re committed to building inclusive teams and cultivating a sense of belonging so our people can bring their whole authentic selves to work each day. We seek to make reasonable adjustments throughout our recruitment process to create an even playing field for all candidates. Thanks to the tireless efforts of the entire SafetyCulture team we’ve built an incredible culture which has seen us recognised as a Best Place to Work in Australia , the US and the UK .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Even if you don''t meet every requirement listed in the ad, please consider applying for this role. We prioritise inclusion and value individuals with potential over a checklist of qualifications. Don''t rule yourself out, hit that apply button if this job resonates with you&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can find out more about life at SafetyCulture via Youtube , Twitter , Instagram and LinkedIn .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To all recruitment agencies, we do not accept resumes or partnership opportunities. Please do not forward resumes to SafetyCulture or any of our employees. We are not responsible for any fees associated with unsolicited resumes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This employer participates in E-Verify and will provide the federal government with your Form I-9 information to confirm that you are authorized to work in the U.S. If E-Verify cannot confirm that you are authorized to work, this employer is required to give you written instructions and an opportunity to contact Department of Homeland Security (DHS) or Social Security Administration (SSA) so you can begin to resolve the issue before the employer can take any action against you, including terminating your employment. Employers can only use E-Verify once you have accepted a job offer and completed the Form I-9. E-Verify Works for Everyone. For more information on E-Verify, or if you believe that your employer has violated its E-Verify responsibilities, please contact DHS: 888-897-7781 or dhs.gov/e-verify"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFMxR0B_JddtQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1688336869599/safetyculturehq_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=bVetXTTd_B_RNsqwmz4yCqOjKnu6E5bmRwhObcK9rj4', '2025-09-28T14:40:34.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recHddrivn6ZgJqSj', 'Euromonitor International', 'http://www.euromonitor.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/euromonitor-international', 'London, England, GB', 'Market Research', '1001 - 5000', '62', 'Euromonitor International is a growth-stage market research company (2,150 employees) with operations in Australia and Singapore, fitting the target size for external recruitment. The trigger role is ''Sales Director, APAC,'' which is a high-priority core sales position. The industry is market research/consulting, which is only an acceptable fit for commercial B2B tech recruitment (15 points). Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (General Manager, Sales Director, Regional Account Director) are present, providing strong access (max 20 points). However, there are no recent growth or hiring signals, and no recent funding or expansion activity, which limits the immediate recruitment opportunity. Overall, this is a medium-priority lead due to role and decision maker quality, but limited by industry fit and lack of growth signals.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nReleased a major industry resource, the \"Top Global Consumer Trends 2025\" whitepaper and hosted a related webinar in mid-2025, highlighting changing lifestyle and market trends for global business leaders[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Euromonitor International leads the world in data analytics and research into markets, industries, economies and consumers. We provide truly global insight and data on thousands of products and services; we are the first destination for organisations seeking growth. With our guidance, you can make bold, strategic decisions with confidence."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recHhOvuJvZbH8i57', 'Cresta', 'http://www.cresta.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cresta-inc', 'Sunnyvale, California', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '100', 'Cresta is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (AI-powered contact center software) with 201-500 employees, now operating in Australia with a new Melbourne office. They are actively hiring for Go-To-Market sales roles, including Strategic Sales Director, and have a Tier 1 decision maker (GM APAC) in-market. Recent Series D funding, regional leadership appointments, and explicit APAC expansion signal immediate and significant recruitment needs for sales talent. This is a top-priority, high-probability recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Cresta officially **opened its Melbourne office** as part of a major global expansion in September 2024, with the city explicitly highlighted as a strategic hub for the APAC region[1].  \n[REGIONAL] The expansion includes a direct focus on Asia-Pacific (APAC) markets, bringing Cresta’s AI-powered contact center and customer engagement solutions to local enterprises. Their platform is notably in use by a top APAC retailer for multilingual live support, indicating active regional deployments[1].  \n[GLOBAL] This move follows Cresta''s accelerated global push, with new offices in EMEA (London) and key regional leadership appointments linked to recent funding[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Melbourne office is led by Andrew Cannington, recently appointed **General Manager APAC**, based out of Melbourne. His immediate mandate includes scaling sales and customer delivery capability for regional enterprise clients[1].  \n[LOCAL] Melbourne listed as an official operating location on Cresta’s careers page, with associated opportunities in sales, solutions consulting, and technical roles, indicating local hiring activity since Q4 2024[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Cresta’s global headcount is at 250+ employees, with continued team expansion driven by recent capital and international growth mandates[2].  \n[REGIONAL] APAC hiring, especially for customer delivery and go-to-market (GTM) sales functions, is priority per leadership statements on APAC strategy[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] **Series D funding of $125M** closed in mid-2024, with express allocation for APAC and EMEA expansion[1][2]. Total funding for the company stands at $276M as of September 2024[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Successful APAC deployments include partnerships with top regional retailers for AI-powered multilingual support, highlighting the platform’s real-world traction in Australia and broader Asia-Pacific[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Cresta’s platform demonstrated customer results such as increased revenue (+20%), expanded manager span of control (+40%), and improved customer save rates (+56%) for global users, bolstering its commercial validation in Australia[1].  \n[LOCAL] Melbourne staff cite collaborative culture and strong career progression in recent testimonials[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] **Andrew Cannington** appointed General Manager APAC, based in Melbourne, in September 2024[1]. He is responsible for scaling the regional business and bringing Cresta’s AI contact center platform to the Australian market.  \n[GLOBAL] Executive leadership expanded post-Series D, with strategic roles focused on international growth, including APAC and EMEA[1].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Demand for **AI-driven customer engagement** and contact center software in Australia is accelerating, driven by large enterprises seeking operational efficiency and customer personalization. Melbourne is increasingly home to APAC hubs of US software firms pending favorable market conditions and local talent access[4].  \n[INDUSTRY] Competition for sales talent, solutions engineers, and AI specialists in Melbourne, VIC remains strong, particularly among SaaS vendors focused on enterprise customer acquisition and retention.\n\n**Scope indicators summary:**  \n- Melbourne office launched and operational, signaling deep local commitment [LOCAL][1][3].  \n- APAC strategy actively managed from Melbourne, with regionally relevant leadership and sales focus [REGIONAL][LOCAL][1].  \n- Series D fundraise and global expansion underpins ongoing growth and hiring [GLOBAL][2][1].  \n- Industry context for software development and AI-powered SaaS is highly favorable for expansion in Australia [INDUSTRY][4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Cresta is on a mission to turn every customer conversation into a competitive advantage by unlocking the true potential of the contact center. Our platform combines the best of AI and human intelligence to help contact centers discover customer insights and behavioral best practices, automate conversations and inefficient processes, and empower every team member to work smarter and faster. Born from the prestigious Stanford AI lab, Cresta''s co-founder and chairman is Sebastian Thrun, the genius behind Google X, Waymo, Udacity, and more. Our leadership also includes CEO, Ping Wu, the co-founder of Google Contact Center AI and Vertex AI platform, &amp;amp; co-founder, Tim Shi, an early member of Open AI.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’ve assembled a world-class team of AI and ML experts, go-to-market leaders, and top-tier investors including Andreessen Horowitz, Greylock Partners, Sequoia, and former AT&amp;amp;T CEO John Donovan. Our valued customers include brands like Intuit, Cox Communications, Hilton, and Carmax and we’ve been recognized by Forbes and Bain Consulting as one of the top private AI companies in the world.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Join us on this thrilling journey to revolutionize the workforce with AI. The future of work is here, and it''s at Cresta.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Strategic Sales Director you will focus on some of the largest companies in Australia, working on big strategic deals that will change the trajectory of the company. You’ll identify and articulate how Cresta can unlock significant value for our customers, build relationships with key executives and evangelize cutting edge AI technology. As an early member of the team at a growing startup, you’ll have the opportunity to help define our sales process, participate in regional expansion strategy and help build the APAC region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the sales experience while building and managing relationships with key decision-makers and executives &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Run complex sales cycles from initial contact to close&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect for new clients, design product presentations and business cases, develop and deliver proposals, negotiate and close contracts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a command of the Cresta product, the Contact Center market, our unique competitive differentiators, and our customers’ needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product, Marketing, Customer Success and Engineering to deliver an exceptional customer experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hit your number&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications We Value&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;7+ years of SaaS software sales experience at an enterprise level &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience negotiating, structuring and executing complex enterprise-level agreements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prior experience leading cross-functional teams through large deal close processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to articulate contractual, technical, and financial value points to customers, including executives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills with experience presenting to C-level executives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel up to 25%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We offer Cresta employees a variety of medical benefits designed to fit your stage of life&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible vacation time to promote a healthy work-life blend&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave to support you and your family&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Compensation for this position includes a base salary, variable (OTE), equity, and a variety of benefits. Actual base salaries will be based on candidate-specific factors, including experience, skillset, and location, and local minimum pay requirements as applicable. We are actively hiring for this role in Australia, and offer competitive local pay and benefits. Your recruiter can provide further details.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We have noticed a rise in recruiting impersonations across the industry, where scammers attempt to access candidates'' personal and financial information through fake interviews and offers. All Cresta recruiting email communications will always come from the @cresta.ai domain. Any outreach claiming to be from Cresta via other sources should be ignored. If you are uncertain whether you have been contacted by an official Cresta employee, reach out to recruiting@cresta.ai"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHdfq5NX-XSDw/company-logo_200_200/B56ZgJWEscHMAI-/0/1752503438463/cresta_inc_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=Gv2507j5lFsOyU1hRJcYc8MsaynMxKGYTCxs-dMX8z8', '2025-09-20T14:16:03.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recI4BFZfPQg7ESaj', 'Proofpoint', 'https://www.proofpoint.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/proofpoint', 'Sunnyvale, California', 'Computer and Network Security,Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '80', 'Proofpoint is a growth-stage cybersecurity SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) with active operations in Australia and Singapore, making it an ideal commercial fit. The filtered employee list includes multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Area VP ANZ, Regional Sales Directors, Senior Sales Managers, Enterprise Sales, Channel Managers), providing strong access for recruitment. The company is hiring for core sales roles such as Account Executive and Enterprise Sales, which are high-priority targets. Recent local growth signals include major partner expansion, flagship events, and increased channel activity, though no recent funding or leadership changes were reported. This positions Proofpoint as a strong, high-priority recruitment opportunity for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Hosted the inaugural **Proofpoint Protect Tour 2025 in Sydney** on 5 March 2025, a flagship event focused on human-centric security, cyber risks, and new solution showcases, with senior leaders and top partners participating[1]. \n\n[LOCAL] Released the **2025 Voice of the CISO report** in Sydney on 26 August 2025, highlighting heightened cyber risk awareness among Australian CISOs: 77% expect a material cyberattack in the coming year, with GenAI-related data loss a key concern[3].\n\n[REGIONAL] Recognized expanding partner ecosystem in Australia and New Zealand, with awards to major local partners for expanding Proofpoint''s footprint in 2024[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Expanded engagement with key Australian cybersecurity partners, including Lumen IT, The Missing Link, NTT Data, Security Centric, and NEXTGEN as key distributors and system integrators across Australia (awards acknowledged at Sydney event)[1].\n\n[LOCAL] Area Vice President for Australia & New Zealand, **Crispin Kerr**, continues to oversee business expansion and local go-to-market strategy, signaling ongoing focus on local sales and partner activities[2].\n\n[REGIONAL] Strengthened go-to-market strategy in Australia and APAC via the revamped **Proofpoint Element Partner Program**, providing enhanced resources and incentives for managed service providers, MSSPs, distributors, and value-added resellers in the region to scale their co-selling activities[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding rounds or major financial milestones were disclosed for the Australia or APAC region in the last 12 months, and no local or regional investment announcements were found in the available results.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Recognized top local partners at the Sydney Proofpoint Protect Tour 2025, including **Lumen IT**, **The Missing Link**, **NTT Data Inc.**, **Security Centric**, and **NEXTGEN** for accelerating Proofpoint solution adoption and supporting customers across Australia and New Zealand[1].\n\n[REGIONAL] Accelerated channel marketing initiatives and expanded partner enablement across Australia as part of the Element Partner Program, driving “record-breaking success” and higher demand for Proofpoint’s integrated cyber and compliance solutions in 2024–2025[1].\n\n[LOCAL] Fostered closer collaboration between Australian CISOs and Proofpoint through knowledge-sharing and skills certification initiatives at the Sydney Protect Tour and follow-on customer events[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] **Crispin Kerr** remains the Area Vice President, Australia & New Zealand, directly accountable for local and regional sales growth. No recent leadership changes for the regional executive or sales team were reported in the available results[2].\n\n[GLOBAL] No major global C-suite changes with APAC/ANZ impacts have been announced in the last year.\n\n---\n\nThis synthesis is based primarily on [LOCAL] and [REGIONAL] sources—chiefly, Proofpoint’s flagship Sydney event and local partner awards, with supplementary input from APAC-wide channel initiatives and executive leadership confirmations. No significant company funding, executive transition, or office expansion announcements have been reported for Sydney or ANZ in the public domain over the past 6–12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are the leader in human-centric cybersecurity. Half a million customers, including 87 of the Fortune 100, rely on Proofpoint to protect their organizations. We’re driven by a mission to stay ahead of bad actors and safeguard the digital world. Join us in our pursuit to defend data and protect people.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;How We Work&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Proofpoint, you’ll be part of a global team that breaks barriers to redefine cybersecurity, guided by our BRAVE core values Bold in how we dream and innovate, Responsive to feedback, challenges, and opportunities, Accountable for results and best-in-class outcomes, Visionary in future-focused problem-solving, Exceptional in execution and impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate Overview&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Proofpoint is a leading cybersecurity company protecting organisations greatest assets and biggest risks vulnerabilities in people. With an integrated suite of cloud-based solutions, Proofpoint helps companies around the world stop targeted threats, safeguard their data, and make their users more resilient against cyber attacks. Leading organisations of all sizes, including more than half of the Fortune 1000, rely on Proofpoint for people-centric security and compliance solutions mitigating their most critical risks across email, the cloud, social media, and the web.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are singularly devoted to helping our customers protect their greatest assets and biggest security risk their people. That’s why we’re a leader in next-generation cybersecurity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Protection Starts with People.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;An excellent hands-on opportunity at a fast-growing, US-based software cybersecurity company that is rapidly expanding internationally. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As our Business Development Manager, you will lead our BDR teams in Australia, New Zealand, SE Asia and Korea, and India to lead both inbound and outbound BDR activities to generate quality pipeline (qualified meetings) for the APAC sales team. Our team is composed of in-house BDRs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this role, you will work closely with the APAC sales leadership team as well as the demand generation and field marketing team in region; this is a unique opportunity for an experienced B2B inside sales leader to continue building Proofpoint international presence and accelerate our growth. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our next leader should have a proven track record of success, a verifiable history of exceeding inside sales KPIs, and the aptitude and attitude to make a difference in a fast-paced environment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Orchestrate and manage the Business Development team to ensure we meet our lead follow-up SLAs, meet our activity KPIs and ultimately over-achieve our objectives of qualified meetings for each region &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Onboard, coach and mentor new BDRs so that they ramp-up quickly and over-achieve their quarterly targets (# qualified meetings) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide and deliver continuous training plan including role plays on a quarterly basis. Organise and deliver training material (call scripts, FAQs, Battle cards) for all Proofpoint priority sales plays &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Streamline, optimise and localise outreach sequences to be used by BDRs in their prospection efforts in collaboration with the demand generation team  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure sales and marketing interlock, and actively participate to regional sales meetings &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Field Marketing to ensure every member of the BDR team is fed with the right volume of Marketing Qualified Leads and Marketing Qualified Contacts &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop cross-sell/up-sell as well as competitive take-out BDR programs to expend our footprint. Develop an account based BDR strategy. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Analysis of team and campaign performance and recommendations for optimisation and future enhancements. Manage outreach and SFDC dashboards to track all activity and performance KPIs &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide monthly and quarterly regional business reporting and analysis on all programs and campaigns run in region &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring To The Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Related Business Development &amp;amp; Demand Generation leadership experience in SaaS, Cloud or IT Security enterprise software &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Email automation (Outreach) and CRM (Salesforce) experience required  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with BDR Account Based Marketing methodology and tactics &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to form strong partnerships internally with sales stakeholders &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to train, coach, motivate and lead a team of young sales professionals &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Innovative and creative thinker who contributes valuable new ideas and insights &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilience, drive and adaptability to thrive in a fast-changing market &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI Tools &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The candidate will travel across the region as appropriate (20% of time). Occasional travel to the US as required for Sales Kick-Off. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Proofpoint&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Protecting people is at the heart of our award-winning lineup of cybersecurity solutions, and the people who work here are the key to our success. We’re a customer-focused and a driven-to-win organization with leading-edge products. We are an inclusive, diverse, multinational company that believes in culture fit, but more importantly ‘culture-add’, and we strongly encourage people from all walks of life to apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in hiring the best and the brightest to help cultivate our culture of collaboration and appreciation. Apply today and explore your future at Proofpoint! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Why Proofpoint? At Proofpoint, we believe that an exceptional career experience includes a comprehensive compensation and benefits package. Here are just a few reasons you’ll love working with us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Competitive compensation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Comprehensive benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Learning &amp;amp; Development We are committed to the growth and development of our team members, offering a range of programs including leadership and professional development workshops, stretch project assignments, and mentoring opportunities to help employees reach their full potential.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Flexible work environment [Remote options, hybrid schedules, flexible hours, etc.].&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Annual wellness and community outreach days&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Always on recognition for your contributions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Global collaboration and networking opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Our Culture&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our culture is rooted in values that inspire belonging, empower purpose and drive success-every day, for everyone. We encourage applications from individuals of all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. If you need accommodation during the application or interview process, please reach out to accessibility@proofpoint.com. How to Apply Interested? Submit your application here https //www.proofpoint.com/us/company/careers. We can’t wait to hear from you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFEzwJn3C-nDQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1726764831463/proofpoint_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=aStCpDbDFQICbN9BUt0d1yiPC2JKrPbtDYfj8bIspj0', '2025-09-23T14:33:30.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recIF7ycOHjDWWUUc', 'Onside', 'https://getonside.com/', 'https://nz.linkedin.com/company/onside-technology', 'Christchurch, Canterbury', 'Software Development', '11-50 employees', '80', 'Onside is a small growth-stage software development company (11-50 employees) with a strong commercial B2B fit in AgriTech, actively hiring Sales Development Representatives (SDRs) in Australia. The presence of a Head of Commercial (VP Sales equivalent, Tier 2 decision maker) provides direct access for recruitment discussions. While there are no recent funding rounds or leadership changes, strong local growth signals—including a growing Melbourne team, major client wins, and ongoing regional expansion—indicate a high likelihood to use external recruitment for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Onside maintains an office in Melbourne, VIC, focusing on supporting Australian agribusinesses with its rural operations software[1]. Over the past year, the platform has highlighted case studies from large Australian producers such as Van Dairy, indicating growing adoption in Victoria and broader AU[3]. [REGIONAL] Onside''s software is now trusted by over 16,000 agribusinesses across Australia and New Zealand as of mid-2025, evidencing strong regional market presence and ongoing expansion[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Melbourne office is home to a growing team including engineers, designers, and commercial leads, underpinning local capability for customer success and technical support[1]. [LOCAL] Key Australian clients—including Van Dairy—demonstrate penetration into the Victorian agricultural sector[3]. [REGIONAL] Active hiring for sales and GTM roles (such as Sales Development Representatives) continues in Australia, supporting further regional scaling and market capture[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Onside remains at the seed stage and has not publicly announced new funding rounds in the past 12 months[1]. No major Series A/B/C activity has been reported during this timeframe[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Successful onboarding of major Australian enterprises like Van Dairy in VIC, accompanied by glowing client case studies and operational impact stories[3]. [REGIONAL] Significant growth in platform usage, with the Onside network logging over 3 million digital check-ins across 21,000+ rural properties throughout ANZ in the past year[1]. [GLOBAL] The platform continues to leverage biosecurity and compliance features, differentiating itself as an industry-leading solution for agricultural safety and rural operations[1][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] No publicly disclosed senior executive appointments, departures, or leadership transitions specific to Melbourne, Australia, or the ANZ region in the last 12 months. Existing organizational structure focuses on cross-regional commercial and technical leadership across Christchurch HQ and Melbourne offices[1].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian software development sector, especially in AgriTech, has seen accelerated digitization of rural workflows—driven by compliance, biosecurity, and operational efficiency needs among farms and growers. Solutions supporting safety management, contractor onboarding, and audit readiness remain highly sought after by scale producers in Victoria and across AU in 2025[4][5]. High-growth Australian providers compete by offering streamlined integrations, real-time data capture, and mobile-first interfaces serving the primary industries."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;One of Asia-Pacific''s top 100 startups (Forbes Asia 100 To Watch, 2025), and recognised as Christchurch''s fastest-growing tech company (Deloitte Fast 50, 2024) we''re scaling rapidly - and looking for a Senior Account Executive to help fuel our next stage of growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Onside is a SaaS company trusted by 16,000+ agribusinesses, industry bodies, and government agencies across Australia and New Zealand to manage safety, compliance, and biosecurity - making rural industries stronger and more resilient every day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This mid-market sales role puts you in the virtual room with senior decision-makers across agribusiness. You''ll own the full sales cycle - prospecting, pipeline, and close - across ANZ, with ~120-day cycles. It''s complex SaaS, made simple and valuable for customers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Every deal you close strengthens Onside''s mission to protect the world''s food supply. And with 91% revenue growth in three years, there''s clear runway to grow your career as we scale into larger markets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you''ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the entire sales journey - from outreach to close&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect, qualify, and build a healthy pipeline of ANZ mid-market accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell strategically to senior stakeholders in agribusiness/food production&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product, Marketing &amp;amp; CS to drive Onside''s success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Operate with autonomy, influence outcomes and act like an owner&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Full-cycle SaaS sales experience, in mid-market or commercial segments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fluency in SaaS fundamentals - ARR, MRR, subscription models, solution selling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence solving complex customer problems with software - and making it simple for the customer&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive to prospect, commercial sharpness, and a track-record of closing quality deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High standards, high ownership, and a hunger to grow alongside other high-performers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;50:50 base + uncapped commission - you control your rewards&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid, dog-friendly Richmond office, close to public transport&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with leaders who''ve scaled SaaS companies at speed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A culture of clarity, rapid execution, and trust from day one &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Award-winning company - Forbes Asia 100 To Watch (2025), Deloitte Fast 50 (Winner - Fastest Growing Tech in Christchurch, 2024)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEFZFVm0qEWsw/company-logo_200_200/B56ZiXogCMHQAM-/0/1754890634340/onside_technology_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=WwdqPFDQ-QX8oiEgQvzXHLwDZ602IcgK61wk8pWGoPk', '2025-09-20T02:48:01.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recIFqAZL6qIrGiRd', 'Deputy', 'https://www.deputy.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/deputyapp', 'Sydney, New South Wales', 'Software Development,IT Services and IT Consulting', '201-500 employees', '81', 'Deputy is a growth-stage SaaS company (201-500 employees) in core commercial B2B tech, actively expanding its platform and launching new products in Australia. The presence of Tier 1 (VP of Sales) and Tier 2 (Sales Director, Manager Sales & Sales Development Teams) decision makers provides strong access for recruitment opportunities. The most relevant sales role is Senior Account Executive, a high-priority core role. Multiple strong growth signals are present, including a major product launch and active market expansion. This combination makes Deputy a high-priority recruitment opportunity for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Deputy launched **Deputy Payroll in Australia** on June 3, 2025, from its headquarters in Sydney, NSW, offering a purpose-built solution for shift-based businesses. The launch closed the loop for clients, integrating compliance, scheduling, timesheets, and payroll in one platform and marking a significant expansion of Deputy’s product suite in Australia[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Deputy is actively promoting and implementing its expanded platform capabilities in Sydney, targeting verticals including hospitality, healthcare, retail, construction, and supermarkets. The launch is built on customer feedback and collaboration with local payroll officers, HR, and business owners, indicating a focus on solving Australian operational complexities at scale[1][2].\n[LOCAL] The company highlights its **multi-entity payroll** feature (managing separate business units/ABNs under one account) and rapid payroll processing—customers report up to 80% faster pay cycles—suggesting strong uptake among Sydney-based enterprises and multi-site operators[1].\n[LOCAL] Implementation campaigns and AI-powered scheduling features are currently emphasized for Sydney and national clients, driving increased interest from businesses aiming to streamline operations and ensure Fair Work compliance[2].\n[GLOBAL] Deputy continues to scale globally from its Sydney HQ, supporting enterprise operations with robust API integrations, security, and configurable workflows for workforce management across multiple geographies[2][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds or financial milestones for Deputy in the last 6–12 months were found in the Sydney or regional context. Previous global capital rounds were used to support product expansion, including Australian payroll capabilities, but no Sydney-specific investments are publicly reported for 2025[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] The **Australia Payroll launch** is highlighted as a key achievement for Deputy in Sydney, transforming it from a workforce management solution to a complete people platform for shift-based businesses. This launch responds to direct requests from Australian customers for an all-in-one solution tailored to complex award interpretation and compliance needs[1].\n[LOCAL] The new Payroll module offers enhanced compliance features with configurable pay rules and automated award interpretation, supporting Sydney’s extensive hospitality, healthcare, and retail sectors[1][2].\n[GLOBAL] Deputy’s platform is widely recognized for its fast implementation, AI-powered labor cost insights, and end-to-end workforce management capabilities, with thousands of businesses joining monthly for its all-in-one solution[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL/SYDNEY] **Silvija Martincevic**, CEO of Deputy, has been prominently quoted in Sydney platform launch communications, but no specific leadership hires, promotions, or departures within the Sydney team or key APAC sales/revenue/people roles have been reported over the past 6–12 months[1].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian software development and IT services sector is experiencing strong growth, particularly with demand for **compliance-driven HR and payroll solutions** among businesses with large shift-based workforces. There is increasing adoption of AI-powered tools and cloud SaaS platforms for operational efficiency and award interpretation, especially in hospitality, retail, healthcare, and construction in Sydney and nationwide[2].\n[INDUSTRY] Competition is increasing among SaaS providers in workforce management, with focus shifting to integrated solutions that deliver rapid payroll, compliance automation, and seamless scheduling for distributed teams. Deputy is positioned as a leader within this niche, especially following its recent payroll product extension tailored for the Local/ANZ market[1][2][3].\n\nIf more detail is required on expansion, hiring, specific partnerships, or executive movements in Sydney/ANZ, please specify which category is of highest priority."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Deputy is a global SaaS remote-first workforce management company with hubs in Sydney, Melbourne, San Francisco and London, plus team members working remotely across the United States. Our platform serves over 1.5 million workers and 375,000 workplaces across 100+ countries. We are backed by top global investors and recently achieved Unicorn status.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Deputy, we’re improving the world of work, one shift at a time, for 80% of the world’s workforce: hourly workers. These are the dedicated employees who keep our world running – from baristas to nurses, cleaners to delivery drivers, florists to factory workers. Despite their vital role in society, most workplace technology has focused on those workers who sit behind a desk, but at Deputy, we transform the frontline. When businesses use Deputy, their workplaces thrive – the business is more profitable, compliant, and productive, while the workers are more engaged and happier at work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you’re passionate about creating solutions that put people first and helping businesses and their teams thrive, join us at Deputy and make an impact where it matters most!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our Customer Success team is passionate, creative, and customer-centric. We help advise and guide a wide variety of global customers from industries like healthcare to entertainment to retail and many more. Our key focus is empowering customers to utilize Deputy’s tools to achieve strategic outcomes and help them grow their businesses into thriving workplaces. As a team we value the diverse perspectives and experiences each team member brings to the table and are looking for individuals who are passionate about having a huge part in building a best in class experience for our customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Senior Account Manager, you will focus on the commercial aspect of the customer partnership. You will proactively manage customer relationships around renewals and expansion conversations while becoming a trusted advisor to these customers. You will identify and understand new business opportunities that add value to your customer’s business and align Deputy with their strategic plans to build a stronger partnership. You are a highly motivated self-starter looking to engage and manage customers to ensure long term retention.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage with multiple customers ranging from Mid-Market to Enterprise to build a stronger partnership between their business and Deputy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the relationship with key decision makers to drive renewal, expansion, and upsell conversations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use data and work closely with Customer Success Managers to identify trends with accounts and strategic growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive higher levels of adoption for customers who are underutilising the Deputy solution&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a thorough understanding of a customer’s business needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage sales funnel of renewals and expansion opportunities while working closely with legal, sales and marketing on commercial aspects of partnerships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be proactive about flagging customer risk, issues and threats&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain knowledge of trends in workforce management, and time &amp;amp; attendance industry&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuously analyse and deliver feedback to leadership teams and participate in process improvements as well as optimisation of existing procedures&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of B2B Account Management experience (managing a book of revenue and upselling)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation skills and ability to navigate multilayer organisations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Results oriented and demonstrate integrity with a proven and consistent record of top performance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and assess client objectives and create solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, in particular a strong telephone presence and web presentation skills &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong technical aptitude, previous use of Salesforce or similar CRM system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness and ability to meet with key accounts face to face (when safe to do so)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Perks&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Enjoy a flexible remote-first work policy (with a work-from-home stipend to set you up for success!)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Own A piece of Deputy via our Employee Share Ownership Plan (ESOP)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Take paid parental leave to support you and your family&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Stay protected with Group Salary Continuance Insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Access support through our Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Enjoy additional leave days — including study assistance, celebration days and volunteering&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Join our global working groups focused on collaboration, belonging and connection&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Get creative at our annual Hackathons&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Take advantage of our novated leasing for electric vehicles, internet reimbursement and more!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Deputy believes in equal opportunity and that inclusiveness and diversity promotes innovation. Our global team members are from a variety of cultures. And we welcome different perspective and skills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEcLng7pJK8Ow/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1686767983785/deputyapp_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=-GVJpxMuWtK5GNMqgQhLIe5lDcA-DfYqmTyWM4BgkRI', '2025-09-20T14:13:42.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recIU5FVfXbixJiOn', 'OPSWAT', 'https://www.opswat.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/opswat', 'Tampa, Florida', 'Computer and Network Security', '501-1,000 employees', '81', 'OPSWAT is a growth-stage computer and network security company (501-1,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively expanding its presence in Australia through major cybersecurity events and a new ANZ distribution partnership. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Regional Sales Directors, Regional Sales Managers, VP APJ) in Australia and Singapore provides direct access for sales recruitment. While no explicit active sales role was cited, ongoing regional expansion, channel investment, and repeated event participation signal strong hiring probability for core sales roles. These factors make OPSWAT a high-priority recruitment opportunity for commercial sales roles in APAC.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] OPSWAT is exhibiting at major Australian cybersecurity events such as the Security Exhibition & Conference in Sydney from 21-23 August 2024, highlighting a direct presence and active marketing in the Greater Sydney Area[2].  \n[LOCAL] OPSWAT is also participating in the OT Cyber Resilience Summit NSW in Sydney on June 17, 2025, reinforcing ongoing engagement with NSW-based stakeholders[5].  \n[REGIONAL] OPSWAT has appointed Sektor Cyber as its distributor for Australia and New Zealand as of April 2025, increasing market reach and local representation in the ANZ region[3].  \n[REGIONAL] The company is a regular exhibitor at key APAC events, such as AUSCERT 2025 (May 2025, Gold Coast) and AISA CyberCon Canberra (March 2025), presenting its CIP (critical infrastructure protection) solutions and engaging with regional enterprise customers in Australia[1][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Multiple event participations in Sydney and wider NSW across 2024-2025 indicate focus on local sales, marketing, and technical enablement[2][5].  \n[REGIONAL] The 2025 partnership with Sektor Cyber enables broader ANZ coverage and likely signals ongoing recruitment and channel investment in the region[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Significant expansion efforts such as the opening of a new cybersecurity lab and office in Arlington, VA (May 2025) demonstrate strong corporate momentum, which historically precedes regional hiring and GTM expansion[5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No explicit funding rounds in the past 6-12 months were cited in available results; OPSWAT’s expansion activities and increased global footprint signal healthy financial status and reinvestment, particularly in international and government markets[3][5].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Sektor Cyber distribution partnership (April 2025) was positioned as “strengthening OPSWAT’s presence in the APAC region,” responding to increased compliance requirements and critical infrastructure legislation such as Australia’s Security of Critical Infrastructure (SOCI) Act[3].  \n[GLOBAL] OPSWAT MetaDefender Unidirectional Security Gateway achieved Common Criteria EAL4+ certification, underlining its fit for highly regulated and critical sectors globally and regionally[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL/GLOBAL] No specific Sydney/AU/ANZ executive appointments or departures were reported in the provided results. Recent global leadership visibility includes CEO Benny Czarny and SVP International James Neilson participating in thought leadership around industry transformation, with Neilson addressing financial sector threats[5].\n\nSummary of Scope Used:\n- Most details are LOCAL (Sydney, NSW, Australia)\n- Additional insight from REGIONAL (ANZ/APAC) and GLOBAL developments augments local context where direct data is limited\n- No significant recent funding or Sydney-specific leadership changes found in the past 6-12 months in provided sources"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"OPSWAT, a global leader in IT, OT, and ICS critical infrastructure cybersecurity, delivers an end-to-end platform that gives public and private sector organizations and enterprises the critical advantage needed to protect their complex networks, secure their devices, and ensure compliance. Over the last 20 years our commitment to innovative technology has earned the trust of more than 1,700 organizations, governments, and institutions globally, solidifying our role in protecting the world’s critical infrastructure and securing our way of life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;OPSWAT is looking for a seasoned and technically strong &lt;strong&gt;Regional Sales Manager - BFSI – ANZ &lt;/strong&gt;. The Regional Sales Manager’s primary role is to expand the footprint of OPSWAT’s customer base primarily via the recruitment and close management of a value-added channel ecosystem, while, in parallel, actively participate in customer-facing actions (from prospecting to opportunity creation, advancement, and closure) alongside channel partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities of the &lt;strong&gt;Regional Sales Manager&lt;/strong&gt; will include learning the OPSWAT technology, developing and executing a strategic account plan aimed at deploying our &lt;strong&gt;Cybersecurity platforms&lt;/strong&gt; and solutions in the &lt;strong&gt;Public and BFSI Sector (State Government, Local councils, Universities, Banking, Insurance, Superannuation funds, Insurance and Legal&lt;/strong&gt;) building relationships within a target account and with channel/SI partners; leveraging company resources and closing deals and celebrating successes. The position reports to the Regional Sales Director and will have daily interface /coordination/collaboration with Channel Manager, SDR and APAC Marketing. The ideal candidate will have a multi-year track record of consistently exceeding sales quotas, while accurately forecasting and selling cybersecurity solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position will be based in &lt;strong&gt;Sydney covering NSW, QLD, ACT Gov and NT&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strategically target business opportunities that leverage high value use cases, in key verticals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute sales strategies and tactics to sell OPSWAT products, solutions, and services to exceed your sales quotas&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communicate value propositions to clients that speak intimately to their needs and requirements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize client-centric, solutions-oriented selling strategies and hunter’s mentality to identify, qualify, convert enterprise sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively articulate financial ROI/TCO value, and build value throughout the negotiation process&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain extensive account and opportunity detail in Salesforce CRM, including account win plans, customer touch points, sales inhibitors, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Forecast and report revenue projections accurately to management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Overachieve on annual quota, measured quarterly&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need From You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have 7-10 years of experience successfully selling Cybersecurity technology products and solutions to enterprise business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have a bachelor’s degree and equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;English skills: conversational skills are a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have a successful track record selling complex-solutions directly to enterprise customers and through Channel/SI Partners&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’re persuasive and have excellent negotiation and presentation skills. You can effectively communicate with both technology-oriented and senior business executives at the “C” level and are comfortable articulating the technical and business value of the OPSWAT platforms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Your work is a mix of strategic and proactive account activity, and you have a demonstrated ability of uncovering, qualifying, developing, and closing new accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to set goals, prioritize tasks, and achieve success with minimal oversight in a sometimes-ambiguous work environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You keep your pipeline accurate, and your forecast updated for management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You possess, at minimum, a fundamental understanding of security threats, solutions, and security tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have excellent time management skills, and work with high levels of autonomy and self-direction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’re highly competitive, ramp quickly, are extremely adaptive, and pride yourself on exceeding sales goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You can travel as necessary to your assigned accounts, and to Company meetings.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly ethical and professional personal conduct.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;OPSWAT is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to providing an environment where equal employment opportunities are extended to all employees and applicants, free of discrimination and harassment of any type. All employment decisions are based on individual qualifications, job requirements, and business needs without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other category protected by federal, state, or local laws.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Recruiting Agencies: we do not accept unsolicited resumes from third party agencies for any of our open positions. To submit resumes for our jobs, there must be a recruiting contract approved by our legal team and endorsed by both parties. We are currently not accepting additional 3rd party agencies at this time."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFb_JWJK4Sazg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1686761865930/opswat_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=gQF-WOx_xAwRuBF1V-JsPFxDdk44Mbt5xjlOFTLIt54', '2025-09-20T14:17:31.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recIq6Xw0kxoo8A5z', 'WEKA', 'http://www.weka.io', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/weka-io', 'Campbell, California', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '92', 'WEKA is a growth-stage software company (201-500 employees) actively hiring for a Senior Sales Engineer role in Australia, reflecting ongoing GTM and technical sales expansion in the region. The company operates in the core commercial B2B tech space, with a strong fit for external recruitment. Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present (Regional Sales Managers in both Australia and Singapore), providing direct access to hiring authorities. Multiple strong growth signals are evident, including recent Series E funding, major product launches, executive leadership appointments, and a doubling of revenue, all supporting immediate and high-value recruitment opportunities for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] No public reports within the last 12 months of new Sydney office openings or major Australia-specific events.  \n[REGIONAL] WEKA is actively hiring for sales and technical roles across Australia, including a Senior Sales Engineer position posted for remote work throughout the country in 2025, indicating ongoing expansion of GTM and solution engineering presence in AU/NZ[4].  \n[GLOBAL] WEKA debuted major product developments in 2024-2025—including NeuralMesh Axon for exascale AI deployments and expanded NVIDIA integrations—which drive global and regional relevance for AI/data-intensive enterprise markets[2]. WEKA surpassed $100M ARR in fiscal 2024 and underwent strategic restructuring of go-to-market functions to accelerate innovation and regional scale[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Actively recruiting sales-focused roles in Australia throughout 2025, specifically targeting enterprise solution engineering and GTM capabilities in Sydney and broader AU regions[4].  \n[REGIONAL] Increasing GTM headcount in APAC as part of company-wide hiring push, with career postings highlighting Australia and remote ANZ positions[4][3].  \n[GLOBAL] WEKA doubled revenue for the third consecutive year (2024), expanded R&D and customer-facing teams across all business functions, and is currently advertising numerous open roles as part of its international growth trajectory[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Completed Series E funding in fiscal 2024, achieving a $1.6B valuation and unicorn status. Investment proceeds are being deployed for international expansion, including APAC markets[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] No publicly disclosed APAC/Australia enterprise awards or local partnerships in the past year.  \n[GLOBAL] Named a 2025 Customers’ Choice in Gartner Peer Insights for File & Object Storage Platforms[2]. Recognized as a Visionary in the 2024 Gartner Magic Quadrant for File & Object Storage[2]. Recently launched NeuralMesh Axon and WEKApod Appliances to support AI workloads in enterprise and research sectors globally[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] In Q2 2025, WEKA bolstered its executive leadership with new appointments in CRO, CPO, and CSO roles, aimed at accelerating global/regional revenue and operational growth[2]. Meini Heuberger was named CFO in June 2025[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Lauren Vaccarello, a software industry luminary, was appointed as WEKA’s first CMO in September 2024 with remit covering strategic growth, including APAC[2].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Software development in Australia is being shaped by rapid enterprise adoption of AI/ML and high-performance data analytics, resulting in strong demand for data platform vendors adaptable to hybrid cloud environments. Market growth is concentrated in Sydney, with increased focus on sales engineering and technical GTM roles to support the AI-driven transformation in the region[5].\n\n**Summary:**  \nWEKA, headquartered in Campbell, CA, is actively scaling its presence in Australia and APAC, with ongoing recruitment for key sales and engineering roles—especially in Sydney—as part of a broader international growth strategy. Recent product and executive developments support expansion in AI/data-centric enterprise markets, while strong funding and industry validation underpin regional ambitions. No evidence of a physical Sydney office, but local hiring signals a strengthening footprint in the Australian enterprise software sector."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"WEKA is transforming how organizations build, run, and scale AI and accelerated compute workflows with NeuralMesh™, our intelligent, adaptive mesh storage system. Unlike traditional data infrastructures, which become more fragile as compute environments grow and performance demands increase, NeuralMesh becomes faster, stronger, and more efficient as it scales, providing a flexible, adaptable foundation for enterprise and agentic AI innovation that maximizes GPU utilization, accelerates time to first token, and lowers the cost of innovation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;WEKA is a pre-IPO, growth-stage company backed by world-class venture capital investors and AI infrastructure industry leaders. Our technology, purpose-built for AI, has garnered over 140 patents and is trusted by more than 30% of Fortune 50 enterprises, as well as the world’s leading hyperscalers, neoclouds, and AI innovators. Our team is customer-obsessed and works accountably, boldly, and collaboratively to ensure their success. If we sound like your kind of people, join us!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s Cool About This Job&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for a proactive and strategic Sales Development Representative (SDR) to join our high-performing sales team. In this role, you will be responsible for sourcing and building a robust sales pipeline, focusing on Fortune 500 companies, AI native companies as well as foundation model builders. You will be tasked with opening new business opportunities with your assigned accounts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will be responsible for APAC markets and be based in Singapore or Sydney. Your role will be focused around uncovering opportunities for AI projects within APAC.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities Include&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pipeline Development: &lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and engage with potential clients through cold outreach, including emails, calls, and social media. Research and build targeted lists of Fortune 500 companies and AI factories that align with our ideal customer profile.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strategy and Collaboration: Work closely with Account Executives to develop and execute account penetration strategies. Collaborate with the sales team to refine outreach messaging and improve conversion rates.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Market and Competitive Analysis:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gain a deep understanding of our AI solutions and their value propositions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay informed about the competitive landscape and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop expertise in the typical AI infrastructure and challenges faced by companies in your assigned vertical.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partnership Relationship Development&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise and develop partnerships with OEMs and hardware manufacturers like Dell and NVIDIA to help drive pipeline for WEKA in APAC.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationship Building:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with key decision-makers within target accounts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage with prospects to understand their needs, pain points, and business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualification and Handoff:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualify outbound leads based on their fit and interest.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Schedule meetings and product demonstrations with qualified leads.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure a smooth handoff of qualified opportunities to Account Executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pipeline Management:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records in our CRM system.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track and report on sales activities, pipeline progress, and key metrics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuous Improvement:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine and optimize outreach strategies based on performance data and feedback.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide insights and recommendations to the sales and product teams to enhance our offerings and market positioning.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Education:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree in Business, Marketing, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in outbound sales development, lead generation, or a related role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in the tech industry, preferably in AI or deeptech, is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skills:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong research and analytical abilities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficient in using CRM software (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot) and sales engagement tools (e.g., Outreach, SalesLoft).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and execute strategic outreach plans.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Native level of English required.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attributes:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated, proactive, and results-driven.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills and a strategic mindset.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Passion for AI and a deep curiosity about industry trends and technologies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How We Work: The WEKA Way&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Accountable: We take full ownership, always–even when things don’t go as planned. We lead with integrity, show up with responsibility &amp;amp; ownership, and hold ourselves and each other to the highest standards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Brave: We question the status quo, push boundaries, and take smart risks when needed. We welcome challenges and embrace debates as opportunities for growth, turning courage into fuel for innovation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Collaborative: True collaboration isn’t only about working together. It’s about lifting one another up to succeed collectively. We are team-oriented and we communicate with empathy and respect. We challenge each other and conduct positive conflict resolution. We are being transparent about our goals and the results we achieve. Together, we’re unstoppable. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Customer Centric: Our customers are at the heart of everything we do. We actively listen and prioritize the success of our customers, and every decision we make is driven by how we can better serve, support, and empower them to succeed. When our customers win, we win.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concerned you don’t meet every qualification? Don’t let it stop you from applying!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Studies have shown that traditionally underrepresented groups may be less likely to apply for jobs if they don’t meet every qualification specified. WEKA is committed to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace. If you are excited about this position but are concerned your past work experience doesn’t match up perfectly with the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway – you may be just the right candidate for this or other roles at WEKA.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;WEKA is an equal opportunity employer that prohibits discrimination and harassment of any kind. We provide equal opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws. This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation, and training."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQElJe_74N1hfw/company-logo_200_200/B56ZeEyoT1HoAM-/0/1750279554699/weka_io_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=j0-C8uNzoXmWRQtZblMNdxSfnyu3wzVdLzxTCd-yFsI', '2025-09-20T06:13:19.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recJ65Xu23GC2TmCl', 'Trustwave, A LevelBlue Company', 'http://www.trustwave.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/trustwave', 'Chicago, Illinois', 'Computer and Network Security,IT Services and IT Consulting,Technology, Information and Internet', '501-1,000 employees', '64', 'Trustwave, A LevelBlue Company, is a growth-stage cybersecurity and IT services provider (501-1,000 employees) with active operations and expansion focus in Australia and APAC. The most relevant recent sales-related role is ''Director of Sales - APAC,'' which, while senior, is not a direct core sales hiring trigger (e.g., SDR, AE). The industry fit is strong secondary tech (cybersecurity/IT services). Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including the Director of Sales and regional consulting leaders, providing good access for recruitment discussions. The recent acquisition and regional expansion signal moderate growth, but there are no explicit new sales/GTM hires or funding rounds. Overall, this is a medium-priority opportunity with potential for future sales hiring needs as integration and expansion continue.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[GLOBAL] Trustwave was acquired by LevelBlue, with the transaction completed and announced publicly in August 2025[2][3]. This creates the world’s largest pure-play Managed Security Services Provider (MSSP), combining Trustwave’s managed detection and response (MDR), offensive security, and compliance services with LevelBlue’s AI-powered security and consulting offerings[1][2]. [REGIONAL] The acquisition is explicitly stated to enable broader and deeper service offerings and delivery capability across APAC and Australia, with direct and channel relationships aimed at various industries and government clients[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] The merger is expected to grow LevelBlue/Trustwave’s capability and market reach throughout APAC, including Australia, via expanded consulting, managed security, and incident response services[3]. This includes leveraging the Trustwave SpiderLabs research team and the Fusion Intelligent Security Operations Platform, which are core to regional offerings[2][3]. [GLOBAL] LevelBlue has also completed acquisitions of additional cybersecurity consulting groups such as Stroz Friedberg and Elysium Digital in 2025 to further strengthen global and regional delivery scale[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No explicit mention of new funding rounds. However, the acquisition of Trustwave by LevelBlue is described as a strategic consolidation, with undisclosed financial terms[1]. This follows a string of acquisitions by LevelBlue, indicating robust financial resources backing expanded operations[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] The combination is positioned to increase penetration into the government and enterprise sectors in Australia and APAC, leveraging global FedRAMP and StateRAMP authorizations to serve critical infrastructure clients[1][3]. [GLOBAL] Trustwave remains recognized for its industry-leading SpiderLabs research group and the Fusion platform, now integrated with LevelBlue’s AI Threat Detection Platform for improved threat visibility and response globally and regionally[2][3]. [REGIONAL] The company emphasizes integrated Microsoft Security services as a focus for the ANZ and larger APAC market[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] Eric Harmon continues to serve as Chief Executive Officer of Trustwave under the new combined structure[3]. No specific mention of new appointments, departures, or Melbourne/AU-local sales or GTM hires in the latest cycle; leadership focus is on post-merger integration and service delivery globally and in all key regions[3]. [GLOBAL] Bob McCullen is Chairman and CEO of parent company LevelBlue and is providing strategic direction for all regional operations, including Australia[1][2].\n\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] There is no specific public announcement of new sales/GTM hires, country manager changes, or office expansions in Melbourne, VIC in the last 6–12 months. However, Trustwave’s historical presence in Melbourne and broader Australia is likely to continue and expand under the LevelBlue brand and unified strategy[2][3].\n\n[INDUSTRY] The ANZ cybersecurity market remains highly active, with demand growing for managed detection and response, cloud security, and compliance services, especially as enterprises and government clients seek comprehensive and integrated defense against sophisticated threats[3].\n\n**Summary:**  \nTrustwave, now operating as \"Trustwave, A LevelBlue Company,\" is entering a new growth phase following its August 2025 acquisition by LevelBlue. The strategic focus is to broaden managed security service delivery across Australia, APAC, and key global markets, backed by new resources, platforms, and leadership operational alignment—with significant implications for customers, partners, and the competitive environment in Melbourne, VIC, and across the region[1][2][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Trustwave is a leading cybersecurity and managed security services provider focused on threat detection and response. We uncover threats that others can’t and respond quicker than others can to protect against the devastating impacts of cyberattacks. We’re a world-class team of cyber consultants, threat hunters and researchers serving clients in 96 countries. At Trustwave, you can learn alongside the best, make a personal impact on a global scale, and solve new challenges every day. Learn more about us at https://www.trustwave.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our robust set of solutions and elite team of experts help our clients solve an array of security challenges. As an Enterprise Account Executive, you’ll sell our full portfolio—including our industry-leading Managed Security Services and Managed Detection &amp;amp; Response—to some of our biggest current and potential clients. Our threat hunters are the best in the industry, and we’re looking for an equally aggressive hunter to win new enterprise accounts and grow our revenue.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re always evolving and adapting, so you’ll need to be able to solve practical problems and adjust for variables amid some ambiguity. You’ll also have a lot of autonomy, but you should feel equally comfortable collaborating with others and leaning in to help achieve our sales plan. Reporting to a V.P. of Sales, you’ll have high visibility to other senior leaders, as well as the support of our Sales Engineering team, Account General Managers, Product Specialists and Product Managers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hear from one of our leaders about how we’re helping our sales reps succeed: https://youtu.be/b_yPSRPKl6E.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specifically, Your Responsibilities Will Include&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developing and managing enterprise accounts in your region, territory, or vertical.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generating leads, building relationships with prospects, account profiling, and developing prospects into revenue-generating clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with Channel partners and the Channel Manager to promote Trustwave solution sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developing and managing a pipeline, providing weekly updates to forecast.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiating contracts, upselling, and building rapport with clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales tracking and reporting using Salesforce and Excel.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re looking for people who have:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years’ experience selling to enterprise-level organizations; 3 or more years’ experience in IT solution sales is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience selling to CXO personnel.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A proven understanding of managing a sales territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, coupled with superior negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A validated, successful sales background developing business strategy and multi-year business plans and delivering client success through collaboration and partnership.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience maintaining a multi-million-dollar quota preferred.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A high school diploma or equivalent is required; a college or university degree is a plus.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;This is a remote opportunity open to anyone legally authorized to work in Australia. Guided by our flexible workplace philosophy, Moments That Matter, people gather in the office when in-person interaction is most impactful; full-time remote employees may be asked to travel occasionally based on the needs of the team and the business.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Trustwave is committed to treating everyone with respect, one of our core TRUST Values, and we strive to create a culture that empowers all Trustees to be their best, most authentic selves. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age, or any other federally protected class.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To All Agencies&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please, no phone calls or emails to any employee of Trustwave outside of the Talent Acquisition team. Trustwave’s policy is to only accept resumes from agencies via the Trustwave Agency Portal. Agencies must have a valid fee agreement in place and they must have been assigned the specific requisition to which they submit resumes, by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resume submitted outside of this process will be deemed the sole property of Trustwave and in the event a candidate is submitted outside of this policy is hired, no fee or payment of any kind will be paid.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQGKgcvmwMSkUQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1634936519609/trustwave_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=QjGTkanMOrUZENxdPiz3mz7zOce5aii5itoONSe_Md4', '2025-09-28T14:29:58.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recJR8VMZQkXwJF7h', 'Niche 212', 'http://www.niche212.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/niche-212', 'Sydney, NSW, AU', 'Staffing & Recruiting', '2 - 10', NULL, 'Niche 212 is a staffing and recruiting agency with only 9 employees, falling below the minimum size requirement. The company operates in the recruitment sector, which is excluded from targeting. No recent growth signals or hiring activity are present, and only recruiter-level contacts are available. This lead is not suitable for external recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Niche 212 is an Australian owned, highly personalised, boutique executive recruitment firm.\n\nHeadhunters by nature, we specialise in sourcing the best talent across various sectors including IT & Technology, Financial Services, Finance and Accounting, Sales and Marketing, PR, Media, Advertising, Professional Services and Digital Marketing.\n\nWe are committed to promoting excellence in the recruitment process for both parties.\n\nHiring comes with challenges and getting it wrong can be costly and frustrating. It is critical for organisations to partner with the right recruitment firm to ensure their experience with the recruiting process is thorough and effective. Essentially you need to feel that your recruitment partner is capable and credible when attracting and sourcing the very best talent to put in front of you. \n\n\n"}'::jsonb, 'LOW', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recJY8kO2gDa8MldZ', 'Asana', 'http://asana.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/asana', 'San Francisco, California', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'Asana is a growth-stage commercial B2B software company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for Account Executive and Sales Manager roles in Australia, both high-priority sales positions. The company operates in the core SaaS/collaborative work management sector, which is a strong industry fit. Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Head of Sales, Sales Manager) are present in Australia, providing direct access for recruitment. Multiple growth signals are evident, including ongoing local hiring, regional summits, product launches, and market expansion activities. While no recent funding is noted, the combination of role priority, industry fit, decision maker quality, and growth activity makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] In March 2025, Asana hosted its Work Innovation Summit in Sydney, bringing together 75 executives from leading Australian organizations to discuss strategies for improving workplace collaboration, productivity, AI adoption, and innovation[1][2]. Asana’s Melbourne Work Innovation Summit is scheduled for August 2025, indicating continued active engagement within Australia[1].  \n[REGIONAL] These summits, along with the newly released State of Work Innovation: Australia 2024 report, signal an ongoing strategy to build thought leadership and drive adoption of collaborative work management tools across ANZ[1][3].  \n[GLOBAL] Asana remains positioned as a global leader in collaborative work management according to the 2024 Gartner Magic Quadrant, highlighting product credibility and impact on international markets including Australia[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office is Asana''s flagship APAC location, supporting Sales, Customer Success, and Marketing functions. The team has grown steadily since 2019, with internal milestones noted and continuous hiring for roles in sales, account management, and customer success in 2025[1][5]. Sydney-based employees receive substantial benefits (private health insurance, healthy in-office amenities, annual growth budgets, and mental health support), indicating investment in employee well-being and retention[5].  \n[REGIONAL] Asana maintains active recruitment and development activities across Melbourne and broader ANZ, expanding direct engagement with local enterprises and knowledge workers through high-touch summits and research initiatives[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Product launches in AI-powered work management tools have emphasized scalability for enterprise clients worldwide, benefiting regional offices through improved offerings and deployment capabilities[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No Australia-specific funding events have been reported in the previous 6-12 months. Asana’s last major global investment rounds occurred before 2024, with current spending and R&D focused on AI features and enterprise expansions[4].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Asana’s research-led “State of Work Innovation: Australia” report became a central source of industry information in March 2025, surveying 2,000 Australian knowledge workers and guiding local AI adoption strategies[1][3].  \n[REGIONAL] The Work Innovation Summit series is a recognized platform for regional innovation dialogue, often featuring prominent academic and business figures (e.g., Dr. Rebecca Hinds, Monash University’s Dr. David Gilbert) to highlight productivity and work management trends specific to ANZ[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Asana was named a Leader in the 2024 Gartner Magic Quadrant for both Collaborative Work Management and Adaptive Project Management, underpinning the software’s international reputation and relevance for Australian enterprise clients[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Alesia Venuto, cited as a senior Customer Success Manager and one of Asana’s first six ANZ hires, has continued to play an active role in strategic customer management in Australia as of March 2025[1]. No recent major leadership appointments or departures have been publicly reported for Sydney or Australia in the last six months.  \n[GLOBAL] No new globally relevant executive appointments specific to APAC expansion were uncovered in recent months, but leadership maintains ongoing engagement in research, AI innovation, and regional events[1][4].\n\n[INDUSTRY] *Software development market trends in Australia* reflect stalled AI adoption, with only 14% of organizations scaling AI across their businesses according to Asana’s 2025 report; this presents major opportunity for market education and solution deployment by firms with robust AI and workflow capabilities[3]. Demand for platforms that unify remote and distributed teams with integrated AI continues to accelerate, with collaborative work management a strategic priority for large Australian enterprises[3][4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"As an Enterprise Outbound Business Development Representative, your role is to generate pipeline for the Asana enterprise customer segment by targeting new contacts and departments to educate them on the value of Asana and initiating new sales cycles. As Asana’s first point of contact, you play a key role in building Asana business cases across new lines of business and creating momentum for large enterprise deployments in Australia and New Zealand.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;BDRs who establish high performance and are strong representations of the Asana’s Core Values will have potential for new challenges and career advancement within sales.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is based in our Sydney office with an office-centric hybrid schedule. Along with most Asanas, you’ll work from this office in person on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. Most Asanas have the option to work from home on Mondays and Fridays. If you''re interviewing for this role, your Talent Acquisition Partner will share more about the in-office requirements.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll achieve:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate pipeline for enterprise account executives by researching target customer accounts and personas, and creating customised messaging leveraging existing Asana use cases and industry trends across lines of business to drive qualified opportunities and account expansion.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage multi-channel outbound prospecting approach (calls, emails, social), team sequences, templates, messaging to help build a repeatable process. Proactively implement new &amp;amp; existing processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cultivate value driven conversations with multiple Director and VP level personas across complex cross functional teams and consistently create compelling messaging and events to achieve meeting goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a territory plan with AE and CSM based on account tier scoring to drive the highest ARR. Understand where to leverage customized vs. scaled approaches to optimize sales qualified opportunities. Adhere to SDR/AE Handoff process.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Update activity metrics, meetings, SQO and pipeline on a weekly basis. Proactively identifies gaps between prospecting inputs (calls, emails, social selling,tasks and messaging) and outputs (meetings, SQO’s and Pipeline). &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively execute high-impact trials, meeting SLA requirements, and leverages territory heat maps and buyer’s journey to triage target accounts with ABM strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understands Asana use-cases, relevant workflows/processes, and ways that Asana can deliver value. Comfortable differentiating Asana from the competition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement time management strategy, segmenting time blocks for account research, strategic outreach and scaled Outreach, Enterprise strategy meetings and company meetings.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 1 year sales development experience with at least 6 months of outbound experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with sales tools such as Salesforce, Outreach, ZoomInfo, and LinkedIn Navigator to network with potential customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success in driving outbound prospecting strategy and process to high-level personas and decision makers to achieve pipeline goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates curiosity about AI tools and emerging technologies, with a willingness to learn and leverage them to enhance productivity, collaboration, or decision-making.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;At Asana, we''re committed to building teams that include a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills, as this is critical to helping us achieve our mission. If you''re interested in this role and don''t meet every listed requirement, we still encourage you to apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’ll offer:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our comprehensive compensation package plays a big part in how we recognize you for the impact you have on our path to achieving our mission. We believe that compensation should be reflective of the value you create relative to the market value of your role. To ensure pay is fair and not impacted by biases, we''re committed to looking at market value which is why we check ourselves and conduct a yearly pay equity audit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For this role, the estimated base salary range is between $78,400 AUD - $87,500 AUD. The actual base salary will vary based on various factors, including market and individual qualifications objectively assessed during the interview process. The listed range above is a guideline, and the base salary range for this role may be modified.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In addition to base salary, your compensation package may include additional components such as equity, sales incentive pay (for most sales roles), and benefits. If you''re interviewing for this role, speak with your Talent Acquisition Partner to learn more about the total compensation and benefits for this role.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We strive to provide equitable and competitive benefits packages that support our employees worldwide and include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mental health, wellness &amp;amp; fitness benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career coaching &amp;amp; support&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inclusive family building benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Long-term savings or retirement plans&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;In-office culinary options to cater to your dietary preferences &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;These are just some of the benefits we offer, and benefits may vary based on role, country, and local regulations. If you''re interviewing for this role, speak with your Talent Acquisition Partner to learn more about the total compensation and benefits for this role.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Asana helps teams orchestrate their work, from small projects to strategic initiatives. Millions of teams around the world rely on Asana to achieve their most important goals, faster. Asana has been named a Top 10 Best Workplace for 5 years in a row, is Fortune''s #1 Best Workplace in the Bay Area, and one of Glassdoor’s and Inc.’s Best Places to Work. After spending more than a year physically distanced, Team Asana is safely and mindfully returning to in-person collaboration, incorporating flexibility that adds hybrid elements to our office-centric culture . With 11+ offices all over the world, we are always looking for individuals who care about building technology that drives positive change in the world and a culture where everyone feels that they belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in supporting people to do their best work and thrive, and building a diverse, equitable, and inclusive company is core to our mission. Our goal is to ensure that Asana upholds an inclusive environment where all people feel that they are equally respected and valued, whether they are applying for an open position or working at the company. We provide equal employment opportunities to all applicants without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by law.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQEkMiCf0h2oeA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1711542643480/asana_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=rKPLywOzn6x_vWPj7XYeSdZUyWV5sPMxUiP5pHyjuIk', '2025-09-28T03:52:30.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recJkdpDA6fiS0bMW', 'Rocket Software', 'http://www.rocketsoftware.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rocket-software', 'Waltham, MA', 'Software Development,IT Services and IT Consulting', '1,001-5,000 employees', '75', 'Rocket Software is a growth-stage software and IT services company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively expanding in Australia and Southeast Asia, with recent hiring of Senior Account Executives and Channel Sales roles—core sales positions relevant to 4Twenty''s focus. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, with strong regional sales leadership (VP Sales APAC, Senior Sales Manager, Senior Account Executive) providing Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision-maker access. Multiple growth signals—including regional expansion, executive appointments, and increased enterprise engagement—indicate a high probability of external recruitment needs for sales roles, though absence of recent funding slightly tempers the score.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Rocket Software hosted \"COBOL Day Sydney\" on June 5, 2025 at QT Sydney, focusing on future-proofing COBOL applications and enabling modernization for local Australian enterprises[2][7].  \n[REGIONAL] The company announced the expansion of its operations in Australia and Southeast Asia, with strengthened roles to support demand for mainframe and IBM modernization services in Australia[1][4]. Recent strategic focus includes supporting governmental bodies and major corporates like Qantas, NSW Police, and the Department of Foreign Affairs for IT modernization initiatives[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Rocket Software’s increased event activity, such as COBOL Day Sydney, is indicative of deepened engagement and expansion efforts targeting Greater Sydney’s developer and enterprise communities[2][7].  \n[REGIONAL] Three seasoned technology executives have joined Rocket to spearhead its Australia and Southeast Asia growth. Notable ANZ appointments include Keith Garelja (Senior Account Executive, ex-IBM Australia) and Liam Leaney (Channel Lead for ANZ, ex-VMWare), reflecting a specific sales and partnerships expansion for the ANZ market[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Chip Salyards (VP of International Sales) now manages Asia Pac/ANZ, signaling stronger GTM and sales focus for the region[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Rocket supports global customers in banking, government, and Fortune 500 segments, with mainframe and hybrid cloud modernization as core offerings. Overall customer satisfaction scores and repeat business from major clients drive staffing and operational growth globally[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No notable funding events, rounds, or financial milestones reported in the last 12 months in APAC/Australia operations[Global/Regional].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Rocket Software’s platform modernization activities are credited with enabling digital transformation and compliance for NSW government agencies and other high-profile organizations in Australia[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Rocket Software has positioned itself as an IBM modernization leader across APAC, with increased recognition tied to government IT and enterprise cloud transformation projects[1][4].  \n[GLOBAL] The company leads in GenAI for hybrid cloud integration and is recognized for helping Fortune 50 customers modernize legacy systems and implement automated compliance solutions[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Multiple executive appointments in APAC/ANZ:\n- Keith Garelja (Senior Account Executive, Australia; ex-IBM)[1]\n- Liam Leaney (Channel Lead, ANZ; ex-VMWare)[1]\n- Paul Lin (Senior Channel Manager, SE Asia; ex-BT, ex-Cisco)[1]\n- Chip Salyards now has expanded responsibilities covering Asia Pac/ANZ as VP of International Sales[1]\n\n[GLOBAL] No reported global executive changes directly impacting Australian operations; recent APAC leadership hires are the most relevant.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Sydney and broader Australian market trends show increasing demand for IT modernization, mainframe integration, and cloud migration in both public sector and financial services. Enterprise investment in hybrid cloud, automation, and mission-critical legacy refactoring remains high, driven by ongoing compliance, productivity, and digital transformation mandates[1][3][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;It''s fun to work in a company where people truly BELIEVE in what they''re doing!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description Summary:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Account Executive is an enterprise software sales professional who sells a platform of software solutions to Global 1000 clients. This individual understands executive selling into large companies, has outstanding communication skills and brings current relationships. Proactively prospecting and meeting with customers weekly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell a portfolio of infrastructure and application software that optimizes and modernizes enterprise systems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Field Marketing to develop prospects and events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Supports sales campaigns with the extended team of Rocket sales engineers, marketing and lab groups.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure best-in-class customer sales satisfaction and reference-ability with our customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet revenue targets and strategic objectives, including growing the sales pipeline, creating territory plans.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actively use Salesforce and maintain weekly, monthly and quarterly sales forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with management to negotiate pricing and contact terms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to customer business and IT leaders, aggressively shape opportunities early in the sales cycle. Advance opportunities into profitable revenue growth for the company.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate breadth and depth of knowledge in aligning the company''s capabilities to business and IT priorities and positioning relative to competitors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of sales experience in solution software to Global 1000 clients&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to adapt to the situation, impeccable honesty, integrity, and ethics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work in a company with a sales culture that supports and rewards high achievers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively tackles difficult problems often with a new perspective.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Can articulate a vision, influence others, plan and organize resources and deliver the results.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strive to exceed expectations and able to work effectively with Sales Management support.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Has the business acumen and experience to navigate mid-size customers with a portfolio product line.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information Security:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Information security is everyone’s responsibility. A fundamental principle of information security at Rocket Software is that all individuals in the organization have a responsibility for the security and protection of company information and IT Resources over which they have control, according to their role.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diversity, Inclusion &amp;amp; Equity:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Rocket we are committed to an inclusive workplace environment, where every Rocketeer can thrive by bringing their full selves to work. Being a Rocketeer means you are part of our movement to continually drive inclusivity, diversity and equity in our workforce.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;LI-#Remote&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position is eligible for commissions in accordance with the terms of the company’s plan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rocket Software Inc. is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. Rocket Software Inc. is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rocket is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodation to individuals with physical and mental disabilities. If you need special assistance or an accommodation while seeking employment, please call: 781-577-4321 or send an email to people@rocketsoftware.com. We will make a determination on your request for reasonable accommodation on a case-by-case basis.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you like wild growth and working with happy, enthusiastic over-achievers, you''ll enjoy your career with us!&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGX1UlSsTe8uA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1666879844897/rocket_software_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=RRQXWoY47PuQSd70VgB02NG8M4tzpj1IzQQ1GDUXpww', '2025-09-21T14:13:49.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recJtwg85xKJ5nyuM', 'Qlik', 'http://www.qlik.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qlik', 'King of Prussia, PA, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '75', 'Qlik is a growth-stage computer software company (4,426 employees) in the core B2B tech sector, actively hiring for sales roles such as Enterprise Sales Development Representative and Sales Business Development in Australia and Singapore. The company fits the ideal client profile for external recruitment, with strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers present (Country Manager ANZ, SVP APAC, Sales Directors, etc.), and recent funding plus product launches signaling ongoing growth. While not hiring SDR/BDR as the primary trigger, the presence of high-priority sales roles, strong industry fit, and quality decision makers make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nQlik recently launched its Qlik Open Data Lakehouse and agentic AI tools at Qlik Connect 2025, expanding its data integration and analytics capabilities. This move aims to bridge the \"AI activation gap\" by helping businesses prepare data for AI tasks and integrate analytical insights into workflows. Additionally, Qlik''s announcement of a significant investment led by ADIA and Thoma Bravo signifies strategic financial backing.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nQlik announced the close of a significant minority investment led by ADIA, with Thoma Bravo making a new equity investment alongside other institutional investors. The transaction, originally signed in November 2024, highlights strong investor support for Qlik''s strategy and growth.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nQlik launched the Qlik Open Data Lakehouse and introduced new agentic AI capabilities, including a discovery agent to identify risks and opportunities, during Qlik Connect 2025. Qlik also identified key trends in the AI economy for 2025, focusing on authenticity, applied value, and agents. The company honored its partners for delivering exceptional customer outcomes, showcasing their role in accelerating AI adoption.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes identified. Mike Capone continues as CEO, guiding Qlik''s strategic direction and investment activities."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Wherever there''s business, there''s data. And wherever there''s data, there''s Qlik. Qlik is leading the way to the AI-powered enterprise, with powerful capabilities in data integration, quality, and analytics. With Qlik, organizations get more out of their data and deliver better business outcomes."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recKPCCjd6y9eusOl', 'Simpro Software', 'https://www.simprogroup.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/simpro-software', 'Brisbane, QLD', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '83', 'Simpro Software is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (501-1,000 employees) actively hiring for Account Executive and Customer Success Manager roles, both high-priority for 4Twenty. The industry fit is ideal, with strong regional expansion, ongoing hiring, and recent product launches signaling robust growth. Decision maker access is excellent, with a Vice President of Sales ANZ (Tier 2), Territory Sales Manager, and Strategic Account Executive present. Multiple growth signals (platform launches, headcount growth, regional expansion) further support a strong recruitment opportunity, though no recent funding rounds are cited. This is a high-priority opportunity for immediate sales recruitment engagement.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Launched the expanded **Simpro Marketplace** from HQ in Brisbane, Australia, announced ahead of Simprosium 2025, enabling field service companies to integrate hundreds of partner solutions directly tailored for ANZ customers[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Simpro’s 2025 Trades Outlook report highlights high adoption of field management software in Australia/NZ, with 83% of surveyed service businesses citing digital platforms as key to growth[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Simpro continues integration and collaboration with group companies (BigChange, ClockShark, AroFlo) under its growing parent organization, PRI, broadening its technology and solution reach globally[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Headcount at Brisbane HQ and across Australia continues upward, with local roles supporting software development, customer success, and GTM activities[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Simpro now serves over 25,000 field service customers across Australia, New Zealand, UK, and North America; regional expansion underpinned by new integrations and partner ecosystem[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Simpro’s employee base is reported at 570, with ongoing hiring across key business units in 2025[2]. \n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No specific recent funding rounds within the last 12 months are cited in available sources; Simpro is part of the global portfolio of Providence Strategic Growth (PRI), supporting its expansion and technology investments[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Simpro scheduled to host Simprosium 2025 in Brisbane, emphasizing leadership in field service tech innovation and releasing exclusive IDC research at the event[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] Official launch of the expanded Simpro Marketplace offers access to regionally relevant technology integration partners, consultants, and business enablement experts for APAC field service customers[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Ongoing platform enhancements, including AI-driven partner integrations such as Podium (for customer communications) and broader business intelligence tools, position Simpro as a global field service management leader[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] Gary Specter is cited as CEO as of 2025, overseeing global strategy and APAC-focused growth initiatives[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Recent leadership and business development activities reference appointments in North America to drive field services transformation; no recent local executive appointments in Australia are specifically named in the last six months[2].\n\nIf you need expanded intelligence on hiring or executive pipeline for a specific Australian city, or want more detail on recent customer wins, award recognitions, or platform launches, please specify."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"First Things First - What We Can Offer YouLeave to foster personal connections, health & overall well-beingEmloyee Assistance ProgramGenerous Parental Leave ProgramPaid Volunteer Leave DaysPublic Holiday Exchange SchemeDelicious, free, chef-prepared lunch daily on siteEnjoy up to 4 weeks a year of flexible ''Work from Anywhere'' time!Talent Referral Program – get rewarded for referring a friend to join our team!Casual dress and relaxed office environmentFun team camaraderie and eventsOpportunities for career progression and developmentDiverse training & internal networking opportunities across all of our product linesA range of other fantastic benefits!Check out our website for more about working at Simpro Group https://www.simprogroup.com/uk/company/careers#positionsThe JobAs an Enterprise Account Manager at Simpro Group, you’ll own a book of high-value enterprise accounts and be responsible for uncovering and closing expansion opportunities across our product portfolio. While our Customer Success team manages day-to-day account health and adoption, you own commercial growth - developing strategies to introduce and expand product suites, usage, and drive incremental value. This is an expansion role with a sales hunter mindset - you’re relentless about helping customers do more with SimproGroup products, and you''re commercially sharp enough to spot and close opportunities that others miss.What You’ll DoOwn the commercial relationship for a portfolio of strategic enterprise customers. Develop and maintain a multi-threaded contact strategy, building strong relationships across business units, operations, and IT. Drive cross-sell and upsell motions across Simpro solutions - positioning new capabilities to solve evolving customer needs. Partner with Customer Success to understand adoption trends, risk signals, and upsell potential - but retain ownership of commercial conversations. Build and execute account growth plans that align with customer goals and Simpro’s strategic priorities. Forecast accurately, maintain CRM hygiene, and meet quarterly expansion revenue targets. Collaborate with Pre-Sales, Marketing, Product, and Channel teams to bring the right resources to each opportunity. What You’ll Bring5+ years of SaaS experience in account management, enterprise sales, or expansion roles. Proven ability to grow existing customer relationships through cross-sell and upsell. Experience navigating complex sales cycles in multi-stakeholder environments. Knowledge of field service, construction tech, or operations software is a plus. Skilled in CRM, sales forecasting, account planning, and stakeholder mapping. High integrity, curiosity, commercial acumen, and a team-first mindset.Core values required of all Simpro, AroFlo, BigChange & ClockShark employees:While experience in the above areas will be highly considered, it’s important to note it will be secondary to the person with the right determination, attitude and compatibility. Our culture and core values are very important to us:We Are One Team We Are Customer CentricWe Are Growth MindedWe Are AccountableWe Celebrate SuccessSimpro, AroFlo, BigChange & ClockShark are equal opportunity employers with a best-of-class onboarding program and supportive team environments. We embrace and support culture diversity and Equal Employment Opportunity. Aboriginals, Torres Strait Islanders and minority groups are encouraged to apply. .Visit simprogroup.com/au/company/careers to learn more about us and our values.We would like to take this opportunity to thank all candidates for their application.Please note, no agencies will be accepted in the recruitment of this role."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-29T14:19:21.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recKXkPAOOgK94AMW', 'Vonage', 'http://www.vonage.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vonage', 'Holmdel, New Jersey, US', 'Information Technology & Services', '1001 - 5000', '64', 'Vonage is a growth-stage commercial B2B tech company (2,745 employees) in the UCaaS/CPaaS sector, with active APAC operations in Australia and Singapore. The included sales roles are Business Development and Growth Head - SEA, Senior Director API Sales (APAC), and Senior Regional Business Development, which are medium-priority for recruitment (25 points). The industry fit is strong (25 points) and decision maker access is high, with VP Sales APAC and Senior Director API Sales (Tier 2, 20 points). Growth signals include recent leadership appointments and strategic partnerships, but no explicit recent hiring surges or funding. This presents a moderate recruitment opportunity, with potential but not immediate urgency for external agency use.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nVonage partnered with Singtel in April 2024 to accelerate enterprise and telco innovation via integration with Singtel’s Paragon platform. In July 2024, Vonage launched an expanded Startup Program providing startups with early access to their advanced communications APIs.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nThe company continues to invest in AI and expand its API offerings, with recent strategic focus on geographic and R&D prioritization to drive high-margin growth. No explicit recent hiring spikes or sales/GTM headcount changes identified in the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent standalone funding rounds or new investment announcements identified; Vonage remains a subsidiary of Ericsson since its 2022 acquisition.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nVonage was named a Customers’ Choice and a 2025 Visionary in Gartner’s Magic Quadrant for CPaaS in July 2025. The company also won Gold in the 5G category at the Merit Awards for Telecom 2024 and secured the Best Virtual Agent Platform at CX Awards 2024.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nKristy Thomas was appointed Senior Vice President of Global Channels and Alliances in July 2024. Jim Regan was recognized as a 2024 CRN Channel Chief, confirming his ongoing leadership in channel strategy."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We’re making communications more flexible, intelligent, and personal, to help enterprises the world over stay ahead. We provide unified communications, contact centers and programmable communications APIs, built on the world''s most flexible cloud communications platform. \n\nVonage was founded in 2001 and became a wholly-owned subsidiary of Ericsson in 2022. Vonage is headquartered in Holmdel, New Jersey.\n\nWe hope you''ll join the conversation with us and welcome your feedback. However, we reserve the right to remove comments that are offensive, abusive, spam, or third-party advertisements."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:29:25.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
