    ('recLieAUI9THmg8wv', 'Keepit', 'https://www.keepit.com', 'https://dk.linkedin.com/company/keepit-a-s', 'Copenhagen, , DK', 'Information Technology & Services', '201 - 500', '87', 'Keepit is a growth-stage SaaS data protection company (528 employees) actively hiring for sales roles, with a Regional Sales Manager and Regional Partner Manager based in Australia (Tier 2 decision makers). The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, has recently secured $50M in funding, launched a global Partner Network, and expanded its infrastructure, all strong growth signals. The presence of high-priority sales roles and multiple growth indicators make this a very high priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nKeepit entered a strategic go-to-market agreement with Ingram Micro in Germany and Switzerland in September 2025 to expand its SaaS data protection offerings and support channel partners in these markets. The partnership aims to intensify Keepit''s presence in the DACH region and enable value-added resellers and MSPs to access its solutions[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nKeepit launched its global Partner Network in January 2024, focusing on empowering resellers and MSPs in North America, EMEA, and ANZ. The company expanded its infrastructure in both Germany and Switzerland and continues scaling through strategic channel investments and geographic reach[2][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nKeepit raised $50 million in its third funding round in May 2025, more than doubling its previous two rounds combined and bringing total investment to $90 million. CEO Morten Felsvang stated the funds would be used to strengthen product capabilities and global expansion[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nKeepit won the “Best Cloud-Native Project / Solution” and “Best Cloud DR / Business Continuity Solution” categories at the 2024/25 Cloud Awards in January 2025. The company was also named Champion in the Canalys Managed BDR Leadership Matrix 2025 and received the 2025 Cloud Computing Security Excellence Award[2][3][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nIn 2024, Keepit appointed a new Chief Product Officer to oversee SaaS data protection as part of its continued channel and product investments. No other significant leadership changes identified[2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Streamline your #SaaS backup & recovery with Keepit. 20+ years of providing dedicated data protection, ensuring companies protect and manage SaaS data at scale.\n\nKeepit protects your cloud data and leaves you free to leverage new cloud technologies without fear of data loss. Simple to set up and deploy, with the best restore options available so you can find and recover historic data in no time.\n\nThe Keepit  platform is ready for any Cloud Workload and offers full retention on your terms – from one year to eternity. Born with indexing and search to ensure you always have the complete view of your data."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:28:01.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recLlKW0y7I7vwzcd', 'Box', 'http://www.box.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/box', 'Redwood City, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '80', 'Box is a growth-stage commercial B2B software company (Computer Software, 4,040 employees) actively hiring for a Mid Market Account Executive, a high-priority core sales role. The company operates in Australia, with filtered employees based in Sydney, and fits the ideal industry profile. Tier 2 decision makers (Account Executive) are present, providing suitable access for recruitment. While strong product launch signals (AI-powered products) indicate innovation and market activity, there are no recent funding or explicit hiring surge signals. This makes Box a high-priority recruitment opportunity for sales roles, though not at the very highest tier due to the absence of direct growth or hiring surge indicators.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nBox launched major AI-powered products including Box Shield Pro, Box Automate, and Box Extract at BoxWorks 2025 conference in September 2025, marking a strategic shift to put AI and automation at the center of its growth strategy[1][2]. The company announced new integrations with leading AI model providers including OpenAI, Anthropic, and xAI, along with enterprise software ecosystems like Microsoft, Google, and Salesforce[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nBox unveiled three new AI capabilities at BoxWorks 2025 in September 2025, designed to help organizations extract more value from unstructured data while maintaining security[2]. The company demonstrated practical AI implementations showing 30-50% productivity gains, five hours back per week for teams, and 35% faster SOW cycles according to customer proof points presented at the conference[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Box (NYSE:BOX) is the Intelligent Content Cloud, a single platform that enables organizations to fuel collaboration, manage the entire content lifecycle, secure critical content, and transform business workflows with enterprise AI. Founded in 2005, Box simplifies work for leading global organizations, including AstraZeneca, JLL, Morgan Stanley, and Nationwide. Box is headquartered in Redwood City, CA, with offices across the United States, Europe, and Asia. Visit box.com to learn more. And visit box.org to learn more about how Box empowers nonprofits to fulfill their missions."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:25:50.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recLr7DwfncAoGUVN', 'Notion', 'https://notion.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/notionhq', 'San Francisco, California', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '97', 'Notion is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (501-1,000 employees) actively hiring for Enterprise Account Executive roles in Australia, a core sales position. The company operates in a high-priority industry and has recently launched its Sydney HQ, with strong regional growth signals including team doubling plans, local partnerships, and product rollouts. Tier 1 decision maker access is present via the GM of ANZ, SEA, and India. Multiple strong growth indicators and direct sales hiring make this a top-tier recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Notion launched its **Sydney headquarters in 2025**, specifically targeting Australian small- and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) facing “tech overload” and productivity loss[1]. The Sydney launch follows notable local engagement events, including community meet-ups and “Cafe Notion” for users and businesses to connect with the team and share workflows[2].  \n[LOCAL] Notion has partnered with prominent Australian venture funds such as **Airtree** and **Square Peg**, and reported local business case studies including sales automation platform **Qwilr** and government group **Investment NSW** driving team productivity with Notion[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] Notion’s Asia-Pacific strategy is led by Andrew McCarthy, Head of ANZ, SEA, and India, reflecting a focus on scalable support throughout APAC from the Sydney base[1][2].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office has grown from its first Australian employee in May 2024 to a **15-person team supporting Australia and APAC** as of September 2025, with plans to **double the Australian team within a year** to further business support, particularly for SMEs[2].  \n[LOCAL] Local hiring specifically targets roles supporting sales, partnerships, and 