y losses (valued at AU$228 billion annually), are strong adopters of integrated platforms like Notion for digital transformation and operational efficiency[1]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Notion helps you build beautiful tools for your life’s work. In today''s world of endless apps and tabs, Notion provides one place for teams to get everything done, seamlessly connecting docs, notes, projects, calendar, and email—with AI built in to find answers and automate work. Millions of users, from individuals to large organizations like Toyota, Figma, and OpenAI, love Notion for its flexibility and choose it because it helps them save time and money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In-person collaboration is essential to Notion''s culture. We require all team members to work from our offices on Mondays and Thursdays, our designated Anchor Days. Certain teams or positions may require additional in-office workdays.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for our first Sales Manager in our newly formed Sydney HQ. This person will play an integral role in helping lead our growth efforts across APAC. We need someone with an entrepreneurial and builder spirit, someone who enjoys coaching sales reps to be the best they can be, someone who is data-driven and experienced in managing a high-velocity sales pipeline.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As our first Sales Manager, you and your team will play an important role defining/iterating on our sales motions, providing customer feedback to help share our roadmap, and generating revenue to grow our sales business. You will own the strategy and execution of your team’s territory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Achieve&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead a team of Account Executives who handles full cycle sales activities, including: prospecting/building pipeline, developing new potential accounts, expanding existing customers, and renewing an install base&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the strategy of your team’s territory, including how the team maximizes the revenue it is generating and retaining&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the execution of your team’s strategy, including the team forecast and pipeline generation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with cross functional partners to build playbooks and define our sales motion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise with our incredible user base to provide world class customer experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive executive level relationships - internally and externally&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally and collaboratively with internal teams (sales, inside sales, customer success, solution engineer, deal-desk, ops, legal)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills You''ll Need To Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellence in high-velocity SaaS sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New logo acquisition sales experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A passion for coaching and rep development, specifically around building compelling business cases and creating urgency&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;8+ years of full cycle sales at a fast growing software company&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of leading a sales organization at a fast growing software company&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong leader who builds cross functional relationships inside and outside of sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of leading high performing teams who exceed their quotas&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A phenomenally strong communicator&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong ability to analyze data to build thoughtful strategies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engaging and compelling presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A positive and open minded attitude&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong desire to be successful without sacrificing your values&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A builder mentality who thrives in collaborative environments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An ability to operate within the gray and find creative or out-of-the-box solutions when faced with ambiguity&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice To Haves&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''ve got strong technical chops&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Direct sales plus experience of selling through Partners&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience of quarterly sales planning&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We hire talented and passionate people from a variety of backgrounds because we want our global employee base to represent the wide diversity of our customers. If you’re excited about a role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every bullet point listed in the job description, we still encourage you to apply. If you’re a builder at heart, share our company values, and enthusiastic about making software toolmaking ubiquitous, we want to hear from you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Notion is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate in hiring or any employment decision based on race, color, religion, national origin, age, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), marital status, ancestry, physical or mental disability, genetic information, veteran status, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, or other applicable legally protected characteristic. Notion considers qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Notion is also committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, please let your recruiter know.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;By clicking “Submit Application”, I understand and agree that Notion and its affiliates and subsidiaries will collect and process my information in accordance with Notion’s Global Recruiting Privacy Policy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGwvcv_1tHZ4w/company-logo_200_200/B4EZW25gE2GgAI-/0/1742530282185/notionhq_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=TjS2vynSBhOF0lA-8mORNZFzuAfpcyYNPU6g90Uq1Ng', '2025-09-25T22:27:03.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recMnFScXpM5htzGy', 'Zeller', 'https://www.myzeller.com/au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/zeller', 'Melbourne, Victoria, AU', 'Financial Services', '201 - 500', '80', 'Zeller is a growth-stage fintech company (275 employees) in Melbourne, actively hiring for an Enterprise Account Executiveâone of our high-priority core sales roles. The company operates in the commercial B2B tech space, with strong fit due to its SaaS-driven financial platform and rapid SME customer growth. Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Head of Sales, Regional Sales Managers, Sales Manager) are present, providing direct access for recruitment. Recent product launches and high-profile integrations signal ongoing expansion, though no recent funding or hiring surges are noted. This is a high-priority recruitment opportunity with strong alignment to our service focus.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn August 2025, Zeller announced the launch of \"Zeller for Startups,\" positioning itself as Australia''s first all-in-one financial solution for founders and tech startups. The platform aims to address traditional banking pain points for startups, including slow onboarding and fragmented financial management, with a unified suite accessible via a single online account.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAs of mid-2025, Zeller reported having over 85,000 SME customers, reflecting rapid customer acquisition over the past 3.5 years. The launch of \"Zeller for Startups\" and integration of new features signal continued platform and market expansion, though specific recent hiring or headcount data is not publicly available.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn August 2025, Zeller unveiled its all-in-one Startup-focused platform and announced milestone traction with 85,000 SME clients. The company also secured high-profile integrations with services like Xero and Employment Hero to enhance founder banking experiences.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Accepting payments, managing your finances, and paying recipients should be simple. Unfortunately, this isnât always the case. Finding integrated financial solutions to help your business thrive often requires you to weave together multiple products from different providers. While a small group of large enterprises enjoy the privilege of financial solutions tailored for their specific needs, the vast majority of Australian businesses are underserved due to a lack of innovation, disparate providers, opaque pricing, and restrictive contracts. \n\nWe believe in a level playing field where all businesses benefit from access to smarter payments technology and integrated financial services that enables them to accelerate their cash flow. So weâre hard at work building the tools to make it happen.\n\nZeller is one solution for all of your business finances. From EFTPOS payments to online invoicing, accounts and cards, it''s everything you expect from a business bank, but better. \n\nLearn more, and sign up for your free Zeller Account, at https://www.myzeller.com/au"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recNSDeoBbSRcqibn', 'Patsnap', 'http://www.patsnap.com/', 'https://sg.linkedin.com/company/patsnap', 'Singapore, , SG', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '65', 'Patsnap is a growth-stage computer software company (518 employees) in Singapore, actively expanding its sales and customer success teams, indicating strong hiring momentum. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, and recent achievements such as surpassing $100M ARR and launching new AI products signal robust growth. However, the only available filtered contact is an Assistant Director of PR, not a direct sales or hiring decision maker, which limits immediate recruitment access. The opportunity is high due to industry fit, company size, and growth signals, but would be higher with direct access to sales leadership or talent acquisition contacts.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOn June 11, 2024, Patsnap announced surpassing US$100 million in Annual Recurring Revenue, marking a 20% year-over-year growth in 2023 and reinforcing its global leadership in IP and R&D intelligence. The company introduced its new AI product, Patsnap Eureka, and is actively exploring strategic M&A opportunities to expand capabilities and strengthen market position[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nPatsnap expanded its platform offerings to cover AI tools for patent drafting, claims charting, and life sciences, serving over 12,000 teams in 50 countries and now reaching more than 200,000 users in life sciences alone. The company emphasizes global reach with growing EMEA operations and ongoing team expansion in sales, customer success, and strategic roles, leveraging its London headquarters for access to international talent[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn June 2024, Patsnap achieved the milestone of $100 million in ARR, driven by strong uptake of AI-powered innovation tools and over 50% compounded annual growth rate for its life sciences products in the past three years[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Patsnap, the global leader in AI-powered IP and R&D intelligence, empowers over 15,000 companies to find better answers and make faster, more confident decisions across the innovation lifecycle. By combining our domain-specific LLM, Hiro—our AI assistant—and proprietary innovation data, Patsnap delivers insights that boost IP productivity by 75% and reduce R&D waste by 25%."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:21:11.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recNigFft8LHvwFk9', 'impact.com', 'https://impact.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/impactdotcom', 'Santa Barbara, California', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'impact.com is a growth-stage commercial B2B SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for Account Executive and Sales Manager roles in Australia and Singapore, both high-priority sales positions. The company operates in core commercial tech, with strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Managing Director - APJ, RVP Sales - APJ, Sales Managers) accessible in-region. Multiple strong growth signals are present: expanding ANZ operations, major event execution, leadership appointments, and ongoing product innovation. While no recent funding, robust organic growth and sales hiring indicate a high likelihood to use external recruitment for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Hosted the **third annual iPX Sydney event** in 2024, attracting over 250 brands, publishers, and agencies—highlighting growing influence within the Australian partnership and affiliate marketing sector. Organizers noted strong year-on-year growth, with plans to expand the event in 2025 due to high demand[3].\n[REGIONAL] Promoted **Helena Barroso Zarco to Director, Customer Success and Sales ANZ** in early 2024, aligning the ANZ sales and customer success teams to strengthen service and operational cohesion across Australia and New Zealand[1].\n[GLOBAL] Announced the appointment of **Jessica Breslav as Chief Customer Officer** and expanded into Spain with a new Madrid office in Q2 2025, signaling broader organizational investment in international markets, including APAC[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Demonstrated **increasing event engagement and community presence** in Sydney, with the iPX conference’s expanding attendee base and prominent participation from major brands and agencies[3].\n[REGIONAL] Attracted a broad range of new clients in the ANZ region and reinforced local leadership with the promotion of a dedicated director for Customer Success and Sales[1].\n[GLOBAL] Added **over 900 new global clients** in Q2 2025 alone (portfolio now 5,000+ brands), supported by a headcount exceeding 1,300 employees across 20 countries—indicating continued platform adoption and a robust sales/GTM focus worldwide[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No major **funding rounds** publicly announced in the past 12 months. Previous notable funding reported in prior years; recent growth has been primarily driven by operational expansions, client acquisition, and product innovation (scope: global)[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Successfully executed the largest iPX Sydney event to date, serving as a leading partnership forum for Australia and showcasing adoption among regional brands like July, Shopify, Big Red Group, and Virgin Australia[3].\n[REGIONAL] Enhanced ANZ team alignment and strengthened regional leadership contributed to improved customer success and market performance metrics in 2024[1].\n[GLOBAL] Launched several **product innovations** in 2024–2025, including a new Chrome extension for publishers and dynamic cost-per-click payout features, and published industry benchmark reports analyzing evolving consumer and partnership trends[1][2]. Recognized as a top affiliate network by multiple industry analysts in 2024[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Promoted **Helena Barroso Zarco to Director, Customer Success and Sales ANZ** in 2024, overseeing both sales and support functions across Australia & New Zealand[1].\n[GLOBAL] Appointed **Jessica Breslav as Chief Customer Officer** in mid-2025 and welcomed a new CFO, **Dale Lynch**, in early 2024, both bringing substantial experience in scaling international technology companies and partnership platforms[2][1].\n\nOverall, impact.com is ramping up **ANZ operations** with notable leadership appointments, expanding industry event footprints in Sydney, and remains a global leader in partnership management software, sustaining strong client and product growth across regions in 2024–2025."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;The Company&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At impact.com we are passionate about our people, our technology, and are obsessed with customer success. Working together enables us to grow rapidly, win, and serve the largest brands in the world. We use cutting edge technology to solve real-world problems for our clients and continue to pull ahead of the pack as the leading SaaS platform for businesses to automate their partnerships and grow their revenue like never before. We have an entrepreneurial spirit and a culture where ambition and curiosity is rewarded. If you are looking to join a team where your opinion is valued, your contributions are noticed, and enjoy working with fun and talented people from all over the world, then this is the place for you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;impact.com, the world’s leading partnership management platform, is transforming the way businesses manage and optimize all types of partnerships—including traditional rewards affiliates, influencers, commerce content publishers, B2B, and more. The company’s powerful, purpose-built platform makes it easy for businesses to create, manage, and scale an ecosystem of partnerships with the brands and communities that customers trust to make purchases, get information, and entertain themselves at home, at work, or on the go. To learn more about how impact.com’s technology platform and partnerships marketplace is driving revenue growth for global enterprise brands such as Walmart, Uber, Shopify, Lenovo, L’Oreal and Fanatics, visit www.impact.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role is exciting! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an Account Executive, you are responsible for growing our client base across all segments. You have a proven track record of consultative sales; being the trusted advisor; the ability to negotiate; a strong understanding of the digital landscape and a willingness to embrace disruptive, fast paced technology companies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you are excited about using your creativity, strategic, project management, and consultative selling skills to generate new business then this role will allow you to thrive and succeed. If this is you, we offer competitive compensation with generous benefits, a flexible remote working policy, and a supportive and committed team around you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learning, constantly&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospecting, always&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attending events and being a representative of the Impact.com brand&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leading with insight and delivering an exceptional prospect/ customer experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and grow your assigned territory while benefiting from the support of Marketing and Channels&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieving or exceeding individual quota bringing in new clients to Impact.com&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage multi-threaded sales-cycles engaging end users through to C-level executives and building the value of our product&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Define, execute, and own an engagement plan for key prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage your pipeline, dealflow, forecasting with vigor and accuracy &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All the while creating ‘irrational love’ amongst our customers&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Does this sound like you? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 3 years of closing sales experience, preferably within SaaS and performance marketing/ martech&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have a network of advocates that will support your success in this role&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to reach and develop relationships with decision makers within your territory and key verticals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prior experience driving sales and business development activities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the digital ecosystem landscape and relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of success in carrying an quarterly quotas and building and maintaining pipeline to achieve it&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Successful history of net direct new business sales, with the ability to prove consistent delivery against targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of over-achieving quota (top 10-20% of company) in past positions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in bringing innovative / market defining products to market within a competitive landscape&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The ability to collaborate across internal teams to achieve the business goals and objectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You are a contributor to the team culture &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel if needed and work autonomously in a remote environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience within performance, partner, or affiliate marketing is a plus&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits (Perks):&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Private health insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Office lunches&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Unlimited responsible PTO&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible work hours&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Free Affiliate &amp;amp; Partnerships Industry Fundamentals Certification by PXA.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An employee-led culture team that plans inclusive events &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mental Health and Wellness Benefit - Including 12 Therapy/Coaching sessions + Dependent coverage &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An established company with a cool, high-velocity work ethos, where each person can make a difference!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQF8DyON7WMEEw/company-logo_200_200/B4DZfEtwM6GsAM-/0/1751352018894/impactdotcom_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=FhehZoXkWuJVmssllc3lpAMnGkl2JSIbKOFBsplGU8Q', '2025-09-20T06:37:29.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recO3YuQfyWj1CQcO', 'Cuscal Limited', 'https://www.cuscal.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/cuscal', 'Sydney, New South Wales', 'Financial Services', '201-500 employees', '84', 'Cuscal Limited is a growth-stage fintech/payments provider (201-500 employees, Sydney HQ) actively hiring for Business Development Manager and Senior Business Development Manager roles—both high-priority core sales positions. The company operates in the core commercial B2B tech/fintech sector, aligning strongly with 4Twenty''s target market. Decision maker access includes senior commercial leaders and a Head of Strategic Growth (Tier 2), supporting recruitment engagement. Multiple strong growth signals are present: an upcoming IPO, major acquisition, executive sales leadership hire, and product innovation. This combination of sales hiring, industry fit, company size, decision maker quality, and clear growth trajectory makes Cuscal a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] On 22 August 2025, Cuscal announced plans to acquire Indue, another major Australian payments solutions provider, subject to regulatory approvals. This development signals consolidation in the Australian payments sector and is intended to further strengthen Cuscal’s presence and capabilities in the Sydney and national market[2].\n[LOCAL] Cuscal lodged a prospectus with ASIC for an Initial Public Offering (IPO) and planned ASX listing in Q3 2025, indicating a strategic move to access public capital for growth and expansion[2].\n[LOCAL] FY25 full-year and half-year results were released in recent months, reflecting ongoing financial transparency as Cuscal seeks to reassure investors and clients in Sydney and across Australia[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Cuscal appointed Michael Blomfield as Chief Client Officer in June 2024, an executive hire with broad experience in sales, client management, and operations, tasked with overseeing client and growth functions[1]. This signals increased focus on sales and go-to-market (GTM) expansion from Sydney HQ.\n[LOCAL] The company emphasizes supporting banks, fintechs, and corporates across Australia, leveraging its Sydney base to provide end-to-end payments, real-time payments, card issuing, and regulated data solutions[2].\n[LOCAL] Cuscal has highlighted digital enablement and infrastructure expansion in Sydney, supporting anticipated client and product growth, especially in real-time payments and open data ecosystems[2].\n[REGIONAL] The executive team has experience in APAC and global markets, but the current GTM expansion and hiring signals are strongly focused on Australia.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL] Cuscal has lodged an IPO prospectus with ASIC, aiming for an ASX listing, which would provide fresh funding and broaden its investor base[2].\n[LOCAL] No new private funding rounds were disclosed in the last 12 months prior to the IPO preparation.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Selected by major Australian financial institutions and fintechs as a trusted payments partner, with recent endorsements from Bendigo & Adelaide Bank, ING, and others, who highlighted “collaborative design” and “technological innovation” in the payments ecosystem[2].\n[LOCAL] Launched enhanced fraud monitoring platform leveraging AI and machine learning for real-time and card-based payments, a key milestone in regulated data and financial crime solutions[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Appointed Michael Blomfield as Chief Client Officer in June 2024, bringing explicitly client-facing and commercial leadership experience to Sydney HQ[1].\n[LOCAL] Appointed Bronwyn Yam as Chief Product Officer in May 2023 and Freya Smith as Chief Legal and People Officer in October 2022 to strengthen product innovation and people strategy[1].\n[LOCAL] Managing Director Craig Kennedy continues in his role since 2008, providing strategic continuity during the IPO and acquisition phases[1].\n\nIf you require competitor context or industry market trends for Sydney/AU financial services/payments, request the [INDUSTRY] scope."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our client’s success is our success. And you make it happen&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ever tapped your phone to buy a morning coffee, or made a purchase from your favourite online store? Chances are, we’ve made it happen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Cuscal, we’ve been at the forefront of payments innovation for almost 60 years, enabling seamless, secure solutions that millions of Australians rely on every day. From launching Australia’s first ATM to being the first certified Australian fast payments Payer and Initiator in 2022, we’ve always pushed boundaries - and we’re not stopping now.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are a listed public company (ASX:CCL) and one of five licensed banks in Australia with full direct connectivity and production capability across all domestic payment systems. Whilst the major banks leverage this capability for their consumer and business clients, our B2B model focuses on enabling other banks, fintech’s and corporates to deliver innovative and competitive payment and digital solutions to their clients and customers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a Business Development Lead to join our Client, Growth and Strategy team. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Business Development Lead is a senior leadership role within Cuscal’s Strategic Growth team, responsible for driving revenue growth to meet agreed targets, market expansion, and client acquisition across Cuscal’s core product domains - including Payments, Acquiring, Data and Card Issuing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This role combines strategic sales execution with leadership accountability, overseeing the performance, development, and enablement of Business Development Manager (BDM) and Jnr BDM. The Business Development Lead is instrumental in shaping and executing go-to-market strategies, building trusted client relationships, and positioning Cuscal’s solutions to meet evolving market needs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a highly visible role across Cuscal, with responsibilities sitting across four key areas:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Strategic Sales Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead the execution of Cuscal’s business development team, aligned with enterprise growth objectives and Product domain-specific priorities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet Cuscal new business revenue targets by identifying, pursuing, and closing high-value opportunities with a focus on early ramp and long-term value creation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Cuscal in market, including at industry events, forums, and strategic partner engagements.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product and Marketing to shape compelling value propositions and go-to-market narratives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Client Relationship Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain trusted relationships with senior stakeholders across the industry, positioning Cuscal as an innovative strategic partner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand client needs, challenges, and strategic goals to tailor solutions that drive mutual success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Sales Excellence and Operational Discipline&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Champion best-practice sales methodologies, CRM discipline (Microsoft Dynamics), and pipeline management.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate and timely reporting of sales activities, forecasts, and performance metrics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive the adoption of structured sales cadences, governance processes, and performance reviews.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure all business development activities comply with internal policies, legal standards, and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify, document, and mitigate operational and compliance risks in collaboration with Risk and Compliance teams.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales Enablement, Product, Marketing, Client Delivery, and Technology to ensure seamless client engagement and onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of sales content, playbooks, and training initiatives that support team effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide market feedback to inform product development and strategic planning.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated background in B2B sales and solutions, with understanding of financial services regulatory environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent ability to prospect and self-generate leads&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with CRM (Microsoft Dynamics)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of key local payments market trends&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Successful experience selling complex solutions with long sales cycles, demonstrating patience, persistence, and a consultative approach to client needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong track record of identifying and capturing new business opportunities, consistently achieving or exceeding revenue targetsments &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cuscal? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are in the rapidly evolving world of payments, and we are committed to providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. We support our colleagues with flexible work arrangements through our hybrid model whilst also offering a wide range of educational, financial, lifestyle, health &amp;amp; wellbeing benefits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Step &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you’re excited to join a company that’s shaping the future of how Australia moves money, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now and let’s explore who you are, what drives you and how you can contribute to our vision for the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cuscal is an equal opportunity employer committed to an equitable, diverse, and socially inclusive work environment and a positive, barrier-free recruitment process. We welcome applicants from an Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander heritage, people living with a disability, LGBTQIA+ and people from culturally diverse backgrounds to explore career opportunities with Cuscal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; Note: Cuscal does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruitment agencies or search firms.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHP8tG8bdvt-A/company-logo_200_200/B56ZkCaSCiHMAI-/0/1756682069751/cuscal_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=_Mtw0RU3xJvwIEsBhKYhglb1TudW1BHO8uE7lfAt5vc', '2025-09-29T14:21:51.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recO6QSf4FzyUCo1g', 'Databricks', 'https://databricks.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/databricks', 'San Francisco, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '5001 - 10000', '100', 'Databricks is a leading computer software company with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore, recently closing a $1 billion Series K funding round and launching new AI products. The company is experiencing rapid revenue growth, significant partner expansion, and is actively hiring for senior sales and business development roles across APAC. Multiple high-level sales leaders and decision makers are accessible, indicating immediate and ongoing demand for external recruitment support in sales and revenue teams.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nDatabricks exceeded a $4 billion revenue run-rate and surpassed $1 billion in AI product revenue in Q2 2025, with year-over-year growth over 50%. On September 8, 2025, the company announced the close of its $1 billion Series K funding round at a valuation above $100 billion, coinciding with the launch of new AI products and infrastructure aimed at enterprise agentic applications.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nFrom Q2 2024 to Q2 2025, Databricks expanded its consulting partner ecosystem by 31%, onboarding around 230 new partners. There was notable expansion among smaller organizations, with a 46% increase in partners employing 100-500 staff and 32% growth in those with fewer than 50 employees, reflecting active team and market growth.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nDatabricks closed a $1 billion Series K funding round in September 2025, co-led by Andreessen Horowitz, Insight Partners, MGX, Thrive Capital, and WCM Investment Management, valuing the company above $100 billion.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn September 2025, Databricks surpassed a $4 billion revenue run-rate, with AI product revenue running above $1 billion. The company also reported positive free cash flow and a net retention rate over 140%, with more than 650 customers generating $1 million or more in annual revenue.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Databricks is the Data and AI company. More than 20,000 organizations worldwide â including Block, Comcast, CondÃ© Nast, Rivian, Shell and over 60% of the Fortune 500 â rely on the Databricks Data Intelligence Platform to take control of their data and put it to work with AI. Databricks is headquartered in San Francisco, with offices around the globe, and was founded by the original creators of Lakehouse, Apache Sparkâ¢, Delta Lake and MLflow. \n\n---\nDatabricks applicants\n\nPlease apply through our official Careers page at databricks.com/company/careers. \n\nAll official communication from Databricks will come from email addresses ending with @databricks.com or @goodtime.io (our meeting tool)."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recOaTCofQpQHJhnv', 'InterSystems', 'http://www.intersystems.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/intersystems', 'Boston, Massachusetts, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '44', 'InterSystems is a growth-stage computer software company (2,023 employees) with operations in Australia and Singapore, fitting the commercial B2B tech profile. However, there is no evidence of an active sales role posting or recent sales team expansion in the region, and the filtered contacts include a Regional Director and a Director Customer Relations & Sales (Tier 1 and Tier 2), but also a dedicated APAC Recruitment Team Lead, indicating strong internal TA capability. Recent growth signals are limited to industry recognitions and product enhancements, with no funding or leadership changes. Overall, the likelihood of external recruitment for sales roles is low at this time.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nInterSystems received multiple recognitions from major industry analysts in 2024, including being named a Challenger in the 2024 Gartner Magic Quadrant for Cloud Database Management Systems and a Strong Performer in The Forrester Wave: Enterprise Data Fabric, Q1 2024. The company was also noted for bringing new generative AI functionality to its IRIS data platform[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nInterSystems reported a headcount of roughly 2,000 employees in 2024, with consistent revenue growth and over $1 billion in annual revenue, indicating ongoing business expansion[1]. No Australia-specific hiring or sales team expansion activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified. S&P Global notes that InterSystems is privately held and has been consistently profitable since 1979 with no external funding flagged in the last year[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOn 12 June 2024, Mirus Australia received the InterSystems Global Impact Award at the InterSystems Global Summit for its innovative use of InterSystems technology to improve data and operational efficiency in Australian aged care[2][3]. InterSystems’ IRIS platform also received multiple accolades in 2024 industry analyst reports[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes identified in executive, sales, or revenue roles globally or in Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"InterSystems, a creative data technology provider, delivers a unified foundation for next-generation applications for healthcare, finance, manufacturing, and supply chain customers in more than 80 countries. Our data platforms solve interoperability, speed, and scalability problems for large organizations around the globe to unlock the power of data and allow people to perceive data in imaginative ways. Established in 1978, InterSystems is committed to excellence through its 24×7 support for customers and partners around the world. Privately held and headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts, InterSystems has 39 offices in 28 countries worldwide. "}'::jsonb, 'LOW', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQFhEni_JauxUg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1631300968602?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=K11wdBoJDGxHHjZSS2YTaKBwH-YH043hgS6LatMmkjs', '2025-09-18T21:04:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recPSD9ew7Rb3iEK9', 'Cloudbeds', 'https://www.cloudbeds.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cloudbeds', 'San Diego, California, US', 'Hospitality', '501 - 1000', NULL, 'Cloudbeds operates in hospitality technology with a strong SaaS and software focus, aligning well with 4Twenty''s specialisation. The presence of a Sales Director in Australia and an APAC Team Lead in Singapore demonstrates established sales leadership in key markets. Recent industry awards and a strategic tech partnership signal ongoing relevance and potential for future hiring, though no immediate growth activity is identified.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCloudbeds announced a strategic data automation partnership with STR, a CoStar Group company, in June 2025 to enable seamless benchmarking and performance tracking for hoteliers. The integration allows Cloudbeds users to access real-time market data and analytics directly via STR dashboards[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn January 2025, Cloudbeds won five top honors at the 2025 HotelTechAwards, including Best Hotel Management Software, and was recognized as a finalist for Property Management System and Channel Manager, securing its position among the top technology vendors in the hospitality sector[1][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Cloudbeds is the leading platform redefining the concept of PMS for the hospitality industry, serving tens of thousands of properties in more than 150 countries worldwide. Built from the ground up to be masterfully unified and scalable, the award-winning Cloudbeds Platform brings together built-in and integrated solutions that modernize hotel operations & finance, distribution & marketing, guest experience, and revenue & analytics. Founded in 2012, Cloudbeds has been named a top PMS, Hotel Management System and Channel Manager (2021-2025) by Hotel Tech Report, Worldâs Best Hotel PMS Solutions Provider (2022) by World Travel Awards, and recognized in Deloitteâs Technology Fast 500 in 2024.\n\nCloudbeds will never offer employment without a formal interview process, and we will never request your banking details or money transfers of any kind via email or messaging app. Please be aware of scammers impersonating the Cloudbeds team and report any suspicious activity."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.601Z'),
    ('recPVSFVW4pynZOt4', 'JustCo', 'https://www.justcoglobal.com/about-us/our-brands/', 'https://sg.linkedin.com/company/justco', 'Singapore', 'Leasing Non-residential Real Estate,Real Estate', '201-500 employees', '54', 'JustCo is a growth-stage real estate company (201-500 employees) focused on flexible workspace solutions, actively hiring for roles such as Senior Sales Manager and Enterprise Sales Manager in Australia and Singapore. The industry is classified as an edge case tech vertical (coworking/real estate), limiting commercial B2B tech fit. However, the presence of multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Managers, Senior Sales Managers, Enterprise Sales Managers) provides strong access for recruitment. Recent expansion and sales activity in Australia signal moderate growth, but the lack of recent funding or leadership changes tempers immediate urgency. This is a medium-priority opportunity given the sales hiring activity, company size, and decision maker access, but with limited industry fit for core B2B tech recruitment.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] JustCo currently operates several major coworking centres in Sydney’s central business district—specifically at 135 King Street, 175 Pitt Street, and 60 Margaret Street—catering to businesses of all sizes, with a focus on flexibility and premium event spaces[2][3][4]. [LOCAL] These Sydney locations emphasize enhanced health and safety protocols, event hosting capacity (seminars up to 120 people), and amenities including modern meeting rooms, private phone booths, and secure bike storage[2][3][4]. [REGIONAL] JustCo has continued expansion in Australia with 18 coworking centres across Sydney and Melbourne, as part of its broader strategy for APAC market leadership[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Flexible membership plans and office customisation for Sydney businesses indicate active targeting of enterprise clients and start-ups alike, with visible accommodation for teams of varying sizes (from individuals to 120-person event capacity)[2]. [LOCAL] Sales and customer engagement processes are highlighted by the booking system requiring direct engagement with JustCo’s Sydney-based sales staff, indicating continued local hiring and sales activity[2][3]. [REGIONAL] The company''s commitment to continually investing in Sydney and Melbourne facilities signals ongoing growth in the Australian market[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding activities or investment rounds in the last 12 months could be identified in public sources specific to Australia or APAC.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney locations have enhanced their corporate event and seminar offerings, with dedicated event venues and updated health and safety measures consistent with current regulations[2][3][4]. [REGIONAL] JustCo’s APAC footprint now exceeds 40 coworking centres, positioning it as one of Asia’s leading flexible workspace operators with a strong Australian presence[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No leadership appointments, promotions, or departures specific to the Sydney or broader Australian JustCo team were identified in the last six months from available public sources. [REGIONAL] No regional C-level or sales executive changes relevant to Australia have been reported recently.\n\n[Note: All data reflects public reporting up to September 2025 and may not include internal or unpublished developments.]"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JustCo&lt;/strong&gt; is Asia Pacific''s leading provider of flexible workspaces for businesses of all sizes seeking flexible work solutions. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2011 and headquartered in Singapore, JustCo leads Singapore''s coworking scene with the largest network, offering close to 50 coworking centres across eight gateway cities in the region.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;JustCo empowers flexible work across our network of high-quality coworking centres in prime locations, seamlessly integrated with technology to enable our members to work from any of our premises. Beyond flexible workspace solutions, we also strive to be the place that works for all individuals and businesses, revolutionising how people work by providing a platform that fosters growth, connections, collaborations and opportunities for our ever-growing JustCo community and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Overseeing and managing sales from origination, closure and account management for all JustCo’s products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acquire new sales and achieve sales target&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tour customers to show the range of options available to suit their needs and closing the sale where possible&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work efficiently and effectively on all Key Performance Indicators in line with company procedures and guidelines&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Providing support to the sales team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prerequisites for the role include: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years’ of experience in Sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in co-working, serviced office, service apartments or developers or sales related industry is an advantage&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales driven and results oriented with excellent track record&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We will review your application and will contact you within two weeks if you are shortlisted for an interview.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spark your potential at JustCo! We believe work should be energizing and fulfilling. Our company values growth and offers endless possibilities to develop your career and yourself. Join our passionate team and discover a work environment that helps you thrive. This is the place that works for you.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEyTWrFMJj6_w/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1721267520807/justco_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=kkyz7y4TembRWt5dPTra3u9eFnf-F5y56jg0QTUAn_k', '2025-09-25T05:06:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recPp5YVsJNNsW5XA', 'Canon Australia', 'https://www.canon.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/canon-australia', 'Macquarie Park, NSW', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '501-1,000 employees', '64', 'Canon Australia is a growth-stage IT Services and IT Consulting company (501-1,000 employees) with multiple ongoing sales and account management roles, such as Account Manager and Government Account Executive, indicating steady hiring. The industry fit is strong secondary tech, and the company operates in a highly commercial B2B environment. There is access to Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (General Managers, Sales Directors, Sales Managers), supporting recruitment engagement. While local growth signals are present (recent product launches, steady hiring), there are no recent funding rounds or major leadership changes, and the roles are not primary target SDR/BDR/AEs. This makes Canon Australia a solid but not top-tier recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] On 24 March 2025, Canon Production Printing Australia launched a new **2-year Manufacturer’s Warranty** for Arizona Flatbed and Colorado M-Series printers, including Melbourne-based sales and service, signaling a focus on supporting business growth and customer satisfaction across Australia and New Zealand[2]. \n[LOCAL] Canon’s Melbourne site (Clayton VIC) remains central for sales, service, and support for production printing and large format solutions, serving the city and broader Oceania region[3]. \n[REGIONAL] Canon Australia has maintained its sales and service footprint in both Australia and New Zealand, focusing on innovations in large format graphics, technical printing, and business solutions[2][3]. \n[LOCAL] The Canon Experience Store and SUNSTUDIOS Melbourne continue to provide direct retail access and product demos despite Canon’s shift away from online direct-to-consumer sales in Australia[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Canon Production Printing Australia employs approximately 75 staff and is actively recruiting for roles in Melbourne, with ongoing career opportunities listed on company channels—indicating continued staff investment[3]. \n[LOCAL] Recent months have seen job listings for team member roles in Melbourne as of September 2025, suggestive of steady local hiring and corporate activity[5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No publicised new funding or significant investment events impacting Canon Australia in the past 12 months. Canon Inc. (global parent, Japan) traditionally funds regional expansion via operating revenue and strategic capital allocation rather than through external rounds.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Canon Australia’s community and corporate engagement remains active, with its Canon Oceania Grants program providing $5,000 packages to Australian and New Zealand recipients, reinforcing its local CSR presence in 2025[6].\n[LOCAL] The implementation of an extended manufacturer’s warranty for key printing systems as of March 2025 is positioned as a customer-focused milestone for the Melbourne market[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] No high-profile leadership changes or executive appointments linked specifically to the Melbourne or broader Australia sales, revenue, or people operations have been publicly announced in the last 6-12 months.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian IT services and IT consulting market remains competitive in 2025, with demand for business process outsourcing, cloud services, and managed print/production solutions growing as enterprises focus on efficiency and hybrid work environments. Vendors are differentiating via service reliability, sustainability, and extended customer support packages—represented by recent warranty expansions and direct engagement with corporate accounts.\n\n**Scope notes:**  \n- All trigger events and most growth signals are [LOCAL] to Melbourne or Australia.  \n- Recent achievements span [LOCAL] and [REGIONAL] activities.  \n- Industry context included as company-specific funding and executive data is minimal in recent cycles."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be part of a collaborative Account Management team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Genuine flexibility and autonomy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Join a highly regarded and respected brand&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Canon is the world''s leading imaging organisation. As a Fortune 500 Company, we actively inspire people with imaginative ideas that enable you to connect, communicate and achieve more than you thought possible.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you join us, you’ll find a rewarding culture that values you. You’re empowered to focus on your career progression and turn your goals into reality. You’ll be an integral part of the group’s success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an Account Executive managing a portfolio of Enterprise clients, you will play a vital role in supporting customers across Canon’s core business and solutions offerings, with a strong focus on delivering exceptional service and driving revenue growth throughout Victoria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this role, you will both develop and execute business plans to engage potential key clients in line with our broader business strategy and take full ownership of managing and growing an existing portfolio of top-tier accounts. You will also contribute to shaping the strategic sales plan to meet revenue targets and support sustainable, profitable growth across a range of products and services.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of the role includes:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow accounts for customers you bring on board, as well as those assigned to you&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of new business opportunities and plan and execute Business plans with potential key Customers to deliver against the overall Business strategy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise with any new or existing customers and the business to input to the development of the strategic sales plan to grow, meet and exceed sales and revenue targets and achieve profitable growth commitments across several product and service offerings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively generate new business through a variety of go to market strategies and core propositions as well as the development of new business leads through the sales cycle&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve customer additions, revenue and profit objectives/budgets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate major deals and develop submit tender response within policy guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop business engagement models and identify opportunities for business improvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and steer opportunities for business improvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Report performance to budget with variance analysis and revised projections&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribute to, and devise the development/implementation of sales strategies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend and present at relevant seminars and other customer focussed events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams both locally and interstate, to deliver a seamless customer experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Management of the sales process from initial order through to implementation and beyond&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate major deals and submit tenders within policy guidelines &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You are a motivated sales professional—whether you’re an experienced enterprise account executive or someone earlier in your sales career, ready to take the next step. You have a passion for developing new business, building strong customer relationships, and driving results. Adaptable and commercially minded, you thrive in a dynamic environment and can confidently engage a wide range of stakeholders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are open to considering both seasoned professionals and ambitious candidates looking to grow into this role. To be successful, you will bring:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales experience in Major Accounts / Tier 1 Enterprise Accounts or a strong track record in existing and new business development&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of cross-selling, up-selling, and value-based selling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exposure to selling managed services and/or solutions (preferred but not essential)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage and support stakeholders across opportunities and accounts, both locally and interstate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and relationship-building skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good financial and analytical thinking with commercial awareness&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive, self-managed approach with a strong drive to achieve results&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, influencing, and negotiation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confident presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and resilience in a dynamic sales environment &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Canon will invest in you by providing an inclusive learning environment to support you through continual growth and career development. With the foundation of a globally recognised, award-winning and trusted brand as your platform for success, it’s up to you to grab this opportunity with both hands!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As well as a great career with a globally recognised company, Canon offers:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible working arrangements where suitable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Training and development opportunities to help you bring your goals to life&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Performance Recognition in the form of quarterly and annual awards programs for high-performers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus Leave, including:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Birthday leave, to celebrate, relax or do something special.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Canon Day, an extra day of leave during the Christmas holidays.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Kyosei Day, or volunteer leave to take a paid day off to do good in your community.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Milestone recognition on your work anniversaries includes carbon credits, merchandise, or retirement fund rewards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discounted Canon products, offered at a significant saving.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An employee referral scheme rewarding you for recommending great candidates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Eligibility for specific benefits and perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Canon Group and the country where you work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If this sounds like you, we’d love you to apply!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in the power of an inclusive and diverse workforce. We trust you will bring your authentic self to work, and we will focus on making sure that together, we make a strong contribution to the broader community in which we operate. Where possible, flexible working arrangements are the norm, as we know a better work-life balance can improve your motivation, performance, and productivity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an equal opportunity employer, all applicants will be considered. Benefits/perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Canon Group and the country where you work. All applicants must be eligible to work in the country they are applying to at the time of application.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Looking to join this diverse team? Apply online now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Successful applicants will be notified of next steps"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHeyTVokV8R0g/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1689115608092/canon_australia_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=D0ijUfD8IW2XV8FRPtoaHGICflA-RIrVJwDsS5ozx8A', '2025-09-20T06:27:43.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recPuoZlvtQnucnpl', 'AsiaPay', 'https://www.asiapay.com', 'https://hk.linkedin.com/company/asiapay-limited', 'Hong Kong, China, HK', 'Financial Services', '51 - 200', '53', 'AsiaPay is a growth-stage fintech company (144 employees) specializing in digital payment solutions, with a recent award indicating industry recognition but no strong recent growth signals. The current hiring trigger is not specified, but the presence of a Regional Head of Operations (Tier 1 decision maker) in Singapore provides quality access for recruitment discussions. While the fintech industry is a strong fit and company size is ideal, the lack of clear sales role hiring and limited growth signals result in a medium recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAsiaPay was honored with the title of \"Best Digital Payment Solution Provider - Asia\" at the Global Brands Magazine Awards 2025[2]. This recognition highlights the company''s continued leadership position in the Asian digital payments market.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"AsiaPay is a global leading, award-winning digital payment and technology provider, trusted by thousands of banks and merchants in Asia for over two decades. Partnering with over 100 banks and payment companies and checkout platforms, we have been empowering businesses by offering simplified, integrated and customized payment solutions that optimize sales and productivity.\nAs a trusted digital payment partner, we help businesses thrive globally by reducing complexity and enhancing operational efficiency. From small businesses and startups to multinational corporations, our innovative technologies ensure secure payment transactions while driving growth and maximizing business potential.\nIn 2019, AsiaPay launched AsiaPay Capital, an incubation program dedicated to fostering innovation in the technology space. Through this initiative, we support and drive the growth of cutting-edge financial technology collaboration and adoption in Asia and beyond. \n\nCorporate Websites:\n\nGlobal:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com\n\nHong Kong (Head Office):\nhttps://www.asiapay.com\nhttps://www.paydollar.com\n\nAustralia:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com.au\nhttps://www.paydollar.com.au\n\nChina: \nhttps://www.asiapay.com.cn\nhttps://www.paydollar.com.cn\n\nIndia:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com\nhttps://www.paydollar.in\n\nMalaysia:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com.my\nhttps://www.paydollar.com.my\n\nPhilippines: \nhttps://www.asiapay.com.ph\nhttps://www.pesopay.com\n\nSingapore:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com.sg\nhttps://www.paydollar.com.sg\n\nTaiwan:\nhttps://www.asiapay.com.tw\nhttps://www.paydollar.com.tw\n\nThailand:\nhttps://www.asiapay.co.th\nhttp://www.siampay.com\n\nVietnam:\nhttp://www.asiapay.com.vn\nhttp://www.paydollar.com.vn"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recPx9DiWLf0TDEk0', 'Podium', 'https://www.podium.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/podium', 'Lehi, Utah, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '83', 'Podium is a growth-stage computer software (SaaS) company with 1,453 employees and active operations in Australia, fitting the ideal commercial B2B tech profile. The presence of multiple Tier 1 (Country Manager) and Tier 2 (Sales Managers, VP Strategy & Operations) decision makers provides strong access for recruitment engagement. The inclusion was triggered by the Sales Development Representative role, a primary target for 4Twenty. Recent product launches and platform integrations signal ongoing growth, though there are no explicit recent funding or headcount surges. This makes Podium a high-priority recruitment opportunity with strong but not maximum urgency.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nPodium released several new features in 2025, including enhanced AI lead follow-up and integrations with platforms like Shopify, CDK CRM, and Angi to better serve auto dealerships, HVAC, and plumbing businesses. The company is also focusing on expanding automated workflows and lead management solutions for its user base.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nPodium''s product updates and ongoing investment in platform integrations suggest active team and market expansion, although no explicit recent hiring or headcount growth data is available for 2025. Product development activity remains high, particularly in customer communication and lead management technology.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo new funding rounds or financial milestones have been publicly announced in the last 6-12 months. The most recent significant funding was a $201M Series D closed in November 2021, raising Podiumâs valuation above $3 billion.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nKey recent product milestones include the launch of new AI-powered lead management, two-way Gmail and Outlook email integration, advanced Shopify and CDK CRM integrations, and features to improve team collaboration, reported from November 2024 through August 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures have been identified in the past year."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"A few years back, Eric (Co-Founder and CEO) got a frustrated call from his dad. His dadâs tire shop had plenty of happy customers, but only a handful of angry ones were leaving reviews. So we built a product that made getting more reviews as easy as sending a text.\n\nLaunching in 2014, we set out to solve the same problem for local businesses everywhere, but we realized that messaging with customers wasnât just the better way to get reviewsâitâs the better way to do business. Weâve since built a multi-product platform thatâs modernizing the way local business gets done. \n\nWe are here to provide local businesses with everything they need to win. Get more reviews, collect payments, send text marketing campaigns, and centralize your communicationsâall from one easy-to-use platform.\n\n#Podium #PodiumLove #LocalBusiness #TheFutureIsLocal\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recPzVeptocHxysKy', 'Rapid7', 'https://r-7.co/3i5nlhP', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rapid7', 'Boston, Massachusetts, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '1001 - 5000', '69', 'Rapid7 is a growth-stage computer & network security company (3,143 employees) with active operations in Australia and Singapore, hiring for roles such as Enterprise Account Executive and Sales Development & Enablement Manager. The industry fit is strong (core B2B tech/cybersecurity), and the presence of Tier 1 (VP/GM APJ) and Tier 2 (Sales Director ANZ, Regional Sales Director ASEAN) decision makers provides high-quality access. While there are moderate growth signals (modest customer/revenue growth, product launches, industry recognition), there are no recent funding rounds or explicit hiring surges. The sales roles are high-priority, making this a strong but not top-tier recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \nRapid7 announced the general availability of InsightCloudSec and InsightAppSec in the AWS Marketplace AI Agents and Tools category in July 2025, targeting organizations scaling generative AI initiatives with a focus on security and compliance[1]. No major strategic partnerships, mergers, or acquisitions were disclosed in the past 6-12 months.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \nCustomer count grew modestly year-over-year, from 11,484 to 11,643 as of June 2025[1]. Annualized recurring revenue per customer increased by 2%, suggesting upselling and expansion within the existing customer base[1]. No explicit hiring announcements or significant GTM (go-to-market) team expansion details were made public in recent months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \nNo new funding rounds or major investment announcements were reported in the last 6-12 months. Rapid7 continues to generate positive cash flow, with $48 million net cash from operating activities and $42 million free cash flow in Q2 2025[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \nIn July 2025, Rapid7 was named a Leader in the 2025 Frost Radarâ¢ for Managed Detection and Response (MDR), recognized for deep integration between MDR and exposure management, as well as AI-powered SOC innovations[1][2]. In Q3 2025, Rapid7 was also recognized as a Strong Performer in The Forrester Waveâ¢: Unified Vulnerability Management Solutions[3]. In June 2025, the company announced embedding agentic AI workflows within its next-gen SIEM and XDR platform[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \nNo public announcements regarding executive hires, promotions, or departuresâparticularly in sales, revenue, or people leadership rolesâwere identified in the last 6-12 months. Corey Thomas remains CEO as of August 2025[1]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Hereâs a new cybersecurity posture: in full command. Rapid7 can help you command your attack surface, smash silos, stay steps ahead of attackers, and take breaches from âinevitableâ to preventable. The Command platform, AI-powered technology, elite 24/7 services, and Rapid7 Labs prized research give control to organizations around the world. You can reduce vulnerabilities. Automate routine tasks. See imminent threats coming. And shut them down with confidence."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQEJp1SPwGu3Im0', 'One Identity', 'https://www.oneidentity.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/one-identity', 'Aliso Viejo, CA', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '62', 'One Identity is a growth-stage software company (501-1,000 employees) in the core B2B tech sector, currently hiring for an Enterprise Account Executive role. The company has strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers in-region (Country Manager ANZ, Regional Sales Director, Sales Director), providing solid access for recruitment discussions. However, there are no recent APAC-specific growth or hiring signals, funding rounds, or leadership changes, and all recent achievements are global rather than regional. While the role and company fit are strong, the lack of local hiring momentum limits immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] No major public announcements, new offices, or local event sponsorships from One Identity in Australia or broader ANZ in the last 6-12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] One Identity was named an Overall Leader in the KuppingerCole 2025 Leadership Compass for Identity Fabrics and as a Leader in the 2024 IGA Leadership Compass Report, reflecting ongoing global recognition of its unified identity security platform[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] No evidence of significant new sales hiring or team expansion specific to Australia or the wider APAC region in available sources.  \n[GLOBAL] One Identity maintains a focus on enterprise growth and ongoing investment in product development, including the launch and active support of Identity Manager 9.x product lines with continued technical and customer support[5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There are no announcements of recent funding rounds, financial milestones, or major M&A activity tied to the APAC region or globally within the past year. The company continues to operate as a leading provider in the identity management segment[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] One Identity Manager 9.3.1 received full support as of July 2025, with several other product releases and lifecycle updates in 2024–2025, indicating commitment to ongoing innovation and customer support[5].  \n[GLOBAL] KuppingerCole positioned One Identity as a Leader in both the 2024 IGA and 2025 Identity Fabrics Leadership Compass reports, signaling product maturity and industry recognition[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] No public announcements of Australia/APAC leadership appointments, promotions, or departures in the last 6-12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] No significant recent global executive changes specific to sales, revenue, or regional management roles have been disclosed in available sources.\n\nSCOPE INDICATOR SUMMARY:\n- Most relevant information within the last 12 months is **global** in scope due to limited public news on APAC or Australia-specific activities.\n- Product lifecycle management and continued award recognition remain strong global signals of stability and strategic focus.\n- Industry context: The Australian market is highly focused on digital identity and cybersecurity, with government and private sector investing in identity frameworks, though no direct tie-in to One Identity activity was reported in 2025[3].\n\nIf you require broader industry context or wish to track future APAC hiring or local partnerships from One Identity, monitoring local technology news and company press releases is recommended."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"OverviewAt One Identity, we create and manage the software that makes the benefits of new technology real. Companies turn to us to manage, modernize, and secure their business, from on-prem to in-cloud, from the heart of the network to the vulnerable endpoints. From complex challenges like Active Directory management and Office 365 migration, to database and systems management, to redefining security, and hundreds of needs in between, we help you conquer your next challenge now.We are currently looking for an Enterprise Account Manager to be a part of our Software Sales Team based in Sydney. The role is focused on building deeper and wider relationships across Australia and New Zealand.ResponsibilitiesAs an Enterprise Account Manager, you are selling the \" Value\" of One Identity products through building sales strategies, account and opportunity plans for existing customers and potential prospects. You will be responsible for the achievement of the sales strategies put in place, through the identification of key decision makers and leveraged opportunities. In addition, you will be responsible for creating sales campaigns into large accounts and closely coordinate company executive involvement with customer management. You have the talent to identify and qualify leads, as well as generate new business opportunities contributing to the overall business quota both on an annual and quarterly basis.Your success is also due to your ability to collaborate and maintain C-level strategic relationships so we can ensure our brand position is maximised with customers and partners.Qualifications Minimum of 6 years working in Enterprise Accounts and ideally selling Identity Governance Solutions  A proven \"hunter\" successfully working through a complex sale cycle  Experience in \" value selling\" within dynamic environments  Proven successful sales achievement in both sales targets and establishing relationships.  Experience developing opportunities in Enterprise Accounts in Australia and New Zealand  Superior negotiation and relationship management skills  S ales development and expansion into geographically defined mid-market organisations focused on attainment and over-achievement of assigned quarterly sales targets.  Ongoing prospecting and lead generation to attain new customer acquisition, and highly effective support and management of existing customers  Be continually and consistently generating new pipeline and to be self-motivated and results-oriented. This also requires the skills and capability to nurture, develop, and close numerous opportunities and deals.  Close alignment and engagement with Distribution Partner and Channel Partners, with a particular focus on opportunity and deal support  Be creative and innovative, and contribute to particular Program initiatives and marketing activities.  Accurate and timely updates of all opportunities and activities with SFDC. Provision of accurate and consistent forecasting throughout the Quarter and Fiscal Year.  Prepares and delivers meaningful and credible business justifications and executive summaries to key decision-makers, including, when required, clearly and effectively articulating ROI and total cost of ownership.  Possesses the skills and experience to recognise customer business problems and drive/influence appropriate solutions and resources to resolve  Ensure timely and accurate communications to Customers, particularly regarding problem resolution and pricing information and details.  Be comfortable and capable of engaging with other internal functions, including Presales, PS, Marketing, Sales Operations, Deal Desk, and Legal   Why work with us! Life at One Identity means collaborating with dedicated professionals with a passion for technology.When we see something that could be improved, we get to work inventing the solution.Our people demonstrate our winning culture through positive and meaningful relationships.We invest in our people and offer a series of programs that enable them to pursue a career that fulfills their potential.Our team members’ health and wellness are our priority, as well as rewarding them for their hard work. One Identity is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances.Come join us. For more information, visit us on the web at http://www.One Identity.com/careers. Job seekers should be aware of fraudulent job offers from online scammers and only apply to roles listed on One Identity.com/careers using our applicant system. Note: We do not use text messaging or third-party messaging apps like Telegram to communicate with applicants, so please exercise caution if you are approached in this way and only interact with people claiming to be One Identity employees if they have an email address ending in @One Identity.com. You can report job scams to the FTC (ReportFraud.ftc.gov) or your state attorney general."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-23T14:25:48.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQIS4X2GSc5PHRh', 'Monotype', 'http://www.monotype.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/monotype', 'Woburn, MA, US', 'Design', '501 - 1000', '62', 'Monotype is a growth-stage design technology company (1,585 employees) with commercial B2B offerings and active expansion in APAC, including Australia and Singapore. The current sales role trigger is ''Enterprise Sales Manager,'' a high-priority core role. The company fits as a strong secondary tech (font management software, e-commerce platform) but not core B2B SaaS. Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Manager, Enterprise Sales Manager) are present in both Australia and Singapore, supporting recruitment engagement. Growth signals include major acquisitions, APAC expansion, and leadership appointments, but no recent funding. This represents a medium-priority recruitment opportunity due to strong decision makers and expansion, but the industry fit is not fully core commercial B2B tech.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nMonotype acquired Fontworks, a major Japanese type foundry, in July 2025 and will rebrand Fontworks Inc. as Monotype KK on March 31, 2025 to expand its presence in Japan and Asia[3][1]. On July 8, 2025, Monotype also partnered with Wix to extend its font library for Wix customers and announced the acquisition of 27 font families from Sharp Type[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent press indicated Monotype is expanding through acquisitions, including Fontworks and Sharp Type, and onboarding new creative teams and talent such as Colophon Foundry[1][3]. The company is investing in its flagship e-commerce platform MyFonts.com by retiring legacy sales sites (Linotype, Fontshop, Fonts.com) over the next year to streamline and scale its commercial offering[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOn February 12, 2025, Monotype released its \"2025 Type Trends Report: Re:Vision\" highlighting the global cultural impact of design[2]. Monotype also launched its Creative Partner Program, announced major industry collaborations (including Lippincott and NYC Pride visual identity), and received increased industry recognition for its type design and research into the emotional impact of typography[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nMarie Boulanger was appointed to lead the design team with a focus on design-led campaigns in 2025[1]. Sina Otto was named Creative Type Director based in Berlin, and Fontworksâ President Fuminobu Sato is now part of Monotype leadership in Japan following the acquisition[1][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Monotype brings brands to life through type and technology that consumers engage with every day. \n\nThe company''s rich legacy includes a library that can be traced back hundreds of years, featuring famed typefaces like Helvetica, Futura, Times New Roman and more. \n\nMonotype also provides a first-of-its-kind service that makes fonts more accessible for creative professionals to discover, license, and use in our increasingly digital world. We work with the biggest global brands, and with individual creatives, offering a wide set of solutions that make it easier for them to do what they do best: design beautiful brand experiences."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQN7Zy5ZgfqXSZq', 'Cvent', 'https://bit.ly/3vyiQnI', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cvent', 'Tysons Corner, VA', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '87', 'Cvent is a growth-stage SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) in the commercial B2B tech sector, actively employing a Business Development Representative (BDR) in Melbourne, which is a primary target role. The company has strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers in-region, including a Senior Director/Country Head and multiple Regional Sales Managers. Multiple growth signals are present: ongoing APAC expansion, local leadership, recent product launches, and a growing customer base. These factors, combined with a high-priority sales role and strong industry fit, make this a very high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Cvent opened its Melbourne, Australia office in early 2017, marking a strategic on-the-ground presence for supporting local clients in meetings and event management technology[1][2][3].\n[LOCAL] As of May 2024, Cvent continues to play an active role in Melbourne’s business events ecosystem and participates in high-profile events such as the Asia-Pacific Incentive and Meetings Expo (AIME) at the Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre[1][4].\n[REGIONAL] The company reports that event professionals in Australia and New Zealand are showing strong optimism about in-person meetings and business events growth heading into 2025, supported by the newly published Cvent Event Industry Report (2025)[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Cvent’s Melbourne office directly supports a customer base that includes local enterprise names such as Microsoft Australia, Cotton On Group, and Salvation Army of Australia[1].\n[LOCAL] Jack Ukil serves as Senior Director and Country Head of Cvent Australia, highlighting ongoing leadership presence locally[4].\n[REGIONAL] With more than 3,000 users across Australia and New Zealand and a growing demand for its event tech, Cvent continues to build local account management and delivery teams, focusing on both event planners and hospitality customers[2].\n[GLOBAL] The company has a stated intention of aggressive global hiring; in the most recent disclosed period, Cvent aimed to add 200 new employees (globally), with multiple roles anticipated in Melbourne to support the expanding APAC market[3].\n[GLOBAL] Cvent’s worldwide operations encompass 12 offices across four continents, demonstrating broad capacity to support ongoing expansion efforts[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding or investment rounds specific to Australia or the APAC region are reported in the last 12 months in available search results.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Cvent celebrates key client wins in Australia including enterprise contracts and active participation in AIME Melbourne, where it showcases innovations such as the Cvent Express Challenge (demonstrating rapid event setup using Cvent’s platform)[1].\n[REGIONAL] Launched the “Cvent Top 50 Meetings Hotels in APAC” list, with Australian venues featuring prominently, evidencing Cvent’s influence on venue sourcing and industry benchmarking in the region[2].\n[GLOBAL] Significant product innovations include rollout of Cvent Flex (new registration website building tool), enhancements to the Cvent Supplier Network, and the introduction of a new Business Intelligence Platform for event and hospitality clients, all of which underpin Cvent’s competitive positioning in Australia and APAC[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Jack Ukil, as of 2024, is Senior Director and Country Head for Australia, providing ongoing executive leadership with a mandate to expand local operations[4].\n[REGIONAL/GLOBAL] No recent changes to senior APAC or Australia-specific leadership were disclosed in the last 12 months in available search results.\n\n---\nIf you require additional information on compensation, technical teams, or more granular recent hiring activity in Melbourne, please indicate, as specific AU hiring data for Cvent is not disclosed in recent public sources."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;Cvent is a leading meetings, events and hospitality technology provider with more than 4,800+ employees and nearly 22,000 customers worldwide. Founded in 1999, the company delivers a comprehensive event marketing and management platform for event professionals and offers software solutions to hotels, special event venues and destinations to help them grow their group/MICE and corporate travel business.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The DNA of Cvent is our people, and our culture has an emphasis on fostering intrapreneurship -- a system that encourages Cventers to think and act like individual entrepreneurs and empowers them to take action, embrace risk, and make decisions as if they had founded the company themselves. We foster an environment that promotes agility, which means we don’t have the luxury to wait for perfection. At Cvent, we value the diverse perspectives that each individual brings. Whether working with a team of colleagues or with clients, we ensure that we foster a culture that celebrates differences and builds on shared connections.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We have an opening for an Account Manager, whose main responsibility will be managing existing client accounts. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be tasked with identifying and closing sales opportunities with the clients you manage, such as contract renewals, up-sells, cross-sells, etc. Additionally, you will provide a high level of quality of service to our customers. You will be required to demonstrate solution-selling skills and effectively manage internal relationships with the Sales and Client Services departments to ensure complete customer satisfaction and meet sales objectives.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In This Role, You Will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and close sales opportunities with our clients, such as contract renewals, cross-sells, and up-sells (such as adding additional apps to clients’ packages), etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Present products and services information to corporate accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure relationships with key decision-makers for accounts that will provide business are continuously developed and relationships are strengthened and grown&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Sales and Client Services teams to ensure complete customer satisfaction with the Cvent product and organization&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure customer issues are acknowledged and resolved within 24 hours&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Call on existing clients in an effort to meet and exceed individual and department revenue expectations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developand actively pursue list of targeted Key Accounts within Australia and New Zealand and create individual plans of action to penetrate these accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set aggressive goals for annual revenue achievement against each account&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accurately forecast sales opportunities via pipeline report&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively and accurately manage personal revenue pipeline to maximize all business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report sales activity within the system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here''s What You Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years of experience in customer-facing, revenue-generating role (more is welcomed)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task and ability to work in a dynamic, fast-changing entrepreneurial environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be able to integrate knowledge across disciplines to include relationship management, consultative selling, product demonstrations, closing contracts, operation/process flow, and product function&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High degree of computer literacy is a must&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is not a technical position. Relevant experience might include selling CRM or CMS systems, ASP based data systems, Travel or Meeting Planning Services&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with MS Office Suite (Word, PowerPoint, Excel) and Salesforce.com or similar contact management software&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling or managing accounts in SaaS/technology/hospitality space a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working in the Event Management industry a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQGfyppgQzdZ0A/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1688478119198/cvent_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=yd_n5AlMk81mbaQKT5BxfWkG7D_L9zFL4ZwPvROmsgU', '2025-09-23T14:17:11.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQWbfQj864D5k0w', 'Prophet', 'https://www.prophet.ml', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/prophet-ml', 'Cremorne, Victoria, AU', 'Computer Software', '51 - 200', NULL, 'Prophet operates in the core computer software and AI sector, recently securing $30 million in Series A funding to scale its AI SOC platform, indicating strong growth potential. The company has a Strategic Growth Lead and Executive Chairman based in Australia, demonstrating local leadership and sales focus. While there are no explicit sales hiring signals, the combination of recent funding, platform launch, and industry accolades suggests imminent expansion and recruitment needs in technology and sales domains.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nProphet Security announced a $30 million Series A funding round in August 2025, led by Accel, to launch its agentic AI SOC platform for automating security operations. PRophet (a Stagwell company) completed integration of UNICEPTA into its suite in June 2025, expanding its global media intelligence capabilities and rebranding these offerings under PRophet Media Intelligence.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHiring and team expansion are implied through customer growth and platform launch activities at Prophet Security, as they scale their AI SOC platform after significant new funding. No explicit recent sales/GTM hiring or headcount data identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nProphet Security raised $30 million in Series A funding led by Accel in August 2025, with participation from Bain Capital Ventures and other strategic investors.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nProphet Security was named to the 2025 Redpoint InfraRed 100 list for shaping the future of enterprise infrastructure. PRophet earned the 2024 Webby Award, PRovoke Media''s Innovation SABRE, and was listed on PR News'' 2024 Tech Hotlist.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Prophet is the world''s most advanced, real-time predictive analytics platform. We utilise Nobel Prize-winning mathematics to connect millions of data relationships driving consumer purchase behaviour to predict the most efficient and cost-effective ways to influence them.\n\nFor the first time ever, major global brands and businesses down to scale-ups are now able to accurately measure, forecast and scenario plan their entire marketing mix from offline to digital â and even understand the impact of one channel on another. With third-party cookies set to become a thing of the past, Prophetâs approach to predictive analytics is an invaluable toolkit for all marketers and business leaders."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQvsT7FoBkYkJnf', 'MediaForm', 'https://www.mediaform.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/mediaform-technology-suppliers', 'Glendenning, New South Wales', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '11-50 employees', '48', 'MediaForm is a small, growth-stage IT Services and Consulting company (11-50 employees) with ongoing operations in Australia, currently employing an Account Manager (medium-priority sales role). The presence of a NSW Sales Manager (Tier 2 decision maker) supports recruitment access, but there are no recent growth signals, funding, or hiring surges reported. The industry fit is strong secondary tech, but limited expansion or hiring activity tempers the immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] **No publicly reported major business developments specific to Brisbane in the past 6-12 months.** MediaForm maintains an active Brisbane office at Unit 3, 246 Evans Road, Salisbury, QLD 4107, which continues operations as part of its national footprint[1].  \n[REGIONAL] **No regionally announced expansions, funding rounds, or strategic changes across Australia or APAC within the last year.**  \n[GLOBAL] **No global-level developments (such as global expansion, major partnerships, or financial milestones) impacting regional operations reported in the last 12 months.**\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] **Continued presence in Brisbane with a dedicated office and contact lines, indicating ongoing local business activity[1].** No evidence found of major local hiring drives, new team expansions, or changes to the Brisbane footprint in the past 6-12 months.  \n[REGIONAL] **Offices remain active in SYDNEY (head office), BRISBANE, and MELBOURNE,** suggesting consistent operational coverage across the key Australian markets[1]. No notable spikes in regional hiring or sales/GTM-focused role postings located in recent information.  \n[GLOBAL] **No recent headcount, hiring surges, or international expansion signals reported.**\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL][REGIONAL][GLOBAL] **No evidence of recent funding rounds, investments, or significant financial milestones at the Brisbane, Australia, or global company level for MediaForm in the past year.** The company appears to operate as a privately held entity without recent publicized external fundraising[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] **No Brisbane-specific product launches, awards, or new partnerships reported recently.**  \n[REGIONAL] MediaForm holds key ISO certifications—**ISO 14001 (environmental management)** and **ISO 27001 (information security)**—valid across offices and highlighted in its recent public-facing materials as of 2025, supporting customer trust in IT and consulting service delivery[3].  \n[GLOBAL] **No major new product lines, partnerships, or global awards cited in the last year.**  \n[INDUSTRY] The company continues to position itself as \"a supplier of the biggest range of printers, computers and technology products in Australia at the most competitive prices,\" with activity focused on business-to-business IT hardware, print, and technology supply[5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL][REGIONAL][GLOBAL] **No public announcements regarding executive appointments, departures, or leadership changes related to MediaForm at the Brisbane, national, or global level in the past 12 months.** The only named contact from current public company records is Nadir Hussain, linked to overall company operations[2].\n\n---\n**Summary of available intelligence:**  \nAll verifiable activity points to ongoing, stable operations across MediaForm''s Queensland (Brisbane), New South Wales (Sydney HQ), and Victoria (Melbourne) offices, specializing in the supply of IT hardware, print devices, and related consulting services. As of September 2025, there are no signs of major local/regional restructuring, funding, or headcount growth triggers. The company maintains sector-relevant ISO certifications and continues to operate as an independent, privately held supplier within the Australian IT services and consulting spaces[1][2][3][5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;Company Description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;MediaForm Pty Ltd, proudly 100% Australian owned and operated, has been a pioneer in the printing and IT/Office Supplies industry for 30 years. With a comprehensive distribution network throughout Australia and globally, MediaForm partners with industry-leading brands like HP, Lexmark, Samsung, and Microsoft. The company provides a full range of IT solutions including hardware, software, and managed print services, tailored for enterprise, SMB, and B2B customers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Role Description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, on-site role located in Brisbane, QLD, for an Account Manager. The Account Manager will be responsible for managing client relationships, understanding client needs, and providing tailored solutions. Daily tasks will include developing and executing account management plans, identifying growth opportunities, handling client queries, and coordinating with internal teams to deliver exceptional service. The role requires effective communication, strategic planning, and continuous engagement with clients to ensure satisfaction and retention.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Qualifications&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and relationship management skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in Sales, Account Management, or Customer Service&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and execute strategic account plans&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the IT/Office Supplies industry and products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CRM software and Microsoft Office Suite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and time management skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree in Business, Sales, Marketing, or a related field is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with brands such as HP, Lexmark, Samsung, and Microsoft is a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQGkWbCRKWkLAA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1725943946180/mediaform_technology_suppliers_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=VYEvUOOpu1p4t1_nMUwn9yacpsUcA31qWFvqo43OiwY', '2025-09-23T14:29:29.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recQwj40ouWKORhgD', 'Contentsquare', 'https://bit.ly/4fB0vux ', 'https://fr.linkedin.com/company/contentsquare', 'Paris, , FR', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '84', 'Contentsquare is a growth-stage computer software (SaaS) company with 1,870 employees, fitting the ideal target profile for external recruitment. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers in Australia and Singapore (Regional Sales Directors, SVP Head of Sales-APJ, Country Sales Manager, Regional VP ANZ, Head of Enterprise ANZ) provides strong access for recruitment engagement. While the specific triggering sales role is not listed, the company’s recent platform launches, major acquisition, and large Series F funding round signal robust growth and ongoing hiring needs. This is a high-priority opportunity for commercial B2B tech sales recruitment.', true, false, '{"content":"Based on the available information, here is the business intelligence for Contentsquare:\n\n**RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:**\nContentsquare launched the most significant upgrade to its Experience Intelligence platform in November 2024, introducing advanced AI features and a new freemium model. The company signed a definitive agreement to acquire Loris AI in July 2025 to expand into conversation intelligence and AI agent analytics.\n\n**GROWTH SIGNALS:**\nThe company has accelerated innovation with more than 580 people working in Product and R&D as of June 2024. Contentsquare serves more than 1,300 leading brands and powers insights for over 1.3 million websites worldwide, indicating strong market penetration and growth.\n\n**RECENT FUNDING:**\nThe company completed a $600 million Series F funding round in 2022, backed by leading investors including BlackRock, SoftBank Vision Fund 2, KKR, and others. No more recent funding rounds were identified in the available information.\n\n**RECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:**\nAnnounced new Experience Intelligence platform in June 2024 that connects four analytics domains for the first time. Unveiled refreshed brand identity and platform releases at CX Circle Paris event on November 7, 2024, marking a new era for the unified platform.\n\n**LEADERSHIP CHANGES:**\nJonathan Cherki continues as CEO and Founder, with Lucie Buisson serving as Chief Product Officer as of June 2024. No specific recent executive changes or new hires were identified in the available information."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Contentsquare is the all-in-one experience intelligence platform designed to be easily used by anyone that cares about digital journeys. With our flexible and scalable platform, you quickly get a deep understanding of your customers’ whole online journey. \n﻿\nOur AI-powered insights provide those “ah ha” moments you need to deliver the right digital experiences. You get to work faster and smarter, with the confidence to know what to do next to improve.\n\n﻿Leading brands use Contentsquare to grow their business, deliver more customer delight, and move with greater efficiency in a constantly changing world. Our insights optimize the experience on over 1.3 million websites worldwide.\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:18:53.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
