    ('recS8Awqr8lwNmhzP', 'Elastic', 'http://www.elastic.co', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/elastic-co', 'San Francisco, California', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'Elastic is a growth-stage commercial B2B tech company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong operations in Australia and Singapore. The trigger role is APJ Sr Manager, Sales Development, a primary target sales role. The industry fit is excellent (core SaaS/AI/software). Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including Country Manager, Regional VP, and several Sales Directors. Recent growth signals include major ANZ partnerships, robust revenue growth, and regional leadership appointments. While internal TA exists, the scale and regional expansion indicate a strong likelihood to use external recruitment for sales hiring, making this a high-priority opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Elastic announced a major partnership with Tech Data (TD SYNNEX) on 23 July 2024, making Tech Data its first value-added distributor in Australia and New Zealand (ANZ). The alliance is designed to accelerate AI solution adoption across the region, leveraging Elastic’s Search AI Platform and Tech Data’s Centre of Excellence for tailored support and go-to-market strategies[1].\n[REGIONAL] Elastic revealed winners for its 2025 Partner Awards in ANZ, highlighting a strong partner ecosystem and local engagement: Recon Technologies (ANZ Partner of the Year), NQRY (Innovation Award), Amazon Web Services Australia (Cloud Partner), ctrl:cyber (Managed Services), Atturra (Reseller), Skillfield (Services), and Deloitte (Systems Integrator)[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Gavin Jones serves as Country Manager for Elastic in Australia and New Zealand, indicating dedicated regional leadership focused on market growth[2].\n[LOCAL] Elastic’s partnership strategy in ANZ is expanding, particularly through major hyperscaler alliances with Microsoft, Google, and AWS, plus options for on-premises deployment, relevant to highly regulated or security-sensitive Australian sectors[2].\n[REGIONAL] Elastic is emphasizing the need for accelerated generative AI adoption in Australia, referencing a commissioned report showing 87% of Australian organizations plan increased AI investment in 2024, but adoption rates remain behind Singapore and India (42% of Australian organizations vs. 63% in Singapore and 81% in India), suggesting significant market development potential[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Elastic posted FY25 revenue of $1.483 billion (17% YoY growth) and Q4 revenue of $388 million (16% YoY growth, with Cloud revenue up 23% YoY). Robust performance was attributed to sales execution and growing demand for generative AI solutions, with deferred revenues and cash balances also increasing[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] The 2025 Elastic Partner Awards recognized numerous ANZ partners for their roles in driving growth and digital transformation: Recon Technologies, NQRY, AWS Australia, ctrl:cyber, Atturra, Skillfield, and Deloitte[4].\n[LOCAL] Elastic’s technology powers many daily Australian digital experiences, including finance and travel platforms, and now supports 50% of Fortune 500 companies globally[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Gavin Jones is identified as the key Country Manager for Australia and New Zealand, actively driving Elastic’s market strategy and evangelizing generative AI adoption across the region[2].\n[GLOBAL] There are no reported global executive changes directly impacting ANZ in recent months, though CEO Ash Kulkarni cited strategic focus on AI-driven sales and innovation velocity[3].\n\nScope indicators have been used to clarify regional vs. local relevance per instructions."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Elastic, the Search AI Company, enables everyone to find the answers they need in real time, using all their data, at scale — unleashing the potential of businesses and people. The Elastic Search AI Platform, used by more than 50% of the Fortune 500, brings together the precision of search and the intelligence of AI to enable everyone to accelerate the results that matter. By taking advantage of all structured and unstructured data — securing and protecting private information more effectively — Elastic’s complete, cloud-based solutions for search, security, and observability help organizations deliver on the promise of AI.What Is The RoleAt Elastic, we see endless possibilities in a world of endless data. And we use the power of search to help people and organizations turn that possibility into results. Elastic is the leading platform for search-powered solutions. With solutions in Enterprise Search, Observability, and Security, we help improve customer and employee search experiences, keep critical applications running smoothly, and protect against cyber threats. Elastic enables organizations worldwide to use the power of Elastic, including Netflix, Uber, BBC, Microsoft, and thousands of others.Elastic was built on a foundation of being free and open, which trickles down to how we work. We’re a distributed organization and have been from the beginning. Being distributed isn’t just a way of doing business—it’s a mentality that is at the core of our culture.Elastic is searching for an energetic, motivated Enterprise Account Executive to acquire new business as well as expand our existing Elastic accounts within the Federal Government space. This position will report into the RVP of Public Sector Sales for ANZ.You will work alongside a talented sales team, collaborate with technical and marketing teams, and leverage the power of Elastic''s solutions to meet the needs of clients.What Will You Be DoingBuilding awareness and driving demand for Elastic solutions within Federal Government accounts, by helping users and customers derive value from their data setsServing as an evangelist for our Open Source offerings while communicating and demonstrat