ere for our Privacy Statement.Different people approach problems differently. We need that. Elastic is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, ethnicity, color, religion, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, protected veteran status, disability status, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local law, ordinance or regulation.We welcome individuals with disabilities and strive to create an accessible and inclusive experience for all individuals. To request an accommodation during the application or the recruiting process, please email candidate_accessibility@elastic.co We will reply to your request within 24 business hours of submission.Applicants have rights under Federal Employment Laws, view posters linked below:Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA) Poster; Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) Poster; and Employee Polygraph Protection Act (EPPA) Poster.Please see here for our Privacy Statement."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-20T14:27:22.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recS9H9M74PqRg8yO', 'Airwallex', 'http://www.airwallex.com', 'https://hk.linkedin.com/company/airwallex', 'Global, , HK', 'Financial Services', '1001 - 5000', '70', 'Airwallex is a growth-stage fintech company (1,999 employees) with strong commercial B2B fit, actively expanding its global footprint and product offerings. The company is experiencing rapid growth, evidenced by recent funding ($300M Series F), major acquisitions, and significant revenue/transaction volume increases. While the specific sales role is not detailed, the context suggests ongoing sales and GTM hiring. Multiple mid- to senior-level decision makers are present, supporting recruitment engagement. The combination of high-priority industry, company size, and strong growth signals makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAirwallex acquired OpenPay in early 2025 to expand its billing capabilities and compete directly with Stripe Billing, with the new offering to be rolled out by Q4 2025. The company also gained a capital markets services license in Singapore, expanded to markets such as Japan, Korea, the UAE, and Latin America, and launched a partnership with Arsenal FC in May 2025 to handle international supplier payments and expense management.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAirwallex reported 80%+ year-over-year growth and surpassed $900 million in annual recurring revenue as of Q3 2025, expecting to exceed $1 billion by Q4. Their North America and Europe business grew over 200% YoY, and they have onboarded 150,000 businesses with a goal of reaching over one million active customers by 2030, signalling rapid expansion in sales and GTM activities.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nIn March 2025, Airwallex raised $300 million in a Series F funding round, increasing its valuation to $6.2 billion and bringing total funding to over $1.2 billion.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAirwallex crossed $200 billion in annualized transaction volume in August 2025, reflecting a 92% increase year-over-year, and launched several product updates including billing and point-of-sale terminal rollouts. The company also launched \"Airwallex Yield\" for business customers in Singapore and accelerated its AI-driven infrastructure strategy.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Airwallex is a leading global payments and financial platform for modern businesses, offering trusted solutions to manage everything from business account, payments, treasury, and spend management to embedded finance. \n\nWith our proprietary infrastructure, Airwallex takes the friction out of global payments and financial operations, empowering businesses of all sizes to unlock new opportunities and grow beyond borders. \n\nProudly founded in Melbourne, Airwallex supports over 150,000 businesses globally and is trusted by brands such as Brex, Canva, Rippling, Navan, Qantas, SHEIN and many more. For more information, visit http://www.airwallex.com"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recSYYXmbmN26F1F8', 'Ingenico', 'http://www.ingenico.com', 'https://fr.linkedin.com/company/ingenico', 'Suresnes, Ãle-de-France, FR', 'Financial Services', '1001 - 5000', '55', 'Ingenico is a growth-stage financial technology company (4,251 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, recently launching new payment solutions and expanding through global partnerships. However, there is no evidence of active sales or GTM hiring, and no recent funding or leadership changes. The filtered employee list does not reveal clear Tier 1 or Tier 2 decision makers. While product innovation and market expansion are positive growth signals, the lack of explicit sales hiring and decision-maker access limits immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn March 2025, Ingenico launched the AXIUM CX9000, a new all-in-one integrated POS device, aiming to simplify payment integration for merchants and partners. In Q1 2025, Ingenico partnered with Crypto.com to pilot crypto payment acceptance at POS, with planned rollout across major global regions.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nIngenico remains active in 32 countries and employs over 3,300 people, signaling continued organizational scale. Recent product launches and partnerships suggest ongoing investment in technology and global market reach, but no specific recent hiring surges in sales or GTM roles identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nLaunched the AXIUM CX9000 integrated POS device in March 2025 and initiated a crypto payments solution in partnership with Crypto.com targeting global expansion in Q1 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Ingenico is the global leader in payment acceptance and services. We support our customers, and their customers to do more with payments. Active in 32 countries, with over 3,000 employees we have been at the forefront of the commerce landscape for over four decades. With more than 40 million payment devices deployed worldwide, powered by over 2,500 apps, the company is servicing the needs of millions of consumers every day. Through our advanced integrated solutions and network of partnerships, we simplify the world of payments and bring value added services to move commerce forward."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recSqLSjmTGzhAe5t', 'COSOL', 'https://cosol.global/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/cosol', 'Brisbane City, Queensland, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '201 - 500', '67', 'COSOL is a growth-stage IT & Services company (310 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively expanding through acquisitions and major ERP projects. The presence of decision makers such as the Group COO and Regional Executive (Tier 1 and 2) provides high-level access for recruitment. While no explicit core sales role is listed in the data, the company''s ongoing business development activities and participation in large industry events signal ongoing sales hiring needs. Recent acquisitions and robust revenue growth forecasts further support a high likelihood of external recruitment for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCOSOL forecasted robust revenue growth between 16-19% for fiscal 2025, potentially reaching AU$121 million, though stock dropped 5% in August 2024 to its lowest point since November 2022. The company celebrated its 25th anniversary in 2024 and underwent brand consolidation efforts to unify several acquired companies under one vision.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nCOSOL has been actively expanding through strategic acquisitions, integrating multiple brands including WMS, AssetOn, Clarita Solutions, Core Asset, AddOns, and most recently Toustone since 2020. The company participated in major industry events including MINExpo 2024 in Las Vegas, targeting over 44,000 mining industry professionals for business development.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCOSOL announced the acquisition of Toustone in December 2024, an Australian data analytics and predictive analytics company to enhance data-driven performance capabilities. In April 2024, the company acquired Core Asset, an asset performance advisory firm, expanding capabilities in strategic planning and decision support across natural resources, utilities and agribusiness sectors. The company also partnered with the Australian Department of Defence to deliver the largest ERP implementation in the Southern Hemisphere using SAP S/4HANA.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nScott McGowan serves as CEO and Managing Director and has been actively representing the company in media appearances and industry discussions about AI adoption in July 2025. Anthony Cipolla from COSOL was featured in AI-related discussions in July 2025, though specific role details were not provided."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"COSOL is a trusted, data-led asset management partner for organisations that canât afford to fail. \n\nWhy our customers choose us\nThere are four reasons we hear time and time again: deep industry expertise, dependable delivery, advanced digital capabilities, and the way we work as true partners. With over 25 years of experience, we combine all four -  including AI, data, and proprietary software - to help our clients reduce downtime, improve performance, and optimise the full asset lifecycle with confidence.\n\nWho we serve\nWe donât work with every industry - we serve the ones that canât afford failure, like natural resources, utilities, infrastructure, transport, defence and government.\n\nWhat we do\n1. Asset Management Servicesâ  - Reliable support you need to keep operations moving - from strategic planning to hands-on improvement. When performance, safety, and uptime are on the line, expert insight and dependable execution matter most.\n\n2. Digital Asset Management - Dependable data integrity, system optimisation, and AI-led insights - because in asset-intensive industries, you canât afford decisions based on anything less than trusted, high-quality data. \n\n3. Asset Management as a Services (AMaaS) - COSOLâs unique AMaaS offering combines 25+ years of proven global expertise, proprietary software, and best-in-class technology - delivered through a dependable partnership that keeps your operations running continuously at peak performance. \n\nHow we do it\nThese six pillars define how COSOL shows up, delivers outcomes, and earns your trust.\n1. Reliable Assets\n2 . Reliable People \n3. Reliable Advice \n4. Reliable Data -\n5. Reliable Technology\n\nWhere others advise, we go beyond and deliver - on site, in the field, at the source. Lets connect: https://cosol.global/about-us/contact-us/"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z')
