    ('recSuMplfXu9VL2VO', 'Objective Corporation', 'https://www.objective.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/objective-corporation', 'North Sydney, NSW', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '73', 'Objective Corporation is a growth-stage commercial B2B software company (201-500 employees) with strong industry fit, focused on SaaS and compliance-driven solutions for government and regulated sectors. The inclusion is triggered by the active Business Development Manager role, which is a medium-priority sales role. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including Sales Directors and Regional Directors, providing high-level access for recruitment. The company shows strong growth signals through product launches, regional expansion, and consistent headcount growth, though no recent funding rounds are noted. This combination makes Objective Corporation a high-priority recruitment opportunity for sales talent acquisition.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Objective software is actively used by Victorian public sector agencies including implementing Objective RegWorks for Wage Inspectorate Victoria to enforce anti-wage theft regulations and assist Victorians in recouping over $2 million in the first two years of use, highlighting engagement and sector impact in Melbourne and wider Victoria[4].\n[REGIONAL] In July 2025, Objective announced the acquisition of Isovist to extend capabilities in the planning and building sector, which will impact offerings across Australia and New Zealand[2].\n[REGIONAL] Objective continues to grow visibility in Southeast Asia through partnerships (e.g., with Innovation.is) to expand digital governance and compliance solutions for APAC customers, showing regional expansion focus as of February 2025[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Objective maintains active partnerships and long-term service contracts with Victorian and Australian regional government bodies, including recent product launches and compliance-driven deployments (notably Wage Inspectorate Victoria and regulatory agencies)[4].\n[REGIONAL] Objective held its annual employee conference “Activate” in 2024 to promote cross-team collaboration and strengthen corporate values, signaling ongoing community and team-building initiatives for staff in Australia and APAC[4].\n[GLOBAL] Employee headcount reached 450 in 2024 across all subsidiaries, up from previous years, demonstrating consistent organic growth[1].\n[LOCAL] Objective invested in a state-of-the-art commercial office fit out, fostering collaboration and innovation, with local references to Melbourne activities[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No evidence of major funding rounds or recent capital raises in the past 6–12 months. Objective Corporation remains a publicly traded company on the ASX (ASX:OCL), with revenue of AUD $117.5M in FY2024[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Objective RegWorks supported Wage Inspectorate Victoria in enforcing landmark state wage theft legislation, directly impacting the Victorian workforce and regulatory environment[4].\n[REGIONAL] Objective Keystone was highlighted in October 2024 for supporting climate disclosure compliance among Australian and regional financial services as climate reporting legislation advanced[4][5].\n[REGIONAL] Objective launched purpose-built planning platform “Objective Build” at PIA Congress 2025, signaling product innovation for the Australian urban planning market[3].\n[GLOBAL] Objective continues to add major financial services and regulated entities to its customer roster as showcased at the Asia Risk Congress in August 2024[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] No public announcements regarding leadership appointments or departures within the Melbourne office or global executive team in the past 12 months. Tony Walls remains CEO and Executive Chairman as of the latest filings[1].\n[LOCAL] Increased visibility of women leaders through local events, panels, and leadership showcases, indicating diversity and talent development focus at city and state levels[3].\n\nIf you require further detail or proprietary information on sales/GTM specific hiring in Melbourne, direct vacancy/job board information may be needed, as there were no explicit local executive appointments or sales function expansions published in the last 6–12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Objective , we create software that makes a difference. With over 400 people and five development labs spread across Australia, New Zealand, the United States of America, and the United Kingdom, Objective is a leading developer of SaaS solutions for the government.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Business Development Director - Content Solutions will be based in Melbourne and is responsible for sourcing new customers for Australia wide. They achieve this by aligning and understanding business processes while leveraging senior relationships to develop business opportunities in the public sector and regulated industries.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role reports to the VP, Sales (ANZ) and is an individual contributor with no people management responsibilities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day In Your Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate domain expertise in the public sector and regulated industries while providing value and insight to key stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve annual revenue targets for the sale of software and professional services.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop appropriate pipeline to achieve current and future year’s quota.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage a strong network and develop relevant industry contacts and influencers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records in sales tools such as Salesforce (CRM) and TAS (opportunity management).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continually develop Strategic Sales Skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support Objective team members involved in sales processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with functional teams in pre-sales, services, product management, and marketing to respond to tenders, bids, and opportunities to grow revenue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver an effective Territory Plan.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Skills, Experience And Beyond&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven sales ability, including outstanding negotiation skills and ability to persuade at all levels of business, including GM, CEO, CIO, CFO, Dept. Heads etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experienced in Solution Selling, Strategic Selling or Challenger Selling methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative approach to selling with highly developed interpersonal/relationship-building skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Able to manage and execute long sales cycles (6-24 months).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced user of corporate sales tools (Salesforce, TAS, etc.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work arrangements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discounted health insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rich learning and enablement programs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A team culture built on directness, support, openness, and shared success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular team events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A gender-equal and inclusive workplace&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you do not tick every box, do not let that stop you. We value potential, learning agility, and diverse perspectives just as much as experience, and we encourage you to apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Objective, we recognise and celebrate our diverse team as pivotal to our strong employee engagement and our high-performing culture, underpinned by Our Values .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on any protected characteristics or on any other basis prohibited by applicable laws in the regions where we operate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To ensure a positive experience, please inform our Talent Team of any adjustments or accommodations you may require during the recruitment process, so we can support you effectively."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQF7whw6w5LRHA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1631356460568?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=-TDvmKWx3HJ0ASETVXp7kQToUBcC2XQkRo4aRfY5Uhk', '2025-09-23T14:36:25.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recT2Mf2dcw1vgqUg', 'Cisco ThousandEyes', 'https://www.thousandeyes.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/thousandeyes', 'San Francisco, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '54', 'Cisco ThousandEyes is a growth-stage computer software company (995 employees) with operations in Australia, actively employing Enterprise Account Executives and Senior Account Directorsâcore sales roles. The industry fit is strong (core B2B tech), and filtered employees include Tier 2 decision makers (Regional Sales Leader, Senior Account Director). However, there are no recent funding rounds or explicit sales hiring surges, and the company operates under Cisco''s large enterprise structure, which may limit external recruitment needs. Product expansion and AI-driven enhancements signal moderate growth, making this a medium-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCisco ThousandEyes announced major product integrations and AI-driven enhancements at Cisco Live 2025 in San Diego, including the integration of Cisco AI Assistant, new partnerships with Splunk for unified digital resilience, and broader platform coverage for industrial networks and cloud environments as of June 2025. These moves mark a deeper strategic alignment between Ciscoâs observability stack and digital experience assurance capabilities[1][2][3][4][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo direct headcount expansion or sales/GTM hiring activity has been publicly reported in the past 6-12 months. Product expansion into industrial, Android, and Azure environments indicates ongoing resource investment and signals focus on enterprise market growth[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investments, or financial milestones have been announced for Cisco ThousandEyes in the last 12 months. The company remains under the Cisco corporate structure following its 2020 acquisition. No recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn June 2025, ThousandEyes launched major AI-powered features such as the Cisco AI Assistant for automated troubleshooting, along with enhanced integration across Cisco products and with Splunk, and new solutions for industrial and mobile network assurance[1][2][3][4]. These advancements set new industry standards for digital experience visibility and operational efficiency.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nJoe Vaccaro continues to serve as VP and GM of Cisco ThousandEyes as of mid-2025, with public appearances at major events such as Splunkâs .conf25 in Boston. No recent executive hires, promotions, or departures have been announced within sales, revenue, or people operations roles[5]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Cisco ThousandEyes empowers organizations to assure every digital experience across every network, everywhere, every time. With built-in AI and powerful ecosystem integrations, ThousandEyes enables IT teams to proactively detect, diagnose, and resolve issues before they impact end-user experiences.\n\nThousandEyes is deeply integrated across Cisco''s entire technology portfolio and beyond, enabling customers to deploy at scale while delivering assurance across Cisco''s industry-leading Networking, Security, Collaboration, and Observability solutions.\n"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recT56BHmREZUPvwp', 'Employment Hero', 'https://www.employmenthero.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/employment-hero', 'Sydney, NSW', 'Technology, Information and Media', '501-1,000 employees', '97', 'Employment Hero is a growth-stage SaaS company (501-1,000 employees) headquartered in Sydney, actively hiring for multiple Sales Development Representative (SDR/BDR) and Account Executive roles—core priorities for 4Twenty. The business operates in commercial B2B tech (HR/payroll SaaS), with strong Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers present (GM Revenue, CRO, Head of Sales, Sales Managers, SDR Managers). Recent growth signals include surpassing $250M ARR, major product launches, international acquisitions, and ongoing local hiring surges. This combination of high-priority roles, ideal industry fit, quality decision makers, and strong organic growth makes Employment Hero an immediate and top-tier recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Surpassed **$250M AUD in annualised recurring revenue** as of February 2025, with Sydney serving as headquarters and core product and engineering activities[1].  \n[LOCAL] Rolled out significant **payroll innovations and AI-powered products** throughout 2024–2025, such as Intelligent Payroll and SmartMatch, tailored for Australian compliance scenarios[1].  \n[LOCAL] Processed more than **$125 billion in payroll for over two million employees** in Australia and globally during 2024[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Acquired Humi, a Canadian HR/payroll platform, in early 2025 to expand global reach; product updates and learnings expected to benefit AU customers[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Multiple new roles posted in 2025 for **HR Support Consultants, Product Owners, and Group Engineering Managers**—positions in Sydney and across Australia, signaling local team expansion, notably in product, engineering, and client support[2].  \n[LOCAL] Remote-first model continues, but Sydney remains a strategic site for talent and leadership roles[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Over 300,000 business customers and two million employees managed on the platform across ANZ and APAC[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new public funding rounds reported in the last 6–12 months; recent growth cited as organic and product-driven[1]. Employment Hero previously raised capital for international growth, but most 2025 developments are based on revenue milestones[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Released the **Employment Hero Annual Jobs Report 2025**, offering real-time workforce insights for SMEs in Australia, highlighting demographic changes and gig/multiple job trends[3].  \n[LOCAL] Six of the top ten feature updates in 2024–2025 were based directly on Australian and global customer feedback, including dashboard customization for Australian teams[1].  \n[LOCAL] Launched the **Hero Foundation**—an initiative connecting marginalized Australian job seekers with roles via AI matching and partnerships with local organizations, aiming for 1 million placements by 2034[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Introduced “Employment Hero Jobs,” a talent marketplace with video profiles for fast matching[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/GLOBAL] No Sydney- or Australia-specific C-suite or executive changes publicly disclosed in the last 6–12 months. **Ben Thompson** continues as CEO and co-founder, driving local and global vision[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Leadership focus remains on product innovation, AI adoption and local market customization[1].\n\nIf you require specific contact names in Sydney or additional filtering by sales/GTM roles, please clarify. Current signals point to **continued hiring across technical and client-facing roles in Australia** and strong local, regional, and global product-led momentum."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Employment Hero is on a mission to make employment easier and more valuable for everyone. Our Employment Operating System brings hiring, HR, payroll and benefits into an all-in-one solution.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since our inception in 2014, we’ve scaled to a $2 billion valuation and gained a presence in 6 countries globally - Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Malaysia, the UK and Canada. We now service over 300,000 businesses and more than 2 million employees.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The EH Way&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Employment Hero, we’re proud of our unique DNA, which we call The EH Way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Mission First - everything we do (from what we work on, to how we allocate capital and where we focus) is driven by our Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Remote First - we champion a remote environment with a preference for asynchronous communication and a high degree of autonomy&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are AI First - we are committed to using AI to accelerate our mission; AI is not just a tool, it’s a fundamental part of how we operate, innovate, and scale&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Apolitical - we do not take a position on political or social topics, unless it relates to our Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We Live by Our Values - we role model our values 100% of the time&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We Expect High Performance - we set a high standard and we’re not satisfied with being average&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Kickstart your sales career: $72k base, $128,640 OTE uncapped, 140%+ achievable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Inbound Sales Development Representative, you’ll be working with our ANZ sales team under the guidance of a Sales Development Manager and will be instrumental in shaping and driving a surge in qualified leads and opportunities, contributing directly to our bold goal of transforming workforce management at Employment Hero. Through strategic prospecting, engaging communication, and strong relationship-building, you’ll empower businesses to thrive and employees to excel with our innovative solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role must be based in Australia.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Your key focus areas will be:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualify and Convert Inbound Leads - Efficiently assess and qualify inbound leads to ensure they meet ideal customer profiles, then book high-quality meetings for the sales team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Activity Targets - Consistently generate a set number of qualified opportunities per month, contributing to overall revenue and sales growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fast &amp;amp; Effective Lead Response Time - Engage with inbound leads promptly to maximise conversion rates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CRM Accuracy &amp;amp; Data Management - Maintain up to date and accurate records of lead interactions and progress in the CRM to support sales forecasting and decision-making.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This will include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Initiating contact with potential customers through inbound inquiries to source new sales opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conducting discovery calls to effectively understand customer needs and requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Routing promising opportunities to the appropriate Account Executives for further development and closure&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conducting thorough account research, identifying key decision-makers, and generating interest in our offerings&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and growing your prospect database within your assigned segment&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborating on delivering engaging online demos to prospects as needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;To thrive at Employment Hero, you’ll need to embody The EH Way - operating with focus, agility, and an obsession with impact. For this role, you’ll also bring:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in high-volume inbound sales (B2B)Familiarity with tools like LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Lusha, ZoomInfo, and Outreach&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of consistently exceeding targets&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong phone presence and resilience, comfortable with spending significant time on the phone&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skillsStrong listening and presentation abilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task, prioritise, and manage time effectively&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Employment Hero, we don’t just talk about a better way to work - we live it. Joining Employment Hero means:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will work remotely, with the flexibility to own your time and impact&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will access cutting-edge tools to amplify your work, knowledge and outputs &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll surround yourself with ambitious, outcome-driven colleagues who challenge you to do the best work of your life&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll own ESOP (employee share options) in one of the world’s fastest-growing tech companies &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll also have access to a wide range of benefits that includes: a very generous paternity leave policy, subsidised egg freezing (so you can make the choice that’s right for you, on your terms), a WFH office expense budget, and outstanding learning &amp;amp; development opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;At Employment Hero, we are committed to safeguarding the privacy of your application data. To understand how we do so, you can read our Applicant Privacy Policy here: https://employmenthero.com/legals/applicant-policy/&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Employment Hero celebrates diverse perspectives and experiences, we invite people of all backgrounds and identities to apply for this position.&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEMgvBwgbKtjQ/company-logo_200_200/B56ZWHcbs2HQAI-/0/1741734133378/employment_hero_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=Bgq_oiUm3944eqPXw-_b3CvVUnStif7iYGOsSUXJK9g', '2025-09-28T03:57:59.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recTVzsxGJIQx64gY', 'ESET Australia', 'http://www.eset.com/au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/esetaustralia', 'North Sydney, New South Wales', 'Computer and Network Security', '11-50 employees', '44', 'ESET Australia is a small (11-50 employees) computer and network security company in North Sydney, actively expanding its enterprise-facing product suite and engaging in local partnerships. The filtered contacts include a Director of Channel Partnerships (Tier 2 decision maker) and a Sales Operations Lead (support role). No active core sales role hiring is indicated, and the company operates in a strong secondary tech sector (cybersecurity). While growth signals are present (product launches, awards, partnerships), the small company size and lack of direct core sales role hiring limit the immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] ESET Australia launched **ESET Cybersecurity Awareness Training** targeting Australian businesses in September 2025, with deep integrations for employee education and phishing simulations specifically designed for local organisations[1].\n[LOCAL] On July 22, 2025, ESET Australia announced the winner of its fourth annual **Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship**, supporting STEM students in Sydney and presented in partnership with the Australian Cyber Security Centre at their North Sydney office[2].\n[LOCAL] ESET Software Australia, headquartered at Level 20, 111 Pacific Highway, North Sydney, was recognised as **Gartner Peer Insights Customers’ Choice for Endpoint Protection Platforms** in 2025, reflecting uptake and satisfaction among Australian enterprise clients[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] ESET Australia continues to grow, indicated by investments in local talent via scholarships and training programs, plus expanding its enterprise-facing product suite with new training and awareness solutions[1][2].\n[REGIONAL] ESET’s President for Asia Pacific and Japan, Parvinder Walia, cited ongoing commitment to expanding support and diversity initiatives in Australia and more broadly in APAC, including through scholarships and collaborative events with government agencies[2][3].\n[LOCAL] ESET demonstrated engagement with government and industry leaders—e.g., collaboration with the Australian Signals Directorate and ACSC at events hosted in North Sydney, indicating elevated local market engagement[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding rounds were publicly disclosed for ESET in Australia or APAC in the last 12 months. Globally, ESET operates privately with no announced IPO or major fundraising activity impacting Australian operations in this period.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] ESET Australia was named **Customers’ Choice in the 2025 Gartner Peer Insights “Voice of the Customer” report** for endpoint protection, specifically in the segment of organisations with $50M-$1B annual revenue[4].\n[LOCAL] Launch of **ESET Cybersecurity Awareness Training** in September 2025, delivering new employee resilience and phishing simulation capabilities to Australian enterprises[1].\n[LOCAL] Ongoing partnership and event-based collaboration with government cybersecurity leadership (ASD, ACSC) for scholarships and CXO-level outreach[2].\n[REGIONAL] The Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship expanded to additional APAC countries (Singapore, India) in 2025, signalling ESET’s intent to bolster regional thought leadership in workforce diversity[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No public executive changes or new appointments in the Australian office were announced in the last 12 months. However, Parvinder Walia remains President, Asia Pacific and Japan, and continues to actively represent ESET at key regional events and launches in Sydney[2][3].\n[LOCAL] Recent involvement of Stephanie Crowe (Head of Australian Cyber Security Centre, ASD) in ESET events and program presentations highlights close ties between ESET Australia and local government security leadership, but Crowe is not an ESET employee[2].\n\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian cybersecurity sector continues to signal acute talent shortages, with recent reports estimating a demand for 5,000 more cybersecurity professionals per year and prioritising diversity, education, and resilience-building solutions—areas in which ESET is actively investing through local partnerships and programs[2][3][1]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get to know us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At ESET Australia, we like to think of ourselves as friendly cybersecurity heroes – keeping businesses and individuals safe in an increasingly digital world. Our Aussie team is a key part of the APAC region, working alongside our colleagues in Singapore, Tokyo, and India. But we’re not just about tackling cyber threats; we’re about connecting cultures, ideas, and people.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re a tight-knit, friendly crew. Our stunning North Sydney office, with its breathtaking view of the harbour, makes for a pretty epic place to work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We work hard, but we know how to have a good time too. We’re a bunch of foodies who enjoy our potluck lunches, dinners out, and trying new places to eat. Alongside that, you''ll find us taking part in spontaneous fitness sessions, happy hours, celebrations that embrace our cultural diversity or milestones, and our much-loved table tennis matches, which can get just a little intense. There’s always something fun happening and something exciting to look forward to.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you''re ready to join a team that values creativity, collaboration, and a great time, ESET Australia might just be your next great adventure!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At ESET, our Channel Sales Account Manager''s key responsibility is to generate more revenue for the company, manage client accounts and come up with new sales ideas. This includes new sales strategies, sales pitches, and business plans.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Part of this role requires Business Development within the defined sales territory and focuses on new logo acquisition and large enterprise deal pursuit across key verticals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll be responsible for meeting and exceeding your quota by crafting and implementing strategic territory plans targeting deployments of the ESET Security Platform.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity for a closer with a hunter mentality to manage and enlarge accounts, and obtain net new business and gain market share&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities/Duties -&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect, develop, and close new less complex enterprise customers for ESET security software products in a defined sales territory with the ability to qualify opportunities, and allocate time and resources accordingly to best practices.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage in the entire sales cycle from lead generation to closing new deals, often involving cold calling, networking, and initial client engagement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Frequently interact with potential customers, aiming to convert prospects into clients. Focus on understanding the needs of new markets and customer segments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute territory &amp;amp; account plans to deliver maximum revenue potential, manage sales activities and updates, and create and deliver accurate forecasts in CRM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attain quarterly and annual net new revenue goals and quota targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pursue a “hunter strategy” focused on prospecting and landing of Net New enterprise accounts with (x000+ seats)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell the ESET Security vision to prospects through product demonstrations, events, and target-specific initiatives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage large/global enterprise prospect and customer evaluations, proof of concepts, and any RFP/RFIs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Solve complex business problems for our customers and ensure a positive prospect/customer experience, and make our ESET customers successful&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide detailed knowledge of ESET’s product portfolio and develop the comfort working with VARs to generate new pipeline and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate sales activities across multi-functional groups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with other sales team members to share best practices and insights. Share best practices and insights with other team members&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with management to develop acquisition plan and strategy to deliver long-term goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Suggest improvements in processes/systems to align it with internal''s needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Train the other team members by providing coaching, developing and distributing playbooks, conduct trainings.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Knowledge/Experience -&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of field sales experience, or equivalent quota-crushing role, in the software/technology sector; experience in cyber-security or SecOps preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience evangelizing enterprise technology, with particular focus on SaaS and disruptive cyber security technologies. Security background a plus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Can provide one-on-one coaching to internal teams, sharing insights and strategies for managing complex sales cycles and building relationships with enterprise prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and distribute playbooks that outline effective strategies, scripts, and processes that have proven successful in enterprise account acquisition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Encourage a collaborative approach to selling, where the BDM works alongside other sales team members on high-stakes deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitate collaboration between the sales team and other departments (e.g., marketing, product development, customer support) to ensure a holistic approach to meeting client needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct training sessions focused on acquisition, advanced negotiation tactics, helping the team build stronger pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Share market analysis on the specific challenges and pain points of enterprise clients and how to effectively address them.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience and knowledge of SaaS-based architectures, ideally in a cyber security and/or security context - awareness of EDR/XDR &amp;amp; MDR technology is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead all aspects of the sales cycle with the ability to uncover, qualifying, developing, and closing new, white-space territories and accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Win deals through world-class planning and preparation, as well as being consultative in your approach to solving real business problems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consistent track record of over-achievement; net new logo accomplishments; and keen understanding of how to leverage channel partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong focus on excellence in Pipeline Generation &amp;amp; Opportunity Progression; including meticulous planning and preparation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Evidence of ‘team sales’ and the ability to use internal resources, partners, and team members to be successful.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An ‘in the field’ mentality leading you to meet customers &amp;amp; prospects face to face wherever possible.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional spoken/written language skills required: Ability to read, analyse, and interpret legal documents, ability to respond to common inquiries and complaints, ability to effectively present information to top executive management.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High level of inter-personal relationship and excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented and self-reliant with a high level of inter-personal relationship and excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Benefits&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health &amp;amp; Well-being&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gym perks: Subsidised gym membership to release endorphins at one of Australia’s premium gyms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Time to recharge: Generous leave policies for vacations and all of life’s big moments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workplace &amp;amp; Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modern office perks: World-class facilities that recharge the body, mind and soul&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Centrally located: Right in the heart of Sydney’s CBD, amidst greenery and mouth-watering food options&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexibility &amp;amp; Balance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work culture: Remote work arrangements that balance personal commitments with face-to-face time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth &amp;amp; Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fuel your growth: Access to world-class learning platforms and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture, Recognition &amp;amp; Community&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Team spirit: Regular team events that bring everyone together&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Recognition programs: Celebrate achievements through values awards, loyalty awards, and other benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Additional information&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;No recruiters, please.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We do not offer visa sponsorship for this role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If this role aligns with you, we welcome your application to join the ESET Australia team!&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'LOW', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQGQcf1j9kIgUw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1645177089908/esetaustralia_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=6kY0QBzbFVgMM2ulwcnc3jfkMy3PswMHrQU5Jnt23oo', '2025-10-01T14:19:20.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recUaK8OqvEjAZC4a', 'Devicie', 'http://devicie.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/devicie', 'St Petersburg, Florida, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '11 - 50', '95', 'Devicie is a rapidly scaling cybersecurity SaaS company with recent $14M Series A funding and explicit plans to double headcount for global expansion. Multiple high-profile partnerships, product launches, and industry achievements signal aggressive growth. Active presence of a Sales Director in Australia and a robust sales infrastructure indicate immediate and ongoing need for external recruitment support in sales and revenue roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nDevicie launched new integrations and partnerships including becoming a reporting connector for Microsoft Edge for Business in April 2025, and announcing a strategic partnership with Lansweeper in July 2024 to enhance IT asset management. The company also inked an exclusive deal with managed service provider Entag in November 2024 to power Telstraâs business endpoint management strategy.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nDevicie stated plans to double team size over the next year following its Series A funding in April 2024. This expansion is targeted to support global growth, with a focus on the US, UK, and EMEA markets.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nDevicie completed a $14 million Series A funding round led by Insight Partners in April 2024, with additional support from CyberCX. The funding is designated for international expansion and product scaling.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nDevicie became a member of the Microsoft Intelligent Security Association in August 2024 and launched the Reporting Connector for Microsoft Edge for Business in April 2025, enhancing real-time endpoint telemetry capabilities for customers.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nShane Harding was appointed Chief Executive Officer in April 2025, having joined Devicie as Chief Operating Officer seven months prior to his promotion. No other recent executive appointments or departures identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Devicie empowers in-house IT teams and MSPs to transition their organizations to a cloud-native state by automating the implementation and ongoing management of Microsoft Intune. Our multi-tenant solution allows for efficient and consistent management of endpoints across multiple tenants with zero-touch configuration, automatic updates, application patching, built-in remediation, and enhanced management and compliance reporting. With Devicie, in-house IT teams and MSPs can ensure that end-users are productive, secure, and uniformly adhering to agreed compliance standards at scale, while freeing up critical resources to focus on other high-value projects and professional service offerings. For further details, visit www.devicie.com.\n\nDevicie is proud to be a member of both the Microsoft Intelligent Security Association (MISA) and the Microsoft for Startups Pegasus Program. These partnerships underscore our commitment to innovation and delivering best-in-class solutions that enhance and extend Microsoft technologies. Whether enabling secure endpoint management or helping organizations unlock new efficiencies with Intune, Devicie is at the forefront of modern IT management."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recUirTUXt8GSWOdF', 'Sabre Corporation', 'https://www.sabre.com/about/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sabre-corporation', 'Southlake, Texas, US', 'Computer Software', '5001 - 10000', '93', 'Sabre Corporation is a global computer software leader in travel technology, with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore. The company features an extensive sales hierarchy, including Sales Managers, Regional Sales Directors, and Heads of Strategic Partnerships, indicating robust sales infrastructure and leadership. Recent strategic partnerships and client acquisitions signal ongoing growth and expansion, presenting immediate and diverse recruitment opportunities across technology, sales, and digital roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOn April 28, 2025, Sabre announced the sale of its Hospitality Solutions business unit to TPG for $1.1 billion, with proceeds primarily used to pay down debt and optimize its portfolio[1]. Sabre also secured several strategic travel technology agreements in May 2025, including partnerships with Riyadh Air and LIFT airline[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent expansion is indicated by Sabreâs addition of new clients and multiple multi-year agreements with airlines and travel agencies in 2025, positioning the company for growth despite a Q1 decline in air bookings[5][4]. No substantial public hiring data or specific headcount growth for sales or GTM roles identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or new investment announcements identified within the last 6-12 months. Recent financial activity relates to the $1.1 billion divestiture of the Hospitality Solutions unit in April 2025, with proceeds used for debt repayment[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn May 2025, Sabre secured a global distribution agreement with Riyadh Air and multi-year partnerships with LIFT and Avelo Airlines, as well as a renewed agreement with Fahad Express Travel & Tourism[4]. In Q1 2025, Sabre reported net income of $35.3 million and projected growth due to new client acquisitions[5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures, specifically related to sales, revenue, or people functions, have been publicly disclosed in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We are a technology company that powers the global travel industry. By leveraging next-generation technology, we create global technology solutions that take on the biggest opportunities and solve the most complex challenges in travel. \n\nEvery day, millions of consumers and employees interact with our technology worldwide. We power mobile apps, airport check-in kiosks, online travel sites, airline and hotel reservation networks, travel agent terminals, and scores of other solutions. \n\nPositioned at the center of travel, we shape the future by offering innovative advancements that pave the way for a more connected and seamless ecosystem â empowering both clients and travelers with greater control and convenience. \n\nWant to learn more? Visit www.sabre.com"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recUljQC456Iqq5pz', 'Baidam Pty Ltd', 'https://baidam.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/baidam-solutions-pty-ltd', 'Brisbane City, Queensland, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '11 - 50', '92', 'Baidam Pty Ltd is a cybersecurity-focused IT services company with 32 employees and strong sales leadership, including recent appointments of a Managing Director and National Sales Director. Multiple sales and territory managers indicate a mature sales structure and active market expansion. The presence of a Senior Recruiter and accessible decision makers further supports immediate potential for external recruitment partnerships, making this a high-probability opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nBaidam appointed Jo Masters as Managing Director on May 5, 2025, following an extensive nationwide search, and both co-founders transitioned into Executive Director roles. The company is positioning for strategic growth and reinforcing its leadership as a profit-for-purpose Indigenous cybersecurity provider.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nBaidam recently expanded its leadership team by appointing Anita Sheridan-Roddick as National Sales Director, following Jo Mastersâ arrival. Continued focus on sales leadership and team development signals efforts toward market growth and increased customer acquisition.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nJo Masters was appointed Managing Director on May 5, 2025, with co-founders Jack Reis and Pip Jenkinson moving to Executive Director roles; shortly after, Anita Sheridan-Roddick joined as National Sales Director under Mastersâ leadership."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Baidam Solutions is providing Australia''s leading Supply Nation Certified Indigenous IT security partner to the National economy, servicing enterprise, Federal and State government departments and agencies, and not-for-profit organisations.\n\nOur commitment to giving back to the local economy will help us all âBridge the Gapâ of indigenous representation in the IT Security sector and Baidam has included in its corporate charter, a structured and measurable plan called the Baidam Initiative to provide both specialist IT security training courses and meaningful employment opportunities for regional and remote communities.\n"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recV3lXUCeNb7poHn', 'Wayflyer', 'https://www.wayflyer.com/', 'https://ie.linkedin.com/company/wayflyer', 'Dublin, County Dublin', 'Financial Services', '201-500 employees', '95', 'Wayflyer is a growth-stage fintech company (201-500 employees) with a strong commercial B2B focus, actively expanding its Sydney operations and serving e-commerce clients. The presence of a Managing Director Australia (Tier 1 decision maker) and a Senior Sales Representative indicates direct access to hiring authorities for core sales roles. Multiple strong growth signals—including recent $300M debt financing, Series B funding, rapid team expansion, and major local market achievements—combined with ongoing sales hiring make this a very high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Wayflyer’s **Sydney office** is located at Level 24, Three International Towers, 300 Barangaroo Avenue, Sydney NSW 2000, positioning it as the local base for growing APAC operations and serving Australian e-commerce merchants with tailored revenue-based financing solutions[2].  \n[LOCAL] In the last 12 months, Wayflyer’s Australian arm provided over **$100 million in new financing** and formed new partnerships, supporting more than 200 local businesses[3].  \n[GLOBAL] In June 2025, Wayflyer **secured and deployed a $300 million debt facility from J.P. Morgan**, aimed at expanding origination capacity and offering more competitive rates, with coverage extending to Australia, the U.S., and Western Europe[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There are clear indications of **team expansion and increased market activity in Sydney**, with local operations focusing heavily on sales, GTM, underwriting, and customer success to support e-commerce clients[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Wayflyer experienced a **178% year-over-year growth rate** and a rapid increase in market share, reaching the top three providers for online retail financing as of 2024[4].  \n[GLOBAL] Global headcount and organizational capabilities have grown steadily, especially in commercial and product development roles[2][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Wayflyer raised a **Series B of $150 million** in February 2022 at a $1.6 billion valuation, co-led by DST Global and QED Investors, with J.P. Morgan as a participant[3].  \n[GLOBAL] The **$300 million debt financing** from J.P. Morgan was announced and initiated in June 2025, substantially increasing firepower in core regions, including Australia[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Provided over **$100 million in financing to Australian e-commerce businesses** and formed strategic partnerships in 2024–2025 to deepen local market penetration[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Wayflyer surpassed **$2.5 billion in total funding delivered** to e-commerce companies worldwide, with exceptionally high customer satisfaction and a leading approval rate in the sector[4].  \n[REGIONAL] Wayflyer’s merchant cash advance analytics and underwriting platform is increasingly recognized by Australian online retailers for its flexibility and alignment with e-commerce cash flow[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] No Sydney- or Australia-specific executive appointments publicly announced in the last 6 months. As of April 2025, global leadership remains consistent, supporting regional GTM and sales functions from international offices[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Executive leadership remains focused on APAC expansion and scaling Sydney operations, but no noted local leadership changes in public announcements[2].\n\n---\n**Notes:**  \n- All Australian expansion and major funding events occurred in the last 12–18 months, with strong market momentum in Sydney and broader ANZ region.\n- If local hiring for specific sales/GTM roles is required, public postings and LinkedIn tracking suggest continuing team growth but lack published executive-level specifics.\n\nIf you need only Sydney-specific sales/GTG hiring or want partnerships named, specify further and I will attempt deeper searches."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"📝 &lt;strong&gt;Company Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our mission is to give the world access to the best products by empowering great brands to reach their growth potential.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;💼 &lt;strong&gt;About Wayflyer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Today''s consumer brands need a capital provider that keeps pace with their growth ambitions. Traditional financing options are slow, cumbersome and often out of reach. That''s why we built Wayflyer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our unique technology allows us to assess businesses in minutes, generate financing offers that reflect their growth potential and send funds in as little as 24 hours.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since launching in April 2020, we''ve deployed over $4.5bn to thousands of brands worldwide, backed by Tier 1 banks like J.P. Morgan. We''ve become a trusted financing partner for some amazing brands, like True Classic, Little Words Project and Kekoa Foods.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teams at Wayflyer are truly cross-functional. You''ll be collaborating with ambitious colleagues from around the world - all striving to deliver on a huge opportunity. Check out this video to hear directly from them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;💛 &lt;strong&gt;Culture &amp;amp; Values at Wayflyer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Wayflyer, we value being sound people, excellent operators, and ambitious overachievers, working together with integrity, creativity, and bold optimism to deliver exceptional results. To learn more, please visit our website.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🚀&lt;strong&gt;Your Role at a Glance: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The key ways you''ll bring value to the team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reach out to eCommerce founders to introduce Wayflyer and qualify their need for funding to help grow their business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use creative outreach methods including calls, personalised emails and LinkedIn/social selling to set up meetings for your Account Executive counterpart&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build trust with our customers, acting as a Co-founder to ensure mutually beneficial relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Play a key part in helping us to grow our revenue, predominantly in the Australian market&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''ll join our revenue academy, learning the skills necessary to become one of our top performing Account Executives or Customer Success Associates after 12-18 months!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🔨 What Makes You a Great Fit&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''re excited by the opportunity to work for Ireland''s fastest growing tech company&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have experience working successfully in a target driven environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You enjoy working in a fast-paced environment - previous startup experience is a plus (not a necessity).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have an ownership mentality, always seeking to improve Wayflyer''s prospects, even in functions outside of sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''re ambitious and eager to build a successful career in sales &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''re fluent in English.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;🤝 &lt;strong&gt;What to Expect After You Apply&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You can expect to hear from a member of our Talent Acquisition team soon. If we believe you''re a good fit, the first step will be a conversation with a recruiter who will guide you through the next stages of the process. The full interview process, which includes meeting the Hiring Manager and completing a case study or interview loop, typically takes approximately two to three weeks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🏖️&lt;strong&gt;The Perks of Being at Wayflyer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;🌴 &lt;strong&gt;Time Off That Matters&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Recharge with 25 days of paid annual leave, plus public holidays.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🧘 &lt;strong&gt;Your Wellbeing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Access support and resources to support your wellbeing, including our &lt;em&gt;Wellbeing @ Wayflyer&lt;/em&gt; ERG.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🫀 &lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Health &amp;amp; Protection&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Stay covered with private healthcare, life insurance, and critical illness cover.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;👵 &lt;strong&gt;Secure Your Future with Our Pension Plan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our pension plan helps you build a strong foundation for tomorrow, starting today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🍼 &lt;strong&gt;Family-First Policies&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We offer generous parental and adoptive leave, including 6 months of paid leave for Primary Caregivers and 3 months of paid leave for Secondary Caregivers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;💰 &lt;strong&gt;Share in Our Success&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;With our equity scheme, you''re not just an employee; you''re a stakeholder in our journey.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🌴 &lt;strong&gt;Work From Abroad!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Enjoy the freedom to work remotely from anywhere in the world for up to 60 calendar days a year.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;📍Global Offices and Working Policy&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🇮🇪 &lt;strong&gt;Dublin, Our Buzzing HQ&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our headquarters operates a hybrid model. The number of in-office days depends on your team, but the majority of teams and our SLT are typically in 3-4 days per week, giving you valuable exposure to senior leadership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🇬🇧 &lt;strong&gt;London, One Big Family&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Home to around 30 employees, our brand-new London office also runs on a hybrid model. You’ll often find our CEO working alongside the team with regular visits.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🇦🇺 &lt;strong&gt;Sydney, Small but Mighty&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our close-knit Sydney office has around 20 employees and follows a flexible hybrid model, fostering strong collaboration.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🇺🇸 &lt;strong&gt;Atlanta, New York &amp;amp; Charlotte, Stateside Collaboration&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Each of our US offices has 8-10 employees and operates with a flexible hybrid approach, blending in-person connection with remote freedom.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;🌍 &lt;strong&gt;Remote, Across the US &amp;amp; Europe&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The majority of our Tech org works remotely across the UK and Europe, coming together throughout the year for off-sites, company kick off and technical kick off. We also have a growing number of remote team members across the US.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;💡 &lt;strong&gt;How We Handle Your Personal Data&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Wayflyer Limited will process your personal data for the purpose of evaluating your suitability for the role. Such processing is based on the need to take steps prior to entering into a potential employment agreement. To learn more about how we handle your personal data, you can contact our privacy team at privacy@wayflyer.com or review our privacy notice at https://wayflyer.com/privacy-notice."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQE8ebxEBqAx9Q/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1707227344161/wayflyer_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=pirZUJDqNZY6Lu0VlPtWX9Sljih2r3Qifz-DGLd9hgo', '2025-09-20T06:34:17.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVEeHGFHBqqZ2jN', 'monday.com', 'https://www.monday.com', 'https://il.linkedin.com/company/mondaydotcom', 'Tel Aviv, Israel, IL', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '97', 'monday.com is a leading SaaS company with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore, and a robust sales and revenue team structure. Recent product launches, significant revenue growth, and a strategic shift to enterprise clients signal ongoing expansion and high hiring probability. Multiple senior sales and people leaders are present, indicating immediate opportunities for external recruitment support.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nmonday.comâs shares dropped nearly 30% following its Q2 2025 earnings call due to AI-driven changes in software buying behaviors, particularly affecting small-business leads, while enterprise demand stayed robust. The company is shifting marketing spend for greater precision, doubling down on large-enterprise clients, and announced it will host its 2025 Investor Day on September 17, 2025.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nThe company is focusing growth efforts on large-enterprise customers, with signs of U.S. management team expansion and leadership roles shifting outside Israel for the first time. Its CRM product crossed a $100 million annual run rate three years after launch.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn July 2025, launched the \"monday magic\" AI tool for generative workflow creation, and rolled out a new homepage along with security enhancements for WorkCanvas. The companyâs CRM reached a $100 million annual run rate, and Q2 2025 revenue increased 27% year-over-year to $299 million.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nThe management team has become more U.S.-centric with roles now based outside Israel for the first time, but no specific new executive hires or departures were identified by name in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"The monday.com Work OS is a low code- no code platform that democratizes the power of software so organizations can easily build work management tools and software applications to fit their every need. The platform intuitively connects people to processes and systems, empowering teams to excel in every aspect of their work while creating an environment of transparency in business. monday.com has offices in Tel Aviv, New York, Miami, Chicago, Denver, London, Warsaw, Sydney, Melbourne, SÃ£o Paulo, and Tokyo. The platform is fully customizable to suit any business vertical and is currently used by over 225,000+ customers across 200 industries in over 200 countries and territories."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVSZ1l0CjIUl4Os', 'HCLTech', 'http://www.hcltech.com', 'https://in.linkedin.com/company/hcltech', 'Noida, Uttar Pradesh, IN', 'Information Technology & Services', '10001 -', NULL, 'HCLTech is a global IT services leader with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore, operating across core technology domains including AI, digital, and cloud. The company demonstrates significant growth signals, recent industry awards, and a robust sales leadership team spanning APAC, with multiple Sales Directors and VPs in both Australia and Singapore. This established sales infrastructure and ongoing expansion indicate immediate and ongoing hiring potential across technology, sales, and digital roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nHCLTech was recognized as the 2025 Global Alliances AI Partner of the Year at Dell Technologies World in June 2025, highlighting its expertise in AI and strategic collaboration with Dell. The company also received the 2025 Global Alliances EMEA Acquisition Partner of the Year award, emphasizing its expanding market impact[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHCLTech reported over 223,000 employees across 60 countries as of March 2025, with continued expansion in digital, cloud, and AI divisions. Forbes named HCLTech one of America''s Best Employers for New Grads in 2025, suggesting active hiring and a positive workplace reputation[5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn May 2025, HCLTech won the 2025 ServiceNow Emerging Industry Partner of the Year award for excellence in AI-driven and ServiceNow-powered digital solutions. The company was also named the world''s fastest-growing IT services brand in January 2025 by Brand Finance, with its brand value rising 17% to $8.9 billion, and was recognized as a Leader in the HFS Horizons: Generative Enterprise Services, 2025 report in April 2025[1][2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"HCLTech is a global technology company, home to more than 223,000 people across 60 countries, delivering industry-leading capabilities centered around digital, engineering, cloud and AI, powered by a broad portfolio of technology services and products. We work with clients across all major verticals, providing industry solutions for Financial Services, Manufacturing, Life Sciences and Healthcare, High Tech, Semiconductor, Telecom and Media, Retail and CPG and Public Services. Consolidated revenues as of 12 months ending June 2025 totaled $14 billion. To learn how we can supercharge progress for you, visit hcltech.com."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVbN6XNYBEdgaqN', 'ESET', 'http://www.eset.com', 'https://sk.linkedin.com/company/eset', 'Bratislava, Slovak Republic', 'Software Development,Computer and Network Security', '1,001-5,000 employees', '66', 'ESET is a growth-stage cybersecurity and software company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively investing in Australian channel sales enablement (ESET Connect 2025). The presence of decision makers such as the Director, Sales Operations & Excellence – APAC (Tier 3), Country Manager Singapore and Asia (Tier 1), and Enterprise Sales Lead - APAC (Tier 2) provides quality access for recruitment. While no recent funding is noted, ongoing sales-focused initiatives and stable Sydney operations signal continued hiring needs for core sales roles, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] ESET launched **ESET Connect 2025** in September 2025, a new partner enablement initiative for upskilling resellers and MSPs across Australia with in-person workshops in Sydney, focused on strengthening sales, technical, and customer engagement skills[1].  \n[LOCAL] On July 22, 2025, ESET presented its fourth annual Australia Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship at its Sydney office, highlighting its collaboration with senior national cybersecurity leaders and reinforcing engagement with the local technology education sector[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] ESET is actively investing in its Australian channel ecosystem, delivering in-person partner sales and technical workshops across four major cities, including Sydney[1].  \n[REGIONAL] The ESET Connect 2025 activities in Australia reflect a continued expansion and deep channel engagement, aligning with broader trends in ANZ where partners move toward higher-value managed cybersecurity services[1].  \n[LOCAL] ESET’s Sydney office at Level 20, 111 Pacific Highway, North Sydney, remains a principal hub for Australian operations, indicating stable or growing presence in Sydney[3][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding rounds or local investment disclosures for ESET Australia or APAC operations in the last 12 months were identified in available sources.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] ESET awarded the 2025 Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship to Samia Arshad Mehar, an undergraduate at University of Technology, Sydney, demonstrating both community involvement and support for diversity in cybersecurity[2].  \n[LOCAL] ESET Connect 2025 workshops and webinars deliver the latest threat intelligence, live demonstrations of new ESET features, and direct engagement with the local Australian sales team—a move designed to reinforce ESET’s competitive capabilities in the Australian market[1].  \n[REGIONAL] The ESET Connect 2025 initiative itself is positioned as a significant effort to help partners differentiate and build recurring revenue in Australia’s dynamic cybersecurity sector[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Parvinder Walia continues as President of Asia Pacific and Japan for ESET and maintains a visible role in regional and Australian initiatives, such as the Women in Cybersecurity program[2].  \n[LOCAL] No major executive changes specific to Sydney or broader national office roles in the last 12 months were detected in public disclosures.\n\n---\n\nKey signals for Sydney and Australian market:  \n- **Strategic channel enablement and sales training investment (ESET Connect 2025)**  \n- **Academic and community engagement through scholarships and partnerships with local education and government leaders**  \n- **Ongoing presence and operations from main Sydney office with no signals of contraction**"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At ESET, our Channel Sales Account Manager''s key responsibility is to generate more revenue for the company, manage client accounts and come up with new sales ideas. This includes new sales strategies, sales pitches, and business plans.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Part of this role requires Business Development within the defined sales territory and focuses on new logo acquisition and large enterprise deal pursuit across key verticals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You’ll be responsible for meeting and exceeding your quota by crafting and implementing strategic territory plans targeting deployments of the ESET Security Platform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a unique opportunity for a closer with a hunter mentality to manage and enlarge accounts, and obtain net new business and gain market share&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities/Duties -&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect, develop, and close new less complex enterprise customers for ESET security software products in a defined sales territory with the ability to qualify opportunities, and allocate time and resources accordingly to best practices.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage in the entire sales cycle from lead generation to closing new deals, often involving cold calling, networking, and initial client engagement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Frequently interact with potential customers, aiming to convert prospects into clients. Focus on understanding the needs of new markets and customer segments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute territory &amp;amp; account plans to deliver maximum revenue potential, manage sales activities and updates, and create and deliver accurate forecasts in CRM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attain quarterly and annual net new revenue goals and quota targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pursue a “hunter strategy” focused on prospecting and landing of Net New enterprise accounts with (x000+ seats)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell the ESET Security vision to prospects through product demonstrations, events, and target-specific initiatives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage large/global enterprise prospect and customer evaluations, proof of concepts, and any RFP/RFIs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Solve complex business problems for our customers and ensure a positive prospect/customer experience, and make our ESET customers successful&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide detailed knowledge of ESET’s product portfolio and develop the comfort working with VARs to generate new pipeline and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate sales activities across multi-functional groups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with other sales team members to share best practices and insights. Share best practices and insights with other team members&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with management to develop acquisition plan and strategy to deliver long-term goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Suggest improvements in processes/systems to align it with internal''s needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Train the other team members by providing coaching, developing and distributing playbooks, conduct trainings.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Knowledge/Experience -&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of field sales experience, or equivalent quota-crushing role, in the software/technology sector; experience in cyber-security or SecOps preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience evangelizing enterprise technology, with particular focus on SaaS and disruptive cyber security technologies. Security background a plus. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Can provide one-on-one coaching to internal teams, sharing insights and strategies for managing complex sales cycles and building relationships with enterprise prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and distribute playbooks that outline effective strategies, scripts, and processes that have proven successful in enterprise account acquisition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Encourage a collaborative approach to selling, where the BDM works alongside other sales team members on high-stakes deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitate collaboration between the sales team and other departments (e.g., marketing, product development, customer support) to ensure a holistic approach to meeting client needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct training sessions focused on acquisition, advanced negotiation tactics, helping the team build stronger pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Share market analysis on the specific challenges and pain points of enterprise clients and how to effectively address them.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience and knowledge of SaaS-based architectures, ideally in a cyber security and/or security context - awareness of EDR/XDR &amp;amp; MDR technology is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead all aspects of the sales cycle with the ability to uncover, qualifying, developing, and closing new, white-space territories and accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Win deals through world-class planning and preparation, as well as being consultative in your approach to solving real business problems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consistent track record of over-achievement; net new logo accomplishments; and keen understanding of how to leverage channel partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong focus on excellence in Pipeline Generation &amp;amp; Opportunity Progression; including meticulous planning and preparation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Evidence of ‘team sales’ and the ability to use internal resources, partners, and team members to be successful.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An ‘in the field’ mentality leading you to meet customers &amp;amp; prospects face to face wherever possible.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional spoken/written language skills required: Ability to read, analyse, and interpret legal documents, ability to respond to common inquiries and complaints, ability to effectively present information to top executive management.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High level of inter-personal relationship and excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented and self-reliant with a high level of inter-personal relationship and excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At ESET, diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) are integral to our corporate culture. We believe in creating a respectful environment, where everyone feels valued and respected, welcoming applications from individuals of all backgrounds, including race, gender, age, religion, disability, and sexual orientation.&lt;/strong&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFrAuUUybxjxQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1683816532319/eset_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=oJSl1zOB9RhykjhLpS9t-OGyyEqwkV6ZcPkICD2ttCs', '2025-09-22T14:16:00.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVfbSO38eMI6g4M', 'Carta', 'http://www.carta.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/carta--', 'San Francisco, California', 'Technology, Information and Internet,Financial Services', '1,001-5,000 employees', '95', 'Carta is a growth-stage B2B SaaS/Fintech company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively expanding in Australia with a new Sydney office focused on sales, marketing, and business development. The presence of Tier 1 (Managing Director, Head of GTM) and Tier 2 (Head of Sales & GTM) decision makers provides direct access for recruitment. The inclusion of a Sales Development Representative (SDR) in the team signals active hiring for primary target sales roles. Multiple strong growth signals—market entry, leadership appointments, and partnership expansion—make this an exceptional recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Carta announced the **expansion of its operations into Australia with a new Sydney office**, officially launched on 18 November 2024[1][2][3]. This marks a key milestone intended to actively support the NSW government’s ambitions for Sydney to become a global business hub and foster stronger connections with local startups, investors, and innovation programs[1][3].  \n[LOCAL] The **Sydney office launch** is supported by Investment NSW and targets collaboration with university incubators (UNSW Founders, INCUBATE at University of Sydney), the Techstars Tech Central Sydney Accelerator (powered by NSW Government), and extension of Carta’s free equity management program, Launch[1][2][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office will function as the hub for **sales, marketing, and business development** in Australia, representing a move from previously remote operations to an in-market team[2][3].\n[LOCAL] The **expansion includes plans for further team growth and local partnerships**; leadership has signaled ongoing hiring and deeper integration into the Australian startup and venture capital ecosystem[1][3].\n[REGIONAL] Managing Director Bhavik Vashi oversees the Australian venture, leveraging a track record of growing Carta''s business in Singapore and the Middle East[1][2][3]. His leadership is expected to scale sales and customer operations across ANZ.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No Australia-specific funding in the past 6-12 months; however, Carta maintains a strong global financial position, managing nearly **US$3 trillion in global equity**, supporting more than **40,000 companies** and over **7,000 funds/SPVs**, with US$130B+ in assets under administration and US$15B in facilitated liquidity[3].\n[GLOBAL] These resources underpin Carta’s APAC investments, of which the Sydney expansion is a prominent commitment[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Carta secured **strategic partnerships and event collaborations** with Australian companies, notably Employment Hero and Titanium Ventures (formerly Telstra Ventures), prior to the Sydney launch[1][2][3].\n[LOCAL] Carta''s \"Launch\" equity management program is being rolled out locally in partnership with major universities and accelerator programs[1][2].\n[GLOBAL] Carta has received global recognition for innovation, being included on Fortune’s Best Large Workplaces in Financial Services and Insurance, Forbes’ World''s Best Cloud Companies, and Fast Company''s Most Innovative list[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] **Bhavik Vashi was appointed Managing Director to lead the Sydney operations** and ANZ expansion, bringing significant B2B SaaS and CFO-office platform experience from previous APAC/EMEA roles[1][2][3].\n[GLOBAL] No additional executive hires or departures affecting Australia have been publicly reported in the last 6-12 months.\n\nScope notes:  \n- All *RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS*, *GROWTH SIGNALS*, *RECENT ACHIEVEMENTS*, and *LEADERSHIP CHANGES* above are directly related to Australia and Sydney unless specifically indicated as regional or global.\n- *RECENT FUNDING* information references the global status of Carta due to the lack of AU-specific capital events.\n\nIf further granularity or team-level hiring analytics are needed, please specify."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"The Company You’ll Join&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carta connects founders, investors, and limited partners through world-class software, purpose-built for everyone in venture capital, private equity and private credit. Trusted by 65,000+ companies in 160+ countries, Carta’s platform of software and services lays the groundwork so you can build, invest, and scale with confidence.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carta’s Fund Administration platform supports 9,000+ funds and SPVs, representing nearly $185B in assets under management, with tools designed to enhance the strategic impact of fund CFOs. Recognized by Fortune, Forbes, Fast Company, Inc. and Great Places to Work, Carta is shaping the future of private market infrastructure.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Together, Carta is creating the end-to-end ERP platform for private markets. Traditional ERP solutions don’t work for Private Funds. Private capital markets need a comprehensive software solution to replace outdated spreadsheets and fragmented service providers. Carta’s software for the Office of the Fund CFO does just that - it’s a new category of software to make private markets look more like public markets - a connected ERP for private capital.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For more information about our offices and culture, check out our Carta careers page.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Team You’ll Work With&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carta is looking for a Sydney-based Sales Development Representative to join our Corporations Sales team and support Carta’s expansion across the Australia &amp;amp; New Zealand (ANZ) region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You’ll be part of the broader Asia Pacific Corporations Sales team, which focuses on selling Carta’s cap table and equity management software to private companies. Since launching in the region in 2021, we’ve built a world-class go-to-market organization supporting the growth of our Corporations business across diverse markets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a high-impact role within a collaborative, cross-functional team responsible for Carta’s growth in private markets. You’ll work closely with Sales, Customer Experience, Marketing, and Product to deliver exceptional value to founders, CFOs, and finance leaders across ANZ.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Problems You’ll Solve&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Business Demand Generation&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify Carta’s Ideal Customer Profile (ICP), prospect via multiple channels like Email, Phone, LinkedIn to generate conversations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will help drive the overall company pipeline. Create and manage outreach campaigns to startup founders and employees, leveraging “customer-first” approach&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Match prospect pain points to specific value propositions across various buyer personas, roles, and functions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the AE team to build a healthy sales pipeline&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to elevate Carta’s brand awareness and drive top-of-funnel acquisition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Respond quickly and efficiently triage leads based on channel and need&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;em&gt;Data and Process Integrity &amp;amp; Maintenance&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and manage sizable lead lists in order to glean unique insights and drive desirable business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure data integrity across critical business systems (e.g. Salesforce, Outreach, Marketo, and Carta)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;The Impact You’ll Have&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Sales Development Representative, you will be part of a small team managing all commercial aspects of Carta’s growth in Asia. You will drive demand, develop and iterate on critical internal operations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grit - Ambitious, driven, and fearless in the face of rejection&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coachability - Tremendous desire to constantly improve in a “no-egos” and high velocity environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Emotional Intelligence - Ability to read emotional cues, understand a customer’s needs, and navigate a conversation with meaningful solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customer-Facing Experience - Experience working in a high volume customer-facing role. Able to professionally communicate with founders, CEOs and senior executives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An Interest in APAC’s Startup Ecosystem: Understanding of APAC’s startup scene and a passion for keeping abreast of the latest trends from across the ecosystem. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management skills and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of success in a lead generation role is a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to break down and effectively communicate complex topics&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice To Have&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing data in a CRM system (Preferably: Salesforce)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiencies with Microsoft Office and/or Google Suite (GSuite)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of finance, venture capital, and accounting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working at a high-growth software company or venture capital firm&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclosures&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer and are committed to providing a positive interview experience for every candidate. If accommodations due to a disability or medical condition are needed, please connect with the talent partner via email. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Carta uses E-Verify in the United States for employment authorization. See the E-Verify and Department of Justice websites for more details.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;For information on our data privacy policies, see Privacy, CA Candidate Privacy, and Brazil Transparency Report.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Please note that all official communications from us will come from an @carta.com or @carta-external.com domain. Report any contact from unapproved domains to security@carta.com.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQGq1S8AEOjaTQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1728484586014/carta___logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=Y1-7mu3s0ytnjBAMqzxxxm7ad_WRjbfCbD_VlHh-9Ho', '2025-09-20T02:46:31.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVm8dsGASpqLDic', 'Darktrace', 'http://www.darktrace.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/darktrace', 'Cambridge, Cambridgeshire', 'Computer and Network Security', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'Darktrace is a growth-stage computer and network security company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for Account Executive and Senior Territory Manager roles, both high-priority core sales positions. The company operates in commercial B2B tech (cybersecurity/AI), with strong fit for external recruitment. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including a Sales Director (ANZ), Regional Sales Manager (ASEAN), and VP of Sales (Asia). Significant growth signals include new office openings in Sydney and Melbourne, a doubling of local headcount, and major enterprise contract wins. While no recent public funding, the Thoma Bravo acquisition and ongoing APAC expansion further support robust hiring activity. This combination makes Darktrace a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] **Opened new Sydney office at Australia Square Tower** and Melbourne office at the Rialto Building (announced July 2024) to support surging demand in the Australian market. Customers include City Tattersalls Club, VACCA, Lockyer Valley Regional Council, and Grant Thornton Australia. Notable local partners are Telstra and Tesserant[1].  \n[LOCAL] **Australian customer base grew by over 60%** in the last 12 months across all industries, reflecting strong adoption of Darktrace’s self-learning AI[3].  \n[REGIONAL] Growth in Australia is part of a broader acceleration across APAC, driven by the need for autonomous AI cyber defense as organizations confront increasingly sophisticated threats[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[LOCAL] **Employee headcount doubled in Australia** over the past year, with hiring across Sydney, Melbourne, and Perth offices to support expanding operations and client demand[1][3].  \n[LOCAL] Offices in major cities underline a boots-on-the-ground approach tailored to Australian organizations’ needs.  \n[REGIONAL] Senior leadership, including Hayley Turner (Director of Industrial Security, APAC), have emphasized evolving enterprise security challenges and the strategic role of AI in the regional approach[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \n[GLOBAL] [No recent major public funding rounds reported in the last 12 months; Darktrace was acquired by Thoma Bravo in 2024, which has provided capital and strategic support for expansion, including in the APAC region.][2]\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \n[LOCAL] Secured significant enterprise contracts with leading Australian organizations, including Steadfast Group, Chemist Warehouse Australia, and City Tattersalls Club[1][3].  \n[REGIONAL] Recognized as an AI security innovation leader, with APAC-specific milestones including rapid customer onboarding and technology adoption.  \n[GLOBAL] Announced the acquisition of Mira Security in July 2025 to enhance network capabilities and encrypted traffic visibility, a move that will benefit all markets including Australia[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \n[GLOBAL] Jill Popelka appointed CEO following the Thoma Bravo acquisition in 2024. Recent global executive hires (2025) include Eve Saltman as Chief Legal Officer and Marty Overman as EVP, Sales, Americas[2].  \n[REGIONAL/LOCAL] No specific new sales, GTM, or country manager appointments for Australia reported in the past 12 months, but the doubling of headcount and expansion of local leadership suggest ongoing team growth and senior hires[1][3].\n\n---\n\n**Summary (scope-based):**  \n- [LOCAL] Darktrace has rapidly expanded in Sydney and across Australia both in headcount and customer footprint, driven by AI product demand, new partnerships, and high-profile local enterprise wins.  \n- [REGIONAL] APAC operations are a clear priority in Darktrace’s global growth, with local hiring, product integration (AI, real-time threat response), and visible leadership engagement.  \n- [GLOBAL] Strategic acquisitions and executive changes at the parent company level are supporting regional and local expansion, with the latest technology advances set to flow into Australia operations."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Darktrace is a global leader in AI for cybersecurity that keeps organizations ahead of the changing threat landscape every day. Founded in 2013, Darktrace provides the essential cybersecurity platform protecting nearly 10,000 organizations from unknown threats using its proprietary AI. The Darktrace Active AI Security Platform™ delivers a proactive approach to cyber resilience to secure the business across the entire digital estate – from network to cloud to email. Breakthrough innovations from our R&amp;amp;D teams have resulted in over 200 patent applications filed. Darktrace’s platform and services are supported by over 2,400 employees around the world. To learn more, visit http://www.darktrace.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an Account Executive you''ll play a key role in driving the sales operation, from prospecting for new business to closing deals, and managing an exciting portfolio of client accounts. You''ll work with in-house technical experts to present Darktrace’s unique AI solution to information security experts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Cybersecurity Industry Is One Of The Most Dynamic And Rapidly Evolving Sectors Today—and At Darktrace, We’re At The Forefront Of Innovation, Helping Businesses Protect Themselves From Emerging Threats. Working In Our Fast-paced Cybersecurity Sales Environment Offers Unique Challenges And Rewards That Will Accelerate Your Career And Amplify Your Impact&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rapid Career Growth: As the cybersecurity landscape evolves quickly, so do the opportunities for professionals who are ready to learn and adapt. In our fast-paced environment, you’ll have the chance to rapidly build your expertise, collaborate with industry leaders, and advance your career as a trusted advisor to top-tier clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High Impact, High Reward: The stakes are high in cybersecurity. Closing a deal can mean protecting an organisation’s most valuable assets—its data, intellectual property, and reputation. This sense of purpose drives success and makes every win that much more rewarding. Our performance-driven culture also means your hard work will be recognised and rewarded through competitive compensation and career growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Challenging and Varied: Cybersecurity sales is never boring. With new threats emerging regularly, each sales cycle presents unique challenges and opportunities. You’ll engage with C-suite executives, technical decision-makers, and IT professionals, learning how to navigate complex decision-making processes while tailoring solutions to each client’s specific security needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Transformative Industry Relationships: Cybersecurity touches every industry, from finance to healthcare to government. This gives you the opportunity to build relationships with a broad range of businesses and become a trusted partner in their journey to protect against cyber threats.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities As An Account Executive&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve quarterly revenue targets through the acquisition of new accounts within your assigned territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify, develop, and qualify leads; self-sourcing efforts will be supplemented by regional support from Marketing, Inside Sales, and Channel teams.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Present and demonstrate Darktrace cyber threat defense solutions to information security experts and C-level executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Darktrace Subject Matter Experts, Technical Account Managers and Cyber Threat Analysts who will support you in delivering Proof of Values (POVs) to prospective customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least three years of outbound B2B sales experience selling complex software; past success selling into a highly regulated market is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Clear, working sales methodology and passion for hunting new business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confident, polished communicator with a proven ability to build strong professional relationships.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Seeking a target-driven, meritocratic environment with exceptional opportunities for advancement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree from an accredited university.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQF5s9E8gon52Q/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1724756464441/darktrace_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=GE1RYE3DZy2sMWLATARQPcrqY9gUBNbc_eTdA2FmSAQ', '2025-09-22T14:19:58.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recVp8sBJjxrd1q1y', 'Sensiba LLP', 'http://www.sensiba.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sensiba', 'San Ramon, California, US', 'Accounting', '201 - 500', '50', 'Sensiba LLP is a growth-stage accounting firm (450 employees) with recent expansion into Australia and notable growth signals, including acquisitions and double-digit organic revenue growth. The inclusion is triggered by a Customer Success Manager role, which is a medium-priority sales-adjacent position. The industry is accounting, not core B2B tech, resulting in only acceptable commercial fit. The identified decision maker is a Customer Success Manager (not a hiring authority), and there are no tier 1 or 2 sales/revenue leaders present. While growth signals are strong, the industry fit and role priority limit the recruitment opportunity to a medium level.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSensiba LLP acquired Everoot Consulting in June 2025 to expand its B Corp and sustainability service offerings, following an earlier acquisition of Australia-based AssuranceLab. The firm also advanced its practice in governance, risk, and compliance, including new penetration testing and ISO/IEC 42001 certifications[2][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nSensiba has had its largest single-year expansion of its partner group in 2025 and demonstrated nearly 11% organic revenue growth, with notable expansion in sustainability, risk assurance, and family office services[1][2]. The firm has also announced new practice areas and partnerships to support continued growth[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nSensiba was ranked #80 in Accounting Today''s 2025 Top 100 Firms and #75 in Inside Public Accountingâs 2025 Top 100 Firms[1][2]. The firm was also honored as a 2025 Top Impact Company by Real Leaders for the sixth consecutive year and named to the 2025 Top Workplaces USA list by Energage[3][6].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nJonathan Akhavan was appointed Chief Human Resources Officer in 2025[5]. No other recent executive or sales/revenue/people leadership changes identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Sensibaâs comprehensive accounting, tax, and consulting services help businesses and people solve problems, navigate complexity, and build a foundation for sustainable growth. A top-75 U.S. firm, weâre passionate about collaborating with clients to increase efficiency, mitigate risk, and prepare to embrace emerging opportunities. As a certified B Corp, we foster a culture where people, families, and communities thrive."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recWIHYmneV3lJtdv', 'BeyondTrust', 'http://www.beyondtrust.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/beyondtrust', 'Johns Creek, Georgia', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'BeyondTrust is a growth-stage software company (1,001-5,000 employees) in the core commercial B2B tech sector, actively employing Sales Development Representatives (SDRs) in Singapore, a primary target role for recruitment. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers, including Regional Sales Directors and Regional Sales Managers across Australia and Singapore, provides strong access for recruitment engagement. Recent local growth signals include major partner awards, team expansion, and increased investment in ANZ, indicating a robust hiring environment. While no new funding or direct sales leadership hires were noted, the combination of high-priority sales role hiring, strong industry fit, and quality decision makers makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] BeyondTrust hosted its 2024 PartnerTrust Live event in Melbourne, highlighting its ongoing commitment to the Australian market and close collaboration with major local partners[1]. At this event, several Australian partners were recognized for significant achievements and joint wins across key sectors such as healthcare, retail, education, and critical infrastructure[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Four BeyondTrust solutions completed IRAP assessment at the PROTECTED classification as of April 2025, performed with local partner CyberCX, enabling them to support Australian government cloud requirements under the Australian Cyber Security Centre (ACSC) framework[2].  \n[REGIONAL] BeyondTrust has actively been promoting its high-compliance Remote Support solution to meet increasing public sector regulatory requirements, specifically focusing on security mandates in Australia and the APAC region[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Sydney-based partner 3Columns was named Growth Partner of the Year 2024, driven by expansion in local sales and technical teams, as well as a promotion to Gold-tier partner status[1].  \n[LOCAL] Noteworthy channel partner activity: Four Australian partners (including CyberCX and 3Columns) received awards for growth, technical excellence, and customer impact, underscoring a robust and expanding ecosystem supporting BeyondTrust’s business in the ANZ region[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Increased enablement and investment in strategic partnerships across Australia and New Zealand, with comments from ANZ Regional Sales Director confirming continued scaling and partner-driven innovation for customer solutions[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding or investment rounds specific to the last 6-12 months were reported in the provided information.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Four Australian partners were honoured by BeyondTrust at their annual awards, including 3Columns (Growth Partner of the Year), CyberCX (Partner of the Year), Invise (Customer Impact Award), and Modern 42 (Technical Excellence Award). These awards highlight measurable partner-led gains and increased customer satisfaction in the ANZ market over the past year[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Successfully completed IRAP PROTECTED certification for four solutions, opening expanded opportunities with government clients and regulated industries in Australia—considered a critical achievement for SaaS adoption in public sector environments[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Roshi Balendran continues as Regional Sales Director for ANZ, highlighted as the spokesperson in several recent 2025 announcements[1][2]. No recent local executive hires, promotions, or departures specific to Sydney or broader ANZ sales/GTM leadership were noted in available sources.\n\nIf you require further specifics on hiring or APAC-wide personnel movements, additional search stages may be needed as direct recruitment or team expansion details for Sydney were not surfaced in these sources."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"BeyondTrust is a place where you can bring your purpose to life through the work that you do, creating a safer world through our cybersecurity SaaS portfolio.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our culture of flexibility, trust, and continual learning means you will be recognized for your growth and for the impact you make on our success. You will be surrounded by people who challenge, support, and inspire you to be the best version of yourself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Drive revenue growth by identifying, developing, and closing business within an assigned territory. You’ll lead end-to-end execution of our go-to-market strategy, managing complex, multi-stakeholder sales cycles from initial engagement through to contract closure and long-term expansion. This is a high-impact role within a growing team, offering the opportunity to drive strategic growth across a priority region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Territory Strategy &amp;amp; Execution: Design, own, and drive comprehensive territory plans that maximize market penetration, competitive positioning, and revenue growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accelerate revenue: Consistently achieve and exceed quarterly and annual revenue targets by developing and expanding accounts within your assigned territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Excellence &amp;amp; Forecasting: Maintain strong sales hygiene and cadence, with deep understanding of your customers’ business to drive accurate forecasting and predictable revenue outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customer Partnerships: Build deep, strategic relationships by understanding your customers’ priorities, challenges, and growth plans, aligning BeyondTrust’s solutions with clear business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customer Success &amp;amp; Enablement: Support customers and partners with ongoing education and adoption programs to maximise value realisation and drive solution proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Channel Engagement: Collaborate closely with the BeyondTrust partner ecosystem to co-create differentiated, value-driven solutions that deliver on customer objectives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cross Functional Leadership: Lead your POD through effective territory strategy execution, coordinating closely with marketing, channel, pre-sales, business development, and other internal teams.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be based in Sydney or Canberra&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A high-performing self-starter who thrives on solving complex problems. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success selling into Federal and State Government, consistently meeting or exceeding annual quotas. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in enterprise software, IT services, SaaS, IoT, or managed services within complex environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong team player who values collaboration and effectively engages cross-functional teams to achieve shared goals. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Curious and growth-minded, with a commitment to continuous learning. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen and technical understanding, enabling you to build credible and influential relationships across all levels of customer organisations. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of analysing customer businesses and executing multi-year account strategies that drive revenue growth in complex environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skilled in articulating a strong sales message and advancing deals through the sales cycle. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with and through partners to drive business outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Analytical thinker with strong communication and presentation skills. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Committed to building strong, collaborative relationships that foster creativity and team success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Better Together&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Diversity. Inclusion. They’re more than just words for us. They are the guiding values of how we build our teams, cultivate leaders, and create a culture where people feel connected.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We take care of our employees so they can take care of our customers. Customers who come from all walks of life just like us. We hire incredible people from diverse backgrounds because when we are different together, we are stronger together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;BeyondTrust is the global identity security leader protecting Paths to Privilege™. Our identity-centric approach goes beyond securing privileges and access, empowering organizations with the most effective solution to manage the entire identity attack surface and neutralize threats, whether from external attacks or insiders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;BeyondTrust is leading the charge in transforming identity security to prevent breaches and limit the blast radius of attacks, while creating a superior customer experience and operational efficiencies. We are trusted by 20,000 customers, including 75 of the Fortune 100, and our global ecosystem of partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Learn more at www.beyondtrust.com."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQEjTFSGI6pzWw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1675949763843/beyondtrust_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=qy6U9PtDefWgeIFymjSZTBnKCclicGZs1pd2uu-oPQg', '2025-09-25T05:22:26.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recWc4bs1nEbcJn8Z', 'MartianLogic', 'https://martianlogic.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/martianlogic', 'North Sydney, New South Wales', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '11-50 employees', '68', 'MartianLogic is a small growth-stage HR tech company (11-50 employees) in IT Services/HRIS, hiring for a New Business Sales Director—a high-priority core sales role. The industry fit is acceptable (HR tech), and the company’s modular SaaS platform has demonstrated strong local market adoption, with significant recent client wins and product launches as growth signals. Access to a Tier 2 decision maker (Sales Director) increases the likelihood of external recruitment engagement. While there is no recent funding or leadership change, the combination of role, company size, and growth indicators makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] In 2024, MartianLogic focused on rolling out the first version of its Employee Compliance Management Module and began initial development of Performance Reviews and Employee Surveys, responding to demand from clients across Sydney and Australia[1].  \n[LOCAL] The company defined its CoreHR suite in 2024, consolidating solutions for recruitment, onboarding, compliance, performance, surveys, and employee self-service, specifically addressing Australian HR and Fair Work compliance requirements[1][2].  \n[LOCAL] MartianLogic’s HRIS is developed and supported in Australia, with its HQ in North Sydney, targeting sectors such as education, healthcare, and NDIS by providing desk-less workforce management tools[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] In 2024, 99% of approximately 40 newly signed clients in the Greater Sydney/AU region adopted the full CoreHR suite, indicating strong local market adoption and commercial validation of MartianLogic’s broader HRIS vision[1].  \n[LOCAL] The modular and scalable design of MartianLogic’s platform enables rapid deployment for both SMEs and enterprises (ranging from 50 to 5,000 staff), supporting ongoing expansion within the region[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL/GLOBAL] The company history references early-stage investment by BSI, but there is no evidence of recent (past 12 months) funding rounds, capital injections, or high-profile investors for MartianLogic in the Greater Sydney Area or broader Australia[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] MartianLogic claims to have pioneered the job multi-posting category in Australia/New Zealand with its inaugural product “Adlogic,” which became the fastest-growing recruitment product in the region, adopted by major firms like Adecco and Randstad[1].  \n[LOCAL] In 2024, successful launches of compliance and CoreHR suite modules have been widely adopted by newly acquired Australian clients, reflecting the product-market fit in the local mid-market and enterprise segments[1].  \n[LOCAL] MartianLogic is ISO20771 certified and conducts annual penetration testing, reflecting a commitment to compliance and security for local enterprise clients in regulated sectors[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/GLOBAL] There is no specific mention of recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures within MartianLogic’s leadership team in the past 12 months.\n\n[INDUSTRY]  \n- The Australian HR tech landscape has seen rising demand for all-in-one HRIS platforms due to regulatory complexity (Fair Work Act, hybrid work, and workforce diversity initiatives), placing MartianLogic’s compliance-centric suite in a fast-growing local niche[2][3].  \n- The trend toward mobile-friendly, cloud-based solutions is accelerating adoption across sectors such as education and healthcare in Greater Sydney and nationally[2][3].\n\nIn summary, MartianLogic remains a locally headquartered, founder-led HR tech innovator with a focus on regulatory compliance, CoreHR modularity, and strong client uptake in Sydney and broader Australia. The company’s chief triggers and growth are product-led, with significant local traction and continued platform development as of 2024, but no recent external funding or major public leadership changes reported."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Salary $120,000 - $150,000 + super (OTE circa $250K+)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leading SaaS Human Resources Information Software (HRIS) Platform&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; ‘Seat at the Table’ for Product Meetings&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Martian Logic&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Martian Logic is a pioneering, modern SaaS-based Human Resources Information System (HRIS) platform. As customer satisfaction and market demand surge, we’re scaling our account management &amp;amp; sales team to seize this growth opportunity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Martian Logic success comes from having a category leading product that''s supported by an outstanding client success team and vouched for by many advocate clients.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Account Manager Opportunity&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you gained experience as a Recruitment Agency Recruiter and/or an Internal Talent Acquisition Partner, and wanting to explore a potentially more fulfilling, diverse, and rewarding opportunity? &lt;/strong&gt;This role could be exactly what you’re looking for! We are seeking an experienced recruiter/talent acquisition partner who''s looking to transition into an Account Management role.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Account Manager role is a pivotal role within our organisation, responsible for managing a number of Martian Logic’s key enterprise accounts. This exciting career pivot will enable you to fully utilise your technology skill-sets and exceptional people skills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Your key responsibilities will be a hybrid of increasing &amp;amp; retaining revenue within your customer accounts, as well as developing new business accounts. This is a ‘high touch’ role, most of your energies will be focussed on liaising with key SLT''s/ELT''s, typically HR Directors, CPO’s, CIO’s etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This could genuinely be the life changing career move you''ve been searching for.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience gained as an agency recruiter and/or an internal talent acquisition partner, wishing to explore a new and exciting challenge (whilst still remaining within the talent/people &amp;amp; culture sector)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You are very comfortable communicating/presenting to c-suite executives, you have an innate ability to develop and maintain mutually beneficial relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You are commercially savvy, and you’re often recognised for your superior commercial/business acumen&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to plan and forecast, creating a clear business strategy aimed at expanding &amp;amp; retaining your designated customer accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Key characteristics and personality traits should include self-motivation, energetic, drive, hunger to learn/further develop your skill-sets, creative, solutions driven mindset, tenacious, and resilient&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Please note there will be interstate travel required at times.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Martian Logic? Why This Role?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Salary, dependent on experience between $120,000-$150,000 + super (OTE circa $200,000-$250,000). Uncapped commissions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Company share options&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fantastic team culture, we are supportive, tech-savvy, subject matter experts, and we have a continuous improvement work environment/mindset&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of promoting and developing our people, this particular role has many roads to promotions including leadership, people management, head of implementation/support, to name just a few. Your increased cross-section of skills could provide you a platform to be considered a respected industry voice and leader.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have a key seat at the table, your ideas and feedback will be instrumental in important roadmap discussions, you’ll be a key contributor to the company’s growth strategy, whilst gaining invaluable consultative skills across multiple domains&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee benefits may include a contribution to your gym membership, discounts on a number of products and services etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you believe you''d be a great fit for this role, don''t let imposter syndrome get in your way. Apply today!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply for this role please click on the apply link below, alternatively you can speak to Kevin on or kevin@martianlogic.com for a confidential discussion about the role.&lt;/strong&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQFLMyc4enw0-g/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1715734200600/martianlogic_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=0B4yf24aUvhL9WqpJzUlribbgLkzc650030OxPRhzyo', '2025-09-20T06:17:09.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recWpTUvXectj43WN', 'Anomali', 'http://www.anomali.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/anomali', 'Redwood City, CA, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '201 - 500', '90', 'Anomali is a leading cybersecurity SaaS company with over 300 employees and active operations in Australia and Singapore. Recent appointment of a Chief Growth Officer, multiple product launches, and significant industry awards indicate strong growth and ongoing expansion. Presence of regional sales leadership in both Australia and Singapore, including a Regional Sales Manager, highlights immediate opportunities for external recruitment support in high-value sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAnomali achieved FedRAMP âIn Processâ status at the Moderate Impact level in August 2025, enabling broader adoption by U.S. federal agencies. The company also disrupted the SIEM market in February 2025 by helping a Fortune 500 institution reduce critical incidents by 90% after consolidating onto its unified security data platform.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAnomali appointed George Moser as Chief Growth Officer in June 2025, indicating a focus on scaling operations and go-to-market strategy. Multiple new product and initiative launches suggest ongoing team expansion, though specific hiring numbers are not public.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn April 2025, Anomali won three Global InfoSec Awards at RSA Conference for Market Innovator Next Gen SIEM, Trailblazing SecOps-As-A-Service, and Best Solution Threat Intelligence. The company also launched several new AI-powered offerings, including Anomali Agentic AI and ThreatStream AI Professional and Enterprise solutions between April and June 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nAppointed George Moser as Chief Growth Officer in June 2025 to drive company expansion and sales strategy. No other recent leadership changes identified in key sales or revenue roles."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Anomali delivers the leading AI-Powered Security and IT Operations Platform. Only Anomali integrates ETL, SIEM, Next-Gen SIEM, XDR, UEBA, SOAR, and TIP into one powerful platform. At the center is the Anomali Copilot that navigates a proprietary cloud-native security and IT data lake to drive first-in-market speed, scale, and performance at a fraction of the cost. Modernize security and IT operations to protect and accelerate your organization with better analytics, visibility, productivity, and talent retention.  \n\nBe Different. Be the Anomali. Learn more at www.anomali.com. "}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recWvJQdVffRH4X3c', 'Pure Storage', 'http://www.purestorage.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/purestorage', 'Santa Clara, CA', 'Computer Hardware Manufacturing,Software Development', '5,001-10,000 employees', '45', 'Pure Storage is an enterprise B2B tech company (computer hardware/software) actively hiring for a Sales Development Representative (SDR) in Melbourne, a primary target role. However, with over 5,000 employees, the company is likely to have sophisticated internal TA resources, reducing reliance on external recruitment. Multiple Tier 2 and Tier 1 decision makers (Sales Director, Regional Director, Area VP) are present in ANZ and Singapore, offering quality access. Strong local growth signals are evident through active SDR hiring and regional GTM expansion, but the enterprise size limits the overall recruitment opportunity for external agencies.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Pure Storage posted a Sales Development Representative (SDR) role for Melbourne, VIC as of August 29, 2025. This position is focused on Go-To-Market (GTM) operations and opportunity generation within the enterprise sector, indicating active local demand generation and ANZ pipeline growth[2].  \n[REGIONAL] The SDR role involves close collaboration across sales, marketing, and channel functions specific to the ANZ market, signalling ongoing investment in regional sales operations and expansion[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Pure Storage was named a Leader in Gartner’s 2025 Magic Quadrant for Enterprise Storage Platforms for the twelfth consecutive year, a status that enhances brand positioning and sales effectiveness in all markets[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Hiring an experienced SDR with 3+ years’ tech sales expertise, on-site in Melbourne, indicates growing local sales capacity—especially for early-stage enterprise market capture[2].  \n[REGIONAL] The SDR’s responsibilities include strategic prospecting and channel partner engagement, reflecting regional priorities for expanding Pure Storage’s GTM strength in ANZ[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Pure Storage’s ongoing product innovation—such as expanded object support in FlashArray and enhanced automation with Pure Fusion—underpins global demand and future headcount growth, benefiting local and regional teams[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds or capital milestones for Pure Storage are evident in available results for the past 12 months. As a publicly-traded company, Pure Storage’s recent expansion appears more operational than capital-driven.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] In 2025, Pure Storage received Gartner recognition for its enterprise storage platforms, for its twelfth straight year. Recent product advancements include workload automation, FlashArray upgrades, cyber resilience integrations (with Rubrik and CrowdStrike), all of which support large Australian enterprise requirements[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Customer satisfaction scores are high, with a 4.9/5 rating on Gartner Peer Insights and 98% recommendation rate as of August 2025[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No Melbourne- or Australia-specific executive moves surfaced in recent search results.  \n[GLOBAL] No global executive updates directly impacting APAC/ANZ operations are recorded for the last six months.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] Computer hardware and enterprise storage demand in Australia is being driven by artificial intelligence adoption, increasing data volumes, and the need for unified, cloud-based storage architecture[1]. The local sector is prioritising platforms that offer automation, compliance, and cyber resilience. GTM roles—especially in enterprise sales and channel management—are critical, with an average base salary for mid-level tech SDRs in Melbourne ranging AUD $70,000–$95,000 (OTE $100,000–$140,000+), reflecting high market demand[2].\n\nSummary of recent intelligence:\n- **Active local hiring and market engagement in Melbourne**\n- **Enhanced regional GTM operations and channel collaboration**\n- **Global reputation for innovation and customer satisfaction drives local momentum**\n- **No recent funding or executive changes, but strong industry expansion**\n- **Industry trends in AU align with Pure Storage’s strategic priorities**"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We’re in an unbelievably exciting area of tech and are fundamentally reshaping the data storage industry. Here, you lead with innovative thinking, grow along with us, and join the smartest team in the industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This type of work—work that changes the world—is what the tech industry was founded on. So, if you''re ready to seize the endless opportunities and leave your mark, come join us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role…&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pure Storage &lt;/strong&gt;is seeking a dynamic and driven &lt;strong&gt;Sales Development Representative (SDR) &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team in Australia. You will focus on the &lt;strong&gt;Australia / New Zealand (ANZ) &lt;/strong&gt;market - be the first point of contact between Pure and potential enterprise customers. You’ll be responsible for uncovering new opportunities, generating qualified leads, and collaborating closely with sales, marketing, and channel teams to drive growth in one of Pure’s fastest-growing regions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an exceptional opportunity to build your career in tech sales, gain exposure to enterprise customers, and work at the forefront of one of the most significant tech transitions today—from traditional disk storage to modern flash-based infrastructure.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;YOUR CHALLENGE…&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As An SDR, You Will&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and engage net-new opportunities within the India enterprise market through outbound prospecting and targeted campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualify and convert inbound leads, setting high-quality meetings for Account Executive teams.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Field Sales, Channel, and Marketing to align on territory plans and execute strategic outreach efforts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth account research to personalize your approach and develop meaningful outreach strategies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support sales pipeline progression, contributing to early-stage opportunity development with Account Executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize sales enablement tools daily, including Salesforce, LinkedIn, and other modern tech stacks.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay informed on market trends, competitor movements, and industry news to bring added value to conversations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring…&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;To excel in this role, you should have:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Passion: A strong drive for sales and relationship building.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enterprise Experience: Experience with direct/indirect sales on Enterprise accounts, especially within ANZ.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner Collaboration: Experience working with Channel, GSI, and Ecosystem Partners.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospecting Skills: Advanced skills in engaging new customers required.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ambition and Drive: A goal-oriented attitude and desire to drive change.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven Success: A track record of exceeding quotas and maintaining a robust pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Adaptability: Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Industry Knowledge: Understanding of cloud computing and Data Centre Architecture.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Excellent time management and communication abilities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience: 3+ years of inside / field sales experience.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Language Skills: Professional English proficiency.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Can Expect From Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pure Innovation: We celebrate those who think critically, like a challenge and aspire to be trailblazers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pure Growth: We give you the space and support to grow along with us and to contribute to something meaningful. We have been Named Fortune''s Best Large Workplaces in the Bay Area™, Fortune''s Best Workplaces for Millennials™ and certified as a Great Place to Work®!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pure Team: We build each other up and set aside ego for the greater good.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;And because we understand the value of bringing your full and best self to work, we offer a variety of perks to manage a healthy balance, including flexible time off, wellness resources and company-sponsored team events. Check out purebenefits.com for more information.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accommodations And Accessibility&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates with disabilities may request accommodations for all aspects of our hiring process. For more on this, contact us at TA-Ops@purestorage.com if you’re invited to an interview.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment To a Strong And Inclusive Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re forging a future where everyone finds their rightful place and where every voice matters. Where uniqueness isn’t just accepted but embraced. That’s why we are committed to fostering the growth and development of every person, cultivating a sense of community through our Employee Resource Groups and advocating for inclusive leadership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pure is proud to be an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, transgender status, sexual stereotypes, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or any other characteristic legally protected by the laws of the jurisdiction in which you are being considered for hire.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOIN US AND BRING YOUR BEST.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BRING YOUR BOLD.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BRING YOUR FLASH.&lt;/strong&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHQ2h8UmRkbzw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1720014761477/purestorage_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=Rc91ytTLZxGLPEaYf430L7l1FzkmsqMqEQrq_gfTUJc', '2025-09-20T14:11:51.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recX8M7SJFi0UnrWx', 'Atlassian', 'https://atlassian.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/atlassian', 'Sydney, NSW, AU', 'Computer Software', '10001 -', '90', 'Atlassian is a global leader in enterprise SaaS with strong industry alignment and a robust sales infrastructure in Australia. The company demonstrates exceptional growth signals, including record revenue, rapid product adoption, and major enterprise deal wins. Multiple senior sales and GTM leaders are present, indicating ongoing high-value hiring and a mature sales organization. These factors create an immediate and high-probability opportunity for external recruitment partnerships.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAtlassian surpassed $5.2 billion in annual revenue in Q4 FY25 with strong momentum in enterprise, AI, and workflow system strategy. The company secured a record number of deals greater than $1 million ACV, more than doubling year-over-year, and reached 2.3 million AI monthly active users across its platform as of July 2025.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nJira Product Discovery exceeded 20,000 customers, Loom MAU is growing over 30% year-over-year, and sales of Jira Service Management Premium and Enterprise editions are up more than 50% year-over-year. Atlassian continues to introduce platform-wide AI features and expand product integrations, enhancing enterprise adoption and cloud migration efforts.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAtlassian was recognized as a Leader in the Forrester Waveâ¢: DevOps Platforms, Q2 2025, earning the highest possible scores in vision and execution. Atlassian launched new AI automation features in 2025 and its partners, such as catworkx, won the Atlassian Partner of the Year 2024â2025 for High Velocity Service Management.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Atlassian powers the collaboration that helps teams accomplish what would otherwise be impossible alone.\n\nFrom space missions and motor racing to bugs in code and IT requests, no task is too large or too small with the right team, the right tools, and the right practices. \n\nOver 300,000 global companies and 80% of the Fortune 500 rely on Atlassianâs software, like Jira, Confluence, Loom, and Trello, to help their teams work better together and deliver quality results on time.\n\nWith our 300,000+ customers and team of 10,000+ Atlassians, we are building the next generation of team collaboration and productivity software.\n\nWe believe the power of teams has the potential to change the world â one that is more open, authentic, and inclusive."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
