    ('recYDRBvhEr8f15Zw', 'Wiz', 'https://www.wiz.io', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wizsecurity', 'New York, NY, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '501 - 1000', '45', 'Wiz is a growth-stage computer & network security company (core B2B tech) with 3,021 employees, fitting the ideal size profile. However, there is no explicit active sales role posting provided, and no recent sales/revenue leadership hires are noted. The company shows strong growth signals with rapid ARR increase, major product launches, and a pending $32B acquisition by Google. Decision maker access is unclear from the provided filtered employees, with no clear Tier 1 or Tier 2 sales leaders identified. While the industry and growth context are strong, the lack of explicit role and decision maker details limits immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nGoogle announced a definitive agreement to acquire Wiz for $32 billion on March 18, 2025, in what will be the largest cybersecurity acquisition to date. The transaction is pending regulatory approval and has attracted antitrust review as competition in cloud security intensifies.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nWiz reached annual recurring revenue of $500 million last year and is projected to cross $1 billion this year, indicating rapid revenue growth and adoption. The company has significantly expanded its market footprint by continuing to deliver new product categories and adding customers across startups, enterprises, and public sector organizations.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo new standalone funding rounds since prior to the Google acquisition announcement in March 2025; the $32 billion acquisition itself represents a major financial milestone for the company.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nWiz has become recognized as a leader in cloud and AI security, delivering a platform adopted by a range of customer segments and launching new cybersecurity solutions in the past 12 months. The company played a key incident response 