    ('recYHYuODFusP7WIw', 'Qualys', 'https://www.qualys.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qualys', 'Foster City, CA, US', 'Computer & Network Security', '1001 - 5000', '73', 'Qualys is a growth-stage Computer & Network Security company (3,118 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively expanding in Australia and Singapore. The presence of a Managing Director ANZ (Tier 1) and Principal for SouthEast Asia - New Business (Tier 2) provides high-level access for recruitment. While no specific active sales role is listed, recent expansion, revenue growth, and strategic partnerships indicate ongoing hiring needs, especially for core sales roles. This makes Qualys a high-priority recruitment opportunity for commercial sales talent.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nQualys launched inaugural managed Risk Operations Center (mROC) Alliance Partners in August 2025, strengthening strategic risk management offerings and expanding capabilities for government use with a new FedRAMP High authorized solution[1][2]. Expanded office presence in Washington D.C. and hosted its second annual Public Sector Cyber Risk Conference, reinforcing its commitment to the federal sector[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nQualys reported 10% year-over-year revenue growth and raised 2025 revenue guidance to $656â$662 million as of August 5, 2025[1][2]. Expanded channel momentum and adoption of new managed Risk Operations Center capabilities, alongside increased strategic partnerships, signal ongoing market and team growth[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn Q2 2025, Qualys was named Leader in the 2025 KuppingerCole Leadership Compass for Attack Surface Management and for Cloud Native Application Protection Platforms (CNAPP)[1][2]. TotalCloud and VMDR applications won best cloud security and vulnerability management solution honors at the SC Awards Europe in 2025; launched advanced AI security enhancements within TotalAI and improved Policy Audit capabilities in August 2025[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Qualys, Inc. (NASDAQ: QLYS) is a leading provider of disruptive cloud-based security, compliance and IT solutions with more than 10,000 subscription customers worldwide, including a majority of the Forbes Global 100 and Fortune 100. Qualys helps organizations streamline and automate their security and compliance solutions onto a single platform for greater agility, better business outcomes, and substantial cost savings. \n\nThe Qualys Enterprise TruRisk Platform leverages a single agent to continuously deliver critical security intelligence while enabling enterprises to automate the full spectrum of vulnerability detection, compliance, and protection for IT systems, workloads and web applications across on premises, endpoints, servers, public and private clouds, containers, and mobile devices. \n\nFounded in 1999 as one of the first SaaS security companies, Qualys has strategic partnerships and seamlessly integrates its vulnerability management capabilities into security offerings from cloud service providers, including Amazon Web Services, the Google Cloud Platform and Microsoft Azure, along with a number of leading managed service providers and global consulting organizations. For more information, please visit http://www.qualys.com."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
