cs, or supply chain roles in Australia or APAC/ANZ.\n[LOCAL] Physical office space exists in Melbourne, which could support local sales or support personnel[2]. No specific reports of sales/GTM roles hiring in Australia in the last 60 days.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No public announcements regarding recent investment rounds, financial milestones, or funding related to the Australian market or the APAC region in the last 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] The “Breakthroughs 2025” webinar highlighted Lumivero’s tools (@RISK, NVivo, NVivo AI Assistant) and their use in improving risk analysis, decision support, and qualitative research across multiple sectors, including logistics[4].\n[GLOBAL] Use cases presented in the webinar showed adoption of Lumivero solutions in industries such as project management and risk modeling, relevant to supply chain and logistics professionals[4]. No specific Australian awards, partnerships, or product launches were identified.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] No recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures relevant to APAC, ANZ, or Australia. Current leadership is based out of Denver, Colorado[3].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[LOCAL] The Australian transportation, logistics, and supply chain market continues to experience strong demand for advanced data analytics, risk management, and process optimization tools. Digital transformation and adoption of cloud-based platforms remain key trends, benefiting companies like Lumivero that provide analytics and decision support solutions.\n[GLOBAL] Globally, supply chain organizations increasingly rely on integrated qualitative and quantitative data tools (such as NVivo and @RISK) to mitigate risks and improve strategic decision making—an area where Lumivero positions its offerings[3][4].\n\nScope: Information on Lumivero’s transportation/logistics-specific activities in Australia and APAC is limited; most intelligence is global in nature, anchored in headquarters (Denver, Colorado) and general software capabilities rather than direct market activity."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Join a Global Team Making a Lasting Impact with Lumivero Are you ready to be part of a team that’s changing the world? At Lumivero, we develop powerful data-intelligence software that empowers users to answer their most pressing questions. Our trusted research, decision-making, and organizational tools help academic and corporate professionals create impactful insights from their most complex data – enabling them to work more efficiently and make informed, confident decisions.The Renewals Manager leads the contract renewal process from reach out to confirmation. A curious, creative problem solver, this person is responsible for securing renewals on time, identifying opportunities for account growth, and supporting the health of the account. This person picks up on customer concerns and connects our clients to the correct resource based on their need. They will be assigned a book of business based on factors including ARR spend, industry verticals, and strategic account expansion opportunities.They collaborate cross-functionally to support customer satisfaction, retention, and account growth. Renewals Managers respond to contract questions, requests, and escalations. Exceptional negotiators, they manage difficult conversations with tact. In support of company goals, Renewals Managers contribute to process improvements and supporting the team towards company success.Key ResponsibilitiesManage contract renewals for assigned accounts. Drive on-time renewals, identify cross/upselling opportunities, and ensure an efficient process. Elevate customer renewal retention rates, both in terms of customer numbers and revenue. Effectively negotiate renewal terms, balancing company and customer goals. Respond to contract questions and manage escalations. Provide creative solutions to secure the renewal. Account ExpansionProactively identifyopportunities to upsell and cross-sell our 