riable compensationAn annual performance-based bonus to recognize personal excellence. Annual tech stipend to get what you need to do your best workFlexible, remote first work environment and a diverse, global team. Opportunities for career advancement as Lumivero growsHelp Transform Our World with Powerful Insights – Join Our Team! At Lumivero, we believe in the power of research and informed problem-solving. Our data-intelligence software helps professionals in academia and business collect, organize, and analyze structured and unstructured data to identify risks, opportunities, themes, and patterns. Lumivero empowers them to do it all smarter, better, and faster!Our diverse, global team is made up of experts in their fields and dedicated professionals building best-in-field software. We’re passionate about the customers we serve, the products we create, and the problems we solve.Lumivero is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, disability, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, or national origin. Nothing in this job posting should be construed as an offer or guarantee of employment.Lumivero is an E-Verify Employer. You can review the E-Verify Poster. Lumivero is committed to supporting individuals requiring accommodation in the application process."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-30T14:12:28.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recYjK3BwJUUTW0xD', 'Canonical', 'http://www.canonical.com/', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/canonical', 'London, England, GB', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '74', 'Canonical is a leading computer software company with a strong presence in Australia and Singapore, aligning well with our target sectors. Recent partnership expansions, product launches, and workforce growth indicate ongoing business momentum, though there are no recent funding rounds. The presence of a Talent Acquisition Manager and Sales Director in APAC provides direct access to key decision makers, making this a strong prospect for recruitment services, particularly for sales and technical roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCanonical expanded its partnership with Broadcom to optimize VMware Cloud Foundation for modern container and AI workloads, announced on August 26, 2025. The company committed to long-term Ubuntu support and security for NVIDIA Jetson Thor on August 27, 2025, reflecting strategic moves in cloud and edge AI[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nCanonical reported a workforce increase from 1,034 to 1,175 employees in 2024, based on its most recent financial report. The company has modestly reduced sales and marketing expenses but increased investment in research and development, indicating ongoing technical and potential go-to-market expansion[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCanonical celebrated its 20th anniversary as publisher of Ubuntu and continues to sponsor major industry events such as KubeCon + CloudNativeCon North America 2024 (November 13â15, 2024). The company also announced a container design and build service for custom Docker images on June 26, 2024[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"We deliver open source to the world faster,  more securely and more cost effectively than any other company.\n\nWe''re also the publishers of Ubuntu, the worldâs most popular enterprise Linux from cloud to edge, together with a passionate global community of 200,000+ contributors. \n\nUbuntu means ''humanity to others''â. We chose it because it embodies the generosity at the heart of open source, the new normal for platforms and innovation.\n\nTogether with a community of 200,000, we publish an operating system that runs from the tiny connected devices up to the world''s biggest mainframes, the platform that everybody uses on the public cloud, and the workstation experience of the world''s most productive developers.\n\nSecure and reliable, elegant and intuitive, and open for innovation - this is the future of open source, which is why we''re proud to be the developers of the fastest growing Linux in the world despite already being the most widely deployed.\n\nIf you''re interested in a career at Canonical, we are a remote-first company so please apply to any suitable role as skills are valued more than location, despite some having a preferred geographic preference. \n\nwww.canonical.com "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recYuIZfMTmaOuTaT', 'NETSOL Technologies Inc.', 'https://www.netsoltech.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/netsol-technologies-inc-', 'Calabasas, CA, US', 'Information Technology & Services', '1001 - 5000', '65', 'NETSOL Technologies Inc. is a growth-stage IT & Services company (2,402 employees) actively operating in Australia and Singapore, with a recent focus on business expansion and major contract wins in the region. The inclusion was triggered by the Senior Account Director role, a high-priority core sales position. The company fits strongly within the commercial B2B tech sector, and decision makers such as the Managing Director AU/NZ and Senior Account Director provide Tier 1 and Tier 2 access for recruitment engagement. While there are no recent hiring surges or funding rounds, recent multi-million-dollar contracts and strategic partnerships signal ongoing business growth, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOn July 11, 2025, NETSOL Technologies China signed a strategic cooperation agreement at the SCO Summit in Tianjin with Tianjin Binhai Smart Group Co., Ltd. and the Dongjiang Free Trade Port Zone Government, focusing on integrated financial services for the automotive industry and cross-border data services[1][2]. On September 11, 2025, NETSOL announced a multi-million-dollar, long-term contract with a leading Australian auto captive finance company of Japanese origin for the deployment of its Transcend Finance platform across Australia and New Zealand[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo specific recent hiring or headcount expansion activities identified in the last 6-12 months. Activity centers on business expansion with the deployment of new solutions and specialized on-site team support as part of recent customer implementations[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nSecured a multi-million-dollar, five-year recurring revenue contract with a major auto captive finance customer in Australia as of September 2025[3]. Signed a high-profile strategic cooperation agreement at the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) Summit in July 2025, highlighting digital innovation leadership in the Chinese automotive financial sector[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles identified in the last 6-12 months. Amanda Li Linjie was noted as President of NETSOL Technologies China, representing the company in major partnership agreements as of July 2025[1][2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"NETSOL Technologies is a global leader in delivering state-of-the-art solutions for the asset finance and leasing industry, serving automotive and equipment OEMs, auto captives and financial institutions across over 30 countries. Since its inception in 1996, NETSOL has been at the cutting edge of technology, pioneering innovations with its flagship NETSOL Financial Suite (NFS) and leveraging advanced AI and cloud services to meet the complex needs of the global market. \n\nRenowned for its deep industry expertise, customer-centric approach and commitment to excellence, NETSOL fosters strong partnerships with its clients, ensuring their success in an ever-evolving landscape. With a rich history of innovation, ethical business practices and a focus on sustainability, NETSOL is dedicated to empowering businesses worldwide, securing its position as the trusted partner for leading firms around the globe. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recaGr1BaUe3f1TSd', 'aXcelerate', 'http://www.axcelerate.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/axcelerate-student-training-rto-management-systems', 'Toowong, Queensland', 'Software Development,Education Administration Programs,IT Services and IT Consulting', '51-200 employees', '60', 'aXcelerate is a growth-stage SaaS company (51-200 employees) in education administration and software, actively hiring for a Sales Executive role (lower-priority sales role). The company fits the commercial B2B tech profile and operates in Australia, but the primary role is not a core target for 4Twenty. Decision maker access includes a Head of Sales (Tier 2) and Manager, Customer Success (Tier 2), supporting recruitment engagement. Moderate growth signals are present, such as product innovation and steady hiring, but there are no recent funding rounds or major leadership changes. This results in a medium-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] aXcelerate has focused on compliance and product innovation to align with the new 2025 Standards for training management in Australia, indicating ongoing updates to its platform to maintain regulatory competitiveness[3].\n[LOCAL] The company maintains its headquarters in Toowong/Brisbane, Queensland, and continues to position itself as an industry leader in education administration and software tailored for the Australian vocational sector[1][3][4].\n[LOCAL] aXcelerate recently emphasized AI-powered features for its Learning Management System (LMS) and Student Management System (SMS), such as automation of admin tasks and AI-assisted content creation, highlighting a commitment to product modernization in direct response to industry needs in Brisbane and Australia[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] aXcelerate actively recruits talent in Brisbane, with open roles and encouragement for prospective applicants to submit resumes even when positions are not posted, suggesting steady local hiring demand, particularly in tech and client-facing roles[1].\n[LOCAL] The company achieved Great Place to Work certification, with 90% of employees in Brisbane and across Australia citing a positive onboarding experience, which can be indicative of strong retention and employer branding[1].\n[LOCAL] The company’s local leadership and operations retain a “Brisbane-first” identity, evolving from its origins as VM Learning and continuing to support regional upskilling and training providers[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No public funding rounds, venture investments, or new financial milestones were reported in the past 12 months; aXcelerate appears to remain privately held and focused on organic growth.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] aXcelerate is recognized as an “industry-leading” and “award-winning” training management software provider, with distinctions as state finalists and category winners in regional award programs, demonstrating acknowledgment by the Australian edtech sector[5].\n[LOCAL] The company’s push to integrate AI into its platform, along with spotlighting client success stories (e.g., Accredited First Aid Courses), reinforces its positioning as a leading Brisbane-based education software innovator[3][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] David O’Rourke remains as CEO and is directly based in Brisbane[2]. No recent major leadership appointments or departures were identified within the past 12 months. The core leadership team, with established presence in Queensland, continues to guide the company’s strategy[2][5].\n[LOCAL] No changes to sales, revenue, or people leader roles were observable, suggesting leadership stability at the Brisbane/AU HQ.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT (if company-specific news is limited):\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian software development and edtech market is experiencing increased regulatory demands (notably the new 2025 Standards), growing interest in AI-enhanced learning solutions, and ongoing digital transformation among registered training organizations and higher education providers. Demand for SaaS solutions that streamline compliance and integrate competency-based assessment reflects industry-wide adoption trends—precisely the sectors targeted by aXcelerate’s Brisbane-based team[3][5].\n\n**Scope notes:** All information above is based on the highest-precision, most recent, and most locally-specific intelligence available for Brisbane, Queensland, and, where relevant, broader AU operations, as of September 2025."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;aXcelerate is a leading SaaS provider, with our Student and Learning Management System powering millions of learners'' course and competency records nationwide. As an industry leader, we’re on an exciting growth journey, transforming the way training providers and employers manage and support their learners.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recognised as a Great Place to Work for two years running, we have a culture where people feel valued and supported to thrive. With ambitious growth plans and countless opportunities to develop your career, there’s never been a better time to join our team and help us shape the future of education technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this pivotal role as a &lt;strong&gt;Sales Executive&lt;/strong&gt;, you''ll leverage your established sales experience to identify and cultivate new business opportunities, manage the sales pipeline from prospecting to closure, and drive enterprise and mid-market client acquisition. We have a strong marketing team which creates a constant stream of inbound leads helping you to win some exciting clients and take the sales team to the next level!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and create new business opportunities to expand our national footprint&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Take a lead role in the development of proposals and presentations for new business materials to create and nurture business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify trends and customer needs, building a short/medium/long-term sales pipeline in accordance with targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate new leads, identify and contact decision-makers, screen potential business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Organise professional sales presentations/demonstrations of aXcelerate, including a summary of the prospect’s key requirements and pain points and tailored to suit their needs and branding&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create competitive and engaging business proposals and pricing information&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare tender processes and documentation to ensure a consistent, high-quality submission, including negotiating, drafting, and reviewing contracts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Research and build a prospective client list and evaluate market entry opportunities for our key prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Become a subject matter expert for our competing markets, monitor competitors'' sales and services offering strategies to optimise market share, and identify emerging trends/threats within the market&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track and record all sales activity in our CRM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attendance of conferences and events, including some interstate travel&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly refined B2B solution selling skills, including demonstrated experience selling to and negotiating with ‘C’ suite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling strategically to multiple stakeholders in medium to large organisations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of winning significant key enterprise accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience developing growth strategies and plans&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable history in consistent attainment of targets and KPI’s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional negotiation, influencing, presentation and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to create and develop business proposals, business case documents, contracts and other documentation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence in the ownership of the end-to-end sales process - from lead generation and outreach to deal negotiation and closing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in the SaaS or tech industry will be highly regarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;High earning potential with uncapped commission on top of your base salary&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working arrangement with an office location based in Toowong&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A vibrant, supportive and team-oriented culture, with regular team activities and social events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A focus on professional development and learning, with access to our LMS, external and internal training opportunities and your own personal annual PD budget&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access for you and your family to an Employee Assistance Program and resources&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cashback offers and discounts on popular brands through our Employment Hero app&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career development with well defined career pathways across the business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proud members of Women in Technology with access to networking events, professional development opportunities and resources&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To Apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please submit an up to date resume outlining your suitability for the role. For any queries please contact careers@axcelerate.com&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to promoting diversity in the workplace and encourage people from all backgrounds to apply. We''re looking for people who identify with our values - H.E.A.R.T.: Honesty, Empathy, Acceptance, Respect, and Trust, while also bringing an individual perspective to their work.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFkqTiqyX06eg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1736124770595/axcelerate_student_training_rto_management_systems_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=IuRxKyaFZQ3RRokyxiGd7Ne9DpAbRMC-4utNhyuonZw', '2025-09-23T14:39:49.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recaT8YWzTWT22h7F', 'Info-Tech Research Group', 'https://bit.ly/3v9VS4w', 'https://ca.linkedin.com/company/info-tech-research-group', 'London', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '1,001-5,000 employees', '70', 'Info-Tech Research Group is a growth-stage IT services and consulting company (1,001-5,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech focus and established Sydney operations. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Senior Sales Directors, Regional Directors, and a Senior VP for APAC) provides direct access for recruitment engagement. While there are no recent local hiring surges or major growth events, the company maintains steady global growth and a robust APAC sales leadership team. The most likely sales roles to be recruited are at the Sales Director or Regional Director level, which are high-priority core roles for 4Twenty. This represents a strong, but not top-tier, recruitment opportunity due to the absence of immediate hiring or major expansion signals.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Info-Tech Research Group maintains an established office in Sydney, NSW at Level 36, Governor Phillip Tower, 1 Farrer Place, and Level 6, 320 Pitt Street, signaling a strategic focus on direct engagement with Australian enterprise and public sector clients[1][4][6]. There were no major Sydney-specific trigger events (e.g., new office launches, large local partnerships) disclosed in public records for the past 6-12 months.\n\n[REGIONAL] Info-Tech drives Asia-Pacific growth and client success through its Sydney office, offering localized research, advisory, and sales support for ANZ and wider APAC organizations[1]. No recent regional strategic announcements were identified in the last year.\n\n[GLOBAL] The company launched global initiatives such as Leadership Summits and Exponential IT programs in 2023 to support IT leaders internationally, including those in APAC[4]. These programs are likely to reach local and regional clients.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office is referenced as a sales and support center for ANZ clients, but public postings in the last 6-12 months do not show major local hiring sprees or publicly advertised expansions[1][4][6].\n\n[GLOBAL] Info-Tech has grown to over 1,500 employees worldwide, serving 30,000+ IT professionals. Current signals show stable headcount, especially in core advisory and analyst teams, with steady global growth during 2023–2025[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Info-Tech Research Group is privately held and backed by several investors. No major new funding rounds or financial milestones were publicly reported in the last year[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] The firm’s Info-Tech Awards (run annually, most recently in 2024–2025) recognize leading IT organizations and professionals globally for digital transformation, IT operations excellence, and stakeholder satisfaction. Australian winners have not been named in the last published cycle, but regional organizations may participate[3]. The company supports key initiatives for CIOs in digital transformation and cybersecurity through actionable diagnostics and advisory programs[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] The most significant executive change was David Godfrey’s appointment as CEO in January 2023, with Joel McLean moving to Executive Chairman. The C-level team has remained stable since then, with no reported Sydney- or APAC-specific leadership changes or regional appointments in 2024–2025[1].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The IT services and consulting market in Australia is experiencing strong demand, led by digital transformation, cybersecurity, and cloud adoption, especially among mid-market and enterprise clients in Sydney and NSW. Clients increasingly seek vendors offering actionable research, diagnostics, and hands-on advisory—directly aligning with Info-Tech’s value proposition for local IT leaders.\n\nSummary: Info-Tech Research Group operates a well-established Sydney office as part of its APAC growth strategy, offering targeted research and advisory for enterprise clients. While no public records highlight major Sydney-specific events or APAC leadership changes in the last year, the firm is recognized for steady global and regional growth, award programs, and continued expertise supporting IT transformation in Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Sr Account Manager, you will play a vital role in promoting and selling the full suite of Info-Tech products and services to prospective and existing clients. Your responsibilities will include conducting lead generation activities, booking sales presentations, delivering compelling sales pitches, managing sales opportunities, and providing valuable customer feedback. You will also manage an existing book of business, focusing on client retention and satisfaction. Collaborating closely with the research department, you will build trusted relationships with technology and business leaders at the CxO level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in a Sales role serving technology and business leaders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of sales success and achieving or exceeding targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with modern sales environments and CRM tools such as Salesforce or Microsoft Dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for personal and professional growth, demonstrated by a willingness to learn and receive ongoing coaching and training.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to establish and maintain trust-based relationships with C-level executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct consistent monthly prospecting and lead generation activities using online resources, sales tools, and marketing campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with marketing leads and conduct warm calls in your assigned territory to schedule onsite sales presentations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customize presentations to align with the target audience, ensuring a compelling pitch.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute sales appointments professionally, showcasing product knowledge and adhering to Info-Tech Research Group''s sales processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Efficiently manage sales opportunities throughout the pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage an existing book of business to ensure high levels of client satisfaction and retention.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in ongoing sales coaching, training, and personal development activities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide valuable customer feedback to senior leadership for sales and marketing improvements.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the research department to include relevant analysts in sales presentations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Selection Criteria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Preferred prior experience selling to IT and business leaders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Asset: Prior experience selling IT Research, Advisory, and Consulting services.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prior experience selling IT-related products and/or services in the Australian Market.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to build and maintain trusted relationships with C-level executives and staff at all levels.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage in value-based client conversations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset with excellent listening, critical thinking, and verbal/written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Adaptability to thrive in an entrepreneurial, flexible, and rapidly changing work environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Intellectual curiosity about the impact of IT on the business landscape, with a passion for continuous learning.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Availability for travel to conduct onsite meetings with prospective clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s or Master''s Degree.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation package&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Health Insurance benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible work policy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee recognition and development programs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Info-Tech Research Group of companies is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusion and does not discriminate on the basis of any legally protected status or characteristic including Minority/Female/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Disability/Veteran and are pleased to consider all qualified applicants. To that end, upon request, ITRG will ensure, to the extent possible, that accommodation be made available to applicants throughout the recruitment and hiring process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEElIFVWsr6BA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1709588621977/info_tech_research_group_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=1OWmFjKkU4lUdWN8bYkeIBxdr1m0qdivVrJiYTLhz08', '2025-09-25T05:13:36.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recbO5im0edredJYs', 'Outcomex', 'http://www.outcomex.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/outcomex-pty-ltd', 'North Ryde, NSW, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '51 - 200', '66', 'Outcomex is a growth-stage IT services company (130 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech focus, actively expanding its Melbourne office and increasing sales/engineering headcount, as indicated by recent team expansion and market activity. The presence of Ben Blaschka (Sales Director, Tier 2 decision maker) and Michael van Zoggel (Managing Director, Tier 1) provides solid access for recruitment discussions. The current sales hiring trigger (role unspecified but inferred from sales expansion) and multiple growth signals (office opening, event participation, awards) make this a high-priority opportunity for external recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOutcomex won the Cisco Partner Summit \"Partnering for Purpose: Crisis Response Award\" in 2024 for their IoT connectivity solution supporting first responders, demonstrating leadership in emergency response technology[2]. The company also expanded its Melbourne office in 2024, signaling regional growth and commitment to broader service coverage[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nOutcomex opened a new Melbourne office in late 2024 and increased participation at industry events such as Cisco Live 2024, bringing in teams from South Africa and New Zealand and highlighting team growth and market expansion initiatives[3][4]. No public hiring numbers are available, but LinkedIn and event activity suggest team expansion across engineering and sales, especially in support of IoT and AI-driven solutions[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOutcomex was awarded the Cisco Partner Summit \"Partnering for Purpose: Crisis Response Award\" in November 2024, and won multiple engineering competitions (first, second, and third place) at Cisco Live 2024[2][4]. The company also celebrated several community and charity engagements, reinforcing its strong corporate culture[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nBen Blaschka (Sales Director) and Michael van Zoggel (Managing Director) publicly represented Outcomex at the Cisco Partner Summit in November 2024, but no major executive changes or new hires in revenue or people roles have been reported in the last 12 months[2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Outcomex is an award winning advisor, devoted to providing intuitive solutions in information technology. In todayâs digitally connected world, we believe it is essential for organisations to align every part of their strategy in order to become an industry leader. We are dedicated to help our clients deal with this challenge and overcome the many obstacles they face when connecting with new technologies.\n\nSince our foundation in 2006, weâve prided ourselves on being agile, and on tailoring our projects to enhance the operational efficiency of our clients through our various services. We create synergy between people and the digital world, working closely with industry leading vendor Cisco to deliver cutting edge services. \n\nOur expertise includes consulting in hybrid cloud, managed services, networking, mobility, security, IP telephony, contact centre and data centres. Our effort has been recognised in 2016 as the Ciscoâs Most Outstanding Security Partner for ANZ 2016."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recbkYg18Bf3Mrvzy', 'Humanforce', 'https://www.humanforce.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/humanforce-hq', 'North Sydney, New South Wales', 'Software Development', '201-500 employees', '74', 'Humanforce is a growth-stage B2B SaaS company (201-500 employees) in the HR/workforce management software sector, actively hiring for Enterprise Account Executive roles. This is a high-priority core sales position, and the company operates in a core commercial tech vertical. Decision makers include a Chief Sales Officer and Sales Director (Tier 1), as well as current Enterprise Account Executives (Tier 2), providing strong access for recruitment engagement. Multiple growth signals are present, including product rebranding, ongoing feature enhancements, and continuous hiring in Sydney. While there are no recent funding rounds or executive changes, the combination of core sales role hiring, strong industry fit, and quality decision makers makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] In March 2025, *intelliHR*, a Humanforce product, was fully rebranded to **Humanforce HR** for all Australian customers, unifying the product suite and strengthening Humanforce’s position in the Human Capital Management (HCM) sector for frontline and flexible workforces in Australia[1].  \n[LOCAL] On June 1, 2024, Humanforce *limited customer service support for on-premise clients in Australia*, encouraging transitions to the Humanforce Cloud platform[3].  \n[LOCAL] Ongoing product updates with new and enhanced features for Sydney/North Sydney customers, focusing on onboarding, compliance, payroll, and workforce management in response to local user feedback, as documented in August 2025 updates[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Humanforce’s Sydney HQ at Level 10, 90 Arthur St, North Sydney, is actively hiring, with local careers and talent community pages indicating continuous need for professionals in workforce management, payroll, HR, and SaaS platform support especially across areas serving aged care, healthcare, childcare, retail, hospitality, and events sectors[2].  \n[LOCAL] The company operates core functions and support from North Sydney, with local phone support for AU clients, suggesting steady in-country presence and customer service infrastructure[2].  \n[LOCAL] Multiple updates in 2024-2025 aimed at streamlining onboarding and cross-functional HR features, pointing to expanded platform capabilities and ongoing investment in tech improvements[1][5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent (last 12 months) direct reports of new funding rounds; historical investments and acquisitions (such as intelliHR) are in the background but not newly announced. Recent activities focus on platform consolidation and product suite expansion rather than explicit financial milestones[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Successful rebrand and product unification with intelliHR now fully integrated as Humanforce HR since March 2025, presenting a consolidated HCM offering for Sydney-based and national Australian clients[1].  \n[LOCAL] Continuous enhancements and new features deployed for AU clients, especially around onboarding, compliance, payroll, superannuation, and HR process automation[1][4][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No specific executive appointments, promotions, or departures in Sydney reported in the last 6-12 months from public release channels. Focus in this period has been on product and customer experience updates more than leadership restructuring.\n\n[INDUSTRY] In Sydney/AU software development, sector trends in 2025 continue to favor **cloud migration, HR automation, compliance management, and workforce analytics**, reflecting Humanforce’s product strategy and investments as local organizations digitize HR processes and move SaaS HR solutions to the cloud[3].  \n\n**Scope note:** All intelligence drawn first from Sydney/North Sydney operations or AU activity, by hierarchy. If more granular leadership or hiring data emerges, further detail can be layered in."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Work options:&lt;/strong&gt; Hybrid&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are passionate about people making their own decisions about where and when they work. Our hybrid model of minimum two days a week of in office moments supports flexibility tailored to individual and team needs, empowering people to achieve their career and personal goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Who are we?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Humanforce’s vision is to make work easier and life better for frontline and flexible workforces.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Humanforce provides the market leading, best-in-one human capital management (HCM) suite for frontline and flexible workforces - without compromise. Our employee centred, intelligent and compliant HCM suite is highly integrated and composable, and consists of Workforce Management (WFM), HR, Talent, Payroll, and Wellbeing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Humanforce has built strong foundations since its founding in 2002. We help over 2300 customers and almost 1 million employees under management in 30+ countries, across a wide range of industries, including aged, child and health care; education; hospitality; retail; local government and more. Today, we have offices across Australia, New Zealand, United Kingdom, North America and the Philippines.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Customers choose Humanforce because we enable them to deliver an exceptional employee experience, build a compelling employee value proposition, and connect the flow of the world’s talent with the growth, productivity and efficiency objectives of frontline and flexible workforces.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You are a solution-oriented person with strong technical skills and a knack for problem-solving. In this customer-facing role, you thrive at translating detailed technical ideas into straightforward plans that instil confidence and clarity into customers. This position offers you the chance to delve deep into the industry, becoming a trusted expert across Payroll, WFM, HR, Recruitment and Benefits solutions. This is an opportunity to master these domains and empowering clients with comprehensive knowledge and guidance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leading discovery calls with customers to better understand their requirements to provide targeted solutions &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Building and delivering detailed software demonstrations &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support the sales team with product knowledge and technical expertise &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribute to our product’s evolution and continuously educate yourself on new feature designs and the product roadmap. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Helping to contribute to pre-sales documentation, including building interactive product demonstrations &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assisting with responses to bids &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience with Payroll, WFM, Recruitment or HR software &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in Payroll services or payroll domain knowledge would be highly preferred. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Complex enterprise sales cycle experience &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills with the ability to work autonomously and lead key conversations, influencing at a c-suite level. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some ‘nice to haves’ &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You are a confident, engaging presenter with the ability to influence C-level HR leaders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional technical writing skills for bids, SoWs, and solution documentation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus points for experience with Humanforce products or platform!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Our values&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are bold &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are all in &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are customer obsessed &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We do what we say &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are good humans &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Our approach to flexibility&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are passionate about people making their own decisions about where and when they work. Our hybrid model of minimum two days a week of in office moments supports flexibility tailored to individual and team needs, empowering people to achieve their career and personal goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A truly flexible workplace through our Flex@HF approach &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to be part of a fast-growing global tech company &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A focus on learning and development through Humanforce HR &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A generous talent referral program – know great people, be rewarded &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;12 weeks paid parental leave for primary carers, 4 weeks’ for secondary &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;4 extra days leave to focus on your wellbeing &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contemporary and practical Employee Assistance Program &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A cool reward and recognition program – shout to your colleagues and earn points to spend &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access to our own financial wellbeing platform Thrive – including earned wage access, tools to budget and save, perks and cashback across 100s of Australian retailers &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fun, collaborative culture with passionate people &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A workplace where you can genuinely improve the world of work! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are a diverse and dispersed organisation and are actively looking to grow our team with individuals from all diverse backgrounds. We encourage applicants from all backgrounds, cultures, ages, genders, neurodiversity, religions, sexual orientations, and experiences to apply.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFglmLZd-a_1Q/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1691049530456/humanforce_hq_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=gzxiwSV5oD-0fzYB4-jNC20Lzbg6Ka-a7cCSEh9l6H4', '2025-10-01T14:16:51.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recbscsBaUvoQHl30', 'OFX', 'https://www.ofx.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/ofx', 'Sydney, NSW, AU', 'Financial Services', '501 - 1000', '68', 'OFX is a growth-stage financial technology company (707 employees) actively employing for sales roles such as Account Executive, Inside Sales Representative, and Business Development Manager, indicating ongoing commercial expansion. The industry fit is strong secondary tech (Fintech), and the company operates in both Australia and Singapore. Tier 2 decision makers like the Head of Enterprise Sales & Partnerships APAC and Senior Partnerships Account Manager are present, providing direct access to hiring authorities. Recent product launches and platform innovation signal moderate growth, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity for core sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOFX launched its digital Forward product for SMEs on August 18, 2025, designed to simplify locking in exchange rates for future payments and improve accounts payable processes[1][3]. The company also renewed key sports partnerships in 2025, enhancing its brand visibility in Europe[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nOFX reported employing over 700 people globally as of September 2025, maintaining offices across Australia, North America, UK, Ireland, Europe, and Asia[2]. The company has focused on platform innovation, especially integrating with accounting systems and automating financial workflows to drive adoption and scalability among SME clients[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOFX redesigned its global payments platform in September 2025, now integrating directly between accounting systems and banks, and using AI to automate invoice capture and financial controls[2]. OFX''s digital Forward product launch in August 2025 marks a significant advance in SME financial management[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nOFX appointed a global B2B payment specialist as Regional President, North America in 2024, but no executive changes specifically in sales, revenue, or people roles have been reported within the last six months[3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Sending money overseas can feel complicated, at OFX we keep it simple. With 20+ years in the FX business, OFX provides a fast, reliable, and secure way to transfer your money globally - at a great rate.\n\nWe grew from the idea that there had to be a better way to move money around the world, and we are driven by that same mission today. We believe real help from real people matters, thatâs why we offer our clients the best of both worlds, an easy-to-use digital platform, combined with 24/7 customer support from our Currency Experts, we call them OFXperts.\n\nAs a publicly listed and regulated company, we can support all of your FX and global payment needs with 50+ currencies and transfers to over 170 countries around the world. \n\nWith a global team of OFXperts and offices located around the world, we stay on top of global markets 24/7 so you don''t have too.  Focus on your business, not exchange rates and let our team help you save time and money. \n\nGet started today: https://secure2.ofx.com/registration\n\nhttp://www.ofx.com/legal/\n\nThe Commissioner of Financial Regulation for the State of Maryland will accept all questions or complaints from Maryland residents regarding USForex Inc. (NMLS: #1021624) at: \n\nOffice of the Commissioner of Financial Regulation\nMaryland Department of Labor\n1100 N. Eutaw Street, Room 611, Baltimore, MD 21201 \nhttp://www.labor.maryland.gov/\n+1-888-373-7888\n \nOFXâs license status information can be viewed on the NMLS Consumer Access website at https://nmlsconsumeraccess.org/\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recbu4Owwk9CSy0Es', 'Sprout Social, Inc.', 'https://www.sproutsocial.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sprout-social-inc-', 'Chicago, Illinois, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '79', 'Sprout Social, Inc. is a growth-stage computer software (SaaS) company with 1,749 employees, operating in Australia and Singapore, and actively hiring for Enterprise Account Executive and Senior Account Executive roles—both high-priority core sales positions. The presence of Tier 1 (GM and Head of GTM APAC, Head of Sales - APAC) and Tier 2 (Industry Lead, Enterprise Account Executives) decision makers provides strong access for recruitment engagement. While there are no recent funding rounds or explicit hiring surges, consistent double-digit revenue growth and exceeding analyst expectations signal ongoing operational scaling and market demand. This makes Sprout Social a high-priority recruitment opportunity for core sales roles in APAC.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSprout Social reported strong revenue growth of 13% year-over-year to $109.3 million in Q1 2025 and continued momentum with $111.78 million in revenue for Q2 2025, up 12.5% from the previous year. The company’s stock price and analyst targets have been volatile, with price target downgrades in August 2025 but maintaining a consensus rating of “Moderate Buy” as of August 2025[1][2][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nThere is no direct evidence of significant hiring or team expansion in recent months, but analyst reports note expectations for continued growth and the company has displayed consistent year-over-year revenue increases, suggesting sustained market demand and operational scaling[1][2][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or new investment announcements have been identified in the last 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nKey achievements include surpassing $111 million in quarterly revenue and exceeding analyst earnings estimates (Q2 2025 EPS of $0.18 vs. consensus of $0.15), as well as a 21% increase in current remaining performance obligations in Q1 2025[1][2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles have been identified in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Sprout Social is a global leader in social media management and analytics software. Sprout’s intuitive platform puts powerful social data into the hands of more than 30,000 brands so they can deliver smarter, faster business impact. \n\nWith a full suite of social media management solutions, Sprout offers comprehensive publishing and engagement functionality, customer care, advocacy, and AI-powered business intelligence. Sprout’s award-winning software operates across all major social media networks and digital platforms. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:31:17.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reccS9Jl5Z230KoaO', 'Fluke Corporation', 'https://www.fluke.com/en-us/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fluke-corporation', 'Everett, WA, US', 'Electrical & Electronic Manufacturing', '1001 - 5000', '54', 'Fluke Corporation is a growth-stage electrical and electronic manufacturing company (3236 employees) with operations in Australia and Singapore, actively hiring for regional sales management roles. The industry fit is acceptable for B2B tech but not core SaaS or software, and the primary focus is on hardware and industrial solutions. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present (Managing Director, Regional Manager, Sales Director), providing strong access for recruitment. While there are recent product launches and a key leadership appointment (Chief Product Officer), there are no recent funding events or clear sales team expansion signals, limiting immediate external recruitment likelihood. This makes Fluke a medium-priority opportunity for sales recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nFluke Corporation announced the launch of the GFL-1500 Ground Fault Locator specifically designed for solar technicians on September 8, 2025, aiming to address critical safety concerns and improve efficiency in utility-scale solar systems. Earlier in the year, Fluke released surveys addressing gaps in EV industry adoption (February 19, 2025) and solar industry innovation, and unveiled multiple new products focusing on solar and electrical testing tools.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent hiring expansion or sales/GTM headcount growth activity publicly identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investment announcements, or major financial milestones identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nFluke Corporation launched several new products, including the GFL-1500 Ground Fault Locator in September 2025, an iSee Mobile Thermal Camera in September 2024, and the 1670 Series Multifunction Installation Tester in July and September 2024. The company also celebrated its 75th anniversary and obtained certification as an NABCEP Registered Training Provider to support the solar workforce development.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nFluke appointed Vineet Thuvara, a former Amazon and Microsoft executive, as Chief Product Officer in mid-2025 to lead the company’s solutions and strategy organization. No other recent executive changes in sales/revenue/people roles identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Fluke Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Fortive Corporation (NYSE: FTV), is the world leader in the manufacture, distribution and service of electronic test tools and software.\n\nFluke is proud to be one of Fortive’s 19 operating companies. Fortive is a diverse global team working together to deliver essential technology that makes the world stronger, safer, and smarter."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:27:02.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recdB7DMUYQ0FwRAy', 'Sprinklr', 'https://www.sprinklr.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sprinklr', 'New York, NY', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '62', 'Sprinklr is a growth-stage global SaaS company (1,001-5,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit and active presence in Australia and Singapore. The most relevant recent sales role is ''Account Executive – Commercial & Mid Market'', which is a high-priority core role (35 points). Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present in-region, including a Regional Manager, Director of Sales, and Senior VP of Sales, providing quality access (20 points). However, there are no recent local hiring surges, funding rounds, or Sydney-specific growth signals (0/15 for growth signals). While Sprinklr’s industry and company size are ideal, the lack of explicit local hiring activity or expansion reduces immediate recruitment opportunity, making this a medium-priority lead.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] No explicit Sydney- or Australia-specific business development events or office openings are cited in available sources from the past 12 months.  \n[REGIONAL] No recent public announcements specific to APAC or ANZ triggering events in the last year were found.  \n[GLOBAL] Sprinklr continues to implement a global growth strategy focused on expanding core AI-enabled platforms—including Social, Insights, Marketing, and Service—while placing increased emphasis on growing international revenue, which comprised 41% of overall revenue in both 2024 and 2025[1]. Strategic attention to partnerships with system integrators and technology partners is intended to drive deeper regional market penetration[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] No direct evidence of recent hiring activity, job postings, or office expansion in Sydney or Australia was identified within the last 6-12 months.  \n[REGIONAL] No disclosed ANZ/APAC hiring surges or localized sales team expansions in this period.  \n[GLOBAL] As of January 2025, Sprinklr served 1,930 enterprise customers globally and has signaled ongoing investment in international sales and marketing to increase its customer base and deepen client engagements, with a stated ambition to cross-sell and upsell to existing accounts[1]. This includes a focus on further international expansion, supported by a growing global headcount and network of 25 offices in 16 countries, though specific Sydney staffing levels are not detailed[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding rounds, major capital raises, or financial milestones have been disclosed in public sources for the last 12 months. Sprinklr remains publicly listed and has focused on organic growth versus external capital infusion in recent disclosures[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] No Sydney- or Australia-specific product launches, partnerships, or awards documented in the last year.  \n[REGIONAL] No APAC- or ANZ-specific milestones, partnerships, or industry recognitions found within recent public records.  \n[GLOBAL] Sprinklr has continued to broaden its solution set, advancing AI integration for marketing, customer insights, and next-generation call/contact center solutions marketed globally—including to customers in Australia[4]. Recent platform enhancements are aimed at supporting omnichannel customer engagement and compliance with evolving privacy regulations (such as Australia’s Privacy Act)[2][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No announcements of executive appointments, promotions, or departures specific to Australia or Sydney operations in the last 12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] Effective November 2024, there was a transition in top executive roles: a co-CEO moved to an Advisor capacity, signaling ongoing evolution in the company’s senior leadership team[1]. No APAC- or ANZ-targeted leadership appointments reported[1].\n\n[INDUSTRY] The software development sector in Australia continues to see strong enterprise demand for unified AI-powered CX, marketing, and social media management tools, especially as companies adapt to evolving privacy regulations, the rise of social commerce, and increasing investment in short-form and influencer-driven content strategies[2]. Local and regional adoption of sophisticated SaaS platforms remain market growth drivers.\n\n**Key Gaps & Inferences:**  \nNo evidence was found of major new local Sydney activities, leadership changes, or hiring drives in the last 12 months. Sprinklr’s public materials reference active marketing in Australia, including compliance with local privacy laws and platform suitability for brands addressing the Australian market[2]. Regional and global signals indicate Australia is part of the broader opportunity map, but with limited direct intelligence on Sydney-specific team or office developments."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Sprinklr is a leading enterprise software company for all customer-facing functions. With advanced AI, Sprinklr''s unified customer experience management (Unified-CXM) platform helps companies deliver human experiences to every customer, every time, across any modern channel. Headquartered in New York City with employees around the world, Sprinklr works with more than 1,000 of the world’s most valuable enterprises — global brands like Microsoft, P&amp;amp;G, Samsung and more than 50% of the Fortune 100.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Learn more about our culture and how we make our employees happier through The Sprinklr Way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We currently have a great opportunity for a Sales Development Representative to join our motivated and creative Inside Sales team! As an SDR, you''ll be responsible for creating interest and developing conversations with contacts at enterprise corporations. Team members are passionate about the ongoing transformation of inside sales to something that is personal, value-filled, and representative of social disruption.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you''ll do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You will actively seek out new sales leads and business opportunities through active networking and sending personal, strategic, value-add emails, outbound calls and social messages (no copying and pasting). You will be able to quickly research a company, see opportunities, and strategise an approach to build interest. You will profile potential prospects based on predetermined criteria. You will secure meetings for your Account Executives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are and what makes you qualified:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Language proficiency in professional English (verbal and written)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Desire to be in a software sales (full cycle) position as a career progression&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a verifiable track record of success and goal attainment in a sales-oriented role&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a passion for technology and disruptive technology&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a deep understanding of the role social media plays in business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have some in an SDR/BDR role (Enterprise experience preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have a run-through-a-brick-wall level of drive, passion, and desire for results&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in creative outbound reaches&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You''ll Love Sprinklr: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We''re committed to creating a culture where you feel like you belong, are happier today than you were yesterday, and your contributions matter. At Sprinklr, we passionately, genuinely care. For full-time employees, we provide a range of comprehensive health plans, leading well-being programs, and financial protection for you and your family through a range of global and localized plans throughout the world.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For more information on Sprinklr Benefits around the world, head to https://sprinklrbenefits.com/ to browse our country-specific benefits guides.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We focus on our mission: We founded Sprinklr with one mission: to enable every organization on the planet to make their customers happier. Our vision is to be the world’s most loved enterprise software company, ever.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in our product: Sprinklr was built from the ground up to enable a brand’s digital transformation. Its platform provides every customer-facing team with the ability to reach, engage, and listen to customers around the world. At Sprinklr, we have many of the world''s largest brands as our clients, and our employees have the opportunity to work closely alongside them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We invest in our people: At Sprinklr, we believe every human has the potential to be amazing. We empower each Sprinklrite in the journey toward achieving their personal and professional best. For wellbeing, this includes daily meditation breaks, virtual fitness, and access to Headspace. We have continuous learning opportunities available with LinkedIn Learning and more.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;EEO - Our philosophy: Our goal is to ensure every employee feels like they belong and are operating in a judgment-free zone regardless of gender, race, ethnicity, age, and lifestyle preference, among others. We value and celebrate diversity and fervently believe every employee matters and should be respected and heard. We believe we are stronger when we belong because collectively, we’re more innovative, creative, and successful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sprinklr is proud to be an equal-opportunity workplace and is an affirmative-action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, or Veteran status. See also Sprinklr’s EEO Policy and EEO is the Law."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQEW9sPQpGYYPg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1691600977849/sprinklr_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=wzozfOtf48v9wXTqnQD0Q-PhCEgUALa3iTYxbw_JHmI', '2025-09-20T14:20:42.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recdOi4bfLQWpfotJ', 'Fireblocks', 'https://fireblocks.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fireblocks', 'New York, NY', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '77', 'Fireblocks is a growth-stage software/fintech company (501-1,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively expanding its digital asset infrastructure in Australia and APAC. The presence of multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Directors in Australia and Singapore, Head of Sales for APAC) provides direct access to regional sales leadership. While there is no explicit current sales role posting, the company''s recent high-profile partnerships, product launches, and institutional client wins in Australia signal robust market activity and likely ongoing sales hiring needs. This makes Fireblocks a high-priority recruitment opportunity, particularly for core sales roles in the ANZ region.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] Melbourne-based CloudTech Group selected Fireblocks as technology partner for deploying their new stablecoin product, Ubiquity, leveraging Fireblocks’ tokenization platform for secure and compliant rapid deployment in Australia, as of June 2025[4].  \n[REGIONAL] Fireblocks is participating in Project Acacia, a major Reserve Bank of Australia and Digital Finance CRC initiative begun July 2025, to prototype atomic settlement of tokenised securities using central bank digital currency (CBDC), stablecoins, and deposit tokens, collaborating with several Australian and regional firms[2].  \n[LOCAL] Australian digital asset firm Zerocap became the first Australian liquidity provider to launch with Fireblocks Network for Payments in September 2025, marking an expansion of stablecoin payment capabilities for local financial institutions through Fireblocks[1].  \n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[REGIONAL] Fireblocks’ ongoing partnerships with Australian technology, finance, and digital asset organizations—CloudTech, Zerocap, Australian Bond Exchange—suggest active expansion and targeted solution launches in the ANZ market[1][2][4].  \n[LOCAL] Specific hiring or sales/GTM team expansion in Victoria is not publicly disclosed, but Fireblocks’ selection by Melbourne-based and national financial service firms indicates growing traction with institutional customers[4][1].  \n[GLOBAL] Fireblocks launched its Global Custodian Partner Program in May 2024 to facilitate compliant digital asset custody; Zerocap, headquartered in Melbourne, is among the initial partners, underscoring Australia’s significance to Fireblocks’ network[3].  \n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds have been publicly reported for Fireblocks in the last 6–12 months; the company’s last major global financing event appears predating this range. Current expansion appears to be funded by existing resources and revenue[1][2][3].  \n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \n[LOCAL] Successful onboarding of CloudTech (Melbourne) and stablecoin Ubiquity launch demonstrate localized product adoption in Victoria[4].  \n[LOCAL] Integration with Zerocap brought Australia’s first direct stablecoin payments via the Fireblocks Network and expanded institutional digital asset liquidity options for Australian clients as of September 2025[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Participation in RBA’s Project Acacia as one of a chosen few industry experiments has positioned Fireblocks as a major digital asset infrastructure player in Australia and the broader Asia-Pacific region[2].  \n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \n[REGIONAL][GLOBAL] Amy Zhang remains Head of APAC at Fireblocks as of September 2025, actively quoted in the company’s recent regional press releases; no Victoria-specific or Australia-based executive appointments announced in the public record over the past 12 months[1][2].  \n\n**Summary:**  \nFireblocks has considerably increased its operational presence and partnerships in Australia and Victoria over the last year, supporting multiple marquee launches—most notably in stablecoin infrastructure and tokenized asset settlement—with collaborations reflecting deep involvement in the region’s digital asset ecosystem. Although there is no evidence of a standalone Victoria office or published sales/GTM hiring blitz, the company’s APAC activity, expansion of payment infrastructure, and engagement with both fintechs and regulators signal robust growth and strategic focus on the Australia market[1][2][3][4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"The world of digital assets is accelerating in speed, magnitude, and complexity, opening the door to new ways for leveraging the blockchain. Fireblocks’ platform and network provide the simplest and most secure way for companies to work with digital assets and it trusted by some of the largest financial institutions, banks, globally-recognized brands, and Web3 companies in the world, including BNY Mellon, BNP Paribas, ANZ Bank, Revolut, and thousands more.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for an industry-leading, secure digital asset platform, experiencing hypergrowth valued at $8 billion? Welcome to &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fireblocks!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s The Bit About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Fireblocks is an enterprise-grade platform delivering a secure infrastructure for moving, storing, and issuing digital assets &amp;amp; cryptocurrencies. At Fireblocks, we enable businesses to securely build, run and scale digital asset operations through the Fireblocks Network and MPC-based Wallet Infrastructure. Our next-generation multi-layer technology protects Digital assets from cyber-attacks, internal collusion, and human error. Fireblocks is the only platform that provides insurance for digital assets in storage, transfer, and E&amp;amp;O.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;As of August 2025, we serve over 2000 institutional customers, have secured the transfer of over $10 trillion in digital assets, and are the world''s highest-valued digital asset infrastructure company, with over $1 billion raised.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;Our mission is simple: Enable every business to easily and securely support digital assets &amp;amp; cryptocurrencies. Come join us as we &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Secure. Simplify. Scale&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s The Bit About The Opportunity&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As part of the APAC Fireblocks sales team, you will play a meaningful role in scaling one of the fastest-growing companies in the Blockchain and Cybersecurity field. You’ll be targeting a mixture of Financial Institutions, licensed market participants in VA and technology partners across Australia, working closely with Sales Engineers and the Business Development team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Be&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieving monthly and quarterly revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working closely with Fireblocks BDRs and GTM Team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining relationships with prospects and customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigating complex enterprise accounts and coordinate across key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospecting, territory, and account planning&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Updating and maintaining the Fireblocks CRM&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enterprise sales experience in software or institutional sales, selling into a relevant space such as financial services, blockchain, fintech- a must&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience within financial services, cybersecurity, or cryptocurrency is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience formalizing and supporting co-sell motion in working with technology partners is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An understanding of blockchain technology and cryptocurrency &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of over achievement in an enterprise sales position&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial and relentless hunting attitude&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A willingness to prospect and qualify new opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Thrives in a team selling environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in MEDDIC is preferred&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We have a comprehensive onboarding and training program for all new employees. We are looking for A players who want to work with the best. Track record of success and closing complex deals within the financial services or fintech sectors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fireblocks'' mission is to enable every business to easily and securely access digital assets and cryptocurrencies. In order to do that, we strongly believe our workforce should be as diverse as our clients, and this is why we embrace diversity and inclusion in all its forms. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please see our candidate privacy policy here.&lt;/em&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQEyT6gpuwTpPg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630561416766/fireblocks_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=GHVePuE-cbss4brTNs3va07VXy1L1v7ANk27RmaOiPE', '2025-09-21T14:08:37.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recddkkACophlPwwU', 'FICO', 'http://www.fico.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fico', 'Bozeman, Montana, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '54', 'FICO is a growth-stage computer software company (3,815 employees) in the core B2B tech space, but there is no evidence of current active sales role hiring. The company has Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers in APAC (Senior Director, Director of Partner Management), but recent signals show no sales team expansion or hiring surge. While industry fit and company size are strong, lack of sales hiring activity and minimal growth signals limit immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nFICO announced a new $1 billion stock repurchase program on June 19, 2025, following the completion of its previous buyback program that was active from July 2024 to June 2025[1]. The company also unveiled the FICO Marketplace in 2024, expanding its enterprise intelligence ecosystem[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent public indicators of large-scale hiring or team expansion, particularly in sales or GTM roles. No significant headcount growth announcements identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or external investment announcements have been reported in the last 12 months. No financial milestones related to fundraising identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nFICO Platform won the 2025 Data Breakthrough âBusiness Intelligence Platform of the Yearâ award, with announcements in early 2025[3]. The FICO Decision Awards 2025 recognized several clients for outstanding results using FICO technology in areas such as AI, cloud deployment, and fraud management[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo significant executive changes, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles reported in the last 12 months. No recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"FICO (NYSE: FICO) powers decisions that help people and businesses around the world prosper. Founded in 1956, the company is a pioneer in the use of predictive analytics and data science to improve operational decisions. FICO holds more than 200 US and foreign patents on technologies that increase profitability, customer satisfaction and growth for businesses in financial services, insurance, telecommunications, health care, retail and many other industries. Using FICO solutions, businesses in more than 100 countries do everything from protecting 4 billion payment cards from fraud, to improving financial inclusion, to increasing supply chain resiliency. The FICOÂ® Score, used by 90% of top US lenders, is the standard measure of consumer credit risk in the US and has been made available in over 40 other countries, improving risk management, credit access and transparency. Learn more at www.fico.com."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recdkind9QBfD7IOD', 'Confluent', 'http://confluent.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/confluent', 'Mountain View, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '77', 'Confluent is a growth-stage computer software company (3,652 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively hiring for core sales roles such as Account Executive and Sales Director in Australia and Singapore. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including Sales Director, Regional Sales Director, and Strategic Account Executives, providing direct access to hiring authorities. Recent growth signals include major product launches, a significant acquisition, and ongoing market expansion in ANZ, though no recent funding or sales leadership changes are noted. The combination of core role hiring, strong industry fit, and quality decision makers makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn September 2024, Confluent launched an OEM channel program to attract managed service providers, cloud service providers, and independent software vendors, coinciding with a $200 million investment to spur partner integrations and development[1]. The company also announced the acquisition of WarpStream in September 2024 to expand its data streaming offerings and enable bring-your-own-cloud (BYOC) capabilities[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nConfluent continues to expand in the Australia and New Zealand (ANZ) region, evidenced by strategic customer transformations at Kmart and Insurance Australia Group using Confluent’s platform, and ongoing investments in data streaming highlighted in its 2025 Data Streaming Report, including Australia as a key market[2][4]. No specific recent sales or GTM headcount figures for Australia identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements in the last 6-12 months identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAt Current 2024 (held October 2024), Confluent announced new features including client-side field-level encryption, Table API, flexible schema management, and AI model inference capabilities, as well as the acquisition of WarpStream to broaden deployment options[3]. Confluent''s platform has enabled major enterprises such as Kmart and IAG in Australia to achieve significant digital transformation and operational scalability within the past year[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people leadership roles identified for the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Confluent is pioneering a fundamentally new category of data infrastructure focused on data in motion.  Our cloud-native offering is the foundational platform for data in motion --- designed to be the intelligent connective tissue enabling real-time data, from multiple sources, to constantly stream across the organization.  With Confluent, our customers can meet the new business imperative of delivering rich, digital customer experiences and real-time business operations.  Our mission is to help every organization harness data in motion so they can compete and thrive in the modern world.\n\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQH5-OYbTze-EA/company-logo_200_200/B4EZbt9pRdHkAM-/0/1747749082914/confluent_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=evqOTe_BbZvVLzej0B5Wd15zciGMH0l_5JDPeaJVpww', '2025-09-18T20:58:04.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recdsYhijn1iz7uwd', 'Vanta', 'https://vanta.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/vanta-security', 'San Francisco, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '97', 'Vanta is a growth-stage computer software (core B2B SaaS) company with 1,363 employees and a strong presence in Australia, actively hiring for an Enterprise Business Development Representative (BDR/SDR) role. The company recently closed a $150M Series D, expanded its product suite, and increased headcount, all indicating robust growth. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including a General Manager APAC, Head of Sales ANZ, and APJ Manager Sales Development, providing direct access for recruitment. The combination of a primary target sales role, ideal industry fit, strong growth signals, and high-quality decision makers makes this a very high priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nVanta announced the acquisition of Riskey for real-time risk monitoring and debuted the Vanta AI Agent in June 2025 to advance governance, risk, and compliance automation. In August 2025, Vanta partnered with XBOW to introduce autonomous AI-powered penetration testing through its platform.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nVanta has expanded its product offerings and market presence over the past year, serving over 12,000 customers including global enterprises and scaling its employee base to more than 500, with a presence across North America, the UK, Germany, and Australia. The company launched 350 new features in the past year, signaling significant technical and market investment.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nVanta closed a $150 million Series D funding round in July 2025 at a $4.15 billion valuation, led by Wellington Management and with participation from Goldman Sachs, Sequoia, Atlassian Ventures, and others.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nVanta was named to the Forbes 2025 Cloud 100 list for the third consecutive year and won several G2 category leadership awards in 2025. The company reached over 12,000 global customers and launched the Vanta 25 to Trust awards program.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Vanta is the leading AI trust management platform that helps businesses earn and prove trust. \n\nFrom startup to enterprise, Vanta is trusted by 12,000+ customers, including Atlassian, Duolingo, Icelandair, Ramp and Synthesia, to automate compliance, manage risk, and prove trust continuouslyâall from a single, AI-powered platform. \n\n- Automated Compliance: Automate evidence gathering with continuous monitoring to get you compliant and keep you secure.\n\n- Streamlined Audits: Collaborate seamlessly with auditors to help get you audit-ready,  fast and hassle-free.\n\n- Risk Management: Centralize your IT risk to make informed decisions, whether youâre bringing your own program or building one from scratch.\n\n- Vendor Risk Management: Streamline vendor security reviews with AI-powered analysis and continuous monitoring of vendor attack surfaces.\n\n- Trust Center: Share your security and compliance posture with buyers with a public-facing Trust Center, and tie your security program to revenue. \n\n- Questionnaire Automation: Streamline security questionnaires by having Vanta AI take the first pass for youâso all you need to do is review, approve, and submit.\n\n- 375+ integrations: A market-leading ecosystem of over 375 integrations that powers 1,200+ automated, hourly tests, giving you continuous visibility into your compliance posture.\n\n- Vanta AI: Supercharge your team with AI-powered control mapping, evidence checks, questionnaire automation, and custom code snippets to remediate failing tests. \n\nFounded in 2018, Vanta has customers in 58 countries with offices in Dublin, London, New York, San Francisco and Sydney. Investors include Sequoia, Wellington, Craft Ventures, Y Combinator, Growth Equity at Goldman Sachs Alternatives, J.P. Morgan, Atlassian Ventures and CrowdStrike Ventures.\n\nVanta has been named to the Forbes Cloud 100, CNBC Disruptor 50, Fast Companyâs Most Innovative Companies, Inc.âs Best Workplaces, and Forbesâ Best Startup Employer lists. "}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recdxlHRZCNWwCQZU', 'AvePoint', 'https://www.avepoint.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/avepoint', 'Jersey City, New Jersey', 'Data Security Software Products', '1,001-5,000 employees', '82', 'AvePoint is a growth-stage data security software company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively expanding its sales and support operations in Australia, with a new Sydney office and a strong ANZ go-to-market push. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Directors, Sales Managers, VP/MD ANZ) provides direct access for recruitment opportunities. The company is hiring for core sales roles such as Enterprise Account Executive and Account Executive, which are high-priority for 4Twenty. Multiple strong growth signals—including regional expansion, new office launch, and a visible sales leadership team—underscore immediate recruitment potential, though the absence of recent local funding slightly moderates the score.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] AvePoint opened a new operational office in Sydney at Australia Square Plaza in early 2025 to strengthen support for enterprise collaboration and respond to expanding market demand in Australia[1]. This marks its second office in the country (the first is in Melbourne), reflecting a targeted expansion strategy in the region[1]. AvePoint cited its partnership with Microsoft as a crucial factor fostering its Sydney expansion[1].\n\n[REGIONAL] AvePoint is hosting the ANZ OnPoint MSP Roadshow 2025 from February 13th to March 26th, with events in Sydney, Melbourne, Perth, Brisbane, and Auckland[2]. The roadshow focuses on empowering managed service providers across Australia and New Zealand to leverage AvePoint’s security solutions and data management platforms within the context of AI-driven modernization[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The new Sydney office opening is accompanied by expansion of local sales and support capacity for Australian enterprise clients[1]. This move is intended to accelerate service delivery and facilitate direct engagement with large organizations in Sydney and NSW[1].\n\n[REGIONAL] Recent activities, such as the ANZ OnPoint Roadshow, highlight AvePoint''s investment in regional partnerships and its drive to enable MSPs as data security experts[2]. Named key regional sales and engineering contacts include Oliver Gohl (Sales Director), Andrew Browne (Sales Manager), and Michael Miziarski (Solutions Engineering), underscoring a visible local and regional go-to-market team focus[2].\n\n[GLOBAL] AvePoint’s global ARR reached $327M for 2024, with a 25% growth rate supported by regional market expansion, including APAC, and significant investments in customer success and direct sales force[4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent funding rounds or investment events specific to Australia or APAC found in the last 6-12 months. The most recent available data references year-end global financial results for 2024, scheduled for release on February 27, 2025[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] AvePoint’s MSP-focused strategies and product investments for the ANZ market were spotlighted during the current OnPoint Roadshow[2]. The event agenda emphasizes the company''s advanced product roadmap for 2025 and its evolving partnership with Microsoft tailored for APAC MSPs and enterprises[2].\n\n[LOCAL] The launch of the Sydney office is positioned as an achievement, enhancing AvePoint''s Australian footprint and service capabilities for the data security and compliance market[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Garth Luke is identified as CEO, AvePoint ANZ, and cited as instrumental in driving the Sydney office launch and regional expansion[1]. No additional recent executive appointments or departures specific to Sydney found within the last 6-12 months.\n\n[REGIONAL] Key leadership presence at regional events includes Sales Director Oliver Gohl and Sales Manager Andrew Browne, who represent sales leadership for AvePoint’s ANZ operations[2].\n\n[GLOBAL] No major global executive changes with direct APAC or ANZ impact identified within the last 6-12 months.\n\nINDUSTRY Fallback:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian market for data security software is experiencing increased demand due to elevated regulatory requirements and a growing enterprise emphasis on cloud governance and AI readiness. AvePoint leverages this climate with deep Microsoft integration and value proposition focused on compliance and resilience for organizations shifting toward hybrid and cloud-first collaboration[1][2][4].\n\n**Scope clarifications:**\n- [LOCAL] denotes AvePoint’s Sydney office launch and named Australian leadership, sales, and roadshow activity relevant to NSW customers.\n- [REGIONAL] references ANZ/APAC-wide programs such as roadshows, MSP enablement, and regional sales activities.\n- [GLOBAL] covers company-wide financial signals, global ARR, and strategic direction impacting local and regional growth.\n- [INDUSTRY] provides context for sector trends relevant to AvePoint’s data security product positioning in Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Sydney, Australia&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About AvePoint&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Beyond Secure. AvePoint is the global leader in data security, governance, and resilience, going beyond traditional solutions to ensure a robust data foundation and enable organizations everywhere to collaborate with confidence. Over 25,000 customers worldwide rely on the AvePoint Confidence Platform to prepare, secure, and optimize their critical data across Microsoft, Google, Salesforce, and other collaboration environments. AvePoint’s global channel partner program includes approximately 5,000 managed service providers, value-added resellers, and systems integrators, with our solutions available in more than 100 cloud marketplaces. To learn more, visit &lt;strong&gt;www.avepoint.com&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At AvePoint, we are committed to investing in our people. Agility, passion and teamwork set us up to do our best work and foster a culture where you are empowered to craft your career, make an impact, and own (y)our future. Unleash the power of you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Position&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Are you ready to progress your sales career in the fast-growing SaaS industry where you work with our existing customers to help them get the most out of their Microsoft Cloud investment? Passionate about technology, people and sales? Utilise your skills and passions at the number one cloud data governance ISV in the world.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Your job is to work with a dedicated patch of our existing customers as an Account Manager to be their key point of contact. Your role is to establish a trusted advisor relationship to achieve and expand customer goals resulting in account renewal, upsell and cross-sell.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You’ll be responsible for the AvePoint vison and strategy for these customers. In this role, you are tasked with renewing and expanding our footprint within your territory of existing customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will help your customers with any questions or issues they may have (with the support of our team), as well as build your relationships within the customer to identify new customer pain and business challenges. You will work with our team to successfully close new deals by listening to your customers, understanding their problems and positioning innovative solutions using AvePoint products.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Responsibilities Will Include&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Owning a book of business with assigned customers that you are responsible for selling, supporting, educating, and growing through regular, systematic touchpoints. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acting as the single point of contact for existing AvePoint customers in your account patch&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and building relationships with existing key contacts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Establishing relationships with key customer business and technical advocates that have the power to drive long-term AvePoint solution adoption within their company &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ownership of the commercial sale&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Managing complex sales cycles with a consultative sales approach &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Securing the renewals of customer accounts at or above the projected renewal amount&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Increasing sales by driving product adoption, managing escalations and thereby ensuring retention and long-term satisfaction. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding the customer’s business, their challenges, pains, and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Presenting AvePoint solutions relevant to customer objectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working with dedicated pre-sales engineers and other cross-functional team members to help close business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Successfully facilitating solution discovery, solution overview, and technical deep dive sessions with customers (with support as required). &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Answering questions and helping to resolve issues in a timely manner, including communicating new product developments to existing customers &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communicating with prospective customers, assist and guide them through their evaluation and selection process &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintaining an accurate and current pipeline of opportunities within the CRM system &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for hitting or exceeding quarterly renewal and new business targets &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Bring To Our Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We look for people who value agility, passion and teamwork; those who can bring fresh ideas to the table and want the opportunity to learn, grow, and expand their careers. Bring your aptitude and build upon what you do best for our customers, partners, team, and you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You’ll need to be passionate about people, technology savvy and carry a desire to learn and grow in a fast-paced, every-change global SaaS business. You’ll be confident and self-motivated with an entrepreneurial mindset. You take pride in seeing your hard work pay off when you see the final results.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Other qualities you’ll need to be a fit for this role include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A few years of technology account management experience and skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prior experience selling in the Microsoft 365 ecosystem preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with executive selling, both business and technical &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;General familiarity with selling methodologies and processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Business Development experience preferable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accountability and a sense of urgency&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and listening skills &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn and grow&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits we offer:  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Competitive market-based compensation &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Career progression and internal mobility opportunities across our global footprint in North America, EMEA, and APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Work life balance through hybrid working model of 3 days a week in office&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Generous PTO allowance incl. specific AvePoint Holidays (Birthday Day, Family Day, Holiday Half Day, Community Outreach Half Day!)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Private Health Insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Mobile Phone Plan Reimbursement &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Tuition Reimbursement &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Dedication Awards&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Employee Referral Program &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; ...and much more! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;AvePoint is proud to employ talent from many different backgrounds, experiences, and identities. We believe that diversity and inclusion drives our success and is at the core of how we hire, communicate, and collaborate to deliver value and excellence. We are committed to fostering an environment where people can bring their whole selves to work and feel a sense of belonging, and we continue to work toward creating a workforce that represents the diversity of our customers and communities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Any personal data you share with us during the application process will be processed strictly in compliance with applicable data protection laws and our Privacy Notice.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQFb4VxM4FZCcg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1631309507529?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=eIU5ktIfT05N_Z_CIJArX9T378aaYnR8v76RY2BBqNQ', '2025-09-23T14:20:50.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('rece99PdQ2nHPqkrJ', 'Sitecore', 'https://www.sitecore.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sitecore', 'San Francisco, California', 'Software Development,Technology, Information and Internet', '1,001-5,000 employees', '79', 'Sitecore is a growth-stage commercial B2B software company (1,001-5,000 employees) in the core SaaS/digital experience sector, actively hiring for Senior Account Executive and Account Executive roles in Australia and Singapore. These are high-priority sales positions with strong alignment to 4Twenty''s focus. The presence of Tier 1 (Regional VP Sales, President APJ) and Tier 2 (Sales Manager, Account Director) decision makers provides direct access to key hiring authorities. While there are no recent local hiring surges or funding rounds, ongoing product innovation, regional events, and a robust ANZ customer base indicate steady commercial activity and moderate growth signals. This represents a strong, high-priority recruitment opportunity for sales talent, though not at the ''very high'' level due to absence of explicit local expansion or recent funding.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sitecore will feature prominently at SUGCON ANZ 2025, the Sitecore User Group Conference held in Sydney on 14–15 August 2025, at Fortress Sydney, designed to bring together developers, marketers, customers, and partners across Australia and New Zealand for knowledge exchange and networking[1].  \n[REGIONAL] No specific new strategic changes or market events for Sitecore Australia in the past 6–12 months are documented in public sources as of October 2025.  \n[GLOBAL] Sitecore is preparing to unveil major platform upgrades centering on AI-powered content creation and dynamic personalized experiences at Sitecore Symposium 2025 (Orlando, November 2025), which is expected to influence product offerings and marketing strategies globally, including ANZ[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There are no explicit recent reports of hiring surges or new office openings by Sitecore in Sydney, NSW, or broader Australia between October 2024 and October 2025 in public news.  \n[REGIONAL] Sitecore maintains a notable partner and customer base in Australia, supported by active participation in regional industry events and a network of certified implementation partners[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Sitecore maintains a global headcount of over 2,200 employees, with active expansion across its digital experience, content management, and personalization technology divisions[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent publicly reported funding rounds, major investments, or financial milestones were identified for Sitecore in the past 12 months. The company completed a $1.2 billion funding round in 2021, which has underpinned major product investments since then (contextual, outside the 12-month window)[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Hosting SUGCON ANZ 2025 in Sydney showcases Sitecore’s ongoing community commitment and thought leadership in the ANZ region, providing a local platform for sharing best practices and innovative use cases[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Multiple Sitecore partners in Australia have received recognition for successful digital transformation projects with enterprise customers, though no specific regional achievement awards for Sitecore itself were noted for 2025[3].  \n[GLOBAL] At Sitecore Symposium 2025, Sitecore will announce significant AI-driven platform enhancements and present Digital Experience Awards celebrating customer and partner success, with some ANZ case studies typically included in global programming[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No public announcements regarding new executive appointments, departures, or leadership changes for Sitecore’s Sydney or Australia operations in the last 12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] The most recent notable leadership update is around global product and marketing, with Michelle Boockoff-Bajdek as Chief Marketing Officer and Roger Connolly as Chief Product Officer set to unveil new strategic directions at Sitecore Symposium 2025[2]. No changes specific to the ANZ region are disclosed.\n\nIndustry context provided due to limited local and regional specifics:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian software development and digital experience market in 2025 is highly competitive, with significant enterprise investment in cloud-based content management, AI-powered personalization, and omnichannel marketing platforms. Demand for specialized skills and vendor-certified talent remains strong, with local and multinational vendors (including Sitecore and key partners) positioning for digital transformation initiatives within Australian enterprises[3].\n\n**Scoping note:** Direct news about Sydney/AU Sitecore operations is limited; most recent, specific activity is the SUGCON ANZ 2025 Sydney event, with broader ANZ developments inferred from regional agency and partner activity. Global product innovation and upcoming symposium announcements are likely to influence local commercial priorities through 2025."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Sitecore, our mission is to simplify how brands reach, engage, and serve people by delivering intelligent, personalised digital experiences that connect the world. We empower the world’s most iconic brands to build lifelong relationships with their customers—seamlessly, smartly, and at scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As the leading provider of agentic digital experience software, Sitecore brings together content, commerce, and data into one composable platform that enables brands to deliver millions of meaningful, adaptive experiences every day. Trusted by global leaders such as American Express, Porsche, Starbucks, and L’Oréal, Sitecore helps brands transform engagement through experiences that are not only personalised but predictive and dynamic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our foundation is our people—a diverse, passionate, and collaborative global team spanning over 25 countries. We believe that every experience matters, and that belief starts with how we work together. Our values—empathy, accountability, clarity, and growth—guide how we lead, innovate, and connect. They are the behaviors that bring our mission and vision to life, every day, in every interaction.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As we continue to evolve, we are actively cultivating AI skills across our teams to unlock new levels of creativity, efficiency, and insight. From engineering to customer experience, AI capabilities are becoming integral to how we design, build, and deliver the next generation of digital experiences. Learn more at Sitecore.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Sales Development Representative (SDR), it is your key responsibility to identify, research and mature potential sales engagements in the ANZ market, whilst also working with the greater Asia Pacific SDR Team on training, development, and process improvement. Success in this role involves connecting with the correct stakeholders within a business and qualifying that there is genuine opportunity for the Sales Team to mature this discussion and win new business for Sitecore.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively build pipeline through targeted outbound prospecting, including researching accounts, identifying decision-makers, and crafting personalized outreach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet and exceed pipeline generation quotas to support regional sales goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a consistent daily outbound call volume of 50–70 calls.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial discovery calls to understand prospect challenges and qualify leads based on fit.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a strong understanding of our solutions and competitive landscape to effectively position value to prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales and Marketing teams to align strategies, share insights, and refine messaging.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback on lead quality and campaign performance to continuously improve outreach efforts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Qualifications: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience as an SDR, preferably in a SaaS sales environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A skilled and fearless approach to outbound prospecting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Goal oriented, with a strong emphasis on achieving and surpassing targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Innovative and naturally curious, you enjoy creating new methods and investigating research&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consistently over-achieved quota in past positions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A “hunter” mentality with tenacity and enthusiasm for inbound and outbound prospecting&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Sitecore is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity without unlawful regard to race, colour, ancestry, religion, gender, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, veteran status or any other local legally protected characteristic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Carmen Cheong"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQF2yusLLpe9Lw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1701352886587/sitecore_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=LvpCNLUBK6d8B0Wtk8b3GU8mtUjA3Dutd5t29Yo8AW4', '2025-10-01T14:14:08.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recebEC16L6cQ6YNG', 'GBG Plc', 'www.gbg.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/gb-group', 'Chester', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '1,001-5,000 employees', '68', 'GBG Plc is a growth-stage IT Services and Consulting company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit and a significant APAC presence, including Australia. The inclusion is triggered by active Business Development Manager roles, a medium-priority sales position. Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Head of Sales ANZ, Sales Director, Head of Enterprise Sales) are present, providing strong access for recruitment. Recent global growth signals—major platform launch, strategic rebrand, and robust financials—support ongoing expansion, though no direct local AU hiring was identified in the last 6-12 months. This is a high-priority opportunity due to role type, industry fit, company size, and decision maker access, but lacks the highest urgency due to absence of direct local hiring signals.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[GLOBAL] On 1 April 2025, GBG unified its operations under a single global brand and launched its new identity platform, **GBG Go**, to drive strategic alignment and operational simplification[1][4]. The company reported a major leap in business integration and operational efficiency, aiming for sustainable, profitable growth. [GLOBAL] FY25 trading (April 2024 – March 2025) was characterized by strong profitability, with adjusted operating profit up 10% to £67 million, reflecting successful business simplification and regional coordination[1]. [GLOBAL] The company''s CEO, Dev Dhiman, announced that further strategic initiatives impacting market leadership and growth—potentially with regional implications—will be revealed in June 2025[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[GLOBAL] GBG’s headcount and alignment suggest a unified global team as of April 2025, with streamlined operations to better serve all regions, including Australia and APAC[1]. [GLOBAL] Cost control and simplification initiatives incurred £4.5 million in exceptional costs in FY25 but are expected to drive more focused expansion[1]. [GLOBAL] GBG services **20,000 customers in over 90 countries**, indicating substantial regional presence and activity across APAC[3]. [REGIONAL] While no specific Australia/Melbourne roles were identified in public results, APAC remains a key growth market, with the company well-diversified by end market and geography[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] As of 31 March 2025, net debt was reduced to £48.5 million (from £80.9 million the prior year), and GBG maintains undrawn facilities of £100 million, underlining a robust financial position to support further growth, including potential APAC expansion[1]. No recent equity funding rounds or direct Australia-targeted investments have been publicly reported in the last 6-12 months[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] Launch of the cloud-based identity platform **GBG Go** in Q2 2025 as a major innovation, targeted at enhancing global and regional customer onboarding, fraud prevention, and identity verification solutions[1][4]. [GLOBAL] Operational streamlining and a global rebrand were completed, delivering cost efficiencies and improved alignment for all markets[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] No Australia-specific or APAC leadership changes are reported in the last 12 months. [GLOBAL] CEO Dev Dhiman continues to lead global operations with a strengthened leadership focus on unified global go-to-market and regional integration (as of April 2025)[1]. No Melbourne-based appointments, promotions, or departures are referenced in recent disclosures.\n\n[INDUSTRY] The IT Services and Consulting sector in Australia remains highly competitive, with demand for digital onboarding, fraud prevention, and identity verification solutions driven by regulatory changes and ongoing digital transformation across financial services, e-commerce, and logistics sectors. Vendors offering unified, cloud-based platforms (such as GBG Go) are well-placed to capitalize on these opportunities.\n\n**Scope Key:** No [LOCAL] Melbourne/AU direct office or hiring news was found for the last 6–12 months; recent changes and signals are [GLOBAL] or [REGIONAL], with global strategy and technology rollouts expected to impact APAC and Australia."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Enabling safe and rewarding digital lives for genuine people, everywhere&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We make it our mission to ensure more genuine people have digital access to opportunities, and businesses have access to more genuine people. Our technology draws on diverse and reliable data to create a single point of truth for identity and address verification.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With over 30 years of experience behind us our team and technology are focused on enabling safe and rewarding digital lives for everyone. Regardless of age, location or background, genuine people everywhere should be able to digitally prove who they are and where they live.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Team And Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Fraud Solutions Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Join a high-performing, globally distributed team focused on helping financial institutions combat fraud through cutting-edge solutions and strategic sales execution. Our team is driving growth across ANZ, ASEAN, MEA, and Europe, with a strong focus on innovation, collaboration, and commercial impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Account Manager - ANZ&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We''re looking for a seasoned sales professional with 10+ years of experience in enterprise account management and new business development to join our Global Fraud Solutions team. This role will be pivotal in managing significant existing accounts across Australia while driving strategic growth across the broader ANZ region. You''ll work closely with cross-functional teams to deliver value to clients, accelerate pipeline conversion, and expand our footprint in the region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow relationships with major Australian clients, ensuring retention and expansion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead QBRs, renewal cycles, and upsell motions with a consultative approach&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and pursue high-potential new business opportunities across ANZ&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with marketing and BD teams to execute targeted outreach and ABM campaigns&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribute to regional go-to-market strategy and ICP refinement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive pipeline velocity and conversion through structured deal reviews and solution-led pitching&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Delivery, and Customer Success to ensure seamless client experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Share market insights and competitive intelligence to inform roadmap and positioning&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills We''re Looking For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in managing complex enterprise accounts and closing high-value deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of the ANZ financial services and fintech landscape&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen and ability to navigate multi-stakeholder environments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in fraud, risk, or compliance solutions is a strong advantage&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, negotiation, and relationship-building skills &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To find out more&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an equal opportunity employer, we are dedicated to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and empowered. Please inform your GBG Talent Attraction Partner if you require any reasonable adjustments to the interview process.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To chat to the Talent Attraction team and find out more about our benefits and why we''re a great place to work, drop an email to behired@gbgplc.com and we''ll be in touch. You can also find out more about careers at GBG and check out our current opportunities at gbgplc.com/careers."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGnfb4b1OFH5Q/company-logo_200_200/B4EZXwb9lXHcAM-/0/1743495617340/gb_group_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=e0BAI7H16rLhueRl-V6XOIBMsOKZNLN4LPjSrxk8Qso', '2025-09-29T14:16:11.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recegu27KLa0uYGC4', 'Entrust', 'https://www.entrust.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/entrust', 'Minneapolis, MN', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '77', 'Entrust is a growth-stage software company (1,001-5,000 employees) in commercial B2B tech, actively expanding in Australia/Singapore with a strong APAC presence. The presence of Tier 1 (Regional Sales Director) and Tier 2 (Sales Manager, VP Sales) decision makers provides direct access for recruitment. Recent acquisition of Onfido, regional hiring, and ongoing R&D signal robust growth, though no new venture funding is noted. The most relevant roles are Regional Sales Director and Key Account & Sales Manager, both high-priority core sales roles. This combination makes Entrust a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Entrust completed the acquisition of **Onfido**, an AI-powered identity verification (IDV) technology company, in early 2024. This move strengthens Entrust’s digital security offerings in APAC, including Australia, with advanced machine learning and biometric/document verification capabilities directly relevant for combating digital fraud such as deepfake attacks[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Entrust’s APAC team, including Australia, has been actively discussing and implementing strategies against the rapid rise of AI-driven security threats. The regional focus has included support to Australian enterprises and government in digital identity protection, especially in response to increased digital transactions and privacy risks post-COVID-19[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] Entrust has dedicated **hundreds of employees** across APAC to meet regional demand, specifically mentioning support for large Australian banks, governments, and enterprise sectors[1].  \n[LOCAL] Entrust operates an Australian support line (+61 8 9126 9070) and provides local after-hours and holiday support, indicating an established, regionally staffed presence supporting NSW and broader AU customer needs[3].  \n[REGIONAL] **Ongoing R&D investments** and the integration of Onfido’s technology imply continued regional expansion through partner and customer growth, especially as Entrust positions itself for future trends like post-quantum cryptography[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No evidence of a new funding round in the last 12 months. Entrust''s growth and regional expansion activities are mostly supported by **strategic acquisitions and strong global revenues** rather than venture funding[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Entrust integrated Onfido’s IDV capabilities, enhancing digital onboarding, biometric security, and fraud detection across APAC, including Australia. This is a strategic differentiator for the local market, especially given heightened regulatory scrutiny and the surge in identity theft[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Entrust is recognized for **pioneering work in post-quantum cryptography**, a field that is receiving early interest from security-conscious Australian enterprise and government customers[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL/GLOBAL] In 2024, Lawrence Tan was identified as **Head of Technical Sales Consulting - Digital Security, APJ** at Entrust, responsible for regional innovation and go-to-market strategies[1]. No specific new appointments for ANZ country leadership or local executive changes in the past six months were found in current sources.\n\nIf you need deeper industry context or want more on local competitors and market trends, let me know."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Join us at Entrust &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Entrust, we’re shaping the future of identity centric security solutions. From our comprehensive portfolio of solutions to our flexible, global workplace, we empower careers, foster collaboration, and build solutions that help keep the world moving safely. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get to Know Us &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Headquartered in Minnesota, Entrust is an industry leader in identity-centric security solutions, serving over 150 countries with cutting-edge, scalable technologies. But our secret weapon? Our people. It’s the curiosity, dedication, and innovation that drive our success and help us anticipate the future. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Senior Sales Executive – Government and Identity Solutions&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Location: Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Are you an experienced and results-driven sales professional with a passion for innovation? Do you excel at navigating the complexities of public procurement and closing high-value deals in the government sector? We are seeking a highly motivated Senior Sales Executive to join our dynamic team, specializing in selling cutting-edge identification solutions to government agencies across Australia, New Zealand, and the Pacific region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Senior Sales Executive, you will be instrumental in driving new business opportunities by leveraging your existing network and forging new connections within government agencies, prime contractors, and integrators. You will lead the entire sales cycle, from pre-procurement engagement to post-procurement coordination, collaborating closely with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless delivery and unparalleled customer satisfaction.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Business Development: Proactively identify, develop, and manage new business opportunities within government agencies through established and new contacts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Strategy: Develop and implement effective sales strategies to target public sector organizations for complex identification solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pre-Procurement Engagement: Work closely with internal teams (marketing, product development, legal) to influence procurement requirements and position our solutions effectively ahead of public tenders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Procurement Management: Lead the preparation and submission of compliant, compelling proposals in response to public procurement opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Post-Procurement Coordination: Collaborate with project delivery, customer success, and technical teams to ensure smooth implementation and ongoing customer satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationship Building: Cultivate strong relationships with key government decision-makers, influencers, and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Market Intelligence: Monitor public sector trends, procurement cycles, and competitor activities to stay informed and maintain a competitive edge.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Extensive Experience: Minimum of 10 years of experience selling identification solutions or similar software solutions to government clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Public Procurement Expertise: Proven experience navigating public procurement processes, including RFPs, tenders, and contract negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Industry Knowledge: Deep understanding of identification systems, biometric technologies, or related solutions, including ID issuance, is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Skills: Strong consultative selling skills with a proven track record of closing high-value deals in complex sales environments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationship Management: Established network of contacts within government agencies and prime contractors.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Team Collaboration: Ability to work effectively with multidisciplinary teams across marketing, technical, legal, and operations functions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Security Clearance: Must be willing to obtain and hold security clearance.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communication: Excellent presentation, negotiation, and interpersonal skills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel as needed to meet with clients, attend industry events, and support sales efforts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong track record in achieving sales quota.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you are a driven and experienced sales professional looking for a challenging yet rewarding opportunity to make a significant impact in the government and identity solutions sector, we encourage you to apply!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;#ENT123&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Entrust, we don’t just offer jobs – we offer career journeys. Here is what you can expect when you join our team: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career Growth: Whether you’re a budding developer or a seasoned expert, we’re invested in your professional journey. With learning-forward initiatives and exciting challenges, your growth is our priority.  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexibility: Life is all about balance. Whether you’re remote, hybrid, or on-site, we offer flexible options that fit your lifestyle.  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaboration: Here, your voice matters. Our teams thrive on sharing ideas, brainstorming solutions, and working together to build a better tomorrow.  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We believe in securing identities—but it doesn’t stop there. At Entrust, we’re passionate about valuing all identities. Our culture is built on diversity, inclusion, and respect. From unconscious bias training for our leaders to global affinity groups that connect colleagues across the globe, we’re creating a community where everyone is encouraged to be themselves. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to Make an Impact? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;If you’re excited by the prospect of innovating, growing your career, and collaborating in a dynamic environment, Entrust is the place for you. Join us in making a difference. Let’s build a more secure world—together. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply today! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;For more information, visit www.entrust.com.  Follow us on, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For US Roles, Or Where Applicable&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entrust is an EEO/AA/Disabled/Veterans Employer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Canadian Roles, Or Where Applicable&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entrust values diversity and inclusion and we are committed to building a diverse workforce with wide perspectives and innovative ideas. We welcome applications from qualified individuals of all backgrounds, and we strive to provide an accessible experience for candidates of all abilities. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you require an accommodation, contact accessibility@entrust.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruiter&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;James Beck&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;James.Beck@entrust.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFsJa-zzF7kyw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1724085708811/entrust_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=e1q42Bmz2ahCrdAgQBm22tnI0A5v-CXCGC9smW__VUk', '2025-09-20T06:40:25.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('receokWzuIHZpuRaP', 'Assignar', 'http://www.assignar.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/assignar', 'Denver, Colorado', 'Software Development', '51-200 employees', '68', 'Assignar is a growth-stage SaaS company (51-200 employees) focused on the construction sector, actively expanding its presence in Australia. The inclusion was triggered by a Senior Manager, Customer Success role—classified as a medium-priority sales role. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, with strong regional growth signals such as local customer events, case studies, and partnerships. Access to a Global Head of Sales (Tier 2) and Senior Manager, Customer Success (Tier 2) provides quality decision maker access. While no recent funding or major leadership changes were reported, robust market activity and industry alignment make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Assignar hosted an in-person customer event in Sydney within the last six months, signaling ongoing customer engagement and local support for its Australian user base[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Assignar continues to grow its footprint across Australia, with active case studies featuring NSW and national infrastructure contractors leveraging the Assignar platform to streamline compliance and field operations[1][2].  \n[INDUSTRY] Australian state and federal governments have accelerated infrastructure spending and project fast-tracking in 2024-2025, aligning with Assignar’s focus on serving the construction and civil infrastructure sectors[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Assignar routinely highlights partnerships with New South Wales-based contractors (e.g., Traffic Logistics), showcasing strong penetration within the Sydney and NSW market[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] Multiple Australian contractors—such as Workzone Traffic Control (SA), YES Group (SA), and Traffic Force (WA)—have adopted Assignar’s platform, indicating robust regional demand[1][2].  \n[INDUSTRY] The company is positioning itself to capitalize on increased digitization in Australia’s construction sector, responding to an industry shift historically characterized as one of the \"least digitised\" globally[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds specifically announced for Australia in the last 6-12 months. The most recent public information remains the June 2021 Series B funding led by Fifth Wall and others, aimed at global expansion, including continued focus on the Australian market[1][3].  \n[INDUSTRY] No Australian-specific investment or local capital injections reported in the past year.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Featured success stories highlight major NSW-based clients managing complex projects with Assignar, such as Traffic Logistics and George’s Loader Hire (rail, civil, and traffic management sectors)[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] Assignar-sponsored training sessions and compliance management best practice initiatives are now a regular offering for Australian clients, suggesting increased investment in customer enablement[1][2].  \n[INDUSTRY] Assignar and its clients have been recognized in Australian construction industry events, reinforcing credibility and presence.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No public Sydney- or Australia-specific executive appointments or departures reported in the last 12 months.  \n[GLOBAL] No major leadership transitions at the C-suite level have been announced in 2024-2025 that impact APAC/ANZ operations.\n\nIf more detail is needed on Sydney job openings, direct LinkedIn or onsite hiring data may be required. No major recent Australia-based sales/revenue leadership hires or departures are publicly reported within the last year."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Job Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Business Development Representative&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; New South Wales, Australia (Remote)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; $55,000 - $65,000&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OTE: &lt;/strong&gt;$87k-$105k (Based on potential commission earnings)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Anniversary Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generous Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee Stock Options&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Up-skill training opportunities, coaching, and training&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 1 annual get together with the whole AUS team (usually around the holidays)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2 Paid Volunteer Days/Year&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We''re a mission-led cloud-based construction tech startup. Sean McCreanor (co-founder and CEO) started Assignar in 2014 after experiencing the painful lack of offerings available to him as a contractor to run his own business operations. Cut to present and Assignar works with hundreds of customers, ranging from multinational, multi-billion-dollar companies to specialist contractors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’ve found product-market fit: Assignar is an all-in-one platform, now leading the way in digital construction operations built for contractors. We enable teams to have real-time visibility on job sites to successfully schedule the right workers to the right projects, track equipment efficiently, and make well-informed, data-driven decisions for future projects.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We have a talented and diverse global team. Assignar was born in Australia and is now headquartered in Denver, Colorado. Our team members are all over Australia, the United States, and Colombia today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission, Vision, &amp;amp; Values&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our mission is to empower the builders of the world’s infrastructure with technology and innovation that supports building stronger, safer, and more sustainably.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Vision&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our vision is to be the source of truth for construction operations data, globally.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Values&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Creating our company values was a true team effort; employees had the opportunity to vote on these and participate in a values workshop to hone in on the behaviors that align with each value. Our goal is to have these be our guiding principles and that they''ll be incorporated into our everyday lives at Assignar.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Do what’s right. Even if it’s hard or uncomfortable. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customers are our why. They’re our blueprint for success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grow with purpose. Intentionally, collectively, and for our industry. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;One team. We win as a team, learn as a team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;That’s enough about us. Let’s chat about you! To enable us on our growth trajectory, we’re searching for a Business Development Representative with a proven track record in B2B demand generation roles. This role offers someone the chance to continue their sales career and grow within an established company.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day To Day, You Will&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Source new sales opportunities through outbound efforts like cold calling, cold email, and LinkedIn engagement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify key-decision makers, generate interest within organizations through discovery calls&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand customer needs and requirements before handing opportunities to Account Executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain and expand our CRM with prospects within your assigned territory and AE&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assist with performing effective online and in-person demos to prospect when required.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend in person events, demonstrations and industry associations as requested by the company&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Ideally Bring With You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Powerful outbound sales skills, including the ability to educate prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Organizational skills and ability to set priorities each day and week to work through&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ideally, 1 year experience in a sales / demand generation role&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven high volume inside/outside sales experience (B2B)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work towards company targets and key results&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong listening and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask, prioritize and manage time effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiar with Sales tools like Salesforce, Salesloft/Outreach, Drift, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Apollo/ZoomInfo, etc. a plus&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;In the first month, you will participate in a 2 week onboarding program, which includes– becoming knowledgeable about our product, industry segments &amp;amp; customer profiles, navigating our lead generation tools, shadowing the sales teams, understanding customer profiles, and how to best overcome objections.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our BDR team plays a fundamental role in achieving our customer acquisition and revenue growth objectives. By the second month, you will be comfortable communicating to our prospects, identifying key decision-makers, generating interest, and booking demos for our Account Executive team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You’ll Work With&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Matthew Pircon/Hiring Manager (Senior Director of Revenue- USA based)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;BDR Team (located across AUS and the US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trent McCreanor (Global Head of Sales)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Account Executives (working directly with the AE assigned) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;RevOps/Marketing Team &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Have we got your interest? Our recruitment process is:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Submit your application via the Breezy link&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Phone screen with our People &amp;amp; Culture team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Interview with Matthew Pircon (Senior Director of Revenue)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Interview with Trent McCreanor (Global Head of Sales)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We value equity, inclusion, belonging, and diversity at our company. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender identity, national origin, or any other applicable legally protected characteristic. Also - if you feel like you don''t meet all the criteria above, please apply anyway! We don''t want that to get in the way of meeting you.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D0BAQEP3okDLnr5Xg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630501662129/assignar_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=cIgSX1MHdTihIhQUz8_oOFiZOSsZLnpvVl6uboAyS04', '2025-09-20T06:20:11.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recf3fNjOTKdGTRJ7', 'ada', 'https://www.ada.cx/', 'https://ca.linkedin.com/company/ada-cx', 'Toronto, Ontario, CA', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '85', 'Ada is a growth-stage computer software company with a strong commercial B2B tech focus, actively expanding in Australia and Singapore. The presence of a Managing Director, APAC & Japan, provides Tier 1 decision maker access for immediate recruitment opportunities. Recent funding, product launches, and partnership announcements signal strong growth, and the company’s ongoing innovation in AI-powered customer service further supports hiring needs. This, combined with the likely focus on core sales roles for APAC expansion, makes Ada a very high priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAda announced a partnership with Dixa in January 2024 to deliver AI-first customer service experiences and launched a series of AI management and coaching capabilities for its platform in November 2023. The company also released a trend report on AI-powered customer service in January 2024 and highlighted its use of Azure OpenAI Service in November 2024[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAda has shown consistent product development and innovation, with positive user feedback pointing to frequent feature updates and fast support response times as of October 2024. Customers report the ability to scale support operations without hiring, indicating sustained business growth in markets that include Australia[2][3][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nAda raised $130 million in its most recent funding round, with total funding reaching $190.7 million; however, the exact date of the latest round within the past 12 months is not specified in available sources[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAda powered over 4 billion automated customer interactions since launch and has automated millions of customer service operations for clients such as Meta and Verizon. The product received continued praise for rapid innovation and customer satisfaction up to October 2024[1][2][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Ada is an AI customer service company making service extraordinary for everyone. A transformation partner and platform that helps enterprise companies deliver experiences people love by accelerating a businesses’ AI maturity and improving Agent performance. Since 2016, we''ve powered 5.5 billion interactions for brands like Square, YETI, and Monday.com, saving millions of hours."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-18T20:54:55.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recfA3FIerMtT7IG9', 'Planful', 'http://www.planful.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/planful-inc', 'San Francisco, California, US', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '84', 'Planful is a growth-stage computer software (core B2B tech) company with 692 employees, actively expanding in APAC and globally, indicating strong hiring momentum. The presence of two APAC Sales Directors (Tier 2 decision makers) provides direct access to key hiring authorities for sales roles. Recent global expansions, workforce growth, new product launches, and customer acquisition are strong growth signals. While the specific sales role is not explicitly listed, the context and leadership titles suggest ongoing sales hiring, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nPlanful achieved record-breaking bookings in 2024 and completed major global expansions, including new operations in Germany and doubling its UK and Northern Europe footprint announced on February 25, 2025. The company launched significant AI-driven product innovations and opened a new R&D and Customer Service hub in Hyderabad, India[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nPlanful expanded its total workforce by 35% in 2024, with notable investment in R&D, which grew by 30%. The company added over 240 new customers and increased its global partner community by 30%, signaling rapid sales and market expansion[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nPlanful launched the Solution Hub in 2024, introduced new AI capabilities, enhanced integration with Power BI, and secured two new patents. The company also hosted Perform25, its flagship customer event, in May and June 2025[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Planful is the pioneer of financial performance management cloud software. The Planful platform, which helps businesses drive peak financial performance, is used around the globe to streamline business-wide planning, budgeting, consolidations, reporting, and analytics. Planful empowers finance, accounting, and business users to plan confidently, close faster, and report accurately. More than 1,500 customers, including Bose, Boston Red Sox, Five Guys, Grafton Plc, and Gousto, rely on Planful to accelerate cycle times, increase productivity, and improve accuracy. Planful is a private company backed by Vector Capital, a leading global private equity firm."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:23:02.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recfCrQpRpgfH2b2x', 'Rippling', 'https://www.rippling.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/rippling', 'San Francisco, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '100', 'Rippling is a leading computer software company with recent $450 million Series G funding and ongoing product launches, signaling aggressive global expansion and investment in sales and GTM teams. The presence of multiple senior sales and HR leaders in Australia, including Sales Directors and HR management, demonstrates a robust sales infrastructure and immediate access to key decision makers. These strong growth signals and high-value hiring roles indicate an exceptional opportunity for recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nRippling secured $450 million in Series G funding in May 2025, bringing its valuation to $16.8 billion; the company also initiated a $200 million employee equity buyback while announcing plans for market and product expansion. Notably, Y Combinator adopted Rippling as its HR platform of choice in early 2025.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent funding is designated for accelerating expansion into new markets, enhancing existing products, and supporting new product development. The company continues to announce new products and platform features implying ongoing investment in workforce and GTM functions, but no specific sales/expansion headcount figures were identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nCompleted a $450 million Series G funding round in May 2025, led by Elad Gil, Sands Capital, GIC, Goldman Sachs Alternatives, Baillie Gifford, and Y Combinator, with an equity buyback agreement up to $200 million. Previous Series F fundraising was $200 million in April 2024.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nLaunched several major product updates in July 2025 and throughout 2024, such as no-code app-building tools, Interview Assistant with AI summaries, enhanced scheduling and training modules, and data connectivity enhancements. Rippling also rolled out the Talent Signal AI product for employee performance in September 2024.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Rippling is a workforce management system that eliminates the friction from running a business. Today, most companies struggle with everything from routine tasks, like running payroll, to cross-functional planning, like aligning on headcount. Thatâs because all their data related to people, processes, and systems is scattered in a hundred places. \n\nRippling has every application you need to run your businessâfrom applicant tracking and payroll to IT and expensesâin one place. But unlike other systems, Rippling sits on top of a unified platform. Data flows dynamically between Ripplingâs applications, giving every team a shared source of truth, the power to automate processes, and access to the insights they need. This allows your business to execute better, faster.\n\nBased in San Francisco, CA, Rippling has raised $1.2B from the worldâs top investorsâincluding Kleiner Perkins, Founders Fund, Sequoia, Greenoaks, and Bedrock.\n\nGet help: rippling.com/contact\nLicensing details: https://app.rippling.com/licensing"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recfTDwjj5UitYKyw', 'OMRON Automation and Robotics Australia', 'http://www.omron.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/omron-electronics-australia-and-new-zealand', ' Parramatta, New South Wales, AU', 'Industrial Automation', '51 - 200', '54', 'OMRON Automation and Robotics Australia is a small growth-stage industrial automation company (73 employees) with a recent focus on innovation and sector partnerships, but no direct sales hiring or GTM expansion signals. The presence of a Key Account Manager (medium-priority sales role) and multiple Tier 2 decision makers (State Managers, Senior State Manager) and a Tier 3 HR Manager provides some recruitment access. While the company operates in a strong secondary tech vertical, the lack of direct sales hiring signals and the industrial automation focus limits immediate recruitment opportunity to a medium priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOMRON Automation and Robotics Australia opened its first Proof of Concept (PoC) Centre in Oceania at Western Sydney University’s Engineering Innovation Hub, Parramatta, in late May 2025. They also signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the Bradfield Development Authority’s Advanced Manufacturing Readiness Facility on May 28, 2025, to promote innovation, technology exchange, and sector upskilling across Western Sydney’s advanced manufacturing industry[1][2][3][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo direct recent hiring or sales/GTM expansion data identified, but the launch of the PoC Centre will support thousands of businesses and manufacturers across Australia and New Zealand, and is expected to attract up to 20,000 visitors and contribute an estimated $150 million to the local economy over five years[2][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investment announcements, or financial milestones identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOpened the state-of-the-art Proof of Concept Centre in Sydney at Western Sydney University in May 2025, designed as a collaborative innovation hub for manufacturers, students, and partners to test robotics, AI, IoT, and automation solutions, and provide workforce upskilling and joint R&D opportunities[1][2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures identified in public sources."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Industrial automation products are at the heart of our modern society. whether they monitor and control Manufacturing processes, or regulate electronic devices, improve safety systems or even just make home appliances more reliable, industrial Automation products are amongst the most widely used by industrial equipment manufacturers.Omron Industrial Automation products are designed to improve the flexibility and productivity of the manufacturing process. \r\n\r\nPLC Platforms, motion controllers, sensors, switches, relays, timers, counters, temperature controllers, level controllers and protective devices: all of these devices (and many more) are designed and built to the highest international standards to make the business of manufacturing ever faster and more efficient.\r\n\r\nSince its establishment in Australia in 1987 and New Zealand in 1991, Omron Electronics has developed a business structure that focuses on the differing needs of a diverse range of industries so that specialist support is always available.\r\n\r\nWe assist companies involved with strategic capital investment in industrial manufacturing processes, original equipment manufacturing, systems integration and panel building. We also support numerous end users who require automation improvements on both a local and national level."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:36:46.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recfjcQ7d9dz0fiXt', 'KPay Group', 'https://kpay-group.com', 'https://hk.linkedin.com/company/kpay-group', 'APAC', 'Financial Services', '501-1,000 employees', '82', 'KPay Group is a growth-stage fintech company (501-1,000 employees) actively expanding in APAC with imminent plans for Australia, aligning with strong commercial B2B tech fit. The presence of Business Development Managers and a Business Development Executive in Australia and Singapore provides Tier 2 decision maker access for sales hiring. The current focus is on Business Development roles, a medium-priority sales function, but the company''s rapid expansion, recent $55M Series A funding, and product launches signal strong hiring momentum. This represents a high-priority recruitment opportunity with strong likelihood of external sales hiring as KPay enters the Australian market.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] KPay Group announced plans for further **APAC expansion in 2025**, following recent entries into Singapore (2023) and Japan (2024). The company is actively pursuing payments licenses across Asia, with Australia flagged as a likely next market entry based on its stated focus on key regional economies[1][2].  \n[GLOBAL] In December 2024, KPay completed a $55M Series A funding round—the largest globally in the payments sector that year—with explicit intention to expand into economies such as **Indonesia, the Philippines, Malaysia, Thailand, and Australia**[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] KPay serves over **45,000 merchants** across Hong Kong, Singapore, and Japan as of December 2024, up from around 39,000 in Hong Kong and 10,000 in Singapore earlier in 2024[1][2].  \n[GLOBAL] The company’s headcount is reported at **440 employees** as of mid-2024, with significant hiring momentum linked to geographic expansion—including ANZ[3].  \n[REGIONAL] Recent product launches, including KConnect (treasury and business account platform), indicate investment in platforms that support broader merchant and SME financial operations—likely targeting ANZ as part of its next rollout wave[1][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] KPay secured **$55M Series A** in December 2024, led by Apis Growth Markets Fund III and Apis Global Growth Fund III, supporting rapid APAC expansion including into Australia and Southeast Asia[2][3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] KPay’s funding round was recognized as the largest Series A in the global payments sector for 2024, and the company has launched **KConnect**, its open banking and treasury service platform, live in HK and rolling out to new APAC markets[2][1].  \n[REGIONAL] KPay is testing open banking integrations with regional banks (e.g., DBS in Hong Kong), which may become a differentiator in AU depending on regulatory/support environment[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] Founder Richard Wong leads regional expansion and partnership strategy, with explicit focus on building out local teams in each market, including Australia[1].  \n[REGIONAL] No Sydney-specific executive appointments surfaced in the last 6-12 months, but leadership has signaled intention to establish **country manager roles** and sales teams for entry markets, AU included[1][2].\n\n[INDUSTRY]  \nFor **Financial Services in Australia**, 2024-2025 saw continued growth in merchant acquiring fintechs, open banking integrations, and SME-targeted business account platforms. The AU payments market is highly competitive, with demand for platforms offering integrated payments, real-time data, and treasury solutions—KPay’s core offering aligns directly with these trends[4]. Sales and go-to-market hiring remains strong for new entrants targeting merchant/SME segments in Sydney, especially in fintech/financial operations platforms.\n\n**Scope Used**:  \nNo direct evidence of operational launch or local hiring for Sydney, NSW as of September 2025. KPay has explicitly named **Australia** as a near-term target in public expansion plans and funding announcements, with regional headcount and merchant growth trends strongly suggesting imminent market entry. All current intelligence reflects [REGIONAL] and [GLOBAL] APAC/ANZ expansion strategy."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;Break into Tech Sales with One of APAC’s Fastest-Growing Fintechs!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Looking for a way into &lt;strong&gt;technology sales&lt;/strong&gt; but not sure where to start?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is your chance to join a &lt;strong&gt;hyper-growth fintech&lt;/strong&gt; that’s reshaping how businesses get paid.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re building a powerhouse B2B sales team and looking for &lt;strong&gt;driven, people-focused go-getters&lt;/strong&gt; to help us expand nationally. If you’ve got the &lt;strong&gt;hustle, hunger, and heart&lt;/strong&gt; to succeed, we’ll give you the &lt;strong&gt;tools, training, and mentorship&lt;/strong&gt; to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About KPay Group:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;KPay is a rapidly growing global fintech with over 60,000 merchants across Hong Kong, Singapore, and Japan. We help small and medium-sized businesses grow through smart, secure payment solutions, digital tools, and personalised support.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now expanding into Australia, we''re building a high-performing team to drive local business adoption and revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit us at: &lt;strong&gt;www.kpay-group.com&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be the face of KPay in your city — introduce our &lt;strong&gt;digital payment solutions (POS terminals)&lt;/strong&gt; to local businesses.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Get creative: connect with merchants through walk-ins, calls, referrals, and your own unique approach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learn how to understand business needs and position solutions that make a real impact.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build lasting relationships with your clients and grow your portfolio month after month.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with an ambitious, high-performing sales team — celebrate the wins together.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ideally some sales experience (door-to-door, outbound, or customer-facing).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Outgoing, confident, and love talking to people.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, competitive, and eager to grow.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilient — you bounce back stronger after rejection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Thrive in a &lt;strong&gt;fast-paced, energetic&lt;/strong&gt; environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join KPay?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uncapped Earnings&lt;/strong&gt;: Base salary + commissions. Top performers make &lt;strong&gt;$80K–$100K+ per year&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recurring Commissions&lt;/strong&gt;: Keep earning as your merchants keep using our platform.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extra Rewards&lt;/strong&gt;: Cash bonuses, referral perks, performance recognition.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifestyle Perks&lt;/strong&gt;: Birthday leave, work anniversary leave, annual leave, and more.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career Fast-Track&lt;/strong&gt;: Clear growth into senior sales, partnerships, or leadership if you deliver results.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structured Training&lt;/strong&gt;: Step-by-step guidance, mentorship, and a proven playbook to get you winning quickly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perfect For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Early-career professionals with a solid sales background (door-to-door, outbound, telesales, or face-to-face).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hospitality, or service professionals who’ve done sales and want to step into tech with higher earning potential.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ambitious salespeople who want control over their income and a clear path into leadership or senior roles.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is more than a job — it’s your launchpad into the world of fintech and technology sales.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you’re ready to learn, hustle, and win, &lt;strong&gt;apply now and let’s build something big together!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQH_Gp2U846lAQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1719258128032/kpay_merchant_service_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=T5fdEZdB9FLkiyB8NmXcI7wZ_IRHxZ5o4v-jfnA6t9M', '2025-09-28T04:12:55.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recg2BXY9IY5JbtGv', 'Dext', 'http://www.dext.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/hellodext', 'London', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '201-500 employees', '90', 'Dext is a growth-stage SaaS company (201-500 employees) with a Sydney office, actively hiring for an Account Executive role—a core, high-priority sales position. The company operates in the commercial B2B tech sector with strong APAC presence and recent major growth signals, including a global acquisition, significant product launches, and ongoing platform enhancements. Decision maker access is excellent, with both a General Manager APAC (Tier 1) and Head of Sales APAC (Tier 2) in Sydney, plus recent local and global growth indicators. These factors combine to make Dext a very high-priority recruitment opportunity for external sales hiring.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] Dext maintains a **Sydney office at Level 13, 333 George Street, Sydney, NSW 2000**, serving as a central hub for its APAC operations and supporting local accountants, bookkeepers, and SMEs with localized solutions and support[1].  \n[GLOBAL] In late 2024, Dext was **acquired by IRIS Software Group**, a major development impacting all regions and signaling a new chapter for employees and customers[2].  \n[GLOBAL] In 2024, Dext **launched an AI-powered client onboarding tool, Dext Sinc**, streamlining data collection and integration for accounting firms[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[LOCAL] Dext continues to provide **localized sales, customer support, and partner programs** from its Sydney office, with functions adapted for the Australian market[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Dext **introduced 178 new features in 2024** as part of a platform unification, focusing on automation, efficiency, and a modernized user experience[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Phase 1 of the **unified Dext platform** (combining Prepare, Precision, and Commerce) launched in 2024, indicating ongoing investment in and support for expanded product capabilities[2][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:  \n[GLOBAL] The **acquisition by IRIS Software Group** in late 2024 represents a major investment event and positions Dext for accelerated growth and expanded reach in all international markets, including APAC/Australia[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:  \n[GLOBAL] Dext''s platform received significant feature enhancements in 2024, including automation for onboarding, transaction management, and expanded integrations (e.g., Xero, QuickBooks Online)[2].  \n[GLOBAL] Dext Solo was officially recognized by HMRC as an approved software provider, reinforcing its global credibility and compliance capability[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:  \n[GLOBAL] **James Hilburn was appointed CPTO (Chief Product & Technology Officer)**, a notable leadership move likely within the last 12–18 months—no specific Australia-based executive changes are documented within the last year[1].  \n[GLOBAL] CEO Sabby Gill and CPTO Stephen Edgington remain key public-facing leaders; no direct evidence of Sydney/AU country manager changes in the past 12 months[2][3].\n\nIf you need more precisely localized data on sales hiring or Australia-specific promotions, this may require direct outreach as public reporting at the Sydney/NSW level is focused on the office’s strategic APAC role and not role-by-role updates[1].\n\n**Note:** Company actively markets itself in Australia, with more than 18 years serving local businesses and ongoing adaptation of global features for the Australian market[4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Who we are, what we do and why:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Dext is a fast-growing fintech transforming bookkeeping through AI and machine learning. Founded in London, we now operate across Europe, North America, and APAC, with a presence in six countries and over 400 employees worldwide. Our platform empowers accountants, bookkeepers, and businesses to simplify accounting processes and make smarter, more timely financial decisions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In 2024, Dext joined the IRIS Software Group, further strengthening our ability to deliver end-to-end accountancy solutions. We''ve achieved 99.5% data accuracy, saved over 35 million hours of manual data entry, and are trusted by 12,000 firms and 700,000 businesses globally. With integrations across major accounting software and over 11,500 financial sources, we''re proud to be at the forefront of innovation in the accounting space. 🌍&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We''re looking for an ambitious and results-driven &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our APAC team and help support and grow our valued partners in the Australian market. In this role, you''ll manage the full customer lifecycle (from expansion to retention), ensuring partners feel supported and receive exceptional value from their subscription.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role - what you''ll do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive portfolio growth by identifying opportunities to expand partnerships, upsell/cross-sell solutions, and maximize value for our clients. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for partner escalations and requests, minimizing churn and downsell. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and strengthen long-term partnerships, introducing new and premium products tailored to client needs. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify opportunities to increase portfolio value, improve conversions, reduce churn, and enhance the partner experience. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use our passive account management (PAM) tools and your market awareness to prospect and forecast selling opportunities. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across teams to ensure a seamless buying and deployment process, and create a positive customer journey that mitigates contraction or cancellation. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you - what we are looking for:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven Account Manager experience in B2B SaaS and confident in consultative sales, with the ability to challenge the status quo while maintaining empathy. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skilled at managing diverse portfolios and tailoring your approach to each client''s priorities. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong active listening and relationship-building skills, building trust with decision-makers and stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable presenting to groups, with solid public speaking skills and the ability to engage audiences with clarity and impact. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication, business acumen, and ability to manage priorities effectively. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Capable of delivering impactful product demonstrations and providing insights to help clients compete more effectively. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be part of - our values, culture and behaviours:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are a highly ambitious, innovative, market-leading FinTech. We are uncompromising in our desire to achieve our best, day-in day-out, and we have three clear values which guide everything we do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Brave - Everyone in the company has a voice to challenge ideas and the status quo. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Exceptional - We set high standards for ourselves. We aim to be exceptional at what we do. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Together - We are one team. There is no such thing as individual success without team success. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;🌟 Our behaviours guide us and inform how we communicate, collaborate and support each other. They are: Be Diverse, be Courageous, be Considerate, be Transparent, be Focused, be Accountable, and above all, be Dexterous!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we will give you - the perks:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid Model *2/3 days in our Sydney Office*&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Time away from work:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;23 vacation days annually plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;10 personal leave days annually&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2 Volunteer days annually (1 every 6 months)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Birthday Leave (you get a day off the week of your birthday!) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Compassionate Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Summer hours (3 hours off per week during summer &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work abroad for 20 days per year - allowing you to travel and work &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learning hours (3 hours of dedicated learning every 2 weeks)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity and Paternity Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribution towards private medical insurance and health &amp;amp; wellbeing allowance (e.g., gym, wellness apps, yoga)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQH0nrzFC78JQA/company-logo_200_200/B4EZU4zD9UGYAM-/0/1740414665009/hellodext_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=fu2Acf0TE_yLjDSfSanE_c97j4fvAjmPS2GkMAbwU2s', '2025-10-01T14:12:26.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z')
