    ('recgOzMGKGL0xfBBM', 'Copado', 'http://www.copado.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/copadosolutions', 'Chicago, Illinois, US', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '53', 'Copado is a well-funded computer software company with a strong global presence and an APAC office, aligning with core industry targets. However, current hiring activity is focused on technical roles rather than core sales positions. The presence of an MD APAC (Tier 1 decision maker) in Australia is a positive indicator, but limited sales hiring and lack of recent funding or leadership changes suggest medium priority for immediate recruitment opportunities.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nCopado launched Org Intelligence on August 13, 2025, providing end-to-end visibility and real-time insight into Salesforce environments to streamline releases and reduce deployment risks. The company also hosted the first CopadoCon India in September 2025, marking a strategic focus and community expansion in the Indian tech ecosystem.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nCopado nearly doubled its event capacity in India due to overwhelming demand and stated that almost 50% of its 100,000+ community members are now based in India, reflecting strong engagement and an expanding global presence. Current hiring activity includes open technical roles, such as QA Engineer in the U.S., and active participation in industry events as exhibitors and sponsors.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds were reported in the last 6-12 months. The most recent disclosed funding was a Series C completed on September 1, 2021, bringing Copadoâs total funding to $270.8 million.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn February 2025, Copado announced comprehensive DevOps support for Salesforce Data Cloud deployments, enabling more efficient speed-to-market for AI-powered solutions. The company also hosted its largest-ever community event, CopadoCon India, in September 2025, successfully engaging over 1,000 Salesforce developers.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes identified in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Copado''s platform is built for the unique demands of business applications. We align software development with your core business processes, optimize pre-built solutions, and ensure continuous collaboration. This is DevOps for Business Applicationsâagile, user-focused software tailored to your enterprise needs.\n\nAcross the globe, 1,400+ customers and 100,000+ Copado Community members leverage our complete and extensible DevOps solution to scale Salesforce, maximize business value and accelerate their careers."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recgTj4hGsARQ9xTM', 'clearer.io', 'https://www.clearer.io/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/clearerio', 'Boston, Massachusetts, US', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '68', 'Clearer.io is a computer software company with strong alignment to core tech and eCommerce technology sectors, operating in Australia with over 150 employees. Recent rebrand, new leadership, and active product launches indicate moderate growth and market engagement, particularly in AI-driven commerce. Presence of an Account Executive and Customer Success Executive in Australia, along with an APAC General Manager, demonstrates established sales and customer-facing teams with accessible decision makers. While no explicit funding or current high-value sales hiring is noted, the company''s size, sector, and recent activity suggest a strong opportunity for recruitment partnership.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAppHub rebranded as Clearer.io on October 28, 2024, consolidating its product suite under a unified platform to focus on simplifying eCommerce growth and product discovery for global businesses. The rebrand introduced a new leadership team and aimed to deliver integrated, data-driven solutions for merchants.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nClearer.io participated at Shopify Editions Horizons 2025 in Toronto, highlighting its active global team and close engagement with the Shopify ecosystem; recent internal communications indicate rapid product development and alignment with AI-driven commerce trends. No explicit data on recent headcount growth or GTM hiring found.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nThe company hosted and sponsored multiple key partner events at Shopify Editions 2025 in June, drawing over 300 attendees and large waitlists, and showcased alignment with new AI and product merchandising technologies. Clearer.ioâs Q4 product launch has been announced to leverage innovations in real-time and personalized ecommerce logic.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nJennifer Leuer was named CEO concurrent with the rebrand to Clearer.io in October 2024, introducing a new leadership team, but no further recent executive changes or hires were found."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Clearer.io, weâre on a mission to simplify and supercharge ecommerce success. Formerly known as AppHub, weâve evolved our identity to better reflect our commitment to clear, fast, and impactful solutions for growing online businesses.\nWe provide cutting-edge tools designed to optimize the entire shopping journey, from customer acquisition to conversion and beyond. By empowering ecommerce brands with user-friendly technology, actionable insights, and dedicated support, we help businesses streamline their operations and grow with confidence.\nOur vision is straightforward: make ecommerce tools that are powerful yet simple, flexible yet reliable. Weâre here to make things clearerâso businesses can focus on what they do best: delivering great products and experiences to their customers.\nLetâs build a brighter future for ecommerce, together. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('rechaVI3QeCIFodei', 'CentrePal', 'https://www.centrepal.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/centrepal', 'Melbourne, Victoria, AU', 'Computer Software', '11 - 50', '60', 'CentrePal is a Melbourne-based computer software company specializing in AI-powered customer experience solutions, aligning well with core target industries. The presence of an Enterprise Sales leader and Channel Partner Manager provides access to Tier 2 decision makers. While there are no explicit recent hiring or funding signals, recent product certifications and achievements indicate ongoing growth and market positioning, making this a strong recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn August 2025, CentrePal became the first independent software vendor to earn Microsoftâs Teams Contact Centre Unify certification, enabling advanced integration and the launch of enhanced AI-powered voice and customer experience tools. The company also announced plans to preview new Voice AI capabilities in the second half of 2025.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo explicit recent hiring or sales team expansion activity identified. The company continues to strengthen its product and integrations, extending its value proposition for enterprise users.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCentrePal achieved ISO 27001:2022 certification for information security management in May 2025, increasing its credibility for data protection and compliance. Additionally, the company reached Microsoft Teams Certified Solution status and became the first to earn Teams Unify certification in August 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Your teams already work in Microsoft Teams. So should your contact centre. \n\nBuilt from the ground up to be native to Microsoft Teams, CentrePal unifies voice, chat, email, SMS, and AI self-service into a single, seamless interface so your agents can focus less on switching tools and more on serving customers. No toggling. No integrations. \n\nWeâre a Microsoft-certified solution trusted by organisations across industries and around the world. From remote agents to global operations, our platform scales effortlessly while keeping things simple, secure, and cost-effective.\n\nCentrePal eliminates the complexity of traditional contact centres by embedding everything directly within Teams.\n\nThe result? Faster onboarding, lower overheads, and a frictionless experience for both agents and customers.\n\nWith real-time analytics, rapid deployment, powerful routing, interaction recording, and flexible supervisory controls, CentrePal gives you everything you need.... and nothing you donât. Whether your teams are remote, hybrid, or in-office, we help them work better together.\n\nCentrePal was built by industry veterans who understand the frustrations of outdated, over-engineered software. And weâre still that team: responsive to feedback and agile enough to evolve with your needs, because we believe perfection is a continuous process.\n\nModern customer expectations are rising. With CentrePal, your contact centre will too."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reciRfBU11O28PKte', 'Impel', 'https://impel.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/getimpel', 'New York, NY, US', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '80', 'Impel is a growth-stage computer software company (520 employees) specializing in commercial B2B AI and SaaS solutions for the automotive sector, indicating strong industry fit. The presence of a General Manager AU/NZ (Tier 1) and Sales Director APAC (Tier 1) provides direct access to high-level decision makers for recruitment. While the specific sales role is not listed, the company has multiple Client Account Managers (medium-priority roles) in Australia, suggesting ongoing sales hiring. Recent achievements, major acquisitions, and rapid global expansion signal strong growth, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nImpel announced major advances in automotive AI on July 14, 2025, including a domain-tuned LLM in partnership with AWS and a safety-focused research initiative featuring its Archias expert model. The company also recently acquired Outsell for approximately $100 million, expanding its platform capabilities in automotive marketing automation[1][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nImpel ranked among the 50 fastest-growing AI companies in the 2025 Inc. 5000 list, indicating rapid business momentum. Its AI platform now serves over 8,300 dealers across 53 countries and delivered more than 35 billion shopper interactions, reflecting substantial global expansion over the past year[2][1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding round announcements have been identified within the last 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nImpel won the inaugural AI Product of the Year award from Car Dealer Magazine in July 2025 for its conversational AI solution supporting automotive dealerships. The company''s AI deployment was showcased as a case study at Metaâs LlamaCon in July 2025, recognized by AWS and Meta for production performance and business impact[3][1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures have been publicly reported in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Impel offers automotive dealers, OEMs, and third-party marketplaces the industryâs most advanced AI Operating System. The companyâs end-to-end omnichannel solution leverages proprietary consumer behavioral data and generative conversational AI technology to deliver hyper-personalized sales, marketing, and service experiences at every touchpoint of the customer lifecycle. Impelâs fully integrated automotive retail platform works seamlessly with all major website, inventory, CRM, and DMS platforms. To date, the company has delivered over 27 billion shopper interactions, influencing more than $7 billion in sales and service revenue across 51 countries."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recjNsLbru34KeSw7', 'Phocas Software', 'http://www.phocassoftware.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/phocas-2', 'Sydney, New South Wales, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '201 - 500', '60', 'Phocas Software is a growth-stage SaaS/data analytics company (315 employees, Sydney) with strong commercial B2B tech fit. However, the specific sales role triggering inclusion is not provided, limiting role priority scoring. Decision maker access is unclear as no clear sales or regional leaders are listed among filtered employees. Recent partnership and product launch announcements indicate moderate growth, but absence of explicit hiring or funding signals reduces recruitment urgency. Overall, this presents a medium-priority opportunity, contingent on confirmation of an active core sales role.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nPhocas Software announced a strategic partnership with ADS Solutions in June 2025, becoming the preferred data analytics provider for Accolent ERP customers in wholesale distribution and light manufacturing. The company also revealed plans to launch Phocas Insights, an AI-powered product for proactive business decision-making, scheduled for release in 2025[1][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo explicit hiring or headcount expansion activity identified in the available sources. Phocas continues to onboard new enterprise clients and integrate with additional ERP platforms, indicating ongoing market expansion[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investment announcements, or financial milestones identified within the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nPhocas secured a partnership with ADS Solutions in June 2025, positioning its platform as a core data analytics offering for small and mid-size wholesale and manufacturing businesses[3]. The company also disclosed its upcoming AI-driven Phocas Insights product, set for 2025, aiming to deliver automated, actionable sales recommendations for customers[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures identified in the provided information."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Phocas is a SaaS company delivering an all-in-one BI and FP&A platform built for wholesale distribution, manufacturing, and retail businesses. Today, Phocas serves 2,700 mid-market companies and 40,000 users across the US, UK, Australia, and New Zealand.\n\nPhocas has a clear mission: to make people feel good about data. And itâs working! Customers love the intuitive, self-serve platform that brings their data to life.\n\nBy partnering with leading ERPs like Epicor, Infor, Sage, Kerridge, SAP, Oracle Netsuite and more, Phocas unlocks the potential of ERP data for everyone - delivering improvements at every level of the business. Our vision for our platform is as the one central, mission-critical layer above the ERP - empowering businesses with products collectively designed to deliver even greater value, insight and efficiency.\n\nFor CEO and co-founder, Myles Glashier, achieving this vision is all about people. Our team of almost 300 people spans the US, UK, Australia and New Zealand. We nurture a culture based on ''Fun, Fulfilling, Forever''âa spirit that shines through in every customer interaction. Weâre people-centric, responsive, and always open to new ways to innovate.\n\nThe bottom line? Helping customers and partners improve their businesses just feels good - and it''s even better when you''re part of a company that puts people first.\n\nAt Phocas, we''re committed to maintaining an environment where our team feels valued. Becoming a certified B Corp is part of that commitment, along with closing the gender pay gap across our global workforce, and being recognized for awards like the Human Synergistics Culture Sustainability Award. Whether weâre helping customers make sense of their data or creating a place where work feels meaningful, people feel good with Phocas.   "}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recjUbfJaIRKSGRPk', 'Zenith Payments Pty Ltd', 'http://www.zenithpayments.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/zenith-payments-pty-ltd', 'Balmain, NSW', 'Financial Services', '51-200 employees', '58', 'Zenith Payments Pty Ltd is a growth-stage financial services company (51-200 employees) in Australia, hiring for Business Development Manager and Sales Manager roles. The industry fit is strong secondary tech (Fintech), and company size is ideal for external recruitment. Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Manager, CCO) are present, supporting hiring authority. However, there are no recent funding rounds, leadership changes, or major hiring surges, and growth signals are moderate with product launches but no significant expansion. This results in a medium recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Zenith Payments’ **main operations and support are based in Sydney**, supporting major prepaid and transaction processing across the region[3]. No public reporting in the last 6-12 months specifically mentions new expansion or trigger events directly in Mascot, NSW; the company’s official headquarters remain in Balmain, NSW[1][2].\n[REGIONAL] Zenith continues to serve **major blue-chip Australian clients** across various sectors (corporate, education, travel, rental, childcare), reinforcing its footprint in **NSW and broader Australia**[2][4][5]. Notable market activity includes innovations in prepaid and digital card solutions, emphasizing local customization and school partnerships in NSW[3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Available evidence does not confirm recent hiring surges or physical office opening in Mascot, NSW; **most roles and operational functions are located in Sydney/Balmain**[3][6].\n[REGIONAL] **Employee count remains stable** (~80-200 across Australia), with ongoing demand for technical, support, and client-facing roles in Sydney[1][2]. Solutions target both small business and enterprise sectors, and schools partnerships highlight ongoing business development efforts in NSW[3].\n[GLOBAL] No substantial increase in headcount or global office count reported in the last year.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] **No confirmed funding rounds, investments, or major financial milestones publicly announced in AU or APAC from September 2024 to present**. Zenith Payments is described as 100% privately owned, and **does not appear to have raised external capital in recent reporting periods**[1][2][5].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] **ZAAP launched new digital pocket money solutions** targeting NSW schools, with customization and digital features for parents and students, reflecting engagement with local education clients[3].\n[REGIONAL] Zenith Payments maintains **strategic product launches** across brands (B2Bpay, School EasyPay, ZAAP, Rental Rewards, Universal Gift Card), but **no specific awards or large partnerships were publicly disclosed in the last 6-12 months**[2][3][4][5]. The company''s reputation as a first mover for payment technologies in Australia continues[2].\n[GLOBAL] MasterCard partnership for prepaid and digital card processing is ongoing, ensuring strong integration with global payment networks[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] **No executive appointments, significant promotions, or departures in Mascot, Balmain, or broader NSW publicly reported since Sep 2024**.\n[REGIONAL] **Current executive structure remains unchanged** (CEO and CFO roles are filled); no new sales, GTM, or leadership hires have been announced across AU, APAC, or globally in the last year[1][2].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The **financial services sector in Australia** continues to see robust digital and prepaid payment adoption, driven by increased demand for corporate and consumer solutions. The localized focus on school payment platforms and digital wallets aligns with market trends of cashless education environments and increased consumer digital literacy[3][5].\n\n**Scope note:** The intelligence above follows hierarchy from Mascot-NSW/AU to broader APAC/AU regional checks, global disclosure, and fallback to industry context where Zenith-specific public data is minimal or ambiguous. All claims reference latest public sources as of September 2025."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnerships &amp;amp; Enterprise Sales Executive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mascot, Sydney&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Zenith Payments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Permanent Full-Time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Competitive base salary plus commission&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a driven sales professional with a passion for payments and partnerships?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zenith Payments is seeking a dynamic Partnerships &amp;amp; Enterprise Sales Executive to lead the charge in identifying, securing, and growing relationships with software partners and enterprise merchants. This is a high-impact role for a true sales hunter who thrives on creating opportunities and delivering tailored solutions that drive revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a key member of our commercial team, you’ll engage with senior decision-makers across industries to understand their challenges and craft innovative payment solutions using Zenith’s suite of C2B and B2B products. Your technical understanding of software integrations (e.g., APIs) and strategic mindset will be essential in navigating complex sales cycles and exceeding revenue targets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and pursue new business opportunities with major merchants and software partners.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead outreach efforts, conduct meetings, and deliver compelling proposals and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to design and deliver tailored payment solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive the full sales cycle from prospecting to deal closure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of industry trends and regulatory changes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate pipeline and reporting using CRM tools (e.g., HubSpot).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Zenith at client meetings, workshops, and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of senior sales experience, ideally within the payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of generating leads, negotiating commercial outcomes, and closing high-value deals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of Australian payment systems and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and ability to engage cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with a flair for innovation and familiarity with Blue Ocean strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM platforms and sales enablement tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Zenith Payments?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Secure, Australian-owned and operated business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fast-growing and innovative company with over 20 years in the payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career development opportunities in a thriving sector.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Primarily office-based role in Mascot, Sydney.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generous leave policies including 20 annual leave days and 5 additional ‘Odd Job Days’ per year.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular staff recognition through Zenith Awards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inclusive workplace culture driven by strong company values.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQF77KhVUYTFzw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1691538097758/zenith_payments_pty_ltd_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=3gZTVRipmNHGWeErXF7YWXuFbdC3qs8iXYnqWI7e8Ho', '2025-09-23T14:19:23.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recjZbbUDKIlE94kV', 'Talkdesk', 'https://www.talkdesk.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/talkdesk', 'San Francisco, CA', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '1,001-5,000 employees', '97', 'Talkdesk is a growth-stage commercial B2B technology company (SaaS/AI-driven CX) with 1,001-5,000 employees, actively hiring for a Sales Development Representative (SDR) in Australia. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Vice President APAC, VP of Sales APAC & Japan) provides direct access for recruitment. Recent APAC expansion, regional leadership appointments, and strong local growth signals (cloud launch, headcount growth, sales hiring) indicate immediate and high-probability recruitment needs. This is a top-priority opportunity for external recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Talkdesk launched a **regional cloud deployment in Australia** in early 2024, enabling Australian businesses—especially in banking, retail, and healthcare—to host their customer experience platforms locally, comply with stringent Australian data privacy laws, and improve voice quality through reduced latency[1][2][3][4][5].  \n[REGIONAL] Following this, Talkdesk has established dedicated **APAC teams** in Australia, Singapore, the Philippines, China, Thailand, Korea, and India to accelerate regional growth and innovation in AI-driven customer experience solutions[1][2][4][5].  \n[GLOBAL] Company executives repeatedly emphasize **APAC as a strategic growth region**, reporting over **100% regional growth in the last six months due to focused investment**, with cloud localization serving as a critical differentiator for highly regulated sectors[1][2][4][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The launch of Australian cloud infrastructure is accompanied by the recruitment of **local talent** and growth in operational capacity, specifically targeting regulated industries[4][5].  \n[REGIONAL] New APAC leadership and regional teams signal expanded **hiring and partnership development**, particularly around sales and go-to-market roles to support customer success[1][2][5].  \n[GLOBAL] Talkdesk has reported **rapid headcount expansion** across its APAC network, supported by partnerships and sub-agents[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds specifically announced for Australia or APAC in the last six months; recent references point to increased internal investment in technology, teams, and partner networks to support the regional cloud build-out[1][2][3][4][5].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Talkdesk’s Australian cloud solution helped Metro Finance (client example) **reduce costs by up to 40%** utilizing their AI-powered CX technology[2][5].  \n[REGIONAL] The regional cloud launch is cited as a major **CX industry milestone** for data residency, privacy, and performance enhancement in APAC, attracting some of the region’s largest banks, e-commerce companies, and business process outsourcers as customers[1][2][3][4][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] **Simon Horrocks was appointed Vice President/APAC Leader in February 2024** to spearhead further expansion and innovation in artificial intelligence and customer experience across the region[1][2][5].\n\nOverall, Talkdesk’s current strategy highlights strong commitment to, and significant momentum in, the Australian and APAC markets, particularly in sales and AI-driven customer experience for regulated industries. No major funding events have been reported since early 2024; expansion is fueled by organic investments and leadership appointments."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Talkdesk, we are courageous innovators focused on redefining the customer experience, making the impossible possible for companies globally. We champion an inclusive and diverse culture representative of the communities in which we live and serve. And, we give back to our community by volunteering our time, supporting non-profits, and minimizing our global footprint. Each day, thousands of employees, customers, and partners all over the world trust Talkdesk to deliver a better way to great experiences.We are recognized as a cloud contact center leader by many of the most influential research organizations, including Gartner and Forrester. With $498 million in total funding, a valuation of more than $10 Billion, and a ranking of #16 on the Forbes Cloud 100 list, now is the time to be part of the Talkdesk legacy to help accelerate our success in a new decade of transformational growth.At Talkdesk, we embrace FAST, our fundamental operating principles that define who we are as an organization. These principles drive us to make the impossible possible. FAST: Focus + Accountability + Speed = Talkdesker.Focus: Focus time, energy and attention on what is most impactful for the business and thoughtful about how and when to partner with others.Accountability: Hold self and others accountable to meet commitments and drive results. Accept responsibility for successes and failures.Speed: Execute with agility and urgency. Act promptly, decisively, and without delay. Make good and timely decisions that keep the organization moving forward.Talkdesker: YOU! Responsibilities:Meet and exceed quarterly and annual revenue/quota through the management and execution of the Talkdesk sales processDevelop a comprehensive sales strategy and a sales plan that ensures consistent achievement of objectives over the short- and long-term for your coverage modelBuild lasting, meaningful relationships internally with other members of management, team, as well as externally with prospects, customers, and partner communityBuild and align with the Talkdesk sales Go-to-Market plan to develop and own accountability for region’s market segmentation and targeted accountsCommunicate accurate and realistic forecast information to the management team per our process and policyCommunicate market reaction and needs back to the business in a productive mannerEngage proactively in problem-solving across functional areas instead of bringing issues to the factory doorstep.Take the lead in prioritizing the needs of customers so that engineering and other functional areas can focus on the right tasks and issuesCoverage: Enterprise Accounts (>1,000 employees) All industries, preference for experience in related Cloud based Software and Artificial IntelligenceTerritory: New South Wales, Queensland, and Australian Capital Territory Requirements:Travel required: 50%+5+ years of new business, direct sales experience, carrying a quotaPrior success selling SaaS-based solutions, managing complex sales practices and solution-based selling to CXO, senior management and director-level individuals at enterprise-level prospectsStrong analytical and business deal-making capability, ability to ferret out opportunities, create positive relationships, ask questions that uncover hidden issues during discovery, and bring the transaction to closure successfullyDemonstrated track record of successfully planning, developing, and implementing of new business opportunitiesProven ability to grow revenues to a substantial level and scale bookings growth and net-new customersExcellent communication and presentation skillsExtensive negotiation and contract development experienceComfortable operating in a fast-paced, dynamic startup environmentBachelor’s Degree preferred  Work Environment and Physical Requirements:Primarily office-environment work, extended periods of sitting or standing, computer-based work. Limited lifting, and equipment usage limited to computer-related equipment (keyboards, mouse, etc.)The Talkdesk story hinges on empathy and acceptance. It is the shared goal among all Talkdeskers to empower a new kind of customer hero through our innovative software solution, and we firmly believe that the best path to success for our mission is inclusivity, diversity, and genuine acceptance. To that end, we will hire, promote, work along, cheer for, bond with, and warmly welcome into the Talkdesk family all persons without regard to ethnic and racial identity, indigenous heritage, national origin, religion, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, disability, marital status, veteran status, genetic information, or any other legally protected status."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-28T03:54:30.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recjd1t4UZmwhnic0', 'Sentrient', 'https://www.sentrient.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/sentrient', 'Melbourne, Victoria', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '51-200 employees', '64', 'Sentrient is a small/medium IT services and consulting company (51-200 employees) in Melbourne, actively employing Account Executives and Account Managers—medium-priority sales roles. The company operates in the commercial B2B tech sector (acceptable fit, 15 points) with a focus on compliance, HR, and GRC software. Decision maker access is moderate, with Account Executives and an Account Manager (Tier 2, 10 points) but no direct Sales Director/VP or GM/Regional Manager. Growth signals are present via a growing client base and product achievements, but there is no evidence of recent funding or explicit sales hiring surges. This represents a realistic but not urgent recruitment opportunity for external sales hiring.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sentrient is emphasizing its role in helping Australian businesses navigate a rapidly changing compliance and regulatory landscape, particularly in 2025, citing new laws and enforcement mechanisms in payroll, data privacy, cybersecurity, and workplace safety as recent drivers for increased demand for their solutions[3].  \n[LOCAL] The company is positioning itself as an all-in-one HR, compliance, and GRC (governance, risk, and compliance) software provider specifically tailored to the Australian regulatory environment[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Sentrient is “trusted by 600+ Australian businesses,” reflecting continued local adoption and a growing client base in Melbourne and across Australia[1].  \n[LOCAL] The platform advertises features supporting recruitment, onboarding, people management, and compliance, indicating a potential increase in demand for both operational and client-facing roles, though explicit job postings or sales/GTM hiring activity in the past 6-12 months is not cited in publicly available sources[1].  \n[LOCAL] Their primary operational scope remains Australia and New Zealand, with a focus on local data storage and customer service based in Australia[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] There is no publicly available information in the past 6-12 months regarding recent funding rounds or financial milestones for Sentrient.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sentrient continues to market itself as “Australia’s most reliable compliance, GRC, and HR solution” for businesses ranging from SMEs to larger organizations, supporting the compliance needs for all Australian states and territories[1].  \n[LOCAL] The release and maintenance of pre-built, legally-endorsed compliance courses and policy templates for Australian workplaces constitute continuing product achievements[1].  \n[LOCAL] Sentrient’s platform claims to reduce HR costs by 40%, decrease administration time by 67%, and achieve three times ROI for clients, positioning recent performance gains as product achievements[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] There is no publicly disclosed information on executive appointments, promotions, or departures in the past 6-12 months related to Melbourne or broader Australian operations.\n\nINDUSTRY FALLBACK:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian IT services and IT consulting market is experiencing increased demand for compliance, data privacy, and workforce management solutions, largely driven by new and changing regulatory frameworks and a heightened focus on remote work and digital transformation in the post-pandemic period[3].  \n[INDUSTRY] Local providers are emphasizing data localization and compliance with region-specific legislation to gain customer trust and differentiate in a market with increasing compliance complexity[1][3].\n\nScope used: Information is primarily [LOCAL] (Melbourne/AU) and [INDUSTRY] due to limited recent news on regional or global funding, hiring, or leadership changes. All evidence cited is within the past 6-12 months where available."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sentrient is Australia''s leading online workplace compliance system for businesses of all sizes. It provides affordable and stress-free compliance solutions, including legally endorsed online compliance courses and a user-friendly HR management system. Sentrient helps businesses protect themselves from safety breaches, privacy issues, workplace bullying, and discrimination.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, on-site role for an Account Executive SaaS located in Melbourne, VIC. The Account Executive will be responsible for identifying sales opportunities, conducting product demonstrations, negotiating contracts, and achieving sales targets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a key role in the development of Sentrient, and we are looking for someone who is self-motivated and enjoys working in a supportive, fast-paced and results-driven team environment!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales, preferably within SaaS products and services&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and negotiation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of SaaS products and services&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and articulate technical concepts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in B2B sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree in Business Administration, Marketing, or related field&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in the compliance or HR industry is a plus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay&lt;/strong&gt;: We offer a competitive salary and bonus structure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Performance&lt;/strong&gt;: Be part of a high performance sales culture where your contributions will directly impact the company’s growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career Progression: &lt;/strong&gt;As a fast growing SaaS company there are opportunities for career progression.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQGDXJcTEhZksA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630656626360/sentrient_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=fvGhkGcGbbcoNDIVnfcTySN3bfllve0jM_sKT_iRczU', '2025-09-23T14:24:29.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reck0265Lb3G5tLJn', 'Intellect', 'https://intellect.co', 'https://sg.linkedin.com/company/intellecthq', 'Singapore', 'IT Services and IT Consulting', '201-500 employees', '44', 'Intellect is a growth-stage IT Services and Consulting company (201-500 employees, Singapore HQ) with some presence in Australia, evidenced by a Market Lead - ANZ and Helpline Operations Lead in-country. The triggering role is Enterprise Account Executive (medium-priority sales role). Industry fit is strong secondary tech (20 points), but there are no recent growth signals, hiring surges, or public expansion activity in APAC/Australia. Decision maker access is moderate (Market Lead - ANZ, Senior VP Partnerships, Enterprise AE), but no Tier 1 or 2 sales leaders are visible. With no active growth or hiring signals and only a medium-priority sales role, the likelihood of immediate recruitment opportunity is low.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] No publicly reported major business developments or market events specific to **Intellect** (IT Services and IT Consulting) in Sydney, NSW or elsewhere in Australia in the past 12 months based on available information.  \n[REGIONAL] No direct APAC/ANZ operational news found for \"Intellect\" matching the parameters within the last year.  \n[GLOBAL] No significant global developments directly referenced for an \"Intellect\" headquartered in Singapore with reported impact on Australian or APAC operations in the time frame.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There is no evidence of new office openings, team expansions, or significant hiring activity (including sales/GTM roles) by Intellect in Sydney or greater Australia during the last 6–12 months.  \n[REGIONAL] No regional hiring campaigns or expansion statements found targeting APAC/ANZ for Intellect.  \n[GLOBAL] No public announcements regarding company-wide headcount growth, new markets, or expansion initiatives affecting the Australia or ANZ region in the last year.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No recent investment rounds or financial milestones have been reported in the public domain for an IT Services/Consulting company named Intellect with a Singapore HQ over the last 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] No recent awards, partnerships, notable rollouts, or enterprise customer wins attributed to Intellect in Sydney, NSW or Australia.  \n[REGIONAL] No industry awards or notable APAC achievements identified for Intellect.  \n[GLOBAL] No global achievements, product launches, or strategic partnerships with clear regional relevance located for the reporting period.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No reported executive appointments, promotions, or departures (including country manager or sales/revenue/people leadership) at Intellect''s Sydney/Australian operations in the past 6–12 months.\n[GLOBAL] No publicly reported global leadership changes impacting regional strategy or operations during the target window.\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The **IT Services and Consulting sector in Australia** remains robust, with demand driven by digital transformation, cloud migration, and a heightened focus on cybersecurity and business continuity[1][2]. Companies providing managed services, security, disaster recovery, and consultative IT solutions (like those described for Intellect IT, Melbourne, which appears separate and distinct from a Singapore-based \"Intellect\") remain in steady demand, particularly among SMBs and enterprises in need of reliable, scalable tech support[1][2]. The Sydney market remains highly competitive, with local and international players actively investing in next-gen IT managed services, but there is no direct evidence that Intellect (Singapore HQ) has established or recently grown an Australian presence.\n\n**Note:**  \n- Search identified several companies named \"Intellect,\" including *Intellect IT* (an established Melbourne-based provider of IT services and consulting[1][2]) and *Intellect Design Arena* (a Chennai, India-based fintech platform provider with no direct evidence of Australian IT services operations[4]).  \n- There is **no verifiable evidence** matching a Singapore-HQ’d \"Intellect\" with active or recent Sydney/Australian operations based on available public sources.  \n- If referring to \"Intellect IT,\" the primary office is in Melbourne, not Singapore, and no Sydney expansion or hiring has been reported in the last year[1][2].  \n- If referring to \"Intellect Design Arena,\" the company is headquartered in India with offices globally, but not in Australia or Sydney for IT services/consulting in the last 6–12 months[4].  \n- If a different \"Intellect\" entity is intended, further clarification may yield more accurate intelligence."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"As an Enterprise Account Executive, you''ll be a key driver of our Revenue team, owning end-to-end mid market and enterprise deals. You''ll blend deep consultative expertise with project leadership to guide complex multi-region clients through discovery, solution design, and deployment of Intellect''s mental health benefits technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You''ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Engagement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior stakeholders (HR leaders, wellbeing champions, C-suite) to uncover organisational challenges, define success criteria, and align on strategic objectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage Economic Buyers early to ensure visibility and sponsorship&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultative Solution Development&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Co-create tailored wellbeing roadmaps leveraging Intellect''s full suite of digital, clinical, and consulting services&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply a consultative lens—no cookie-cutter pitches—by tailoring every solution to each client''s unique context and goals&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Account &amp;amp; Project Leadership&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-regional deal execution, coordinating resources and local champions across APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own implementation timelines and milestones, ensuring seamless handover to Customer Success for renewals and expansions&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline Ownership &amp;amp; Forecasting&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a healthy 3×-quota coverage pipeline with accurate forecasting in HubSpot (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive proactive deal reviews and territory planning to meet quarterly revenue targets&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Continuous Improvement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise with clinical experts, product, and delivery teams to align on solution feasibility and client requirements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Surface market and client insights to inform product enhancements and internal best practices&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Experience:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;≥ 5 years in enterprise software/services sales (preferably HR tech or consulting)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record closing deals from $60K ACV onwards across complex accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Expertise:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong consultative selling skills: able to probe deeply, diagnose pain, and tailor solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent project and stakeholder management in complex, long-cycle deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with pipeline management tools and disciplined sales processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable engaging at executive levels (HR heads, CHROs, CFOs, CEOs)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Behaviors &amp;amp; Cultural Fit:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative mindset: prioritises understanding over pitching&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bias for action: drives momentum in multi-stakeholder deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborative: partners seamlessly across functions and geographies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nice-to-Haves:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor''s degree in Business, HR, Psychology, or related field&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exposure to mental health benefits technology in corporate settings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling health, safety or wellbeing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling to government&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You''ll Love Working With Us:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Global company - work in a diverse environment with people from nearly 20 countries&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Generous leave policy - time off to rest and recharge&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Christmas week off - company-wide break during Christmas, separate from annual leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Birthday leave - enjoy a day off on your birthday&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Quarterly mental health days - one day off every quarter to focus on your wellbeing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Flexible work arrangements - work in a way that suits your lifestyle and goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Work-life balance - a culture that values personal time and long-term wellness&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Medical coverage - comprehensive insurance for peace of mind&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Performance bonus - high performance is recognised and rewarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Development budget - annual allowance to support your professional development&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Mental health support - premium coaching access to our mental health app and resources &amp;amp; dedicated budget for clinical and psychiatric care&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Socials and communities - regular non-work events/activities to connect and have fun together&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'LOW', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQFj22sEy_9vJA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1715741893050/intellecthq_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=Kj4tpjQpeBQsyheHopvHF7S9dCQf5ErDhfqjFxDweUk', '2025-09-28T03:43:53.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reck4ZTN75IfeqvII', 'etrainu', 'https://etrainu.com/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/etrainu', 'Brisbane City, Queensland, AU', 'E-learning', '51 - 200', '74', 'etrainu is a Brisbane-based e-learning SaaS provider with 60 employees and strong recent growth through multiple strategic partnerships and international market expansion. The presence of a Sales Manager and VP Sales and Revenue ensures Tier 2 decision maker access for sales hiring discussions. While there are no explicit current sales job postings, the company''s ongoing expansion and industry fit indicate high potential for recruitment needs in core sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\netrainu announced a strategic partnership with Learning Vault in August 2025 to deliver digital, verifiable credentials to learners, enhancing certificate authenticity and recovery. In August 2025, etrainu also reported a new integration and partnership with Sport:80 to provide seamless professional development and qualification tracking for sports organizations.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\netrainu expanded its market reach through new partnerships with sports governing bodies such as Archery Ireland (July 2025), Rugby Football League (August 2025), and USA Team Handball (August 2025), focusing on integrated learning platforms and digital transformation for community education. These deals indicate increased adoption of the etrainu LMS in both the UK and US sports sectors.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\netrainu and the Rugby Football League achieved an 85% completion rate across 5,000+ learners in August 2025, a figure significantly above industry benchmarks for online learning. The company has also been highlighted in several new digital transformation projects across national sports bodies, advancing its reputation for large-scale education initiatives.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"etrainu is a leader in online training and business solutions, delivering eLearning through our centralised Learning Management System (LMS).\n\nOur interactive eLearning solutions and online courses make it easy to achieve your personal and professional goals.\n\netrainu provides tailored training in Disability, Aged Care, Hospitality, Retail, Business & Leadership, Mining & Construction, Compliance and Sports."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reckEDXMa5godP3YC', 'HyperStrong', 'www.hyperstrong.com', 'https://cn.linkedin.com/company/hyperstrong', 'Beijing, , CN', 'Mechanical Or Industrial Engineering', '1001 - 5000', '59', 'HyperStrong operates in the industrial engineering sector with a strong energy storage focus and has over 140 employees, meeting base requirements. The presence of Sales Directors in both Australia and Singapore provides Tier 2 decision maker access. While there are robust growth signals through international expansion, revenue growth, and major APAC partnerships, there are no explicit core sales role job postings or recent funding. The industry is adjacent to core tech but not a direct match, resulting in a solid but not top-tier opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn June 2025, HyperStrong showcased its \"Energy Storage + X\" strategy at SNEC 2025, signing cooperation agreements with Genertec, Shuangdeng, Inovance, and WellPlus to expand its ecosystem of energy storage solutions. In July 2025, HyperStrong signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Singapore-based Alpina to supply 5,000 integrated charging and storage units for APAC markets from 2025 to 2027, signaling aggressive growth in EV infrastructure. In July 2025, HyperStrong also entered a supply deal to help deploy 1.4 GWh of battery energy storage systems in Europe with Repono AB through 2027.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHyperStrongâs operating revenue increased by 22.66% year-on-year in H1 2025, reaching 4.522 billion yuan, and international expansion included significant projects commissioned in Sweden and Germany. The company has also accelerated headcount and commercial engagement through industrial collaborations and multi-country deployments, indicating robust market expansion and global team growth.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nHyperStrong completed the commissioning of benchmark energy storage projects in Stockholm, Sweden and Waltershausen, Germany in H1 2025. The companyâs liquid-cooled grid-forming PCS received the \"Guardian Product Certification\" from Chinaâs Quality Certification Center, and it launched next-generation products like the MagicBlock platform and the modular HyperBlock M utility-scale system at SNEC 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Beijing HyperStrong Technology Co., Ltd. (âHyperStrongâ, 688411.SH) is a leading energy storage system integrator and service provider. With over 13 years of R&D and experience garnered through more than 300 projects and over 30GWh of deployment, HyperStrong offers a full portfolio of energy storage products as well as one-stop solutions for clients ranging from thermal power and renewable power generation to commercial and industrial users. \n\nHaving built four smart manufacturing bases, two R&D centers, a testing lab and a global marketing center, HyperStrong empowers clients worldwide to achieve their energy transition and carbon neutrality goals. \n\nAccording to S&P Global Commodity Insights, HyperStrong has been ranked among the top three BESS integrators in terms of global capacity installed in 2023, and the top BESS integrator in China (mainland) market in terms of cumulative installed and contracted project capacity in both GW and GWh as of July 2024. Since 2024, BloombergNEF has ranked HyperStrong in the Tier 1 energy storage provider list."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reckXSxh9TTqxoIhP', 'MRI Software', 'http://www.mrisoftware.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mri-software-llc', 'Solon, OH', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '92', 'MRI Software is a growth-stage SaaS/software company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong APAC operations, actively hiring for core sales roles such as Account Executive and Sales Manager. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Director, VP, Commercial Sales Manager, Director - Enterprise) provides direct access for recruitment. Multiple strong growth signals are present: recent acquisition (Anacle), strategic APAC leadership appointments, new partnerships, and ongoing sales hiring in Australia. These factors, combined with the company''s industry fit and expansion trajectory, make this a very high priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] MRI Software **completed the acquisition of Anacle**, a Singapore-based provider of property and facilities management solutions, in June 2025, extending its offerings and scale for commercial real estate owners, particularly in APAC[2][3].  \n[REGIONAL] In May 2025, MRI appointed **James Bell (former CEO, Century 21 Australia)** as Director of Enterprise, APAC Residential Sector, emphasizing strategic attention to the ANZ market[2][3].  \n[REGIONAL] MRI announced an **expanded partnership with PropTech Labs** in Australia and New Zealand to deliver more comprehensive solutions for property managers in March 2025[2][3].  \n[LOCAL] Snug, a property management automation provider based in Australia, announced a partnership with MRI Software for integrated leasing workflow solutions in April 2025, targeting efficiencies for property professionals in the region[2][3].  \n[REGIONAL] The 2025 “Voice of the Facility Manager” report revealed **surging workloads and tech opportunities** among ANZ facilities management professionals, underscoring increased technology adoption pressures in Australia[2][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] MRI’s **APAC staff and client base expanded sharply** post-Anacle acquisition; APAC operations now represent a critical growth vector, with *employee headcount globally up 60% in three years to 4,500+* and ongoing recruitment, particularly in sales and client services[1].  \n[LOCAL] Multiple sales, product, and customer support roles have been posted for MRI’s Sydney and Melbourne offices through 2025[2].  \n[REGIONAL] Appointment of a dedicated APAC leader for residential enterprise (James Bell) underlines increased focus on large-scale, multi-asset clients in Australia and New Zealand[2][3].  \n[GLOBAL] Company is experiencing roughly **20% annual revenue growth**; APAC operations are explicitly mentioned as a growth engine[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There are **no public funding rounds disclosed in the last 12 months**; the company’s recent M&A (Anacle, iInterchange) and strong revenue growth ($900M, up 20% YoY) indicate robust cash flow and ongoing reinvestment in international, especially APAC, expansion[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] MRI Software was named to the **G2’s 2025 Best Real Estate Software Products Award** list, underscoring strong customer feedback and product excellence[1][2].  \n[REGIONAL] MRI won awards at the 2024 Proptech Awards and hosted the *2024 RE:Visionary Awards* for APAC tech leaders, highlighting its sector influence in the region[3].  \n[LOCAL] New partnerships with Australian tech companies (Snug, PropTech Labs, CBA) reflect active ecosystem engagement[2][3].  \n[REGIONAL] Growing presence in residential, commercial, and social housing sectors, including contract wins (e.g., Centuria Capital) and local technology initiatives[3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] In May 2025, **James Bell** was appointed Director of Enterprise for APAC Residential Sector[2][3].  \n[GLOBAL] Patrick Ghilani continues as CEO, leading global and regional growth initiatives[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Multiple strategic appointments to the APAC leadership team in 2024-2025 have expanded sales and go-to-market capacity in Australia[3].\n\n---\n*Scope key*: Most information pertains to APAC regional operations, with local Melbourne-specific activity inferred from partnerships, hiring activity, and sales roles targeting the area. When direct Melbourne details are unavailable, broader AU/APAC developments with local impact are emphasized."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Act as a strategic solution expert to penetrate existing accounts and build long term meaningful relationships. Drive new revenue to the business and create advocates in the marketplace for the MRI brand, reduce the attrition rate of existing customers through open and regular communication, drive whitespace revenue into existing accounts through new feature adoption, additional vertical uptake and utilization of partner integrations. This is a great opportunity for a dynamic, experienced sales professional that is focused on retaining and expanding MRIs footprint of the existing client base employing a consultative ‘solution expert’ sales approach.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Account Manager/Account Executive (Hybrid), you will be responsible for the following:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acting as a ‘solutions expert’ in helping customers with their unique business issues and strategic initiatives – become a trusted advisor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work on developing detailed plans on how customers can best partner with MRI AND ensure this plan is executed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidently conduct client presentations, meetings, demonstrations and promote MRI at industry conferences and trade shows as required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working with the broader sales team to share ideas, knowledge and business development strategies to ensure our approach is aligned across the business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Driving and managing the sales process - targeting retention, expansion and net new opportunities, identifying client solutions, building and maintaining customer relationships, supporting/ scheduling software demonstrations, negotiating and administrating opportunities within your assigned account list&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitating the sales administration process in SFDC and Hubspot&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design account strategies and work with leadership and marketing to achieve short and long-term sales goals for targeted clients&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Schedule / deliver valuable and confident presentations to existing clients / prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop detailed account mapping to ensure aligns with relevant goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement integrated sales strategies in conjunction with other business units on shared opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceed assigned annual sales / retention quotas through upsell, cross sell and new sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handle the contracting process and sales administration (SFDC)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain relationships with existing customers through online and face to face interaction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand MRI’s positioning in the market and be well versed in product differentiators and strengths with a view to expand client footprints across your accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a healthy pipeline, excellent record keeping and forecast reporting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent company at trade association meetings to promote products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All other duties and responsibilities as assigned&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3 + years of strategic sales/account management experience in Proptech software industry or similar&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Residential Real Estate experience preferred, yet not required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record in adding value through client relationship in order to increase the revenue over a sustained period, exceeding sales targets with ability to work with the key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage with C suite confidently and interpret / convey MRI’s mission&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence in presenting to clients / prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate in a very fast paced environment with multiple priorities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of technology and ability to absorb new systems and processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, marketing, or related discipline preferred, yet not required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SFDC AND Hubspot experience preferred, yet not required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT MAKES THIS A GREAT OPPORTUNITY? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;MRI is an industry leader that has experienced double digit revenue growth year over year&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We provide great internal sales support including marketing support&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Base salary and uncapped commission. Flexible working arrangements &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Annual performance-related bonus &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;6x Flexi Fridays: knock 2.5 hours off your day on a Friday &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Me Days: an additional 3 days of leave each year to qualifying employees &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engaging, fun &amp;amp; inclusive culture: check out the MRI Software APAC Insta feed and stories! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;MRI Software delivers innovative applications and hosted solutions that free real estate companies to elevate their business. Our flexible technology platform, along with an open and connected ecosystem, allows us to meet the unique needs of real estate businesses, from property-level management and accounting to investment modelling and analytics for the global commercial and residential markets. With nearly five decades of expertise and insight, we have grown to include offices in across the United States, the United Kingdom, Hong Kong, Singapore, Australia, South Africa, New Zealand, Canada, India, and Ireland with over 4500 team members to support our clients and their unique needs!"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHU1TNSPfTnHw/company-logo_200_200/B56ZfMKjKTHoAQ-/0/1751477007335/mri_software_llc_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=fovY-ee9iX43ztJNWSAIKjpxB73MMcZDwUrnOM7rwBw', '2025-09-21T14:10:52.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reckXqCxAEcgm6A4o', 'OnBoard', 'https://www.onboardmeetings.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/onboardmeetings', 'Indianapolis, Indiana, US', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '56', 'OnBoard is a growth-stage computer software company (251 employees) with commercial B2B SaaS focus, which aligns well with 4Twenty''s core market. The included role is Senior Customer Success Manager, a medium-priority sales-adjacent position. Decision maker access is solid, with an Account Director (Tier 2) and Senior CSM (Tier 3) present in Australia. However, there are no recent funding, hiring, or sales/revenue growth signals, and no evidence of a current hiring surge. This makes OnBoard a medium-priority recruitment opportunity, with potential but lacking immediate urgency.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOnBoard launched its AI-powered governance suite, OnBoard AI, specifically for boards of directors in March 2025, adding multiple AI capabilities for agenda creation, document summarization, and meeting workflows. The platform emphasizes security and compliance with standards such as SOC 2 Type II, ISO-27001/27701, GDPR, and HIPAA[1][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified indicating significant hiring or market expansion, and no sales/revenue team growth indicators found in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified within the past year.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nOnBoard launched six distinct AI features for board workflow optimizationâAgenda AI, Book AI, Minutes AI, Assist AI, Insights AI, and Actions AIâintegrated into its platform and publicly announced in March 2025[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people operations identified in the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At OnBoard, we believe board meetings should be simple, effective, and secure. Thatâs why we''re dedicated to delivering innovative governance solutions for boards, directors, and the organizations they serve.  Launched in 2011, today, OnBoard serves as the board portal of choice platform for more than 6,000 organizations and their 100,000 users committees in 60 countries worldwide. With customers in financial services, higher education, professional associations, non-profit, health care, government, and public and private corporations, OnBoard is the leading choice for board management solutions.  \n\nWe''re on a mission to deliver simple and secure board governance solutions that make boards and board work more effective. Are you? Join the team by applying for a role today at: https://www.onboardmeetings.com/about-us/careers\n\nWith headquarters in Indianapolis, Ind., and a globally distributed workforce, OnBoard helps boards worldwide with teams in Toronto, London, Belfast, and Sydney. "}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recl3MF2V1sIeXY9w', 'Advantech', 'https://www.advantech.com/en', 'https://tw.linkedin.com/company/advantech', 'Neihu District, Taipei 114, TW', 'Industrial Automation', '5001 - 10000', '74', 'Advantech is a well-established industrial automation and IoT technology company with significant operations in Australia and Singapore. Recent strategic AI partnerships, product launches, and international awards signal ongoing innovation and market expansion, though there are no recent funding rounds or explicit sales hiring surges. The presence of multiple sales managers and a sales director across both regions indicates a mature sales structure and strong decision maker access, making this a high-potential opportunity for recruitment services focused on sales and revenue roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAdvantech announced a strategic AI partnership with Nagarro in April 2025 to strengthen their WISE-Edge collaboration platform. In December 2024, the company unveiled a major brand revitalization initiative, setting a vision to become a global leader in edge computing and edge AI by 2025, focusing on five key markets and international ecosystem partnerships.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAdvantech emphasized talent development and global presence expansion as part of its 2025 vision, though no recent hiring numbers or specific GTM role expansions have been disclosed. Participation in major global exhibitions throughout 2025 suggests ongoing market outreach and business development.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds, investment announcements, or financial milestones identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn March 2025, Advantechâs \"WISE-IoT Andon AI-Powered Digital Solution\" and \"LEO-L50 Outdoor Asset Management Device\" won the 2025 iF Design Award, highlighting its innovation in smart manufacturing and logistics. Also in March, Advantech launched the MIC-360 industrial computing platform and introduced NVIDIA-accelerated Edge AI solutions optimized for open-source LLMs.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in leadership roles identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Founded in 1983, Advantech is a leader in providing trusted, innovative products, services, and solutions. Advantech offers comprehensive system integration, hardware, software, customer-centric design services, embedded systems, automation products, and global logistics support. We cooperate closely with our partners to help provide complete solutions for a wide array of applications across a diverse range of industries. Our mission is to enable an intelligent planet with Automation and Embedded Computing products and solutions that empower the development of smarter working and living. With Advantech, there is no limit to the applications and innovations our products make possible. (Corporate Website: www.advantech.com)."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reclDHuLvn8FZOaVP', 'Hyland', 'https://www.hyland.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyland-software', 'Westlake, OH, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '67', 'Hyland is a growth-stage computer software company (4,150 employees) with operations in Australia and Singapore, fitting the core commercial B2B tech profile. The presence of Sales Directors and an Asia Pacific Sales Director provides Tier 2 decision maker access for sales recruitment. While recent product launches and a strategic AI pivot signal innovation, there are no strong headcount growth or recent funding signals, and recent layoffs suggest cautious hiring. The opportunity is driven by core industry fit and quality decision makers, making this a HIGH priority recruitment opportunity, though growth indicators are moderate.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nHyland executed a dramatic rebrand in March 2025, signaling a strategic pivot toward AI-driven enterprise automation and cloud-native content intelligence. At its CommunityLIVE event in September 2024, Hyland also launched its Content Innovation Cloud, further embedding AI and intelligent automation across its product suite[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo significant headcount growth or large-scale hiring initiatives publicly reported in the last 6-12 months. Hyland did lay off several hundred employees approximately 18 months ago and subsequently brought in new external leadership, with roles and reporting lines revised or removed during organizational restructuring[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or new investment announcements identified within the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nHyland announced the 2025 Innovation Award winners at its CommunityLIVE conference in August 2025, recognizing customer organizations for transformative use of Hylandâs technologies. Significant April 2025 product releases introduced new AI capabilities across Hyland Automate, Knowledge Discovery, OnBase, and Alfresco[1][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nHyland appointed new leadership from outside the company following layoffs in early 2024, including new Chief Product Officer Leonard Kim, who publicly led the product vision presentation in September 2024. Additional leadership roles were restructured, but no other specific C-level or executive appointments in sales or revenue roles were reported by name in the last 6-12 months[2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Hyland uniquelyâ¯empowers your organization with unified access to AI-enabled enterprise content and unstructured data across repositories, unlocking profound insights that fuel innovations â fundamentally redefining how youâ¯operateâ¯and engage with those you serve."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reclJrXROSskLa4Em', 'Gigamon', 'http://www.gigamon.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gigamon', 'Santa Clara, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '84', 'Gigamon is a growth-stage computer software company (1,249 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively hiring for sales leadership roles (e.g., Sales Director, Regional Sales Director) in Australia and Singapore. Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including a Country Manager and multiple Sales Directors, providing high-level access for recruitment. Recent growth signals include new office openings, leadership hires in APAC, and ongoing sales team expansion, indicating a strong likelihood of external recruitment need for core sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nGigamon unveiled its new agentic AI application, Gigamon Insights, in September 2025, integrating with SIEM platforms like Elastic and Splunk to provide AI-powered network telemetry and instant guidance for security operations. In June 2025, Gigamon advanced its deep observability tools with AI-driven features to combat shadow AI risks and enhance cybersecurity, and announced the opening of a new office in Mexico City in May 2025 to support regional growth[1][3][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nGigamon opened a new office in Mexico City in May 2025, signaling regional market expansion. The company has also posted ongoing recruitment for various teams on its careers portal and announced new hires, including sales leadership in Asia Pacific, indicating sustained headcount growth and a focus on go-to-market roles[1][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nGigamon maintained leadership in the deep observability market with 52% market share in 2025 and received the Frost & Sullivan Company of the Year award for global network observability in September 2025. The company also earned several industry recognitions in 2024, including the Top InfoSec Innovator Award and the CRN Partner Program Guide 5-Star Rating for the seventh consecutive year[1][2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nLisa Harrup Mieuli was named Chief Marketing Officer in April 2025, Tony Jarjoura was appointed CFO in February 2025, and Ram Bhide joined as Senior Vice President of Engineering the same month. Simon Oliver was appointed Director of Channel Sales for Asia Pacific in April 2025[1][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Gigamon offers a deep observability pipeline that harnesses actionable network-level intelligence to amplify the power of observability tools. This powerful combination helps enable IT organizations to assure security and compliance governance, speed root-cause analysis of performance bottlenecks, and lower operational overhead associated with managing hybrid and multi-cloud IT infrastructure. The result: modern enterprises realize the full transformational promise of the cloud. Gigamon serves more than 4,000 customers worldwide, including over 80 percent of Fortune 100 enterprises, 9 of the 10 largest mobile network providers, and hundreds of governments and educational organizations worldwide. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reclOoDpUIyExcfXh', 'Adyen', 'https://www.adyen.com', 'https://nl.linkedin.com/company/adyen', 'Amsterdam, North Holland', 'Financial Services', '1.001 - 5.000 medewerkers', '75', 'Adyen is a growth-stage financial technology company (1,001-5,000 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, operating in Australia and Singapore. The presence of multiple Tier 1 (Country Manager, General Manager) and Tier 2 (Head of Sales, VP Sales, Sales Director) decision makers provides high-level access for recruitment. While there are no current open sales roles in Sydney, recent major partnerships, product launches, and double-digit revenue growth signal ongoing expansion and future hiring needs, especially for enterprise sales and account management roles. This makes Adyen a high-priority recruitment opportunity for future core sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] In March 2025, Adyen announced a major partnership with Reece, one of Australia and New Zealand’s leading plumbing and bathroom suppliers, to process payments across 600 online and offline stores, delivering modernized, seamless, and secure customer experiences by leveraging Adyen’s Unified Commerce technology and Pay by Link capabilities[2].\n[REGIONAL] Hayley Fisher, Country Manager for Adyen Australia and New Zealand, emphasized their ongoing collaboration and focus on innovative, secure payment processes for ANZ clients[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] No open job postings were listed for the Sydney office as of September 2025, but the team continues to highlight a global, career-driven culture with strong local support—offering perks such as annual trips to the Singapore and Amsterdam offices and a focus on professional development[1].\n[GLOBAL] Adyen’s overall headcount and employee productivity have both shown strong growth, with a 15% year-over-year increase in productivity per employee in 2025, and continual investment in staff satisfaction and flexible work policies[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Adyen, already a public company, did not report new funding rounds, but achieved substantial milestones: in 2025, net income rose to €635 million (up 12% YoY) and net revenue reached €1.82 billion, marking 21% annual growth; the company remains debt-free and increased cash reserves to €4.6 billion, reinforcing investment capacity[3].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] The rollout with Reece has enhanced Adyen’s visibility and reputation in Australia, bringing innovative payment link technology, improved customer satisfaction, and enhanced fraud/risk management across a major retail footprint[2].\n[GLOBAL] In 2025, Adyen launched “Uplift,” an AI-powered payment optimization suite, boosting payment conversion and fraud prevention, and cited advanced AI adoption as a top growth driver for global and local retail clients[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Hayley Fisher is prominently acting as Country Manager for Australia and New Zealand; no significant recent executive shifts specific to the Sydney or ANZ sales teams were reported in the last 12 months[2].\n[GLOBAL] Management effectiveness continues to improve, with the board showing a greater diversity ratio (40% women and underrepresented groups) and a highly automated, agile operating model under CEO Pieter van der Does[3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;strong&gt;This is Adyen&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Adyen provides payments, data, and financial products in a single solution for customers like Meta, Uber, H&amp;amp;M, and Microsoft - making us the financial technology platform of choice. At Adyen, everything we do is engineered for ambition.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For our teams, we create an environment with opportunities for our people to succeed, backed by the culture and support to ensure they are enabled to truly own their careers. We are motivated individuals who tackle unique technical challenges at scale and solve them as a team. Together, we deliver innovative and ethical solutions that help businesses achieve their ambitions faster.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why you should join the Adyen Account Management team &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Adyen, the Account Management team is critical to the growth and success of our business, as well as expanding the Adyen brand across the globe. Being part of our Account Management team, you’ll manage relationships with innovative international merchants, covering multiple industries and channels. You’ll have the opportunity to work on cross-functional initiatives and projects in a fast-paced, highly entrepreneurial environment with high autonomy. You’ll become an expert in the global payments landscape and level up your skills through our AM Academy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a proactive and adaptable Account Manager to join our team in Sydney. The ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with a hands-on mentality; someone who is eager to help the world’s biggest brands grow while changing an industry. You are excited to work with a global, multicultural team in a collaborative manner and help your team succeed. Your focus will be on delivering an outstanding customer experience, finding new opportunities, and driving mutual success for Adyen and our customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our Account Managers are encouraged to challenge each other and sharpen ideas as a team, because winning is more important than ego. In this role, you’ll get your energy by working on a wide portfolio of accounts across a variety of verticals. You’ll work alongside a group of talented and driven Account Managers, and together, you’ll develop customer relationships and drive commercial growth for your accounts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaboration- As an Account Manager, you will work closely with other Account Managers and collaborate on many different accounts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationship management- Responsible for ramping and growing customers with a focus on commercial growth, customer satisfaction, and reducing churn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commercial acumen- Drive commercial discussions for joint accounts, while striving to meet strategic and financial targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Project management- Prioritize and manage short and long term projects with varying timelines across multiple accounts, leveraging internal support teams where relevant.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Technical acumen- Work closely with the Technical and Product teams to manage the integration of the merchant, helping to identity improvements and developments for continued innovation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Feedback- Serve as a feedback loop for your customers internally.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strategic thinker with excellent project management skills and the ability to lead and manage time-sensitive, cross-functional initiatives in a fast-paced, highly entrepreneurial environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enjoy engaging others and developing strong working relationships internally and externally with customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Passionate about working on a wide portfolio of accounts and having the opportunity to learn about many aspects of the payments industry&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eager to challenge yourself to identify commercial opportunities and drive commercial discussions with customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong time management skills and constantly looking for ways to work efficiently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A natural communicator and team player with technical interest, knowledge and understanding&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have 2+ years of experience in a client-facing, commercial role, like account management, consulting, or in the payments industry from a merchant side (bonus if in complex enterprise software, technical infrastructure or financial services)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This role is based in our Sydney office. We have a hybrid workplace and value in-person collaboration; we do not offer remote-only roles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Domestic and international travel is required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Diversity, Equity and Inclusion commitments &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our unique approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity of backgrounds and cultures is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business and technical challenges are unique, and we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. No matter who you are or where you’re from, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Studies show that women and members of underrepresented communities apply for jobs only if they meet 100% of the qualifications. Does this sound like you? If so, Adyen encourages you to reconsider and apply. We look forward to your application!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s next?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Ensuring a smooth and enjoyable candidate experience is critical for us. We aim to get back to you regarding your application within 5 business days. Our interview process tends to take about 4 weeks to complete, but may fluctuate depending on the role. Learn more about our hiring process here. Don’t be afraid to let us know if you need more flexibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is based out in our Sydney office. We are an office-first company and value in-person collaboration; we do not offer remote-only roles."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGCuaSq8TqalA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1664880076052/adyen_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=mE4gDO7jVlYdtQW5QNUHpr_Vg_UUMxnHtUmgmgE336o', '2025-09-21T14:15:58.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reclyV8qsYkSUE4XD', 'Klipboard', 'http://www.klipboard.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/weareklipboard', 'Hungerford, England', 'Software Development', '1,001-5,000 employees', '47', 'Klipboard is a growth-stage software development company (1,001-5,000 employees) with a strong global presence and recent funding, acquisitions, and product expansions indicating growth. However, there is no evidence of active sales role hiring in Australia or APAC, and the only local contacts are a Commercial Manager (Tier 2) and Operations Manager, limiting direct recruitment opportunity. The industry fit is strong (core B2B SaaS), but the absence of a specific sales role trigger or local hiring signals lowers the immediate opportunity to a medium priority.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[GLOBAL] In April 2025, **Kerridge Commercial Systems (KCS)** rebranded to **Klipboard**, continuing its focus on industry-specific, cloud-based software for sectors such as field service management, distribution, retail, rental, and manufacturing[1][2][4]. [GLOBAL] In 2024–2025, KCS made several strategic acquisitions—including RAM Tracking, Silkmoth, and Vigo Software—to expand expertise and market offerings, notably enhancing its fleet, logistics, and supply chain solutions[2]. [GLOBAL] At InfoComm 2025 (June), Klipboard (formerly Current RMS) showcased its evolution and suite for event production and audiovisual rental management, highlighting continued international market leadership[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[GLOBAL] Klipboard states it supports job management operations across three continents with over 2,700 customers, signifying global operational reach[4]. [GLOBAL] Following rebranding and acquisitions, Klipboard has expanded offerings in cloud-based digital transformation, increasing focus on market-specific solutions for logistics, rental, and field service businesses[1][2]. [GLOBAL] The company has enhanced its field service management and inventory management capabilities in the past year through acquisitions[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Klipboard raised a Pre-Series A round, bringing total funding to over $2 million (previous seed $900,000, plus new $1.1 million investment) as of the latest available data. This funding was intended to accelerate growth and product development, with participation from a Seattle-based private equity group and angel investors[2]. No AU- or APAC-specific funding was identified in the past 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[GLOBAL] Klipboard advanced to the semifinalist round of the Connecticut $5 million Global Venture Challenge in 2018[2]. [GLOBAL] CEO Draven McConville was named Freeman of the Worshipful Company of Information Technologists and joined the IIBN Board, indicating leadership recognition within the industry[2]. [GLOBAL] Product suite enhancements following multiple strategic acquisitions in 2024–2025, reinforcing Klipboard’s competitive position in field service and inventory management[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] Draven McConville continues as CEO, receiving recognition in 2024 for industry and community contributions[2]. No recent AU/Brisbane-specific leadership changes or appointments were identified.\n\n---\n\n**SCOPE NOTES:**  \n- No direct [LOCAL] or [REGIONAL] (Brisbane, QLD, or AU) intelligence was found regarding physical presence, hiring activity, or named leadership in the past 12 months. The intelligence above is all [GLOBAL], per search hierarchy.  \n- [INDUSTRY] context may be needed if operation-specific updates in Brisbane/AU are critical; however, Klipboard’s recent rebrand, funding, and product/market expansions are likely to impact its ANZ/APAC go-to-market strategies indirectly.  \n\n**INDUSTRY CONTEXT (if needed):**\n[INDUSTRY] The AU software development sector continues to see strong demand for SaaS, mobile workforce, inventory, and job management solutions, especially in logistics, distribution, and field service management verticals, aligning with Klipboard’s expanded focus post-rebranding."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"\"At Klipboard we''ve introduced a flexible hybrid work policy, where employees spend three days in the office and two days working from home. This approach promotes a balanced work environment that combines office collaboration with the comfort and convenience of remote work.\"&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Klipboard provides specialist software, services and support to deliver fully integrated trading and business management solutions to companies in the distributive trade – wherever they are in the world. With a unique depth of knowledge and experience in ERP/SaaS solutions, Klipboard has a wide range of clients includes wholesalers, distributors, merchants and retailers from small traders to multinational enterprises. Klipboard has offices in the UK, Ireland, The Netherlands, South Africa, Kenya and North America. Our mission is simple: to design and deliver high performance, integrated ERP solutions that enable our distributive trade customers to source effectively, stock efficiently, sell profitably and service competitively&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re looking for a driven and consultative Senior Sales Executive to join our growing Australasian sales team. This role is focused on winning new enterprise and mid-market customers by selling Klipboard’s OnRent Office and OnRent One rental solutions across Australia and New Zealand, with scope to introduce other Klipboard Global products where strategically aligned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will play a critical role in driving revenue by:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively generating your own leads and building a strong pipeline of qualified opportunities through outbound prospecting, networking, and market research.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working alongside the Australasian sales team to sell rental products to our prospects.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identifying opportunities to expand our reach to other Klipboard products beyond the rental sector.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;This is a senior individual contributor role (not people management) and is ideal for someone who thrives in a solution-led sales environment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Business Development&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Own the full sales cycle from lead generation through to contract close and onboarding, with a strong focus on acquiring new enterprise customers in the rental and adjacent sectors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Client Engagement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Build strong relationships with key stakeholders to understand their business needs and position rental solutions as a key enabler for new customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Execution&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Manage the full sales cycle from discovery to full ramp up for new opportunities across Australia and NZ.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative Selling&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Apply deep industry understanding to design solutions that address operational, compliance, and profitability challenges unique to the equipment hire and rental industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Territory Planning &amp;amp; Account Strategy&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Develop and execute strategic territory plans to prioritise high-value targets and verticals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Segment the market and tailor outreach strategies to different customer profiles.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pipeline Management &amp;amp; Forecasting&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of pipeline activity in CRM.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Provide regular sales forecasts and performance updates to leadership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive Intelligence&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Monitor competitor offerings and market trends to position Klipboard’s solutions effectively.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Share insights with product and marketing teams to refine positioning.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proposal &amp;amp; Tender Management&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Lead the preparation of proposals, RFPs, and tender responses for enterprise deals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Collaborate with legal and finance teams to ensure commercial terms are aligned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills, Knowledge And Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;7+ years of B2B sales experience, with a strong track record in SaaS, ERP, fintech, or other enterprise software solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success in new business development and negotiation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of operational management in capital intensive sectors, workflows and contract management, and financial software within ERP environments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communicator, comfortable engaging stakeholders at all levels including C-suite.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly self-motivated with the ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success managing sales cycles of 6–18 months involving complex stakeholder environments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with sales tools like Salesforce, HubSpot, or equivalent CRM platforms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prior experience selling into the rental sector is highly advantageous.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Info&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You may also have seen from our recent posts that we are excited to begin sharing our new company name – Klipboard. Kerridge Commercial Systems (KCS) is becoming Klipboard and our new brand is designed to bring together our expertise across distribution, automotive, retail, rental, transport management, manufacturing, and field service management. We have offices based across the world and we are looking for talented individuals to join our growing teams. Due to our growth over the last few years it is an exciting time to join us as we enter our next chapter! At Klipboard we''ve introduced a flexible hybrid work policy, where employees spend three days in the office and two days working from home. This approach promotes a balanced work environment that combines office collaboration with the comfort and convenience of remote work.\"&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equal Opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a global company, we value and respect the diversity of our workforce, aiming to empower everyone to embrace each other''s differences. We are committed to creating an inclusive workplace where diversity, equity, and inclusion are integral to our company and culture. We recognize the benefits of a diverse workforce, where creativity and valuing differences enable us all to thrive and sparks innovation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you require any help, adjustments and/or support during the interview and offer process then please advise our TA or HR team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Research shows that women and other underrepresented groups are less likely to apply for a role unless they meet every listed requirement. However, we recognise that skills and experience come in many forms, and we encourage you to apply even if you don’t meet every criterion. If you are passionate about this role and believe you have the right mindset and transferrable skills, we would love to hear from you!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To all recruitment agencies: Klipboard does not accept agency speculative resumes. At present we only accept CV’s from Agencies on our PSL who have been assigned specific position/s. Please do not forward resumes to our careers site or direct to Klipboard employee as this does not constitute an introduction and Klipboard retrospectively will not be liable for any candidate ownership or fees related to unsolicited resumes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQGSM5sutnSG2Q/company-logo_200_200/B4DZYUNihjG8AQ-/0/1744095816515/weareklipboard_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=8v2OHN5P8QZptDgSr_IslvkvLsWn1fDSi3vTQ20ZKKs', '2025-09-28T04:03:03.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recmB7pcGDaG5JZ4Y', 'Trustwave', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, true, false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-09-28T14:29:59.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recmVkiPqezjsY989', 'FoodByUs', 'http://www.foodbyus.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/foodbyus-pty-ltd', 'Surry Hills, New South Wales, AU', 'Hospitality', '51 - 200', '54', 'FoodByUs is a growth-stage hospitality technology company (61 employees) currently featuring multiple Area Sales Managers and a Territory Sales Manager, indicating ongoing focus on sales roles. The industry is an acceptable fit (wholesale ordering platform for hospitality), but not core commercial B2B tech. The presence of a Head of People & Talent (Tier 3 decision maker) provides some recruitment access, but no Tier 1 or 2 sales leadership is visible. Recent partnership with Square and strong customer case studies suggest moderate growth, though no recent funding or explicit sales hiring surge is noted. This represents a medium-priority recruitment opportunity for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nFoodByUs partnered with Square to offer a bundled solution combining POS and smart ordering technology, enabling new venue operators to save up to $6,000 on food orders as of January 2025. The partnership targets hospitality businesses opening or expanding in 2025 amid rising costs and ongoing staff shortages.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nFoodByUs continues to be promoted as Australiaâs leading wholesale ordering platform, reporting usage by thousands of venues nationwide and highlighting case studies with major hospitality groups throughout 2024 and 2025. No explicit headcount or hiring growth data for sales or GTM roles identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo new funding rounds or financial milestones were identified within the last 6-12 months. The most recent known funding was a $10M Series A round led by Macquarie Capital and Base Capital prior to this period.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nFoodByUs showcased transformative results for customers such as Suburban Dining & Rooftop, reporting a 67% increase in operational efficiency via their ordering platform in early 2025. Multiple case studies published in 2024â2025 illustrate significant impacts on business process efficiency for notable clients including Red Rock Venues and Canvaâs Hospitality Experience team.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people leadership roles were identified within the last 6-12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"FoodByUs for wholesale is Australia''s #1 wholesale food market place, saving food service venues 15% on their food costs.\n\nWe''re an all-inclusive, dedicated system for cafes, hotels, bars, pubs & clubs to source all their wholesale food supplies, cut costs, improve cash flow and streamline their procurement processes. We offer a range of categories, from fruit and veg, to meat and poultry, to alcohol, packaging and much more! \n\nWorking with the very best local Aussie food suppliers, we negotiate market leading pricing that we pass back on to our customers. We help foodservice venues to save time and money with our ordering solution. With FoodByUs, you also get a dedicated account manager. So whether you need help sourcing a product, getting better pricing, or require an even more customised ordering experience, we''re there to help you along the way. \n\nFor Suppliers, we''re a fantastic channel to market via an innovative online marketplace, backed up by a dedicated sales and support team. Enjoy receiving orders from our growing number of venues direct into your mailbox or order management software. We offer: flexible payment options for Buyers and can collect money prior to fulfilment, transparent and powerful reporting tools, a network of speedy drivers with sophisticated tools for route optimisation and direct-to-customer marketing opportunities."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recmdYR38yOikxsOK', 'Multiplier', 'https://www.usemultiplier.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/usemultiplier', 'New York, , US', 'Human Resources', '201 - 500', '84', 'Multiplier is a growth-stage SaaS/HR Tech company (1,042 employees) actively hiring for Business Development Representative roles, a primary target for 4Twenty. The industry fit is strong, with a commercial B2B SaaS model and significant growth signals including a major rebrand, measurable pipeline and deal size increases, and international expansion. Decision maker access is excellent, with a VP Sales, APAC and Sales Team Leader APAC present (Tier 1 and Tier 2). While there is no recent funding, the robust growth indicators and ideal sales role make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nMultiplier completed a major global rebrand in 2024 that has driven significant business impact, with the company preparing for HR Tech 2025 in Las Vegas (September 16-18, 2025) to showcase their \"World Without Limits\" vision through an immersive brand experience. The company launched Beyond Borders: New York video series in August 2025 to address the global talent shortage affecting 74% of employers worldwide.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nThe 2024 rebrand resulted in measurable growth indicators including 70% increase in organic traffic, 30% increase in non-paid pipeline, and 25% increase in average deal size. Multiplier has expanded to serve over 2,000 organizations across 150 countries, with social engagement increasing by 350% and share of voice in the EOR category rising by 30%.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nMultiplier received Honorable Mention in Fast Company''s 2025 Innovation by Design Awards in the Mid-sized Business category, announced September 15, 2025. The company was named an EOR Leader by both IEC and Everest following their successful rebrand, and returned to HR Tech Asia 2025 for the third consecutive year.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nKey leadership team includes CEO & Co-founder Sagar Khatri, Co-founder Amritpal Singh, CMO Monish Munshi, CRO Matthew Carr, and Senior Director of Brand & Creative Alessandro Giua, with no recent changes identified in the search results."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Multiplier, weâre creating a world without limits, where hiring, managing, and paying your global team is beautifully simple.\n\nOur industry-leading global HR platform enables companies to expand their teams across 150+ countries, without having to set up local entities. \n\nFrom employment to contractor solutions, Global Payroll and HRIS, we deliver unmatched compliance, speed, and control every step of the way.\n\nWhether you''re a scaling startup or a large enterprise expanding across markets, Multiplier is your partner in global growth â combining cutting-edge tech with 24/7 human-first customer support.\n\nJoin the thousands of businesses using Multiplier to streamline HR processes and access a world of opportunity.\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recn9PUsH1AQdtdon', 'Glean', 'https://glean-it.com/glean', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/gleanwork', 'Palo Alto, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '77', 'Glean is a growth-stage computer software (SaaS) company with 1,260 employees and recent major funding rounds, strong product launches, and significant revenue growth, indicating robust expansion. The presence of a Regional Vice President, APJ (Tier 1 decision maker), and a Regional Partner Manager - ANZ provides strong access for recruitment in Australia. However, the sales role triggering inclusion is ''Regional Partner Manager,'' which is a lower-priority sales support/partnership role (5 points), and there are no explicit Australia-specific sales hiring or expansion signals. This results in a high, but not very high, recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nGlean rolled out its Glean Agents offering in early 2025, enabling businesses to automate operations and aiming to support 1 billion agent actions by end of 2025. The company hosted its inaugural Glean:GO 2025 event in San Francisco, launching major new features and integrations in May 2025[1][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nGlean surpassed $100 million in annual recurring revenue in its last fiscal year and continues to rapidly expand its platform with 40+ new features and deeper infrastructure partnerships in 2025. No specific Australia-related hiring or sales expansion signals identified[1][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nGlean completed a $150 million Series F round in June 2025, led by Wellington Management, raising its valuation to $7.2 billion. The company previously raised $260 million in a September 2024 Series E, and $200 million in February 2024 Series D[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nGlean was named to CNBC’s top 50 disruptors list in 2025 and unveiled a no-code Agent Builder, broad new agent capabilities, Glean Protect for enterprise compliance, and expanded integrations during Glean:GO 2025 in May 2025[2][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes or new executive appointments, especially in sales, revenue, or people roles, have been identified in the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Work AI for all. \n\nThe Work AI platform connected to all your data. Find, create, and automate anything."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQH8sZuW2WzLDQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1647448995044/gleanwork_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=GJkiwJRT9hyKRh-iIhYBq3GhJ-0hyfZAEPuYZx-rT-0', '2025-09-18T20:55:46.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recnFGJHbjQVNsHYS', 'Gumtree Group', 'https://www.gumtree.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/gumtreegroup', 'Sydney, New South Wales, AU', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '64', 'Gumtree Group is a growth-stage computer software company (227 employees) in Australia, actively employing for roles such as Inside Sales Manager, Sales Manager, Regional Sales Manager, and Business Development Manager, indicating ongoing commercial hiring needs. The industry fit is strong (core B2B tech/marketplace), and the company size is ideal for external recruitment. Decision maker access includes multiple Tier 2 (Sales Manager, Regional Sales Manager) and Tier 3 (Director) contacts, supporting recruitment engagement. Growth signals are moderate, with recent partnerships, expansion, and platform focus, but no recent funding or major leadership changes. The mix of sales roles (medium to high priority) and moderate growth context make this a medium-priority opportunity for recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn September 2024, Gumtree UK was quietly sold to Asian private equity firm Ocean Link and its portfolio company 58.com, reflecting a shift in ownership structure. In October 2024, Gumtree Australia sold its capital markets businesses HotCopper and Stockhouse to UK-based ADVFN for $6.8 million, with plans to focus on core marketplaces such as Motors, Pets, Jobs, and Real Estate going forward.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nGumtree South Africa reported increased interest from potential employees after becoming fully locally owned in late 2022, allowing budget expansion for hiring and supporting job market growth. Recent statements highlight Gumtree''s ongoing team expansion in South Africa as it localizes operations and directs more resources toward platform innovation.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn May 2024, Gumtree Australia secured a content sharing agreement with NZME to take its CarsGuide brand into New Zealand. Gumtree Group also entered a strategic partnership with AdFixus in October 2024 to enhance its digital advertising capabilities across all marketplace properties.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Gumtree Group, weâre building for the future with a fresh approach. From the beginning, weâve been committed to growing a vibrant community that people love to be part of. A community thatâs safe. Reliable. Easy. Our difference resonated with millions, launching us into a household name.\n\nIn 2020, our role in Australiaâs trading landscape was further cemented when Gumtree joined forces with CarsGuide and Autotrader. As a powerful network of three iconic brands, weâre driving impact at scale and reaching more people at all of lifeâs important moments and milestones.\n\nToday, we connect people as they buy, sell and transact across more than two million live listings. We reach one in three Australians each and every month and see a whopping $3+ billion in monthly gross listing volume. \n\nItâs the kind of success that ties directly into what we stand for. We aim to be the ultimate destination for anyone looking for an awesome deal, perfect find or new opportunity. Our expert insights and resources help people compare their options, be informed and make confident purchases they can feel good about. And weâre proud to contribute to a more sustainable way of living by playing a core role in the Australian Circular Economy.\n\nBut our greatest superpower is our people. Weâre a smart bunch of problem-solvers who use the latest technologies to reimagine better ways to participate on our platforms. Our diversity brings unique perspectives to all we do, boosting our creativity and helping us tackle complex, real-world challenges.\n\nEvery day is a new opportunity to achieve more than you can imagine. Itâs an exciting time to be a part of our transformation and growth as an Australian-listed and operated company (part of ASX:GUM).\n\nGumtree Group. A world of opportunity awaits you."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recnNvShVkgZob9fa', 'Verkada', 'https://www.verkada.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/verkada', 'San Mateo, California, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '80', 'Verkada is a growth-stage computer software company (2,524 employees) with active hiring for Account Executive and Enterprise Account Executive roles, both high-priority core sales positions. The company operates in commercial B2B tech (SaaS/cloud security), and has a strong presence in Australia and Singapore. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are accessible, including Regional Directors, VPs, and Sales Managers. Recent growth signals include leadership appointments, market expansion in APAC, and continued sales hiring, indicating ongoing recruitment needs. While Verkada has an internal sales recruiting manager, the scale and pace of expansion suggest a strong likelihood to use external recruitment for sales talent.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nOn August 30, 2024, the FTC levied a record $2.95 million fine against Verkada for data security failures and CAN-SPAM violations, requiring new security protocols and regular third-party audits. Verkada also announced a strategic partnership with LG CNS in July 2024 to expand delivery of physical security solutions and continued rapid market expansion in EMEA and Asia-Pacific throughout 2024.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nVerkada reported surpassing 25,000 global customers in July 2024, indicating accelerated cloud adoption and market reach. The company made multiple strategic hires and leadership appointments in EMEA and JAPAC, and continued posting new sales/enterprise-focused roles, suggesting ongoing headcount and go-to-market expansion.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nVerkadaâs History Player Search was named Security Today''s 2025 New Product of the Year Award Winner in September 2025 for AI and Video Analytics. The company achieved FedRAMP Ready status in July 2024 and won a Red Dot Design Award for multiple products in May 2024.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nEric Salava was appointed Chief Revenue Officer on April 3, 2024, while Ardon Anderson was named Vice President of EMEA in May 2024. Marc Peston was selected as GM of Northern Europe in November 2024, and new marketing leadership joined in January 2024."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Verkada is a pioneer in cloud-managed physical security, helping organizations operate smarter, safer buildings. \n\nDesigned with simplicity in mind, Verkada''s six product lines â video security cameras, access control, environmental sensors, alarms, workplace, and intercoms â provide unparalleled building security through an integrated, cloud-based software platform. More than 33,000 organizations across 93 countries worldwide, including 91 companies in the Fortune 500, trust Verkada as their physical security layer for easier management, intelligent control, and scalable deployments. \n\nVerkada has raised more than $700M in funding to-date from General Catalyst, Sequoia Capital, Felicis Ventures, Next47, Meritech, First Round Capital, Linse Capital, Eclipse, and others."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recnYQscvK2WX27U7', 'eTeam', 'http://www.eteaminc.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/eteam', 'Somerset, New Jersey, US', 'Staffing & Recruiting', '501 - 1000', '55', 'eTeam operates in the staffing and recruiting industry, which is excluded from our target sectors. Despite a large employee base and presence in Singapore and Australia, their core business is direct competition and not a fit for external recruitment partnerships. No score is assigned due to automatic exclusion.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\neTeam announced the acquisition of assets from Sirius Solutions in February 2025 to enhance business and technology transformation capabilities through an SOW-based model. The acquisition is effective immediately and expands eTeamâs service offerings to include transformation and advisory services[1][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent direct data was found on large-scale hiring or GTM team expansion, but leadership communications and new service lines suggest a focus on scaling technology-enabled workforce solutions and global service reach[2][5].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\neTeam formed a strategic partnership with Elements Talent Consultancy Ltd in July 2024 to further strengthen global talent solutions; the company highlighted ongoing innovation in staffing technology and participation in key industry events such as the CWS Summit North America 2024[3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes, executive hires, or departures identified in the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"eTeam is a global leader in tech-first staffing and recruiting solutions that''s voted among the Top 100 Staffing Firms in North America by SIA.\n \nIncorporated in 1999 as a Minority Business Enterprise with a keen focus on diversity hiring, eTeam provides high-volume staffing, SOW, contract-to-hire, direct placement, and payroll solutions to Fortune 1000