    ('recorMHRpubDgnVln', 'Vertice', 'https://eu1.hubs.ly/H01VJC70', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/verticeone', 'London, England, GB', 'Computer Software', '201 - 500', '100', 'Vertice is a high-growth computer software company with recent $50 million Series C funding, aggressive global expansion plans, and a focus on scaling GTM teams. The presence of a Vice President of Sales APAC in Australia provides direct Tier 2 decision maker access. Multiple strong growth signals and core industry alignment indicate an immediate and high-probability opportunity for recruitment services, especially for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nVertice announced a â¬47.9 million ($50 million) Series C funding round in January 2025, aiming to open new regional offices and triple its engineering team for expanded product development. The company continues to scale globally and has been entrusted with over $3.4 billion in SaaS and cloud expenditure management for enterprise clients.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nVerticeâs global headcount has reached 250, with notable expansion in engineering and regional office openings planned for 2025. The company has grown revenue 13x over the past two years and is focused on scaling GTM teams to support increasing enterprise demand.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nVertice completed a $50 million Series C round in January 2025 led by Lakestar, with participation from Perpetual Growth, CF Private Equity, Bessemer Venture Partners, and 83North, bringing total funds raised to over $100 million and estimated company valuation to $500 million.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nVertice was named the fastest-growing startup in the UK in 2025 by Sifted and has established partnerships with major clients such as ASML, Euronext, Grant Thornton, and Santander. The platform has achieved significant traction by processing over â¬3.2 billion in procurement spend and integrating new AI-driven product features to streamline enterprise purchasing.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Vertice is a spend optimization platform that saves companies 20% on their SaaS and cloud costs.\n\nIt empowers companies of every size and industry to get more visibility and control of their procurement spend and leverages automation and machine learning to deliver guaranteed cost savings and streamlined processes.\n\nToday, Vertice manages over $10B in contract spend and is the only platform worldwide that empowers companies to view, control, and save on both SaaS and cloud costs, whilst simplifying their procurement with an integrated unified offering."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recpddOtKfhJOtJc3', 'Sitemate', 'https://sitemate.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/sitemate-technologies', 'Sydney, NSW', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '51-200 employees', '100', 'Sitemate is a growth-stage B2B technology company (SaaS/workflow automation) with 51-200 employees, actively hiring for Senior Inbound Sales Development Representative and multiple Account Executive roles. The company operates in Australia with strong commercial tech fit and is experiencing rapid growth, evidenced by recent Series A funding, international expansion, and a doubling of GTM headcount. Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (General Manager, Directors of GTM, Sales Leaders) are present, providing direct access for recruitment. Multiple strong growth signals and high-priority sales roles make this an exceptional recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Sitemate, headquartered in Sydney, raised a significant $27.5 million Series A round in August 2024, led by Blackbird Ventures, to further accelerate product and engineering growth, expand the customer base, and scale presence locally and internationally[1][2].  \n[LOCAL] In early 2024, Sitemate acquired Nomad Fleet (now rebranded as Gearbelt), strengthening its asset management capabilities for the built world sector[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Announced plans to open an Austin, Texas office in 2025 as part of international expansion, adding to existing offices in London, Vancouver, and Toronto[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Sitemate doubled its headcount in the last 12 months, growing from 70 to 140 employees, including dedicated go-to-market (GTM) teams in Sydney[1].  \n[REGIONAL] Committed to doubling GTM teams in Oceania (including Australia and New Zealand), Europe, and North America through 2024, with hiring focused on commercial/sales/market-facing roles[3].  \n[LOCAL] Continues to actively support over 2,000 customers across infrastructure, construction, energy, and utilities, with major accounts such as Transgrid, Siemens Energy, and John Holland in Australia[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL] Raised $7.5M in a Pre-Series A round in November 2023, bringing in Marbruck Investments alongside repeat support from Blackbird Ventures and Artesian[3].  \n[GLOBAL] Completed the $27.5M Series A in August 2024, valifying the company above $150 million; funding earmarked for product/platform innovation and international expansion[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Launched the Flowsite Integrations Cloud in November 2023, Australia’s first dedicated no-code integration and automation platform for the built world, with integrations including Xero and PowerBI[3].  \n[GLOBAL] The acquisition and integration of Gearbelt expanded Sitemate’s asset management offerings globally[1].  \n[LOCAL] Achieved consistent monthly growth for six years; growth rate in Australia continues to accelerate[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] Company co-founders Hartley Pike (CEO) and Sam McDonnell (VP Product Strategy) remain in key leadership roles; no major Sydney-specific executive appointments or departures noted in the past year[1][3].  \n\n[INDUSTRY]  \nAustralia’s technology sector, especially no-code and workflow automation platforms for industrial/construction, continues rapid digitization, with significant VC investment and preference for fit-for-purpose tools serving regulated, compliance-heavy industries[1][3]. Sitemate’s product-led model caters to a sector-wide trend towards domain-specific digital transformation, outpacing more horizontal software platforms."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Thanks for stopping by and learning more about this role at Sitemate! ✨🏗️&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’d love to hear from you 👩💻👩🏽💻🧑🏿💻👨🏻💻&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief Overview Of This Role At Sitemate&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for an Inbound Sales Development Representative (SDR) to join our Sydney team, to help accelerate our growth in the Oceania region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Sales Development Representative is responsible for qualifying and routing inbound leads across three channels: self-service and inside sales. This role involves frequent engagement with prospects through phone calls, emails, live chat, and internal tools such as Slack and Salesforce. Success in the role is measured by the number of product demonstrations booked and completed, with a strong track record of team performance consistently meeting or exceeding monthly targets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🔧 Day-to-Day&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will be qualifying and routing inbound leads through two channels; self service &amp;amp; inside sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll be spending most of your time with prospects across phone calls, emails and live chat on our website, as well as internal tools like slack and salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Your quota is measured by the number of demonstrations booked and completed at the subsequent stage of the process. Our current team in this role have achieved &amp;gt;=95% of their targets each month since starting&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⚡ Challenges&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learning about the built world if you haven’t had any exposure to it - there are a lot of different types of companies and plenty of new terminologies to learn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Up-skilling your call/phone and email skills - although we have plenty of examples for you to learn from during your onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding SaaS financial acronyms and common terminology - if you have not worked in a SaaS company before, there is going to be a lot of metrics to learn. This cheat sheet is a good resource: The Ultimate SaaS Acronyms Cheat Sheet&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We move very quickly, so you’ll need to be excited to come in and learn extremely fast.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✅ Who This Role Is For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ambitious individuals wanting to pursue a career in SaaS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;People who thrive in a structured, high-agency, KPI-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communicators who enjoy building relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilient individuals who can persevere and perform with high-volume tasks&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚫 Who This Role is &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Those unwilling to handle rejection frequently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;People uncomfortable with people and conversations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Tools&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must Have:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confident and clear communication skills, with excellent writing and presentation skills over email, phone, video conferencing and in-person.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent task organisation and prioritisation skills, you’re able to multi-task efficiently.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice To Have&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with modern tooling - CRMs, Health Scoring, Live chat, Knowledge bases.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience conducting customer meetings digitally (e.g. Zoom/Teams) and/or physically (in person/face to face with customers).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Patience working in an industry where not all users are tech-savvy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why should I consider joining Sitemate?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Check out Sitemate’s team at the offsite: Sitemate Offsite 2022, Sitemate Offsite 2023 &amp;amp; recently Sitemate Offsite 2024&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You can see what people really think about working at Sitemate here: Working at Sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2024 Podcast: CEO Hartley Pike on his personal journey, scaling Sitemate, diversity and culture at sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2023 Podcast: Listen to CMO Lance Hodgson’s tips on how to supercharge your career&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2022 Podcast: Listen to CEO Hartley Pike speak about the company’s founding and broader Go To Market strategy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2022 Podcast: Listen to CTO Tim Bray speak about building high quality features that solve customer problems at Sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We have equal opportunity for applicants of all genders, ethnicities, ages, sexualities &amp;amp; people with disabilities - Sitemate''s team is proudly diverse and accessible. 55% of our team identify as coming from underrepresented ethnic backgrounds. 43% identify as female. Our team ranges in age from 22 to 51 years old.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We''re proud to have a global team with team members from Australia, Kenya, Brazil, France, Chile, United Kingdom, Ireland, Spain, Portugal, Vietnam, the Philippines, Kazakhstan, USA, Canada, Indonesia, Venezuela, Sri Lanka, and Uruguay.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Our office has fantastic on-site facilities including a rooftop garden, wellness centre, showers and cycle storage. The transport connections are excellent. Every Monday, the team enjoys a catered lunch together from one of the many nearby options.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will be remunerated based on your performance. If you are performing well, you won’t need to wait 3 years or have to find better offers elsewhere to receive an increase to your remuneration. 7 out of the last 10 remuneration increases for Sitemate team members have been made pro-actively by management, without the individual needing to even raise the topic of remuneration.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get a laptop and a budget to set up your home office.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have visibility into the standardised career development plan for your role, and access to a professional learning and development budget.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get additional benefits and support as parents - with paid leave for both primary (min. 16 weeks) and secondary carers (min. 6 weeks) including adoption, as well as support and leave for the tragic circumstances of stillbirth or miscarriage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have 20 days PTO, as well as paid compassionate &amp;amp; bereavement leave, sick &amp;amp; carer’s leave, and the ability to work from anywhere for a few weeks per year.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get equity options and ownership in Sitemate on a standard vesting schedule. See here for a general overview of how this works.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate has grown from 5 employees in 2018 to 150+, and we’re moving into the next stage of growth! We have a product that customers are strongly engaged with, and every month we get 1000s of new leads in our core/target regions with 0 cold calling and limited marketing spend (made possible by strong word-of-mouth and organic marketing efforts).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate’s founders have diverse backgrounds - one coming from engineering on major infrastructure projects; the second coming from product and graphic design. This brings a unique perspective internally where we blend deep industry experience with a passion (obsession) for modern best practices in product design.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate graduated from Australia’s #1 Technology Company Accelerator - Startmate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate has strong financial backing from Blackbird (Australia and NZ’s #1 Vc), Shearwater Growth Capital &amp;amp; Marbruck Investments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;See info on our latest raise here.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the working environment like at Sitemate?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are very transparent - monthly Allhands meetings provide the team with direct insight into team updates, customer stories, hiring plans and key metrics (NPS, Revenue, Financial Performance). During this Allhands meeting we also hear one ‘life story’ from one of our team each month - learning about different countries and cultures around the world.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We place an extremely high value on your time - you won’t be spending your days wasting time on fighting internal systems, botched together spreadsheet processes or doing data entry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We use best in class systems that are seamlessly integrated to deliver our team the right information at the right time, allowing them to get their work done efficiently and to a very high standard.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have a core and close team around you, but you will also be exposed to and working directly with multiple departments - engineering, product, design, marketing, sales and customer success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have a high degree of autonomy, as the focus is on outcomes and not hours. If you want to block off a few hours to run a personal errand or block off an hour to pick up the kids from school - no worries. No one will be monitoring your time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are constantly working to minimise the number of group meetings - daily check ins are all done asynchronously (in your own time) each morning. But spontaneous 1:1s or small sessions are strongly encouraged!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does Sitemate do, exactly?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate builds best in class software products for the built world.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Industrial companies operating in the built world are facing a number of mission critical challenges - changes in work behaviour as Generation Z start to enter the workforce as mobile first users of software, and the drastic shift away from traditional mining to renewable energy projects such as wind farms and solar farms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Our first product - Dashpivot, is a platform where industrial style companies streamline and standardise their processes in a new digital format. This new digital format enables them to complete and track work in the field on a mobile or tablet, and automate repetitive tasks and tracking through automated workflows and real-time analytics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See Some Of Our User Reviews For Dashpivot Here&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;G2 Crowd&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trust Radius&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE Note&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you go on our website and enter your email, you will become a lead in our CRM. To avoid this, you can watch videos directly here&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We do not use recruitment partners or services, so please save your time and don''t reach out&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Compensation Range: A$75K - A$110K&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQHu6tRma5JtHg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630667954956/sitemate_technologies_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=m-6_obs6mLTvq1Clbdbr6Obqiar1G1Ur2PdKnqhKsk4', '2025-09-20T06:18:00.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recpnLH09GkMZeggI', 'PROLIM Australia & New Zealand', 'http://www.prolim.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/prolimtechnologies', 'Melbourne, Vic, AU', 'Computer Software', '11 - 50', '54', 'PROLIM Australia & New Zealand is a small (16 employees) computer software company in growth mode following its acquisition of Edge PLM and expansion into ANZ, but there is no explicit sales/GTM hiring activity identified for the region. The presence of a Senior Vice President ANZ (Tier 1 decision maker) and a Business Development Manager (Tier 2) provides quality access for recruitment discussions. The industry fit is strong (core commercial B2B tech), but the lack of current sales role postings and only moderate growth signals in ANZ reduce the immediate recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nPROLIM expanded into Australia and New Zealand through the acquisition of Edge PLM, announced via press release in early 2025. The move aims to deliver turnkey Industry 4.0 solutions to the ANZ region[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nPROLIM reported a global headcount of 600+ professionals in June 2025 and emphasized ongoing expansion in the Asia Pacific region, including Australia and New Zealand, following its acquisition strategy[2]. No specific sales/GTM hiring activity for ANZ was identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nPROLIM celebrated its 20th anniversary in June 2025, reaching 1,700+ customers and winning more than 40 industry awards globally[2]. PROLIM Government Technologies ranked #1525 on the Inc. 5000 list in August 2025, reflecting strong growth, though this is a subsidiary milestone[4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes specific to Australia & New Zealand identified. Nathan Rajen was appointed Chief Technology Officer in early 2025 and Ashwini Patil received recognition for technological leadership, but these relate to global operations[3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"PROLIM Australia and New Zealand is a global leading provider of PLM solutions, services and services. As a leading Siemens Expert Partner in our region, our solutions include Solid Edge, NX CAD, NX CAM,TeamCenter, SimCenter, Mendix and Diaspora Data Migration.\n\nWith 9 global offices in US, India, and Australia, Prolim has won over 30 awards and proudly serves over 1200 customers to innovate and improve their profitability and efficiency.\n"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T14:34:09.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recqFq67awc5jagTg', 'HelloTeams', 'https://helloteams.global/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/helloteamsapp', 'Melbourne, VIC, AU', 'Telecommunications', '2 - 10', '75', 'HelloTeams operates in telecommunications with a strong technology focus, recently achieving Microsoft-certified Operator Connect provider status and planning global expansion, both clear growth signals. The presence of a Global Sales Director and Business Development Executive indicates established sales leadership and decision maker access. While there is no recent funding, the companyâs industry achievements and expansion plans suggest a high likelihood of external recruitment needs for sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn May 2025, HelloTeams became a Microsoft-certified Operator Connect provider, joining a select group of around 50 global companies with this recognition. The company also announced planned expansions into the US, UK, Asia, and Europe to broaden access to its VoIP and Teams Calling services.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHelloTeams currently serves customers in 19 regions globally and has publicly indicated upcoming geographic expansion plans. The company emphasizes automation technology and low-cost transitions, suggesting ongoing market and likely headcount growth focused on delivering scalable solutions.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nHelloTeams achieved Microsoft-certified Operator Connect provider status in May 2025, a notable industry milestone. Its appearance high on the 2023 Inc 5000 list highlights recent business growth.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"HelloTeams is a Microsoft Teams Phone provider. We empower businesses around the world to connect and deploy Teams Calling in 15 minutes with our smart automation technology, valuable support, and competitive call rates. Founded in 2021 and headquartered in Australia with additional offices  around the world our mission is to challenge the status quo of the telco industry and put solutions in the hands of every customer. "}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recqeWEFD5B71KLhZ', 'Abnormal AI', 'https://abnormal.ai/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/abnormal-ai', 'Las Vegas, Nevada', 'Computer and Network Security', '1,001-5,000 employees', '83', 'Abnormal AI is a growth-stage computer and network security company (1,001-5,000 employees) actively hiring for core sales roles such as Account Executive, Enterprise Account Manager, and Regional Sales Manager in Australia and Singapore, indicating strong commercial expansion in APAC. The industry fit is strong (cybersecurity/AI SaaS), and the presence of Tier 1 (VP APJ, Regional Director) and Tier 2 (Regional Sales Manager, Enterprise Account Director) decision makers provides high-level access for recruitment engagement. Recent partnership with Singapore EDB, APAC market expansion, and new product launches are strong growth signals, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity despite no recent public funding and limited direct evidence of Australian operations expansion.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[REGIONAL] In April 2024, **Abnormal AI (Abnormal Security)** announced a strategic partnership with the Singapore Economic Development Board aimed at rapidly expanding AI engineering and cybersecurity capabilities across the ASEAN region, with Singapore as a growth hub to support broader APAC ambitions[1].  \n[GLOBAL] 2024 saw Abnormal Security advancing its detection capabilities and product suite, responding to a sharp increase in advanced threat campaigns, including multi-factor authentication bypass and novel phishing attack vectors[2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[REGIONAL] As part of the Singapore partnership, Abnormal is ramping up **AI engineering hiring** and developing internship programs in Southeast Asia to cultivate and secure technical talent in the cybersecurity and AI space[1].  \n[GLOBAL] The company continues to expand its distributed workforce model and maintains global operations, including dedicated APAC functions out of Singapore and remote roles to support regional and global growth[3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] There is no confirmed public funding round in the past 6-12 months, but the company''s recent milestones, regional expansion, and engineering investment suggest **ongoing financial health and strategic backing** (inference, based on company activity)[1][2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[REGIONAL] Established a **strategic presence in Singapore** in partnership with EDB in April 2024 to amplify R&D and deliver next-generation AI-powered email and SaaS security across the APAC market[1].  \n[GLOBAL] Launched new AI-driven security features and expanded platform capabilities in 2024, leading to significant customer base growth and industry leadership within advanced cloud and email security[2][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[GLOBAL] No specific APAC or Australia-focused senior appointments were reported in public results for the past year; executive leadership and innovation strategy remain anchored at global headquarters in San Francisco[3]. However, the regional expansion effort likely includes **new engineering and GTM roles** (go-to-market) in Singapore and surrounding regions[1].\n\n**Scope limitations:**  \n- [LOCAL] No public sources reference a physical office or major operations in Las Vegas, Nevada as of September 2025; the company''s principal headquarters and executive leadership reside in San Francisco, with APAC growth anchored out of Singapore[3].\n- [REGIONAL] Expansion in Asia is confirmed and ongoing, with a strategic, talent-driven focus via Singapore, but no direct evidence identified for Australia/Australian-specific operations in the last 12 months.\n- [GLOBAL] The company is scaling aggressively powered by AI/ML, targeting global enterprise customers with a distributed operations model and a focus on behavioral-based threat detection across email and SaaS ecosystems[3][4].\n\n**Industry context:**  \n[INDUSTRY] Demand for **AI-powered, cloud-native email and SaaS security** continues to surge across APAC and globally, driven by a 50-350% year-on-year increase in sophisticated cyberattacks, which motivates enterprises to seek advanced behavioral anomaly detection solutions like those provided by Abnormal AI[2][4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"About The RoleAbnormal AI is looking for a Mid-Market Account Executive to join our Sales org. The Mid-Market sales team is responsible for bringing new, small to medium-sized business into Abnormal’s portfolio of customers. This is a full-cycle sales role, working the deal cycle from prospect to close for accounts located in your territory (VIC / SA). The ideal candidate will have a hunter mentality, experience in & a passion for cybersecurity, team selling experience, and be ready to hit the ground running.What you will doSell Abnormal security solutions to your defined territory (Victoria, South Australia) with the goal to overachieve new annual recurring revenue quota.Work Mid Market accounts (<3k mailbox organizations) from initial conversations through signing a contract and up-selling once they’re a customer.Prospect and generate new business opportunities with Mid Market accounts (<3k mailbox organizations) to supply enough pipeline for them to hit sales targets.Work with Customer Success to ensure a timely renewal and expansion sale opportunities.Be a voice for the customer/prospect with internal teams including Sales Engineering/POV team, Product and Marketing to ensure appropriate prioritization to close more revenue.Must Haves Ability to hunt: a disciplined approach to early pipeline development.Comfortable and have demonstrated ability to prospect into Mid-Market accounts with the ability to leverage/ balance the pillars of demand generation: AE prospecting, Marketing, Channel, and Customer referrals.Located in Melbourne (preferred)Good qualifier: Ability to uncover/discover customer problems and painsGood presenter: the ability to present and demonstrate value based off customer pain points.Disciplined in sales methodology / time management: Ability to systematically execute a disciplined sales process that can be repeated in parallel without sacrificing qualityAbility to develop and present a business case to a customer showing high ROI across different dimensions to multiple stakeholdersAbility to extract, document and organize lessons, knowledge and information about customersAbility to guide internal stakeholders through their own internal buying processesGrit; ability to find success in an early-stage environment without all the resources/teams available to much larger organizationsGood understanding of how to leverage other departments including Sales Engineering, Marketing, Product and Customer Success.Cultural fit: VOICEVelocity to outpace attackers and outpace our competitionOwnership to empower new leaders to step up and take actionIntellectual Honesty to uncover the best ideas and the right actionsCustomer Obsession to focus us on what is most valuableExcellence to achieve our ambition of being the bestNice to Haves2+ years of experience selling in cybersecurity4 Years in an individual contributor roleMEDDIC, MEDDPICC, or Command of the Sale sales methodology trainingAbnormal AI is an equal opportunity employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law. For our EEO policy statement please click here. If you would like more information on your EEO rights under the law, please click here."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-28T04:10:16.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recqhLfgTxD8Kn9Rt', 'SPS Commerce', 'https://www.spscommerce.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/sps-commerce', 'Minneapolis, MN, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '70', 'SPS Commerce is a growth-stage computer software company (3,201 employees) with active operations in Australia, indicating strong commercial B2B tech fit. The presence of multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Managers, Director - APAC Sales) provides direct access for recruitment. While the specific sales role is not explicitly listed, the filtered employees suggest ongoing hiring in core sales and customer success roles. Strong growth signals include 22% YoY revenue growth, international expansion, and increased sales investment, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSPS Commerce reported second quarter 2025 revenue growth of 22% year-over-year, reaching $187.4 million and marking its 98th consecutive quarter of topline growth as of July 30, 2025. The company executed $20 million in share repurchases during the same quarter and continues to project strong performance for the remainder of the year[1][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecurring revenue in Q2 2025 grew 24% year-over-year, with increased investments in sales and marketing spend. SPS Commerce continues international expansion, highlighting a focus on the European market and increased support for e-invoicing compliance, which signals ongoing hiring and operational growth in sales and compliance services[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nRecognized as the #1 IT Infrastructure Software in G2âs 2025 Best Software Awards earlier in 2025. Achieved milestone of 98 consecutive quarters of topline growth and launched enhanced e-invoicing and analytics products for global retail compliance earlier this year[2][1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"SPS Commerce is the worldâs leading retail network, connecting trading partners around the globe to optimize supply chain operations for all retail partners. We support data-driven partnerships with innovative cloud technology, customer-obsessed service, and accessible experts so our customers can focus on what they do best. \n\nTo date, more than 120,000 companies in retail, distribution, grocery, and e-commerce have chosen SPS as their retail network. SPS has achieved 97 consecutive quarters of revenue growth and is headquartered in Minneapolis. \n\nFor additional information, contact SPS at 866-245-8100 or visit www.spscommerce.com."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recr54Zh9v5n8XW90', 'Nightingale Software', 'https://www.nightingalesoftware.com.au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/nightingalesoftware', 'Burswood, Western Australia', 'Desktop Computing Software Products', '11-50 employees', '54', 'Nightingale Software is a small growth-stage desktop care management software provider (11-50 employees) actively operating in the ANZ region. The inclusion is triggered by the presence of a Senior Business Development Manager and Presales Consultant, both in Melbourne, indicating ongoing commercial sales activity. The company fits the commercial B2B tech profile (acceptable/edge case), but the desktop focus and sector specialization (NDIS, aged care) slightly limit fit. Tier 2 and Tier 3 decision makers are present, but there are no recent funding rounds or strong growth signals. This presents a moderate recruitment opportunity, with some likelihood of external sales hiring needs.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] No recent Melbourne-specific public announcements found in the last 6-12 months regarding new office openings, major customer wins, or events; Nightingale’s site and customer references do, however, emphasize deployment with Victorian and wider-Australian providers, suggesting active operations in the Greater Melbourne Area[5].\n[REGIONAL] Continued strong focus on NDIS, aged care, and community health providers across Australia, with marketing and customer support tailored for the ANZ market as of 2025[1][2][4][5].\n[GLOBAL] Australian ownership and HQ in Perth, with no recent global expansion, funding, or merger activity impacting regional operations noted as of September 2025[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] There are no public records of large-scale recruitment or Melbourne office build-outs; however, customer stories feature Victorian organizations like \"Together We Care\" and \"Albany Halfway House,\" indicating recent active projects and support delivery in Victoria[5].\n[REGIONAL] Nightingale actively promotes ease of onboarding and rapid rollout for new provider clients, and third-party consultants emphasize platform integration services, reflecting ongoing regional market penetration and customer growth[3][5].\n[GLOBAL] No direct evidence of company-wide headcount increases; public materials stress continuity in local support and implementation.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL/GLOBAL] No disclosed investment rounds, venture funding, or recent capital raises in the last 12 months. Nightingale appears privately owned and self-funded as of September 2025[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Highlighted case studies from Victorian and regional Australian care providers indicate recent successful implementations and platform migrations—emphasizing customer satisfaction and operational efficiency improvements[5].\n[REGIONAL] Nightingale maintains ongoing ISO 27001:2022 certification for information security, demonstrating sector leadership in compliance and data protection for care providers across Australia[4].\n[GLOBAL] No internationally recognized awards or new cross-border partnerships have been reported in this period.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[LOCAL] No reported executive appointments, departures, or sales/GTM leadership changes in the Melbourne area.\n[GLOBAL] Sandy Forrest is listed as CEO as of September 2025; no announced executive transitions in the last 12 months[1].\n\n[INDUSTRY] CONTEXT:\n[LOCAL/REGIONAL] The **desktop care management software** market in Australia remains highly regulated and competitive, driven by NDIS reforms, funding compliance, and digital transformation agendas. Providers prioritize platforms with strong compliance automation, integration with State and Federal claim systems, and support for distributed (remote and mobile) workforces[3][4]. Demand for “all-in-one” solutions—integrating rostering, billing, compliance, and analytics—remains strong, especially in Victoria and New South Wales where NDIS and Aged Care reforms are most active[2][3].\n\nIn summary, Nightingale Software remains a prominent local provider of care management solutions for NDIS, aged care, and allied health sectors, with active Victorian clients and strong regional relevance. No major external capital, global expansion, or senior Melbourne hiring has been disclosed recently, but market demand continues to drive steady adoption and implementation projects in the region."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development Representative (Aged Care &amp;amp; NDIS) — East Coast (Melbourne based only)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re growing! Nightingale Software is hiring a Business Development Representative to help aged-care and NDIS providers modernise operations across the East Coast. If you love prospecting, social selling, and turning conversations into qualified opportunities, let’s talk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Focus: Aged Care, NDIS, HCP, CHSP, Support at Home providers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Territory: NSW / VIC / QLD (hybrid, with travel)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tools: HubSpot, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Comp: Competitive base + super + uncapped commission (realistic OTE $110k-120k+)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Impact: Bring real efficiency to frontline care via rostering, mobile workforce, funding claims &amp;amp; AP automation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply via LinkedIn or DM me for a confidential chat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;About Nightingale Software&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nightingale is an Australian SaaS platform built for disability, community, and aged-care providers. We streamline client &amp;amp; resource management, rostering, mobile workforce, NDIS/HCP/CHSP funding &amp;amp; claiming, and AP automation—all with local compliance at the core (including ISO 27001:2022). Our mission: help providers spend less time on admin and more time delivering quality care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As one of our Business Development Representative (BDR) you’ll build top-of-funnel pipeline across the East Coast and partner closely with Senior BDMs to progress qualified meetings and opportunities with NDIS, Aged Care, HCP, CHSP, and upcoming Support at Home providers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll combine outbound prospecting, event follow-ups, inbound leads, social selling, video outreach, and tight CRM hygiene to open doors with CEOs, COOs, CFOs, Clinical/Operations leaders, and IT/Transformation teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Drive outbound sequences (email, phone, LinkedIn, video) to book qualified meetings for Senior BDMs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Research and segment named accounts by provider type, funding stream (NDIS/HCP/CHSP/SAH), and region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Turn event leads and partnerships (e.g., industry forums, Alliance20, webinars) into pipeline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualify using clear criteria (fit, pain, timeline, stakeholders, funding mix, tech stack).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Maintain spotless HubSpot hygiene: tasks, notes, next steps, sequences, and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Collaborate with Marketing on messaging, sequences, and content that resonates by persona.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Report weekly on activity, meetings set, conversion rates, and pipeline influenced.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;1–3+ years in BDR/SDR (SaaS or healthcare tech preferred) with a track record of meeting setting targets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Familiarity with NDIS / Aged Care / HCP / CHSP / Support at Home landscape—or strong aptitude to learn fast.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Confident with HubSpot CRM (or similar), Sales Navigator, video outreach, and data-driven cadence management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent written &amp;amp; verbal communication; resilient, curious, and coachable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full Australian work rights; based in VIC (hybrid). Willing to travel for events and customer visits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nice to have: experience selling into providers, knowledge of SCHADS/roster operations, and basic procurement/RFP exposure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why Nightingale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Meaningful impact: your work helps providers return time to care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Growth &amp;amp; coaching: clear 30/60/90 plan, call coaching, and enablement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Modern stack: HubSpot, Sales Nav, Zoominfo (where available).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rewards: competitive base + super + uncapped commission (realistic OTE $110k–$120k+).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexibility: hybrid work (office once a fortnight), travel to industry events, and autonomy to experiment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply via LinkedIn or message me for a confidential chat. If you prefer email, send your CV and a short note on a pipeline win you’re proud of to clara.buonanno@nightingalesoftware.com.au with subject “BDR – East Coast”.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQFRtg393Xyxwg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1638423874944/nightingalesoftware_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=fZuTLyGoA-AHw1VNRgMVUnq0glR6I_IHvBMgqodzeT0', '2025-09-23T14:27:36.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
