    ('recrUjhBv2fFxnKId', 'Myriota', 'http://www.myriota.com', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/myriota', 'Adelaide, SA, AU', 'Telecommunications', '51 - 200', '61', 'Myriota is a growth-stage telecommunications company (75 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech elements focused on IoT satellite connectivity. The presence of a Director, Regional Sales (Tier 2), and VP Commercial Operations (Tier 2) provides solid decision maker access for sales recruitment. Recent funding and significant international expansion (satellite launches, new markets) are strong growth signals. However, the specific sales role triggering inclusion is not identified, and telecommunications is an edge-case industry for 4Twenty, limiting the overall fit. This represents a moderate recruitment opportunity if a core sales role is confirmed.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nMyriota expanded its IoT satellite constellation with the successful launch of four new low Earth orbit satellites via SpaceXâs Transporter-12 rideshare mission in January 2025, enhancing resilience and opening new markets including Mexico, Brazil, Chile, Argentina, and the Middle East. The company also announced, on April 30, 2025, an expanded agreement with Spire Global to add 16 more satellites, bringing the total to over 40 satellites in its constellation[2][3][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nMyriota is scaling its satellite network and increasing market coverage internationally, indicated by its ongoing investments in satellite deployment and expansion of services across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East. The company is actively investing in global network operations and technology improvements, but no specific recent hiring or sales/GTM headcount data has been identified[1][2][3][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nIn December 2024, Myriota closed a US$32 million funding round led by National Reconstruction Fund Corporation (NRFC) with participation from Main Sequence and Inter Valley Ventures. The funding supports acceleration of IoT digitization efforts, global expansion, and network scaling[2].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nMyriota completed the Kingdom of Saudi Arabiaâs CST Sandbox program in late 2024, deploying a remote water metering communications network for the Saudi Ministry of Environment, Water and Agriculture. The company also launched four additional nanosatellites in January 2025 and announced the expansion to a constellation of 40+ satellites in April 2025, reflecting accelerating advancements in global IoT connectivity[2][3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Connect anything, anywhere. Global IoT solutions that âjust workâ.\n\nMyriota was founded in 2015 to revolutionise IoT through simple, secure and affordable access to data using advanced, direct-to-satellite technology. Myriota IP covers all aspects of the end-to-end solution; edge, satellite and cloud.\n\nEnabled by anywhere connectivity, a vibrant ecosystem of Myriota Partners including Solution Providers and Original Equipment Manufacturers are unlocking previously impossible or impractical use cases to deliver tangibly better outcomes across water, agriculture, defence, logistics, environmental monitoring and more.\n\nFrom safeguarding critical resources to maximising operational efficiency, global organisations now have access to critical data, anywhere and everywhere itâs needed. For more information please visit: www.myriota.com   "}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recrl7EE99zsEERBS', 'Square', 'http://squareup.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/joinsquare', 'San Francisco, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '77', 'Square is a major computer software and fintech company with a strong presence in Australia, actively hiring for core sales roles such as Senior Account Executive, Account Executive, Sales Manager, and Business Development Representative. The company operates in a core target industry and has multiple Tier 2 decision makers, including Sales Managers and a Head of Sales, providing strong access for recruitment engagement. Recent product launches and new partnerships signal ongoing market growth, though there are no recent funding or sales leadership appointments. High potential for immediate recruitment partnership.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nSquare launched the biannual \"Square Releases\" program in May 2025, delivering bundled new features, tools, and partnerships for key verticals, notably unveiling the Square Handheld portable POS device and integrating deeper with platforms like WooCommerce and DoorDash. The company opened \"The Corner Store\" in San Francisco in May 2025 as a new local business community hub and began offering all new sellers automatic Square Checking accounts to streamline banking services.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified specifically regarding sales or GTM headcount growth, but expansion of product lines and entrance into new industry partnerships such as with WooCommerce and expanded banking offerings indicate ongoing market and customer base growth.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or financial investment announcements identified in the past 6â12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nSquare AI entered open beta in May 2025, enabling business insights for sellers. Major product launches in 2025 include Square Handheld and the next-generation Square Point of Sale app, with public recognition for innovative industry-specific solutions and expanded seller enablement. \n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people roles identified in the past 6â12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Since we opened our doors in 2009, the world of commerce has evolved immensely, and so has Square. After enabling anyone to take payments and never miss a sale, we saw sellers stymied by disparate, outmoded products and tools that wouldnât work together.\n\nSo we expanded into software and started building integrated, omnichannel solutions â to help sellers sell online, manage inventory, offer buy now, pay later functionality through Afterpay, book appointments, engage loyal buyers, and hire and pay staff. Across it all, weâve embedded financial services tools at the point of sale, so merchants can access a business loan and manage their cash flow in one place. Afterpay furthers our goal to provide omnichannel tools that unlock meaningful value and growth, enabling sellers to capture the next-generation shopper, increase order sizes, and compete at a larger scale.\n\nToday, we are a partner to sellers of all sizes â large, enterprise-scale businesses with complex operations, sellers just starting, as well as merchants who began selling with Square and have grown larger over time. As our sellers grow, so do our solutions. There is a massive opportunity in front of us. Weâre building a significant, meaningful, and lasting business and helping sellers worldwide do the same.\n\nSquare is part of Block, Inc. (NYSE: SQ), a global technology company with a focus on financial services."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recsWBwaqhZRQDuub', 'Atturra', 'https://atturra.com/au-en/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/atturra', 'Sydney, New South Wales, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '1001 - 5000', '84', 'Atturra is a growth-stage IT services company (982 employees) actively hiring for Enterprise Account Executive and Sales Manager roles, both high-priority core sales positions. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, offering SaaS, cloud, and digital transformation services. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (General Managers, Sales Managers, Executive GMs) are present, providing strong access for recruitment engagement. Recent acquisitions, market expansion, and significant revenue growth signal robust hiring needs. While there is no recent funding, the combination of strong industry fit, company size, decision-maker access, and growth signals make this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAtturra reported 24% growth in revenue and uEBITDA for FY25, reaching $300.6 million and $31.5 million respectively, attributed significantly to six acquisitions including Chrome Consulting, Plan B, Kitepipe, and DalRae Solutions throughout late 2024 and 2025. The company announced and completed the acquisition of Melbourne-based IT services provider Blue Connections on September 1, 2025, expanding its national and managed services footprint.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nMultiple acquisitions between August 2024 and September 2025 indicate direct expansion in new markets, including New Zealand and the US, and increased service capacity, particularly through sales, managed services, and GTM-related roles. Headcount and operational scale have grown notably with rebranding and integration of new teams, including the onboarding of all Plan B staff in New Zealand.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nRebranded New Zealand subsidiary Plan B to Atturra in June 2025, enabling broader enterprise service offerings. Achieved 78% of revenue from predictable sources in FY25, and maintained financial performance despite challenging conditions in certain markets; completed six strategic acquisitions and integrated new regional business divisions in FY25.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nFrazer Scott, former CEO of Plan B, appointed as Atturraâs New Zealand Country Lead following the rebrand in June 2025. No other significant executive changes in sales/revenue or people operations roles identified in the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Atturra (ASX: ATA) is one of Australia''s leading advisory and IT solutions providers, focused on providing end-to-end transformation services to its clients. Atturra is headquartered in Sydney and has offices across the rest of Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Hong Kong and USA. With more than 1200 people, Atturra helps both public and private sectors adapt and grow by delivering business and technology outcomes."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recsr70hZ10BrcItW', 'Yokogawa Australia & New Zealand', 'http://www.yokogawa.com/au', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/yokogawa-australia-newzealand', 'Macquarie Park, New South Wales, AU', 'Industrial Automation', '201 - 500', '54', 'Yokogawa Australia & New Zealand is a growth-stage industrial automation company (246 employees) with a strong presence in Australia. The trigger role is Business Development Manager, which is a medium-priority sales role for 4Twenty (25 points). The industry is edge-case tech (industrial automation, not core commercial B2B SaaS), earning 5 points. Company size is ideal, with a slight boost for being under 500 employees (+5). Multiple Tier 2 decision makers are present (Sales Director, Regional Sales Managers, National Business Development Manager, 10 points). Growth signals include recent partnerships and product launches (6 points). However, there is no evidence of recent sales team expansion or active hiring for core sales roles, limiting the overall recruitment opportunity. This is a moderate opportunity, best suited for targeted outreach rather than immediate high-priority engagement.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nYokogawa Australia & New Zealand signed a strategic MOU with UNSW TRaCE in February 2025 to collaborate on recycling and clean energy technologies[2][6]. The company also announced a multi-faceted partnership with Jinggong Group for mutual business development on June 10, 2025[5][6]. Participation in various 2025 exhibitions, including the Asia-Pacific Hydrogen Summit, signals ongoing engagement in sustainable and hydrogen-focused innovations[1][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nYokogawa Australia has been actively supporting work-integrated learning and internship programs as part of its UNSW TRaCE partnership, aiming to attract and develop engineering talent with a focus on industry and academia collaboration[2]. No recent hiring or headcount expansion activity specifically for sales or GTM roles identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nCelebrated the 50th anniversary of its CENTUM Distributed Control Systems in mid-2025 and released the next-generation CENTUM VP Integrated Production Control System[5][6]. Announced advancements in AI-powered solutions and recent collaboration with Shell for robotics and AI technologies in plant maintenance during the last six months[5][6].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Established in 1915, Yokogawa is a leading provider of Industrial Automation, Process Safety, Process Instrumentation, Cloud, Data Analytics and Energy Management solutions. Combining ultra-reliable technology with engineering excellence, Yokogawa delivers field proven operational improvement, safety, quality, and reliability.\nWith a presence in the region for over thirty years, we have been improving the lives of everyday Australians and New Zealanders through the provision of engineering and solutions excellence to key industries and critical infrastructure. Our reputation for quality and reliability ensures the highest standards of water purity, food quality, reliable and sustainable energy provision plus minerals supply to help grow our economies. Our dedication to building a safe and sustainable future through emissions monitoring, raw materials reduction and process improvements have been rewarded with globally recognised awards.  \nAs an energetic, service-focused business with an enviable reputation for quality and reliability, our people are our strength. Acknowledged at the highest levels for meeting the most demanding of schedules, often on applications that test the limits of conventional platforms and expertise, we work collaboratively with our clients to ensure an optimal outcome designed and installed to the highest possible safety standards. Our resilient transformation approach to improving your operations not only utilises our fit for purpose technology but delves into the best-in-class expertise which is the foundation for some of the worldâs most successful Power generators.\nA proudly diverse and inclusive organisation, we provide solutions that enhance safety, ensure accurate and reliable operation, open windows to previously inaccessible process insights and increase overall plant efficiency. Our total solutions approach ranges from specific process measurement, through packaged applications to complete remote operations solutions.\n"}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recsszCe0DI2Yr9Eh', 'Pax8', 'http://www.pax8.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/pax8', 'Greenwood Village, Colorado', 'Technology, Information and Internet', '1,001-5,000 employees', '92', 'Pax8 is a growth-stage commercial B2B technology company (cloud marketplace/SaaS) with 1,001-5,000 employees and a major new Brisbane head office, indicating strong regional investment and ongoing hiring. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers—including a VP Sales ANZ, Regional Sales Managers, and Sales Managers—provides direct access to key hiring authorities. Multiple growth signals are present: APAC leadership appointments, rapid employee expansion, and strategic office launches. Current sales hiring includes Channel Account Managers and Sales Managers (core/high-priority roles), making this a very high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Opened a new **Brisbane Australian head office** in 2024, blending Pax8’s global standards with local Australian influences, featuring advanced collaborative and tech-driven workspaces designed for future growth[2].\n[REGIONAL] In August 2025, appointed **Lindsay Zwart as EVP and General Manager, APAC**, signaling a strategic realignment and preparing Pax8 for a major growth phase across Asia-Pacific, headquartered from Australia[3][4].\n[REGIONAL] Announced initial expansion into **Australia and New Zealand** in April 2022, launching the cloud marketplace with dedicated support, education, and local leadership[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] Office design and infrastructure indicate intent to **grow Brisbane operations** substantially, with workspace planned to eventually occupy the entire building—supporting an expanding local team and increased client-facing activity[2].\n[REGIONAL] Employee base in APAC expanded from a one-person start to **300 employees** across the region as of 2025, with ongoing scale-up plans[4].\n[REGIONAL] Leadership emphasizes “significant scaling of operations” throughout APAC, with expectations for **continuous hiring** and expansion in both sales and corporate teams[3][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] No new funding rounds have been publicly reported in the last 6-12 months based on available sources. Most recent substantial funding occurred prior to 2024; focus has shifted toward reinvestment and regional growth[3][1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Created a **cutting-edge Australian head office** in Brisbane (2024), integrating a multifunctional content creation studio, entertainment/social hub, and modern meeting spaces to support dynamic team and event activities[2].\n[REGIONAL] Pax8’s marketplace now gives **ANZ MSPs** access to global cloud vendors, channel support, and education, making it easier for local partners to cloud-enable client businesses[1].\n[REGIONAL] APAC leadership team recognized for channel industry influence; ongoing focus on enabling partners to build value-based, technology-forward offerings across the region[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] In **August 2025, Lindsay Zwart** appointed as EVP and General Manager, APAC, taking over from **Chris Sharp**, who transitions to a global Senior Vice President, Business Development role focused on **global partnerships and market expansion**; both positions impact ANZ operations[3][4].\n[REGIONAL] Key leaders still linked to ANZ/APAC operations include **Tracy Lacewell** (VP of Sales, Pax8 Asia) and **James Bergl** (VP, Business Development), both with mandates covering support and expansion throughout Australia and New Zealand[1].\n\nINDUSTRY CONTEXT:\n[INDUSTRY] The Australian technology, information, and internet sector continues robust growth, with demand for **cloud marketplace services and managed service providers (MSPs)** accelerating due to ongoing digital transformation post-pandemic—driving investment, hiring, and client adoption, particularly in regions like Queensland.\n\n**Summary of Scope:**  \n- Multiple signals confirm **Brisbane’s head office is a strategic hub** for ongoing regional scale-up.  \n- APAC executive changes and workspace investment in 2024–2025 reflect heavy focus on Australian/regional market development.  \n- Pax8 is currently prioritizing **organic growth and executive talent** as a pathway to capture ANZ/APAC share, with continuing emphasis on sales, partner support, and go-to-market expansion."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀 Join Pax8 as a Business Development Representative!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to kickstart your sales career in the fast-paced world of cloud technology? Pax8, the world’s favourite cloud marketplace, is looking for a Business Development Representative to help drive our partner growth across APAC.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Business Development Representative (aka Cloud Generation Specialist @ Pax8), you’ll be a key part of our sales team, contributing to corporate sales goals. You''ll participate in a development program to build and master foundational sales skills, offering uncapped earning potential and a clear career path.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This role is based in Brisbane, QLD.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💼 What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive new business by introducing Pax8 Cloud Services to potential partners via calls, emails, and social media.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set appointments and coordinate meetings between prospects and our Channel Account Managers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Secure 15 signed partners per month to our marketplace.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate Salesforce records and support our sales funnel with energy and precision.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🌟 What You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A hunger to learn and grow in tech sales – experience in lead generation or sales is a plus, but not essential.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence making a high volume of outreach calls with a great attitude and resilience.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, coachability, and a passion for customer success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A collaborative spirit and the drive to thrive in a high-energy, results-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;💜 Why Join Pax8?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Pax8, we know our people are our power. That’s why we’re all in on supporting your growth, well-being, and success—both in and out of the office. Here’s what you can expect when you join the team:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;🌴 Extra Time Off, On Us We get it—life’s busy. That’s why we give you 2 bonus weeks of leave every year, starting from day one. More time for you, your family, and the things you love.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🩺 Private Health Insurance Because life happens. We’ve got you covered with private health insurance for peace of mind when you need it most.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📚 Unlimited Learning &amp;amp; Growth Whether you''re climbing the ladder or carving your own path, our Learning &amp;amp; Development programs and strong culture of internal promotion will help you get there.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎓 Paid Industry Certifications We’ll fund your journey to becoming a cloud expert with fully paid, industry-recognised certifications that boost your skills and your career.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pax8 is the leading value-added cloud-based SaaS marketplace, simplifying the cloud journey for our partners by integrating technology, business intelligence and proactive service to deliver an unparalleled experience. Serving thousands of partners through the indirect sales channel, our mission is to be the world’s favourite place to buy cloud products.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equal Opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pax8 is an equal opportunities employer and welcome individuals who are in possession of the appropriate requirements to work within the country the role is based in. Offered individuals will be asked to undertake identity, security compliance and reference checks. Your privacy is important to us. Your data will be held in accordance with Data Privacy best practices and processed only in accordance with our recruiting processes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Job Applicant Privacy Notice&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQGgOoFobR1V2A/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1656937495292/pax8_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=OoG-qt-5I9fJngFIM7nPfNfK2Zhby0FW0D6gV5kKvWs', '2025-10-01T14:21:09.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recstzQKWfhY5U2wP', 'ShipBob', 'http://www.shipbob.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/shipbob', 'Chicago, IL, US', 'Transportation/Trucking/Railroad', '501 - 1000', '63', 'ShipBob is a growth-stage logistics technology company (1,422 employees) with a strong commercial fit due to its technology-driven fulfillment solutions, recent $200M funding, and significant expansion signals. The inclusion is triggered by the Merchant Success Manager role, which is a medium-priority sales-adjacent role. The presence of a Tier 3 decision maker (Merchant Success Manager) in Australia provides some access but lacks direct senior sales leadership. Multiple growth signals and recent funding indicate a moderate likelihood to use external recruitment for sales roles, but the specific role and decision maker limit this to a medium-priority opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nShipBob launched its De Minimis Defense Program in August 2025 to help merchants adapt to new U.S. customs rules, adding more Foreign-Trade Zone warehouses. In June 2025, ShipBob debuted nationwide zone skipping to enhance supply chain efficiency and transparency for customers.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nShipBobâs 2025 State of Ecommerce Fulfillment report (January 2025) states that 80% of ecommerce brands using ShipBob saw revenue growth in 2024, and over 50% of brands plan on adding new sales channels or expanding to new countries in 2025, indicating significant market expansion and increased demand for fulfillment solutions. 38% of brands surveyed intend to add more distribution centers, suggesting continued logistics facility growth.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nIn April 2025, ShipBob raised $200 million at a valuation exceeding $1 billion, supporting its ambition to expand its technology and global fulfillment network.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAnnounced ShipBob Plus in May 2025, a fulfillment solution for mid-market and enterprise merchants, and launched a new merchant financing program called ShipBob Capital in partnership with Slope and J.P. Morgan. Released its fourth annual State of Ecommerce Fulfillment Report in January 2025, highlighting substantial customer growth and market insights.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Founded in 2014, ShipBob offers best-in-class supply chain and fulfillment capabilities for thousands of brands. ShipBob has an international fulfillment network across the US, Canada, UK, EU, and Australia. ShipBob''s proprietary technology combines order and inventory management, warehouse management, predictive data and analytics, as well as optimized shipping for ecommerce companies."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('rectQe4a2YhVzISjA', 'Zilliz', 'https://zilliz.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/zilliz', 'Redwood City, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '51 - 200', '78', 'Zilliz is a high-growth AI and database software company with recent $60M funding, multiple product launches, and international expansion, indicating strong hiring momentum. The presence of senior sales leadership in Singapore and an established sales team structure signals immediate relevance for external recruitment support. Recognitions in industry reports and ongoing investment in go-to-market activities further reinforce high hiring probability for sales and revenue roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nZilliz released Milvus 2.6 in June 2025, focusing on reducing AI infrastructure costs and simplifying deployment for enterprises scaling AI initiatives. In February 2025, the company enhanced its Zilliz Cloud service with updated \"Bring Your Own Cloud\" (BYOC) offerings to address enterprise data sovereignty and compliance requirements.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent public hiring announcements or sales/GTM-specific expansion identified, but multiple product releases and international relocations indicate sustained team growth and ongoing investment in cloud and AI infrastructure.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nZilliz raised $60 million and announced relocation to San Francisco in June 2025, marking its latest significant investment milestone for product, cloud infrastructure expansion, and go-to-market activities.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nZilliz was recognized as the \"Highest Performer\" and \"Easiest to Use\" in G2''s Summer 2025 Grid Report for Vector Databases in July 2025. The company was also named a Leader in the September 2024 Forrester Wave report for Vector Database Providers and released major Milvus updatesâ2.5 in December 2024 and 2.6 in June 2025.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes or executive appointments identified in the past six months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Zilliz is a leading vector database company for enterprise-grade AI. Founded by the engineers behind Milvus, the world''s most widely-adopted open-source vector database, the company builds next-generation database technologies to help organizations create AI applications at ease. On a mission to democratize AI, Zilliz is committed to simplifying data management for AI applications and making vector databases accessible to every organization. \n\nContact us here for time-limited discount and demo request for scalable enterprise AI infra: https://zilliz.com/contact-sales?utm_source-linkedin"}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('rectYK5mEx41XtKj5', 'Kyriba', 'https://www.kyriba.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/kyriba', 'San Diego, CA, US', 'Computer Software', '501 - 1000', '80', 'Kyriba is a growth-stage SaaS and Fintech company (1,245 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively operating in Australia and Singapore. The presence of Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (VP Sales APAC, multiple Sales Directors) provides direct access for recruitment. While there is no explicit recent sales hiring surge, recent major funding ($152.5M), strategic partnerships, and product launches indicate robust growth signals. The most relevant roles for recruitment are Sales Director and VP Sales, which are high-priority core sales roles, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nKyriba announced a collaboration with BNY Mellon in April 2024 to integrate its SaaS treasury solution with BNY Mellon''s LiquidityDirect platform, enhancing liquidity management for clients. Additionally, Kyriba expanded its payments technology through a new integration with J.P. Morganâs Kinexys Digital Payments platform in April 2024, streamlining cross-border payments for treasury customers[2][4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nHeadcount remains strong with an estimated 501-1000 employees, and recent partnerships such as with BNY Mellon and J.P. Morgan signal focus on expanding reach and product relevance. No recent major hiring surges or significant sales team expansions publicly disclosed in the last 12 months[1][2][4].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nKyriba raised $152.5 million in its latest funding round on October 1, 2024, with investors including Bridgepoint and General Atlantic[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nKyriba launched its agentic AI solution, TAI, designed to deliver secure, compliant generative AI capabilities for finance teams, announced at KyribaLive in mid-2025. The company now processes over $1 trillion in payments annually through its solutions, reflecting significant operational scale[3][4].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nMelissa Di Donato is identified as the current Chair and CEO as of 2025. No recent executive hires, promotions, or departures identified in the last 6-12 months[3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Kyriba is the global leader in liquidity performance, empowering CFOs, Treasurers and IT leaders to connect, protect, forecast and optimize their liquidity amid economic complexity. As a secure and scalable SaaS solution trusted by 3,000 customers, Kyriba delivers intelligence and financial automation through innovative technologies â including its trusted agentic AI (TAI) â bringing precision, efficiency, and insight to financial operations. With an expansive ecosystem of banking, technology and consulting partners, Kyribaâs platform powers more than 3 billion bank transactions and $15 trillion in payments across 9,900+ banks annually â helping companies gain enterprise-wide visibility, ensure financial stability, and outperform their business strategy."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('rectdWjggjwSOALvf', 'Convera', 'http://www.convera.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/converaholdings', 'Seattle, Washington, US', 'Financial Services', '1001 - 5000', '73', 'Convera is a growth-stage fintech company (1,791 employees) with active hiring for Business Development Manager and Senior Account Executive roles in Australia and Singapore, both high-priority sales positions. The company operates in the core B2B fintech/payments sector, offering a strong industry fit. Multiple Tier 2 decision makers (Sales Manager, Head of Sales, Director, Business Development Manager) are present in APAC, providing solid access for recruitment engagement. While there are no recent funding rounds or major leadership changes, ongoing hiring and regional sales expansion signal moderate growth. This makes Convera a high-priority recruitment opportunity for commercial sales roles.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nConvera released the \"Fintech 2025+\" report, developed with Oxford Economics and The Paypers, in July 2025, highlighting trends and growth projections for global cross-border payments and emphasizing the company''s strategic focus on leading fintech innovation in B2B and institutional payments[4][5]. No other major acquisitions, divestitures, or significant market events have been reported in the past 6-12 months.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nConvera currently employs more than 1,900 people across 31 global offices and continues to list multiple open positions, indicating ongoing hiring across regions[2]. There is sustained demand for operational and client-facing roles, including in sales and account management[1][2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or investment announcements identified in the last 6-12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nConvera published the \"Fintech 2025+\" industry report in July 2025 in partnership with respected research organizations, reinforcing its position as an industry thought leader[4][5]. No other specific awards or new product launches have been noted within this timeframe.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive hires, promotions, or departures disclosed in the last 6-12 months. Patrick Gauthier remains CEO[1][2]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Convera is a global leader in commercial payments. With an unrivaled regulatory footprint and a financial network spanning more than 140 currencies and 200 countries and territories, weâre reimagining the future of business payments to better serve our customers. Our tech-led payment solutions are built on deep expertise in foreign exchange, risk management, and compliance - helping businesses grow with confidence. From small businesses to CFOs and treasurers, we make business payments simple, smart, and secure."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recvcA3groZ1IoH79', 'Lumi', 'https://www.lumi.com.au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/lumi-finance', 'Sydney, NSW, AU', 'Financial Services', '51 - 200', '70', 'Lumi is a growth-stage fintech company (143 employees) in Sydney, actively hiring for Business Development Manager roles, which are medium-priority sales positions. The company operates in the core commercial B2B fintech sector, aligning well with our target market. Tier 2 decision makers such as the Head of Internal Sales and multiple BDMs are accessible, supporting recruitment engagement. While there are no recent funding or hiring surge signals, Lumi''s recent innovation awards and product launches indicate moderate growth and a strong commercial focus, making this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nBMO launched the Lumi Assistant, an AI-powered digital tool for employees, which has been recognized for innovation in financial services as of June 17, 2025. Lumi Assistant aims to accelerate and personalize financial services delivery for BMO clients.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nLumi Assistant received two major digital innovation awards in June 2025: \"Best Use of Gen AI for Customer Experience â Canada\" from The Digital Banker and \"Top Innovation in Finance â North America\" by Global Finance.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Lumi takes the guesswork out of small business funding. We offer small business loans and lines of credit from $10kâ$750k with 3â60 month terms. \n\nAt Lumi, we donât believe in surprises (at least, not when it comes to finance). Instead, we pride ourselves on offering straightforward loans to give your venture the financial boost it needs. No guesswork, no hassles, no reading between the lines. Just totally transparent loans to help you get ahead.\n\nHereâs how it works:\n\n1) Apply online in less than 5 minutes\n2) Get an outcome within 2 hours\n3) Receive your funds within the same business day\n\nItâs that easy!\n"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recvnwWgrL7FP0sW7', 'A LevelBlue Company', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, true, false, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-09-28T14:29:59.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recvsz44K7Gx3YHbh', 'Wild Tech', 'https://wild-tech.com/au/', 'https://au.linkedin.com/company/wild-tech-pty-ltd', 'Sydney, New South Wales, AU', 'Information Technology & Services', '51 - 200', '90', 'Wild Tech is a growth-stage IT services company (75 employees) actively hiring for a Business Development Representative, a primary target sales role. The company operates in core commercial B2B tech, focusing on ERP, SaaS, and cloud solutions, making it an ideal industry fit. Decision makers include a Head of Microsoft Singapore (country lead, Tier 1) and a Business Development Manager (Tier 2), providing strong access for recruitment. Multiple recent leadership hires and a major platform launch signal robust growth and ongoing sales team expansion, indicating a high likelihood of external recruitment needs.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nWild Tech appointed Dirk Vorster as Western Australia practice lead in September 2025 to drive growth in the WA market, aiming to deepen client relationships and expand local delivery capabilities. In August 2025, the company announced a strategic expansion into enterprise-grade managed services and transformation partnerships with a focus on AI, cloud, and Microsoft technologies.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent high-level hires—including Dirk Vorster, Dan Whittle as General Manager of Managed Services in February 2025, and Andrew Kirk as Senior Business Development Manager—indicate significant headcount growth, especially in client-facing and enterprise sales roles. Wild Tech is targeting growth in the WA region and expanding into enterprise markets, particularly government, retail, and financial services.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nIn May 2025, Wild Tech launched a platform designed to help organisations reduce AI sprawl and improve governance, marking a key innovation milestone in digital transformation consultancy and AI management.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nAugust 2025: Dirk Vorster appointed as WA Practice Lead. February 2025: Dan Whittle hired as General Manager, Managed Services. July 2025: Andrew Kirk joined as Senior Business Development Manager to lead enterprise market expansion efforts."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"With real-world experience, a global team, and the trust of local clients, we’re the end-to-end technology partner businesses rely on to turn bold ideas into powerful results. \n\nWe transform businesses by deeply understanding their processes, pressures, and potential. We help them break free from legacy systems and deliver best-in-class digital solutions that remove barriers and help them thrive.\n\nFrom AI and automation to ERP, CRM, and best-in-class managed services we deliver the digital backbone  that empower organisations to adopt new technologies, streamline operations, and make data-driven decisions that accelerate growth.\n\nWe thrive on working shoulder-to-shoulder with our clients to solve problems, simplify complexity, and lead meaningful digital transformation both now and well into the future. "}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQGg5SoSERxdPg/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1630658191115/wild_tech_pty_ltd_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=NKISIaNVUEeasp79RpHPzuceX72ERV8vaTrcaqnCT4c', '2025-09-18T21:05:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z')
