 last 6-12 months. No recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Jamf, the standard in managing and securing Apple at work, extends the legendary Apple experience people love to businesses, schools and government organizations through its software and the 100,000 members of Jamf Nation, the largest community of Apple IT admins in the world. Today, 76,500 global customers entrust Jamf with more than 33.2 million devices as of 12/31/24. \n \nWe are growing and actively building our team across the globe. Visit the Careers section of our LinkedIn page to learn more about our open positions."}'::jsonb, 'MEDIUM', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recx5Dx66zLeQlziW', 'GitHub', 'https://github.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/github', 'San Francisco, CA', 'Software Development', '501-1,000 employees', '74', 'GitHub is a growth-stage commercial B2B software company (501-1,000 employees) actively hiring for multiple core sales roles, including Senior Enterprise Business Representative and several Account Executives, indicating strong ongoing sales expansion in Australia. The industry fit is ideal (core SaaS/software), and the company is investing heavily in regional growth, as evidenced by the recent launch of Enterprise Cloud data residency and a rapidly expanding developer ecosystem. High-quality decision makers are present, including a Regional Director, Director of Corporate Sales APAC, and Vice President APAC, providing Tier 1 and Tier 2 access for recruitment. Multiple strong growth signals are present, but as a Microsoft subsidiary, there is no recent funding. This is a high-priority recruitment opportunity for core sales roles in APAC.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:  \n[LOCAL] GitHub launched **Enterprise Cloud data residency in Australia** in February 2025, enabling organizations—especially in regulated sectors like banking, healthcare, and government—to store code and repositories locally using Microsoft Azure’s Australian data centers[1][2][3]. This move targets compliance, data sovereignty, and network latency requirements. [REGIONAL] Australia is home to 1.7 million developers and serves as GitHub’s APAC headquarters, highlighting a regional commitment to growth[2]. [REGIONAL] There was a 231% surge in public generative AI projects in Australia in 2023, signaling rapid AI adoption among local developers[4].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:  \n[LOCAL] The introduction of Australian data residency directly addresses enterprise and public sector demand for local cloud deployment, opening new opportunities for large, regulated organizations to migrate to SaaS models with GitHub[2][3].