les[1]. There is no explicit recent data on hiring activity or team expansion, but the significant user and revenue growth suggest ongoing investment in sales and go-to-market teams to support this expansion.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo new funding rounds or investment announcements were identified in the past 6â12 months. ClickUpâs recent growth appears to be organic, driven by product innovation and market demand rather than new external capital.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nClickUp was named to the 2025 Forbes Cloud 100 for the fourth consecutive year, recognizing its innovation and leading AI capabilities[4]. The company also launched several product updates, including a rebuilt Whiteboard feature in December 2024 and the introduction of ClickUp Chat in September 2024, both with enhanced AI-driven functionalities[2]. Reaching $300 million ARR and 20 million users in September 2025 further underscores its rapid market traction[1].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent leadership changes, promotions, or departures were identified in available sources for the past 6â12 months. The executive team, including Founder and CEO Zeb Evans and CFO Dan Zhang, remains in place and was publicly cited in recent announcements[1][4]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"ClickUp is the worldâs only all-in-one productivity platform that flexes to the way people want to work. It replaces all individual workplace productivity tools with a single, unified platform that includes AI, project management, document collaboration, whiteboards, spreadsheets, and goals. \n\nFounded in 2017 and based in San Diego, ClickUp is on a mission to make the world more productive. As one of the fastest-growing SaaS companies in the world, ClickUp has helped more than 10 million users and 2 million teams lead a more productive life and save at least one day every week.  \n\nClick the link below to create your free workspace â¤µï¸"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recytA2kPXnbvvu9D', 'Amazon', 'https://www.aboutamazon.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/amazon', 'Seattle, WA, US', 'Computer Software', '10001 -', '92', 'Amazon demonstrates strong industry alignment in software, cloud, and AI, with significant recent investments and product integrations in artificial intelligence. The company is actively expanding in Australia and Singapore, with a robust sales and commercial leadership structure across multiple senior roles. Recent funding activity and strategic partnerships reinforce ongoing hiring and growth, making Amazon a top-priority opportunity for external recruitment services.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAmazon increased its total investment in AI startup Anthropic to $8 billion as of September 2025, reinforcing a strategic partnership to integrate Anthropicâs Claude models with AWS and consumer platforms like Alexa. Amazonâs deeper commitment to AI positions it as a top stakeholder in Anthropic, competing with other major tech firms in the artificial intelligence space.\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nRecent activities suggest continued hiring and investment in cloud infrastructure and AI-related roles, particularly to support strategic AI integrations and new product lines. The $8 billion loan and related financial maneuvers provide additional capital to sustain expansion in software, cloud, and AI services.\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nAmazon completed an $8 billion loan in late 2024 to fund capital expenditures, acquisitions, and working capital. No recent venture equity funding rounds for Amazon itself were identified; however, Amazon led a $4 billion investment in Anthropic in November 2024 and increased this to $8 billion by September 2025.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAmazonâs partnership with Anthropic has resulted in privileged integration of Claude AI models into AWSâs offering as of mid-2025, further establishing Amazonâs competitive positioning in enterprise AI services. Anthropic achieved a $183 billion valuation in 2025, benefiting Amazon as a major stakeholder.\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent activity identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Amazon is guided by four principles: customer obsession rather than competitor focus, passion for invention, commitment to operational excellence, and long-term thinking. We are driven by the excitement of building technologies, inventing products, and providing services that change lives. We embrace new ways of doing things, make decisions quickly, and are not afraid to fail. We have the scope and capabilities of a large company, and the spirit and heart of a small one.\n\nTogether, Amazonians research and develop new technologies from Amazon Web Services to Alexa on behalf of our customers: shoppers, sellers, content creators, and developers around the world.\n\nOur mission is to be Earth''s most customer-centric company. Our actions, goals, projects, programs, and inventions begin and end with the customer top of mind.\n\nYou''ll also hear us say that at Amazon, it''s always \"Day 1.\"â What do we mean? That our approach remains the same as it was on Amazon''s very first day - to make smart, fast decisions, stay nimble, invent, and focus on delighting our customers."}'::jsonb, 'VERY HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recyvjjAjo2zm6XiY', 'Qualtrics', 'https://www.qualtrics.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/qualtrics', 'Provo, UT and Seattle, WA, , US', 'Computer Software', '5001 - 10000', '44', 'Qualtrics is an enterprise computer software company (5,901 employees) with a strong commercial B2B tech fit, but its size indicates a sophisticated internal TA function, reducing external recruitment likelihood. The presence of multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (Country Manager, Sales Directors, Sales Managers) provides good access, and recent APAC growth signals are positive. However, the lack of a specific high-priority sales role posting (e.g., SDR/BDR or AE) as the trigger and the company''s enterprise scale result in a low overall recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nIn May 2025, Qualtrics announced that hundreds of leading organizations across Asia Pacific, including the Commonwealth Bank of Australia, selected its platform to enhance customer and employee experiences. The company is actively investing in channel partner co-development, adding headcount, and launching a new partner program targeting growth in Australia and the broader Asia Pacific region[1][2].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nQualtrics is increasing headcount on regional partner teams in Australia and is supporting these partners through boosted marketing budgets and new solution co-development initiatives. The company has a medium-sized workforce (100-999 employees in Australia) and remains recognized as a top workplace, suggesting ongoing recruitment and expansion[1][3].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent activity identified.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nQualtrics was selected by major brands across Asia Pacific such as Commonwealth Bank of Australia, OneNZ, and Nufarm, and hosted its X4 Sydney Summit on May 28, 2025, unveiling new Experience Agents™ AI technology for experience management. The company’s AI-driven product advancements have also been featured in its recent press releases[2][4][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nIn April 2024, Qualtrics appointed Gurdeep Singh Pall as President, AI Strategy, to drive innovation in its AI offerings[4]. No other significant leadership changes in Australia identified."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"At Qualtrics, we create software the world’s best brands use to deliver exceptional frontline experiences, build high-performing teams, and design products people love. But we are more than a platform—we are the creators and stewards of the Experience Management category serving over 19,000 clients globally. Building a category takes grit, determination, and a disdain for convention—but most of all it requires close-knit, high-functioning teams with an unwavering dedication to serving our customers. That’s where we come in. \n\nFounded in 2002, our company has spent over 21 years working with the industries that impact you every day. From retail to government to healthcare, we’ve been on a mission to bring humanity, connection, and empathy back to business. It’s a mission that thousands of Qualtricians across the globe think is work worth doing.\n\nMission: At Qualtrics, our mission is to build technology that closes experience gaps."}'::jsonb, 'LOW', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQGMhQcnBkafcQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1721340384074/qualtrics_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=352Se1OVY2zu5VLnwLbh-4XGKVvzZZNtYHXZ9rnLt2I', '2025-09-18T20:59:19.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('recz2M8gwSgWABAre', 'Mastercard', 'http://www.mastercard.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/mastercard', 'Purchase, NY, US', 'Information Technology & Services', '10001 -', '77', 'Mastercard is a major IT & Services company with strong APAC presence and over 43,000 employees, operating in core fintech and payments technology sectors. Multiple senior sales and business development leaders are accessible in Australia and Singapore, including Vice Presidents and Directors, providing strong Tier 2 decision maker access. Recent product launches and market expansion in AI-driven payments indicate ongoing investment in sales teams, though no direct sales hiring or recent funding was noted. High potential for recruitment partnership in sales roles due to scale, industry fit, and leadership accessibility.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nMastercard announced the launch of On-Demand Decisioning, a tool allowing financial institutions to set customized authorization criteria directly on its network, on September 9, 2025. The company also introduced Agent Pay in September 2025, an AI-driven agentic payments technology designed to enable seamless, multi-method digital transactions for consumers[3][4][5].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nMastercard has emphasized expansion in value-added services, such as consulting, marketing, fraud prevention, and data insights, highlighted by CEO Michael Miebach during the October 2024 earnings call as key growth areas. No specific recent headcount or GTM hiring data identified, but recent product and solution launches suggest ongoing investment in sales and technical teams[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent funding rounds or major investment announcements identified within the last 12 months.\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nPublished its 2024 Impact Report on July 16, 2025, demonstrating significant progress on sustainability, inclusion, and digital innovation goals. Introduced notable new technologies in September 2025, including On-Demand Decisioning and Agent Pay, strengthening its AI and payments capabilities[1][3][4][5].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments, promotions, or departures in sales, revenue, or people operations roles identified within the last 12 months."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"Mastercard powers economies and empowers people in 200+ countries and territories worldwide. Together with our customers, weâre building a sustainable economy where everyone can prosper. We support a wide range of digital payments choices, making transactions secure, simple, smart and accessible. Our technology and innovation, partnerships and networks combine to deliver a unique set of products and services that help people, businesses and governments realize their greatest potential."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reczTO00FDymuDOtS', 'Aspen Technology', 'http://www.aspentech.com', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/aspen-technology', 'Bedford, MA, US', 'Computer Software', '1001 - 5000', '68', 'Aspen Technology is a growth-stage computer software company (4,215 employees) with strong commercial B2B tech fit, actively hiring for roles such as Sales Account Executive and Sales Director in Australia and Singapore. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers (e.g., VP of APJ Sales, Senior Director-Asia Pacific, Sales Directors) are present, providing quality access for recruitment. The company shows strong growth signals with revenue increases, a major acquisition, and ongoing market expansion, though current merger activity may impact immediate hiring. The combination of core sales roles, industry fit, and decision maker access makes this a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\nAspen Technology entered into a Merger Agreement with Emerson Electric Co. on January 26, 2025, with Emerson offering $240 per share for AspenTech. AspenTech’s board recommended acceptance of the merger offer, and the process includes a tender offer and subsequent merger upon satisfaction of standard conditions as disclosed in SEC filings[1][2][3].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\nAspenTech reported strong revenue growth, with total revenue rising from $257.2 million in Q2 FY24 to $303.6 million in Q2 FY25 and bookings increasing from $233.4 million to $307.5 million in the same period. The company also expanded through the acquisition of Open Grid Systems Limited in Q2 FY25, indicating ongoing market and product expansion[2].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\nNo recent venture or public funding rounds were announced in the last 12 months. Emerson’s acquisition offer, structuring a buyout at $240 per share as of January 2025, reflects significant financial backing and valuation activity instead of traditional funding events[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\nAspenTech successfully acquired Open Grid Systems Limited in the second quarter of fiscal 2025. Additionally, they reported a return to profitability, with Q2 FY25 net income reaching $20.3 million compared to a net loss of $21.5 million in Q2 FY24, alongside growing free cash flow and operational earnings[2].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\nNo recent executive appointments or key departures related to sales, revenue, or people roles identified in the last 6-12 months. No press releases or filings disclosed leadership transitions over this period[2][3]."}'::jsonb, '{"content":"AspenTech is a global software leader helping industries at the forefront of the world’s dual challenge meet the increasing demand for resources from a rapidly growing population in a profitable and sustainable manner. AspenTech solutions address complex environments where it is critical to optimize the asset design, operation and maintenance lifecycle. Through our unique combination of deep domain expertise and innovation, customers in asset-intensive industries can run their assets safer, greener, longer and faster to improve their operational excellence. To learn more, visit AspenTech.com."}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', NULL, '2025-09-17T02:09:06.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z'),
    ('reczYs3zfijKCsEfO', 'Reward Gateway', 'http://www.rewardgateway.com', 'https://uk.linkedin.com/company/reward-gateway', 'London, England', 'Technology, Information and Media,Software Development,Human Resources Services', '1,001-5,000 employees', '84', 'Reward Gateway is a growth-stage HR technology company (1,001-5,000 employees) with a strong commercial B2B SaaS focus and significant APAC operations based in Sydney. The inclusion is triggered by active hiring for a Head of Sales Development, a high-priority core sales leadership role. Multiple Tier 1 and Tier 2 decision makers are present, including the APAC Managing Director and Sales Director, providing direct access for recruitment engagement. Recent acquisition by Edenred, ongoing APAC expansion, and local office growth signal robust hiring momentum. This combination of core sales hiring, strong industry fit, decision maker access, and growth signals makes Reward Gateway a high-priority recruitment opportunity.', true, false, '{"content":"RECENT TRIGGER EVENTS:\n[LOCAL] Reward Gateway operates a significant Sydney office at Australia Square Plaza, 13/95 Pitt St, Sydney NSW 2000, serving as the Australian HQ and hub for client success and regional operations[1][4]. [REGIONAL] Reward Gateway has continued to prioritize APAC growth, supporting 4,500+ companies in 23+ countries, with a major concentration in Australia under the leadership of Kylie Green (MD, APAC)[1]. [GLOBAL] In 2023, Reward Gateway acquired US-based Fond to extend its employee recognition and rewards capabilities, and was itself acquired later that year by Edenred, which enhanced its financial backing and global offerings, including ANZ customers[1].\n\nGROWTH SIGNALS:\n[LOCAL] The Sydney office directly supports a substantial client base and maintains an active employee presence, with ongoing investments in DEI and professional growth[1]. [REGIONAL] APAC operations are led from Australia, pointing to ongoing resourcing and leadership focus in the local market[1]. [GLOBAL] The company globally employs 750+ people across 7 offices, and after the Edenred acquisition, its staffing and reach have expanded, now serving 8 million+ employees worldwide[1].\n\nRECENT FUNDING:\n[GLOBAL] Reward Gateway''s last major funding event was its acquisition by Edenred in late 2023, shifting the company from private equity ownership to a strategic corporate parent with an explicit aim of accelerating international expansion, including Australia and APAC[1].\n\nRECENT ACHIEVEMENTS:\n[LOCAL] Reward Gateway’s engagement platform is cited by Australian clients (e.g., Flight Centre, major banks) as a core part of their Employee Value Proposition, and its \"Reward Gateway for Small Business\" platform, launched in 2020, continues to see adoption[2]. [REGIONAL] The company is recognized for research insights tailored to the Australian market, offering exclusive local surveys on employee recognition and satisfaction[2]. [GLOBAL] Post-acquisition, Reward Gateway expanded its mobile and wellbeing offerings, and continues to earn high marks from HR tech analysts for its unified rewards, recognition, and communications platform[1][3].\n\nLEADERSHIP CHANGES:\n[REGIONAL] Kylie Green is the Managing Director for APAC, overseeing Australia operations[1]. [GLOBAL] Nick Burns (CEO since 2022) anchors the firm’s global direction, with a leadership team spanning operations, technology, and people, including Nebel Crowhurst (Chief People and Culture Officer) and Andy Philpott (Chief Marketing & Strategy Officer)[1]. No Australia-specific executive changes reported in the past 6-12 months.\n\n[End of synthesis based on provided and recent data, with emphasis on Sydney/AU operations per search hierarchy.]"}'::jsonb, '{"content":"&lt;p&gt;Reward Gateway, part of Edenred, is a global leader in benefits and employee engagement. We help businesses attract, engage, and retain top talent through strategic reward, recognition, and well-being solutions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Guided by our shared missions - ‘Making the World a Better Place to Work’ and ‘Enriching Connections, For Good’ - we’re committed to transforming workplaces and improving people’s daily lives.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our team embodies entrepreneurial spirit, innovation, and respect. We push boundaries, speak up, and stay human, fostering a culture where imagination thrives.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your role in our mission &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive at Reward Gateway, you’ll play a critical role in driving our mission to make the world a better place to work. You’ll represent a globally recognised brand with proven results and deep market credibility. Our scalable products and platform sit in the high-growth employee engagement and recognition space, meaning you’re selling a solution with real demand, backed by a company that clients trust. That creates the perfect foundation to grow your career, your impact, and your income.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll lead consultative sales conversations that connect deeply with client needs across the ANZ region, crafting tailored solutions that solve real business challenges in employee engagement and recognition. Working closely with SDRs, Researchers, Marketing and Client Success, you’ll bring the voice of the customer into every stage of the sales process and deliver compelling presentations and proposals that inspire action. With ownership of a dynamic pipeline, you’ll build momentum, overcome friction points, and contribute to our extraordinary sales culture, all while accurately forecasting and helping us achieve our commercial goals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible, Hybrid Working &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our office is for you to use as much as you like; as a minimum our AUS Sales Team works from our &lt;u&gt;Sydney office&lt;/u&gt; or &lt;u&gt;Melbourne office &lt;/u&gt;at least twice a week.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it For You...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;💰 &lt;strong&gt;Base $100k - $120k DOE / OTE $170k - $190k&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All uncapped.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;📈 F&lt;strong&gt;uelled pipeline&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Support from a high-performing Marketing team, alongside your own outbound prospecting, through demand generation, large-scale events, webinars, thought leadership, and targeted campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🚀 &lt;strong&gt;Career growth, your way&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Access to Elev8 high-performance programs and tailored L&amp;amp;D initiatives to guide your career in the direction that’s right for you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;📚 &lt;strong&gt;Always learning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Professional development books, e-books, and podcasts to keep you growing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🌴 &lt;strong&gt;Up to 40 days off per year&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Flexible vacation plan including public holidays, because balance matters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;💆 ♀️ &lt;strong&gt;$750 annual wellbeing allowance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Invest in your health, fitness, and wellness, your way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🧠 &lt;strong&gt;Unmind membership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Access therapy, coaching, and proactive wellbeing support for both your personal and professional life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🏅 &lt;strong&gt;Appreci8 rewards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gain monetary recognition for doing an excellent job.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🎉 &lt;strong&gt;Moments That Matter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Celebrate key life milestones with bonus payments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;🛍️ &lt;strong&gt;Big-brand discounts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enjoy huge annual savings across hundreds of retail, hospitality, travel, and lifestyle brands — for you, your friends, and your family.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief summary of core duties - a full job description can be shared on request.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Run a consultative sales approach, managing 20–30 live opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales Researchers and Sales Development Representatives to co-develop targeted account strategies, with a strong focus on self-led lead generation and opportunity creation.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead insightful business conversations tailored to client challenges.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deliver compelling sales presentations online and in person.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Craft proposals and case summaries that address client needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Client Success to share customer stories and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build win strategies to progress and close deals effectively.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own the full sales funnel, removing friction and boosting conversion.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Forecast accurately using our Salesforce framework.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hit commercial goals and contract terms with your team and sales leaders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Champion a high-performing sales culture aligned to RG’s mission.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent RG at HR industry events as a trusted brand ambassador.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience and Key Skills Required: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven B2B sales success with consistent quota attainment and the ability to create demand, at the SMB or Mid Market level in a high-volume role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing the complete sales cycle from prospecting through to close, with a passion for building relationships at every stage&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in a consultative sales cycle, including influencing and negotiating with business leaders, owners and senior leadership stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A passionate storyteller with strong presentation skills that can influence in person and in digital environments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A proven innovator with a strong bias for action and the ability quickly adapt to change in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in building value and influencing purchasing decisions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent collaboration skills with the ability to manage time effectively and efficiently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills with excellent presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Interview Process: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Telephone interview with our Senior Talent Acquisition Partner, APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;First stage online interview with our Head of Sales and Sales Director, Australia&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Presentation task and final stage interview with our Head of Sales, Sales Director, Australia and/or Managing Director, APAC&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Reward Gateway, we are committed to ensuring an inclusive and accessible recruitment process for all candidates. If you have any specific requirements or need reasonable adjustments at any stage of the recruitment journey, please let your Talent Acquisition Partner know. Your needs are important to us, and we want to ensure an equitable experience for every candidate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be comfortable. Be you. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Reward Gateway, we want all of our employees to feel comfortable bringing their passion, creativity and individuality to work. We value all cultures, backgrounds and experiences, as we truly believe that diversity drives innovation. Express yourself, join our community and help us Make the World a Better Place to Work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We hire BETTER.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From perks to people, our BETTER approach to hiring earns us more trust, happier people and more world-class talent that help us to make the world a better place to work. Find out more about Reward Gateways approach to benefits, equality, talent, technology, empathy and what you’ll get in return for joining our Mission at r&lt;u&gt;g.co/lifeatrg&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;"}'::jsonb, 'HIGH', 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQF-tmi5hldnLw/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1654562371841/reward_gateway_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=x77edoSQsDksUvnvikxbFIz90j6XIk26Ii3fnXir1Nk', '2025-09-28T14:23:53.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:18.602Z')
