    ('rec0012xeGqnyK8NW', 'Partnerships & Enterprise Sales Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/partnerships-enterprise-sales-executive-at-zenith-payments-pty-ltd-4303821821', '2025-09-23', '2025-10-23', 'Mascot, NSW', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnerships &amp;amp; Enterprise Sales Executive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mascot, Sydney&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Zenith Payments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Permanent Full-Time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Competitive base salary plus commission&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a driven sales professional with a passion for payments and partnerships?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zenith Payments is seeking a dynamic Partnerships &amp;amp; Enterprise Sales Executive to lead the charge in identifying, securing, and growing relationships with software partners and enterprise merchants. This is a high-impact role for a true sales hunter who thrives on creating opportunities and delivering tailored solutions that drive revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a key member of our commercial team, you’ll engage with senior decision-makers across industries to understand their challenges and craft innovative payment solutions using Zenith’s suite of C2B and B2B products. Your technical understanding of software integrations (e.g., APIs) and strategic mindset will be essential in navigating complex sales cycles and exceeding revenue targets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and pursue new business opportunities with major merchants and software partners.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead outreach efforts, conduct meetings, and deliver compelling proposals and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to design and deliver tailored payment solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive the full sales cycle from prospecting to deal closure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of industry trends and regulatory changes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate pipeline and reporting using CRM tools (e.g., HubSpot).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Zenith at client meetings, workshops, and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of senior sales experience, ideally within the payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of generating leads, negotiating commercial outcomes, and closing high-value deals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of Australian payment systems and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and ability to engage cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with a flair for innovation and familiarity with Blue Ocean strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM platforms and sales enablement tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Zenith Payments?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Secure, Australian-owned and operated business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fast-growing and innovative company with over 20 years in the payments industry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career development opportunities in a thriving sector.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Primarily office-based role in Mascot, Sydney.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generous leave policies including 20 annual leave days and 5 additional ‘Odd Job Days’ per year.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular staff recognition through Zenith Awards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inclusive workplace culture driven by strong company values.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Partnerships & Enterprise Sales Executive at Zenith Payments (Mascot, Sydney). Permanent, full-time role focused on identifying and securing new business with software partners and enterprise merchants. Responsibilities include managing the full sales cycle, delivering tailored payment solutions, and maintaining CRM records. Requires 5+ years of senior sales experience in payments, strong negotiation skills, and technical understanding of payment systems. Offers competitive salary, career growth, and a supportive, office-based work environment.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4303821821', 'MEDIUM', '58', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-23T14:19:24.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.742Z'),
    ('rec05rq6Ce6wD24aq', 'Account Manager - Expression of Interest', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/account-manager-expression-of-interest-at-mri-software-4269387800', '2025-09-21', '2025-11-15', 'Greater Melbourne Area, ', '&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Act as a strategic solution expert to penetrate existing accounts and build long term meaningful relationships. Drive new revenue to the business and create advocates in the marketplace for the MRI brand, reduce the attrition rate of existing customers through open and regular communication, drive whitespace revenue into existing accounts through new feature adoption, additional vertical uptake and utilization of partner integrations. This is a great opportunity for a dynamic, experienced sales professional that is focused on retaining and expanding MRIs footprint of the existing client base employing a consultative ‘solution expert’ sales approach.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Account Manager/Account Executive (Hybrid), you will be responsible for the following:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acting as a ‘solutions expert’ in helping customers with their unique business issues and strategic initiatives – become a trusted advisor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work on developing detailed plans on how customers can best partner with MRI AND ensure this plan is executed&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidently conduct client presentations, meetings, demonstrations and promote MRI at industry conferences and trade shows as required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working with the broader sales team to share ideas, knowledge and business development strategies to ensure our approach is aligned across the business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Driving and managing the sales process - targeting retention, expansion and net new opportunities, identifying client solutions, building and maintaining customer relationships, supporting/ scheduling software demonstrations, negotiating and administrating opportunities within your assigned account list&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitating the sales administration process in SFDC and Hubspot&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design account strategies and work with leadership and marketing to achieve short and long-term sales goals for targeted clients&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Schedule / deliver valuable and confident presentations to existing clients / prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop detailed account mapping to ensure aligns with relevant goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement integrated sales strategies in conjunction with other business units on shared opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceed assigned annual sales / retention quotas through upsell, cross sell and new sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handle the contracting process and sales administration (SFDC)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain relationships with existing customers through online and face to face interaction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand MRI’s positioning in the market and be well versed in product differentiators and strengths with a view to expand client footprints across your accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a healthy pipeline, excellent record keeping and forecast reporting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent company at trade association meetings to promote products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All other duties and responsibilities as assigned&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3 + years of strategic sales/account management experience in Proptech software industry or similar&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Residential Real Estate experience preferred, yet not required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record in adding value through client relationship in order to increase the revenue over a sustained period, exceeding sales targets with ability to work with the key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage with C suite confidently and interpret / convey MRI’s mission&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence in presenting to clients / prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate in a very fast paced environment with multiple priorities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of technology and ability to absorb new systems and processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, marketing, or related discipline preferred, yet not required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SFDC AND Hubspot experience preferred, yet not required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT MAKES THIS A GREAT OPPORTUNITY? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;MRI is an industry leader that has experienced double digit revenue growth year over year&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We provide great internal sales support including marketing support&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Base salary and uncapped commission. Flexible working arrangements &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Annual performance-related bonus &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;6x Flexi Fridays: knock 2.5 hours off your day on a Friday &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Me Days: an additional 3 days of leave each year to qualifying employees &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engaging, fun &amp;amp; inclusive culture: check out the MRI Software APAC Insta feed and stories! &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;MRI Software delivers innovative applications and hosted solutions that free real estate companies to elevate their business. Our flexible technology platform, along with an open and connected ecosystem, allows us to meet the unique needs of real estate businesses, from property-level management and accounting to investment modelling and analytics for the global commercial and residential markets. With nearly five decades of expertise and insight, we have grown to include offices in across the United States, the United Kingdom, Hong Kong, Singapore, Australia, South Africa, New Zealand, Canada, India, and Ireland with over 4500 team members to support our clients and their unique needs!', 'The Account Manager/Account Executive (Hybrid) is responsible for retaining and expanding MRI Software’s client base by building strong relationships, identifying growth opportunities, and driving adoption of new features and integrations. Key duties include developing account strategies, conducting client presentations, managing the sales process, and exceeding sales and retention targets. Requirements include 3+ years of sales/account management experience (preferably in Proptech), strong communication and presentation skills, and the ability to engage with senior stakeholders. Experience with SFDC and Hubspot is preferred. The role offers a competitive salary, uncapped commission, flexible work arrangements, and additional leave benefits.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4269387800', 'VERY HIGH', '92', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-21T14:10:52.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.743Z'),
    ('rec0RlxycOSkgpGCp', 'Head of Sales', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/head-of-sales-at-zib-digital-australia-4267008117', '2025-08-13', NULL, 'Melbourne, Victoria, AU', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;An experienced leader in Digital Sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive sales and support training&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work in rapidly growing and high performance agency&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reporting to CEO&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zib Digital is a leading Digital Marketing Agency specialising in SEO, Adwords, paid and organic social media marketing, and digital strategy. We operate in Australia and New Zealand, with offices in Melbourne, Brisbane, Adelaide, Auckland, and Christchurch.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For over 15 years, Zib has been supporting business growth through digital marketing solutions. With over 800 clients, ranging from SMEs to international retailers, we’ve proven we can deliver results for everyone. We love what we do.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zib is growing rapidly! We’ve tripled our salesforce in the last 9 months with our unique commercial model, and we have no intention of stopping. We are a fast-paced, high-performance digital marketing growth company with an ambitious vision. Our teams are characterised by energy ambition, and a relentless focus on high standards – and we enjoy the journey…&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our culture is king, and we are passionate about finding the best talent who love what they do, and it shows. Our social committee keeps the office fun, and we have industry-leading benefits to keep our zibsters engaged and happy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does a day in the life of a Head of Sales look like?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inspire, influence, and support the Partners and their teams (20+ people) to achieve and exceed their monthly sales goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead pitches for new business and identify opportunities to upsell/cross-sell&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend new business opportunities and drive the sales process through to closure&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assist in training and upskilling Growth Partners and Specialists in all things digital strategy, digital marketing best practices, tools and publishers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build sales opportunities through partnerships and clever commercial opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work alongside the sales enablement team and CEO to identify capability gaps, build programs and create support systems to drive performance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively drive new business opportunities through strategic networking and pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What skills do you need?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The ability to lead through influence by demonstrating what good looks like&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A combination of business acumen, a strategic approach to new businesses and an ability to close deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ultimate relationship building skills with a high EQ&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven 7 years + experience in similar sales leadership roles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated and results driven, with the ability to multitask while maintaining attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commercially savvy - &lt;u&gt;Digital marketing knowledge is essential&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and influencing skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Love the hunt, and enjoy meeting new people&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Agency experience is preferred but not essential&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where you’ll be based:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our Zib Digital Head Office in Cremorne – working with clients across Australasia. You’ll be rewarded with an exceptional package, exposure to top-tier brands, and the opportunity to make a real impact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to apply:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re only interested in applications that show you &lt;em&gt;really&lt;/em&gt; want to be part of Zib. That means no generic cover letters. Send us a tailored cover letter or a short video alongside your CV to show us why you belong on our team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Experienced Head of Digital Sales to lead and support a 20+ person team in a fast-growing digital marketing agency. Responsibilities include driving new business, leading pitches, training staff in digital strategy, and building sales through partnerships. Requires 7+ years in sales leadership, strong digital marketing knowledge, excellent communication, and relationship-building skills. Based in Cremorne, working across Australasia, reporting to the CEO. Agency experience preferred.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LOW', '36', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:47.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.743Z'),
    ('rec0hu9dXj7VjrKMV', 'Regional Sales Manager, Canberra, Australia', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/regional-sales-manager-canberra-australia-at-airlock-digital-4278510908', '2025-09-11', NULL, 'Canberra, ', 'Location: Canberra, Australia - Remote&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Who Are We?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Airlock Digital&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Airlock Digital is a global leader in application control and allowlisting. We seek to empower every organization to run only what they trust and operate free from malware and ransomware. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With rapid growth across Australia, North America, and EMEA. We are committed to our core values, respect, determination, and integrity. We support a diverse and expanding global customer base. At Airlock, we pride ourselves on being a team of humble, collaborative, and driven professionals who support one another and share a passion for cybersecurity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Regional Account Manager is responsible for driving new business and managing existing customer relationships within an assigned region and federal government accounts. This individual contributor role is customer-facing, quota-carrying, and focused on executing Airlock Digital’s go-to-market strategy in collaboration with partners and internal technical resources.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will be responsible for the full sales lifecycle – from identifying and qualifying opportunities, leading product demonstrations (with pre-sales support), through to commercial negotiation and handover to customer success&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive new business growth within the assigned territory by identifying and qualifying opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with key customers, strategic partners, and stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute against sales targets and KPIs aligned with company goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand customer business drivers, pain points, and cybersecurity maturity to position Airlock Digital''s value proposition.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with internal pre-sales engineers to deliver compelling product demonstrations and proofs of concept.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage with strategic partners, resellers and Airlock Digital Channel team to drive indirect sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accurately maintain CRM records, including pipeline forecasting and activity tracking.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay current with market trends, competitor offerings, and relevant regulatory frameworks (e.g. Essential Eight, DISP).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage sales cycle – prospects through to onboarded customers. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate commercial terms with customers. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide an orderly and seamless hand-over of new customers to our Customer Success and Customer Support teams. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend conferences and industry events to promote Airlock Digital. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years in technology sales. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience executing go-to-market strategies and managing sales cycles across channels. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of achieving or exceeding sales targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication (both verbal and written), presentation and speaking skills. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A sound understanding and working knowledge of cyber security industry, market and trends. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong connections in relevant markets and/or ability to network with business owners and technology leaders of all-size. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing full sales cycles from discovery to close.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build rapport and negotiate effectively. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of enterprise/government procurement processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Current Australian Security Clearance (preferred) or ability to obtain or reinstate&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We don’t think money is everything, but we know it is an important part of your decision to apply for a role. Additional factors considered in extending an offer include responsibilities of the job, education, location, experience, knowledge, skills, abilities, and internal equity, alignment with market data, or applicable laws. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Flexible Work Environment, Hybrid or Remote – Time Off - Paid Volunteering Time - Birthday Leave - Paid parental Leaves - Home Office Allowance&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We believe in supporting our team members both personally and professionally. Named one of the Australia’s Greatest Places to Work and 5th best technology company for 2025, we value flexibility, trust, and a work environment that empowers our team to do their best work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;We will be assessing applications as they come in, so we encourage you to send your resume through to us as soon as possible. All official job offers from our company are extended directly by our recruitment team and will be sent through an official BambooHR document for your review and signature. Please be aware that we do not ask for any personal information in the process of extending offers of employment, such as financial details. Upon acceptance of any offer, we will request such information as part of the onboarding process prior to or on your first day of employment, and only after completing a National Police Check through an authorized third-party vendor. If you receive any communication asking for personal details outside of these processes, please contact us immediately to verify the authenticity of the request. Your security is important to us, and we are committed to a safe and transparent hiring experience. No contact from recruitment agencies, thank you.&lt;/em&gt;', 'Airlock Digital is seeking a Regional Account Manager based in Canberra (remote) to drive new business and manage federal government accounts. This quota-carrying, customer-facing role involves full sales cycle management, including opportunity identification, product demonstrations, negotiations, and handover to customer success. Candidates should have 5+ years in technology sales, strong cybersecurity knowledge, experience with enterprise/government procurement, and preferably hold or be able to obtain Australian Security Clearance. The company offers a flexible work environment, competitive benefits, and a supportive culture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '53', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.743Z'),
    ('rec0invjCjUMdZSHa', 'Business Development Representative', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/business-development-representative-at-nightingale-software-4303860908', '2025-09-23', '2026-03-22', 'Greater Melbourne Area, ', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development Representative (Aged Care &amp;amp; NDIS) — East Coast (Melbourne based only)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re growing! Nightingale Software is hiring a Business Development Representative to help aged-care and NDIS providers modernise operations across the East Coast. If you love prospecting, social selling, and turning conversations into qualified opportunities, let’s talk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Focus: Aged Care, NDIS, HCP, CHSP, Support at Home providers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Territory: NSW / VIC / QLD (hybrid, with travel)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tools: HubSpot, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Comp: Competitive base + super + uncapped commission (realistic OTE $110k-120k+)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Impact: Bring real efficiency to frontline care via rostering, mobile workforce, funding claims &amp;amp; AP automation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply via LinkedIn or DM me for a confidential chat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;About Nightingale Software&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nightingale is an Australian SaaS platform built for disability, community, and aged-care providers. We streamline client &amp;amp; resource management, rostering, mobile workforce, NDIS/HCP/CHSP funding &amp;amp; claiming, and AP automation—all with local compliance at the core (including ISO 27001:2022). Our mission: help providers spend less time on admin and more time delivering quality care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As one of our Business Development Representative (BDR) you’ll build top-of-funnel pipeline across the East Coast and partner closely with Senior BDMs to progress qualified meetings and opportunities with NDIS, Aged Care, HCP, CHSP, and upcoming Support at Home providers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll combine outbound prospecting, event follow-ups, inbound leads, social selling, video outreach, and tight CRM hygiene to open doors with CEOs, COOs, CFOs, Clinical/Operations leaders, and IT/Transformation teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Drive outbound sequences (email, phone, LinkedIn, video) to book qualified meetings for Senior BDMs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Research and segment named accounts by provider type, funding stream (NDIS/HCP/CHSP/SAH), and region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Turn event leads and partnerships (e.g., industry forums, Alliance20, webinars) into pipeline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualify using clear criteria (fit, pain, timeline, stakeholders, funding mix, tech stack).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Maintain spotless HubSpot hygiene: tasks, notes, next steps, sequences, and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Collaborate with Marketing on messaging, sequences, and content that resonates by persona.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Report weekly on activity, meetings set, conversion rates, and pipeline influenced.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;1–3+ years in BDR/SDR (SaaS or healthcare tech preferred) with a track record of meeting setting targets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Familiarity with NDIS / Aged Care / HCP / CHSP / Support at Home landscape—or strong aptitude to learn fast.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Confident with HubSpot CRM (or similar), Sales Navigator, video outreach, and data-driven cadence management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent written &amp;amp; verbal communication; resilient, curious, and coachable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full Australian work rights; based in VIC (hybrid). Willing to travel for events and customer visits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nice to have: experience selling into providers, knowledge of SCHADS/roster operations, and basic procurement/RFP exposure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Why Nightingale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Meaningful impact: your work helps providers return time to care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Growth &amp;amp; coaching: clear 30/60/90 plan, call coaching, and enablement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Modern stack: HubSpot, Sales Nav, Zoominfo (where available).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rewards: competitive base + super + uncapped commission (realistic OTE $110k–$120k+).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexibility: hybrid work (office once a fortnight), travel to industry events, and autonomy to experiment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply via LinkedIn or message me for a confidential chat. If you prefer email, send your CV and a short note on a pipeline win you’re proud of to clara.buonanno@nightingalesoftware.com.au with subject “BDR – East Coast”.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Business Development Representative (Melbourne-based) at Nightingale Software, responsible for generating and qualifying leads with aged care and NDIS providers across NSW, VIC, and QLD. Key tasks include outbound prospecting, managing CRM (HubSpot), and booking meetings for senior sales. Requires 1–3+ years BDR/SDR experience (SaaS or healthcare tech preferred), strong communication skills, and willingness to travel. Offers hybrid work, competitive salary with uncapped commission (OTE $110k–$120k+), and opportunities for growth.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4303860908', 'MEDIUM', '54', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-23T14:27:37.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.743Z'),
    ('rec0vXq7B2CDkHe0C', 'SMB Account Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/smb-account-executive-at-clickup-4300986569', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', 'ClickUp is revolutionizing the way the world works. As the only all-in-one productivity platform built from day one for true convergence, ClickUp unifies tasks, docs, chat, calendar, enterprise search, and more—supercharged by context-driven AI. While others scramble to bundle fragmented tools or bolt on AI, we anticipated this future and made it our foundation from the start. Headquartered in San Diego with a rapidly expanding global footprint, we empower over three million teams to break free from silos and reclaim their time—saving at least one day every week. Join ClickUp, one of the fastest-growing SaaS companies on the planet, and help millions of users transform the way they work. We’re not just building software. We’re shaping the future of work. Come join us in building the future—together. 🦄&amp;nbsp; We’re looking for an Account Executive who has a consistent track record of exceeding quota via net new account acquisition, plus some account management experience with expansion and renewals. You should have experience with consultative sales processes, selling SaaS (ideally productivity solutions), and working with mid-size to large companies, across a variety of industries.&amp;nbsp;You are a solution seller by nature, training, and experience, who is genuinely curious and confident speaking with customers. And, you’re a persuasive self-starter, a good listener, while having a high degree of personal accountability in communicating cross-functionally and maintaining a healthy sales pipeline. Since a majority of your time will be spent on emails, calls, and web conferences with customers, we expect an infectiously positive attitude when prospecting, presenting and closing!&amp;nbsp;We believe the product is the real reason for converting. Our secret sauce should be framed around how we can ensure people see the value of the solution we provide. If you’re ready for the ride of a lifetime into the billion-dollar unicorn club, please, by all means, click the apply button!&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work all new business leads with a focus on the APAC region.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve and consistently exceed pipeline and sales targets by converting free trials, marketing-qualified leads, or demo requests into paid customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master the product and be able to field customer service and product questions from your leads.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform customer presentations and demos via online web conferencing tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with the Growth and Marketing teams to optimize lead generation and sales conversion tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify customer segments and new opportunities to improve the quality of the sales pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;1+ years of relevant full sales cycle experience where you were responsible for converting net new prospects to growing and retaining existing customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1-3+ years of SaaS sales cycle experience.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written, verbal, and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Process-driven with diligent attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with completing and leading Requests for Information or Requests for Quotes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We work a lot and love it, you LOVE work as much as we do and can dedicate your life to this while it gets off the ground.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with project management software or other productivity tools.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with e-commerce signup flows and field sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with Slack, Front, Salesforce, POCUS and Outreach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Some exposure to Customer Service and Technical Support processes, and sending responses quickly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You prefer building rapport with customers over annoying, aggressive sales tactics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unsure if you meet all the qualifications of this job description but are deeply excited about the role? We hire based on ambition, grit, and a passion for improving the way people work. If you think ClickUp is the company for you, we encourage you to apply!&lt;/p&gt;At ClickUp, we assess every candidate based on the potential impact they can have. We hire the best people for the job and support each person’s journey to build their boldest career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;C&lt;span class="ql-comment"&gt;lickUp is an Equal Opportunity Employer, and qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, or national origin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ClickUp collects and processes personal data in accordance with applicable data protection laws.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you are a European Job Applicant, see our privacy policy&amp;nbsp;for further details.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you are a Philippine Job Applicant, see our &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;privacy policy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; and our &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Philippine Data Privacy Notice&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; for further details. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note we are unable to sponsor or take over sponsorship of an employment visa for roles outside of engineering and product at this time. Sponsorship for engineering and product roles is not guaranteed, but is instead based on the business needs for that specific role at that time. Please reach out to the recruiter with any questions.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ClickUp Talent Acquisition will only initiate contact via an &lt;strong&gt;@clickup.com&lt;/strong&gt; email or through our official careers portal on clickup.com. We will never request fees, payments, or sensitive personal information. Please disregard any offers received outside these channels and report them to support@clickup.com.&lt;/p&gt;', 'ClickUp is seeking an Account Executive to drive new business and manage accounts in the APAC region. The role involves converting leads into customers, conducting product demos, and collaborating with marketing to optimize sales. Candidates should have 1+ years of full sales cycle experience, preferably in SaaS, strong communication skills, and a consultative sales approach. Experience with productivity tools and CRM platforms is a plus. The company values ambition, grit, and a passion for improving work processes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '80', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:43.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.743Z'),
