rturing prospects, managing the sales cycle from lead to close, and coordinating meetings between sales reps and clients. Requires 1+ year B2B sales experience, strong communication, problem-solving, presentation, and negotiation skills. CRM experience (Salesforce preferred) is a plus. Birdeye offers a fast-paced, innovative culture with opportunities for career growth.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '65', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recjCYDJVAPxUNWXf', 'Enterprise Sales Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/enterprise-sales-executive-at-absorb-software-4274226297', '2025-09-12', NULL, ', ', '“I have worked in many roles over my 7 years at Absorb and in each and every one of them I have been supported by my team and my leadership. As an Account Executive this support is essential if I am going to be successful and every day that I am at Absorb and in every interaction I have with my colleagues I feel set up for success. Everyone here works towards the same goal of being the best we can be. We work to consistently improve our processes and product which means we are never getting left behind in the market. All of this together means that when I am speaking with prospects I can sell a product and a company I believe in.” – Mark Collery, Enterprise Sales ExecutiveAbout the role:Are you someone always seeking that adrenaline rush at work? Perhaps you like fast-paced environments where your biggest competition is your last best achievement. You have the autonomy to move things forward, knowing that the next move or decision could easily make or break a deal. You love the chase, knowing that the more you push yourself, the more likely it is that you will succeed and be that much closer to a successful closed sale. There is nothing quite like the satisfaction when you reach your targets, knowing that you not only did it for yourself but for the team as well! Still reading? then look no further, as Absorb''s Sales Executive team is growing!You are a seasoned SAAS sales professional, who has extensive knowledge in SAAS and LMS software sales. You are a self-starter, who is motivated from within and loves being part of a team environment. Further to this, you have an organized and meticulous approach to pipeline management and use a highly communicative manner to interact with your prospects.Working in our APAC territory, you will help develop new business by selling our products to inbound leads. Your high-energy approach will include impeccable communication, high-velocity turnaround times and attention to detail that is able to build rapport with our prospects. No KPI is too daunting for someone with your drive to succeed and ability to make realistic decisions efficiently and effectively.Absorb Culture - Absorb LMSWhat you’ll do:Contact prospects via phone, email, and /or face-to-face in order to complete salesWork collaboratively with the Support, Marketing, Client Success and Product teams to become an expert in Absorb LMS and the overall learning management landscapeDemonstrate Absorb LMS functionality and provide pricing options to prospectsPresent Absorb LMS quotes with approval from the EVP of Global Sales to prospectsAssist Accounts Receivable collections if necessary in a professional manner, ensure all relationships, both external and internal are maintainedUse customer and prospect contact activities tools and systems, and update relevant information held in these systemsWhat you’ll bring:At least 5 years in selling B2B Software/SaaSTrack record of over-achieving quota on a monthly, quarterly and yearly basisExperience working in SalesforceProficient with corporate productivity and web presentation toolsExcellent verbal and written communications skillsStrong listening and presentation skillsAbility to multi-task, prioritize, and manage time effectivelyAdditional preferred qualifications:A Bachelors degree in Communications, Business or Psychology would be considered an asset, but not requiredExperience with the Sandler Sales MethodologyTechnologies we use:Absorb LMS, Salesforce, Salesloft, LinkedIn SalesNavigator, GongAre you ready to become an Absorber? What we offer: Fully remote-first work with flexible work arrangementsSuperannuation ContributionEligibility for two different bonus plansNew Hire Equipment Allowance and monthly Flex Allowance to support your successEndless opportunity for career growth and internal mobilityEmployee driven DE&I programsWho are we?Absorb Software is a remote-first company that provides online training solutions to leading organizations around the world. Absorb is a cloud-based learning management system (LMS) engineered to inspire learning and fuel business productivity. Our online learning platform combines forward-thinking technology built to scale as our customer’s organizations grow. We empower learners to enrich their lives, workplaces and communities.Our values are simple:We achieve exceptional results by genuinely caring about each other and the work we doWe’re united, and we grow through our commitment to elevating continual learning!Absorb is proud to be an equal opportunity employer, we celebrate diversity and are committed to creating a safe and inclusive environment for all our people. All employment decisions are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications. In the event a current Absorb employee would like to apply for this role they will inform their supervisor prior to submitting their application. Successful candidates for this position will be subject to pre-employment background screening, including a criminal record check and must be able to show proof of legal eligibility to work in the country they have applied to without sponsorship.Should you require any accommodation during the recruitment process, please indicate this on your application and we will work with you to meet your accessibility needs. For any questions, please contact us at accessiblecareers@absorblms.com', 'Experienced SaaS Account Executive needed to drive new business in the APAC region by selling Absorb LMS to inbound leads. Must have 5+ years B2B SaaS sales experience, proven quota overachievement, strong communication, and pipeline management skills. Responsibilities include prospect outreach, product demonstrations, quote presentations, and collaboration with internal teams. Remote-first role offering flexible work, career growth, and competitive benefits. Proficiency in Salesforce and sales tools required.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '77', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recjTM0fd6iqoEJhl', 'Business Development Director', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/business-development-director-at-objective-corporation-4304644064', '2025-09-23', '2025-10-23', 'Melbourne, VIC', 'At Objective , we create software that makes a difference. With over 400 people and five development labs spread across Australia, New Zealand, the United States of America, and the United Kingdom, Objective is a leading developer of SaaS solutions for the government.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Business Development Director - Content Solutions will be based in Melbourne and is responsible for sourcing new customers for Australia wide. They achieve this by aligning and understanding business processes while leveraging senior relationships to develop business opportunities in the public sector and regulated industries.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role reports to the VP, Sales (ANZ) and is an individual contributor with no people management responsibilities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day In Your Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate domain expertise in the public sector and regulated industries while providing value and insight to key stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve annual revenue targets for the sale of software and professional services.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop appropriate pipeline to achieve current and future year’s quota.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage a strong network and develop relevant industry contacts and influencers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records in sales tools such as Salesforce (CRM) and TAS (opportunity management).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continually develop Strategic Sales Skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support Objective team members involved in sales processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with functional teams in pre-sales, services, product management, and marketing to respond to tenders, bids, and opportunities to grow revenue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver an effective Territory Plan.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Skills, Experience And Beyond&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven sales ability, including outstanding negotiation skills and ability to persuade at all levels of business, including GM, CEO, CIO, CFO, Dept. Heads etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experienced in Solution Selling, Strategic Selling or Challenger Selling methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative approach to selling with highly developed interpersonal/relationship-building skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Able to manage and execute long sales cycles (6-24 months).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced user of corporate sales tools (Salesforce, TAS, etc.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work arrangements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discounted health insurance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rich learning and enablement programs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A team culture built on directness, support, openness, and shared success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular team events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A gender-equal and inclusive workplace&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you do not tick every box, do not let that stop you. We value potential, learning agility, and diverse perspectives just as much as experience, and we encourage you to apply.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Objective, we recognise and celebrate our diverse team as pivotal to our strong employee engagement and our high-performing culture, underpinned by Our Values .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on any protected characteristics or on any other basis prohibited by applicable laws in the regions where we operate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To ensure a positive experience, please inform our Talent Team of any adjustments or accommodations you may require during the recruitment process, so we can support you effectively.', 'The Business Development Director – Content Solutions at Objective is responsible for sourcing new customers across Australia, focusing on the public sector and regulated industries. Based in Melbourne, this individual contributor role involves achieving sales targets, developing pipelines, leveraging industry networks, and collaborating with internal teams. Key requirements include proven sales ability, experience with solution selling, strong relationship-building skills, and proficiency with sales tools like Salesforce. The company offers hybrid work, learning programs, and an inclusive culture.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4304644064', 'HIGH', '73', 'Business Development and Sales', '2025-09-23T14:36:26.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recjliCQ50rRqGlhO', 'Sales Development Representative Inbound AU - Remote', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-representative-inbound-au-remote-at-employment-hero-4305416807', '2025-09-26', '2025-10-26', 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Employment Hero is on a mission to make employment easier and more valuable for everyone. Our Employment Operating System brings hiring, HR, payroll and benefits into an all-in-one solution.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since our inception in 2014, we’ve scaled to a $2 billion valuation and gained a presence in 6 countries globally - Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Malaysia, the UK and Canada. We now service over 300,000 businesses and more than 2 million employees.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The EH Way&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Employment Hero, we’re proud of our unique DNA, which we call The EH Way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Mission First - everything we do (from what we work on, to how we allocate capital and where we focus) is driven by our Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Remote First - we champion a remote environment with a preference for asynchronous communication and a high degree of autonomy&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are AI First - we are committed to using AI to accelerate our mission; AI is not just a tool, it’s a fundamental part of how we operate, innovate, and scale&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are Apolitical - we do not take a position on political or social topics, unless it relates to our Mission&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We Live by Our Values - we role model our values 100% of the time&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We Expect High Performance - we set a high standard and we’re not satisfied with being average&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Kickstart your sales career: $72k base, $128,640 OTE uncapped, 140%+ achievable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Inbound Sales Development Representative, you’ll be working with our ANZ sales team under the guidance of a Sales Development Manager and will be instrumental in shaping and driving a surge in qualified leads and opportunities, contributing directly to our bold goal of transforming workforce management at Employment Hero. Through strategic prospecting, engaging communication, and strong relationship-building, you’ll empower businesses to thrive and employees to excel with our innovative solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role must be based in Australia.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Your key focus areas will be:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualify and Convert Inbound Leads - Efficiently assess and qualify inbound leads to ensure they meet ideal customer profiles, then book high-quality meetings for the sales team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Activity Targets - Consistently generate a set number of qualified opportunities per month, contributing to overall revenue and sales growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fast &amp;amp; Effective Lead Response Time - Engage with inbound leads promptly to maximise conversion rates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CRM Accuracy &amp;amp; Data Management - Maintain up to date and accurate records of lead interactions and progress in the CRM to support sales forecasting and decision-making.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This will include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Initiating contact with potential customers through inbound inquiries to source new sales opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conducting discovery calls to effectively understand customer needs and requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Routing promising opportunities to the appropriate Account Executives for further development and closure&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conducting thorough account research, identifying key decision-makers, and generating interest in our offerings&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and growing your prospect database within your assigned segment&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborating on delivering engaging online demos to prospects as needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;To thrive at Employment Hero, you’ll need to embody The EH Way - operating with focus, agility, and an obsession with impact. For this role, you’ll also bring:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in high-volume inbound sales (B2B)Familiarity with tools like LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Lusha, ZoomInfo, and Outreach&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of consistently exceeding targets&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong phone presence and resilience, comfortable with spending significant time on the phone&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skillsStrong listening and presentation abilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task, prioritise, and manage time effectively&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Employment Hero, we don’t just talk about a better way to work - we live it. Joining Employment Hero means:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will work remotely, with the flexibility to own your time and impact&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will access cutting-edge tools to amplify your work, knowledge and outputs &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll surround yourself with ambitious, outcome-driven colleagues who challenge you to do the best work of your life&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll own ESOP (employee share options) in one of the world’s fastest-growing tech companies &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll also have access to a wide range of benefits that includes: a very generous paternity leave policy, subsidised egg freezing (so you can make the choice that’s right for you, on your terms), a WFH office expense budget, and outstanding learning &amp;amp; development opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;At Employment Hero, we are committed to safeguarding the privacy of your application data. To understand how we do so, you can read our Applicant Privacy Policy here: https://employmenthero.com/legals/applicant-policy/&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Employment Hero celebrates diverse perspectives and experiences, we invite people of all backgrounds and identities to apply for this position.&lt;br&gt;', 'Employment Hero is hiring an Inbound Sales Development Representative (remote, Australia-based) to qualify and convert inbound B2B leads, book meetings, and support sales growth. Responsibilities include lead qualification, discovery calls, CRM management, and collaborating with Account Executives. Requires experience in high-volume inbound sales, strong communication skills, and proficiency with sales tools. Offers remote work, flexible hours, ESOP, and comprehensive benefits.', 'full-time', 'Entry level', '4305416807', 'VERY HIGH', '97', 'Sales', '2025-09-28T03:58:00.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recjuo8wTYUVHXhXK', 'Sales Development Associate', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-associate-at-myriota-4299547286', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Adelaide, SA', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Myriota&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Myriota, we''re revolutionizing global connectivity with our patented direct-to-satellite technology, delivering secure, cost-effective, and low-maintenance IoT solutions with long battery life. Our innovations are transforming industries like agriculture, logistics, defense, and more, enabling real-time access to critical data anywhere, anytime.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The incredible opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Based at our headquarters'' located in Adelaide''s vibrant Lot Fourteen, this dynamic, dual-focus role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of sales coordination and business development. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Sales Director ANZ, you will generate leads, support sales operations, build strong customer relationships, and play a key role in growing the pipeline across the region. Your work will directly contribute to expanding Myriota’s footprint and shaping our go-to-market strategy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How you will drive success:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expand Customer Base &amp;amp; Drive Revenue:&lt;/strong&gt; Generate leads through email, calls, and relationship building across global markets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Generation &amp;amp; Qualification: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify and qualify new opportunities to keep the pipeline strong.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CRM &amp;amp; Pipeline Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Maintain accurate CRM data to support sales decisions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Process Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Assist the Sales Director with meetings, follow-ups, and customer communication.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Research &amp;amp; Strategy: &lt;/strong&gt;Monitor industry trends and competitors to inform sales tactics.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Engagement: &lt;/strong&gt;Connect with prospects, understand their needs, and position Myriota’s solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Reporting: &lt;/strong&gt;Align with sales and marketing on targets and report on pipeline progress.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt; Build expertise in Myriota’s tech to clearly communicate value&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we value in you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success in sales, business development, or sales support, preferably within ANZ&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of sales processes, CRM systems, and customer engagement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing sales operations and supporting pipeline growth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive lead generation and qualification skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and relationship-building abilities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Organised, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple priorities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, adaptable, and collaborative team player&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Myriota stands out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Purpose That Matters&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Myriota, we''re driven by a bold vision: a world made better through a pervasive Internet of Things. Everything we do is about delivering real, lasting impact for individuals, industries, and the planet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Values That Drive Us&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We don’t just write values on walls, we live them. We build solutions that disrupt and delight, deliver relentlessly, embrace challenges, measure what matters, and always have each other’s backs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Growth That Empowers&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We invest in your potential with tailored development and opportunities to take on hard problems because growth comes from challenge, not comfort.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Flexibility With Purpose&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Whether it''s work-life balance, continuous learning, or space to follow your passions, we empower you to bring your best in and out of work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;A Team That Sticks Together&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re in this for the long haul, and for each other. With mental health support, paid parental leave, volunteering days, birthday leave, and comprehensive health coverage, we take care of our people in good times and bad.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovation doesn’t come from playing it safe.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Myriota, we are building something bold and we know innovation comes from diverse experiences, not cookie-cutter CVs.If you bring curiosity, drive, and a willingness to grow, we want to hear from you.Even if you don’t meet every requirement, your unique perspective might be exactly what we need.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We''re excited to be hiring directly and are not seeking support from recruitment agencies. Thanks for respecting this approach.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Myriota is seeking a Sales Coordinator & Business Development professional based in Adelaide to support lead generation, sales operations, and customer relationship management across the ANZ region. Reporting to the Sales Director, you will drive pipeline growth, assist with sales processes, conduct market research, and collaborate with sales and marketing teams. Candidates should have proven sales or business development experience, strong CRM and communication skills, and be organized and proactive. Myriota offers a purpose-driven, innovative work environment with growth opportunities and employee support.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '61', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recjyhYhzvwOxfwNI', 'Technical Sales Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/technical-sales-executive-at-hello-clever-4294944999', '2025-09-24', '2025-11-07', 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;About Hello Clever&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Hello Clever isn’t your average fintech. We move fast, challenge, and make sure payments actually work for people. We’re proudly female-led, and we’re the first in Australia to combine real-time payments with Instant Cashback Rewards and intelligent insight. Our platform enables seamless, secure, and rewarding transactions, both in-store and online, driving business growth and enhancing customer experiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Technical Sales Executive at our payments company, you’ll bridge the gap between technology and client needs, helping merchants and partners unlock the full potential of our solutions. This hybrid role combines in-office collaboration with the flexibility to work remotely, giving you the best of both worlds. You’ll be partnering with our Account Executives during the sales cycle in order to deliver tailored solutions that drive customer success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with merchants, partners, and enterprise clients &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand client payment requirements and recommend tailored solutions &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deliver engaging product demos and presentations &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product, engineering, and compliance teams to ensure seamless solution delivery &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the sales team to drive end-to-end sales process and ensure success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Keep up to date with payment industry trends, compliance requirements, and competitor offerings &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2–3 years’ experience in technical sales, pre-sales, account management, or business development (ideally within payments, fintech, SaaS, or financial services) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of payment gateways, acquiring, card processing, and/or alternative payment methods (advantageous) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Able to translate complex technical capabilities into clear, commercial benefits &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, presentation, and negotiation skills &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive, driven, and target-oriented with a solutions-focused mindset &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us? &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Innovative Product: Be part of a company at the forefront of real-time payments and loyalty innovation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Growth Opportunity: Play a key role in shaping Hello Clever’s expansion in the Australian market. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive Compensation: Attractive salary package with uncapped commission potential. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Supportive Culture: Join a passionate, fast-paced team that values collaboration, innovation, and impact. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To Apply&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We like to keep things simple, but we also want to make sure this is the right fit for both of us. Here’s what to expect: &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Virtual Chat – A casual video call to get to know you, your experience, and what makes you tick. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Meet the Team – An in-person catch-up at our office to see if we vibe and chat about how you’d make this role your own. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Show Us Your Thinking – A short presentation where you’ll bring some ideas to life (nothing scary, we promise). &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If that sounds like your kind of process, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ready to Make Your Mark? APPLY NOW via careers@helloclever.co', 'Hello Clever is seeking a Technical Sales Executive to support merchants and partners in leveraging its real-time payments and rewards platform. The role involves building client relationships, understanding payment needs, delivering product demos, and collaborating with internal teams to ensure successful solution delivery. Candidates should have 2–3 years’ experience in technical sales or related fields, strong communication skills, and a proactive, solutions-focused approach. The position offers hybrid work, growth opportunities, and a competitive compensation package.', 'full-time', 'Not Applicable', '4294944999', 'HIGH', '83', 'Consulting', '2025-09-25T05:16:04.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reckJe8kPrcepaYRt', 'Senior Enterprise Sales Executive, New and Existing Accounts', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-enterprise-sales-executive-new-and-existing-accounts-at-akamai-technologies-4306898633', '2025-09-28', NULL, ', ', 'Job DescriptionWould you like to work in a dynamic sales-growth role?Do you love collaborating across teams to deliver customer success?Join our world-class Security Technology Group!The Security business operates as a Sales Pursuit Team with deep domain knowledge of enterprises'' digital business. That includes network infrastructure and application security requirements. As a Sales Specialist you will collaborate with the wider Akamai team and channel partners to pursue and generate sales opportunities.Partner with the bestOur Enterprise Security team focuses on highly scalable security products. It enables us to provide our customers with high-quality Application Security and Zero Trust solutions. Our security solutions include API Security, DNS Security, Zero Trust Access and Micro-segmentation to protect our customers. Our goal is to secure, protect and accelerate all enterprise communication as a cloud security service.As an Enterprise Sales Executive Senior New and Existing Accounts, you will be responsible for:Being a leader in driving the Enterprise Security agenda internally and externally.Possessing charisma, energy and finesse to be a leader in driving the Enterprise Security agenda internally and externallyBeing adaptive, creative and resourceful, with a desire to operate in a start-up, undefined and matrix modeDemonstrating Enterprise Domain Expertise - Infrastructure, applications, networking or security background(s) in selling to senior executivesDo What You LoveTo be successful in this role you will:Have a proven track record of creating interest and pipeline within new or existing accountsBe able to understand why customers have brought from Akamai and articulate these in anecdotes or case-studiesDemonstrate experience working with multiple teams including Sales, SE, Customer Success, Renewals and Customer AdvocacyHave experience leading teams within a matrixed organizationDemonstrate excellent communication and presentation skillsHave the following experience: Cybersecurity including WAF and API Security, Zero trust technologies such as SASE and Micro Segmentation (ex. Cisco Tetration, VMware NSX), Firewall.Work in a way that works for youFlexBase, Akamai''s Global Flexible Working Program, is based on the principles that are helping us create the best workplace in the world. When our colleagues said that flexible working was important to them, we listened. We also know flexible working is important to many of the incredible people considering joining Akamai. FlexBase, gives 95% of employees the choice to work from their home, their office, or both (in the country advertised). This permanent workplace flexibility program is consistent and fair globally, to help us find incredible talent, virtually anywhere. We are happy to discuss working options for this role and encourage you to speak with your recruiter in more detail when you apply.Learn what makes Akamai a great place to workConnect with us on social and see what life at Akamai is like!We power and protect life online, by solving the toughest challenges, together.At Akamai, we''re curious, innovative, collaborative and tenacious. We celebrate diversity of thought and we hold an unwavering belief that we can make a meaningful difference. Our teams use their global perspectives to put customers at the forefront of everything they do, so if you are people-centric, you''ll thrive here.Working for youBenefitsAt Akamai, we will provide you with opportunities to grow, flourish, and achieve great things. Our benefit options are designed to meet your individual needs for today and in the future. We provide benefits surrounding all aspects of your life:Your healthYour financesYour familyYour time at workYour time pursuing other endeavorsOur benefit plan options are designed to meet your individual needs and budget, both today and in the future.About UsAkamai powers and protects life online. Leading companies worldwide choose Akamai to build, deliver, and secure their digital experiences helping billions of people live, work, and play every day. With the world''s most distributed compute platform from cloud to edge we make it easy for customers to develop and run applications, while we keep experiences closer to users and threats farther away.Join usAre you seeking an opportunity to make a real difference in a company with a global reach and exciting services and clients? Come join us and grow with a team of people who will energize and inspire you!Akamai Technologies is an Affirmative Action, Equal Opportunity Employer that values the strength that diversity brings to the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, race/ethnicity, protected veteran status, disability, or other protected group status.', 'The Enterprise Sales Executive at Akamai will drive sales of security solutions—including Application Security, API Security, DNS Security, and Zero Trust technologies—to new and existing enterprise accounts. The role requires strong experience in cybersecurity sales, excellent communication skills, and the ability to collaborate across teams in a matrixed environment. Flexible working options are available.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4306898633', 'MEDIUM', '45', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-28T14:36:12.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reckRz3IrodpXD53Q', 'Territory Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/territory-manager-at-baidam-pty-ltd-4296871343', '2025-09-08', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who is Baidam Solutions?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Baidam Solutions is a Supply Nation certified, award-winning Indigenous Cyber Security consultancy servicing Enterprise customers, Government Departments and Agencies, and Not-for-Profit organisations. We are a profit-for-purpose business delivering high-quality cyber security outcomes, with over 50% of our gross profits reinvested into "The Baidam Initiative"—creating ICT training and employment pathways for the First Nations community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Partnering with leading technology vendors and providing Professional and Managed Services, Baidam delivers:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cyber Security Products and Licensing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cyber Security Professional Services (Penetration Testing, GRC Consultancy, Security Awareness Training)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cyber Security Managed Services (SIEM-as-a-Service, Managed Endpoint Detection, Vulnerability Management as a Service, Incident Response)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;IT Recruitment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As Senior Territory Manager, you will grow Baidam’s enterprise and government business in NSW, reporting to the National Sales Director. This role is new to the team and reflects our growth trajectory.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive new business by proactively identifying, targeting, and developing opportunities with large enterprise and government clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and execute strategic business development and territory plans, focusing on growing your presence and pipeline with key logos and high-value clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead complex, multi-solution sales cycles—including security, cloud, network, and modern workplace solutions—crafting tailored solutions from Baidam’s service portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with presales, marketing, delivery, and leadership to convert insight into value for clients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop strong, trusted-advisor relationships with customer and vendor stakeholders at all levels, including C-suite.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and contribute to tender responses and submissions, with precision and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage industry insights and market data to inform customer solutions and refine your sales strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Articulate the Baidam Solutions value proposition, demonstrating both commercial and social impact.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain, qualify, and accurately forecast sales pipeline in Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve and exceed quarterly sales targets through a process-driven, structured approach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5+ years’ experience selling to enterprise and/or government clients in NSW with a successful record in cyber security and complex IT solution sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven new business “hunter”—skilled at opening doors, building trust, and closing in competitive markets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in Cyber Security Sales, hitting and exceeding targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Structured, process-driven approach to pipeline, territory management, and deal execution.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen, curiosity, urgency, and outcome focus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal, negotiation, and relationship skills, with the confidence to engage at C-level.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Professionalism, integrity, and ability to work independently as a self-starter.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of and experience with vendor partnerships and channel ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing and responding to complex tenders and proposals in the public sector.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commitment to Baidam’s mission of social impact and diversity.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll be closely supported by the leadership team and rewarded for your sales from day 1 via a highly competitive commission structure.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Baidam is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people of all ages, people living with a disability, LGBTIQ+ candidates, and people from multi-cultural backgrounds.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Baidam Solutions, an Indigenous cyber security consultancy, seeks a Senior Territory Manager to grow enterprise and government business in NSW. The role involves driving new business, managing complex sales cycles, building strategic relationships, and achieving sales targets. Candidates should have 5+ years in cyber security sales to enterprise/government clients, strong negotiation skills, and experience with tenders and vendor partnerships. The position offers leadership support and competitive commissions, aligned with Baidam’s social impact mission.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'VERY HIGH', '92', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:46.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reckdgmNhZ3KPlxRI', 'Account Executive (Existing Business), Commercial', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/account-executive-existing-business-commercial-at-intercom-4289131624', '2025-09-20', '2025-10-20', 'Sydney, NSW', 'Intercom is the AI Customer Service company on a mission to help businesses provide incredible customer experiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI agent Fin, the most advanced customer service AI agent on the market, lets businesses deliver always-on, impeccable customer service and ultimately transform their customer experiences for the better. Fin can also be combined with our Helpdesk to become a complete solution called the Intercom Customer Service Suite, which provides AI enhanced support for the more complex or high touch queries that require a human agent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2011 and trusted by nearly 30,000 global businesses, Intercom is setting the new standard for customer service. Driven by our core values, we push boundaries, build with speed and intensity, and consistently deliver incredible value to our customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What''s the opportunity?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an Account Executive (Existing Business), you will be a key member of the team leading the growth of our existing business. We’re building a world-class sales organization, and the road ahead is going to be very exciting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Intercom, we are striving to do sales differently. We are asking our customers to put Intercom at the core of their businesses, and we can only do this by putting them at the core of ours. We strongly believe in the overall growth and continued development of each new hire. In joining the Existing Business team at Intercom, you join a community that believes in development and promotion from within. As a rapidly expanding business, there is a high degree of opportunity for progression, creativity, and ownership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What will I be doing?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with Intercom’s small business customers ensuring revenue growth and customer retention&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with current customers to understand their business pains, and provide solutions based on our platform to alleviate them&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic territory plans outlining opportunities for upsell, cross-sell, expansion to new business units, and achieve business goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop advanced knowledge of your customers'' businesses and goals while accurately forecasting sales pipeline&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Marketing, Product, and Customer Success by providing customer feedback to drive product innovation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track and report all key metrics related to customer growth, retention and Intercom product usage growth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage in team development and mentoring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;What skills do I need?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2+ years managing a large book of business; 150 accounts (retention, renewals, &amp;amp; account growth) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1+ years selling SaaS products&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience managing procurement processes &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong sales instincts and track record hitting and exceeding quota&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communicator &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable and energized operating and problem-solving in a fast-moving organization. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exhibits a growth mindset, intellectual curiosity, and ambition&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to build and maintain deep client relationships across levels in complex organizations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable history of leadership, with both immediate and cross-functional teammates&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are a well-treated bunch, with awesome benefits! If there’s something important to you that’s not on this list, talk to us!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary and equity in a fast-growing start-up&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Catered lunch every weekday, plus a fully stocked kitchen&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Regular compensation reviews - we reward great work!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible paid time off policy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Healthcare stipend towards private health insurance for you and your partner/spouse&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MacBooks are our standard, but we also offer Windows for certain roles when needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policies &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Intercom has a hybrid working policy. We believe that working in person helps us stay connected, collaborate easier and create a great culture while still providing flexibility to work from home. We expect employees to be in the office at least three days per week.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We have a radically open and accepting culture at Intercom. We avoid spending time on divisive subjects to foster a safe and cohesive work environment for everyone. As an organization, our policy is to not advocate on behalf of the company or our employees on any social or political topics out of our internal or external communications. We respect personal opinion and expression on these topics on personal social platforms on personal time, and do not challenge or confront anyone for their views on non-work related topics. Our goal is to focus on doing incredible work to achieve our goals and unite the company through our core values.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Intercom values diversity and is committed to a policy of Equal Employment Opportunity. Intercom will not discriminate against an applicant or employee on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, national origin, ancestry, sex, gender, age, physical or mental disability, veteran or military status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, marital status, or any other legally recognized protected basis under federal, state, or local law.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Is this role not quite what you''re looking for? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join our Talent Community&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; to stay connected with us.&lt;/strong&gt;', 'Intercom is seeking an Account Executive (Existing Business) to drive growth and retention among small business customers. Responsibilities include managing a large book of accounts, identifying upsell and cross-sell opportunities, building client relationships, and collaborating with internal teams. Candidates should have 2+ years of account management experience, 1+ year in SaaS sales, strong sales skills, and a proven record of exceeding targets. The role offers competitive salary, equity, flexible time off, and a hybrid work policy. Intercom values diversity and maintains an inclusive, non-political workplace.', 'full-time', 'Not Applicable', '4289131624', 'HIGH', '80', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-20T06:30:05.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recklCFXlFuTNEW1P', 'Manager II, Sales', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/manager-ii-sales-at-sps-commerce-4275432039', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'North Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;SPS Commerce is a leading provider of cloud-based supply chain management solutions, serving a global network of retail trading partners. We foster a collaborative and inclusive work environment where innovation and continuous improvement are highly valued. Join SPS Commerce and be part of a dynamic team that’s transforming the global retail supply chain!  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Sales Manager on our Mid-Market sales team, you will work with a high performing team focused on growth and winning. You will partner with other internal SPS teams. You''re not afraid to get in the trenches to help your team to help them succeed, win and further develop in their sales career.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Work closely with the Mid Market Sales Director to drive and deliver expectations of the business &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Identify key selling trends and communicate them to senior management &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Manage pipelines of the team through individual contributor and team pipeline reviews &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Aggregate pipeline for Sales and Marketing Management for forecasting purposes &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Resolve tactical issues with SPS Finance and Operations as they arise &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Collaboratively work both within the team and cross-functionally &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Ensure the team documents key findings, progress, insights, and pipeline within Salesforce.com &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Cultivate a culture that grows together and aligns with SPS Values &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Recruit, hire, and develop sales representatives; mentor, motivate, and coach to ensure success and team continuity; manage for performance &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Partner with Sales Training and leverage training resources to ensure proper training for all employees of the team regarding SPS Commerce products, services, and sales techniques &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Develop/improve core selling processes &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Location: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;In this hybrid role, you will be required to work onsite from our Melbourne office&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;  5+ years sales experience preferred; quota-carrying sales experience a plus  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; 2+ years of formal management experience strongly preferred; 2+ years minimum informal leadership experience required  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Proven success developing individual contributors, demonstrated experience working with others to complete work and resolve issues and &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Retail supply chain experience and/or EDI background highly desired  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Strong track record of successfully developing others and coaching for performance  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Proven competence with Microsoft Office (e.g., Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) and a CRM, preferably Salesforce.com  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Bachelor''s degree OR an equivalent combination of education and professional relevant work experience  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commitment To Our Employees&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At SPS we power connections that drive the world of commerce forward, and our success depends on making strong decisions, fostering innovation, delivering unparalleled customer solutions, and driving outstanding business performance. We achieve this by creating an environment where every employee feels a true sense of belonging. We embrace diversity, equity, and inclusion, ensuring everyone feels accepted, valued, and empowered to make a meaningful impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are committed to affirmative action and equal opportunity in all aspects of employment. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.', 'Sales Manager role at SPS Commerce leading the Mid-Market sales team to drive growth and performance. Responsibilities include managing pipelines, forecasting, cross-functional collaboration, recruiting, coaching, and improving sales processes. Requires 5+ years sales experience, 2+ years management, retail supply chain or EDI knowledge preferred, and proficiency with Microsoft Office and Salesforce. Hybrid role based in Melbourne. Committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '70', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclA9H6kYre7M1Le', 'Commercial Account Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/commercial-account-executive-at-celigo-4300367911', '2025-09-18', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', 'Celigo is the modern integration platform as a service (iPaaS) that simplifies how companies integrate, automate, and optimize processes. The platform has been ranked #1 in iPaaS user feedback by G2 for five quarters in a row. Purpose-built for mission-critical processes, Celigo offers unique tools such as runtime AI and prebuilt integrations tailored to resolve the biggest integration challenges, making Celigo incomparably easier to maintain.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Celigo is on a mission to simplify how companies integrate and automate their business processes. We’re looking for a driven &lt;strong&gt;Account Executive&lt;/strong&gt; to lead new logo acquisition efforts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What would you do, if hired?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with a dedicated Business Development Representative (BDR) to drive pipeline growth in your territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead the full sales cycle – from discovery and demo to negotiation and close.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with key ISVs and channel partners, especially in the Salesforce and NetSuite ecosystems, to deliver compelling integration solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work alongside Solution Architects and Consultants to tailor solutions that solve real customer challenges.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accurately forecast revenue and consistently meet or exceed your monthly and quarterly quotas.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage contract negotiations and pricing discussions with a customer-centric approach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ensure smooth handoffs to our Account Management team post-sale to maintain long-term success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’re skilled at managing complex, consultative sales cycles, from initial contact through close.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to consistently meet sales targets and provide accurate sales forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You understand the business impact of integration and automation technologies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, and you''re confident presenting to senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deep product curiosity and the ability to translate features into business value.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High adaptability to shifting market needs and fast-paced growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A collaborative mindset – you thrive in cross-functional environments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Well-organized with excellent time and pipeline management skills&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have 5+ years of direct SaaS sales experience in quota-carrying roles.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working within or alongside Salesforce or NetSuite ecosystems is a strong advantage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You''re equally comfortable building your own pipeline and qualifying inbound leads.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong sales acumen and a consultative approach to problem-solving.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Celigo&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Number one solution for the fourth consecutive quarter in the G2 Winter 2025 iPaaS report&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Celigo is a Visionary in the 2024 Gartner Magic Quadrant for iPaaS, a 2025 Gartner Customer Choice for iPaaS, a G2 iPaaS Leader, and a recognized leader in AI&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;High-growth, collaborative, and inclusive work environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Starting with your first year, we offer 3-weeks of vacation, wellness days, and holidays to recharge and spend time with family and friends&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generous benefits package, including parental leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Monthly tech stipend&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Recognition opportunities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a company, one of the values we hold most dear is fostering a safe, collaborative environment to bring out the best in us, so we created our Taking a Stand Initiative. Our TAS initiative is a volunteer committee open to all Celigans, with representation from underrepresented voices within our company. We believe, unequivocally, that everyone deserves to be in a place where they feel welcome as they are. Learn more about Taking a Stand.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Celigo is proud to be an equal-opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunities regardless of race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion, creed, age, disability, sex, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, medical condition, genetic information, marital status, military and veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;', 'Celigo seeks an experienced Account Executive to drive new business for its leading iPaaS platform. Responsibilities include managing the full sales cycle, collaborating with partners and internal teams, and meeting sales targets. Candidates should have 5+ years of SaaS sales experience, strong consultative skills, and familiarity with Salesforce or NetSuite ecosystems. Celigo offers competitive compensation, benefits, and a collaborative, inclusive work environment.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', NULL, 'HIGH', '65', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-18T20:53:10.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclBEwIXszWqWssf', 'Sales Development Representative', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-representative-at-ninjaone-4279692263', '2025-09-11', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Sales Development Representative, you will research potential clients, connect with and educate prospects, and qualify leads, throughout the APAC region. You will do this through outreach in the form of cold calls, emails, or social networking with the purpose of scheduling demos for your Account Executive.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;** We have built a team of successful SDRs coming from a wide variety of backgrounds- teachers, baristas, car salespeople, firefighters, recent grads, etc. If you have a deep passion for sales and are excited to kickstart your tech sales career - we would love to have you apply! **&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location &lt;/strong&gt;- Sydney, NSW (North Sydney) - Hybrid, in office on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday plus additional days as required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grow your individual book of business by proactively generating new qualified leads&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify, connect with, qualify, sort, and track leads&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hustle to achieve and exceed various core metrics, quotas, and KPIs as set by your manager, such as a minimum number of daily cold calls, emails, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Display exceptional cold-call prospecting using consultative phone skills, including the ability to clearly articulate, inspire, project confidence, influence, overcome objections, and remain resilient throughout&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize Salesforce to ensure activities are documented properly, contact information remains updated, opportunities are forecast accurately, and adequate information regarding the prospect and/or opportunity is communicated&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain knowledge of market conditions and competitive activities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Other duties as needed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive eagerness to set yourself apart and achieve success&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Aggressive, energetic self-starter who enjoys working in a quota-driven environment, works well under pressure, and enjoys being on a large team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Superior verbal and written communication skills via phone and email, with a keen attention to detail and excellent follow-up skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent listening and analytical skills to assess the interests of prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience meeting minimum call volume and/or talk-time goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and ability to manage time and workload&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Technical aptitude and the ability to successfully demonstrate and convey the value proposition behind NinjaOne’s IT management software&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coachable and eager to learn, with a solid work ethic and positive attitude&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, prioritize tasks, honor rules of engagement, and follow policies, processes, and procedures&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus Skills include experience with Salesforce (or other CRM), SalesLoft, and other sales tools; as well as experience specifically working in or with, or selling, to IT departments, Resellers, MSPs, and Director/C-Level IT executives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;No degree requirement&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;NinjaOne automates the hardest parts of IT to deliver visibility, security, and control over all endpoints for more than 30,000 customers. The NinjaOne automated endpoint management platform is proven to increase productivity, reduce security risk, and lower costs for IT teams and managed service providers. NinjaOne is obsessed with customer success and provides free and unlimited onboarding, training, and support. NinjaOne is #1 on G2 in endpoint management, patch management, remote monitoring and management, and mobile device management.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Love&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are a collaborative, kind, and curious community&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We prioritize your work/life balance offering a hybrid work environment and free in-office lunches throughout the week&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We reward your work with opportunity for growth and advancement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grow personally and together with one of the fastest growing companies globally&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop your skills through our renowned training platform&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Receive competitive compensation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with an amazing international workforce&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Information&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This position is &lt;strong&gt;NOT&lt;/strong&gt; eligible for Visa sponsorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, genetic information, marital status, veteran status, or any other status protected by applicable law. We are committed to providing an inclusive and diverse work environment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;#BI-Hybrid&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;', 'Sales Development Representative based in North Sydney (hybrid) responsible for researching and qualifying leads across APAC through cold calls, emails, and social networking to schedule demos. Requires strong communication, organizational skills, resilience, and a self-driven, quota-focused approach. Experience with Salesforce and sales tools preferred. No degree required. NinjaOne offers growth opportunities, training, competitive pay, and a collaborative work environment. Visa sponsorship not available.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'VERY HIGH', '100', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclY2locC8g6AsqD', 'Sales Engineer', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-engineer-at-omron-automation-and-robotics-australia-4287322632', '2025-09-17', NULL, ' Parramatta, New South Wales, AU', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-18T21:11:34.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recldl4h7G4hj3zvE', 'Sales Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-manager-at-asiapay-4301112802', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Melbourne, VIC', '&lt;p&gt;About the job&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The candidate for this position shall excel at creating and closing new opportunities. By using a consultative approach to selling, this person shall use their expertise to identify and qualify leads, eventually converted to sales opportunities with both new and existing clients.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you have an entrepreneurial mindset and want to make a difference to the market and your career life – we invite you to join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify new sales opportunities and develop new prospect leads and account relationship to meet sales goals and objectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present proposals to clients and effectively negotiate and close deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Devise and manage effective sales and marketing plans for targeted services, solutions and segments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and build strong relationships with banks, merchants and business partners&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Keep up with payment industry trends, product offerings and best practices in market&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with senior sales management and overseas team members in new programs and initiatives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support other related duties assigned as needed.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Degree holder in Business Administration, Marketing, IT or related discipline&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 3 to 10 years relevant experience in sales in payment, banking, eComm or IT solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;General knowledge of financial or payment service and technologies an advantage&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good network and connections in the merchants, eCommerce or payment/banking sectors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong B2B consultative drive, able to drive revenue and client growth, and maintain long lasting client relationship&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen and innovative with a passion to success in digital or fintech industry&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Able to understand business requirements and formulate service solutions to address client needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent oral and written, presentation and interpersonal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, result-oriented and able to work independently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Occasional travel may be required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We offer attractive remuneration to the right candidate with fast track career development opportunities and fringe benefits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only. Applicants who are not contacted within 4 weeks should consider their application unsuccessful and will be filed for opportunities in future.&lt;/p&gt;', 'Seeking a sales professional with 3-10 years'' experience in payment, banking, eCommerce, or IT solutions. Responsibilities include identifying and closing new sales opportunities, managing client relationships, preparing proposals, and staying updated on industry trends. Requires a degree in Business, Marketing, IT, or related field, strong B2B consultative skills, business acumen, and excellent communication. Self-motivated, able to work independently, with occasional travel. Offers competitive salary, career growth, and benefits.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '53', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclg5YWhaSiPxZTH', 'Enterprise Account Manager, Public Sector- Remote', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/enterprise-account-manager-public-sector-remote-at-beyondtrust-4271198930', '2025-09-25', '2025-11-19', 'Sydney, NSW', 'BeyondTrust is a place where you can bring your purpose to life through the work that you do, creating a safer world through our cybersecurity SaaS portfolio.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our culture of flexibility, trust, and continual learning means you will be recognized for your growth and for the impact you make on our success. You will be surrounded by people who challenge, support, and inspire you to be the best version of yourself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Drive revenue growth by identifying, developing, and closing business within an assigned territory. You’ll lead end-to-end execution of our go-to-market strategy, managing complex, multi-stakeholder sales cycles from initial engagement through to contract closure and long-term expansion. This is a high-impact role within a growing team, offering the opportunity to drive strategic growth across a priority region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Territory Strategy &amp;amp; Execution: Design, own, and drive comprehensive territory plans that maximize market penetration, competitive positioning, and revenue growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accelerate revenue: Consistently achieve and exceed quarterly and annual revenue targets by developing and expanding accounts within your assigned territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Excellence &amp;amp; Forecasting: Maintain strong sales hygiene and cadence, with deep understanding of your customers’ business to drive accurate forecasting and predictable revenue outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customer Partnerships: Build deep, strategic relationships by understanding your customers’ priorities, challenges, and growth plans, aligning BeyondTrust’s solutions with clear business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customer Success &amp;amp; Enablement: Support customers and partners with ongoing education and adoption programs to maximise value realisation and drive solution proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Channel Engagement: Collaborate closely with the BeyondTrust partner ecosystem to co-create differentiated, value-driven solutions that deliver on customer objectives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cross Functional Leadership: Lead your POD through effective territory strategy execution, coordinating closely with marketing, channel, pre-sales, business development, and other internal teams.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be based in Sydney or Canberra&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A high-performing self-starter who thrives on solving complex problems. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven success selling into Federal and State Government, consistently meeting or exceeding annual quotas. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in enterprise software, IT services, SaaS, IoT, or managed services within complex environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strong team player who values collaboration and effectively engages cross-functional teams to achieve shared goals. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Curious and growth-minded, with a commitment to continuous learning. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen and technical understanding, enabling you to build credible and influential relationships across all levels of customer organisations. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A track record of analysing customer businesses and executing multi-year account strategies that drive revenue growth in complex environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skilled in articulating a strong sales message and advancing deals through the sales cycle. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with and through partners to drive business outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Analytical thinker with strong communication and presentation skills. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Committed to building strong, collaborative relationships that foster creativity and team success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Better Together&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Diversity. Inclusion. They’re more than just words for us. They are the guiding values of how we build our teams, cultivate leaders, and create a culture where people feel connected.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We take care of our employees so they can take care of our customers. Customers who come from all walks of life just like us. We hire incredible people from diverse backgrounds because when we are different together, we are stronger together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;BeyondTrust is the global identity security leader protecting Paths to Privilege™. Our identity-centric approach goes beyond securing privileges and access, empowering organizations with the most effective solution to manage the entire identity attack surface and neutralize threats, whether from external attacks or insiders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;BeyondTrust is leading the charge in transforming identity security to prevent breaches and limit the blast radius of attacks, while creating a superior customer experience and operational efficiencies. We are trusted by 20,000 customers, including 75 of the Fortune 100, and our global ecosystem of partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Learn more at www.beyondtrust.com.', 'Drive revenue growth for BeyondTrust’s cybersecurity SaaS solutions by developing and closing business within an assigned territory, focusing on Federal and State Government clients. Responsibilities include territory planning, managing complex sales cycles, building strategic customer relationships, collaborating with partners, and leading cross-functional teams. Requires proven enterprise software sales experience, strong commercial and technical skills, and a collaborative, growth-oriented mindset. Must be based in Sydney or Canberra.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4271198930', 'HIGH', '84', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-25T05:22:28.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclkLRpnuGxVL7dB', 'Business Development Account Management TGA', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/business-development-account-management-tga-at-euromonitor-international-4215541190', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;Overview Of The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Business Development Account Manager (BDAM)&lt;/strong&gt;, you''ll &lt;strong&gt;own and grow&lt;/strong&gt; a portfolio of &lt;strong&gt;Trade, Government, Academic&lt;/strong&gt; clients across ANZ. This is &lt;strong&gt;not just about renewals&lt;/strong&gt;—it''s about &lt;strong&gt;strategic account expansion, deepening relationships, and unlocking new revenue opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Balance revenue growth with client success, ensuring long-term partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Ensure high renewal rates while identifying upsell and cross-sell opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Act as a strategic advisor, helping clients leverage insights for profitable growth, innovation, and competitive advantage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Navigate complex, multi-stakeholder corporate environments, demonstrating clear ROI and strategic value.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Build executive-level relationships, becoming a trusted advisor within client organizations, expanding engagement and usage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Euromonitor as a thought leader at industry events and corporate forums, driving brand visibility and new business opportunities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Success is measured by your ability to &lt;strong&gt;exceed revenue targets, significantly expand existing accounts, and deepen strategic client relationships&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Renew &amp;amp; Expand Existing Accounts&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify growth opportunities within existing client portfolios, managing a robust pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Align Euromonitor solutions closely with clients'' strategic goals and priorities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Effectively navigate and manage multi-stakeholder decision-making processes to demonstrate the strategic value and ROI of our intelligence.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Client Relationship&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cultivate and maintain long-term relationships at senior executive levels.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Position Euromonitor as an essential partner to clients'' strategic decision-making processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuously expand your network within client organizations to deepen engagement and ensure sustained growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver Strategic Value&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Act as a strategic consultant to corporate executives, enabling them to use Euromonitor''s insights for business growth, innovation, and market leadership.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Collaborate with internal teams to deliver tailored, high-impact research and consulting solutions addressing specific client challenges.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strengthen market visibility and identify opportunities for further commercial growth through strategic networking.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Training &amp;amp; Support&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Conduct strategic client trainings and demos to ensure maximum utilization and value extraction from Passport.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Encourage client feedback to continually enhance the value and relevance of our market intelligence offerings.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Proven track record in Government Sales and or Account Management in ANZ.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Strategic thinker who understands corporate decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Revenue-driven professional, adept at exceeding ambitious targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Exceptional communicator, capable of influencing senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Highly driven individual who thrives in high-performance, competitive environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years in Government account management, business development, or consultative sales.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in market intelligence, consulting, or B2B sales preferred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation, networking, and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Data-driven, with a business case mindset.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Business Development Account Manager responsible for managing and expanding Trade, Government, and Academic client portfolios across ANZ. Focus on strategic account growth, renewals, upselling, and building executive-level relationships. Act as a trusted advisor, delivering tailored market intelligence solutions and driving client success. Requires proven government sales/account management experience, strong communication, strategic thinking, and a track record of exceeding revenue targets. Preferred 3+ years in government or B2B sales, with skills in negotiation, networking, and data-driven decision-making.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '62', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclpTyGQXEOGSHUF', 'B2B Sales Executive (SaaS)', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/b2b-sales-executive-saas-at-axcelerate-4304611523', '2025-09-23', '2025-10-23', 'Brisbane, QLD', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;aXcelerate is a leading SaaS provider, with our Student and Learning Management System powering millions of learners'' course and competency records nationwide. As an industry leader, we’re on an exciting growth journey, transforming the way training providers and employers manage and support their learners.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recognised as a Great Place to Work for two years running, we have a culture where people feel valued and supported to thrive. With ambitious growth plans and countless opportunities to develop your career, there’s never been a better time to join our team and help us shape the future of education technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this pivotal role as a &lt;strong&gt;Sales Executive&lt;/strong&gt;, you''ll leverage your established sales experience to identify and cultivate new business opportunities, manage the sales pipeline from prospecting to closure, and drive enterprise and mid-market client acquisition. We have a strong marketing team which creates a constant stream of inbound leads helping you to win some exciting clients and take the sales team to the next level!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and create new business opportunities to expand our national footprint&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Take a lead role in the development of proposals and presentations for new business materials to create and nurture business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify trends and customer needs, building a short/medium/long-term sales pipeline in accordance with targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate new leads, identify and contact decision-makers, screen potential business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Organise professional sales presentations/demonstrations of aXcelerate, including a summary of the prospect’s key requirements and pain points and tailored to suit their needs and branding&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create competitive and engaging business proposals and pricing information&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare tender processes and documentation to ensure a consistent, high-quality submission, including negotiating, drafting, and reviewing contracts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Research and build a prospective client list and evaluate market entry opportunities for our key prospects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Become a subject matter expert for our competing markets, monitor competitors'' sales and services offering strategies to optimise market share, and identify emerging trends/threats within the market&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track and record all sales activity in our CRM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attendance of conferences and events, including some interstate travel&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Highly refined B2B solution selling skills, including demonstrated experience selling to and negotiating with ‘C’ suite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling strategically to multiple stakeholders in medium to large organisations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Track record of winning significant key enterprise accounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience developing growth strategies and plans&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable history in consistent attainment of targets and KPI’s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional negotiation, influencing, presentation and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to create and develop business proposals, business case documents, contracts and other documentation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confidence in the ownership of the end-to-end sales process - from lead generation and outreach to deal negotiation and closing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in the SaaS or tech industry will be highly regarded&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;High earning potential with uncapped commission on top of your base salary&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working arrangement with an office location based in Toowong&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A vibrant, supportive and team-oriented culture, with regular team activities and social events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A focus on professional development and learning, with access to our LMS, external and internal training opportunities and your own personal annual PD budget&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access for you and your family to an Employee Assistance Program and resources&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cashback offers and discounts on popular brands through our Employment Hero app&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career development with well defined career pathways across the business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proud members of Women in Technology with access to networking events, professional development opportunities and resources&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To Apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please submit an up to date resume outlining your suitability for the role. For any queries please contact careers@axcelerate.com&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to promoting diversity in the workplace and encourage people from all backgrounds to apply. We''re looking for people who identify with our values - H.E.A.R.T.: Honesty, Empathy, Acceptance, Respect, and Trust, while also bringing an individual perspective to their work.&lt;/p&gt;', 'aXcelerate is seeking a Sales Executive to drive new business and manage the sales pipeline for its SaaS Student and Learning Management System. The role involves identifying and securing enterprise and mid-market clients, developing proposals, negotiating contracts, and tracking sales activity. Key requirements include strong B2B sales experience, proven success with enterprise accounts, excellent negotiation and communication skills, and experience in SaaS or tech. The position offers uncapped commission, hybrid work, professional development, and a supportive team culture.', 'full-time', 'Associate', '4304611523', 'MEDIUM', '60', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-23T14:39:49.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recltpvKXmAAnjxW3', 'Business Development Representative', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/business-development-representative-at-shipbob-4289049688', '2025-09-12', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;p&gt;As a member of the ShipBob Team, you will...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow with an Ownership Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; We champion continuous learning and proactive innovation. Team members are encouraged to identify challenges and take ownership of initiatives that drive merchant, company and personal growth. By tackling complex problems and exploring creative solutions, you won’t just follow a playbook, you’ll be actively building the future of ShipBob.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate with Peers and Leaders Alike:&lt;/strong&gt; ShipBob values collaboration and support, where team members and leaders alike are committed to helping each other succeed. We all set high standards and understand the importance of transparency at all levels. We’ve created an environment where trust, open communication, and mutual respect motivate our teams to reach new heights.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience a High-Performance Culture and Clear Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; Our commitment to delivering results creates a goal-driven, high-performance culture where everyone is empowered to contribute to our mission with a clear understanding of their direct impact and accountability. We measure success in tangible ways, allowing each team member to see the positive outcomes of their work and celebrate shared victories.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;This is a hybrid position which requires you to work from the Sydney office 2–3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our Business Development Representatives (BDRs) develop logistical solutions for small to medium-sized businesses using the full suite of ShipBob''s services. A BDR''s primary responsibility is to evaluate each merchant''s unique business needs and collaborate with ShipBob''s Account Executives to close deals with merchants that have not previously worked with us. Our representatives achieve quota by meeting expected metrics for outbound touches and demos set for their respective Account Executives. This role reports to Vice President, General Manager – Australia.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide new business by identifying, researching, and qualifying new opportunities weekly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prospect a pipeline via high volume of outbound cold calls, emails, and social selling.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent ShipBob at Trade Shows, Partner and ShipBob led events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify client needs through assessing their current fulfilment methods and use discretionary judgment to determine if they are a fit for our business model.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Make recommendations to management from merchants who do not “fit the box”.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Schedule demos with potential merchants and Account Executives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve daily activity requirements through outbound merchant contact and accurately track merchant interactions and information in the designated tracking system.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Report to designated manager/team lead to strategize more effective prospecting methods.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consistently exceed monthly and annual quota.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Additional duties and responsibilities as necessary. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring To The Table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;2 years of sales experience, as Business Development or Sales Development Representative is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of consistently hitting and exceeding quota expectation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience selling over the phone and smart calling various types of businesses or merchants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Logistics experience is preferred&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a high degree of diligence and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in a achievement-oriented environment, with evidence of personal ambition.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relentless persistence in the face of daily rejection and delays from potential merchants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An aptitude for research and understanding data. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks &amp;amp; Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Health and Wellness Benefits Stipend&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;WFH Phone/Internet Stipend&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;See Our High-Performing Culture &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Check us out on Instagram (@lifeatshipbob) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We recognize that people come with a wealth of experience and talent beyond just the technical requirements of a job. If your experience is close to what you see listed here, please still consider applying. Diversity of experience and skills combined with passion is a key to innovation and excellence; therefore, we encourage people from all backgrounds to apply to our positions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The work we do at ShipBob is both challenging and rigorous, which means our environment isn’t the right fit for everyone, and that’s okay. We welcome energetic high performers who thrive in a dynamic, collaborative, results-driven environment. We value individuals who embrace accountability and humility, push boundaries, and are motivated by challenging work. Every team member, no matter their role or tenure, is expected to roll up their sleeves and tackle the complex problems we face in today’s global supply chain.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn more about our core values and how we perform at a high level in our day-to-day work on our Culture page (https://www.shipbob.com/careers/culture/).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;ShipBob is a leading global supply chain and fulfillment technology platform designed for SMB and Mid-Market ecommerce merchants to provide them access to best-in-class capabilities and to deliver a delightful shopper experience. Merchants can outsource their entire fulfillment operations, utilize ShipBob’s proprietary warehouse management system for in-house fulfillment, or take advantage of a hybrid solution across ShipBob’s dozens of fulfillment center network in the United States, Canada, United Kingdom, Europe, and Australia. ShipBob is backed by leading investors like Menlo Ventures, Bain Capital Ventures, Hyde Park Venture Partners, and SoftBank Vision Fund 2, and is one of the fastest-growing tech companies headquartered in Chicago.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;ShipBob provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Business Development Representative at ShipBob (Sydney, hybrid 2-3 days/week). Identify, research, and qualify new SMB logistics clients, conduct high-volume outbound outreach, schedule demos, and collaborate with Account Executives to close deals. Requires 2+ years sales experience, strong communication, persistence, and quota achievement. Logistics experience preferred. Reports to VP, General Manager – Australia. Offers health and wellness stipends and remote work support. ShipBob is a global supply chain tech leader focused on SMB ecommerce fulfillment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '63', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recltqo7su76oxV48', 'APAC Corporate New Logo Account Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/apac-corporate-new-logo-account-executive-at-lucid-software-4299450701', '2025-09-12', NULL, 'Melbourne, VIC', 'Lucid Software is the leader in visual collaboration and work acceleration, helping teams see and build the future by turning ideas into reality. Our products include the Visual Collaboration Suite (Lucidchart and Lucidspark) and airfocus. We hold true to our core values: innovation in everything we do, passion &amp;amp; excellence in every area, individual empowerment, initiative and ownership, and teamwork over ego. At Lucid, we value diverse perspectives and are dedicated to creating an environment and culture that is respectful and inclusive for everyone. Lucid is a hybrid workplace. We promote a healthy work-life balance by allowing employees to work remotely, from one of our offices, or a combination of the two depending on the needs of the role and team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since the company''s founding, Lucid Software has received numerous global and regional recognitions for its products, business, and workplace culture. These include being listed to the Forbes Cloud 100, Fast Company Most Innovative Companies, Fortune Best Workplaces in Technology, and PEOPLE''s Companies that Care. Lucid''s solutions are used by more than 100 million users across the globe, making Lucid the most used visual collaboration platform by the Fortune 500. Our customers include Google, GE, and NBC Universal, and we partner with leaders such as Google, Atlassian, and Microsoft.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;New Logo Account Executive (AE)&lt;/strong&gt; to join our &lt;strong&gt;APAC sales team based in Melbourne, Australia&lt;/strong&gt;. In this role, you will drive growth by acquiring new customers and expanding relationships within assigned territories. AEs partner with prospects and existing customers to identify business value, close sales opportunities, and collaborate with Customer Success Managers (CSMs) to ensure renewals and expansion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage a book of accounts, forecast accurately, and close pipeline to achieve quota.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Source leads and identify new opportunities across net-new and existing customers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build pipeline and close business through prospecting, cold outreach, and executive-level negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop expertise in Lucid''s product suite and position solutions effectively.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assess and navigate the competitive landscape within territory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Share market insights with internal teams to inform product and marketing strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Expand business into new markets, industries, and personas.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform other related duties as assigned.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years of sales experience (Account Executive or similar), preferably in tech/SaaS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven record of exceeding quotas and KPIs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in the Melbourne office two days per week (Tuesday and Thursday)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience closing high-level business in SaaS or evangelist sales environments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Salesforce and sales acceleration tools (e.g., Outreach, ZoomInfo)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation skills and familiarity with software contracts; formal sales training a plus&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Lucid Software seeks a New Logo Account Executive for the APAC sales team in Melbourne. The role focuses on acquiring new customers, managing accounts, building pipeline, and closing sales to meet quotas. Candidates should have 3+ years in tech/SaaS sales, a proven track record, strong communication and organizational skills, and be able to work in-office two days a week. Preferred qualifications include experience in SaaS sales, proficiency with Salesforce and sales tools, and strong negotiation skills.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '80', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:45.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('reclxFnLp00hlf9Xu', 'Key Account Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/key-account-manager-at-advantech-4297339594', '2025-09-09', NULL, 'Melbourne, VIC', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Job Overview &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Key Account Executive to join our growing iAutomation team. This role report to the iA lead, you will work with a diverse portfolio of products, driving revenue growth across the business. You will enhance our planning, communication, and strengthen client relationships, becoming a trusted advisor to both internal and external stakeholders. You will be a skilled communicator, capable of managing corporate clients across Australia in the B2B sector.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and generate new business by leveraging industry trends while maintaining relationships with key accounts – Particularly in BESS &amp;amp; Renewable Energy Sectors.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on company offerings, competitors'' products, and pricing to drive sales and achieve organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Present the value of our products and services to uncover growth opportunities; analyse data to spot market trends.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead prospecting efforts, strategic account planning, and pricing negotiations, ensuring a solid understanding of sales contracts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Participate in team meetings, maintain the client database, and provide reports to management.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resolve customer issues promptly and ensure high satisfaction rates, aligned with company standards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with other sales departments and internal stakeholders to ensure seamless project execution and long-term customer success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and manage a strong sales pipeline, ensuring alignment with our long-term business strategy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in trade fairs, industry events, and technical conferences to represent Advantech and stay ahead of market trends.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accomplish the assigning sales quota &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To be successful, we are looking for people who want to be a part of our success story and have a deep passion for technology and innovation. People who are always looking for ways to do things better and are committed to going above and beyond for our customers. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;At least 5+ years of sales experience in roles such as Key Account Manager or BDM.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong background in automation, industrial engineering, computer hardware, electronics, or IoT.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in B2B sales within Industrial automation, Edge Computing, or Industrial IoT solutions, with quota achievement or notable growth accomplishment &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive and independent approach, with the ability to develop and execute key account strategies &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Business acumen to plan and execute strategic sales initiatives and achieve ambitious targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding &amp;amp; solid experience in BESS &amp;amp; Renewable Energy &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication, negotiation, and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage competing deadlines and perform under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in SAP &amp;amp; CRM systems and Microsoft Office.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel interstate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career development with the global leader in Industrial PCs, Edge AI and IIoT.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Diverse portfolio of products and established customer accounts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A supportive and collaborative environment that values growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation package including commission and car allowance.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enjoy secure and stable employment in a rapidly growing technology sector! &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If this opportunity interests you and you meet most of the qualifications, we encourage you to apply! Feel free to message us on LinkedIn if you have any questions. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover more about Advantech at https://www.advantech.com/en-au&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow Advantech on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/advantech-au/&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow Advantech on Facebook&lt;/p&gt;', 'Key Account Executive for iAutomation team managing B2B corporate clients across Australia, focusing on BESS and Renewable Energy sectors. Responsibilities include driving revenue growth, strategic account planning, sales negotiations, client relationship management, and market trend analysis. Requires 5+ years in sales, strong background in automation, industrial IoT, or related fields, proficiency in SAP/CRM, and willingness to travel. Offers career development, competitive compensation, and a collaborative work environment with a global technology leader.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '74', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:57.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recm6zBS2u00l13au', 'Sales Development Representative', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-representative-at-sitemate-4298132808', '2025-09-19', '2025-10-19', 'Sydney, NSW', 'Thanks for stopping by and learning more about this role at Sitemate! ✨🏗️&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’d love to hear from you 👩💻👩🏽💻🧑🏿💻👨🏻💻&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief Overview Of This Role At Sitemate&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for an Inbound Sales Development Representative (SDR) to join our Sydney team, to help accelerate our growth in the Oceania region.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Sales Development Representative is responsible for qualifying and routing inbound leads across three channels: self-service and inside sales. This role involves frequent engagement with prospects through phone calls, emails, live chat, and internal tools such as Slack and Salesforce. Success in the role is measured by the number of product demonstrations booked and completed, with a strong track record of team performance consistently meeting or exceeding monthly targets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🔧 Day-to-Day&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will be qualifying and routing inbound leads through two channels; self service &amp;amp; inside sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You’ll be spending most of your time with prospects across phone calls, emails and live chat on our website, as well as internal tools like slack and salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Your quota is measured by the number of demonstrations booked and completed at the subsequent stage of the process. Our current team in this role have achieved &amp;gt;=95% of their targets each month since starting&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⚡ Challenges&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learning about the built world if you haven’t had any exposure to it - there are a lot of different types of companies and plenty of new terminologies to learn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Up-skilling your call/phone and email skills - although we have plenty of examples for you to learn from during your onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding SaaS financial acronyms and common terminology - if you have not worked in a SaaS company before, there is going to be a lot of metrics to learn. This cheat sheet is a good resource: The Ultimate SaaS Acronyms Cheat Sheet&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We move very quickly, so you’ll need to be excited to come in and learn extremely fast.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✅ Who This Role Is For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ambitious individuals wanting to pursue a career in SaaS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;People who thrive in a structured, high-agency, KPI-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communicators who enjoy building relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilient individuals who can persevere and perform with high-volume tasks&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚫 Who This Role is &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; For&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Those unwilling to handle rejection frequently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;People uncomfortable with people and conversations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Tools&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must Have:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confident and clear communication skills, with excellent writing and presentation skills over email, phone, video conferencing and in-person.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent task organisation and prioritisation skills, you’re able to multi-task efficiently.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice To Have&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with modern tooling - CRMs, Health Scoring, Live chat, Knowledge bases.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience conducting customer meetings digitally (e.g. Zoom/Teams) and/or physically (in person/face to face with customers).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Patience working in an industry where not all users are tech-savvy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why should I consider joining Sitemate?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Check out Sitemate’s team at the offsite: Sitemate Offsite 2022, Sitemate Offsite 2023 &amp;amp; recently Sitemate Offsite 2024&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You can see what people really think about working at Sitemate here: Working at Sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2024 Podcast: CEO Hartley Pike on his personal journey, scaling Sitemate, diversity and culture at sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2023 Podcast: Listen to CMO Lance Hodgson’s tips on how to supercharge your career&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2022 Podcast: Listen to CEO Hartley Pike speak about the company’s founding and broader Go To Market strategy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2022 Podcast: Listen to CTO Tim Bray speak about building high quality features that solve customer problems at Sitemate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We have equal opportunity for applicants of all genders, ethnicities, ages, sexualities &amp;amp; people with disabilities - Sitemate''s team is proudly diverse and accessible. 55% of our team identify as coming from underrepresented ethnic backgrounds. 43% identify as female. Our team ranges in age from 22 to 51 years old.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We''re proud to have a global team with team members from Australia, Kenya, Brazil, France, Chile, United Kingdom, Ireland, Spain, Portugal, Vietnam, the Philippines, Kazakhstan, USA, Canada, Indonesia, Venezuela, Sri Lanka, and Uruguay.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Our office has fantastic on-site facilities including a rooftop garden, wellness centre, showers and cycle storage. The transport connections are excellent. Every Monday, the team enjoys a catered lunch together from one of the many nearby options.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will be remunerated based on your performance. If you are performing well, you won’t need to wait 3 years or have to find better offers elsewhere to receive an increase to your remuneration. 7 out of the last 10 remuneration increases for Sitemate team members have been made pro-actively by management, without the individual needing to even raise the topic of remuneration.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get a laptop and a budget to set up your home office.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have visibility into the standardised career development plan for your role, and access to a professional learning and development budget.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get additional benefits and support as parents - with paid leave for both primary (min. 16 weeks) and secondary carers (min. 6 weeks) including adoption, as well as support and leave for the tragic circumstances of stillbirth or miscarriage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have 20 days PTO, as well as paid compassionate &amp;amp; bereavement leave, sick &amp;amp; carer’s leave, and the ability to work from anywhere for a few weeks per year.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get equity options and ownership in Sitemate on a standard vesting schedule. See here for a general overview of how this works.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate has grown from 5 employees in 2018 to 150+, and we’re moving into the next stage of growth! We have a product that customers are strongly engaged with, and every month we get 1000s of new leads in our core/target regions with 0 cold calling and limited marketing spend (made possible by strong word-of-mouth and organic marketing efforts).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate’s founders have diverse backgrounds - one coming from engineering on major infrastructure projects; the second coming from product and graphic design. This brings a unique perspective internally where we blend deep industry experience with a passion (obsession) for modern best practices in product design.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate graduated from Australia’s #1 Technology Company Accelerator - Startmate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate has strong financial backing from Blackbird (Australia and NZ’s #1 Vc), Shearwater Growth Capital &amp;amp; Marbruck Investments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;See info on our latest raise here.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the working environment like at Sitemate?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are very transparent - monthly Allhands meetings provide the team with direct insight into team updates, customer stories, hiring plans and key metrics (NPS, Revenue, Financial Performance). During this Allhands meeting we also hear one ‘life story’ from one of our team each month - learning about different countries and cultures around the world.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We place an extremely high value on your time - you won’t be spending your days wasting time on fighting internal systems, botched together spreadsheet processes or doing data entry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We use best in class systems that are seamlessly integrated to deliver our team the right information at the right time, allowing them to get their work done efficiently and to a very high standard.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have a core and close team around you, but you will also be exposed to and working directly with multiple departments - engineering, product, design, marketing, sales and customer success.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have a high degree of autonomy, as the focus is on outcomes and not hours. If you want to block off a few hours to run a personal errand or block off an hour to pick up the kids from school - no worries. No one will be monitoring your time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are constantly working to minimise the number of group meetings - daily check ins are all done asynchronously (in your own time) each morning. But spontaneous 1:1s or small sessions are strongly encouraged!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does Sitemate do, exactly?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sitemate builds best in class software products for the built world.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Industrial companies operating in the built world are facing a number of mission critical challenges - changes in work behaviour as Generation Z start to enter the workforce as mobile first users of software, and the drastic shift away from traditional mining to renewable energy projects such as wind farms and solar farms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Our first product - Dashpivot, is a platform where industrial style companies streamline and standardise their processes in a new digital format. This new digital format enables them to complete and track work in the field on a mobile or tablet, and automate repetitive tasks and tracking through automated workflows and real-time analytics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See Some Of Our User Reviews For Dashpivot Here&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;G2 Crowd&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trust Radius&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE Note&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you go on our website and enter your email, you will become a lead in our CRM. To avoid this, you can watch videos directly here&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We do not use recruitment partners or services, so please save your time and don''t reach out&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Compensation Range: A$75K - A$110K&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;', 'Sitemate is hiring an Inbound Sales Development Representative (SDR) in Sydney to qualify and route inbound leads, primarily via phone, email, and live chat, using tools like Slack and Salesforce. The role is target-driven, focusing on booking and completing product demonstrations. Ideal candidates are strong communicators, highly organized, resilient, and interested in SaaS sales. Experience with CRMs and digital customer meetings is a plus. Sitemate offers a diverse, flexible, and transparent work environment, career development opportunities, performance-based remuneration, equity, and comprehensive benefits. Compensation: A$75K–A$110K.', 'full-time', 'Entry level', '4298132808', 'VERY HIGH', '100', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-20T06:18:00.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recmN8Kl4QyuhVScc', 'Sales Development Representative, Australia', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-representative-australia-at-impel-4290966233', '2025-09-16', NULL, ', ', 'We are looking for a motivated, tenacious, and results-oriented Sales Development Representative (SDR) to join our high-performing sales team. The SDR will be at the forefront of our business growth, responsible for generating qualified leads, initiating meaningful conversations with potential prospects, and setting up valuable meetings for our sales team. The ideal candidate is an excellent communicator with a passion for sales, a drive for success, and a strong desire to grow and thrive in a fast-paced, ever-evolving environment.Lead Generation: Proactively identify and qualify new business opportunities through strategic outbound prospecting efforts across phone, email, and marketing campaigns. Leverage industry insights to target the right decision-makers and drive conversations that lead to sales opportunities.Outreach and Engagement: Effectively engage with potential customers, building relationships and trust through personalised cold calls, targeted emails, and strategic follow-ups. Set up meetings or product demos with the sales team, ensuring a smooth handoff and paving the way for successful sales engagements.CRM Management: Consistently maintain and update lead information within the CRM system, ensuring accurate tracking of prospects and activities. Leverage CRM insights to monitor lead progress and follow-up strategies.Collaboration and Teamwork: Work closely with Account Executives and the broader sales team to ensure the seamless transition of qualified leads. Collaborate with team members to align on strategies and share best practices for success.Target Achievement: Take ownership of meeting or exceeding monthly and quarterly lead generation targets and KPIs, contributing directly to the overall sales goals and success of the team.Market Research and Insight: Stay up-to-date with industry trends, competitor activity, and customer needs to proactively identify new sales opportunities. Use this market knowledge to refine outreach strategies and improve lead quality.OtherMaintains confidentiality of work-related issues, records, and company information.Demonstrates a commitment to Diversity, Equity and inclusion by treating everyone with respect and dignity, ensuring all voices are heard and advocating change.', 'Sales Development Representative responsible for generating qualified leads through outbound prospecting, engaging potential customers via calls and emails, and setting up meetings for the sales team. Manages CRM data, collaborates with sales colleagues, meets lead generation targets, and stays informed on market trends. Committed to confidentiality and promoting diversity, equity, and inclusion.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '80', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:43.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recnPVIM9aKDrvmE5', 'Sales Manager (ANZ)', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-manager-anz-at-rapid7-4300424022', '2025-09-15', NULL, 'Melbourne, VIC', '&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Manager, Australia &amp;amp; New Zealand&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Are you a results-driven sales leader who thrives in a high-performance culture? As our Sales Manager – ANZ, you’ll take the helm of a dynamic team of Account Executives and Renewal Account Managers across Australia &amp;amp; New Zealand. With a territory that spans both established relationships and untapped potential, and the full support of our sales engineers, channel experts, marketing, and customer success teams—you’ll have everything you need to lead from the front and deliver excellence, together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Team&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This role sits within our APAC Leadership team. Our wider APAC Sales organisation serves as a strategic partner for our customers, helping them achieve a more secure digital future. By leveraging the full value of our product portfolio our Sales teams create relevant solutions to meet our customers needs and keep them secure.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This position reports to our Director, ANZ Sales and will lead a team of Account Executives and Renewal Account Managers across our entire Commercial portfolio in addition to the Enterprise teams in New Zealand and Western Australia. We are focused on creating regional intimacy and market presence to support deep, strategic relationships with customers before, during, and after the buying journey. To accomplish this we leverage a diverse set of backgrounds and experiences across the team to shape a winning culture and create the model for field sales excellence at Rapid7. Specifically, your focus will be to:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement sales strategies in alignment with business objectives, monitoring regional market trends and competitor activity to identify opportunities and threats.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively look for new revenue generating opportunities &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead, inspire, develop and manage an existing team of Account Executives and Renewal Account Managers &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with new hires to develop mastery of the Rapid7 sales process, forecasting methodology, and product knowledge&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Own renewal success for the Territories, managing Renewal Account Manager(s) to oversee and manage the renewal process for clients in our existing customer base. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Go-to-Market leadership team as well as cross-functionally across other departments within Rapid7 to create the ultimate end-to-end customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage teams remotely, while also being willing to travel to meet with distributed teams throughout the region.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Close commercial, enterprise software deals leveraging internal and external partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Establish individual and team budgets, quotas, activity metrics, and forecasts to support company business objectives. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Foster a positive environment of collaboration and professional growth, acting in a regional leader capacity for internal initiatives and activities within the employee base.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Skills And Qualities You’ll Bring Include&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;8+ years of sales and high ARR growth experience &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;5+ years of sales management and leadership experience, including building and developing management teams and cross-functional organizations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Superior track record of building dynamic, diverse teams across remote locations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in an evangelical sales model disruptive to a traditional industry to define a new market evolution and customer needs &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Direct SaaS sales background, with recurring subscription revenue models&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to position multiple product and technology solutions to solve business problems; experience in the Security, Cloud, or IT ecosystem beneficial&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;History of coaching and developing employees &amp;amp; leading through change&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in building out a Channel focus &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We know that the best ideas and solutions come from multi-dimensional teams. That’s because these teams reflect a variety of backgrounds and professional experiences. If you are excited about this role and feel your experience can make an impact, please don’t be shy - apply today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Rapid7&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Rapid7 is creating a more secure digital future for all by helping organizations strengthen their security programs in the face of accelerating digital transformation. Our portfolio of best-in-class solutions empowers security professionals to manage risk and eliminate threats across the entire threat landscape from apps to the cloud to traditional infrastructure to the dark web. We foster open source communities and cutting-edge research–using these insights to optimize our products and arm the global security community with the latest in attacker methods. Trusted by more than 11,000 customers worldwide, our industry-leading solutions and services help businesses stay ahead of attackers, ahead of the competition, and future-ready for what’s next.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;', 'Sales Manager, ANZ at Rapid7 leads Account Executives and Renewal Account Managers across Australia and New Zealand, driving sales growth in commercial and enterprise segments. Responsibilities include developing sales strategies, identifying new revenue opportunities, managing renewals, coaching teams, and collaborating cross-functionally. Requires 8+ years in sales with 5+ years in leadership, SaaS experience, and a strong track record in building remote, diverse teams. Focus on security, cloud, or IT ecosystems preferred.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '69', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recnr1VLFBGKfPWNq', 'Account Manager - B2B SaaS', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/account-manager-b2b-saas-at-dext-4307605628', '2025-10-01', '2025-10-31', 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;Who we are, what we do and why:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Dext is a fast-growing fintech transforming bookkeeping through AI and machine learning. Founded in London, we now operate across Europe, North America, and APAC, with a presence in six countries and over 400 employees worldwide. Our platform empowers accountants, bookkeepers, and businesses to simplify accounting processes and make smarter, more timely financial decisions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In 2024, Dext joined the IRIS Software Group, further strengthening our ability to deliver end-to-end accountancy solutions. We''ve achieved 99.5% data accuracy, saved over 35 million hours of manual data entry, and are trusted by 12,000 firms and 700,000 businesses globally. With integrations across major accounting software and over 11,500 financial sources, we''re proud to be at the forefront of innovation in the accounting space. 🌍&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We''re looking for an ambitious and results-driven &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our APAC team and help support and grow our valued partners in the Australian market. In this role, you''ll manage the full customer lifecycle (from expansion to retention), ensuring partners feel supported and receive exceptional value from their subscription.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role - what you''ll do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive portfolio growth by identifying opportunities to expand partnerships, upsell/cross-sell solutions, and maximize value for our clients. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for partner escalations and requests, minimizing churn and downsell. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and strengthen long-term partnerships, introducing new and premium products tailored to client needs. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify opportunities to increase portfolio value, improve conversions, reduce churn, and enhance the partner experience. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use our passive account management (PAM) tools and your market awareness to prospect and forecast selling opportunities. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across teams to ensure a seamless buying and deployment process, and create a positive customer journey that mitigates contraction or cancellation. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you - what we are looking for:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven Account Manager experience in B2B SaaS and confident in consultative sales, with the ability to challenge the status quo while maintaining empathy. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skilled at managing diverse portfolios and tailoring your approach to each client''s priorities. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong active listening and relationship-building skills, building trust with decision-makers and stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable presenting to groups, with solid public speaking skills and the ability to engage audiences with clarity and impact. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication, business acumen, and ability to manage priorities effectively. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Capable of delivering impactful product demonstrations and providing insights to help clients compete more effectively. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be part of - our values, culture and behaviours:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are a highly ambitious, innovative, market-leading FinTech. We are uncompromising in our desire to achieve our best, day-in day-out, and we have three clear values which guide everything we do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Brave - Everyone in the company has a voice to challenge ideas and the status quo. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Exceptional - We set high standards for ourselves. We aim to be exceptional at what we do. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be Together - We are one team. There is no such thing as individual success without team success. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;🌟 Our behaviours guide us and inform how we communicate, collaborate and support each other. They are: Be Diverse, be Courageous, be Considerate, be Transparent, be Focused, be Accountable, and above all, be Dexterous!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we will give you - the perks:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hybrid Model *2/3 days in our Sydney Office*&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Time away from work:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;23 vacation days annually plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;10 personal leave days annually&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2 Volunteer days annually (1 every 6 months)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Birthday Leave (you get a day off the week of your birthday!) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Compassionate Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Summer hours (3 hours off per week during summer &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work abroad for 20 days per year - allowing you to travel and work &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learning hours (3 hours of dedicated learning every 2 weeks)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity and Paternity Leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribution towards private medical insurance and health &amp;amp; wellbeing allowance (e.g., gym, wellness apps, yoga)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Dext, a global fintech leader in AI-driven bookkeeping, seeks an Account Manager for its APAC team in Australia. The role focuses on managing and growing B2B SaaS client portfolios, driving expansion and retention, and delivering value through consultative sales and strong relationship management. Candidates should have proven account management experience in SaaS, excellent communication and presentation skills, and a client-focused approach. The position offers a hybrid work model, generous leave, learning opportunities, and health benefits.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4307605628', 'VERY HIGH', '90', 'Sales', '2025-10-01T14:12:28.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recoARQoVCyRlsnR5', 'Account Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/account-manager-at-adyen-4191547479', '2025-09-21', '2025-12-22', 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;strong&gt;This is Adyen&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Adyen provides payments, data, and financial products in a single solution for customers like Meta, Uber, H&amp;amp;M, and Microsoft - making us the financial technology platform of choice. At Adyen, everything we do is engineered for ambition.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For our teams, we create an environment with opportunities for our people to succeed, backed by the culture and support to ensure they are enabled to truly own their careers. We are motivated individuals who tackle unique technical challenges at scale and solve them as a team. Together, we deliver innovative and ethical solutions that help businesses achieve their ambitions faster.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why you should join the Adyen Account Management team &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Adyen, the Account Management team is critical to the growth and success of our business, as well as expanding the Adyen brand across the globe. Being part of our Account Management team, you’ll manage relationships with innovative international merchants, covering multiple industries and channels. You’ll have the opportunity to work on cross-functional initiatives and projects in a fast-paced, highly entrepreneurial environment with high autonomy. You’ll become an expert in the global payments landscape and level up your skills through our AM Academy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a proactive and adaptable Account Manager to join our team in Sydney. The ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with a hands-on mentality; someone who is eager to help the world’s biggest brands grow while changing an industry. You are excited to work with a global, multicultural team in a collaborative manner and help your team succeed. Your focus will be on delivering an outstanding customer experience, finding new opportunities, and driving mutual success for Adyen and our customers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our Account Managers are encouraged to challenge each other and sharpen ideas as a team, because winning is more important than ego. In this role, you’ll get your energy by working on a wide portfolio of accounts across a variety of verticals. You’ll work alongside a group of talented and driven Account Managers, and together, you’ll develop customer relationships and drive commercial growth for your accounts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaboration- As an Account Manager, you will work closely with other Account Managers and collaborate on many different accounts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationship management- Responsible for ramping and growing customers with a focus on commercial growth, customer satisfaction, and reducing churn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commercial acumen- Drive commercial discussions for joint accounts, while striving to meet strategic and financial targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Project management- Prioritize and manage short and long term projects with varying timelines across multiple accounts, leveraging internal support teams where relevant.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Technical acumen- Work closely with the Technical and Product teams to manage the integration of the merchant, helping to identity improvements and developments for continued innovation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Feedback- Serve as a feedback loop for your customers internally.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A strategic thinker with excellent project management skills and the ability to lead and manage time-sensitive, cross-functional initiatives in a fast-paced, highly entrepreneurial environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enjoy engaging others and developing strong working relationships internally and externally with customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Passionate about working on a wide portfolio of accounts and having the opportunity to learn about many aspects of the payments industry&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eager to challenge yourself to identify commercial opportunities and drive commercial discussions with customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong time management skills and constantly looking for ways to work efficiently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A natural communicator and team player with technical interest, knowledge and understanding&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Requirements&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have 2+ years of experience in a client-facing, commercial role, like account management, consulting, or in the payments industry from a merchant side (bonus if in complex enterprise software, technical infrastructure or financial services)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This role is based in our Sydney office. We have a hybrid workplace and value in-person collaboration; we do not offer remote-only roles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Domestic and international travel is required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Diversity, Equity and Inclusion commitments &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our unique approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity of backgrounds and cultures is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business and technical challenges are unique, and we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. No matter who you are or where you’re from, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Studies show that women and members of underrepresented communities apply for jobs only if they meet 100% of the qualifications. Does this sound like you? If so, Adyen encourages you to reconsider and apply. We look forward to your application!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s next?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Ensuring a smooth and enjoyable candidate experience is critical for us. We aim to get back to you regarding your application within 5 business days. Our interview process tends to take about 4 weeks to complete, but may fluctuate depending on the role. Learn more about our hiring process here. Don’t be afraid to let us know if you need more flexibility.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is based out in our Sydney office. We are an office-first company and value in-person collaboration; we do not offer remote-only roles.', 'Adyen is seeking an Account Manager in Sydney to manage and grow relationships with international merchants across various industries. The role involves driving commercial growth, ensuring customer satisfaction, and collaborating with internal teams on technical integrations and projects. Candidates should have 2+ years of client-facing experience, strong project management and communication skills, and be comfortable working in a fast-paced, hybrid office environment with some travel required.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4191547479', 'HIGH', '75', 'Sales, Business Development, and Information Technology', '2025-09-21T14:15:58.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recp1LckZHoiwGjTe', 'Sales Development Representative', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-development-representative-at-rms-4299935555', '2025-09-17', NULL, 'Melbourne, Victoria, AU', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-18T21:11:33.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recpE4f6gAyisgyaK', 'Senior Account Executive - Australia', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-account-executive-australia-at-storyblok-4293953238', '2025-09-26', '2025-11-04', 'Melbourne, VIC', 'Storyblok is a headless CMS that enables marketers and developers to create with joy and succeed in the AI-driven content era. It empowers you to deliver structured and consistent content everywhere: websites, apps, AI search, and beyond.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Marketers get a visual editor with reusable components, in-context preview, and workflows to launch fast and stay on brand. Developers have freedom to use their favorite frameworks and integrate with anything through the API-first platform. Brands get one source of truth for content that is accurate, flexible, and measurable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Legendary brands like Virgin Media O2, Oatly, and TomTom use Storyblok to make a bigger, faster market impact. It''s Joyful Headless™, and it changes everything.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT IS IN IT FOR YOU&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You will be joining a growing company where you can contribute to many "firsts". Plus these benefits:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Monthly remote work stipend (home internet costs, electricity). Home office equipment package right at the start (laptop, keyboard, monitor…)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Home office equipment upgrade (furniture, ear plugs …) or membership to a local co-working space after your onboarding&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sick leave benefit, parental leave and 25 days of annual leave plus your local national holidays&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Personal development fund for courses, books, conferences, and material&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;VSOP (Virtual Stock Option Plan)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The annual international team-building trip, quarterly and monthly online get-togethers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;As a fully remote company, with work-life balance at its core, you''ll enjoy flexible schedules&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An international team that loves to have fun at work and works hard together to accomplish shared goals&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Join Storyblok''s dynamic sales team as a Senior Account Executive covering Australia and wider APAC. Drive growth in one of the fastest-growing markets by selling our industry-leading headless CMS platform to enterprise clients across diverse industries and geographies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;APAC Regional Lead&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and implement a strategic go-to-market plan alongside the regional leadership team that contributes to the regional revenue growth strategy and maximizes territory growth potential&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serve as a regional thought leader by evangelizing the Storyblok vision through product demonstrations, strategic partnerships, market events, and tailored account initiatives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Business Development&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively generate new business by sourcing enterprise opportunities (with a target of 20% self-sourced pipeline), alongside regional partners and our business development team, whilst contributing ongoing insights on the evolving market dynamics to our internal leadership team &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Sales focus&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Directly contribute to the expansion of the APAC region by signing new Enterprise clients &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Execute effectively on inbound deals using our proven MEDDIC sales playbook and process to lead potential new customers through the sales journey and presentation of Storyblok''s solution&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with and support the BDR &amp;amp; Partner team in shaping proactive pipeline and prospecting activities &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiation of commercial offers for customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate through the legal and procurement process in complex B2B SaaS sales&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain a healthy relationship with existing clients and support Customer Success in upselling into existing accounts&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Partner Management&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Expand our partner network by identifying and qualifying new agencies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enable our partners for success by providing the necessary tools, sales trainings and guidance to deliver outstanding enterprise projects on Storyblok&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare and host Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs) with key partners to secure their commitment to the GTM strategy (review pipeline, revenues outcomes and partner tier status)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Proven record of success in closing large and complex SaaS Enterprise deals in Australia &amp;amp; APAC region&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; Ability to autonomously define and execute strategic account and territory plans that inform and influence broader regional sales strategy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Familiarity with common sales methodologies like MEDDPIC, Challenger, Gap Selling, SPIN Selling, Sandler, etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 6 years of proven SaaS solution selling experience as a Senior Account Executive orchestrating a wider GTM team such as BDRs, PMs and CSMs to drive new revenue. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Examples of deep relationship-building skills with an ability to both grow and nurture clients and partners for expansive business relationships &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relative experience in working with solution partners within a co-selling motion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; "Ideally brings domain expertise from the digital or e-commerce software industry or Martech agencies, with a proven ability to act as a trusted advisor to executive-level stakeholders"&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to craft, refine and navigate different sales messaging and strategy for both technical (developers) and business (marketing) personas &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Must be a native English speaker &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ideally based in Australia, where a majority of our partners and customers are located &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Travel primarily within the assigned region, to foster client relationships and participate in events that contribute to the growth and success of Storyblok&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MENTAL, PHYSICAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL REQUIREMENTS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Remote (home) work opportunity or funded by Storyblok co-working space&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GENERAL TERMS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Storyblok has a commitment to diversity and inclusion. We strive to create a hiring environment in which all people feel they are equally respected and valued, irrespective of gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, ethnicity, age, religion, citizenship or any other characteristic. &lt;em&gt;You can find more information about our privacy policy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;here&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;All communications regarding job opportunities at Storyblok will come from an official Storyblok employee with an email address ending in @storyblok.com. We will never redirect you to another portal or another site that is unrelated to our domain (storyblok.com).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Here is a sneak peek of &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Storyblok''s Visual Editor&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you need an accommodation for any part of the application process, please email talent.acquisition@storyblok.com&lt;/em&gt;', 'Storyblok is seeking a Senior Account Executive for Australia and APAC to drive enterprise sales of its headless CMS platform. Responsibilities include developing go-to-market strategies, generating new business, managing partner relationships, and closing complex SaaS deals. The role requires at least 6 years of SaaS sales experience, strong relationship-building skills, and familiarity with sales methodologies. Benefits include remote work, equipment stipends, personal development funds, and flexible schedules. The position is remote, ideally based in Australia.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4293953238', 'HIGH', '70', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-28T14:21:34.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recpOrtsDwdpRWQ5K', 'Outbound Sales Development Representative - Australia/ New Zealand', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/outbound-sales-development-representative-australia-new-zealand-at-remote-4304683403', '2025-09-27', NULL, ', ', 'About RemoteRemote is solving modern organizations’ biggest challenge – navigating global employment compliantly with ease. We make it possible for businesses of all sizes to recruit, pay, and manage international teams. With our core values at heart and future focused work culture, our team works tirelessly on ambitious problems, asynchronously, around the world. You can find Remoters working from 6 different continents (Antarctica left to go!) and all of our positions are fully remote.We encourage every member of the Remote team to bring their talents, experiences and culture to the table to help us build the best-in-class HR platform.If you are energetic, curious, motivated and ambitious, be part of our world. Apply now and define the future of work!What This Job Can Offer YouSales helps our prospective customers and active customers to fully experience our Global HR Platform. Sales is the team responding to incoming queries and helping customers understand how to maximise Remote’s full suite of products to meet their employment needs. To enable them to embody our value of Transparency, we have a fair price guarantee. This is an exciting time to join Remote and make a personal difference in the global employment space as a Outbound Sales Development Representative, joining our Sales team.What You BringProven business development success through effective use of core sales tools (Knowledge of Hubspot, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Chorus is a plus)Experience working as an SDR in a B2B SaaS Tech companyAble to negotiate skillfully, promote/sell ideas persuasivelyExceptional communication skills, both oral and written, coupled with excellent listening skills and a positive and energetic phone presenceAble to think strategically and tactically. Able to maintain a positive attitude in the face of criticism, rejection, or failurePromotes a strong sense of urgency for reaching goals and key deliverables. Self Starter. proactive and brings new ideas to the teamExtremely self-motivated with a diligent work ethicDemonstrated success in the below areas listed in key responsibilitiesWrites and speaks fluent EnglishIt''s not required to have experience working remotely, but considered a plusKey ResponsibilitiesRespond, engage and qualify outbound leads and inquiriesSourcing new sales prospects and reaching out to them to book appointments for Account ExecutivesClearly communicating Remote''s value propositions to prospects and learning about their needs to see if there’s a good fitProviding support to Account Executive team as neededBe responsible for educating and developing prospects leading to hand-off to sales teamsCreate target prospects lists and penetrate key accountsCold call into prospects generated by variety of outside sourcesIdentify key players, researching and obtaining business requirements, and presenting solutions to begin sales cyclePracticalsYou''ll report to: Manager, Outbound Sales DevelopmentTeam: SalesLocation: Australia/ New ZealandStart date: As soon as possibleRemote Compensation PhilosophyRemote''s Total Rewards philosophy is to ensure fair, unbiased compensation and fair equity pay along with competitive benefits in all locations in which we operate. We do not agree to or encourage cheap-labor practices and therefore we ensure to pay above in-location rates. We hope to inspire other companies to support global talent-hiring and bring local wealth to developing countries.At first glance our salary bands seem quite wide - here is some context. At Remote we have international operations and a globally distributed workforce. We use geo ranges to consider geographic pay differentials as part of our global compensation strategy to remain competitive in various markets while we hiring globally.The On-Target Earnings for this position is between $61,000 USD to $71,000 USD. The base salary is 70%. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level and location, and our job titles may span more than one career level. The actual base pay for the successful candidate in this role is dependent upon many factors such as location, transferable or job-related skills, work experience, relevant training, business needs, and market demands. The base salary range may be subject to change.Application processInterview with RecruiterInterview with Manager, Outbound Sales Development Exercise Stage + Mock Call SessionInterview with Senior ManagerBar RaiserPrior employment verification check BenefitsOur full benefits & perks are explained in our handbook at remote.com/r/benefits. As a global company, each country works differently, but some benefits/perks are for all Remoters:work from anywhereflexible paid time offflexible working hours (we are async)16 weeks paid parental leavemental health support servicesstock optionslearning budgethome office budget & IT equipmentbudget for local in-person social events or co-working spacesHow You’ll Plan Your Day (and Life)We work async at Remote which means you can plan your schedule around your life (and not around meetings). Read more at remote.com/async.You will be empowered to take ownership and be proactive. When in doubt you will default to action instead of waiting. Your life-work balance is important and you will be encouraged to put yourself and your family first, and fit work around your needs.If that sounds like something you want, apply now!How To ApplyPlease fill out the form below and upload your CV with a PDF format.We kindly ask you to submit your application and CV in English, as this is the standardised language we use here at Remote.If you don’t have an up to date CV but you are still interested in talking to us, please feel free to add a copy of your LinkedIn profile instead.Not only do we encourage folks from all ethnic groups, genders, sexuality, age, abilities, disability status and any other under-represented group to apply, but we prioritize a sense of belonging. We have 4 ERGs (Women, Disability, Queer, Minorities in Tech) who meet regularly with the People team. During your interviews and beyond, we ask & encourage anybody who needs an accommodation to request one from their recruiter.We will ask you to voluntarily tell us your pronouns at interview stage, and you will have the option to answer our anonymous demographic questionnaire when you apply below. As an equal employment opportunity employer it’s important to us that our workforce reflects people of all backgrounds, identities, and experiences and this data will help us to stay accountable. We thank you for providing this data, if you chose to.At Remote, we embrace AI as a valuable tool while prioritizing human creativity and authenticity. We look forward to meeting candidates who balance innovation with genuine expertise and experience. To learn more about Remote''s AI guidelines check see here.Please note we accept applications on an ongoing basis.', 'Remote is hiring an Outbound Sales Development Representative (SDR) to generate and qualify leads, support Account Executives, and promote Remote’s global HR platform to prospective clients. The role requires B2B SaaS sales experience, strong communication and negotiation skills, and proficiency with sales tools like Hubspot and LinkedIn Sales Navigator. The position is fully remote, based in Australia/New Zealand, with flexible hours and competitive compensation ($61,000–$71,000 USD OTE). Remote offers global benefits, supports diversity, and encourages work-life balance.', 'full-time', 'Entry level', '4304683403', 'HIGH', '84', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-28T04:09:01.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recpX36epJcJLvVlk', 'Strategic Account Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/strategic-account-executive-at-commvault-4285295515', '2025-09-26', '2025-11-12', 'Victoria, Australia', '&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment Fraud Alert&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’ve learned that scammers are impersonating Commvault team members—including HR and leadership—via email or text. These bad actors may conduct fake interviews and ask for personal information, such as your social security number.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What To Know&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commvault does not conduct interviews by email or text.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We will never ask you to submit sensitive documents (including banking information, SSN, etc) before your first day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;If you suspect a recruiting scam, please contact us at wwrecruitingteam@commvault.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Commvault&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Commvault (NASDAQ: CVLT) is the gold standard in cyber resilience. The company empowers customers to uncover, take action, and rapidly recover from cyberattacks – keeping data safe and businesses resilient. The company’s unique AI-powered platform combines best-in-class data protection, exceptional data security, advanced data intelligence, and lightning-fast recovery across any workload or cloud at the lowest TCO. For over 25 years, more than 100,000 organizations and a vast partner ecosystem have relied on Commvault to reduce risks, improve governance, and do more with data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a dynamic and results-driven Strategic Account Executive to lead Commvault’s growth across Victoria. You will be accountable for achieving quota by selling Commvault solutions into a defined account list, comprising both existing enterprise customers and high-value prospects within this strategic territory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will own the full sales lifecycle and work closely with cross-functional teams to plan, coordinate, and drive multi-quarter sales growth, account penetration, and long-term customer success. Your focus will be on secure software, SaaS, AI-enabled, and cloud-based data protection solutions that support compliance, resilience, and digital transformation goals across regulated industries.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Objectives&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Achieve and Exceed Sales Quota&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Drive quarterly and annual revenue by securing new wins and expanding existing accounts across your territory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Strategic Campaigns and Account Plans&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Develop multi-year account strategies to win and grow high-potential customers, incorporating performance objectives, financial goals, and customer success metrics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Executive and Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Coordinate internal and external stakeholders including SEs, partners, marketing, and executive sponsors to build and close high-value sales campaigns.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Commvault as the Data Resilience Partner of Choice&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Demonstrate our leadership in secure, scalable, and compliant data management solutions, integrating AI and cloud capabilities to deliver measurable business value.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Make An Impact&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sell Commvault’s secure software, SaaS, AI-enabled, and cloud solutions through direct engagement and partner collaboration. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement territory and account plans for long-term expansion and strategic customer acquisition. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build high-value sales campaigns and manage multi-stakeholder buying groups, from technical evaluators to procurement and executive sponsors. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with SEs, Marketing, Channel, Legal, Finance, and Delivery teams to progress opportunities to successful outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Present compelling business cases and executive briefings that demonstrate Commvault’s value in meeting AI, cloud transformation, and cyber resilience objectives. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain high levels of activity, pipeline growth, and CRM hygiene to support forecasting and sales operations. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stay current with industry trends in cybersecurity, AI/ML, secure cloud, and digital transformation. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage alliances and partners to support joint solutions, accelerate procurement, and expand reach within the territory. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Bring&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in enterprise software and SaaS sales to large organisations in regulated or complex industries. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in AI, Cloud, or Security solutions, with measurable achievements in delivering business outcomes. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of complex buying cycles, including procurement processes, compliance frameworks, and security requirements. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience closing six- and seven-figure deals in strategic, consultative sales environments. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong background in data protection, disaster recovery, or information management solutions. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to engage and influence CIOs, CISOs, procurement leaders, and other senior stakeholders. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience working with and through channel and alliance partners. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with structured methodologies such as MEDDPICC or equivalent. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and executive presentation skills. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Operational discipline and experience using tools like Salesforce to manage pipeline, forecasting, and deal progression. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet The Leader&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Reporting to the AVP, ANZ – Craig Bastow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Love Working Here Because&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;High income earning opportunities based on self-performance. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Opportunity for Presidents Club &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee Stock Purchase Plan (ESPP) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuous professional development and product training &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales training in MEDDPICC and Command of the Message &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Commvault is an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are always committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status and we will not discriminate against on the basis of such characteristics or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Commvault’s goal is to make interviewing inclusive and accessible to all candidates and employees. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation to participate in the interview process or apply for a position at Commvault, please email accommodations@commvault.com For any inquiries not related to an accommodation please reach out to wwrecruitingteam@commvault.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Commvault''s Privacy Policy', 'Commvault is seeking a Strategic Account Executive for Victoria to drive sales of secure software, SaaS, AI-enabled, and cloud-based data protection solutions to enterprise customers and prospects. The role involves full sales lifecycle management, developing account strategies, building high-value campaigns, and collaborating with cross-functional teams. Candidates should have proven enterprise software/SaaS sales experience, expertise in AI, cloud, or security, and a strong background in data protection. The position offers high earning potential, professional development, and is based in an inclusive, equal opportunity workplace.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4285295515', 'HIGH', '75', 'Sales', '2025-09-28T14:33:28.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recpmSvhOk0UyPcwZ', 'Senior Business Development Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-business-development-manager-at-foodbyus-4259949552', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Surry Hills, NSW', 'FoodByUs is a B2B market-leading wholesale ordering software used by thousands of hospitality suppliers and venues nationwide. We connect these two sides, providing an incredible software experience for both restaurants and suppliers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a Senior Business Development Manager to join our Sydney team helping sell our leading software solution to hospitality businesses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Reporting to the &lt;strong&gt;Territory Sales Manager&lt;/strong&gt; you''ll generate leads, pitch them on the FoodByUs platform, explain the benefits of moving to an efficient online order management system, run price comparisons, and ultimately get venues to order everything through FoodByUs - all while working within our uncapped commission structure!!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify new buyers, and hospitality businesses (cafes, restaurants, bars, clubs, pubs, etc) that would benefit from utilising FoodByUs’ platform as their primary ordering system (we also have an extensive database of existing leads). &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement effective business development strategies to achieve revenue and growth targets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide regular reports and updates on business development activities, sales pipelines, and progress towards targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with prospective and existing clients, understanding their requirements and providing tailored solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Experience&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience as a Business Development Manager/ Sales professional&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will be a proven hunter who is not afraid to cold call and utilise your networks&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Skilled in communication and negotiation, with a knack for closing deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-starter, and commercially savvy where you possess the ability to excel in both a team-based and autonomous environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the hospitality/ F&amp;amp;B industry is highly desirable but not essential &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why FoodByUs? What''s in it for you?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Our start-up culture allows you to become a pioneer in the business and contribute to how our business operates&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Company share options we want you to be part of our journey &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Birthday leave, mental health leave - awesome pet friendly offices&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'FoodByUs is seeking a Senior Business Development Manager in Sydney to sell its B2B wholesale ordering software to hospitality businesses. Reporting to the Territory Sales Manager, you will generate leads, pitch the platform, run price comparisons, and close sales within an uncapped commission structure. Key duties include identifying new clients, developing business strategies, reporting on sales progress, and maintaining client relationships. Candidates should have proven sales experience, strong communication and negotiation skills, and be comfortable with cold calling. Hospitality industry knowledge is a plus. The role offers a start-up culture, company share options, and additional leave benefits.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '54', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recqh1nQrub4BLWyt', 'Business Development Representative – Fintech | Uncapped Commission', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/business-development-representative-%E2%80%93-fintech-uncapped-commission-at-kpay-group-4305961851', '2025-09-25', '2025-10-25', 'Sydney, NSW', '&lt;p&gt;Break into Tech Sales with One of APAC’s Fastest-Growing Fintechs!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Looking for a way into &lt;strong&gt;technology sales&lt;/strong&gt; but not sure where to start?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is your chance to join a &lt;strong&gt;hyper-growth fintech&lt;/strong&gt; that’s reshaping how businesses get paid.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re building a powerhouse B2B sales team and looking for &lt;strong&gt;driven, people-focused go-getters&lt;/strong&gt; to help us expand nationally. If you’ve got the &lt;strong&gt;hustle, hunger, and heart&lt;/strong&gt; to succeed, we’ll give you the &lt;strong&gt;tools, training, and mentorship&lt;/strong&gt; to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About KPay Group:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;KPay is a rapidly growing global fintech with over 60,000 merchants across Hong Kong, Singapore, and Japan. We help small and medium-sized businesses grow through smart, secure payment solutions, digital tools, and personalised support.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now expanding into Australia, we''re building a high-performing team to drive local business adoption and revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visit us at: &lt;strong&gt;www.kpay-group.com&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be the face of KPay in your city — introduce our &lt;strong&gt;digital payment solutions (POS terminals)&lt;/strong&gt; to local businesses.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Get creative: connect with merchants through walk-ins, calls, referrals, and your own unique approach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Learn how to understand business needs and position solutions that make a real impact.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build lasting relationships with your clients and grow your portfolio month after month.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with an ambitious, high-performing sales team — celebrate the wins together.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ideally some sales experience (door-to-door, outbound, or customer-facing).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Outgoing, confident, and love talking to people.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, competitive, and eager to grow.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Resilient — you bounce back stronger after rejection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Thrive in a &lt;strong&gt;fast-paced, energetic&lt;/strong&gt; environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join KPay?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uncapped Earnings&lt;/strong&gt;: Base salary + commissions. Top performers make &lt;strong&gt;$80K–$100K+ per year&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recurring Commissions&lt;/strong&gt;: Keep earning as your merchants keep using our platform.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extra Rewards&lt;/strong&gt;: Cash bonuses, referral perks, performance recognition.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifestyle Perks&lt;/strong&gt;: Birthday leave, work anniversary leave, annual leave, and more.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career Fast-Track&lt;/strong&gt;: Clear growth into senior sales, partnerships, or leadership if you deliver results.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structured Training&lt;/strong&gt;: Step-by-step guidance, mentorship, and a proven playbook to get you winning quickly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perfect For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Early-career professionals with a solid sales background (door-to-door, outbound, telesales, or face-to-face).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hospitality, or service professionals who’ve done sales and want to step into tech with higher earning potential.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ambitious salespeople who want control over their income and a clear path into leadership or senior roles.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is more than a job — it’s your launchpad into the world of fintech and technology sales.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you’re ready to learn, hustle, and win, &lt;strong&gt;apply now and let’s build something big together!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Join KPay Group, a fast-growing fintech, as a B2B Tech Sales Representative. Introduce digital payment solutions to local businesses, build client relationships, and drive revenue growth. Ideal candidates are outgoing, resilient, and motivated, with some sales or customer-facing experience. Offers base salary plus uncapped commissions, bonuses, career progression, and structured training. Suitable for early-career sales professionals or those in hospitality/service looking to move into tech sales.', 'full-time', 'Entry level', '4305961851', 'HIGH', '82', 'Business Development and Sales', '2025-09-28T04:13:01.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recrNt5cWyNs0nFq7', 'Senior Sales development rep - Large Enterprise', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-sales-development-rep-large-enterprise-at-sprinklr-4257842921', '2025-09-20', '2025-11-23', 'Sydney, NSW', 'Sprinklr is a leading enterprise software company for all customer-facing functions. With advanced AI, Sprinklr''s unified customer experience management (Unified-CXM) platform helps companies deliver human experiences to every customer, every time, across any modern channel. Headquartered in New York City with employees around the world, Sprinklr works with more than 1,000 of the world’s most valuable enterprises — global brands like Microsoft, P&amp;amp;G, Samsung and more than 50% of the Fortune 100.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Learn more about our culture and how we make our employees happier through The Sprinklr Way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We currently have a great opportunity for a Sales Development Representative to join our motivated and creative Inside Sales team! As an SDR, you''ll be responsible for creating interest and developing conversations with contacts at enterprise corporations. Team members are passionate about the ongoing transformation of inside sales to something that is personal, value-filled, and representative of social disruption.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you''ll do:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You will actively seek out new sales leads and business opportunities through active networking and sending personal, strategic, value-add emails, outbound calls and social messages (no copying and pasting). You will be able to quickly research a company, see opportunities, and strategise an approach to build interest. You will profile potential prospects based on predetermined criteria. You will secure meetings for your Account Executives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are and what makes you qualified:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Language proficiency in professional English (verbal and written)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Desire to be in a software sales (full cycle) position as a career progression&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a verifiable track record of success and goal attainment in a sales-oriented role&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a passion for technology and disruptive technology&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have a deep understanding of the role social media plays in business&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Have some in an SDR/BDR role (Enterprise experience preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You have a run-through-a-brick-wall level of drive, passion, and desire for results&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience in creative outbound reaches&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You''ll Love Sprinklr: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We''re committed to creating a culture where you feel like you belong, are happier today than you were yesterday, and your contributions matter. At Sprinklr, we passionately, genuinely care. For full-time employees, we provide a range of comprehensive health plans, leading well-being programs, and financial protection for you and your family through a range of global and localized plans throughout the world.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For more information on Sprinklr Benefits around the world, head to https://sprinklrbenefits.com/ to browse our country-specific benefits guides.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We focus on our mission: We founded Sprinklr with one mission: to enable every organization on the planet to make their customers happier. Our vision is to be the world’s most loved enterprise software company, ever.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in our product: Sprinklr was built from the ground up to enable a brand’s digital transformation. Its platform provides every customer-facing team with the ability to reach, engage, and listen to customers around the world. At Sprinklr, we have many of the world''s largest brands as our clients, and our employees have the opportunity to work closely alongside them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We invest in our people: At Sprinklr, we believe every human has the potential to be amazing. We empower each Sprinklrite in the journey toward achieving their personal and professional best. For wellbeing, this includes daily meditation breaks, virtual fitness, and access to Headspace. We have continuous learning opportunities available with LinkedIn Learning and more.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;EEO - Our philosophy: Our goal is to ensure every employee feels like they belong and are operating in a judgment-free zone regardless of gender, race, ethnicity, age, and lifestyle preference, among others. We value and celebrate diversity and fervently believe every employee matters and should be respected and heard. We believe we are stronger when we belong because collectively, we’re more innovative, creative, and successful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sprinklr is proud to be an equal-opportunity workplace and is an affirmative-action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, or Veteran status. See also Sprinklr’s EEO Policy and EEO is the Law.', 'Sprinklr is seeking a Sales Development Representative to join its Inside Sales team. The SDR will generate and qualify leads at enterprise companies through strategic outreach, research, and networking, and secure meetings for Account Executives. Candidates should have professional English skills, a track record in sales, passion for technology, and experience in SDR/BDR roles (enterprise preferred). Sprinklr offers comprehensive benefits, a supportive culture, and values diversity and inclusion.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4257842921', 'MEDIUM', '62', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-20T14:20:43.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recrvhEgSsdYT8b3j', 'Channel Account Manager', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/channel-account-manager-at-qualys-4190514368', '2025-09-15', NULL, ', ', 'Come work at a place where innovation and teamwork come together to support the most exciting missions in the world!Position Overview: As a Channel account manager, you will play a pivotal role expanding our ANZ partner market through regional channel partners such as VARs, resellers or distributors. You will be responsible for developing and driving incremental joint business opportunities with assigned Qualys partners. The successful candidate will have a proven track record in building and managing a successful partner ecosystems in cybersecurity. The role requires a deep and broad understanding of the how Partners operate, architecting strategies, initiatives, and influence driving growth and marketshare.Key Responsibilities include:Partner Enablement: Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure assigned partners are equipped to deliver exceptional customer experiences. Drive key partner enablement and govern program compliance across sales, pre-sales and technical roles. Work with the partners to create compelling offerings and services generating demand within their customer base and new prospects.Joint Business Planning: Work closely with key focus partners creating joint business plans aligned with both organizations'' goals. Manage execution of plans with proactive management and follow up. Establish and track key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure the success of all the partner initiatives.Sales and Revenue Growth: Drive revenue growth through partners identifying and capitalizing on joint business opportunities with a particular focus on new logos and customer upsell. Develop strategies to activate, enable, and build pipeline with partners increasing partner-initiated opportunities Collaborate with the sales team to develop and execute co-selling strategies with partners including Joint Business Plans. Experience with partner forecasting developing internal processes and prowess driving forecast accuracy with partner business. Ability to leverage available data, metrics, and trends to proactively manage the business. Enabling and implementation of framework agreements signed in the relevant territoryQualifications: Bachelor''s degree in Business, Marketing, or a related field; MBA is a plus. +5 years of proven experience in channel partner/GSI development and management; +5 years of experience in software/SaaS markets; preferable experience in cybersecurity. Proven experience and ability building a cohesive, quantifiable strategic plan for the region. Able to build trust and influence executive level relationships internally with excellent communication, negotiation and interpersonal skills. Effective cross-functional collaborator driving consensus and resolution to challenges. Strategic thinker with the ability to develop and execute plans that drive results. Results-oriented with a focus on achieving and exceeding revenue targets. Experienced presenter Experience with tools such as SFDC to leverage data, make trending observations and properly manage business expectations and goals.Key Responsibilities: Able to drive results of stated goals and KPIs. Experience working with partners and internal stakeholders activating a successful partner ecosystem of channel partners Proven experience and ability building a cohesive, quantifiable strategic plan for the Partner ecosystem Build partner executive relationships with key partners or distributors Weekly cadence managing the business to the numbers and able to leverage metrics measuring progress, challenges Able to build and execute recommended initiatives aligned to company goals working closely with Product Management and partner Sales and architect teams. Engage the Qualys Sales, partner Sales and offering heads to create and drive revenue opportunities. Review, draft and manage partnership focused commercial agreements. Execute on partner program requirements including enablement, demand generation, and joint-engagement with focus partners. Achieve and exceed annual goals, including revenue, new customer acquisition, existing customer retention and account expansion targets through partners. Partner with marketing to define and execute partner pipeline generation, communications, program messaging, positioning. Ability and willingness to travel for partner meetings, industry conferences, QBRs on a regular basis. Effective cross-functional collaborator driving consensus and resolution to challenges', 'Channel Account Manager responsible for expanding the ANZ partner market through VARs, resellers, and distributors. Key duties include partner enablement, joint business planning, driving sales and revenue growth, and managing partner ecosystems in cybersecurity. Requires 5+ years in channel partner management and software/SaaS, strong strategic planning, executive relationship building, and proficiency with tools like SFDC. Focus on achieving revenue targets, partner program execution, and cross-functional collaboration. Willingness to travel regularly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '73', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('recs26b8LGC7xpuUU', 'Sales Executive', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/sales-executive-at-atturra-4301264115', '2025-09-16', NULL, 'Brisbane City, QLD', '&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our Data &amp;amp; Integration Practice help clients realise greater agility and resilience, by helping their teams have greater confidence in how they use their data and the decisions they make. This allows our clients to improve business performance using solutions that combine human expertise with smart technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Sales Executive will support the growth of the Data &amp;amp; Integration business by identifying new opportunities, building initial client relationships, and supporting the sales cycle from prospecting through to proposal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a mid-level sales role ideal for someone with 5-10 years of relevant experience, looking to build a career in technology sales, with a focus on data platforms, integration solutions, and digital transformation services.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Including (but not limited to) the following:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Business Development &amp;amp; Lead Generation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Research and identify potential customers and markets within target industries&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Prospect and qualify new leads through calls, emails, LinkedIn outreach, and events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Schedule introductory meetings and demos&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Build and maintain strong relationships with clients, acting as a trusted advisor and ensuring high levels of customer satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales Support&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Assist or actively contribute to the end-to-end sales process, from initial engagement to contract negotiation and closing deals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Maintain accurate records of sales activities and leads in the CRM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Coordinate meetings, follow-ups, and client communications&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Market Insights&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Work closely with the Data &amp;amp; Integration technical and delivery teams to understand services and offerings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Represent the company at industry events, conferences, and networking opportunities to promote our services and generate leads&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Keep up to date with industry trends, competitors, and emerging technologies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Provide feedback from the market to support product/service positioning&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Conditions:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employment Type: Permanent full time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work Arrangement: Onsite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Location: Brisbane&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Travel Opportunities: Occasional travel to client site/s &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will make you successful in this role?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You are a motivated and results-driven sales professional with a proven track record in technology or consulting services sales. You thrive in a client-facing role, are passionate about helping organisations solve complex challenges, and excel at turning opportunities into long-term partnerships.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5-10 years’ experience in sales, business development, lead generation or account management in IT services, consulting, enterprise software, or similar environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience with various data and integration technologies (e.g., Boomi, Databricks, Denodo, Snowflake, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of integration solutions, middleware, APIs, cloud platforms, or enterprise applications.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to meet or exceed sales targets in a competitive environment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong relationship-building and stakeholder engagement capability.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel as needed to meet with clients and attend industry events.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, resilient, and able to work independently as well as collaboratively.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Business, IT, or related field (preferred but not essential).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why is this an exciting opportunity?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Atturra is one of the fastest growing ASX-listed advisory and IT solutions companies in Australia, giving you a strong foundation to fulfil your career ambitions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We currently have 1200+ professionals working across Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Hong Kong, and USA who are using innovation to lead the way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Data &amp;amp; Integration business unit helps clients unlock the full potential of data by integrating systems and applications, enabling digital transformation through our comprehensive on-premises, hybrid, and cloud integration solutions. We specialise in Boomi, Smartsheet, and OpenText.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is your chance to make an impact. Come and join our talented and creative team of change makers to redefine the future through technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Our People Say:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;“We are working towards a very bright future.”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;“It''s a company with vision and a promising future.”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why you’ll love working here &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture of possibility &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Atturra we embrace innovation within our teams, fostering an environment of possibility and growth. We believe in creating a supportive and welcoming culture, where everyone is encouraged to achieve success through collaboration, continuous learning, and smart work practices.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A strong set of company values&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our culture is reflected by our employees who demonstrate camaraderie, innovation, dedication, respect and excellence in everything they do. These traits have become integral to the way we do business and are the values we strive for.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Valuable Employee Benefits &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee benefits, recognition, and wellbeing platform&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Career growth via succession planning, internal promotions, and mentorship opportunities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ongoing investment in professional development through industry and technology certifications, and study assistance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mental health support through our Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support for family and caring responsibilities, including paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employee referral program, with monetary incentives offered &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commitment to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Atturra, we are committed to addressing the digital skills gap and championing diversity, equity, and inclusion. We welcome applications from individuals of all backgrounds — including Veterans, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disability, members of the LGBTQI+ community, culturally diverse individuals, and other underrepresented groups.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supporting Australia’s veterans &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are proud to be recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer under the Department of Veterans’ Affairs Veteran Employment Commitment (VEC). Atturra is dedicated to supporting Australia’s veteran community by enhancing recruitment, support, retention, and leadership opportunities. Our goal is to ensure veterans build meaningful and impactful careers with us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Our People Say: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;“Atturra has a great working environment and management are very supportive of their staff. We celebrate success and have fun while working hard.”&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How To Apply &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;All applications must be submitted online via our Careers page. Late applications or those sent by email will not be prioritised. Please ensure your application is complete and that you have answered all required questions before submitting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;https://atturra.com/au-en/careers&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent Pool&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This recruitment process may also be used to create a talent pool for similar ongoing or temporary opportunities that may arise within the next 12 months.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment Agencies and Headhunters&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Our Talent Acquisition team is managing this recruitment process and will reach out if additional support is required. Atturra only accepts referrals from agencies on our official supplier list via the Agency Portal. To participate, agencies must complete our procurement process, hold an approved fee agreement, and be formally invited by the Talent Acquisition team for a specific vacancy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Submissions made outside of this process will not be considered. We also request that agencies do not contact Atturra employees outside the Talent Acquisition team regarding hiring matters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Agencies interested in joining our official supplier list may send an expression of interest to talentacquisition@atturra.com. Please note, our supplier list is reviewed annually.', 'Mid-level Sales Executive role supporting growth of Data & Integration services by identifying opportunities, building client relationships, and managing the sales cycle. Requires 5-10 years’ experience in technology sales, knowledge of data platforms and integration solutions, strong communication and negotiation skills, and ability to work independently. Based in Brisbane, full-time onsite with occasional travel. Atturra offers career growth, professional development, and a supportive, inclusive culture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HIGH', '84', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:44.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('rect4lHEI8NiUePPf', 'Senior Account Executive, Enterprise', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-account-executive-enterprise-at-safetyculture-4260922810', '2025-09-29', '2025-12-02', 'Sydney, NSW', 'SafetyCulture is a global technology company that is helping to transform workplaces around the world. Our mission is to help working teams get better every day and our technology platform and products give front line workers a voice and leaders the visibility to make smart decisions when driving safety, quality and continuous improvement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SafetyCulture is one of the fastest-growing tech companies. Our bold ambition is to reach 100 million users worldwide by 2032. Opportunities to help shape a journey like this do not come around often!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a customer-centric and ambitious Senior Account Executive within our Enterprise team to join APAC Sales at SafetyCulture. Our Senior Account Executives play an instrumental role in developing and managing customer relationships at an Enterprise level through effective business partnership and solving customer problems. Your collaborative, personable and driven approach, coupled with your strategic value-driven thinking, will seal your success in driving growth and product adoption.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Will Spend Your Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic business plans to drive and deliver commercial business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and implement a strong outbound sales plan for your territory&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain and grow your existing portfolio of customers to deliver long term value&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend roadshows and customer summits, educating prospective customers &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform in-person and online demos, sharing the value of our products to prospective customers, tailored to their needs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage the full sales process to close in order to achieve quarterly targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Partnering closely with our Customer Success and Business Development teams to ensure customers have a smooth onboarding and supporting the development of long-term, successful customer relationships&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be the voice of the customer to our cross-functional partners, including our world-class product team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maintain data integrity through Salesforce and report on all sales activities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand market trends and proactively engage with customers in a meaningful way based on the insights captured. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Senior professional B2B enterprise selling experience with a proven track record in managing a sales pipeline and achieving targets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consultative and customer-centric approach with demonstrated ability to build trust, establish rapport and uncover customer pain points&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Motivated to identify new customer opportunities in conjunction with driving expansion opportunities with existing customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in an agile, fast-moving organisation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in managing opportunities with cross-functional teams including customers success and partnerships. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to demonstrate SafetyCulture values (Think Customer, Open Honest Always, Better as a Team, Be Bold Bring Action)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SaaS sales experience highly desirable&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At SafetyCulture, we care about people and growing the team, through:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Equity with high growth potential, and a competitive salary, &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible working arrangements, we encourage you to create the best work blend while working from your home and the local SafetyCulture office;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access to professional and personal training and development opportunities; Hackathons, Workshops, Lunch &amp;amp; Learns; &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We encourage involvement in the community, open source work, attending talks and events, and experimenting with new technologies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Also Receive Other Perks Such As&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;In-house Culinary Crew serving up daily breakfast, lunch and snacks&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing initiatives such as subsidised fitness programs, EAP services and generous parental leave policy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Quarterly celebrations and team events, including the annual Shiplt global offsite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Table tennis, board games, gym sessions, book club, and pet-friendly offices.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;We’re committed to building inclusive teams and cultivating a sense of belonging so our people can bring their whole authentic selves to work each day. We seek to make reasonable adjustments throughout our recruitment process to create an even playing field for all candidates. Thanks to the tireless efforts of the entire SafetyCulture team we’ve built an incredible culture which has seen us recognised as a Best Place to Work in Australia , the US and the UK .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Even if you don''t meet every requirement listed in the ad, please consider applying for this role. We prioritise inclusion and value individuals with potential over a checklist of qualifications. Don''t rule yourself out, hit that apply button if this job resonates with you&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can find out more about life at SafetyCulture via Youtube , Twitter , Instagram and LinkedIn .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To all recruitment agencies, we do not accept resumes or partnership opportunities. Please do not forward resumes to SafetyCulture or any of our employees. We are not responsible for any fees associated with unsolicited resumes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This employer participates in E-Verify and will provide the federal government with your Form I-9 information to confirm that you are authorized to work in the U.S. If E-Verify cannot confirm that you are authorized to work, this employer is required to give you written instructions and an opportunity to contact Department of Homeland Security (DHS) or Social Security Administration (SSA) so you can begin to resolve the issue before the employer can take any action against you, including terminating your employment. Employers can only use E-Verify once you have accepted a job offer and completed the Form I-9. E-Verify Works for Everyone. For more information on E-Verify, or if you believe that your employer has violated its E-Verify responsibilities, please contact DHS: 888-897-7781 or dhs.gov/e-verify', 'SafetyCulture is seeking a Senior Account Executive for its APAC Enterprise Sales team. The role involves developing and managing enterprise customer relationships, driving sales growth, and promoting product adoption. Key responsibilities include strategic business planning, outbound sales, customer portfolio management, conducting demos, and collaborating with cross-functional teams. Candidates should have proven B2B enterprise sales experience, a consultative approach, and ideally SaaS sales background. The company offers competitive salary, equity, flexible work, professional development, and various employee perks. SafetyCulture values inclusion and encourages applicants from diverse backgrounds.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4260922810', 'VERY HIGH', '92', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-28T14:40:35.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('rectFqgOdSoLP3i8t', 'Consulting Engineer, APAC', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/consulting-engineer-apac-at-jamf-4297562641', '2025-09-09', NULL, 'Sydney, NSW', 'At Jamf, we believe in an open, flexible culture based on respect and trust. Our track record and thriving work environment all stem from the freedom we grant ourselves to get the job done right. We take pride in helping tens of thousands of customers around the globe succeed with Apple.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The secret to our success lies in our connectivity, while operating with a high degree of flexibility. Work-life balance remains our priority while feeling connected is important to maintain our strong culture, achieve our goals, and thrive as #OneJamf.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do at Jamf: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Jamf, we empower people to be their best selves and do their best work. The Consulting Engineer''s (CE) primary role is to partner within Sales and other departments to achieve sales and revenue goals. This role blends deep Apple ecosystem expertise with advanced security knowledge across endpoint protection, identity management, and network security, enabling you to design and deliver integrated enterprise solutions that drive innovation and support our customers beyond traditional device management. You will collaborate closely with Sales, Product, and Marketing teams, as well as industry partners, to deliver secure, scalable, and innovative solutions for enterprise environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role if offered as remote in Australia. You may be required to work periodically at a Jamf office or collaborative work location with other Jamf employees in your area for certain events or moments that matter. We are only able to accept applications for those based in Australia and have Permanent Residency or Citizenship to live and work in Australia. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you can expect to do in this role:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform all job responsibilities in alignment with the core values, mission and vision of the organization&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide technical consultation and technical escalation for Sales and other departments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Continuously update expertise and demonstrate deep understanding of subject matter specific to role assignment, including but not limited to&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Architecture of Jamf''s comprehensive platform solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Architecture of Apple-centric zero-trust network frameworks&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Architecture of Apple-centric security frameworks for enterprise environments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Architecture of advanced Jamf configurations including automation frameworks and API integrations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Custom workflows and automation for large-scale enterprise deployments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Respond to complex RFPs requiring comprehensive Apple enterprise expertise&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deliver technical presentations and product demonstrations for enterprise prospects and customers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales, Professional Services, and Product teams to architect custom Apple enterprise solutions spanning management, endpoint security, and network security&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with partners and complementary solution providers (Apple, Microsoft, CrowdStrike, Zscaler, Okta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide internal training and knowledge transfer on Apple enterprise best practices and emerging capabilities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create implementation templates, automation tools, and methodologies for Apple enterprise deployments&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serve as an escalation point for Sales, Marketing, and Product teams on Apple enterprise matters&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Represent Jamf as an Apple enterprise expert at industry events, conferences, and community forums&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation initiatives to address gaps in current solutions or where no solution exists&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Special projects assigned by management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Active participation in professional development opportunities and industry training&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand cross-platform integration scenarios and coexistence strategies in enterprise environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we are looking for:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Secondary/high school diploma or equivalent (Required) &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;4 Year / Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent qualification) in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field (Preferred),A combination of professional relevant experience and education may be considered&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Jamf Certifications 300, 370, 400 (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Commitment to maintaining current certifications and pursuing emerging technology education&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of regulatory compliance requirements relevant to enterprise IT environments (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, ISO, SOC2)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of professional experience in Apple device management, endpoint and/or network security (Required)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of Apple Enterprise Management technologies, endpoint protection, identity management, and zero-trust network architectures (Required)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of the IT ecosystem integrations with common tools and solutions (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of the Jamf products and solutions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of emerging technologies (AI/ML, Apple Intelligence) and their enterprise applications&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of key partner integrations/complementary solutions including but not limited to Apple, Okta, Microsoft, CrowdStrike, Zscaler, SIEM/SOAR etc&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;API, scripting, automation and Infrastructure as Code expertise and related languages such as Go, Python, PowerShell, bash, Terraform, Ansible (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Apple developer languages such as Swift, SwiftUI, Objective-C, Apple SDKs and Xcode (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience responding to RFPs and developing comprehensive solution proposals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong workshop and facilitation skills to align technical and business stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate complex technical concepts into business outcomes for executives and decision-makers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Experience identifying solution gaps, ability to propose innovations, and execute subsequent implementation strategies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Active participation in the Apple enterprise community (conferences, forums, user groups, thought leadership)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Comfortable engaging with a wide range of personnel, from technical to executive positions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel for customer visits, conferences, or internal events approximately 25% of the year&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security and Privacy Requirements:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Participation in ongoing security training is mandatory. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Established security protocols will be adhered to, sensitive data will be handled responsibly, and data protection practices are followed, including understanding relevant privacy regulations and reporting breaches. &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acknowledging the Jamf Code of Conduct, where applicable security and privacy policies can be found, is a requirement of all roles at Jamf.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How we help you reach your best potential:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Named a 2025 Best Companies to Work For by U.S. News&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Named a 2025 Newsweek America’s Greatest Workplaces for Gen Z&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Named one of Forbes Most Trusted Companies in 2024&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Named a 2024 Newsweek America’s Greatest Workplaces for Parents &amp;amp; Families&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Named a 2024 PEOPLE Companies That Care by PEOPLE® and Great Place To Work®&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We offer a clear and defined sales career path. Our main goal is to help you successfully step into our Account Executive role, but there are many ways to advance your career at Jamf.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We train and then we give you the room to grow. Our Jamfs can explore the vertical career path, as well as the horizontal, to discover new interests and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You don’t have to be a techie to be a Jamf. Our best-in-class sales focused Bootcamp training provides you with the technical and product knowledge required to confidently talk with customers about Jamf.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;We set achievable targets, help each other out, and share best practices across the team.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will have the opportunity to make a real and meaningful impact for more than 75,000 global customers with the best Apple device management solution in the world.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What it means to be a Jamf?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are a team of free-thinkers, can-doers, and problem-crushers. We value humility and the relentless pursuit of knowledge. Our culture flows from a spirit of selflessness and relentless self-improvement - driving both personal growth and collective progress throughout our company. We unite around common goals while respecting personal approaches, believing that fulfilled individuals create a thriving, vibrant workplace.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our aim is simple: hire exceptionally good people who are incredibly good at what they do and let them do it. We provide the support and resources to let everyone be their authentic, best selves at work, at rest, and at play. We are committed to supporting the continual improvement of Apple in the workplace, the organizations that rely on them and the people who keep it all running smoothly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Above it all, waves our banner of #OneJamf – and the knowledge that when we stand together, we accomplish so much more than we could alone. We seek individuals who share this unwavering journey toward growth to join us in our quest for constant improvement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does Jamf do?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Jamf extends the legendary Apple experience people enjoy in their personal lives to the workplace. We believe the experience of using a device at work or school should feel the same, and be as secure as, using a personal device. With Jamf, customers are able to confidently automate Mac, iPad, iPhone and Apple TV deployment, management, and security – anytime, anywhere – to protect the data and applications used by employees in the workplace, students learning in the classroom, and streamline communications in healthcare between patients and providers. More than 2,500 Jamf strong worldwide, we are free-thinkers, can-doers, and problems crushers who are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work each and every day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Get social with us and follow the conversation at #OneJamf&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Jamf is committed to creating an inclusive &amp;amp; supportive work environment for all candidates and employees. Candidates with disabilities or religious beliefs are encouraged to reach out if they need additional support or alternative options to our recruiting processes to accommodate their disability or religious belief. If you need an accommodation, please contact your Recruiter or Recruiting Coordinator directly. Requests for accommodation will be handled confidentially by Recruiting and will not be shared with the hiring manager. Jamf is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate against individuals who request reasonable accommodation for disability or religious beliefs. To request accommodations please email us at recruiting@jamf.com&lt;/em&gt;', 'Jamf is seeking a remote Consulting Engineer in Australia with expertise in Apple enterprise management, endpoint and network security, and advanced Jamf solutions. The role partners with Sales and other teams to design and deliver secure, scalable Apple-centric enterprise solutions, respond to RFPs, provide technical consultation, and drive innovation. Requirements include 5+ years in Apple device management or security, strong technical and communication skills, relevant certifications, and the ability to travel ~25%. Jamf values flexibility, work-life balance, continuous learning, and a collaborative culture. Applicants must have Australian permanent residency or citizenship.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MEDIUM', '52', NULL, '2025-09-17T04:53:57.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
    ('rectTkdsGrFqcWjpj', 'Account Executive - Enterprise', 'https://au.linkedin.com/jobs/view/account-executive-enterprise-at-canon-australia-4254808205', '2025-09-20', '2025-11-23', 'Melbourne, VIC', '&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be part of a collaborative Account Management team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Genuine flexibility and autonomy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Join a highly regarded and respected brand&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Canon is the world''s leading imaging organisation. As a Fortune 500 Company, we actively inspire people with imaginative ideas that enable you to connect, communicate and achieve more than you thought possible.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you join us, you’ll find a rewarding culture that values you. You’re empowered to focus on your career progression and turn your goals into reality. You’ll be an integral part of the group’s success.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an Account Executive managing a portfolio of Enterprise clients, you will play a vital role in supporting customers across Canon’s core business and solutions offerings, with a strong focus on delivering exceptional service and driving revenue growth throughout Victoria.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this role, you will both develop and execute business plans to engage potential key clients in line with our broader business strategy and take full ownership of managing and growing an existing portfolio of top-tier accounts. You will also contribute to shaping the strategic sales plan to meet revenue targets and support sustainable, profitable growth across a range of products and services.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of the role includes:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow accounts for customers you bring on board, as well as those assigned to you&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of new business opportunities and plan and execute Business plans with potential key Customers to deliver against the overall Business strategy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liaise with any new or existing customers and the business to input to the development of the strategic sales plan to grow, meet and exceed sales and revenue targets and achieve profitable growth commitments across several product and service offerings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively generate new business through a variety of go to market strategies and core propositions as well as the development of new business leads through the sales cycle&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Achieve customer additions, revenue and profit objectives/budgets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate major deals and develop submit tender response within policy guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop business engagement models and identify opportunities for business improvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify and steer opportunities for business improvement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Report performance to budget with variance analysis and revised projections&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contribute to, and devise the development/implementation of sales strategies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Attend and present at relevant seminars and other customer focussed events&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams both locally and interstate, to deliver a seamless customer experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Management of the sales process from initial order through to implementation and beyond&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Negotiate major deals and submit tenders within policy guidelines &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You are a motivated sales professional—whether you’re an experienced enterprise account executive or someone earlier in your sales career, ready to take the next step. You have a passion for developing new business, building strong customer relationships, and driving results. Adaptable and commercially minded, you thrive in a dynamic environment and can confidently engage a wide range of stakeholders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are open to considering both seasoned professionals and ambitious candidates looking to grow into this role. To be successful, you will bring:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sales experience in Major Accounts / Tier 1 Enterprise Accounts or a strong track record in existing and new business development&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understanding of cross-selling, up-selling, and value-based selling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Exposure to selling managed services and/or solutions (preferred but not essential)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage and support stakeholders across opportunities and accounts, both locally and interstate&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and relationship-building skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good financial and analytical thinking with commercial awareness&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactive, self-managed approach with a strong drive to achieve results&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, influencing, and negotiation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Confident presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and resilience in a dynamic sales environment &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Canon will invest in you by providing an inclusive learning environment to support you through continual growth and career development. With the foundation of a globally recognised, award-winning and trusted brand as your platform for success, it’s up to you to grab this opportunity with both hands!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As well as a great career with a globally recognised company, Canon offers:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flexible working arrangements where suitable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Training and development opportunities to help you bring your goals to life&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Performance Recognition in the form of quarterly and annual awards programs for high-performers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bonus Leave, including:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Birthday leave, to celebrate, relax or do something special.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Canon Day, an extra day of leave during the Christmas holidays.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Kyosei Day, or volunteer leave to take a paid day off to do good in your community.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Milestone recognition on your work anniversaries includes carbon credits, merchandise, or retirement fund rewards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discounted Canon products, offered at a significant saving.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An employee referral scheme rewarding you for recommending great candidates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Eligibility for specific benefits and perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Canon Group and the country where you work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If this sounds like you, we’d love you to apply!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We believe in the power of an inclusive and diverse workforce. We trust you will bring your authentic self to work, and we will focus on making sure that together, we make a strong contribution to the broader community in which we operate. Where possible, flexible working arrangements are the norm, as we know a better work-life balance can improve your motivation, performance, and productivity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an equal opportunity employer, all applicants will be considered. Benefits/perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Canon Group and the country where you work. All applicants must be eligible to work in the country they are applying to at the time of application.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Looking to join this diverse team? Apply online now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Successful applicants will be notified of next steps', 'Account Executive role at Canon managing and growing a portfolio of enterprise clients, focusing on business development, account management, and revenue growth. Responsibilities include developing business plans, generating new leads, negotiating deals, and collaborating with cross-functional teams. Requires strong sales experience, relationship-building, commercial acumen, and communication skills. Offers flexible work, training, performance recognition, and additional leave benefits. Open to both experienced professionals and ambitious candidates.', 'full-time', 'Mid-Senior level', '4254808205', 'MEDIUM', '64', 'Sales and Business Development', '2025-09-20T06:27:43.000Z', '2025-10-02T02:56:21.744Z'),
